commentary: Smacked through extra cover to get the comp underway! Johnson saw it pitched in his half, got his front foot forward and the bat swing came from second slip but went through the line. Ball raced along the ground and in the gap
summary: Aaron Johnson smacked through extra cover to get the comp underway. Johnson saw it pitched in his half, got his front foot forward and the bat swing came from second slip.

commentary: left-armer to left-hand batter. Full outside off with a slight outswing. Left alone
summary: Over 0 by Kaleem Sana to Steven Taylor. left-armer to left-hand batter. Full outside off with a slight outswing. Left alone.

commentary: Tries to pull the hard-length ball but plinks it just in front
summary: Aaron Johnson tries to pull the hard-length ball but plinks it just in front. Over 0 by Ali Khan to Aaron Johnson.

commentary: Kaleem strikes second ball! Good length ball around off. Skidding through to Taylor as he goes onto the back foot for a flick. Ball doesn't bounce as expected, and he's been caught in front of middle stump. Taylor reviews but looks despondent, and that's because this is crashing into leg stump. Silence all around the ground, except the DJ's music
summary: Kaleem Sana strikes second ball! Good length ball around off. Skidding through to Taylor as he goes onto the back foot for a flick.

commentary: Length on top of the pad, a bit too leg side. Beats the flick and deflects towards square leg
summary: Over 0 by Ali Khan to Aaron Johnson. Length on top of the pad, bit too leg side. Beats the flick and deflects towards square leg.

commentary: length ball around off and fended first ball by Gous
summary: Kaleem Sana to Andries Gous. length ball around off and fended first ball by Gous, first ball fended. Over 0.

commentary: A bit of shape away to beat the edge. Length ball, lands around fifth and Dhaliwal tries following it with a back-foot square drive. Misses
summary: Over 0 by Ali Khan to Navneet Dhaliwal. A bit of shape away to beat the edge. Length ball, lands around fifth.

commentary: full ball outside off. Angling across the batter. Tries to drive away from his body but misses
summary: Over 0 by Kaleem Sana to Andries Gous. full ball outside off. Angling across the batter. Tries to drive away from his body but misses.

commentary: Pitched up on middle and off, driven to mid-off. No lateral movement there
summary: Over 0 by Ali Khan to Navneet Dhaliwal. Pitched up on middle and off, driven to mid-off.

commentary: full ball away from his body. Sliding across and Gous attempts the drive once again. Misses out and the keeper dives to his right to get there
summary: Andries Gous misses a second-half chance to make it 2-0. Kaleem Sana played the ball over to Gous, who missed the shot.

commentary: Tucked up but Dhaliwal is able to jab it to wide mid-on. Shortish ball at the body, he had to jump on the back foot alone and semi-pull it.
summary: Navneet Dhaliwal was caught at mid-on off Ali Khan's bowling. He had to jump on the back foot alone and semi-pull it.

commentary: back of a length ball on off and Gous pumps a front-of-square pull! USA's first four in T20 World Cup history and nerves Kaleem cannot finish with a wicket maiden
summary: Kaleem Sana takes wicket of Andries Gous in first over of T20 World Cup. Sana's wicket is his first of the tournament. USA win their first four

commentary: back of a length ball just outside off from the tall fast bowler. Tries to pull but pulls out of the shot late
summary: Over 1 by Jeremy Gordon to Monank Patel. back of a length ball just outside off from the tall fast bowler. Tries to pull but pulls out of the shot late.

commentary: Length on fifth, patted with an open bat-face to backward point
summary: Saurabh Netravalkar and Navneet Dhaliwal score first wicket of the day for India. Saurabh nets out for over 1 to Nav

commentary: back of a length just outside off. Pokes at it, guided to deep third
summary: Over 1 by Jeremy Gordon to Monank Patel. Back of a length just outside off. Pokes at it, guided to deep third.

commentary: A bit of width and Dhaliwal uses it to steer the length ball between cover point and backward point. Loose wrists helping the batter there. Pace: 128ks
summary: Navneet Dhaliwal hits the length ball between cover point and backward point. Loose wrists helping the batter there. Over 1 by Saurabh Netravalkar to Nav

commentary: ball staying low over here. Length ball wide outside off. Bit of swing away. Gous attempts to pull but the ball goes way under his bat. Two bounces to Movva
summary: Over 1 by Jeremy Gordon to Andries Gous. ball staying low over here. Length ball wide outside off. Bit of swing away. Gous attempts to pull but the ball goes

commentary: Quick single to mid-off, no direct hit at the non-striker's end. Was pitched up and Dhaliwal punched it with the full-faced bat and took off right away
summary: Saurabh Netravalkar to Navneet Dhaliwal. Quick single to mid-off, no direct hit at the non-striker's end. Was pitched

commentary: true bounce, slapped past point! Short and wide, this time the ball sits up and the right-hand batter crunches it square through the infield
summary: Andries Gous hits over 1 by Jeremy Gordon to make it 1-0. The ball sits up and crunches square through the infield.

commentary: Length on the pads, clipped to long leg
summary: Over 1 by Saurabh Netravalkar to Aaron Johnson. Length on the pads, clipped to long leg.

commentary: full ball just outside off and a bit of swing away. Presses forward with the bat's open face. Guided to deep third

Similar shot to the boundary ball but there is deep-backward point now and that's where it goes. Very little follow-through from Dhaliwal but that pinged off the bat. Netravalkar angling it in but got it around fifth-stump

chance of a catch! But Gordon cannot get there and the Canada fielders run to him to lift his spirits. Length ball around off and Monank tries to punch through mid-on but the ball stays low, takes the toe-end of the bat, and very nearly carries to the bowler on the followthrough
Thickish edge runs wide of short third. Wobble ball on fifth stump, Johnson was a bit tentative but pushed at the three-quarter-length ball on fifth stump, aimed at cover but got it in the gap.
Length on leg, clipped off the back foot to deep square leg
short of length ball around off, and he offers a punchy shot towards cover. Can't beat the infield

Thickish inside edge but Johnson's power gets the ball racing between mid-on and midwicket. The former chases but had no chance. Was a three-quarter length ball on fourth stump, Johnson committed on the front foot and tried to smack it down the ground, bat-faced turned a bit but he got it into the ground

Kaleem tries to attack the wide line outside off with a full ball. Gous moves across a little bit but the umpire thinks that's wide length ball on middle and off. Gous plays it between mid off and cover for a quick single

Ouch, Johnson gets hit on the helmet by a bouncer angling in. He was beaten on the pull and the ball deflected in the gap at first slip. Rolls too fine and for four. There will be a concussion test, Johnson looks okay to continue
the captain gets his first boundary! And this is a classy drive over point, reaching out and slashing it over the infield. Kaleem continuing to prefer being full and wide.

The bouncer doesn't put Johnson off, he takes a really big front-foot stride and reaches out to the wide scramble-seam length ball, lifts it over the infield with an open face. Gets four to the forward-point boundary
full ball on off stump. Driven to mid-on for a quick single
Bad ball. Too straight and the length ball is glanced fine. Johnson, and Canada, are off to a flier

misfield from the keeper, and they'll get an extra run there. Another ball angling across Gous and he misses. streaky four! Full ball outside off and Monank attempts a cover drive. But the ball takes an inside edge, flying past off stump to fine leg for four
Dot to finish but it's a 17-run over. Length on fifth, defended with an open face to backward point
full ball around off and Monank absolutely crunches a drive. Played on the up, and falls just short of Dhaliwal at mid-off. Fielder wasn't afraid to put his body on the line there
Fullish and flat. Dhaliwal dances down, gets close to the pitch and punches it to the bowler's left. Harmeet leaps across and parries it to the left

peach of a ball! Length ball on middle. Monank gets set to clip a ball towards the leg side but the ball straightens enough, moving away, and instead goes over off stump. Very much Starc v Abhishek from the IPL final, if you remember, except this went over the stumps

Dhaliwal backs away, rocks back and drives off the back foot through cover. He started to go on the front foot but read the length and decided to go back later. Ball came at an easy pace and the outfield is rapid
back of a length ball around off. Monank charges down and flat-bats a shot towards mid on. Toe-ended again
Darted at leg peg, it's fullish and is defended in front
ball is snaking around a lot. Short of length ball just outside off. Gous makes room to attempt a cut but the ball seams away after pitching, forcing the non-shot
Fullish just down leg, Dhaliwal dances down and drives to long-off
back of a length ball on middle and leg. Totally wrong line and Gous lifts a shot off his waist and deposits it over short fine leg
A bit of low bounce and Johnson tucks the shortish, slow ball from the stumps to midwicket. Gets a quick single, had to hurry but makes it
full ball on middle and hit on the up to mid-on. Bajwa at mid-on dives forward but the ball falls just short
Taylor stops four at backward point. Length ball is wide and Dhaliwal committed to the square slash, it was racing to Taylor's right but he dove across and intercepted
full ball on middle. Bit of movement away with Gous tentatively playing off the front foot. Tapped to point

short and wide outside off. Shaping away further. Misses the cut fullish outside off. Monank comfortably lifts it away, over cover, but it doesn't have the legs to go for four. Fielder does well to drag it back, saving one
Shortish ball beats the pull. Scramble-seam ball lands around fifth and decks back in a bit, Johnson stood tall and didn't get the bounce he wanted
back of a length wide outside off. Tries to slap it over point but misses. Gous looks annoyed at himself
Full around off, 135ks, driven to mid-off
full ball moving away. Gous attempts a drive but misses
Back of length around fifth, guided to deep-backward point off the back foot. Ian Bishop says this is a better length for the pitch, any shorter and the pull shot can be played
full ball around off. Mistimed drive to cover for a quick single
Dhaliwal shows all the stumps and walks into the full ball going down leg to whip it through midwicket. Stopped deep in the outfield. 138ks
good length ball outside off stump. Bit of movement away. Monank loses his shape while trying to slap a shot over the off side but misses
French cut goes past leg stump. Not far. Was a length ball outside off and Dhaliwal wanted to crash it square on the off side
full ball on middle stump. Nearly a yorker, in fact. Monank hits a shot onto his boot and the ball rolls away behind
Jasdeep closes out the over well, almost had a wicket but the ball goes on the bounce to mid-on. Was a hard-length ball just outside the ball that Dhaliwal wanted to drag across with the pull
A bit of turn in beats the bat, lbw appeal is turned down.
the captain now. Gous gets a single first ball

Slapped off the toe of the bat and it's taken at long-off! Harmeet slowed down the pace after predominantly darting the ball so far, Johnson backed away and tried to belt it off side, but made a bit too much room and lost balance. He was falling over leg side and the bat was going the other way. Easy catch and Harmeet is jubilant. The opener gave his side a good start though
pushes this full ball to midwicket
Full on middle and off, defended to cover
makes room and then drives this full ball to cover. Well stopped inside the circle

Lot happening, Nitish almost took a stunner running to the left from long-off. He then bulleted a throw to the keeper, who whipped off the bails but Dhaliwal made it. Quite cool how the fielder caught it on the bounce while sliding. Was a full ball that was flighted and driven inside out
length ball outside off. Bit of turn away. Cuts, but intercepted at point by the fielder
Length ball follows the batter as he made room, punched off the back foot to cover
good length ball just outside off. Gous offers quick hands in his attempted cut,  and the placement is great, behind point, beating the infielder! Waited for the ball this time

Dhaliwal diffuses the pressure, dances down and flays it wide of long-off. Was taken on the up but the flat bat allowed enough surface area to middle it. Not that bad a ball despite the width (given Dhaliwal's charge)
full ball on off stump. Driven straight down the V to long off and the powerplay ends at 41/1 in six overs
hit down the ground to long off for one

Big appeal for lbw, not given. Jasdeep chats with the skip, USA decide to review. Good shout but height might be an issue. Was a length ball that angled in, beat the flick and hit over the knee-roll. Hawk-Eye projects that the ball would have gone over the top of the stumps
length ball on the stumps line and Patel tries to loft it over the leg side but misses
Three-quarter length on off, driven to mid-off
edged and taken! Nicks this full ball outside off after charging down the track. Another wild shot from Monank and the slight shape away after pitching induced the edge.
Makes a bit of room and carves it in the gap behind point. Was a length ball around fourth stump and Dhaliwal's hand speed through the ball was impeccable

terrific delivery, and keeper appeals for caught behind but nobody else is interested. Length ball around off and Jones expects the ball to shape in, but the ball instead holds its line. He tentatively pushes at it, and very nearly gets an edge.
Aims for something similar but has to check the shot due to the room being lesser. Defended to cover in the end
full ball on his pads. This one angles in and Jones is hit on his pads trying to attempt a flick. But this is missing leg stump so the LBW appeal is turned down. Still, questions asked.
So much flair in that bosh over extra cover. Dhaliwal stays leg side of the length ball over off and smears it over the in-field. Held his shape really well on the drive there

full ball on leg. Jones comes down the track to cut the swing but the ball goes past his leg. Keeper does well to dive and ensure it doesn't go to the boundary back of a length outside off. Guided to deep third for a single. Another tidy, testing over
Driven off the front foot through the off side for a single
good length ball outside off. Stays in the crease and punches to deep extra cover
Slower one is fullish and outside off, pushed with the open face to point
good length ball on middle. Tapped to the leg side and Saad runs to his right to intercept. Very quick!
Slow again. Full on off, Pargat leans down towards the ball and taps it to forward point
good length ball outside off. Tries the cut but misses!
Another quick single. Was a length ball at the pads, Dhaliwal inside edges the flick and the ball rolled towards the vacant short-leg area
finally a single after four dots. Length ball on the stumps worked towards square leg for one
Clipped off the hip, deep-backward square leg runs to the right and cuts it off. Quick outfield but quicker running allows the batters to take two
good length ball just outside off stump. Cut in front of square, to cover
Pargat doesn't get the bounce he wanted for the square drive and gets beaten. Falls over too. Length ball on fifth
only three off the over. Length ball outside leg. Gous shapes up for a big back-foot pull over square leg but the ball stays low, hits his pad and rolls away to the leg side

Pargat returns for a risky second, accurate throw from Jasdeep and the keeper does well to whip off the bails. Run-out referral made. This could be out. Yep, he's a goner despite the full-length dive!. Monank got the throw angling at him, he swayed his hands to the right and dislodged the bails with the batter being about a foot short. Was a length ball that was flicked around the corner, off the back foot. Jasdeep ran to the right and flung the ball at pace. A very flat and fast throw
Quick single to short third. Was a length ball that was slapped

wild ball. Slips out of his hand. Is that dew? full and wide, and this will be a free hit again. this time the free hit is put away! Full ball just outside the tram-lines. Big man Gous moves to the off side, gets close to the ball, and hammers it over long off!
Tries to cut the length ball outside off, gets beaten
full and wide outside off. Gous looks for another big shot but it takes a big edge, going past the keeper. Short third gives the ball a chase
Length ball darted at the stumps, clipped to long-on
full ball on middle. Slow through the air. Gous mistimes a launch to the leg side
Dances down, gets to the pitch of the wide-ish ball and drives to deep cover

full ball outside off, floaty, and angling further wide outside off. Left alone into the second tier! Full floaty ball outside off but within Jones' reach. Gets low and slog sweeps for six after getting the ball in his arc
Full ball is slow and drifts in towards off, defended
full ball on off. Jones guides the ball angling across towards backward point
Driven down the ground for a single
19 off the over! Just what USA needed. Dutta ends the over by getting a length ball to angle across and the batter flicks to cow corner
full ball outside off and driven to a wide long off. Couple more for Jones

High-full toss is somehow munched over cover for six! Kirton was backing away but got one around the waist, 97ks, and he went through with the slashing cut shot despite being cramped for room a bit. Just cleared the cushion
The USA flags are flying again! Full ball on middle, attempting to cramp Jones up, but he plays a reverse sweep over conventional short third for four more
Cuts the wide-ish ball to the off side
good length ball just outside off. Punched to deep extra cover
Canada are taking on the offie. This was a slot ball at the stumps and Dhaliwal lines up the part-timer, strides towards the pitch and drives through the line. Ball sails over long-on
full ball on middle and leg. Gous misses a shot through midwicket, ball hits the outside half of his pad, and rolls away to short fine leg
Better from Taylor. Length on middle, 97ks, clipped off the back foot towards wide long-on
flourish in that shot! Saad bowls a fullish ball on middle but Jones dances down the track, brings the bat down in stylish manner, and then hammers a six over wide long on
Fullish length ball outside off is slowish, gets good bounce. Tapped with an open face to short fine
Jones makes room by backing away.  Saad follows by bowling full outside leg stump. Jones is disappointed that he cramped himself after hitting a bunt towards the non-striker. USA 81/2 in 10 overs
Probably the best ball of the over. Length on fourth, 98ks, worked back to the bowler
good length ball around off. Angling in. Nudged towards backward point for a quick single
Length on leg, clipped through midwicket
full ball on off. Clears the front leg and clubbed towards deep midwicket. But protection there
Slow on a length, from around the wicket. Defended in front

length ball on middle and leg. Punched to cover where there's a fumble, and Gous wants one. But Jones doesn't, and Gous is in danger, but a second fumble from the fielder means the throw is delayed and the batter is safe
Pitched up and a bit of room given, Dhaliwal chips a drive over extra cover and picks up two. Holds his shape well
mows this full ball to deep midwicket. But timing is not there
Fullish on leg, clipped through backward square leg
out of the stadium!  Slot ball, just outside off, and Jones shows off his muscles by clattering Heyliger over wide long on
Length on fourth, worked off the back foot to long-on
full ball on leg and clipped to deep midwicket. Ten runs off the over
Length ball over middle and off, defended to the bowler's left
it's getting tough keeping up with Jones'! Half-tracker from Pargat. Jones hangs back, goes deep in his crease, and pulls over square leg
Batters rush for the single. In fact, Ali misfields at short fine leg and that allows two. Was an offcutter on a length at leg stump that was flicked late
length ball around off. Jones muscles a mistimed shot to deep midwicket but there are two outfielders in the deep
Length around off, driven to long-off
11 runs off the first three balls! Full ball around off. Backs away and thumps the offspinner right down the ground. Long off is present, but his dive is futile

Lumped down the ground. This was overpitched and at the stumps, Dhaliwal got leg side of the ball and smoked it through the line. Was like a shot Carlos Brathwaite hit during the 2016 final, forced it a bit but got enough muscle to hit it 74 metres far
slaps a cut to the deep for a single
Carves it off the back foot through the off side. The single brings up Dhaliwal's fifty and Canada's hundred
length ball around off. Jones gets low and tries to club a slog sweep behind square. Mistimed to deep square leg
Length on fourth, 122ks, square driven off the back foot to deep cover's left
flatter. Length ball outside off. Cut behind square and the fielder in the deep covers a lot of ground, but his throw is wild, and therefore USA get an extra overthrow run. 15 off the over
Slower one on a length just outside off, stabbed to short third. Dhaliwal took off right after making contact, which has been a recurring theme tonight
Harmeet keeps it slow and out of Dhaliwal's arc. 81ks, very full and around the off-side tramline. The batter reaches out and oars it over cover
monster six! Makes a bit of room to this full ball and launches Saad over long on!
Length on leg, clipped to deep midwicket

oh this is like a video game! Jones goes way into the leg side, almost out of the pitch. Saad follows him with a full ball way outside leg, but it ends up in his arc. Clobbered high and mighty, and this is out of the ground beyond deep midwicket again.
Dances into the pitch of the 97ks ball, punches it back to the bowler
a 22-ball fifty for Aaron Jones after facing four dots to start his innings. Full on leg, and clipped to the gap at square leg. It is also the fastest T20I fifty for USA. What a time to get it.

Confident stumping appeal. Sent upstairs. Length ball at 86ks, Dhaliwal went for the sweep. HIs foot did drag out as he played the shot but then returned as he lunged back. That helps him get a part of his foot back inside
full ball around leg, and clipped to deep midwicket

Cannoned down the ground, Kirton has to duck for cover. Harmeet went foot and slow, ended up tossing up a slot ball at the stumps. The back lift was high as it was threatening, the contact on the drive was sweet and long-on had no chance
full ball outside leg. Jones stays in position and attempts to drag a reverse sweep from outside leg. Hits the shot right onto his body
A bit of room this time and Dhaliwal dances down, coils his body and bashes it wide of long-off. Harmeet, who was economical for most of his spell, ends up conceding back-to-back boundaries

my oh my oh my!  Jones goes way out towards the leg side exposing all three stumps. And Saad once again follows him, bowling full outside leg. Jones gets low, and slog sweeps a swat over cow corner once more.

length ball on middle and leg. Gous attempts to pull behind square, but misses. No harm for USA as he gets to collect a wide run for his team Gous moves to 49 with a six now! short and wide outside off. Gous reaches out, and reaches out well! Slapped over cover! Shorter boundary on the off side, only 61m, and he clears it despite toe-ending it
Slow on a length, dances down while making room and slaps it to long-off
another fifty for USA! Length ball on leg, and Gous swats this loose ball off his hips away to fine leg for four!
Full on leg, clipped to long-on

full ball on leg. And sliding further down leg. Wide given. Gordon isn't happy, thinks it touched Gous' body or bat. Saad takes a review thinking there's a caught-behind even as the umpire signals wide. No edge, the wide will stand. taken at deep square leg! But wait, it is a NO BALL! Full ball in his pads, and Gous clips it half-heartedly off his shin. Ball goes straight to deep square leg for a catch but Gous gets a reprieve. Front-foot no ball. From agony to ecstasy for Gordon short and wide outside off. Toe-ends a cut over cover for a single. But it is a no ball again! this time the free hit won't be wasted. Well Gordon doesn't overstep this time, but errs by bowling a slot ball on middle stump. Perfect place for the well-set Jones, and he drills the batter over wide long on. Hundred partnership up!

Dipping low full toss has been elevated over cover with panache. Looks like a missed yorker, was angling away towards fourth stump, Kirton's front foot was arrowing towards long-on's direction and his upper body collapsed a bit to access it, somehow got the timing just right on the bat swing

good length ball sliding down leg. Misses the pull but gets the wide run brilliant at long on! Length ball around off. Jones flat-bats a shot that's destined to clear long on but the substitute fielder swats the ball right back in, saving five even though that's painful for his wrist
Overpitched and that's driven firmly through the line. Four down the ground. Technically perfect from Kirton
long on a mere spectator this time as Gous pulls this short of length ball down the V. Gous stands tall, and crunches that like a baseball player representing the Texas Rangers
Length ball is clipped across to long-on
bit of luck and Gous gets four more. Full ball outside off and the attempted drive takes a thick edge over short third. The over is finally done, and the damage is 33 runs!
Square driven off the back foot, should be four... No! Johnson races to the right from deep-backward point and dives to keep it to two

Anderson's first ball in the WC for USA dismisses the well set Dhaliwal. Cutter on a full length angling in and he tried to lash it through the line. The lack of pace meant he was into the shot too early and got it off the bottom of the bat, ball popped straight to Jasdeep at long-off. Again, a good innings from an opener
full and wide ball outside off. Just inside the tram-lines. Batter sticks the bat out but misses
Length on off, clipped through midwicket. Man from the deep runs in and keeps it to one. Anderson almost collided with the non-striker but both players look in good spirit in the end

slower ball full just outside off. Jones swings across the line too quickly, and gets a big top edge. Fielder at short third, Dutta, diagonally behind to take the catch, but he makes a mess of it. Dropped and Jones survives
Bumper just over the waist, from over the wicket. Kirton swivels from off side to leg on the pull, was cramped for room a bit but went through with the pull, got it fine for four
insult to injury. Yorker length ball just outside off. Jones throws his bat at it, gets an outside edge, and the ball goes between keeper and short third for four more

That could be one of the great pick-up-and-throw run outs. Even if not, that's a heck of effort from Anderson, who ran towards the unmanned midwicket region, saw the non-striker's end as the danger one and changed direction. He was rotating, which meant he couldn't get the power behind the throw, and that has given Movva time to make it back. Dive helped too. Was a length ball that was clipped off the back foot, Anderson ran about 20 metres to the left
full ball on off. Swings across the line and mistimes to deep square leg
Length outside off, guided to backward point
full ball on off. Nearly a yorker. Dug out to long on for an easy single
Length just outside off, pushed to deep point
full and wide ball. Jones gently plays it to deep extra cover for a single
Length on leg, clipped to deep square leg's left
length ball outside off. Stays in his crease and slaps a cut behind point for four
Full on middle and leg, 124ks, clipped to the left of long-on. They were thinking of two but Kirton couldn't turn properly. Didn't look like two was on
full ball on off. Slogs across the line, mistimed to deep square leg
Shortish ball around fourth is pulled to long-on. Didn't time it well, might have been the splice
good length ball outside off. Cut in front of square to cover
Nice use of the angle from Kirton. Was a length ball around off, he hopped leg side to make a bit of room and cut it late. Got it in the gap behind point for four

relief for Canada. Length ball on off and Gous tries to club Dutta off the back foot over long on. But the attempted loft with the full face of the bat doesn't have the elevation or the power. But a solid 65 from the vice-captain after a slow start to his innings
Length on leg, clipped to backward square leg
around the stumps. Full on off and tapped to the leg side

Movva goes leg side before swindling the bowler. Finishes wide of off, gets square-on and scoops it over his bending shoulder. Was a fullish ball that was on the rise, making it all the more impressive
length ball outside off. Ends up dragging a mistimed shot to deep square leg
Pulls the length ball to long leg. Brings up Canada's 150
Anderson charges down the ground. Kaleem bowls a full ball outside leg. Anderson drives to mid off
Walks down and Anderson goes wide and slow. Movva speed walked and wanted to use he pace in his attempt to mash the ball over cover but met with air
full ball outside leg. Anderson stays leg-side of the ball and drives to mid off for a single
Movva tries the swindle again but the line of the ball is at the stumps and he holds sway, drives down the ground. Not middled but lands safely
single
Goes back in the crease and pulls. But Anderson doesn't give pace again, finds the edge but the ball again, doesn't carry. Long-on stops it on the bounce
full ball on off stump. Tapped to point and the fielder has a shy at the stumps with Anderson searching for a single. Misses the direct-hit, and they get an overthrow
Kirton shapes for the pull but yoinks his shoulder down to sneak a wide. Not given though. The bouncer was angling down but was too close to the batter
played back to the bowler

Very tight two to backward square leg and Movva makes it, raises fifty too . He raises his bat. Was a slower bumper that was pulled gently and into the ground. Fielder charged in and threw well but the batter was quicker

full ball on middle and leg. Jones misses a flick, keeper can't grab it clean as the ball dips late, and the Americans run two more. Three wides and 19 extras in all so far full toss wide outside off. Guided to deep backward point for a single
Pitched up, driven hard but finds mid-on. Ball went along the ground
moves into the eighties! Reverse swept over short third! Full ball around middle and off. Jones improvises, and ensures the elevation is there to get it over the circle
Goes for the reverse ramp and misses. Kirton went square-on, got his feet wide apart and tried to help the full ball, angling through fifth, between keeper and short third

parried over the ropes! Full on off. Jones waits for the ball to dip and land before playing the slog sweep. Fielder at deep square leg runs around the ropes to try and stop it, but he only gets a fingertip beyond the rope
Ali nearly nails the wide yorker and all Kirton can do is slice it to deep-backward point. 135ks, lands just in front of the crease
length ball outside off. Mistimed to point, a cut.

Late call of wide leaves the keeper, and USA's skipper, unimpressed. Was a shortish ball, and Movva walked towards it real late and tried to reverse-pull it. Beaten. The movement across the crease hasn't helped the batters of late Movva makes room and Ali follows him with a very full ball, close to the block-hole with the batter's movement. Beats the flick and the ball deflects off the pad to the off side
six to finish it and Jones ends 94*. Finishes with ten sixes as this full ball is clubbed over deep midwicket to seal USA's victory by seven wickets and 14 balls to spare.

Full ball has been skewered to cover, Kirton tried to end Canada's boundary-drought by lifting the full ball with an open face but couldn't get under the ball. Front leg was out the way, he got inside the line a bit too mucb as well. Hits it straight to Anderson
Slower bumper is outside off and Bajwa tries to slap it with the cross bat. Misses
Gous runs back... and can't take it. He started from square leg and was late to pick up where the ball was going and that cost him distance.
Goes through with the lofted cover drive but is a bit too early into it. Ball lands safely in front of long-off
Goes across, gets inside the line and essentially sweeps the length ball in the gap to the right of square leg. No one in the deep there
The sound off the bat on that pull is pure!. Bajwa was ever so ready for the slower half-tracker angling in towards fourth stump. Got upright and hauled it over midwicket, 89-metre six. Proper biggie
Canada haven't been able to pull off the unconventional shots. Bajwa changes his guard and winds up big for the reverse sweep, commits fully but the full ball outside off beats him
They look to sneak another two, throw is in at the keeper's end. Bails dislodged, decision sent upstairs. Bajwa dove forward... but is a few inches short. Bajwa had heaved it to the right of long-on
Misses the yorker by a little bit and Heyliger punishes it. Lifts it from shin-height and gets it straight of long-off for a 76-metre six
Lands the yorker near the crease this time. Clips it to deep fine leg
Bumper over leg stump, batter makes room and charges. Doesn't middle the pull but gets it to long-on

Bumper goes down leg, Movva tries to hook it but misses. Keeper lobs the ball up too high, no threat of byes though Movva's quick hands power the ball through the line again. Ali misses the yorker only by a bit Movva clears the front leg, gets into the stablest of bases and drives it straight
That's the flat-bat at its imperious best. Creamed wide of long-off, Steve Smith-esque from Movva, who makes a bit of room and belts the shortish ball on the top of the bounce
Driven down the ground, they scamper back before the throw from long-off comes through. Movva's charge gives Canada a 21-run over to finish off the innings
round the wicket, tossed up and gripping to spin a long way past the bat, with Ura aiming a biff down the ground
Nice shape into the right-hander, full enough to allow the swing come into play, pushed out towards extra cover
sliding in with the arm towards leg stump, tucked off the pads square
Straighter, not as much swing, defended to mid off
bowled into the pitch, skidding on with Vala looking to pull. Struck on the pads but the appeal is muted... pitched outside leg
Moving into leg stump, met with a full stride and pushed to midwicket
pushed through and again Vala can't get it away shoveling to leg
Swing and a miss! King skips down, aims to go over the bowler's head but misses out completely!
beauty! Hosein gets this to go away from the left-hander, bowled from over the wicket and spinning through to the keeper. Vala done all ends up
That's what he wanted to do! King's on the move, Morea's line is straighter and a cautious lofted drive down the ground brings about the first boundary of the chase
tossed up and Vala again can't work it into a gap. Just one run off Hosein's opener
Short, not quick enough and powered well in front of square leg!

Big LBW appeal... Given! Charles reviews straightaway but that looks pretty adjacent... Umpire's Call on impact and Nao starts with a bang! On the money straight away, just getting one to nip in off the straight and hit the right-hander flush on the front pad.
back of a length, 128kph and rising around middle and leg, Ura swats a pull through backward square leg
Full, shaping away late, left alone by the Southpaw
touch short in the channel, angling across from over the wicket. Vala swipes and misses
Great line, same again, decent length to ensure Pooran can't come forward, who lets this one go too
shortish and Vala connects this time, chopped firmly through the covers for his first runs. Might have been four but the outfield looks heavy after plenty of rain

Another LBW appeal.... this time Umpire Rashid Riaz shakes his head. No review and wise from PNG as that looks to have pitched outside leg stump before hitting the front pad... Oh no! It did pitch in line! and it was set to be hitting the stumps flush! Oh dear oh dear - what might have been...
back of a length, zipping through over the top of off as Ura heaves across the line and misses

A charge first ball... but Pooran accidentally turns the delivery into a yorker. Ends up inside edging the ball onto his boot and to fine leg, who is up in the circle. Thinks about a run but King sends him back

back of a length, fended behind! Shepherd strikes in the second over for West Indies. Cracking delivery, prancing and swerving off the seam as Ura looked to open the face playing from the crease. Kissed the outside edge for a straightforward take by Pooran
Swing and a miss! Lovely delivery, arching in a touch, nipping away late, enticing a flourish from Pooran. It's taken a bit of time to completely, but an excellent wicket maiden from Nao
length ball, but fired down leg nurdled wide of short fine leg for a single to get Siaka off the mark

Timbeeeeeeerrrrrrrrrrrrr! Hosein slices through him! A wicked delivery from West Indies' left-arm spin doctor, angling back in with the arm - almost an inswinger, really. Beats the inside edge and rattles middle and off. Siaka heads off after a two-ball stay
Driven on the up... and flies through the gap between cover and mid off! Width on offer, from a fuller length, and King is never going to say no to that
slung down on off, poked through square leg
Straighter, swinging in, off the inside edge and into the front pad. Great comeback from Morea
on the stumps, turned into the leg side
Too wide, clubbed through point! Presses forward, rocks back and cuts with ease
goes over the wicket again, gets Vala coming forward and then spins the ball past the inside edge
Swing again from a full length, kicked around the corner by King whose front foot interrupts his bat flow
the Hosein arm ball again does Vala going back, curving away in the arm with no turn
Good length, swing away, left alone by Pooran
pushed through flat and PNG's captain frees the arms, chops an under-edge past the keeper for two
Length away, not as much swing, allowing Pooran to open his hands into a push, getting off the mark with a single down to third up in the circle
Full, angle into the base of middle and leg, pushed back to the bowler
fired full, just outside off, beats Bau as he attempts to clamp down on it late
Length, straightening off the deck, Pooran is down on one knee trying to blaze this one into the sea and misses completely. Ends up having to wear it instead
full length, punched towards mid-off without much timing
First run off Nao, and it's a tip and run from Pooran, who presses forward and catches cover sleeping to steal that one
back of a length, brushes the hip as he looks to work it fine. Pooran is across to field
Charge... and another miss! Nao nips this one into the right-hander, off a length, and ends up cutting King in half as he skips down the track
very full again, almost yorker length outside off. Bunted back to the bowler
There it is! Nao opts for a wider delivery anticipating the charge, which duly comes. This time, King's weight is perfect - head still - and he powers that through the covers
clubbed down the ground, first boundary for PNG! Too full and this time Bau boshes effectively past mid-off, despite the ball holding up as it trundles towards the rope

Laced through point! Smart batting from King; knows a correction of sorts is coming, and when Nao is fuller with that same width, just throws his hands through the ball, opening the wrists a touch, and bagging his sixth boundary
back of a length but sliding down leg pitched up and thrashes back, through Russell's hands as he tumbles forward in his follow through, but mid-on cleans up
Starts full, on the pads and deflects out into the leg side
hello, Assad Vala! Moosed over extra cover! Tossed up invitingly and Vala hops out of his bunker to slam this all the way over the ropes in regal fashion
Short of a length, almost does Pooran with the lack of pace as he the leftie gets a thick outside edge away to third, who is up
fired in flatter on off, blocked
Better line and length, into the top of off stump from over the wicket. Pooran tries to drop this into point for a run but no dice
forward and steered into the covers, they take on the tight single with success
Heaved to the leg side by Pooran... but the ball plus and Vala goes to collect. No real timing by Pooran, who is trying to hit himself into form on this deck
Chase loses his line down the leg side as Bau swings at it and misses, Pooran can't collect either looped up and defended on the front foot
Keeps his shape to push down the ground and hand the strike back to King
tight leave, but well judged! Spinning through on fourth stump as Vala shoulders arms

Edged! But away beyond the keeper for another boundary to King. Throws everything behind a drive to a ball that isn't as full as anticipated. Even if first slip was in, he'd have to be very fine to have any chance of taking that to his left
floated down the leg side for more extras full and flighted on off, Vala drives down to long-off for one more
over the wicket, full length in the channel. Driven without timing towards cover
Skips down, launches it into the Pavilion! Gorgeous swing from Pooran, straight and true. He was always charging that delivery, and, thankfully for the batter, it was right in the slot
pitched up, possibly a cutter on fifth/sixth stump. Plinked back to the bowler
Overcorrection is a full toss and punched down the ground, over the bowler, for consecutive boundaries!
full and mashed through the covers, four more to Vala! Frees the arms and cracks the ball between mid-off and extra
Six more! Drops to one knee after a skip to the pitch of the ball, launching it over wide long on
back of a length and sizzling through past the shoulder of the bat with Vala looking to defend
Satisfied with his lot, Pooran punches a single down to long off, where there is now a fielder
pitched up and smeared past mid-on! Agricultural but effective from Vala, who seems to have found his timing now
Bit of turn with this off break, tucked away off the pitch, into midwicket, for a single

short and slapped - CHASE HOLDS ON!! A flying two-hander at backward point, then tosses the ball away, cool as you like. Vala is a goner despite hitting his cut right out of the screws. Instinctive grab from Chase, brilliant fielding, and PNG lose their third of the powerplay

Flatter, into the pitch, Pooran tries to slap shot this once more but ends up scuffing into the ground. And that brings the Power Play to an end. A brilliant start followed by an ominous end as Pooran looks to have found his touch
pushed through on off, Bau punches back to the bowler
Flat, skids off a length, muscled down the ground to long off
flat again, swinging away from over the wicket, tapped back
Gets away with that one, dragged down from over the wicket. Pooran tries to help it on its way, but under-edges into the pitch
time for some Bau fun, shuffling around in the crease and lashing an effective reverse-hit past slip through third for four!
Skips down, readjusts to a short than expected length, pushes into the leg side
fired down on the stumps, jabbed to leg
Full, flighted, guided into point
full and straight, Bau sweeps for one to fine leg
Shorter, whipped around the corner on the sweep, but kept to two by the fielder at deep backward square leg to runs to his left to field
round the wicket, tossed up and spinning a touch as Hiri defends on off stump

Deft touch from Pooran, who offers his bat as a ramp to guide down to third as Kariko darts this last delivery in. Good hustle from the fielder chasing from the circle, who clasws the ball back to save two
Just full of a good length, driven out to the man at cover
tossed up and boshed! Bau goes pow, leaping down the track and lumping Chase back over his head through long-off
Back of a length this time, driven back to the bowler
flighted, gripping on off stump, defended coming across
Fuller, into the pads, worked away to a vacant midwicket meaning the keeper has to scurry out from behind the stumps to collect
length ball, cut through point going back in the crease
Onto the pads again, this one punched to midwicket with more force meaning the fielder from cow corner fields and keeps them to one
over the wicket, but spinning down leg looped up and worked on the front foot through midwicket
Into the pads of the left-hander this time, full and tucked away behind square leg
round the wicket again, bowled into the pitch and flicked leg side going back
Full, on off stump, driven to cover once more
pushed through and Hiri defends coming across on off
over the wicket, skips down and loops the ball up outside off. Bau steers one through the covers

Gone! Big wicket as Kariko bags Pooran, but it has been coming... Pooran was again down the pitch, but the length wasn't there. He carries on with the heave and ends up plopping it to the fielder out at wide long on, who ends up taking the catch a good 10 or 15 yards in front of the boundary
round the wicket, flatter outside off. Hiri swats it to backward point
Darted in, skids off the pitch and into the pads of Chase. Impact comfortably outside leg stump, and they get a single as the ball dribbles down to third
tossed up, makes some room to drive through cover to the sweeper
Presses forward and defends a length ball
back over the wicket, Bau advances and hoicks through midwicket
Almost cuts onto the stumps! Not as wide as anticipated, or as short, and King gets away with one there

goes for the reverse - and pouched at slip! Up goes the finger straight away. Came off the back of the bat, I think, then the keeper's thigh. Eventually a simple catch for Powell, as his side continue to dictate proceedings
Worked out to the leg side for a scampered single
round the wicket and angled in, Amini is low and paddles a couple fine to get going
Past the outside edge! Held that one bit, extracted a bit of turn off the pitch and had Chase feeling for the ball outside off stump. Tidy over from the 20-year-old
Sharp, good length, pushed to cover
jumps out and swings leg side, shout of "catch it!" but lands well in front of deep midwicket
Bit of flight with this offie and almost bunted in the air to cover
tossed up on the stumps and swept flat out to deep square leg
To cover once more, this time along the deck
pushed into the covers, Amini thought about running but won't risk it
Sharp again, bit of turn into leg stump, worked away but straight to midwicket
floated up around off stump, defended watchfully

The King is gone! That's a gorgeous piece of bowling - flighted, slower too, asking to be heaved to the short side. King obliges, but goes high rather than far and straight into the hands of Siaka, who steadies himself at deep midwicket to take the catch. Now then!
full and flighted, nudged off the pads through square leg
A second wicket maiden of the innings, as Vala squares Powell up with an arm ball that skews into the covers
dragged down and Bau goes back on off stump to cut one more to the point sweeper
Starts full, no real turn to start, punched beyond him by Chase for a single
lovely, flighted delivery, lures Bau into a drive and beats him on the inside
Flighted leggie but a full toss, slapped deep into the covers where the boundary rider fields
tossed up and punched down to long-off
Full, bit of drift into off stump, Chase steps out and drills this to wide long off for a single
quicker and flatter on fifth stump, skips through past Amini's outside edge
Length, just outside off, cut to backward point
floated up and prodded into the point region coming across
Short, but sharp and straight enough to ensure Powell can't cat, and the West Indies captain settles for working it down the ground for a single
drops a little short and Bau cuts into the wide open acres at backward point for a hustled two
Skiddy off a length, punched out to deep cover
slow and loopy, 81kph and pulled away through backward square leg going deep in the crease
Low full toss on about leg stump, worked out into extra cover for a scampered single
round the wicket, 135kph outside off. Bau steers to backward point
Short of a good length, patted down the ground by Powell who was on the move
length ball angling in, hoicked over square leg. Aggressive intent but not much timing from Bau on this occasion
Dragged down, slapped to deep backward square leg and beats the fielder diving just in front of the sponge! The fielder got around in time and should have gathered cleanly
back of a length, swatted on one leg, Cuthbert Gordon Greenidge-style, but straight to short fine leg
Punched out to cover as Vala goes wider and sharper outside off
back of a length, worked into the leg side
Full, driven on the up and in the air, but bounces a good 15 yards short of long on
continues to hit the pitch, this is dabbed down towards point and they scamper through
Finishes with a straight arm ball which Powell defends back to the bowler
short and flicked off the hip behind square for one more
pushed through, dipping on fourth stump. Punched back to the bowler
Opens the face into the drive, but can't beat point
Bau wow! Woofed back down the ground, through Motie's up-thrust hands as he attempted a spectacular return catch
Chase gets this finer than the previous shot, but still cut off before it leaves the ring
flat and chopped into the off side
Firm drive into the covers, but straight to the fielder
Bau wow wow! Battered over wide long-on! Uses the feet and finds plenty of extra power to clear the ropes
Waits for this flighted delivery, then drives inside cover, down to long off
another boundary, Bau on fire! This time a flowing cover drive - although it probably should have been stopped inside the ring
Fired down leg but intercepted by Powell who is leaning forward feeling for the ball. He might have done well to leave it alone for a wide rather than the single he picks up to midwicket
goes round the wicket, fired down on off stump, defended
Yorker length, outside off, dug out to third by Chase
back of a length, Amini looks to scoop this fine... but fails to connect as he jumps across
Length, sits up and smoked back at the bowler! Soper ducks, and thank god he does because that could have taken his face down to the mid off boundary along with the ball...
shortish and skidding on outside off, Amini dabs it down behind point for one
Flatter, fuller, straighter, timed out to midwicket for a swiftly taken two
short but with pace off, a cutter wide of the stumps. Bau swings hard and misses
Into a length, angled into the hip, Powell gets on top of the bounce and takes the single on offer at midwicket
top-edged over the keeper! Bau makes the most of 139kph behind Joseph's short ball, gets enough bat to send it for four
Length again, fourth stump line, pushed out to the left of cover
back o f a length outside off, steered down into the backward point region
Bit of nibble away from the right-hander off a length, squares up Powell a touch, but adjusts in time to offer more of his bat than simple the edge
slapped through the covers and then there's a misfield as the throw comes in - Joseph not happy - and they steal a couple more
Caught behind?! The umpire's finger is up as Powell attempts a booming drive! He's sent it upstairs for a review... and it's out! Oh my days! Sliver of a spike on UltraEdge off the inside edge
short ball with pace off, paddled away on the pull for two
Flighted, full, driven full-bloodily down the ground to long off
shortish and wide, 129kph. Bau swings and misses
Bit of turn off a full length, into middle stump, defended out to cover
into the pitch, possibly another slower ball. Dabbed wide of backward point
Sharper - hint of a googly? - defended back to the bowler
fired down full, pretty much yorker length. Bau digs it out into the off side
On the up back to the bowler... but just beyond his dive! Rutherford had hard hands into that but it was too far from Amini to be considered a chance
length ball, 136kph and worked through midwicket. Bau on to 49
Flighted wide of off stump, slog-swept into the stands at midwicket! Quality shot from Chase, who finally gets one out of the screws

back of a length, nicked behind! Amini was looking to cut but only manages a little top edge through to Pooran. Pace on, delivered cross seam, and Robert's your mother's brother. A steadying stand for PNG comes to an end
Flatter, slightly shorter this time, and Chase wrists this one down to long on to keep the strike
Full, middle and leg, worked out to long on once more
nudged into the leg side, that's fifty for Bau! From 42 balls, the rock around which PNG have built their innings. Fine work from the No. 4
Around the wicket to Rutherford, who cuts a length ball straight into the ground
pushed through and tapped away watchfully
Similar length, driven this time off the back foot out to deep cover
turned off the pads, can't beat short fine leg
Drops short, but gets away with that as Chase can only work to deep midwicket because of the surprising lack of bounce
flat, 93kph on off stump. Doriga turns to midwicket
Darted into a length, Rutherford duffs a cut into the ground once more
flat outside off, goes back and punches down the track

GOT HIM! The good news for Rutherford is this time he doesn't cut into the ground. The bad news is he's cut straight into right thigh of the keeper Doriga, who ends up keeping the ball in the air and completing the catch. PNG - are you really about to do this?!
angling in on the stumps, Doriga manages to pick a gap on the leg side for his first run

full and swerving down leg 142kph in the channel, beats the bat as Doriga charges... there was a loud, woody noise. Did the ball just clip off stump on its way through? Yes, it fair rattled the woodwork, but the bails didn't move!
Darted in, just off a length, well-timed drive but straight to cover
hoicked away into the leg side
Shorter, this time Chase waits a little and punches beyond that cover fielder

slower ball, bowled 'im! Bau is foxed and punch drunk, backing away and swinging without timing with his stumps exposed. The ball scuds low into middle and leg. Cracking innings from the PNG veteran but Joseph had his number there. West Indies maintaining their grip on proceedings
Darted outside off, Russell defends with an open face into backward point
back of a length, defended stoutly
Fired into leg stump, Russell gets in a tangle as he tries to sweep around his front pad but can't reach
pitched up outside off, 141kph and punched to extra cover
Driven on the up to midwicket, two made with ease as Siaka has to run about 30 yards to his right from long on to gather
into the pitch, 133kph and nurdled through backward square leg for Soper's first run
That's one of them! Enough sighters for Russell - winds up and hooooons a full delivery on the strikes high and handsome over square leg

Back to back boundaries! And how necessary they were... Vala drags another down but doesn't get away with it as Chase flicks it around the corner. In fact, Vala should have got away with it, because the fielder running around from backward square leg got to the ball but didn't get low enough to gather and ends up getting nutmegged
shortish into the body, Soper works it through midwicket and they hurry back for two as the throw comes in. 100 up for PNG
Worked out to deep midwicket
excellent yorker, 129kph and homing in towards the base of off. Soper chops down on it into the covers
Length played off the back foot, punched into deep cover. Great running from Russell puts pressure on the fielder who throws down the middle of the pitch
slower ball, swung away! Doriga is forward and hauls powerfully across the line to deep backward square leg
Driven out to that deep fielder on the off side
full toss, battered in front of the cover sweeper... Joseph does well running around to intercept in front of the rope, a tumbling stop to prevent four
Bang! The ideal release shot for Chase, who presses forward and drives gloriously up and over long off, from low to high
short ball into the pitch, 135kph and swatted out to deep square leg
Flatter, back of a length - powered down the ground for another boundary! The 18th over goes for 18, as Chase stands tall into that lofted drive. Quality
full and crunched, more busy batting from Doriga who pushes hard for two as long-off comes around to field
thick-edged to fine leg! PNG will take them any which way. Full and Soper frees the arms, chops past leg stump to an unguarded part of the ground
Wide yorker, dug out with a horizontal bat down to third. No real pace on the delivery allows deep cover to run around to third and field
pace off, 109kph outside off and dinked for one
Russell steps across to expose his stumps, Morea goes for the toes - on about off stump - and is picked away for a single through midwicket
fired down on the stumps, dragged leg side and into a gap for two more
Flicked over the shoulder for four! Chase steps across and intercepts a full ball on the sweep, lapping it fine on the leg side
length ball, Doriga carves it through extra cover. Super running from Soper as he charges back to the danger end
One bouncer four over cover! Start the car. Morea serves up a full toss outside off stump and Chase gets it out of the middle with a lovely lofted cover drive
Dre Russ nails his yorker, tailing in towards leg stump. Doriga ends up playing it quite well and they pinch one
Wide yorker, ramped out to third to tie the scores...

yorked 'im! Russell rocks middle! Excellent bit of death bowling and Soper can't lay bat on it as he looks to make room for a flap through the off side. Russell finishes his day's work with the most emphatic of dismissals

That's all she wrote! Russell takes West Indies over the line as he digs out a yorker towards long on. West Indies start their 2024 T20 World Cup campaign with victory by five wickets! But my days did they have to work for it! Outstanding fight from PNG, who, truth be told, were ahead of the game on a couple of occasions during this chase but just couldn't stay the course. Plenty of "if only" moments but they've shown the rest of Group C that they're not just here for the ride...
full and lashed through the overs! Doriga brings out the long handle to excellent effect!
short ball, slashed to deep backward point! More prose than poetry from Kiplin, but it's just what his side need. Leans back and lummoxes four more

Joseph runs out the non-striker! Never a run there but PNG are desperate, as the ball ricocheted into the pitch and back off the batter. Joseph hares down in his follow through and underarms into the stumps with Nao well short of his ground
full, straight and turned to leg. They are looking for two, but probably better off with Doriga on strike
goes full and straight, Doriga leaps down the track, but picks out cover. They settle for a scrambled single

low full toss, swatted to mid-off - and that's job done for WI oh dear, Joseph has overstepped. Still a ball to come another full toss, curling in and clubbed to long-on. They hustle back for two to finish off. Spirited effort from PNG, especially Kiplin Doriga at the end
full ball outside off. Bit of movement away. Driven to cover

Strikes first ball! A peach to begin Namibia's T20 World Cup campaign. The perfect left-arm fast bowler's dismissal. Full and straight on middle and leg, just swinging in late a touch. Prajapati looks to flick it across but is done in by the inswing, late one that. Gets rapped low on the front pad. The umpire did not have to be convinced a lot. Raises his finger immediately and Trumpelmann is off the mark in this T20 World Cup! Prajapati chats with his partner about the review but has been sent walking
through the gates! Pitched up around off. van Lingen tries to drive, but the ball takes the inside edge, and rattles his stumps.

Toe-crusher, and that is as plumb as it gets! What a start for Trumpelmann and Namibia. He's rocking the long mane and has a new look, with the head-band on, but the menace with the new ball from left-arm over the wicket to the right-hander stays. Spears it full and straight on middle, and it hits Ilyas full on the front leg, even before he could dig it out. A review wasted as well for Oman
back of a length ball hooked towards fine leg for four!
Full ball around off, strides forward and defends it towards cover
length ball, fourth-stump line. Tapped towards first slip
Play and a miss. Full and outside off, swinging just a shade away. Maqsood goes for the drive but is beaten on the outside edge
full ball just outside stump. Gently tapped to the off side.
Full and swinging in to Maqsood, who gets it off the inner half through backward square leg. Not sure he picked the inswinger there
full and wide. Swinging away. Wild drive attempted. Through to the keeper

Full and sprayed down leg, he misses the flick. Oh my, Trumpelmann has overstepped Wow, a dot ball on the free hit. Bangs it short just outside off, Maqsood pulls it just wide of mid-on, who fires a throw at the bowler's end seeing Khushi take off for a run, but misses. Eventful first over
Welcomed with a four! Length ball angling in to him from outside off, Khushi plants his front foot forward and heaves it over deep midwicket for a one-bounce four
left-arm spin. Around the stumps. Length ball skidding into off stump. Uncomfortably cut to the off side
Edged but well short of short third. A hint of shape away from a good length, he pokes at it
full ball on middle. Darts it in again. Davin tries to fend off the back foot but gets an inside edge onto his pad
Slower one bowled from wide of the crease, Khushi slinks down to hoick it away but is nowhere close to it. 112kph
full ball outside off. Davin cuts, slashes it hard, and gets it past the fielder diving at backward point!
Angling in on a length, 129.2kph, on the pads, Khushi flicks but does so on the pads and to the on side
fullish ball around off stump. Slapped off the back foot to mid off
Length ball moving in to Maqsood, who defends it off the inner half to the on side. Hit him high on the bat, too
good length ball on middle. Extra bounce from the spinner off the deck. Surprises the left-hander, who pulls his bat back in. Keeper takes at chest height
Swinging in from outside off, 128kph, fullish, keeps it out towards cover
length ball around middle and off. Punched back to the bowler
this one's angling away, far across, past the wide-line outside off stump. Keeper and first slip nearly collide full ball, wide outside off. Toe-ended drive to cover for a quick single
Length ball around off, 129.3kph, Khushi looks to paddle but toe-ends it towards midwicket for a quick run
full ball just outside off. Caresses a drive to mid off on this occasion
On a length on off and middle, tucked away through forward square leg
full ball on off. Pace taken off. Fended carefully

A third for rockstar Trumpelmann! Bowls the hard length outside off from around the wicket, despite getting enough swing from over the wicket in the previous over. Khushi is in an attacking mode and looks to take him on. He looks to loft it over the ring on the off side but the bounce is good on this Bridgetown surface. Gets a tad big on him, lobs a catch to mid-off from high of his bat
good length ball, fifth-stump line. Bunted towards cover for a quick single
Inside edged through square leg, as he looks to drive the length ball through off
driven towards cover on this occasion, but can't beat the infield
Full and outside off, wide outside off, Kail goes for the drive but is beaten. 123.6kph
length ball tucks him up, and he works it off his body to the leg side
Full and wide outside off again, 129.8kph, bounces above Kail's blade as he looks to cut it
good length ball around off stump and punched towards cover confidently
Starts off with a full ball outside off, Maqsood goes for the drive but it shapes away to beat his outside edge
length ball around off. Keeps the bat's face open and pushes a shot towards backward point where there's protection
Length ball on off, punched to cover
good length ball around off. Makes room and tries to whack it through the leg side, but the 127kph deceives him slightly. Through to the keeper on the bounce
Connects this time. Angling in on a length, lofts it well over midwicket and it's a vacant space
good length ball outside off. Attempts a cut. Inside edged to the keeper's left
Full and swinging back in, drives it towards mid-on and sprints to the other end
good length ball outside off. Tries to cut, misses, through to the keeper on the bounce. Two-paced again
Full on off and middle, uses his wrists to flick it past short fine leg for two
play and miss. Length ball around off stump, and Davin tried to hit it through the off side
Fuller outside off, driven straight to short cover
Looks to heave it across but gets it off the inner half to short fine leg
fullish ball sits up nicely for Frylinck, and he clatters a shot by reaching forward through the off side for a boundary
Length ball on off, defended towards cover
length ball around off. Punched through to deep extra cover where there's protection
Outside off on a length, 121.9kph, glided to wide third
good length ball around off. Flat-bats a mistimed shot off the back foot, and it very nearly carries to mid on!
Superb shot. Length ball, in the slot, Maqsood flicks it nonchalantly over midwicket after giving him the charge
Length ball outside off, hops and defends it towards cover
half-tracker of sorts on middle. Davin rocks back and this time connects with the pull in front of square well

Bashed away with some swag! Bowled on a length on middle, Maqsood whip-pulls it through forward square leg, beating the man rushing to his right in the deep. He swung himself off his feet while hitting it. Almost Rishabh Pant-esque
length ball on middle. Makes some room and pushes towards cover
Slower length ball, 108.5kph, worked away through backward square leg
back of a length delivery outside off. He inside edges an attempted slap for a single
Angling in on the pads, he misses the flick and gets it to short fine leg off his pad
good length ball outside off. Cut through to deep backward point where some acrobatic fielding saves two
Length ball, slanting in on the pads, he misses the flick and it goes quickly to short fine leg
good length ball outside off and cut hard to deep backward point
Zips back in from a length, 128.7kph, jumps at himi too. He adjusts and steers it through short third
full ball outside off stump and driven to mid off. Crunched
Threads cover. Shortish and outside off, he stands tall and punches it through the off side. Maqsood is batting on a different surface. Was the knuckle ball
good length ball around off stump. Hangs back and swings across the line, pulling over midwicket. Fielder's chase is futile
Fuller on middle and leg, looks to flick it away but gets a soft leading edge towards the bowler
length ball around off. Makes some room and looks to pump a cut through the off side but toe-ends it towards the bowler
full ball on off. Punched off the back foot to cover. This was the legbreak but Ilyas can also bowl offspin
Fires it fullish on the pad, he misses the defence
fuller ball outside off. Turning away. Cut to point
Fuller on off and middle, eased down to long-off
length ball around off. Turning in. Tries to make room and cut. Inside edged to the leg side

Trapped him! Scholtz gets the big man Maqsood, who reviews. Tossed up outside off, fullish length, it spins back in. Maqsood looks to whip it across the line with the spin but perhaps it spins in more than he anticipated. Gets beaten on the inside edge and is struck on the back leg that is in front of the stumps. Three reds on Ball-Tracker and Oman lose both their reviews
length ball around off. Bit of turn away. Cut to point
Fuller and quicker just outside off, he strides forward and blocks
length ball on off. Sharp turn in. Davin is cramped
Full on off again, driven back to the bowler
length ball around off. Cut towards backward point inside the circle. That's a maiden!
Fired full outside off, he slices it to short third
Very full on middle, paddle-swept to short fine leg
good length ball outside off stump. Punched towards point
Edged but no slip. Ayaan comes forward to defend but gets it off the outside edge wide of short third. Turn for Erasmus, who bowled that at 94.4kph
played down the ground for a single
Very full outside off, squeezed it through covers
full ball outside off. Drags the drive towards mid-on for a single
Bowls it from behind the line of the stumps, fullish on off, driven back
full ball outside off stump and he caresses a drive to long off's right for a single
Outside off, full, driven to cover
put down! Goes down as a dropped. Full ball around leg. He loses shape while trying to go over the bowler, but toe-ends it back to Mehran's left. Bowler gets bowl hands to it but it doesn't stick
Slower through the air, on a length on off, he taps it to the off side and rushes to the other end
good length ball outside off and guided to deep backward point. Misfield tempts them for two but they settle for one
full ball on middle and leg. Turning in. Hits the outside of his leg
Fired down leg on a length, he misses the pull Slows it down, lands it on a length on middle and leg, nudged through square leg with the spin
is that the release shot? Tossed up with a bit more air. Wider outside off. Davin gets low, down on one knee, and then hammers a six over wide long on
Full on off, swept to deep backward square leg

falls next ball! And Ilyas picks up the wicket right away. Davin tries to hit the bowler straight down again, but this time holes out to long off. Bowler floats it a bit wider outside off, and the legbreak forces a total mis-hit from Davin
Slows it down, shortens the length, forcing Ayaan to charge down. Gets it off the inner half through midwicket as he looks to hoick it across
gets off the mark first ball. Hit towards long on for a single
Flatter and on a length on middle, nudged through square leg
around the stumps. Length ball on off. Frylinch is hurried onto a defensive shot
Gets hold of that all right. Sees the flight, dances down the track and heaves it well over long-on
full ball on middle and driven through to wide long on for a single
Slows it down, flights it full on off, defended to the on side
Drilled through covers. All timing this. Very full outside off, Kail creams it through cover to beat sweeping rushing to his right
full ball around off and driven to long on for a single
Full and just outside off, guided wide of short third
full ball outside off. Comes down the track and pushes to cover
Full outside off, driven back to the bowler's right
tossed up on off. Bit of turn away. Erasmus tries to drive towards the on-side but it takes a leading edge towards point
The arm ball on a length on off, lunges forward and blocks
good length ball around off. Steered for a single to the off side
Quicker and fuller on the pads, nudged through backward square leg for two
good length ball just outside off. Flat-batted down the ground for a single
Quicker and on a length on the pads, he misses the flick and gets it towards square leg
Namibia 47/2 in ten overs as we take drinks. Zeeshan ends the over with a dot
full ball on middle and leg. Flicked to the leg side
Length ball on middle and leg, he misses the flick and is struck on the front pad. Sliding down though
full ball on middle and he clips it comfortably to deep midwicket for one
Full on the pads again, misses the flick but crosses over for a leg-bye
tossed up around leg stump. Erasmus backs away and finds a way to flick a shot to deep midwicket
Offcutter on a length on off, defended
full ball on middle and leg stump. Tries to flick leg-side but leading edge takes the ball along the ground to the bowler
Length ball outside off, clips it through square leg

is that dropped? Fast, length ball on off stump. Batter makes room and tries to flat-bat it down the V but ends up hitting it to the bowler's left. But he has to move quickly to his left, which he does, however the ball hits his arm
Slides it down leg from a length, Ayaan misses the flick. The keeper collects that and puts out an appeal but given wide Charges down to the full ball and hits it to long-on
cuts this length ball towards point for a single
Full and just outside off, the offcutter again, 112.1kph, Kail pushes forward to defend but gets beaten
Flatter and on a length outside off, goes back and cross-bats it through mid-on
full and wide outside off. Moves to the off side and slaps a shot to the deep
Full on off, drilled down to long-on
full ball around off stump. Driven to wide long off for a single
Flighted full outside off, driven through cover-point
low full toss around off and driven to long on for a single
Quicker and angling away, steered to short third
full ball angling into leg stump. Hurries into him. Tries to flick towards square leg but misses
Slows it down, bowls it on a length on leg, Kali looks to turn it across but gets an inside edge onto the pad and it rolls to the off side
full ball around off. Drilled to wide long off where the fielder dives and ensures it is only two

Erasmus gets on the board and celebrations are back in the Namibia camp. Ayaan's adventurousness does not pay off. Charges down to bash it over the bowler, but he is done in by the flight and the lack of pace in it. Skies it high and long-off settles under it
good length ball around off. Hangs back and plays a very late cut, ensuring it is played fine enough to beat short third
full ball outside leg stump. Tries the sweep but misses, however they get to collect a run slower through the air. Full on off. Tentatively driven to cover
Fuller around off, pats it towards cover and gets to the other end
full ball just outside off. Dances down the track and mis-hits a shot to mid on
Slower through the air, on a length on middle, gets a leading edge towards point
full ball around off. Frylinck gets low and slog sweeps towards deep midwicket. Khalid runs in and appears to be prepped for a catch, but he puts it down after doing the hard yards. Dropped
Fuller on middle, defended to cover
full ball outside off. Erasmus comes down the track and works it to midwicket where there's a gap
Slower one, on middle, 86.6kph, he slogs it off the inner half through square leg
fullish ball around off. Punched to wide long off
Flatter and quicker on middle, punched towards mid-on
full ball on middle and sliding to leg. Frylinck tries the reverse sweep but misses. The ball goes through just past his leg stump and hits the keeper's pad
Once again looks to play it to the on side but gets a leading edge towards cover
fullish ball. Uses his feet to get to the balll but hits it right back to Ilyas
Length ball outside off, zips past the edge as he looks to steer it to third
deposited over cover! Full outside off. Frylinck comes down the track while staying leg-side of the line, and then lifts it over the infield
Full outside off, driven back to the bowler, who stops it in his follow-through
length ball coming into him. Cut tentatively to the off side
Length ball just outside off, 121kph, wrists it to the on side for a quick one
works this off his pads to the leg side for a single
Length ball around off again, 117.9kph, takes off from that spot and raps him on the glove
full ball outside off and he toe-ends a dragged slog to long on
Steers it straight to backward point
overpitched ball around off stump. Toe-ends a shot to the off side
Angling in on off and middle, nudged to square leg
length ball around off. Comes down the track and tries to play it leg side. But it hits his pad
Slows it down, bowls it wide outside off, fetches the slog to deep midwicket
flatter ball. Length ball around off. Makes some room and brings out the cut. But on the bounce to point
Flatter on a length outside off, slapped to cover
the squeeze is working! Length ball outside off. Erasmus tries to flat-bat an aggressive shot over long on, but it doesn't have the elevation or the distance! Taken in the deep
On middle and leg, defended with a full face
full ball on middle stump. Gets forward and tries to play down the V. But it hits the inside half and rolls away to the leg side
Wide outside off, on a length, slapped away from short cover for two
full ball around off. Tries to sweep, and manages to get something on it, even though it wasn't wholly convincing! To fine leg
Length on middle, worked away wide of short fine
good length ball just outside off. Guided towards point
Spins away from wide outside off, he cuts it towards backward point where Smit dives and saves runs

Prolonged appeal and Erasmus gets the decision in his favour. Nadeem wants to review but Oman have none left. Erasmus lands it on a length and spins it in just a touch, beating the batter on the inside edge and rapping him o the front pad. The only question was if it pitched in line. Looks to be the case and a good decision that from umpire Joel Wilson. Three reds, shows the Hawk-Eye
strikes this full ball to the cover fielder in the deep
Quicker on leg, flicked through midwicket
full on the stumps. Frylinck moves off side slightly before clubbing a sweep to deep backward square leg!
Very full on middle, bowled from behind the stumps, gets it off the edge back towards the bowler
shin-high full toss around off. Gets down on one knee and sweep-pulls to deep square leg
Slows it down and lets it spin in from a length, clipped through midwicket
flatter length ball. Angling into his pads. Tucked to the leg side
Slower and on a shortish length on middle and leg, he goes back and works it through midwicket
nudged off his pads to the leg side
Another length ball punched through midwicket
tucked off his pads to the leg side once again
short ball around off. Frylinck is through the pull too early. Mistimed towards midwicket
Length ball outside off, punched towards cover
full ball on off. Bit of swing away. Fended to the off side
Dropped after a valiant effort. Frylink charges in from long-off, gets down low but fails to hang on. Mehran looked to loft the length ball from Lungameni but hit it almost too well to long-off
fullish ball swinging away. Throws his hands at it, slapping a shot through the off side, past the fielder at deep point
Cuts it towards backward point for a quick run
around the stumps, slower ball around off. Struck down the ground for a single

Excellent contact this time. Anticipates another length ball and gets his dancing shoes on. Charges down and hits it well over the bowler's head. No chance of long-off coming around. A boundary after 44 balls
full ball on his toes and tucked to the leg side for a single
Now Lungameni anticipates another charge and bowls a bumper, Mehran charges down and has to duck
