good length ball around off. Smit tries to work it leg side with the bat's closed face but a leading edge very nearly gives cover a catching chance!
Length ball outside off, once again Mehran is down the wicket but misses it because it bounces lower than he expects
Fetch that! That has gone a long, long way. The knuckle ball outside off, 109kph, on a length, Kail clears his front leg and deposits it way over long-on
good length ball outside off. Tries to cut, but extra bounce forces an edge off the bat, and it flies past the keeper for four more!

What a catch, Wiese! The big man's still got it. Goes pace on this time, on a length on off, and the surface helps him. Kail looks to force it back but the ball holds on the surface and he lobs it back. Wiese gets forward and low down in his follow-through and takes it with a tumble
fullish ball just outside off. Cut is stopped by point
LIfts off from a length just outside off, gets Shakeel on his glove and to the off side

twist? Perhaps not given Frylinck is still out there. But some Oman flags flutter as Smit holes out at long on. Variable bounce again as Smith tries to club Mehran for a big-shot, however it comes off the top-half of the bat.

LBW? Nope says the umpire, Wiese wants a review. Goes wide of the crease and angles a length ball in from outside off, Mehran looks to heave it across but completely misses it and is hit on the thigh pad of the back leg. Is height a factor? Not at all, three reds on the Hawk-Eye and Wiese exults as soon as he spots it on the big screen
full ball around off stump. Caresses a drive to cover
Length ball on off, gets across and wrists it through midwicket
full ball wide outside off, but inside the tram-lines. The ball barely bounces and dribbles through to the keeper
Chops the length ball to backward point
good length ball on a fourth-stump line. The cut is hit well, but straight to the man lurking at point. Namibia need 14 off 12
full ball on his pads and clipped to the leg side, but not for any run
Angled in on a length, clipped through square leg
flat-batted down the ground for a single

Chaos! Rolls his fingers on the length ball outside off, Shakeel gets a thick outside edge to short third. He is ball-watching even as his partner comes almost to him for a run, is sent back. The short third fielder throws it to Trumpelmann, who has all the time in the world to take aim and hit the stumps at the bowler's end but he misses, eventually conceding a run

just clears wide long on! Length ball around leg stump and Wiese backs himself to clear the boundary with a big shot. Even though the timing isn't perfect, he targets the shortest boundary of this ground, and Aayan's attempt is futile.

Trapped lbw! No need to review this, as the ump gives it straightaway. Length ball in line of the stumps, Kaleemullah gets across but misses his nudge. Hits him low on the front pad, fourth strike for Trumpelmann
yorker, fourth-stump line. Bit of tail away. Dug away to point
Full and angling in on the front pad, he gets a thick inside edge and the ball rolls to deep third off his pads
yorker on middle stump and all Wiese can do is keep the ball away from the stumps. Dug away to the leg side
Full and outside off, Shakeel looks to go over off but is beaten
yorker length ball on off to end the over, but Frylinck manages to bunt it away to the off side for a single towards square leg
Charges down and gets a thick outside edge to deep third. No five-for for Trumpelmann but what a spell, his best in T20Is

Erasmus tries twice and does not succeed on both occasions. Shakeel treats Wiese as a fast offspinner and charges him to hit over covers. The Namibia skipper gives it the chase, slides and pulls the ball back but it still goes on with the momentum and makes contact with the boundary cushions
oh my days! More drama! Around the stumps. Full ball on middle and leg. Frylinck tries to clip it leg side but the hits his pad, and then it ricochets onto the stumps!
Very full on off, dug out back towards the bowler
and it is a dot ball! Green makes room at first but then returns to his normal stance as Mehran bowls a full ball outside off. Green attempts to ramp it over short-third but misses
Banged short and outside off, Shakeel stays back and hacks it over short third

O man, Oman are in this! Green tries to play a cheeky leg-side scoop over short fine leg but he misses. Mehran's full ball on off stump hits him on the pad and the umpire gives him out LBW. Namibia review. Crashing into the stumps!
All over! Short and wide outside off again, Shakeel backs away and slashes it straight to backward point. Wiese finishes with three as Oman are bowled out for 109
Kruger gets Wiese on strike with a single. Full ball outside off and pushed to cover's left

full ball on off and he creams the straightest of straight drives. Ball smashes into the stumps at the bowler's end and it ricochets away towards cover for a couple of runs. The stumps have probably saved a boundary there!

WE ARE GOING TO A SUPER OVER! Good length ball outside off. Ball takes extra bounce and Wiese can't cut. Keeper can't grab cleanly either, and the ball falls to his left. Wiese and Kruger run across and the keeper tries a reverse throw while diving. He misses, and Kruger completes the run. We finish on a tie.
length ball on off stump, QdK tries to flick through leg I think, but  only hits it into his pad
full one just outside off, just blocked towards mid off, and they call nice and early and sneak a single to start
length outside off, pushed towards cover without much timing. They think about a run and decide against
back of a length ball on the stumps, fended away - not without a little discomfort - toward point
length outside off, blocked towards mid off. Fielder closers in quickly
length ball on the stumps, Kusal gets across and swings it behind square on the legside, and fine leg runs around to keep it to one
length ball just outside off, clips to leg but straight to midwicket
full, swinging  - straightening in the air. This pitches full and might have just pitched on leg but is swinging past the wickets. Nissanka tries to flick through leg but misses and it thuds into pad
length ball, fired down leg. Mendis does well to get a glove behind it length ball just wide of off, squirts that behind square on the offside and they take a comfortable single
back of a length ball just outside off, hurries through and Nissanka's waft does not make contact. That's a little bit of that extra bounce that Jansen generates
length wide of off, and Hendricks pushes out at it, and gets a thick outside edge that sends the ball through deep third for the first boundary. South Africa are on their way

more good bounce. This takes off off a back of a length. It's passing just over off, and Nissanka is lucky not to get glove to that. Carries nicely through to the keeper so there is some pace on this pitch.

a bit of width, about 40 cm outside off, and it's short - about chest heigh. Mendis throws his bat at it and it comes off the top half of the bat and flies away to the boundary beyond deep third. First four.

first ball in a World Cup is a rank full toss. Loses control and sends it waist high way down off. Called a no ball full, on the stumps, swinging in. QdK plays a big shot, closes the face, but can only get a sharp two to deep square leg as fine leg comes around to clean up
back of a length tighter into the stumps. Defended from the crease and they take a single into the infield
fullish on the stumps again, which the batter tries to hit through leg. Goes into the legside infield off the inside half of the bat and they scamper through
length ball just outside off, opens the face and runs it to deep third

Thushara gets a Test-style wicket off a Test match length. This was in the corridor, length ball, a little wide of off, but - vitally -  swinging away. Hendricks pushes at it, gets an edge, and first slip gobbles it  up. Finally a little joy for Sri Lanka. Thushara's job is to give new-ball wickets and he's delivered one.
length ball, angled in and jagging in as well. That's a beauty.  Mendis is leaden footed as he defends and it whizzes between bat and pad and bounces over the stumps
full on the stumps, clipped towards square leg. and they skip through for a single
length ball on the pads, poked square on the leg side but the fielders are all over it so no chance of a run
full on the stumps, swinging in again, clipped straight of midwicket and they scamper one

short ball, but misfired down leg biiig swing and a miss. It's the bounce that is troubling Sri Lanka at the moment. Mendis tried to smash this fullish ball over wide mid on, but the bounce and perhaps a little seam movement takes it past the outside edge.
full, wide-ish of off, swinging away. Markram tries to stroke through the covers but can't time it. Gets it far enough away from the fielder to get a single
length ball on off stump, just defended from the crease
length on the stumps, defended to leg
beauty! This is a length ball, pitching just on off, seaming away, squares the batter up and beats the outside edge as Markram prods at it
struck hard and straight to mid off, but a misfield allows a single. This was full and well outside off, drilled to mid off and the fielder there only gets a knee to it and allows a single

this one comes in with the angle, and maybe jags a bit off the seam as well and hits Markram in the box! Mathews isn't bowling very fast (decidedly in the 120kph range), but he's getting some movement and making Markram uncomfortable. He needs some medical attention after that.
short ball, but poorly directed. This is down leg full outside off, drilled to cover. This time the fielder makes a clean stop
back of a length on the stumps, defended to leg
short of a length outside off, Mendis tries to run it off the face of the bat but doesn't connect
length on about off stump, just defended
full just outside off, opens the face and slices this just in front of point and this is a slooow outfield, so they can only get a couple
back of a length, bit too wide of off, so Markram gets back and plays a nice back-foot punch through point to keep strike
length ball just outside off, Mendis tries to chop it to deep third again, but gets a thick under edge and the ball doesn't go far
full, on the stumps, tailing away. Markram is playing it safe right now. He pushes it back to the bowler.

he gets a wicket off his first World Cup delivery. This was fullish, wide, and Nissanka's eyes lit up. He threw his bat at it, but as has been the case right through these early overs, he underestimated the bounce (Baartman, like the other SA bowlers, is a tall man). Gets a thick edge and it flies pretty much directly to deep third, who barely moves a couple of metres. That pressure had been building.

that's a glorious shot! Soon as he sees some width he goes after it and absolutely nails it! The best timing seen all day. Just leans into this lofted cover drive and sends it over the short boundary on that side. That will deflate Sri Lanka a little.
full ball on the stumps to start, poked towards cover
overcorrects with the line, and goes into the pads. Markram plays this through midwicket
play and a miss, this is a length ball outside off, which Kamindu offers a defensive shot to. Has his outside edge beaten
length on the stumps, again Markram clips to leg, a bit squarer this time, but there's only a single on this occasion
length ball on the pads, pitching outside the stumps and heading to leg. Kamindu tries to turn it around the corner but it hits pad and dribbles away down leg. They take a leg bye
full, wide of off, swinging in a little. QdK plays a big drive but the swing makes him miss it, Beats his inside edge.
another play and miss, this time because of the swing. this is fullish and wide, and there's plenty of curve in the air, and Mendis' big lofted drive does not connect
swinging in a little, yorker length. QdK just keeps it out and jams it back to the bowler
ooof, swinging again! This is full and on the stumps, Mendis just tries to keep this out and just about manages, the ball coming off the outside half of the bat and skidding off towards point
length ball just wide of off, defended towards cover
length ball wide of off, Kamindu lets that one go through, having shouldered arms

is that out? Shanaka squares Markram up and Kamindu Mendis has taken an outstanding slip catch. This is fullish, pitching on the stumps, seaming away and Markram, who is trying to flick through midwicket, gets an outside edge to it. It's dying desperately on Kamindu who is at about second slip, but he gets fingers underneath it and completes the catch comfortably. Sri Lanka still think they are in this.

more swing and more swinging and missing. This is fullish, well outside off stump (Rabada is coming around the wicket to the leftie), and Kamindu throws his bat, but the swing takes it away from the outside edge

big appeal for a caught behind, but did Stubbs touch that? I'm not sure. Sri Lanka have reviewed.  This was a length ball down leg, which the batter tried to glance, but he misses. The on-field umpire has given it a wide. The snicko shows it flicking thigh pad, but it's nowhere near the bat.
finally gets a run, off his sixth ball. This was fuller and closer to the stumps. Kamindu opens the face and squirts it to point, and a slight misfield allows him to get a run
length ball just outside off, defended
length ball on the stumps, Kusal backs away and tries to hack it through the legside, but gets an under edge that goes to midwicket. The fielder shies at the stumps but that's a comfortable single
length outside off, another defensive shot

a big shot and a rare success for Sri Lanka in this powerplay. This was full on the pads, and Kamindu plays a pick up shot over square leg, makes an excellent connection , and gets a one-bounce four. High risk shot, but Sri Lanka need boundaries desperately
dropped by Kusal Mendis. This was fullish outside off, a healthy edge off Stubbs' bat, keeps low and Kusal has to dive hard to his right but he still should have taken that.
length outside off, dropped towards deep third and they scramble one
full ball, just wide of off, QdK tries to chop down on it, but it passes under the bat
beauty! This is almost a test-match delivery, length ball, just seaming away, beating the left-hander's outside edge as he attempts to defend.
full one, swinging in, pitched on the stumps, driven to mid on and they think of a run but decide against
fuller, on the stumps, driven without a lot of timing past the bowler, and they sprint one as mid off comes around to clean up
really cramping him for room with a length ball, seaming in. QdK gets low and chops it towards cover point and get a single
play and miss again, in the channel, nibbling away off the seam, and Mendis' forward defence is not good enough to get a touch
back of a length ball, flicked off the thigh pad - or was that leg byes? Kusal Mendis goes chasing after it and gets there first, near fine leg. Yes, it was off the pad
even better! Angled in, seaming away, missing off by a few centimetres, as Mendis' forward defence again gets beaten. Squared him up properly this time
fullish ball, just outside off, moving away. Play and a miss

wonderful. This is like a Test match so far. Length ball that jags back in, hits Mendis on the pads and raises a big appeal. That was maybe bouncing over, or perhaps seaming too far. No review from South Africa
fullish just outside off, defended into the legside and they can scamper one as midwicket closes in
runs at Baartman, out of frustration than anything. And opens up his shoulders and clubs this over cover, without a lot of timing. Doesn't clear the fielder by that much and they spring two
fullish ball on the pads, poked towards deep midwicket where theer is a fielder
flatter delivery outside off, not a lot of turn but it beats the batter's prod
full, wide of off, opens the face and squirts it out towards backward point. Pathirana makes a nice diving stop there but can't prevent a single
reverse sweep here, flatter outside off again. Beats short third but the slow outfield gives him only two
length ball on the pads, de Kock looks to defend to leg but is struck on the front pad (pitched outside leg). Ball dribbles off towards cover and they take a single
trots down the pitch to another dart, this time on the stumps, pushed to mid on for one
full outside off, pushed to mid off and there's no single
quick one on the stumps again. Kusal goes back plays it under the eyes, and drops it towards midwicket for another quick single
jags it in off a length and beats Stubbs all ends up. This was a length ball, and Stubbs played all around it and the ball whizzed between bat and pad, but over the stumps
flatter ball slightly wide of off, goes back and chops it to the cover sweeper. That outfield is seriously slow
length on the stumps again. This time the batter gets across, works it to square leg and they sprint one

no timing! This is a shorter delivery, and Mendis gets deep in his crease to try and club it over deep midwicket but cannot get any sort of momentum into his shot. Drops halfway between the 30-yard circle and the deep fielder and they only get another single.
bottom edge that bounced short of the keeper? Well, almost. This was an inside edge that bounced short of Kusal Mendis, and he couldn't collect cleanly, so they take the single
back of a length ball wide of off, Kusal tries to bash this over midwicket but the bounce does him in for the umpteenth time. Misses
length on the stumps, defended towards mid off and they sprint through on an early call
pretty much a repeat of the previous shot. Short ball wide of off, and he goes deep in the crease again and tries to smash but not a touch on that
length ball outside off, inside edge into pad.
back of a length over the stumps, Mendis shuffles to off this time and tries to help this over his shoulder but he again cannot connect, perhaps beaten by pace that time
length ball wide of off, opens the face and runs it towards deep third

finally gets some bat to ball, but it's not convincing! This is a ball on the thigh pad that Kusal tried to swing over the legside. Gets a terrible connection and that would have been a simple catch for a square leg, but there's no fielder there
first big one from Quinton de Kock! This is a shortish ball that sits up, and bashing that over deep square leg for six. An authoritative shot and it cleared the short boundary easilty.

Kamindu Mendis is gone! They just can't get power into these shotst. This was length on the stumps, that Kamindu gets across and tries to flick over square leg. Doesn't clear the boundary though. Doesn't even get close. The fielder there takes a simple catch, about 10 metres in from the rope. He was hitting ot the longer side.
length ball outside off, defended towards cover
short ball just outside off, fended defensively towards point, on the hop. Nasty one to get first up
full ball, swinging in slightly, pushed towards mid off
darted in at the stumps, turned towards midwicket
length outside off, Stubbs stays in the crease and defends

gone! Hasaranga down the track to Maharaj straight away trying to bash this one down the ground. But he doesn't get to the pitch of the ball, and although there's not much turn, there's enough to take it away from his shot, and QdK flicks the bails off before Hasaranga can make an attempt at returning to the crease. South Africa are bossing this! Hasaranga's promotion has not worked.
Stubbs comes down the track but can't do much with this length ball. Just defends back to Shanaka.

two in two! Sri Lanka are falling apart. This was not necessarily a great ball, and not even an aggressive shot. This is a quickish delivery headed towards off, and Sadeera, without a lot of foot movement, tries to squirt this through off. He lets the ball slip between bat and pad though, and it clatters into off. Uff, Sri Lanka are struggling bad.
shortish, wide of off, cut out to deep backward point
floated up on the stumps to the lefty, Asalanka gets across and glances it past the keeper and gets two for it.
fullish on the pads, clipped to deep backward square for a single
tossed up wide of off, pushed through point for a single
length ball angled in towards off, just played towards mid on and they take one
shortish, but flat, just wide of off. Kusal goes back and hacks it to deep midwicket
yorker, at 144kph, all Kusal can do is dig this out back towards the bowler
full delivery on the pads, flicked to deep square for single
back of a length ball on about leg, and Kusal drags this aerially over midwicket - an ugly hack - but it gets him a couple at least
back of a length ball just outside off, bounces over the batter's shot. This is what the SA bowlers did
length ball outside off, fended past short third for a single
another one. If you can bowl quickly on this track, you can rock it. This is 150kph, bounced way higher than QdK expected, and bounced way over his shot. PLay and a miss.
fullish outside off, pushed back towards the bowler who fields it on his follow through
shortish, wide of off, cut away to deep backward point
length ball on the legs, which Asalanka tries to turn around the corner. Hits his pad and they scamper a leg bye
full delivery on the stumps, driven down the ground, without a lot of timing. Mid on comes around to clean up but they can sprint one

Kusal goes! This is turning into embarrassing territory. Kusal just has not found any sort of timing and as he tries to launch this one over the square leg boundary, can only get a very imperfect connection that goes hiiiigh towards fine leg. Tristan Stubbs is down there, tracking it against the sunlight, but making sure he gets under it and completes the catch.
bouncer, but too short, over the head. Called a wide. length ball wide of off, chopped just straight of point and they sprint one. There's a shy at the stumps, but Stubbs is home easily
Leading edge! But falls well short of Maharaj as Asalanka lunges out at this
tossed up on the stumps, tucked towards midwicket for one
length ball, swept towards deep backward square from around off stump
length googly, on the pads. Goes back and turns this behind square leg for one
full and quicker on the stumps, defended with a full face
floated on the stumps, nudged towards midwicket and they run hard to make the second. Sensible play here from the two batters
shorter outside off, stands tall and punches this into the covers
good length on middle and leg, defended

Nearly a run out! Good length outside off, goes back and punches this towards point. They think about scurrying a tight single, but Asalanka is turned back and needs a dive here to see him home. Direct hit would've seen him gone. Brilliant work in the field as well
And the captain strikes! This one is tossed up but just stops in the surface. De Kock  pushes at it on the front foot and only manages to chip back a gentle catch to Hasaranga
Edged past a diving slip! Zips off the surface as Asalanka looks to cut this late. Edge doesn't really give slip a chance though
good length googly on off, goes back and punches this down to long-off for one
back of a length angled in, tucked through midwicket for one
back of a length just outside off, left alone

Flicked and straight to the man in the deep! Just like Kamindu earlier, Asalanka whips this off the pads. Catches it cleanly but it's right down Hendrick's throat at deep square leg. Sri Lanka are down for the count
Attempted yorker, 148kph, but it's swinging past leg stump. Inside edge on to the pads and they take a quick single
good length on middle and leg, tucked in front of square leg for one
full and wide outside off, eased towards deep point
back of a length, nipping in. Defensive push towards midwicket

Klaasen is on the floor! But he survives. 151kph yorker, darting in on leg stump. Klaasen somehow gets bat on this and deflects it square on the leg side, but he plants himself on the floor for his efforts. Still manages the run though
Hooks and misses! This was short, 142kph. Mathews goes for it but doesn't get anything on it as it goes over his shoulder
full on middle and off, clipped through midwicket for a couple more
Angled in from wide of the crease on a hard length, Mathews sits deep in his is crease and defends
Bouncer outside off, 148kph, left alone
good length on the stumps, gets forward and defends
tossed up on the stumps, defended
angled on the pads, stays back and clips this behind square leg for one
good length leg break on middle, defended once more
good length, 82kph, on the stumps. Sticks a bit in the surface as Mathews lunges forward to defend
Dragged short and Klaasen rocks back and clubs this down towards long-on
goes back and punches this but it's straight at short mid-on
good length leg break outside off, sliced straight to point
First six of the innings! Skips down the track and lofts this straight over long-off. 50 up for SL too
Scorcher at short cover! My word! This was tossed up on off and Stubbs cracks the leather off this. But Asalanka grabs this nice and low to his left two-handed, with some outstanding reactions
good length on the stumps, gets forward and turns this straight towards short midwicket
tossed up leg break from around the wicket, worked off the front foot straight to square leg
Top edge and safe! This was short of a length on off, angled in from wide of the crease. Shanaka looks to pull this but has to adjust as the ball holds up in the surface. Falls safe behind square leg
good length outside off, Klaasen punches it tentatively to cover
Another short one, angled in straighter. Once more half pulled away, in the air, behind square for one
Good length and this one sticks in the surface. Klaasen is forced to check his drive
back of a length on off, 124kph slower ball, defended back towards the bowler
wide yorker just outside off. Looks to dig this out, but backward point does excellently to save the single
Shanaka finds the short boundary! Short ball and Shanaka goes after it. Top edge, but it sails over the shorter fine leg boundary!
Oof! Inswinging yorker on the stumps, Klaasen gets an inside edge on the drive as he's caught on the crease. Single to deep backward square
Full on off, 136kph, from over the wicket. Opens the face on the drive, but it's straight to point
full on middle and leg, tucked past midwicket. Just the single
short of a length, pace-off and angling away from off. Shanaka opens the face and looks to guide this behind square but can't beat slip
Quality yorker, but Klaasen just about gets bat on it. Ball bobbles away towards square leg and they sneak another single
Oof! Got a hold of this! Greets Rabada with a bang, does Mathews. This was full on off, and Mathews just swings this away over wide long-on. That went far
good length leg break, holds up in the surface as Klaasen stands tall and fends this into the offside
Full and wider of off. Mathews flicks his wrists and punts it over point for one
good length on the stumps, back foot punch. Hasaranga dives to his left and saves the run
back of a length, 140kph, Shanaka looks to drop this behind point for a quick single but the fielder is quick to it
Clobbered down the ground! This is floated right up and Klaasen needs little more invitation, as he leans back and just launches this over long-on
Swings and misses! This was quick and straight, Shanaka makes room and swings big, but he misses all ends up and Rabada hits - smack dab into the middle of middle
And again! Another full one, and this one is pummelled flat and straight
full on the stumps, Theekshana stays deep in the crease and defends
Shorter and pulled away. Timing isn't there as long-on runs around to collect
Short and Theekshana turns away from it. It's not as short as he thinks as this whizzes past his helmet through to the keeper. Wry smile from the batter
good length on the stumps, makes room but ends up punching this to Hasaranga's right. He dives and saves the run
back of a length, angled into the pads. Can't get any bat on this but runs the leg bye
good length on off, stays back and defends
full on off, inside edge on the drive but only one as midwicket dives to his right and gets a good hand on it
length on the stumps, skids through. Back foot punch down to long on
Swing and a miss! Full and slow, 118kph, from the back of the hand. Mathews is way too early on the stroke
short of a length, scuffed pulled down to deep midwicket
And now Sri Lanka's last bastion of hope also perishes! This was shorter and quicker, rushes Mathews on the hook. Top edged and it's straight to Baartman at fine leg
length on off, goes back and punched to short cover
Well directed yorker, and well kept out by Pathirana as well
short-arm pull, on the bounce towards deep midwicket
Swings and misses! Good length just outside off, and Theekshana gets nowhere near it
Appeal for leg before as Miller is rapped on the pads in front of leg stump. Not out is the call but SL review. This looked to be pitching well outside leg on first glance, and indeed it is.
good length on off, gets behind the line and defends
good length leg break just outside off, cut to deep point for a single
full on off, driven but not timed straight to mid-off
And that is that! Miller skips down the track and whips this past Hasaranga to beat the man at long-on. South Africa win by 6 wickets
short and ducked under
good length, 133kph, seams away a touch and beats the outside edge as well as off stumps.
And again! Just too good for Theekshana, who just can't get bat on it
full and slips down leg, wide given. Well kept Back of a length wider of off, Theekshana pokes at it and misses
Makes room and swings hard. Misses by a wide margin as this bounces over off stump
Top edge and taken easily at mid-on! This was full on middle and leg, Pathirana gets a leading edge as he looks to work it onside. Ends up going high but not very far. Sri Lanka are 9 down
low full toss, angled in on leg. Kept out
good length, angled in towards leg. Thushara though is very eager to move out of the way, ball hits high on the bat
Again moves away, ball hits bat rather than the other way around
This time Thushara takes the blow on his pads. Full but angling past leg as Thushara moves away once more. He really isn't keen on being anywhere near the ball
full outside off, Theekshana clears that front leg and swings. Beaten on the outside edge

short of a length on the stumps, worked briefly in the air towards the vacant midwicket. Theekshana is looking to farm the strike but Thushara is already haring away. He's almost at the batting crease before being turned back. Could've run two there honestly
swing and a miss as this short one zips through
Put away as a big cheer goes up! Sits up from a short of a length and Theekshana clobbers this pull wide of long-on
Swing and a miss! Short outside off. Quicker and steeper than the last one as Theekshana misses
full and straight, worked down to long-on for one

full on off, mistimed heave down the ground. They look to run two, but mid-off running back sends in a gun throw and Thushara is well short. Sri Lanka are bowled out for 77, it's their lowest ever T20I score
tossed up on a length just outside off. Gurbaz lunges forward and defends. A hint of spin away from the batter
Ronak starts off with a boundary! Full just outside off. Shapes back in slightly but Ronak accounts for it. Leans into the drive and times it crisply past extra cover!
what a way to get off the mark! Given a bit of air but this is fuller and into the slot on the stumps. Gurbaz backs away, goes through the line and lofts it cleanly over the long off fence!

Farooqi knocks him over now! This is full again and swinging back into Ronak. The major difference from the last ball is that this starts on the stumps and finishes on the stumps. Ronak tries to drive but the ball breezes past the inside edge before thundering into leg stump!
even fuller, just outside off. Perhaps a bit quicker too and Gurbaz pushes it towards cover

huge appeal, and given! Farooqi has two in two! Devilish in-swinging delivery, bowled very full on middle and leg. Mukasa is all at sea and plays down the wrong line completely. The ball kisses the back pad, and the umpire has no hesitation in raising his finger. Mukasa does not bother with the review, and Uganda are two down!
full on middle and leg. Straightens a shade and Gurbaz defends it back to the bowler
oh, nearly! Into the blockhole just outside off. Riazat, rather tentatively, jams down on it and the ball squirts off the toe-end, just past the stumps

angled in, following the batter outside leg. Gurbaz tips it into the off side and calls for the single. Kyewuta picks it up and fires a shy at the batter's end. The keeper cannot gather, though, and Afghanistan get four overthrows. It was definitely worth a shy but the keeper should have perhaps done better!
length ball that finishes on middle and leg. Riazat comes half forward and pokes at it, probably getting an inside edge before the ball hits him on the pads
slanted in full on the pads. Ibrahim gets a big stride in and pokes it towards long on to get off the mark
full just outside off. Hoops back in and Riazat accounts for it, defending it solidly off the front foot
very full on middle and leg. Ibrahim digs it out towards mid on and saunters across to the other end
full on off. Ssesazi comes forward and pushes it to mid off
put away with conviction! Full toss on the pads and that is a freebie for Gurbaz. Shimmies down the track and then clips it to mid on's right!
first boundary for Ssesazi! Shortish outside off. Skids off the surface and rushes Ssesazi on the cut. Gets a nick and it races away past short third!
length in the fifth stump channel. Gurbaz advances again and pushes it into the off side for a sharp single
fired in fuller and quicker on leg stump. Ssesazi has a slog across the line and seems to miss it. Pings off the back leg into the off side
back of a length on middle and off. Ibrahim gets behind the line and taps it into the stumps at the other end

Mujeeb in on the act now! Plenty of revs on this one, and this is bowled on a length outside off. Ssesazi looks for the sweep but the over-spin on the ball means that it bounces extra. Spoons up off the top edge and Farooqi completes the easiest of catches at short fine leg!
four more! Another full toss sliding into the pads and Ibrahim takes full toll. Gets under it and flicks it well over mid on!
angled into the pads. Nakrani lets the ball come to him before working it into the on side to get off the mark
short and wide outside off. Zips off the surface and beats Ibrahim for pace as he looks to cut
peach! Fullish outside off. Pitches and straightens just a shade, enough to take it past the outside edge of Riazat's prod
length on middle and leg. Gurbaz skips down the track and pats it to mid off for another quick single
back of a length on off. Decks back in sharply and Nakrani is too late to get his bat down. Thuds into his pads
shortish outside off. Ibrahim gets up on his toes and punches it towards extra cover
fuller, swinging into middle and off. Nakrani comes forward and bunts it to mid on for a single
cutter on a length on middle and off. Ibrahim presses half forward and jabs it towards extra cover
back of a length delivery pushed across the batter outside off. Riazat lets it go
off-pace on a fullish length on leg stump. Ibrahim advances, gives himself room and chips it on the bounce to mid off. That might have just stuck in the surface too
length ball hung outside off. Riazat watches it go through to the keeper
up and over! Width outside off and Gurbaz pounces. Shimmies down the track to get the length he wants and crashes it over mid off!
length delivery starts outside off and boomerangs back into the batter. Riazat dangles his bat and the ball chunks away off the inside edge towards deep square leg
off-cutter on a length on middle and off. Gurbaz lets the ball come to him before dabbing it behind point
back of a length outside off. This one shapes away and Nakrani, wafting at it, is beaten on the outside
back of a length on middle and off. Nips back sharply and raps Gurbaz on the pad, who has advanced. Pings away towards third man
slanted in full on middle and leg. Riazat comes forward and defends
hard length on middle and leg. Ibrahim is cramped for room and stabs it towards mid wicket
fullish outside off. Does not spin back in and holds its line, breezing past the outside edge of Riazat's bat
goes through! Back of a length outside off. Ibrahim picks the length early, stands up tall and bashes it towards Mukasa at extra cover, who cannot get anything behind it!
pushed into the batter on a length on leg stump. Riazat tucks it off his pads towards deep square leg
back to back boundaries! This is shorter outside off and that is what Ibrahim wants. Gets up on his toes and flays it over backward point!
short, wide and punished! Too much width (from Mujeeb's perspective), and Nakrani cashes in. Waits on it and cuts it fiercely past backward point!
hard length on middle and leg. Ibrahim does not have any room to work with and plays it back to the bowler. That is probably the length the pacers need to be hitting more often
carrom ball on a length outside off. Nakrani opens his bat face and dabs it towards short third
full on middle and off. Ibrahim drives it to mid off and runs as soon as he plays the stroke. Makes the single comfortably
shortish outside off. Nakrani tries to cut it fine but is a touch late on the stroke. Makes no contact in the end
dropped! Tossed up on a length outside off. Ibrahim wafts at it away from his body and gets a thick outside edge that the keeper cannot hold on to. Very tough chance, it must be said
wayward delivery, bowled a mile outside off. Called a wide by the umpire, unsurprisingly length outside off. Riazat presses half forward and stabs it towards deep mid wicket
fuller outside off. Ibrahim comes forward and pushes it into the off side

chopped on! Hard length just outside off. Comes back in with the angle and Nakrani, trying to dab it away, does not quite have the room he wants. Rolls off the higher part of the bat and bobbles into the stumps. Uganda four down now, and staring down the barrel!
angled in full on off. Ibrahim punches it to mid off and with the fielder on the edge of the circle, the single is completed easily
fullish just outside off. Ramjani is awfully late on the stroke and chops it on the bounce to slip
slanted in on a back of a length on middle and off. Gurbaz backs away and cuts it towards backward point. The Ugandan captain misfields and lets in two

edged and taken! Uganda are falling apart! Full outside off, tempting the poke away from the body. Ramjani falls into the temptation and does so with hard hands, meaning that the outside edge carries comfortably to Naib at slip. He gobbles it up and then does his trademark muscle-flexing celebration. Metaphorically too, Afghanistan are flexing their muscles, and they are overpowering Uganda!
high and handsome! Flighted up just a touch on off and that is enough for Gurbaz to put on his dancing shoes. Gets close enough to the pitch of the ball and launches it over long off!
how has that missed?! Length ball on middle and leg. The ball slants back in with the angle and Obuya, who has a wild swing at it, is beaten all ends up. Somehow misses leg stump too!
shorter outside off. Gurbaz stays back and jabs it towards cover
slower ball on a length outside off. Obuya picks it just in time and jams it off the inside edge into his pads
length delivery on the pads. Riazat uses the angle and flicks it away towards deep backward square leg
finds the gap again! Low full toss outside off. Ibrahim gives himself ample room and threads it between cover point and backward point!
hard length on middle and off. Riazat gets up on his toes and defends
four more! Slower ball that lands right in the slot on off stump. Ibrahim plants his front foot and drills it to mid off's right!

length in the channel just outside off. Nips away off the seam and Riazat, trying to drive on the up, seems to be beaten. But hang on. Omarzai is very interested in the caught-behind, as is Ibrahim, and they have talked Rashid into a review. Flat line on UltraEdge when the ball is next to the bat, and Afghanistan have burnt a review!
three fours in a row! Another cutter but there is just enough width on offer. Gurbaz stays back to this shortish ball and opens his bat face to pick the gap between backward point and short third!
shortish outside off. Riazat gets on top of the bounce and punches it neatly towards backward point
make that four in succession! Fuller but the width is again the problem for Nakrani. Ibrahim presses forward and with that slightly open bat face, cracks it through point!
hard length on middle and off. Riazat tugs it to mid on's right and saunters across to the other end
hard length, angling into middle and off. Ibrahim stabs it towards mid on and gets across to the other end
back of a length outside off. Obuya thinks about playing at it initially before letting it go
cutter on a fullish length on off. Gurbaz comes forward and eases it to long on
angled in on a back of a length on middle and off. Keeps a little low and Gurbaz plays it back to the bowler
back of a length delivery angled into off stump. Riazat walks across his stumps and helps it towards deep square leg
back of a length on off. Gurbaz knocks it down the ground to long on
fullish, slanting into off. Obuya presses forward and defends
slowed up on a length on leg stump. Holds a little and straightens. Ibrahim nudges it into the mid wicket region for a single
off-pace on a length on off. Obuya waits for it and prods it towards backward point
floated up fuller outside off. Gurbaz wants to tip and run to point but his partner is not as interested
full just outside off. Obuya plants his front foot and hacks it down the ground towards mid on
great use of the feet! Tossed up a smidgen, and Gurbaz comes out of his bunker. Clean swing through the line and he sends the ball soaring over the bowler's head!
full and wide outside off. Riazat goes searching for it and is beaten on the inside
slower, shorter and wider outside off. Gurbaz hangs back and flat-bats it towards long off
length outside off again. The ball holds its line and beats Riazat on the outside this time

speared down leg. Obuya cannot make it count but does get the wide call dug in short on middle and leg. Zips off the surface and hurries Obuya into the pull. He misses it and cops a blow in the abdomen region
angled in on a length on middle and leg. Gurbaz lets the ball arrive before turning it towards mid wicket
hard length outside off. Obuya manages to get on top of it enough on this occasion and slaps it over mid off for a couple of runs
length outside off. Seems to stick in the surface a little and Gurbaz hits it with just enough pace to collect a brace to long off
back of a length on off. Obuya hops up onto his toes and defends towards backward point
short on off. Gurbaz advances and helps it behind square on the leg side for a single
low full toss on middle and leg. Obuya drives it back at the bowler, who wears a blow on the foot as he tries to stop it
length ball on the pads. Ibrahim is a tad early into his stroke and flicks it towards deep square leg. That seemed to hold in the surface too
ouch! Sharp bumper on middle and leg. Obuya gets into an awkward tangle and has to take evasive action. Flicks the glove and rolls away into the on side
into the blockhole wide outside off. Gurbaz tries to jam it out but is late on the stroke
full outside off. Riazat comes forward and drives it straight to mid off
off-pace on a full length outside off. Gurbaz bunts it to the edge of the ring in the mid on region and wants two. Ibrahim, though, sends him back
that has almost hit the roof! Floated up on middle and off and Gurbaz climbs into it. Gives himself swinging room and boshes it a mile over the bowler's head!
length just outside off. Obuya plays it off the pitch and guides it towards backward point

short and wide outside off. Left alone by Gurbaz and called a wide oh! Fizzed through on a length outside off. Drifts into Gurbaz before straightening off the surface. He goes feeling for it and is beaten on the outside. Seems to over-balance a touch and the keeper takes off the bails. Was there enough in it for a stumping, though? Does not look like it. Back foot well behind the crease, and Gurbaz survives!
floated up fuller on off. Obuya has a wild slog at it and squirts it off the inside edge towards short fine leg
shortish on middle and leg. Gurbaz goes back and works it towards deep mid wicket to bring up a 28-ball T20 World Cup fifty - his eighth in T20I cricket!
very full outside off. Riazat digs it out towards long off
angled in on a length on off. Comes in with the arm and Ibrahim, caught on the crease, scuffs it back to the bowler
back of a length on off. Obuya stays back and plays it towards the bowler
back of a length on the stumps. Ibrahim knocks it down the ground to long on
slowed up on a length outside off. Obuya winds up and hacks it down to long off
length just outside off. Gurbaz opts to stay back and punches it to long off
googly on a length on off. Riazat reads it well enough and blocks
shortish outside off. Gurbaz gets on top of the bounce and cuts it towards deep point for a couple of runs
short outside off. Obuya slaps it straight to extra cover, who misfields and allows a single
dismissed from his presence! This is a low full toss just outside off. Gurbaz backs away to give himself even more room and crashes it over extra cover!
slower on a length just outside off. Riazat stretches forward and turns it towards mid wicket
back of a length on the stumps. Gurbaz bunts it enough to long on's right and scampers back for two
shortish outside off. Grips in the surface and spins back in. Riazat punches it to long off
change-up on a shortish length outside off. Swerves back in and Gurbaz scuffs it towards extra cover
clean as a whistle! Given a bit of air and this is in the slot outside off. Obuya holds his shape, swings through the line and pumps it over long off!
full outside off. Driven out to deep cover point for another single
quicker, flatter and shorter on off. Spins back into Obuya and he the ball strikes him on the body
hard length just outside off. Gurbaz turns it into the vacant mid wicket region and puts on his skates to race back for the second
slowed up now, asking Obuya to fetch it from a length outside off. He has a go but only connects with fresh air
full outside off. Pitches and straightens, going past the outside edge of the bat
Ibrahim welcomes Riazat with a boundary! Strays onto the pads and pays the price. Ibrahim uses the pace and helps it over short fine leg!
full on middle and leg. Riazat comes forward and stabs it towards short mid wicket
back of a length outside off. Ibrahim gets up on his toes and jabs it towards extra cover
googly on a full length on the pads. Riazat plays all over it and the ball pops up off the pads into the on side
has Ibrahim been run out?! Full and slanting into leg stump. Ibrahim tucks it off his pads towards deep square leg and is intent on two. Scurries back and makes it
wrong'un on a length on off. Obuya gets onto the front foot and defends
into the blockhole outside off. Ibrahim scuffs it past the stumps and he races back for two as the ball trickles just past the circle
back of a length just outside off. Obuya goes back and taps it past extra cover
full outside off. Ibrahim comes forward and jabs it into the off side
another googly but this is short on middle and leg, allowing Riazat to read it easily. Punches it to long on
angled in on a length on middle and off. Gurbaz advances and bunts it into the square leg region. The sweeper cannot get to it quick enough and Gurbaz gets a brace
short on leg stump. Ibrahim opens up his stance and heaves it towards deep mid wicket
floated up nicely on a full length outside off. Nips away and breezes past the outside edge
fired into the pads. Gurbaz works it towards deep mid wicket
fullish outside off. Defended towards extra cover
floated up fuller outside off. Ibrahim tries to hit it too hard and miscues his drive towards extra cover

five wides! Darted down leg and that is not great bowling. Gurbaz cannot get to it either, and these are bonus runs for Uganda! was there a nick?! Full outside off. Riazat goes feeling for it and seems to nick it. Gurbaz, though, cannot hold on. Replays confirm there was bat involved
short and wide outside off. Ibrahim holds his stroke and punches it past backward point. Good work on the deep point fence by the fielder to save one. Ibrahim brings up his fifty too!
full on the stumps. Riazat drives it back to the bowler
full on middle and off. Gurbaz comes forward and eases it to long on
full outside off. Riazat gets forward and punches it past extra cover for a single
slower on a length outside off. Ibrahim stretches forward and pushes it towards deep cover point
fired in on a length on middle and leg. Obuya stays back and pats it towards the bowler
darted in on a full length on middle and leg. Ibrahim is caught on the crease and pokes it back to the bowler

castled! Cutter on a back of a length. Pitches just outside leg and continues on with the angle. Riazat does not quite pick it and has an airy swing at it. Makes no contact whatsoever and hears the death rattle soon after as the ball clips the top of middle. Farooqi has three, and he is thoroughly enjoying himself tonight!
full on middle and off. Ibrahim advances and stabs it towards extra cover, who is on the edge of the circle. Easy single on offer

edged and taken! Two in two for Farooqi for the second time this evening! Length ball hung up way outside off. Masaba goes chasing after it but does so without any real footwork. Nicks it through to Gurbaz, who makes no mistake this time. Afghanistan inch closer to a massive win!
slowed up a little and bowled full outside off. Gurbaz has a mighty swing at it and slices it. Loops over point and he gets two for his troubles
dug into the track on middle and off. Bilal hoicks it away towards deep square leg to stave off the hat-trick threat and get off the mark
full on the stumps. Gurbaz advances and drills it back past the bowler. Ramjani might have gotten a hand to it but tough to classify it as a chance
bumper on off. Obuya picks the length early enough and ducks under it. That did not bounce as high as he might have expected
shortish just outside off. Ibrahim rocks back and punches it enough to long off's left to pick up another brace
off-cutter on a back of a length just outside off. Grips in the surface and deviates away. beating Obuya on the outside
angled in on a length on middle and leg. Ibrahim wafts at it and squirts it off the inside edge into the square leg region

another nick, and another wicket for Farooqi! Shortish outside off. Skids off the surface and Obuya, who dangles his bat, gets a healthy edge. Gurbaz claimed the catch, having dived forward but the umpires just want to be sure if this has carried. No doubt about the edge. And no doubt on the fairness of the catch either. Gloves well under the ball, and Farooqi has his first five-wicket haul in T20I cricket!

oh dear! Sprays this a mile down leg and the keeper cannot get close to it either. Five extras added to Afghanistan's total! dropped! And a No ball has been called too, and Gurbaz is down on the deck - it is all happening here! Back of a length outside off. Ibrahim gives himself room and lofts it towards long off. The fielder runs to his left, gets both hands to it but spills it. The ball then seems to roll away into the cushion. The fielder, thinking the ball is still in play, got it back to the bowler's end, where Gurbaz was scrambling to complete the run. Ended up with a blow on the right knee for his toil! into the blockhole on off. Ibrahim can only squeeze it out towards short third
length just outside off. Bilal walks across his stumps and has a swipe across the line. Misses it completely and the ball deflects off the back leg behind point
hard length on off. Gurbaz takes a step down the track and hacks it towards long on
floated up full on off. Kyewuta comes forward and stabs it past short mid wicket
first six for Ibrahim Zadran! Slower delivery on a length just outside off. Ibrahim picks the variation early, plants his front foot and thumps it over wide long on!
length on off. Bilal comes forward tentatively and blocks
very full on off. Ibrahim shuffles across his stumps and chalks his attempted scoop towards short fine leg
oh, hello! Length on middle and leg. Bilal shuffles across his stumps early and smashes it behind square on the leg side!
ouch! Full on off. Gurbaz winds up and smashes it back at the bowler, who gets in the way. Pops up off his right shoulder blade and rolls away into the on side

full just outside off. Bilal continues swinging like a rusty gate and gets pinned on the back leg again. Impact seemed to be outside the line but Afghanistan have reviewed it nevertheless. The initial assessment was indeed right. Impact just outside the line and Bilal survives!
four to end the over! Short down leg and that is a proper buffet ball. Gurbaz can swivel on it and batter it behind square!

this is fuller, just outside off. Bilal fails to make contact with another wild slog. The ball clips the back leg and Afghanistan appeal. Impact again seemed an issue and the umpire was right to turn down the appeal
back of a length just outside off. Ibrahim stands tall and punches it crisply past extra cover for a brace
length outside off. Kyewuta comes half forward and pushes it towards deep cover point
back of a length, following the batter just outside leg. Does not spin and comes in with the arm. Ibrahim shanks it back to the bowler
wide yorker nailed to perfection. Bilal cannot get his bat down in time

cleans him up! The Uganda skipper gets their first wicket at the T20 World Cup! Flighted up deliciously on a length on leg stump. Ibrahim looks at the flight and hares down, only to realise he has been deceived in the air. Gets nowhere close to it and the ball sneaks back in with the angle, clipping the pad before thudding into leg stump. A superb knock, though, and that has set Afghanistan on their way to a big score!
full just outside off. Bilal walks across his stumps and tries to hit it into next week. Only connects with fresh air
full toss outside off. Najib drills it down the ground to long off to get off the mark
yorker on off stump. Bilal sits deep in his crease and squeezes it out towards the bowler
back of a length on middle and leg. Nips back off the surface and beats Gurbaz all ends up. Gets pinged on the pads but that was heading well down
off-pace on a back of a length on leg stump. Bilal walks down the track and whooshes across the line. Misses it by a mile and the ball somehow misses leg stump too!
another similar length ball, sliding into the pads. Gurbaz plays all over it and the ball trickles towards backward point for a leg bye
full and wide outside off. Bilal reaches out for it and clinks it towards deep cover point

two wickets in quick succession for Uganda! Tossed up on a length outside off. Gurbaz walks across his stumps, looking for the sweep. Gets a decent chunk of it but not enough to clear deep square leg. Easy catch for the sweeper, and both Afghanistan openers are now back in the shed!

big appeal, and given this time! Bilal has reviewed it immediately, though! Fizzed through on a length on middle and off. This is the leg-spinner and it turns away just enough to beat the bat and smack Bilal on the back leg. The swiftness of the review, however, suggests there might have been bat involved. That is indeed the case. A big outside edge, and Bilal stays!
length just outside off. Nabi comes forward and pokes it towards extra cover
full on middle and off. Bilal skips down the track and heaves it towards deep mid wicket
fuller and flatter on the stumps. Nabi knocks it down the ground to get off the mark
googly on a length on middle and off. Spins back into Bilal and raps him on the front pad, with the batter having advanced. Was perhaps going down leg
full just outside off. Najib backs away and cloths it down the ground to long off
length outside off. Bilal moves across and has another of those wild slogs. Gets pinged on the back leg
length on middle and off. Nabi gives himself room and goes through the line, chipping it over extra cover for a couple of runs

that looks plumb! Googly on a length on off. Bilal, having not had enormous success with the conventional, now tries the reverse, rather ambitiously. Makes a complete hash of it and gets thumped on the front pad in front of off stump. Kumar Dharmasena gives it out but we go upstairs for a final ratification. No bat involved, and Ball Tracking has the ball smashing into middle stump, two-thirds of the way up!
length on middle and off. Nabi drops it into the off side and canters across to the other end

Rashid inflicts the final blow! Beautifully-disguised googly, bowled on a length just outside off. Ssenyondo has no clue about this and goes searching for it, leaving a huge gap between bat and pad. The ball bursts through and smashes into off stump. All smiles for Afghanistan, and they secure a 125-run win to get their campaign underway!
full and hung wide outside off. Nabi reaches out for it and drills it to long off

Najib bites the dust too! A little like those London buses. Uganda waited an eternity for their first wicket, and they now have three!. Seems a bit of a drag-down but the key thing is that there is no real room to work with for Najib. He swings at it anyway but because he cannot free his arms, he picks out Nakrani at deep square leg. Replays confirm it was an off-spinner angled into Najib!
back of a length just outside off. Punched down the ground to long off
length on middle and off. Nabi tries to poke it past the bowler but Masaba tears off to his left and puts in the dive to save the single
off-spinner darted in full on leg stump. Nabi tucks it off his pads towards deep mid wicket

pushed into the batter on the stumps. Naib uses the angle and uses the vast spaces on the leg side to pick up a brace. Afghanistan's running between the wickets has been excellent throughout this innings
in the slot outside off. Nabi sits deep in his crease and powers it to long off
length ball hung up wide outside off. Naib has a wild swing at it and misses. Was just inside the tramlines and hence was not called a wide
borderline waist-high full toss on off. Naib swings it away towards deep mid wicket. Looks at the umpire for the No ball but gets no favours. That looked touch-and-go
top yorker just outside off. Nabi cannot jam his bat down in time but it is too hot to handle for the keeper too. A fumble allows a bye

holes out to long on! Cross-seam, full and wide outside off again. Naib, rather than going inside out, tries to drag it leg side. Ends up slicing it in the process and only gets height. Masaba settles under it and completes the catch with minimal fuss, well inside the ropes!
length outside off. Omarzai reaches out for it and drives it on the up past extra cover. Off the mark with a brace
low full toss speared into the pads. Nabi tugs it towards deep mid wicket and has enough time to come back for two
slowed up on a length just outside leg. Nabi aims for the moon and only swats away a few flies in the process
full and hung up wide outside off. Nabi powers it on the bounce to long off

almost! Length ball on the stumps. Omarzai pokes it to the bowler's left. Nabi thinks the single is on but his partner sends him back. Masaba, after gathering, decides to run closer to the stumps before throwing it under-arm. Misses the stumps by a whisker and Nabi survives!
length on leg stump. Nabi advances and hoicks it towards deep mid wicket
fired in very full on leg stump. Omarzai backs away and drills it down the ground to long on
length ball on the stumps. Omarzai swings like a rusty gate and shanks it towards deep mid wicket
off-pace and into the track outside off. Nabi almost swings himself off his feet and the miscue trickles away behind square, allowing him to come back for two

appeal, not given! Very full and wide outside off. Nabi gives it all he has and seems to miss it. There was a sound, though, and that got Uganda interested. Was it bat hitting the ground or was it an edge? We go upstairs to find out. Clear gap between bat and ball, and the sound was of the bat hitting the turf. Nabi stays!
full and wide outside off again. Nabi, sitting deep in his crease, can only smash it straight to extra cover. Just a single

goes straight up, and Kyewuta has two! Off-pace on a back of a length outside off. Omarzai tries to hit it into next week and loses all shape. Cuts across it too much and the ball skews off the outside half of the bat. Ramjani gets under it at extra cover and makes no mistake!
short and wide outside off. Rashid reaches out for it and cuts it towards deep cover point. A brace to end the innings
fires in a fast, late-swinging yorker! That's a searing start, does too much as it thuds Munsey's pads, and almost plucks him off his feet
fast and full again, Munsey flicks off the pads, but short backward square swoops to gather
full once more, met right under the eyeline on the full, stabbed back down the track for a scampered single to mid-on
hacked just over the head of mid-on! Enough width outside off, Munsey leathers a flat pull across the line, good connection in the end!
short-arm pull, out to the leg-side, midwicket gathers
up on the toes to meet the length outside off, punched to point
cracked off the back foot, a fumble from Livingstone at short cover allows a single to wriggle through
too much width once more, a chance to free the arms on a well-judged drive in front of short cover. Mopped up in the deep
Not a wonderful over so far from Archer, serving up width from back of a length on a fourth-stump line. Jones' high hands pierce the covers at the top of the bounce. Lovely
better line, and length, tighter to off stump and inducing a leave
rolls the fingers on a fuller-length delivery, more width but this one skids inside a loose drive, not quite to the pitch of that one
yoinked up in the air, over the head of the keeper! Buttler points hopefully at deep fine leg, but that plugged well short of Wood. Decent start for Scotland
onto the front foot, and punched into the covers
down on one knee, Moeen serving it up from round the wicket, and thumped behind square. Good strike
turn and bounce! A slip might have been in business there, kicks into the gloves and loops past Buttler
over the wicket, more gentle turn from off to middle, nudged off the back foot
down on one knee and thumped in front of square, gets low and nails his timing. This is a very proactive start from Scotland
lines up the slog-sweep again, but is a fraction early through the stroke. Toe-ended back down the track
rolls his fingers down the side of the ball, a definite cutter on this occasion, back of a length and grips the pitch. Dabbed to deep third with an open face
good length, angled across the left-hander and kicking into a back-foot block on off stump
full length, into the pads, clipped on the up to deep square leg
back of a length, keeps a touch low off the deck and zags past the inside-edge into Buttler's gloves. 145kph on that occasion
another legcutter, his second of the over, induces a flat-batted slap into the covers, without much timing

short, and sharp! That's what Archer can do, pace back on with a vengeance, as Jones flings into a pull, gets hurried and is lucky his gloved stroke doesn't fly through to the keeper. Much better from Archer and England

fires in the short ball, but that one fizzes straight over the batter's head much fuller length, thuds the pads, but Wood knows deep-down that that pitched outside leg. 151.6kph/94mph on that occasion
punched on the up, another misfield in the covers, this time from Moeen. Doesn't reach the rope

hacked high, high, high in the air! Buttler circles back at deep third, ushering the fielder out of his way as he grabs over his shoulder. But it's a no-ball! Took them a while to notice too... free hit ... round the wicket from Wood,  a big swipe to leg, with impunity this time, but this one doesn't get up at all, and beats his best intentions
round the wicket again, hangs back in the crease and punches the single to cover
full length, angled in at the right-hander, who makes room to leg and thumps a drive back past the tumbling bowler
Wood gets out of a frustrating over well, hitting the splice from a good length as Munsey pushes back down the line. Doesn't carry back to the bowler
tight line on a full length, attacking the pads, pushed to the on-side

smashed over the roof, and into the carpark! That is a magnificent wallop, clattering into the solar panels as Jordan tested the middle of the pitch and got dispatched for his sins! That is an expensive dent! Cricket's carbon footprint just got bigger
full length, outside off, blatted through the covers! This is a feisty assault! Jones is finishing the powerplay in style!
back of a length, crashed through midwicket! Jones is into position so early, waiting for the relative lack of pace, then butchering it!
not far from a fourth boundary in the over. Width outside off, slapped hard at point
better ball, slower ball, wide yorker, reaches on the full length and toe-ends to the off side. Scotland are fechting!
length ball, outside off, punched off the back foot to bring up the fifty partnership
grips on a good length from round the wicket, stretches forward to push to point
wide line, drawing the batter out to meet it, and it grips as well, just a nudge to the on-side
floated out wide on a full length, slapped with a big stride into the covers. Just the single
round the wicket, down on one knee, top-edged on the slogsweep! Over the keeper's head, but minimal damage
flogged flat, off the wide line, out to deep cover. That's an excellent resumption from Moeen. Giving England vital traction
kneels into the length-ball, donked over long-off! Super strike, anticipating the full length and launching it with a solid base
wider line, drawing a slap out to deep cover

over the wicket to the left-hander, pitches outside leg and grips, it's the googly, and is there a tickle as Munsey swings into a slog-sweep? England are reviewing The ball lobbed off the knee-roll, up through the arms, and into Buttler's gloves. But doesn't look like bat, or glove. Still, another dot. Pitched way outside leg for the academic lbw appeal
pre-empts the switch-hit, and it's a wide full-toss! Mashed through the covers, for another boundary!
magnificent clatter of switch slog! That is astoundingly good, like a left-handed KP! Hoisted high and mighty over what were the covers, and is now deep midwicket!
picks off the single out to square leg. That was not the over that England had anticipated from Rashid
a swing and a miss. Full from Jordan, skidding past the off-stump as Munsey loses his shape
pace off, on the pads, clonked over backward square! England are bleeding here! An early shuffle to the off-side to access his legs, and belted over the sweeper's head!
full, fired into the blockhole, across the left-hander, one hand comes off the bat as Munsey yanks a pull to the leg side
good length to the right-hander, Jones can only pump the ball back up the pitch with a straight-bladed drive
fired in onto the legs, hint of swing on the full length, a swish to leg, but the ball deflects into the off-side

yorker, met as a low full toss from outside off stump, and is that a run-out on the second run?! It was a solid connection down to long-on, but the shy was true as Jones coasted in. He dropped his bat, but got his foot down before the direct hit came in
tossed up outside the eyeline, a flog to long-off, striding into the length
another attempted reverse, but this time Rashid held that right back... slow through the air, back of a length, and keeps low. Buttler does very well to prevent byes
more regulation slog-sweep, but there's a man back for the stroke
slow through the air again, Jones lines up the big yahoo, but the ball never quite arrives... good bowling
so slow it barely stays in the air... 66kph... a miscued slap gets the single, as a shy comes in... could have been tight
finds the boundary off the final ball! This time Jones can line up the lack of pace, waits on the slog-pull, and launches through midwicket.
lbw appeal first up, but I think that's going over the top. This was a full ball, pitching on off, wobbling a bit and beating Levitt's shot. Karan was interested but gets no response from the umpire
Beats the bat first up. Goes fuller with the ball shaping away from Bhurtel well outside off. He chases it and can't lay a bat  on it
walks forward in his stance and turns a length ball into a fuller one. Drops it into the offside and they scamper the first run

Stifle appeal for lbw but he got an inside-edge onto the pad there. Was also struck outside the line of off stump. Fuller with a hint of shape away from the batter. He gets across and ticks it to the on-side. Nepal are away to huge roars from the crowd
swing for Karan. And a play and a miss. This was fullish, wide of off, curving away from O'Dowd who pokes his bat at it and misses
Fuller, veering away from Sheikh who leans into the drive but can't beat cover
edged but dropped short. This is another nice outswinger, starts just outside off and draws the shot, and takes the outside edge. Drops about a metre short of the only slip though
Lots of movement on the length ball but the line is well outside off stump. Sheikh throws his bat at it, but can't connect
goes fuller this time, towards the base of off stump, a bit of curve in the air. The batter just digs it out back to the bowler
Similar length ball seaming away well outside off. Aasif tries to hammer that away, can't connect
length ball on the stumps, not as much swing there, played to mid on and they take a quick single
First boundary of the contest and Sheikh is away! Too full from Kingma just outside off, right in the slot for Sheikh to prod forward and drive past the bowler's left. Top shot to get going
length ball wide of off, just a touch of shape away. O'Dowd pushes at it and gets a thick outside edge that skims away to deep third
And he is smoked first ball! Half-volley well outside off, tossed up right in the slot for Bhurtel to absolutely smash him through covers

that goes high. And caught in the covers to the HUUUUGE delight of this very pro-Nepal crowd in Texas. This was a length ball outside off, with just a bit of shape away again, and Levitt tries to crash this over the offside infield I think, but ends up giving only a big top edge that the cover fielder has tons of time to get safely under. Nepal are pumped.
A touch closer to off stump, Bhurtel brings out the sweep past short fine leg

lovely ball to start. Nepal are hunting here. This is a length ball pitching on middle and off and straightening to the leftie. He blocks it towards point and looks for a run but Nepals' infield is all over it.
Ooh, play and a miss! Floated well outside off, the ball grips and turns away from Bhurtel who looks to force one through the inner ring on the off side. Can't connect
length ball, just wide of off, angled across the batter. Vikramjit plays a drive on the up but gets no timing into it
Another play and a miss! Flighted outside off, he backs away, looking to clear the offside. Beaten again.
back of a length ball, angled into off stump. Vikramjit defends towards point
Tossed up outside off, he drives but can't beat extra cover
length ball outside off, Vikramjit tries to crash to leg this time but it's too full a ball for that, and he gets an under edge that skids away to the keeper.

And Pringle strikes. Reward for flighting the ball. Tossed up on middle stump, Sheikh backs away, once again looking to clear the inner ring on the off side. The bounce, however, does him in. Gets a thick outside edge, and short third takes a simple catch

length ball, angled into the stumps, straightening in the air and off the surface. O' Dowd is driving but it comes off the outside half of the bat and is in the air for a bit, and drops just straight of mid off. They scamper one
Length ball outside off, he shoulders arms
back of a length ball, pitching on about off and moving away, taking off off the pitch. Vikramjit plays at it without a lot of foot movement and doesn't get close
Play and a miss once more. Length ball with a hint of shape away from away from Bhurtel who looks for a hard drive, and gets beaten again.
length ball pitching on off. The batter opens the face and tries to square drive it on the up, but can't beat point
Jumps down the track now to the length ball outside off. But there is lot of movement around, as Bhurtel loses his shape and gets beaten
finally nails a drive, does Vikram. This is fuller from Karan, and Vikram gets low to drill it through the covers for four.
Good length ball just outside off, he gets a thickish outside edge towards point

why is there no slip? Would have gobbled this outside edge up. This was full, outside off, and the big drive comes out again from Vikram. He gets a thick edge that flies through conventional second slip and on to the boundary. The bowler is miffed
Ooh, close! On a length with some shape coming into the batter. Bhurtel gets a thick inside-edge onto the pads as the ball rolls to the on-side
length ball outside off, the batter shuffles across the stumps and tries to blast this over the legside, but clean misses
What a way to get going! A touch too full outside off, he leans forward and laces the drive on the up through cover.

And he's struck with his first ball! That looks plumb on first view. Will Bhurtel review, though? Nope, he's off. Length ball angling sharply back into Bhurtel, who was eyeing an across the line hack. Misses and is struck bang in front of off pole.
this is a beautiful lofted flick from O'Dowd. Fullish, on the stumps, gets across nicely and whipped over deep midwicket for four. Lovely.
Fuller in length on middle stump, Paudel gets across and works through midwicket for a couple of runs
length ball wide of off, not a lot of swing. Throws his bat at it and gets a thick outside edge to deep third
Another full-length ball around off stump, he plays the on-drive towards mid-on
length ball angled across the leftie, who plays a drive and misses
Fullish-length ball with a hint of shape away from Paudel. He does not move his feet much and looks for a drive on the move. Gets beaten

hacked that down the ground, and gets enough of it to get a four. This was length outside off again, but the batter shuffles across and bashes that over the  bowler's head. Didn't hit it perfectly, but you don't have to in the powerplay.

Huge, huge appeal for lbw. The umpire takes his time and give the decision in favour of the bowler. Paudel reviews immediately, though. Did he gets some bat on that? Oh, he did. Length ball moving into the batter sharply. Paudel gets across looking to works this away, and luckily he gets a thin inside-edge onto the pad that saves him
length ball on the stumps, played back to the bowler
Four leg-byes, Paudel won't mind. Length ball on middle and leg, the ball strikes his pads and goes past Edwards who dives over the ball.
This is a length ball, angled in but pitching well wide of off. Vikram plays another big drive and misses. Ball bounces through to the keeper
length ball, just wide of off, steers it through short third for a single
Big movement again for Kingma on the length ball outside off stump. Sah eyes the full-blooded drive, gets beaten
cut away for four. That wasn't that wide, but it was short enough for the shot, and Vikram stays in the crease and flays it in front of point. Netherlands are getting into a groove here
Ooh, gets a thick outside edge, but the ball falls short of short third. Fuller in length outside off, he shimmies down and gets it off the cue end of the bat just short of the fielder
length ball just wide of off, tried to club it down the ground, but doesn't hit it properly. Goes to mid off on a couple of bounces
Length outside off, big movement once more. The ball snakes past his outside edge
length ball on the stumps, clips this into the legside infield and they scamper one
On a length outside off, he drives to cover

backs away before the ball is bowled and tries to hit through off. But Karan bowls a short ball over the stumps that jags in a bit and the batter misses. He's overstepped though, so it's a no-ball and a free hit. decent free hit delivery. This was length just wide of off, jagging in off the seam again. O'Dowd tries to bash that over leg but gets only a leading edge to it that floats over the bowler and lands short of mid off
Cross-batted hack, he gets a thick outside edge over slip! He will take those. Was a length ball just outside off, he goes for an almighty slog, the ball catches his edge and pops over slip.
length ball on the pads, clipped to deep square leg for a comfortable single
Beaten on the inside-edge. On a length shaping sharply back into the batter who can't get a bat on it
full toss wide of off, which Vikram tried to flay through off but hits straight to backward point. Could have done more with that
Yorker to start off on offstump. Paudel digs it out back to the bowler
excellent stop from Airee at cover. This is a fullish ball outside off and Vikram has nailed the cover drive, but Airee goes hard to his right and makes a diving save to the delight of his teammates
Fuller-length ball on middle and leg and Paudel says thank you very much. Gets across and clips this through midwicket. The outfield is lightning quick
fullish, wide of off, Vikram tries to drive through off again but gets a thick inside edge into the legside infield and they sneak through a run
Good length ball that shapes back into Paudel who gets hit on the thigh pad with the ball going to the keeper. Loud appeal all around, but the umpire stays unmoved
fullish ball, just outside off, and O' Dowd gets across and clips this over deep midwicket, using a lot of bottom hand, to get another boundary in that area. He's keeping Netherlands ticking
Goes on a length outside off, Paudel throws his hands at it and gets beaten again
length ball outside off, driven straight to mid off
Short and wide, seaming away from Paudel. He looks for a cut, but misses
length ball on off stump, fended away towards point
Fuller outside off stump, Paudel looks for an on-the-up drive but misses
Bit of turn furst up. Pitching outside off and cutting in to the batter, who tried to flick to leg but unsuccessfully

He is still getting the ball to move around. On a length well outside off, he reaches for the ball and is lucky to not get an edge on that Length ball outside off, he punches this neatly over the in-field on the offside to deep backward point
gets the single this time, through midwicket. Fuller ball
PUMPED! Length ball outside off, he jumps down the track, frees his arms and hammers him over covers
flatter and faster through the air, Vikram tries to chop down on it but can't get it away
Fuller on the stumps, he pushes to long on for a run
flatter outside off, not much turn. Tries to chop it again but misses completly
Goes fuller again outside off, he presents the full face of the bat and drives to mid-off
