gets some bat to another dart, but hits it too close to the bowler, who runs into the legside and does the fielding
On a length just outside off, he opens the face of the blade and guides to deep third

floats this one up and turns it, and Vikram tries to drag it to leg, and gets a top edge that falls about a metre in front of the diving short third. Big shout of catch it, but that wasn't a serious chance

Banged in short, but the line was down leg and even though Paudel did not get a bat on this, the line was down leg. Called a wide Almost pops a leading edge back to the bowler. Was on a length on middle, he closes the face of the bat early in a bid to turn it to the on-side
length ball outside off, dragged towards long on for a single
Tossed up well outside off, he slashes to deep point
length ball on the pads, Vikram tries to flick it over short fine but doesnt' connect. It thuds into pad and they scamper a leg bye
Just falls short of a diving backward point. Was flighted outside off, he looks to carve it away, gets a thick outside edge that just falls short
could have been a run out. Big mix up for Netherlands as O'Dowd tears out of the crease, but the throw to the bowler from short fine isn't great and O'dowd gets home
Reaches the pitch of the ball this time outside off and drives to wide long off

big top edge and that's dropped by Sompal Kami who is running in from deep square and puts in a dive but can't hold on. It was a length ball on the legs that Vikram tried to crash over the legside. But he survives
Pringle gets his second! Floated well outside off, he eyes a sweep, but has to fetch it and that means he gets a top edge that goes to Van Beek at deep backward square leg.
length ball wide of off. Batter throws his bat and it and misses
Tossed up outside off, he bends forward and defends
back of a length ball, defended
Goes on a length on off and middle, he turns it to short fine leg
Length ball on off stump, he ticks it to the on-side with soft hands
flatter ball, wide of off, cut through to deep point and the fielder down there makes an excellent diving stop to save two runs
Short, wide but he can't cash in. Cuts it hard past a flying point but deep point is placed in perfect position

He's got him now! The drop didn't end up costing Nepal much. This is tossed up, tempting Vikram into a big slog sweep. Oitched on middle and off, and would have been hitting middle. The umpire didn't take long to raise the finger, and Vikram doesn't really think about reviewing. Looked pretty plumb.
Edged but past the lone slip. Length ball outside off, he prods at it and gets a thick outside edge down to deep third
floated up outside off, gets forward and pushes it to mid on for a single
Another edge that flies down to deep third again. Was fullish in length outside off, he drives without a lot of foot movement.
slower through the air, pitching outside off, turning in. O'Dowd gets across and clips through square leg
And now the bouncer at pace. Banged in short, Malla is caught by surprise and ducks under quite late. Edwards is a tad surprised as well
flatter one outside off, clipped to midwicket
Good length ball outside off, he gets a thick outside edge down to deep third
slower through the air, on the stumps. Batter goes back and flicks to deep midwicket
fullish ball, wide of off, driven just straight of short cover for a single
Oh, shot! In the slot outside off, he lofts it up and over mid-off for a four. That was played superbly.
length ball wide of off, flayed square through backward point, and the offside sweeper has a lot of ground to cover so they take two
Banged in short, he gets across and plays the swivel-pull down to deep fine leg
length ball on the pads, turned around the corner and they scamper one
Nicely done. Was a back of a length ball outside off, he pats this to the right of deep third
fullish ball, just wide of off, driven straight to cover

Gone straight up and O'Dowd makes no mistake. Malla perishes.  Rolls his fingers on the ball and deceives the batter. He looks to go up and over again, skies it straight up. O'Dowd gets across from mid-off and takes a simple catch
fullish ball, on off stump, pushed to long on
Length ball to start off, he gets across and defends
length ball wide of off, driven nicely to long off for another single
Bouncer, he gets across and slams the pull to deep backward square leg
length ball, angled in slightly from over the wicket, leaving the batter off the pitch. There's a prod from Airee, and it whizzes past his outside edge
floats up the first one on off. O'Dowd goes back and watches this one on to his bat

uff! Almost a run out chance at the non-striker's. This was fuller and on the stumps from De Leede, and played to mid on, who sees that Paudel wants a run and has scampered out. He has a shy at the stumps as Paudel tries to get back and if he'd hit, there's a chance he would have caught him short

tossed up outside off, and O'Dowd gets a boundary thanks to a misfield by short third. Batter had gone back and cut it late, but it should have been stopped with a better dive. Slips through the fingers and on to the rope
back of a length ball outside off, beats the outside edge again
flatter one outside off. Again O'Dowd goes back and drags this to long on this time

another one! De Leede has been threatening to do this all over. This is back of a length pitching on about off, and Airee is squared up. It takes the outside edge and flies to van Beek at wide slip, at about throat height. Netherlands keep rocking these conditions, and Nepal have lost one of their big hitters.
tossed up just outside off, driven to long on for one
this is fuller, and wide of off, seaming away from the new batter, who flashes at it and collects only fresh air
tossed up again, just on off stump, again they get a single to long on
another play and a miss - the fourth in the over - as Kami pushes at another full outswinger outside off and does not connect.

early call and fast running to get two for that shot. This was straighter, but tossed up, and flicked to deep midwicket who had to run to his left to get to it. A better throw might have had O'Dowd in trouble, but he gets in with a dive and the stumps are never broken
fuller ball, slower one, floated up on off stump. O'Dowd waits for it and drives it to long on
floated up outside off, chopped somewhat aerially and without a lot of timing towards short third, who makes a diving stop
that's a poor ball and that's sent scorching through the covers for four. Full, wide, and gives Engelbrecht the chance to open up his shoulders. He nails the drive
big sweep. This is tossed up on the stumps and Paudel gets this to fine leg and they scamper two
full and even wider this time, and the batter has to reach for it. Square drives it to the deep point on this occasion
pushed through a little more, attacking the stumps. Paudel is back playing this towards cover
slower one again, full and wide of off. Sliced square on the offside, and backward point makes a diving stop but can't prevent the single
quicker again, pitching on the stumps, and Paudel plays a drive, and it comes off the inside half of the back and dribbles back to the bowler
length ball just wide of off, driven straight to cover
shorter one, spun hard, pitching outside off and straightening. Paudel gets low and sweeps, gets it to deep square leg for a single
length ball wide of off, cut away to the offside sweeper
floated up outside off, pushed towards cover and Kami looks for a run (he's yet to get off the mark). None there though

Van Beek strays and concedes a boundary. This is a short of a length ball down leg and Paudel manages to catch up with that and flicks it just past the keeper and on to the fine leg boundary. Much needed runs
flatter on off stump, pushed straight to cover
jags in and beats the shot. This was a length ball that pitched well wide of off and seamed in. Paudel plays a leaden-footed punch and it whizzes between bat and pad
pushed through on the stumps, forward defence keeps that out
back of a length ball outside off, seams away and bounces as well. Paudel doesn't get close to it
tossed up wide of off, turning away. Batter throws the bat at it and misses completely as it bounces over the shot
down the track, turning a length ball into a fullish ball, and he slices that over backward point for four. Made a lovely connection there. Second boundary in the over
tossed up on the stumps, worked straight of midwicket for a single
Van Beek replies with a bouncer, and Paudel controls that hook shot nicely and gets a single to deep square leg
tossed up outside off, driven to cover
length on the stumps. Kami makes room and pushes square on the off side but still can't get that run to get him off the mark
flat one, and short, O'Dowd goes back and drags it straight of deep midwicket for a single
full delivery straying into the pads, flicked to deep midwicket who has a bit of work to do to get to that one

run out at the non-striker's end! Not the Mankad kind - the type when the batter hits straight, the bowler gets a tickled on the ball and the non-striker fails to make his ground before the ball hits the stumps. Engelbrecht seems to think he's out! And yes, Kami has got a finger to that straight drive from O'Dowd, and redirected it slightly (it might have missed the stumps otherwise). The non-striker is out too far and puts in a dive, but is caught about 10 centimetres short.

bowled him! Kami's pained stay is at least mercifully brief. This was a length ball that pitched outside off for van Meekeren. It jagged in (it was a wobble-seam ball), and Kami had his inside edge beaten, and had a huge gap between bat and pad, which the ball zipped through to take off stump.
length ball outside off, dropped towards cover and they sprint one.
fuller ball, angled across the leftie. Pitches and takes off off the surface and beats Gulshan's push. A play and a miss for hi to start
yorker, honing in towards middle stump, just dug out by Edwards
another full one, almost a yorker, hits Gulsan on the pad as he tries to flick. But it pitched outside leg

he's given out lbw! Sompal Kami is ecstatic. But Edwards reviews. It sounded like two noises. Yep, there's a BIG inside edge into pad, so Edwards will bat on. This was a length ball on off stump, and headed to the stumps but for the big edge
back of  length ball on the hips, Gulsan gets some back to that one and deflects it just wide of the keeper and scampers down the other end
comes down the track a bit and hacks it straight of mid off. They sprint through
length ball, just wide of off, Paudel pushes at it and gets a thick outside edge that skips away to deep third
length ball a little wide of off. O'Dowd tries to spank it through off but it comes off the under half of the bat and goes straight to cover

down the track and nails it! Advancing has worked for Paudel the last couple of times. This was a length ball that he turned into a very full delivery, and having backed away he throws his bat and drills it beautifully through cover point for four. That traveled quickly to the rope
fullish, wide of off, square driven behind square on the off side for a couple
length ball, seaming away off the deck, Paudel pushes at it and is beaten
slower through the air, but a bit shorter, cut away again to deep point but the fielder keeps it to one this time
back of a length ball into the body, pulled to deep square leg
slower again, pitching outside off, cut shot once more and they get another single
back of a elngth ball, slower one I think from de Leede, which Gulshan tries to run past short third, but finds the fielder
brings out the sweep, but Dhakal has darted this under the shot and Edwards misses

bouncer, over the inside shoulder, but that's a bit too far dow leg says the umpire length ball into the pads. Gulshan tires to crash that way over the legside but it bounces away towards backward point off the pad. Gulshan tries to run without knowing where the ball is and Engelbrecht only has to hit with his throw to see the back of Gulshan, but misses. He was well out of his crease.
reverse paddle sweep to a tossed up delivery. That should have been a dot ball, but an over throw from the short third fielder lets them take the single
fuller, on the stumps, flicked through to deep midwicket for one
floated up outside off, driven hard to long on
length ball on off stump, worked to long on for one
fires this in on the stumps, driven to long on for one

bowled! Do Nepal have a hope here? Their death overs bowler Bohara has got the opposition captain. This was a length ball just wide of off, that Edwards stays in the crease to and tries to chop in front of square. The ball has skidded a bit though, and takes an under-edge that cannons into middle and off
tossed up a little bit outside off, Paudel gets low and bludgeons this down the ground. Goes to long on off a couple of bounces
length ball just outside off, opens the face and gets it to deep point for a single

first big hit from Gulshan. This is tossed up outside off, and Gulshan gets the big slog  out, getting on his front knee and clobbering it high over long on for six. Got all of that and the heavily Nepal crowd is loving it.
length tight on the stumps, driven square this time and again deep point has work to do but keeps it to one
single through the covers
short ball, on leg stump, with the keeper up to the stumps. De Leede tries to help it around the corner, but only edges it and they take one as it goes off towards short fine leg
goes for his own big hit, but this is nicely flighted and this dips and spins over the shot
length ball on the stumps. driven to long on

Paudel goes, playing a chip when perhaps he should have committed to a big shot. This was fired in outside off, and Paudel tries to go inside out but plays a checked lofted shot, which long off runs forward to and gets underneath. That's a soft dismissal
drops this length ball on to the pitch and they hurry through for one
fired through wide of off, O'Dowd makes room and chops it through point for another single
length ball at the top of off, Just defends this back to the bowler
flattish, fired through outside off. De Leede tries to flay this square but it's straight to backward point

that's a poor ball and that's been punished. NIce one to get second ball. This is a legside short ball and Karan shovels this over his shoulder and gets a good enough connection to send it high over the fine leg boundary
length ball on the stumps, driven to cover
decent response from Van Beek - a short of a length ball wide of off, that Karan tries to run off the face of the bat and misses
tossed up a little, wide of off again, goes back and squeezes this to deep point
slower ball I think, full outside off, Karan squeezes the bat down on it but can't beat backward point
floated up on the stumps, driven just to the left of the bowler who dives and gets a hand to it, preventing the run
length ball outside off that the batter again tries to hit through to deep third, but again finds backward point
fired through on the stumps, driven to deep cover for a single
length ball on off stump, just bunted into the legside infield and they scamper through
attempted yorker first up but it's a low full toss in the end. De Leede drives, doesn't hit cleanly but gets it past the bowler and gets a single
back of a length ball just outside off, fenced away to deep third and he gets one this time

dropped! Is that the match? That's captain Paudel down there and he should have taken it. O'Dowd went for the big shot against this fullish ball and Paudel only had to go a couple of metres to his left at long off and hold on and he grasses it. Such a big moment

length ball just wide of off. Gulshan cuts this just to the right of backward point and they call a quick run. The fielder there collects and throws the stumps down, but Karan is home by a few centimetres. Was close though.
length ball on off, driven to long off
length ball wide of off, Karan tries to chop down on it but misses
length on off, dragged through midwicket

slower one on the stumps, length ball. Karan tries to turn it to leg but gets an inside edge on to pad and the ball drops by his feet. Gulshan is charging down for a single though, and although the bowler runs through in his follow through and attempts a run out, he can't get collect the ball
length wide of off, bashed down to Paudel. The ball's following him at long off

bouncer over the stumps but too short. He'll have to rebowl. length ball on off. Gulshan clears the front leg and tries to bang that over long on, but gets a big inside edge into his body and it goes nowhere.
almost a chance again. O' Dowd is going for it and hits this full ball down towards long off again. Paudel runs around but can't get to the ball, it bounces a couple of metres short.
there's the boundary they needed! O'Dowd delivers it. This was a length ball on the pads, and he gets across and flicks this fine of the deep square leg and makes a dent in that requirement
fullish, wide of off, Karan makes space and slices this over cover point. Does not hit it well so it drops in space and they sprint a couple

is that a a six? It is. A lovely scoop over the shoulder, and that also takes O'Dowd to fifty. This was a length ball on the stumps, he gets low and shovels it nicely right on to the boundary cushion to collect six.
length ball just wide of off, bashed down towards long on for a single
fullish outside off, driven square, to deep point
short ball over leg stump. Gulshan tries to hammer that over deep backward square but doesn't connect well and just gets a single to fine leg
fullish ball, wide off off, and that's the game! De Leede beats cover with a strong drive and it skips away to the boundary and Netherlands breathe a sigh of relief
length ball outside off, and Karan stands and delivers! Just stays in his crease, transfers weight back and clobbers this high over the bowler's head for six. Nepal's heaving crowd is ecstatic.

tries it again, but de Leede has gone a touch shorter this time, so Karan gets only a big top edge to it, and the fielder at deep third (Kingma) runs around to get under that one beautifully. Karan had to go for it, but he's been done in by a smart bit of bowling, and Netherlands' frequently excellent fielding.
cutter to the end the over. This is back of a length, pitching on off and darting in with the spin. Batter gets bat to ball, but had been expecting a quicker delivery so hasn't hit it anywhere

scrambled seam ball, fullish, honing in on the stumps, Gulsan tries to launch this into the stratosphere beyond deep midwicket, but misses the ball completely and has it clatter into the stumps. That's the last of Nepal's batters gone, and they've got five balls left. More smart bowling from Netherlands.

that's out as well and van Beek wraps it up smartly, to finish with three all up. This was a back of a length ball on about off stump, which Bohara goes back to and tries to crash over long on I think. It ends up hitting the top edge near the splice, and pops up for Van Beek himself to get under it and take the simplest of catches
full and swinging back into middle and leg, neatly clipped to deep backward square leg
back of a length and shaping away wide of off as Rohit has a swipe. Missed it by some distance, called wide shortish, 133kph outside off, dabbed down towards backward point
gives him the charge and punches this length ball on the up through cover point, Jadeja with the chase and he hurls the throw back to keep it to two.
length ball, 131kph aiming for the top of off. Rohit shows it a diligent straight bat
gets good shape back in as he bowls full on off-stump, defended confidently to cover
beats him on the inside, Rohit taking a couple of steps down but the ball keeps coming back at him. Tucker didn't grab it cleanly going to his left
beaten by one that holds its line. Stirling played for the late inward movement. Lovely from Arshdeep
pitched up and flicked off the pads, won't get more than a couple on this outfield. Deep square leg tracks it down
cramped for room as he charges down the pitch again in trying to access the off side, defended into the off side as Arshdeep did well to follow him
back of a length, 131kph and there's still a hint of nibble. Thick-edged to short fine leg
dug in short to beat an advancing Stirling for pace as he bails out of the tangle

edged through Balbirnie at second slip! Sharp chance as Rohit slashed at a wide one, just above head height for Balbirnie and he couldn't get his hands up in time. Not sure he even got a touch on it. Boy, Ireland could have done with that sticking
angled across and sliced through third for a single
full on the stumps, gets this to shape away as Balbirnie defends towards mid-off
length ball, 135kph and curling down leg as Rohit moves across pitched up and swinging, Rohit clips off his toes for a couple out to deep square leg
shortens his length a touch and gets it to nip away off the deck from a fourth-stump line, Balbirnie is beaten as he attempts to punch on the up
full and swinging back in, deflects off the pad down leg but Tucker does well to get across
pressure building as he gives him the charge and is beaten trying to wallop that over cover
pitched full on the stumps, dug out towards mid-off

excellent one-handed grab by Pant as he leapt high like a goalkeeper! Balbirie looked to pull, but this wasn't all that short. The ball leapt off a length to surprise the batter, somehow he managed to bail out in the nick of time.

short and jagging down leg as Rohit aims a big hoick across the line. Another wide full, wide of off, edged past the stumps for four! Perilously close to cannoning back into the stumps as he skids off to fine leg, Little throws his hands up in frustration. But Rohit will take the runs
off the glove and just past Pant down the leg side. Not where he intended, but Ireland will take the welcome boundary.
rifled down the ground, first six of the innings! That was hit clean as a whistle. Full on the pads, no inhibition from Rohit, pumping Little over long-on
gets right behind the line of this short of length delivery as he defends to point

the swirler is taken nicely by Pant running back! Stirling looks to heave this length ball on middle and leg over square leg, but gets a leading edge that goes quite high. Not easy taking that with the sun breaking out of the clouds, but Pant had it completely in control as he called early to keep Bumrah out of the way running around from short third.
back of a length, 125kph wide of off as Kohli comes down and slashes without making contact
beats him on the drive! Arshdeep dangles the carrot with the angle, this one holds its line.
pitched up, 127kph and punched to mid-off
steered down to third man as Tucker gets off the mark
little nibbler, beats him on the inside! Nothing on it, fortunately for Virat
squared up as he's beaten by one that nips away from a length on middle. Superb from Arshdeep

hacked straight to deep third! The approach was clear but even Virat Kohli can't tame this Nassau County deck. Premeditated charge-and-swipe, fat top edge and and comfortable catch for the man down there, White, a few yards in from the rope. Ireland have the early wicket they needed

beaten for pace as he runs down the wicket and attempts to pull the short ball. Way over the batter's head, and it's been called wide. nips back in off a length to cramp Balbirnie as he backs away to go off side, hits the pad off an inside edge
round the wicket, full outside off and dug out watchfully

more trouble for Ireland as Arshdeep cleans him up with one that nips away. Balbirnie tries to stay besides the line, hanging leg side, to try and defend but is beaten by the fizz away as the ball crashes into the stumps.
full and chipped back past the bowler! Ruins what could have been a wicket-maiden from Adair. Pant's had a sighter and decides he's happy to hit through the line, trundles away to long-on
shortish outside off, Rohit watches this through
beats him with a length ball outside off
length ball, Rohit opens the face and jabs one through third
shapes away from off as Siraj angles it in from wide of the crease, Tucker is beaten as he prods forward tentatively
full, 135kph, chopped into the point region
short of length as the ball skids back in to hit him on the thigh pad. Tucker is late on the ball
touch shorter, tapped down towards backward point
walks across to scoop this over Pant. Made clean connection there, one bounce to the boundary.
back of a length, slugged to mid-on... Rohit was struggling at the non-striker's end! Adair fielded and had a shy in one fluid movement, but missed the stumps
beaten as he tries to flay that on the up through point. Extra bounce off the deck for Siraj
back of a length, Pant almost keel-hauls himself trying to hit this off Long Island. Fails to connect
strikes him on the pad as he angles one back in from wide of the crease. Tucker was well outside leg trying to go off-side once again. Pressure firmly on Ireland here to force the pace.
strikes him on the glove as the ball takes off from good length once again, was no more than a tentative push
pitched up and driven, Rohit gets a thick outside edge down to deep third

don't want that. Pant has a wry smile, he had absolutely no chance with that one. Rohit isn't impressed either. Arshdeep looks for a big inswinger but ended up dragging it way down. much better, floats it fuller and just outside off, Tector lets it go at the very end
round the wicket, length ball angling in on the stumps, Pant tucks one through midiwcket

beaten by one that slants across, but it's bowled too far wide outside off. Pant dives full length to his right to take that as the ball scurries through the turf. rapped on the glove by extra bounce as Tector is looking to tuck this through square leg. Ouch, that will hurt.  Took it on the thumb.
fuller, played with a straight bat and soft hands, runs another one down through third
gets the radar wrong again as he slips one down leg once again, through to Pant squirted off the inside edge to long leg
tight line, 131kph on off stump. Pant dabs it towards backward point
looks to slant one across and ends up bowling way outside off, no swing that time beats him with the zip off the pitch as Tucker hangs his bat out at an angle
over the wicket, full outside off, 133kph. Pant left the safety off again, aiming to bludgeon over mid-on. In the end, the ball bobbles to the man along the carpet
short, wide and that has been  thumped through the covers.  It was in all fairness begging to be smacked.
round the wicket, pace off but sliding down the leg side short of a length outside off, Pant fails to connect with an expansive drive
and nearly through Tector!  Gets the ball to nip back in and sneak through the gap between bat and pad. Flew over the stumps.
pitched up in the channel, big ole swing and a miss from Rohit
driven straight to cover point, Axar the man
fullish again, tempting the drive. Left alone this time
chops the cut to point
pitched up and Rohit flashes, gets a thick edge into the leg side
full and just outside off, Tector is well forward as he defends. He's on 1 off 8
sliding in and whipped off the pads
and more pressure builds as Tector is beaten by one he had no clue about.  Plays for the nip-backer but the ball angles in and straightens
eased over backward point, Rohit shows some touch here. Full and inviting, he extends the arms and opens the face to pick up four
this one cuts back in to hit him high on the thigh pad.
back of a length, this one zips through past the bat. India reach the end of the powerplay comfortably placed, perhaps already thinking about their afternoon of sightseeing
scurries in and bowls full outside off, Pant clips him through midwicket
floated full on the stumps, pushed to cover
uff, that's kicked from a length! Rohit is flummoxed as he pushes forward and the ball squirts through past the shoulder of the bat

terrible, terrible mix-up with the running. Tucker said no as he tapped it to backward point, Tector was through with the run to leave Tucker with no choice but try and scamper. A direct hit at the bowler's end would've had him.
full, 130kph and nips past the bat again! Rohit was giving him the charge, the ball seaming away and missing leg stump on its way through
gets right on top of the bounce and defends it to Jadeja rushing in from backward point
comes down again, helped into the leg side for one
deflects to point again, but off the pad as he tries to tuck it square, they scamper a leg bye
tight lines, this stands up a touch, beats Pant hanging back

through the gate!  Hardik goes full on off, the ball nips back in and beats Tucker as he leans into the stroke to try and blast that through cover. The late movement did the trick for Hardik as the ball flattened the middle stump.
short outside off, 134kph and slashed away wide of deep third for a couple more
picked away into the gap at square leg! Hardik errs marginally by veering this into middle and leg, Campher timed it wonderfully.
shortish, nudged off the hip for one
hits hard lengths as this one skids back in, tapped into the leg side for a single
shortish length, clubbed through midwicket without any timing for one to the sweeper
can't pierce the gap at point as he punches on the up
tucked into the leg side
advances down the pitch and flays this through to Siraj at sweeper cover
length ball angling across, Pant looks to manufacture something spectacular and ends up getting two as the ball sails over the keeper and plugs in the outfield
beaten by the pace on the bumper! Also didn't help his cause by trying to fetch it from way outside off. Through to Pant.
muscled down the ground, gets four this time... not timed by any stretch but it clears McCarthy in his follow through and bounces away to long-on
gets a thick inside edge as he looks to whip it through midwicket, the ball instead rolls towards long leg
banged in outside off, swiped into the ground towards mid-off

comes off the glove, another one that rushes the batter and surprises him.  All told, it was a rip-roaring bouncer. Tector walks off shaking his head and wincing in pain. Looks to swivel back to play the pull but the extra bounce means this one pings him on the gloves and then lobs to the fielder off the deflection onto the helmet.
that's been clobbered over long-on! Hardik overpitches and this is right into his hitting arc. Clean strike down the ground.
this jumps to hit the splice of the bat with Rohit defending
flies off a thick edge down to third man

shortish, Rohit heaves at it, the ball deflects off the upper arm, I think, and is taken at backward point... nothing from the umpire, Chris Gaffaney but Ireland review, Paul Stirling having a punt. Clearly missed the bat, though
flicked down to deep square as Hardik errs in line

swung high and handsome over deep backward square leg! Fetched from outside off, gets plenty of height and just enough distance. Rohit loves this shot and brings the crowd to their feet with a punishing blow
gets right on top of the ball as he defends back
goes again, slammed over the fence! Swivels and hits this flatter and harder into the stands at fine leg
check punches to short cover where Kohli throws himself at the ball to try and stop that. Took it on the half-volley.
skips outside leg stump and thrashes across the line, doesn't connect
the thin edge has been taken. Campher flirts with a harmless length ball outside off, there's a hint of movement away, and that's enough for Hardik to strike again.
length ball, jabbed into the off side
round the wicket, slower ball but it veers down leg short ball, 127kph but well-directed. Pant sways underneath the last moment
short of length and angling in from wide of the crease, defended back
pitched up, pace off again and Pant's attempt to launch it out of the Eisenhower Park ends up plinky-plonking down to long-on
just ends up chipping it wide of Rohit's outstretched hands at mid-off.  Rohit threw himself at the ball, went one-handed. Tough chance, those ones stick.
full and Rohit throws the bat, gets enough on sliced drive to clear mid-off for two

is that a missed opportunity? Looks like. Dockrell slaps it to cover, Delany was halfway down the wicket when he was sent back. Siraj wasn't at the stumps, so  Kohli  Rohit fired the throw in and missed.
full and straight, 128kph and whipped off the toes out to the midwicket sweeper

the freefall continues.  Dockrell attempts to take Siraj's short ball on but is done in by the skid off the pitch, also didn't have the room to pull and ends up getting a top-edge as Bumrah takes a comfortable catch at mid-on.

full toss, munched through midwicket! That was a meatball with marinara sauce, in the approved style of my old colleague, the USA's finest, Peter Della Penna. Clonked for a boundary to bring up 50 for India's captain
heaved across the line into the leg side, Bumrah runs back to the boundary from mid-on and they get three
hacked over the leg side again, not a clean hit but it lands safely for a couple
gets right on top of the bounce and defends back

they're falling like nine pins. This is a nothing shot from Adair. Backs away to manufacture a stroke, Hardik does well to dig it in and away from the batter, Adair simply throws his bat at that and ends up hitting it straight to Dube coming in from deep point.
length ball, Pant swings across the line... takes a blow on the body. He's hurt now, too. Took a smack on the left elbow. Going to need some treatment from the physio
ooohhh! The skid off a length has McCarthy rushing into his stroke as he defends awkwardly.
fired down the leg side length ball, again Pant can't get this away
goes full on the stumps, defended to mid-off
short and smoked! Doesn't get up high enough to trouble Pant as he rocks into a flat pull over deep midwicket
skids through off a length, keeps a tad low to hit McCarthy on the back thigh as he tries to pull in front of squaee
shortish and skidding on, he takes another blow on the body before jogging up to the other end
beaten by a bumper again, Hardik dug it. Effort ball.
fired across the bows, Suryakumar aims to swing it behind square on the leg side. Doesn't connect
beaten as he chips down the track to heave across the line
back of a length, 131kph and dabbed down to deep third
tucked to deep square
pushed through and worked away behind square from middle and leg

outstanding catch by Axar! Harmless ball drifting into middle and leg, McCarthy gets a leading edge that appears to be drifting away from Axar's reach, but he does superbly well to run a couple of steps to his right before putting in the dive and taking it one-handed.
stretches out and swipes over cover, Pant isn't hanging around now. Steps down and hoicks clear of the ring for four
reverse-swept to deep point, so much risk for a single
clipped down the ground

beaten as he tries to hack this into the leg side from well outside off. The third umpire is checking for a stumping but no one's really excited about the call. Delany's foot is grounded. Not out it is.

slog-sweep, but it doesn't have the distance! Suryakumar looking to finish it in style but sends the ball high and spiralling towards deep midwicket, on the longer side of the ground - well held by Dockrell as it dropped like a stone
makes room and cuts to deep point
looped up and nudged to midwicket
dabs it straight to short third
flat outside off, Dube drops back and slams a cut to backward point
hits a length and this kicks like a mule as Pant tries to get his hands up. Takes another blow on the upper arm
heaved over the ropes at deep square! Premeditated and very effective. Delany backed away and fetched this pull from way outside off. Picked the bones of it.

reverse-scooped for six! Audacious from Pant, some trademark flamboyance to seal the win, he's truly back and India are on their way at this World Cup. Ireland were up against it after being blitzed by India's attack and could not drag the game back
swung away towards deep midwicket
slapped back past mid-on! Ball made a thumping sound as Josh Little swatted it away.
slapped to the right of mid-off this time. Rohit with the chase, manages to pull it back in.
beats him with the short ball as Hardik follows him. Little was backing away to pull, but ended up bailing out of the stroke
mistimes a heave, one bounce to mid-on as they scamper a single
drifts in a quicker one from around the wicket, pushed to point
fired in and Little brings out the reverse sweep, makes excellent connection as he beats point.
covers the line nicely as he defends
tucked wide of short fine for a single
makes room and clubs it to sweeper cover
gets across the stumps and paddles it neatly past short fine leg.
deflects off the pad and beats Pant behind the stumps for four leg byes. The ball also just bounced over the helmet kept behind. Lucky runs. Bumrah dug it in from wide of the crease to cramp Little

'you miss, I hit stuff.'  Bumrah's calling card. A ripper of a yorker angled into the middle of middle at 145kph. Little had exposed all three stumps even before Bumrah delivered the ball, thereby giving him little or no chance to squeeze that out if it was speared in at a furious pace.
off a thick edge down to third man
mistimes a heave down to long-on, refuses the single
high full toss, swung away towards long-on.
squeezes this full-length delivery to point
slapped over mid-off, clean connection. Arshdeep bowled short of length and he picked it away superbly.

dropped by Jadeja running back from point! Tough chance but Jadeja sets such high standards. This was ramped back. Jadeja's hat bobbled out and that may have distracted him as he attempted the swirler. Axar was in his eye line as well.
belted handsomely over the deep square leg ropes. It's the longest boundary at the ground but he's hit that way over the ropes.

and more runs! Arshdeep's bleeding runs. This one spins away over short third. Axar was a fraction late to move, and by the time he decided to try and stop that, the ball had already dribbled over his head.
rolls off the bottom edge into the off side

rip roaring bouncer that White somehow manages to evade. And it looks like that's the third bouncer of the over so it's a no-ball.  Freehit coming up scythed away into the gap at deep point. But that's  absolute hara-kiri from the batters.  Total breakdown in communication. White wanted to come back for the second to keep Delany on strike for the next over, but the throw from the deep was right on the bounce to Pant, who whipped the bails off. White took off for the second and just stopped. As it turns out, even if he'd hared instantly on the turn, chances of making it back were remote.

full and wide outside off, swinging away further. Mukasa goes fishing at it and misses. Called a wide, though length in the channel just outside off. A hint of shape away and Mukasa pushes it off the front foot towards extra cover
length delivery angled across the batter just outside off. Vala goes feeling for it and is beaten by the angle
length on middle and off. Straightens off the surface and squares up Mukasa, who plonks it into the off side

huge appeal, and given! Ramjani with the early breakthrough! Fizzed through on a length on middle and leg. Grips in the surface slightly and spins back in. Vala is caught on the crease and has a hurried prod at it, only to play all over the line. The umpire raises his finger but Vala, after a chat with his partner  has gone upstairs. Not sure if this is the right call. No bat involved. Pitches in line, impact in line and smashing into middle and leg. The PNG captain has to go, and he takes a review along with him too!

pinned on the pad, and that is two ducks in a row for Mukasa! Length in the channel and this decks back sharply. Mukasa does not really commit to the front foot and has a waft at it. Misses the ball by a mile and it strikes him right in front. The umpire has no hesitation in raising his finger, and Mukasa does not even bother with the review! Just the start PNG would have hoped for!
floated up full outside off. Bau comes forward and pushes it towards extra cover
full just outside off. Obuya goes searching for it away from his body and chunks it off the inside half of the bat towards mid wicket
oh! Back of a length outside off. Pitches and skids on, beating Bau for pace on his back-foot punch
length delivery pushed across the batter outside off. Ssesazi presses forward and watches it go through to the keeper
slower and wider outside off. Bau goes chasing after it and is beaten for the second ball in succession. That went on with the arm
full just outside off. Ssesazi comes forward and punches it to mid off. Hares across for the single and gets there comfortably, courtesy of a misfield
wicket-maiden to start off! Full just outside off. Bau gets onto the front foot and plays it back to the bowler

rapped on the pads again, and the finger goes up too! Length ball on middle and off, and this decks back sharply. Ura's feet go nowhere and he gets pinned on the pads in front of middle and leg. Kyewuta's appeal is upheld, but Ura wants to have another look. Was it doing too much? That and height could save him. No bat involved, like it was in Vala's case. Ball Tracking comes up and it reckons the ball would have gone over leg stump. Ura survives!

speared well down leg. The keeper cannot gather cleanly either, and Uganda get two extras. PNG cannot afford many more of these length delivery way outside off. Obuya swishes and misses but then sees the umpire indulge in some exercise clothed to mid on! Now then. Now then! Hard length on off, and this seems to rush onto Obuya. He tries to muscle it over mid on but the ball comes onto him much quicker than he anticipates. Spoons it up to Vala, and Uganda in some early strife!
back of a length on middle and off. Nips back again and cuts Ura in half. Pings into his pads and rolls away towards backward point. This was definitely higher. First run for PNG
length outside off. Shapes away late and Riazat is happy to let it go
up and over! Full and wide outside off. Bau cashes in on the width and throws his hands at it, flaying it over backward point for four!
back of a length just outside off. Riazat presses half forward and defends
back of a length on off. Bau gets up on his toes and drops it into the off side for a quick single
length outside off. A hint of swing away from Riazat and he is beaten on the outside as he goes feeling for it

flies away off the thigh pad! Hard length on middle and leg. More sharp movement back into Ura and he is all at sea. Too late on the stroke and the ball clips the thigh pad before racing away past the keeper!
length in the sixth stump channel. Leaves the batter again and Riazat, nibbling at it away from his body, is beaten for the second ball in succession
length outside off. Ura comes forward and tips and runs to cover to get off the mark
full and wide outside off, tempting the poke away from the body. Riazat gives in to the temptation but luckily for him, does not nick it through to the keeper

another massive appeal, and the finger goes up! Uganda are rocking now! Length ball that finishes on the stumps. Ssesazi, like Mukasa earlier, does not really come forward and plays from his crease. Plays all over it, though, and gets rapped on the flap of the front pad, in front of leg stump. Ssesazi has a chat with his partner and decides to review. Did that pitch outside leg? No, it did not. Pitching in line, impact in line and hitting the stumps. Three reds, and Uganda are three down!

back of a length on leg stump. Tucks up Ura for room and he cannot get his bat to it. Trickles off the thigh pad for a leg bye. But hang on...Miyagi has overstepped... shortish outside off. Bau has a massive mow across the line but only connects with fresh air. That might have kept a little low
back of a length just outside off. Ramjani tips it to mid off and scurries across to the other end. Makes it despite a direct hit
peach, but it goes through! Back of a length in the channel. Jags away sharply off the surface and beats both the batter and the keeper. Four extras added to PNG's total!
hard length just outside off, seaming back in off the surface. Riazat plays it back to the bowler

Bau bites the dust! Hard length on middle and off. Bau has had enough of the pushing and prodding and goes walkabouts. Tries to muscle it over mid off but the ball does not quite arrive. Chalks it off the toe-end and Mukasa, back-pedalling from mid off, completes a smart overhead catch!

wayward, beyond the tramlines on the off side. The out-swing makes it worse and the umpire has no qualms in calling it a wide length delivery hung outside off. Shapes away late and goes past Riazat's flailing blade
short and wide outside off. Siaka flashes hard at it but is just a touch late on the stroke. Makes no contact in the end
almost! Short and wide outside off. Riazat has a waft at it and nearly shanks it back onto his stumps. On another day, he'd have been walking back!
back of a length just outside off. Siaka hops up onto his toes and defends
slanted in on a length on off. Riazat comes half forward and stabs it towards mid wicket
hard length just outside off. Siaka gets on top of the bounce and runs it down to third man
length on off. Siaka comes half forward and defends
fullish on the pads. Ramjani comes forward and flicks it past short mid wicket to pick up a single
back of a length just outside off. Seams back in a mile and cuts Siaka in half. Brushes the back thigh and bobbles away past the keeper for a leg bye

full and wide outside off. Another fresh-air shot for Riazat but the umpire comes to his aid. Called a wide back of a length on off, coming back into Riazat. He uses the angle and works it into the mid wicket region

Ura falls too! PNG are capsizing! Another hard length delivery, on middle and off. Bounces a little more than Ura expects and that meddles with his timing. Looks to go over mid on but can only splice it tamely to Mukasa. Kyewuta is delighted, and Mukasa does a salute too in celebration. Uganda well in the ascendancy here!
gets it through! Enough width on offer and this is short too. Ramjani throws the kitchen sink at it and cracks it past backward point!
shortish outside off. Hiri waits for the ball, opens his bat face and glides it down to third man to get off the mark
back of a length outside off. Ramjani hangs back and jabs it towards cover point
back of a length outside off. Siaka pushes it into the off side and scampers across to the other end
length delivery pushed across the batter outside off. Ramjani goes fishing at it and is beaten on the outside
short, wide and punished! Too much width on offer and that is just what Hiri is after. Stands up on his toes and crashes it to cover point's right!
back of a length outside off. Ramjani tries to force it through the off side but makes no contact for the second ball running
zipped into the stumps. Riazat plays it down the ground
short outside off and this nips away from the batter. Siaka is late on the stroke and is beaten by the movement
full just outside off. Riazat gets forward and drives it down to mid off
back of a length, angling into off. Siaka gets onto the back foot and stabs it towards backward point
back of a length outside off. Riazat waits on it and dabs it to third man
hard length just outside off. This keeps low, decks back and breezes past Siaka's attempted pull. That was not far away from off stump either
back of a length on the pads. Ramjani gets inside the line and tucks it away towards deep backward square leg
shortish outside off. Siaka has another swipe across the line and only swats away a few flies in the process
full and wide outside off. Swings away late and that movement beats Riazat's attempted cover drive
fuller outside off. Siaka comes forward and jabs it towards backward point, who misfields and ends up conceding the second

oh dear! Goes for the in-swinger but this tails down leg. Riazat misses his flick and the keeper cannot get around to it in time. Five vital runs added to Uganda's total! back of a length outside off. Sticks in the surface a little and Riazat scuffs it back to the bowler
back of a length outside off. Siaka throws his hands at it and scuffs it towards extra cover. Retains strike for the start of the next over
shot! Drifts onto the pads and pays the price. Siaka picks the line early, gets down on one knee and belts it between square leg and short fine leg!
into the blockhole just outside off. Ramjani squeezes it out towards mid on and calls for the single. Riazat is a little late to react but completes the single, via a dive
back of a length on off. Siaka hangs back in his crease and works it into the mid wicket region

speared down leg, and this is exactly what PNG do not need at this stage. Another wide, and another extra added to Uganda's total full on middle and off. Riazat presses forward and plays it back to the bowler
slowed up on a length on middle and off. Hiri lunges forward and defends
back of a length on leg stump. Riazat tucks it off his hips into the square leg region
length on middle and off. Hiri gets a big stride in and presents the full face of the bat
full delivery that starts outside off and swings back into Ramjani. Pushed down the ground to mid off
fuller and slightly flatter on off. Hiri plays it back to the bowler

cleans him up with an absolute ripper! Length in the channel just outside off. Snakes back in with the angle from around the wicket and Ramjani is all at sea. Goes for the booming drive but leaves a massive gap between bat and pad. The ball bursts through gap, and flattens off stump. Uganda lose another in the powerplay!
angled in on a back of a length on leg stump. Hiri plays all around it and the ball thuds into his thigh pad
length just outside off, angling into Nakrani. He comes forward and pokes it towards the bowler
back of a length on middle and leg. Riazat lets the ball come to him before helping it round the corner
safe! Hard length just outside off. Gets extra bounce because of his height and Siaka cloths it, just past the bowler
slower on a length just outside off. Nakrani meets it right under his eyes with a dead bat
shortish on middle and off. Siaka waits in his crease and hacks it towards deep square leg

simple return catch, and Vala has a wicket in his first over! Tossed up full otside off, enticing the drive. Nakrani cannot resist the temptation and goes after it. He is not to the pitch of the ball, though, and cannot keep it down. Chips it back at Vala, and the PNG skipper does the rest!
that is sharp! 137.2kph, back of a length outside off. Zips off the surface and Hiri is a week late into his cut
arm-ball on a back of a length outside off. Nips away and Miyagi prods it into the off side to get off the mark
short just outside off. Hiri gets on top of this one nicely and jabs it towards deep cover point
slower and shorter on middle and off. Riazat nudges it behind square and calls his partner through, who makes it just in time. A direct hit and it might have been interesting

Has Siaka been run out?! Back of a length outside off. Siaka rides the bounce and dabs it towards third man. They decide to come back for the second but the second run was never on. Siaka stretched every sinew, evening sprawling across the turf but was well short as the keeper gathered the throw and whipped off the bails. Just what PNG did not need at this stage!
shortish outside off. Looks like the arm-ball again and Miyagi punches it past short extra cover for a brace
back of a length on off. Amini hops up onto his toes and defends
floated up nicely on leg stump. Hiri lunges at it and has a fence at the ball. Gets beaten on the inside and the ball hits the pads
darted in on a length on leg stump. Riazat is late on the flick and misses. The ball thuds into the pads
fuller on middle and off. Hiri comes forward and pokes it towards the bowler
fuller on middle and off. Riazat opens his bat face and guides it towards backward point
tossed up on a length just outside off. Hiri advances but is not to the pitch of the ball. Stabs at it and chunks it off the inside edge into the on side
slanted in on a back of a length on leg stump. Miyagi works it away towards deep backward square leg
slanted in on a length on leg stump. Amini plays all over it and gets struck on the thigh pad
length outside off. Riazat stands tall and punches it to long off
length ball on the stumps. Amini turns it into the on side. Short fine leg picks it up and hits the stumps at the bowler's end, conceding an over-throw off the deflection
floated up full outside off. Driven down the ground to long off
length just outside off. Amini pushes it towards cover and hares across to the other end
hard length on off. A bit of extra bounce but Riazat rides it well, dropping it into the backward point region for a single
full on middle and off. Riazat gets onto the front foot and flicks it straight to mid on
fired in on a fullish length just outside off. Amini gets forward and defends
back of a length on off. Riazat gets behind the line and defends
angled into the pads from around the wicket. Amini tucks it away towards deep mid wicket

dropped, oh dear! Hard length just outside off. Riazat, feeling the pinch, has a swipe across the line. Goes straight up off the outside half of the bat. Amini circles under it at backward point and then spills it. Could that be the game-changing moment?
length on middle and leg. Hiri works it towards mid wicket and sets off for the single, only to be sent back. No damage done this time
length outside off. Curves away beautifully and Miyaji, prodding at it, is beaten comprehensively
darted down leg. Hiri glances it behind square and the ball looks destined to hit the fence, until Riazat sprawls to his right at short fine and saves three
fuller, slanting into middle and off. Miyagi advances and works it past mid wicket for a single
length outside off. Holds in the surface a shade and spins away, taking the outside edge and dribbling towards short third
back of a length outside off. Riazat does not try anything ambitious this time and runs it down to third man
length outside off. Dabbed with an open bat face towards short third
given plenty of air and bowled very full on leg stump. Hiri tucks it off his toes towards deep square leg
floated up full outside off. Riazat plants his front foot and drills it towards extra cover
tossed up off-spinner on a full length on off. Spins away a touch and Amini prods it towards short third
back of a length on middle and off. A bit of spin away and Riazat plays against it, helping it towards deep backward square leg
off-spinner angled in on a length on off. Defended back to the bowler
very full on middle and leg. Miyagi knocks it down the ground to long on
length on off. Amini comes forward and blocks
full on leg stump. Riazat pushes it back towards the bowler, who misfields and ends up conceding a single
shorter on leg stump. Amini goes back and helps it towards deep square leg
length just outside off. Miyagi presses half forward and pushes it towards point
edged and four! Darted in at 101.5kph, full just outside off. Hiri has a flat-footed poke at it and the ball flies off the outside edge past the keeper!
flighted up full outside off. Riazat holds his shape and drives it past extra cover for a couple of runs
full outside off. Miyagi gets to the pitch of the ball and knocks it to long off
oh! Fired in on a length on off. Amini goes back and then just manages to jam his bat down in time. That kept very low
slower on a length on middle and off. Defended into the on side

Nsubuga has his first T20 World Cup wicket! Pushed in fuller on middle and off. Looks like an arm-ball or a slider from the release. Amini hares down the track, trying to smash it into next week but does not get to the pitch. The ball comes into him with the arm, beats his swing and rattles leg stump. PNG sink further!
finds the fence! Vital boundary! Given plenty of air and this ends up as a low full toss outside off. Riazat goes through the line and cracks it past extra cover!
length on off. Doriga comes forward and defends
full on off. Seems to curve away and Riazat pokes it towards short extra cover
length just outside off. Doriga gets half forward and plays it back to the bowler
full on middle and off. Riazat turns it towards short mid wicket
length on middle and off. Doriga taps it gently back to the bowler
length on middle and off. Riazat lets the ball come to him before defending
fullish just outside off. Doriga comes forward and pokes it towards extra cover. Second wicket-maiden of the innings!
a proper drag-down on middle and off. But because it is so short, it barely gets up to the ankle. Hiri swishes at it and edges it behind point
full on off. Miyaji presses forward and pushes it to mid off
beautifully bowled. Tossed up, on a length on off. Drifts into the batter before pitching and ripping away. Doriga beaten all ends up
length on off. Miyagi skips down the track and powers it uppishly towards long on
another play and miss! Floated up fuller and wider outside off. Perfect seam position and the ball snakes past the outside edge again

appeal! Zipped in very full on off. Riazat opens his bat face and dabs it towards backward point. There is a bit of slack fielding elsewhere, and that allows the second. The bowler, coming back to the appeal, thinks it might have grazed the boot first, and PNG have reviewed. Nothing on the boot and straight into the middle of the bat. PNG burn a review!
shorter on middle and leg. Doriga brings out the reverse and helps it towards short third man
length just outside off. Riazat comes forward and with an open bat face, steers it fine past the keeper. Kariko puts on the stakes at third man, dives to his left and saves two
flighted up very full on the pads. Hiri misses his flick and the ball pops up off the front pad towards the bowler
back of a length on middle and leg. Riazat turns it into the on side towards short mid wicket
full on off. Hiri gets to the pitch of the ball and drives it to long off
full on middle and off. Punched down the ground to mid off

big appeal, not given! Fired in full on middle and leg. Hiri comes down the track and then has a fresh-air shot. Gets struck on the pads but the umpire is not convinced. Was he too far down? We go upstairs to find out. Nothing on UltraEdge, and the ball has hit Hiri on the back pad. Impact in line and Ball Tracking reckons it would have crashed into the middle of middle stump. Uganda have another, and PNG are now six down!
full on off. Miyagi comes forward and taps it enough to extra cover's left for a single
floated up very full on middle and off. Soper pats it back to the bowler
slowed up on a length outside off. Riazat dabs it to short third and picks up another run
length on middle and off. Soper comes onto the front foot and blocks
tossed up full outside off. Grips in the surface and spins past the outside edge of the bat
fullish on middle and off. Soper wants to tip and run to get off the mark but his partner is not interested. Good work by the keeper to prevent the run
shorter outside off. Miyagi rocks back and cuts it towards deep cover point
back of a length on off. No room to work with again and Soper can only play it back to the bowler
angled in fuller on leg stump. Riazat has a poke at it and the ball squirts away off the inside edge. Riazat gets two for his toil
back of a length just outside off. Jabbed out to short extra cover. Back to back wicket-maidens for Nsubuga!
more turn! Fizzed through on a length outside off. Grips in the surface again and the appreciable spin takes it past the outside edge
very full just outside off. Miyagi has a swish at it and jams it off the inside edge into his pads
shortish outside off. Doriga goes back and jabs it towards backward point
low full toss on middle and off. Driven crisply down to long on
back of a length on middle and off. Doriga punches it off the back foot towards short extra cover
full outside off. Riazat comes forward and pushes it towards extra cover
length on middle and leg. Doriga comes half forward and nudges it to the bowler's right

oh dear, that is shocking running between the wickets! Zipped in full on the pads. Riazat flicks it towards long on. The second always seemed tight and that was made even riskier after both batters hesitated on the turn. Miyagi went through with it in the end, only to fall short by a fair distance. Will that moment of madness turn this game?!
fired in on a length on leg stump. Soper goes back to a ball he should be forward to, and gets struck on the back pad. Going down leg, though
back of a length outside off. Riazat guides it past backward point and the sweeper at third man misfields too, meaning that the second is completed without any hassle
shorter outside off. Soper hops onto the back foot and cuts it towards deep cover point
length in the sixth stump channel. Nips away just a smidgen and breezes past the outside edge of Riazat's bat
safe! Length on middle and off. Doriga gets down on one knee and has a big swipe across the line. The ball skews off the top edge and luckily for PNG, it evades short fine leg
slanted in full on leg stump. Doriga stabs it towards short mid wicket
tossed up on a length on leg stump. Waiswa lunges forward and plonks it back to the bowler
just over! Darted in on a length on middle and leg. Doriga advances and chips it over short mid wicket for a single
fuller, angling into leg stump. Waiswa defends
back of a length on the pads. Soper waits for it and tucks it past short mid wicket
length ball down leg. Waiswa looks for the sweep and seems to help it into the keeper's pads. Not given a wide, so it may have struck something on the way
fuller on middle and leg. Doriga skips down the track and hoicks it towards short mid wicket
full on the pads again. Waiswa flicks it to short mid wicket
zipped in even fuller, just outside leg. Doriga has a swing at it but does not make any contact. Good take by the keeper
full just outside off. Waiswa pokes it towards the bowler, who in trying to dive and save the run, ends up parrying it past the fielder at short mid wicket
angled in on a back of a length on the pads. Doriga charges down the track and swipes at it. Misses again and cops a blow on the thigh pad
shortish just outside off and that almost rolls along the turf. Riazat watches it all the way and knocks it to long off
darted in full on the stumps. Soper, having advanced, knocks it to long on

sprays it down leg, and some more exercise for the umpire. PNG not helping themselves with these wides full outside off. Riazat opens his bat face and steers it down to third man. Gets another brace to bring the equation down to 10 off 29
this is a clean strike! Given a hint of air on a length on middle and off. Doriga comes out of his bunker again, goes through the line and pumps it over the bowler's head!
fullish, slanting into middle and leg. Riazat works it towards deep square leg
much fuller and much flatter on the stumps. Doriga jams it off the inside edge into his pads
low full toss on middle and off. Waiswa comes forward and clips it past mid wicket for a couple of runs
length on middle and leg. Doriga plays the trajectory rather than the length and goes back. Stabs at it hurriedly and squirts it off the inside edge past short fine leg for a brace
full just outside off. Waiswa comes onto the front foot and pats it to mid off

massive appeal, turned down! Slanted in on a length on middle and leg. Doriga gets down on one knee and has a yahoo across the line. Misses it completely and gets rapped on the back thigh. The umpire is not interested, but Uganda are, and they review. The major question here is whether this was sliding down. Looked good on height. No bat involved. All eyes on Ball Tracking now and....it shows the ball would have thundered into leg stump. Three reds and Doriga is outta here!
length just outside off. Waiswa wants to drop and run to point but Riazat sends him back
very full on off. Vanua digs it out towards short extra cover
length ball hung outside off. Waiswa wafts at it away from his body and is beaten for pace
shortish on middle and off. Skids onto Soper and he pulls it away towards deep mid wicket
fullish just outside off. Riazat pokes it back towards the bowler
short and wide outside off. Does not get up very much and Vanua jabs it towards extra cover
fuller outside off. Riazat plays it with an open bat face towards backward point

hot knife through butter! Fizzed through on a length on middle and leg. The trajectory is flat, and that makes Soper go back. The ball, though, is not quite short enough to be camping in the crease. Pitches, skids on and Soper is awfully late on the stroke. Breezes past his bat to knock back the stumps, and Uganda are just two wickets away from bowling PNG out!
length outside off. Riazat eases it down to third man
shortish on the stumps. Nao waits back and punches it to long on
full on the stumps. Waiswa stabs it towards short mid wicket
tossed up on a length on middle and leg. Vanua lunges forward and smothers it
length on middle and off. Waiswa bunts it to mid off and dashes across to the other end
back of a length just outside off. Keeps low and Vanua knocks it to long off
length on off. Riazat lets the ball come to him before meeting it right under his eyes
full on off. Vanua comes forward and pushes it past the bowler for a single

another wayward delivery down leg, and PNG are not helping themselves. Called a wide, and Uganda need just four runs now! dropped again! Short and wide outside off. Waiswa, having taken a step down the track, flashes hard at it. Slashes it uppishly towards backward point, where Bau puts it down. Relatively straightforward chance too!
short outside off. Nao uses the pace on offer and runs it down to third man
fullish just outside off. Waiswa scuffs his attempted drive towards the bowler
length in the sixth stump channel. Proper Test match length and this zips past the outside edge of Vanua's poke
length just outside off. Waiswa plants his front foot and nurdles it into the gap between point and cover
length just outside off. Vanua presses half forward and jabs it into the cover region
back of a length outside off. Jabbed out towards backward point
off-pace on a length well outside off. Nao thinks about playing at it initially before letting it go

goes straight up, and taken this time! Hard length just outside off. Riazat, like he did earlier in the evening, hacks across the line and skews it off the outer half of the bat. Kariko comes running in from third man, dives forward and takes the catch. Riazat walks off to applause from his teammates and the support staff. Is it too little, too late, though, from PNG's POV?
low full toss just outside off. Nao has a massive swish at it and the ball dribbles off the outside edge towards third man

another wide down leg, and this is an issue that has plagued PNG throughout. 15 runs off wides now, and Uganda inch closer to victory! into the track outside off. Does not bounce very much and Masaba clinks it towards extra cover
length outside off and this keeps low too. Waiswa shapes for the cut but the ball squirms well under his bat
hard length on middle and leg. Cuts back into Vanua and he is late in bringing his bat down. Clips the back thigh and rolls away into the off side

History for Uganda! Their first men's T20 World Cup, and they now have their first win in the competition. Kampala, Nansana, Kira - wherever you are in Uganda, this is your moment to party. A night to savour for everyone associated with Ugandan cricket, and a night that they will never forget! This is flatter and fuller on leg stump. Waiswa gets inside the line and paddles it away fine. Smiles all around in the Ugandan camp. They have achieved what they sought to accomplish tonight, and they have points on the board!
hard length on middle and off. Gets big on Nao as he swings at it and he cloths it on the bounce to mid off
shortish on off. Vanua backs away and throws his hands at it. All he manages is an inside edge that bobbles towards short fine leg

leg stump knocked back! Back of a length delivery that pitches on off and continues on with the angle. Nao swings like a rusty gate and his bat ends up in a different postcode to the ball. Hits the top of leg stump, and PNG are on the brink of getting bowled out!
back of a length on leg stump. Kariko stays back and stabs it towards short mid wicket
back of a length in the channel. Pitches and nips away with the angle. Kariko goes feeling for it and is beaten all ends up

edged and gone! Kyewuta hammers the final nail in PNG's batting coffin! Back of a length outside off. Vanua skips down the track and aims for the moon. Loses all shape and only manages to nick it through to the keeper. Kyewuta is jubilant, and Uganda will be thrilled to bits with their effort so far!
Bilal slides it down leg, Warner just nudges it through square leg and Australia get underway
Gorgeous square drive to begin with! It's full outside off, swinging back in. Prajapati leans into the drive and caresses it through point
And Head is away! Full and wide, Head gets low and reaches out with an expansive drive, crashing it through cover point
Full and swinging down leg. Good stop by Wade behind the wicket Inswinger, full on leg, Prajapati digs it out square on the leg side
Length ball outside off and this shapes away nicely to beat Head's outside edge. Better from Bilal Khan

Starc goes up in appeal as a low inswinging full toss hits Athavale on the pads. But did he get an inside edge first? Australia review. Athavale was looking to flick. But this looks to have hit pad first before deflecting onto the bat and back onto his feet. And ball tracking on DRS shows that to be smashing the base of middle stump. Golden duck for Athavale. Starc strikes in the first over
Full on off, swinging away again, Head parries to cover

Almost a first-baller this time as well, but it just beats the cover fielder! It's a low full toss fired across Ilyas, who opens the face and drives it aerially in front of point. The cover fielder hurled himself to his left, but in the end the ball was well wide of him
On a length, wide of off, slashed away along the ground to deep point

Length ball fired across him, he leaves it alone as it's quite wide and the umpire thinks so too Starc strikes again! But is that going down leg? Ilyas reviews. It's that full inswinger to the right-hander again. But there is a question of whether it pitched in line and whether it was swinging down leg. Ilyas missed his attempted flick. But that's pitching outside leg. Ilyas survives
Full around middle, Warner pushes it out to the off side
Full and wide, Ilyas hits a grounded drive wide of mid-off
Full around off, parried back to the bowler
Length ball on off and angling across Head, who brings his bat down and gets an inside edge to the leg side
Full on off, steered wide of deep third for a single
Warner slaps it away through cover. Length and width on offer and that's all the invitation Warner needs to pick the gap between point and cover
Length ball outside off, left alone by Prajapati
Slower ball around leg, Warner misses and he's struck on the pads. Kaleemullah tries his best to convince the umpire that that's out, but the umpire doesn't think so! Could have been going down leg
Length ball around off, tapped towards backward point. They can't sneak a single
Length ball outside leg, drops to Warner's right off his pads and Australia get the leg bye
Full on a fourth stump line and angling into the stumps, he looks to work it leg side and gets an inside edge onto the pads
ON a length on leg, 127kph, Head hops and blocks back to the bowler
Length ball steered fine on the off side for a single
Head gets lucky! Length ball angled across him, Head went for the cut, but nearly dragged it on with the ball narrowly going past the stumps. Oman won't mind the start they have gotten so far
Full around off, Head looks to swing it away through midwicket but gets an inside edge through square leg instead
Full on middle and off, 135.1kph, defended back to the bowler by Prajapati
Length ball outside off, crisply driven out to sweeper cover
Length ball around leg, he misses the flick and the ball drops to his left off his pads
Dug in short, put away through square leg! He can't hurr Head on with that short ball and the batter's able to  swivel and pull it away, beating the fielder in the deep running to his left
Swings one down leg side for a wide Nails that inswinging yorker, and Ilyas is just about able to jam his bat down in time. Edges it onto his boots

Taken at mid-off! Full outside off and Head drives down the ground. Can't get the elevation and Khalid Kail takes it moving to his right. That's a huge strike for Oman, not very surprising that it's Bilal Khan who gets it
Low full toss wide of off and Ilyas is onto it in a flash, but hits it too close to Warner at point, who is not letting that get through
Length ball on off, Marsh defends
Lovely drive down the ground. This was overpitched on off, mid-off was wide, and that's all Ilyas needed to give the ball a gentle push that sees the ball race away
On a length on off, Marsh takes a step forward to counter the swing, and meets it with an open face to steer it to short third

Huge mix-up and Oman could have lost one to a run-out here! Oh no, the batter may have just survived here. Australia miss a big opportunity! This was flicked to Head's right at midwicket and the batter took off. Prajapati at the non-striker's wasn't sure and he sent Ilyas back and when Head's throw came in at the striker's end, Ilyas was nowhere in sight. But the throw missed the keeper and the stumps and by the time the stumps were thrown down, he made his ground
Back of length delivery angled into Prajapati, hurries him for pace as he looks to hook it fine on the leg side. Gets it to the fine leg region for a single
Just a little short around off and Warner stands tall and pulls it away through midwicket
Full outside off, he looks to go across and sweep it but misses
Beaten! Length ball angled across Warner, fired in flatter and quicker. Warner can't get bat on it and it hits the keeper's pad and deflects onto the stumps, causing momentary excitement
Clipped through square leg for a single
Pushed towards cover
Full outside off, Prajapati defends
Full on middle and leg, squeezed out towards cover
Length delivery around off, steered to backward point
Length ball on leg, clipped down to long-on
Length ball outside off, hint of movement away from the right-hander. Prajapati prods at it but is beaten on the outside edge
Length ball fired in flat on off and angling towards leg, Marsh nudges it leg side for his first run
Length ball, fended to the off side
Slower ball on a length outside off, Ilyas steers it fine on the off side for a single
Back of length delivery, punched to mid-off
140kph length ball bounces sharply and stings Prajapati on the gloves as he looks to fend at it. The ball drops in front to his right and they don't try a risky single
On a length outside off, he takes a few steps forward and smothers it
Banged in short around off, Prajapati is beaten on the pull
Full, driven to cover point, but the fielder is a little sloppy there and can't collect. That allows Marsh to get off strike
Slower ball, on a length around off, Prajapati taps it in front
Length ball on off, Warner is able to steer it past the backward point fielder, and the batters run two

That looks plumb! And given immediately. But Oman review. This is on full around middle. Was there an inside edge as Prajapati looked to flick? Nope, no bat, and that's shown to be clipping leg stump, so the decision stands! Prajapati has to go and Australia have the second wicket
Classic Warner! Full around off and going across Warner, but he is across the stumps early. Gets on one knee and flicks it over backward square
Length ball angled across him, he defends to the off side
Very full on leg, dug out towards midwicket
Length ball around off, Marsh looks to rock back and pull but is beaten by the lack of pace and bounce
Length ball outside off, opens the face and runs it to short third. They can't sneak a quick run
Darted in full on middle and off, Marsh pushes it out to mid-off
Back of length on a fifth stump line, Ilyas fends
Driven in the air, but in the gap. This is a full length ball around middle and off, Marsh backs away leg side and drives on the up. Perfectly picks the gap between extra cover and mid-off
Oh, hello! That's swung off his hips!  Length ball angled into him and he whips it over backward square and it goes all the way
Dragged down outside off, Marsh cuts it hard to cover point. The fielder puts in a dive and gets a hand on the ball. Australia manage just the single
Yorker on off, Ilyas blocks
Big swing and a miss! Fired in full on middle, Warner was going for a big heave over the leg side, but the ball stays low

Edged and taken. Length ball outside off that straightens after pitching. Ilyas looks to drive and gets a thick outside edge. Wade dives and takes it to his right. And that's a big wicket, from Australia's perspective. The Oman skipper looked like the best batter of the lot for them. And talk about finishing the powerplay on a high

Full around middle and off, blocked back to the bowler. And that will be the powerplay done, with Australia barely crossing run-a-ball, and having lost the wicket of Travis Head. Oman will be happy to take this.
Length ball around off, he defends
Full on a fifth-stump line, driven along the ground to the cover fielder
Driven out to sweeper cover
Full outside off, Marsh hits a hard drive to Aqib Ilyas' left at cover, and the Oman skipper throws himself at it. Excellent stop to save the run
Dragged short outside off, Kail can't clear backward point with his cut

Full around off, he looks to flick it and gets it off the inside half of the bat to deep square leg. And that's a no ball, so Mehran will have to bowl a free hit! Sees Warner standing leg side, tries to go for the full yorker and misses. Warner is quick to move across and get low to slice the low full toss over backward point
Dragged short again and this time Kail picks the gap between backward point and short third for his first boundary
Length ball angled in from outside off, Warner steers to backward point
On a length outside off, Kail defends
Full outside off, Warner brings out the cover drive and this time it's Zeeshan Maqsood diving to his right to make a good stop. Oman have been pretty good in the field today
On a length outside off, tapped behind point

Has Warner's back foot lifted up there? Sharp keeping from Athavale. This is being checked. The keeper was standing up to the stumps. Mehran goes wide, Warner is dragged forward and misses his drive. Warner's foot was dragging forward, but it never lifted off the ground. Good keeping nonetheless, but Warner will survive here
Tossed up on middle, blocked to the off side
Length ball outside off goes past the outside edge as Maqsood prods at it
Length ball, tossed up slow from around the wicket. And Warner pushes it out through cover point. With that, Warner goes past Finch to become Australia's leading scorer in men's T20Is
Full outside off and angling in, Maqsood's drive goes straight to the cover fielder
Length ball, cut to point
