Sharp bounce there! Length ball spits up and hits Zeeshan Maqsood on the arm as he was leaning forward to defend
Full outside off, Marsh goes for the sweep but gets an inside edge
It's all coming up Stoinis today! Short and wide from him, but he can do no wrong today, eh? Maqsood looks to cut but feathers it behind where Wade laps it up
Nails the sweep this time! On a length around off, he gets low and powers it away

Length ball outside off, dropped behind point and they take off for a quick single. David Warner runs in from short third and has a shy at the striker's end. Direct end would have been a wicket, but misses. Tim David then misses his attempt at the non-striker's end
Full on middle and off, driven along the ground to sweeper cover and the single brings up fifty for Australia
Length ball around off, Kail meets it with a solid defence
Floated up full outside off, driven to cover's right
Full outside off, he looks for a drive through the off side but gets an inside edge onto the pads
Googly on a length on off, spins past the outside edge as Ayaan looks to drive straight

Bison is gone! He has picked out long-on! This is in the slot and there to be hit, but Marsh doesn't get the distance on it as he goes downtown. Shoaib Khan takes it just above head height Mehran Khan is absolutely pumped.

THAT IS A BLINDER! Aqib Ilyas said before the game that there are no big names once you are on the pitch, and that Oman aren't fazed by facing Australia, and isn't he leading by example? This is full outside off and Maxwell hits a cover drive first ball. It's hit hard and low, and Ilyas flies to his left to grab it low, and at full stretch. He was parallel to the ground when he grabbed that! Shout for the catch of the tournament so far! Maxwell's horror run continues, meanwhile, and Mehran's dream World Cup continues!
Short and wide and Ayaan cuts it away hard through point. They get two as sweeper cover runs across
Full outside off, Stoinis is able to drive it past the bowler to long-off
On a length on off, Ayaan defends
Length ball angles in from outside off, Warner inside edges it onto himself trying to work it leg side
Length ball around off, slapped away to deep cover
Length ball outside off, Warner punches it away in front of point to end the over with a single

Warner misses the reverse-sweep. Appeal for lbw turned down. Probably sliding down leg. This was bowled from wide of the crease, angling into Warner, who switched position but missed out. Oman have reviewed this. They want to strike when the iron is hot. It pitches around middle and leg, straightens and it's hit Warner on the glove so Oman lose a review
Length ball angled in from wide of the crease flies past the outside edge
Length ball around off, cut hard to backward point

Slashed for four past the keeper! Length ball outside off and with no slip fielder or short third in place, Ayaan is happy to slice it wide of the keeper. Safe shot for him, and he picks up a boundary
Tossed up loopy and full around off, Warner just taps it in front on the off side for a quick single
Length ball angling in, he opens the face to run it down to deep third
Floated up full on off, Stoinis pushes it out to long-off
Back of length outside off, cut away to deep point
On a length around off, Warner backs away and slaps it out to sweeper cover for a brace
Short outside off, left alone by Ayaan. But that was inside the wide line
Tossed full around off, driven back to the bowler's right. Just four runs off the over and Australia are 56 for 3 at the halfway mark
Oh, what a drive! That's definitely the most elegant drive we have seen this evening. Overpitched outside off, he leans into it and strokes it between mid-off and cover
tossed up on off, gets a good stride in but still has to reach for this as it's swept behind square leg
full on off, scuffed drive into the turf fielded by Mehran to his left
pushed through flat on a back of a length, back foot punch down to long-on
back of a length on off, stands tall and punches this down to long off
low full toss on the pads, paddle swept fine but just the single
angled in to the leftie from around the wicket, back foot push towards long-on for another single
full on off, watches this on to the bat and dabs it into the offside for one
length wide of off, 116kph, sticks in the surface as Stoinis pushes at this on the front foot. Inside edge into the leg side for a single
Again waits for it and stabs it late behind point for another single
Warner looks for the reverse and misses. Optimistic appeal for leg before but this clearly pops up off the glove
swept down to backward square leg, takes this from a good length on the stumps
full on off, conventional play this time. Driven down to long-off for another single
good length on off, backs away and chops this into the offside for one
good length on off, has to check the drive as this one doesn't quite come on to the bat as expected. Straight to mid-off
good length googly from over the wicket, Stoinis checks his drive into the covers for one
full on off, bat twists in the hand has Ayaan looks to drive this. Bobble just in front of short extra leads to a misfield and a single
good length off break, stabbed in front of square on the offside
Wide yorker, and this looks to be just along the blue wide line. Too wide says the umpire angled in on the stumps now, backs away and slaps this straight back at Starc
rips past the outside edge! Dips and draws Stoinis into the drive and then zips away
Wide full toss, 135kph, play and a miss
full on off, eased straight to short extra cover
Holes out at deep point! This was another one full and wide, Kail slices it in the air but just can't get the power that he's looking for. Straight at Maxwell in the deep. Oman lose their fifth
good length googly this time around off, zips through as Stoinis only ends up chopping this into the turf near the crease

Given out lbw, but they review. This was angled in from wide of the crease to the right hander, and struck him right on the front knee roll. Was it going down leg? That's the only question. And indeed it was, this is missing leg stump! Good review.
tossed up on the stumps, defended into the onside
good length on middle and leg, tucked through midwicket for one
Appeal for leg before as this skids on to the pads and catches Ayaan on the crease. Umpire Joel Wilson thinks it's sliding down leg and Australia opt against a review
angled in from around the wicket, 89kph, back foot punch through extra cover
swept from a good length down towards deep square leg
Warner looks to make something happen by coming down the track, but is forced to adjust as Zeeshan drags it shorter. Ends up dabbing this square on the offside for one

Another decision overturned! This was tossed up on a good length around off. It's the leg break that drags the batter into the drive before gripping and turning away just enough to take the outside edge. Or does it? There is a review from the batter and shows that there is in fact no bat involved
good length on off, goes back and works this through mid-on
tossed up on the stumps, whipped to midwicket
First boundary since the 9th over! Slides on to the pads, as Warner just helps it around the corner past short fine

No doubt about this though! Zampa fires this in much quicker, 90kph, it drifts in as Shoaib yorks himself coming down the track and gets into all sorts of trouble. The ball clatters into the off stump as Zampa brings up 300 T20 wickets!
Two in two! This was full outside off, and Warner lashes a drive through the covers
Aqib slows it down as this slides on with the arm from around the wicket. Raps Stoinis on the front pad but it is clearly sliding down leg. They run the leg bye
back of a length on off, opens the face and runs this down to third man
good length on off, gets a good stride in and drives but straight to short extra cover
short on off, breezy pull down towards deep square leg
fuller on middle and leg, eased down to long-on for one
back of a length, angled in on off. Run down to third man
Another ripper to Stoinis! Tosses up this leggie, drags the batter forward and just inches past both the edge and off stump. Close
Full on middle and leg, looks to loft this down the ground but catches this inside half of the bat as this loops over midwicket for a couple
length googly which Warner deals with by sweeping square on the onside
hard length nips back in and catches Mehran on the back thigh as he looks to work this onside
full on off, driven down to long-off
Hello! This time Mehran gets a solid connection, as he picks up this slightly overpitched delivery and belts it straight back down the ground
good length on the stumps, front foot push towards cover
length ball on off, swings at this and gets a thick edge in the air but safe. Over point for a couple
full and down leg
length on the stumps, goes back and tucks this towards midwicket. Early call for two, but the man in the deep makes up ground fast to keep this to one

Caught and six! Stoinis gets a better hold of this one, lofts it on the up and Ayaan Khan takes a good catch back pedalling on the cover boundary, but his momentum sees him tumble over the ropes with the ball in tow
flatter outside off, goes back and across to work this down to long-on
This one goes even further! Again pitched up, but this time Stoinis launches it straight back down the ground. No chance for the man in the deep this time

full, slides down leg. Wade with some quick glove work collects and whips off the bails. They go upstairs for a quick stumping check, but despite the back foot coming off the ground briefly Ayaan is in when the bails come off good length off break from around the wicket, bit of grip and turn as Ayaan carefully guides this behind point for one
full once more, and Stoinis might feel he's missed out. Simply driven back to the bowler
good length outside off, chopped towards cover point for a single
Flat and all the way! Mehran keeps tossing it up and Stoinis keeps going after it. Absolutely annihilates this straight back over the bowler
good length angled in, worked to Maxwell's left for another run
Fourth six of the over! This one is not as short but Stoinis just swings through the line and sends it sailing over the man at long-on

Whipped for a maximum! This was short and flat from Zampa around off, but Ayaan just whips this flat over deep square leg with a lovely flick of the wrists. Maxwell was about 10 yards in from the ropes and it sails over him
darted in from around the wicket, Warner gets and inside edge into his pads attempting the slog sweep. They run the single length ball angled in, punted one bounce to the man at wide long-on
good length on the stumps, turned around the corner for one
full and wide, Warner has to reach for this as he slaps it towards deep cover point
full outside off, looks to heave this leg side but only manages an inside edge towards backward square leg
Stoinis backs away, making room to free his arms. Shakeel follows him as Stoinis muscles this down to long-on
Another huge one from Ayaan! Down on one knee and slog sweeps this leg break all the way over deep midwicket
Warner mistimes the big swing, scuffs it towards midwicket for one

Zampa gets the last laugh though! Ayaan goes for another sweep, but this one is much slower than the last one. It means the ball has enough time to grip in the surface, which sees Ayaan only able to top edge this straight to short fine
good length on off, backs away and flat bats it off the bottom of the bat down the ground for a couple
Beauty! Deserved a wicket with that one. This was a beautifully flighted googly, that just squared up the new man. Zips past the outside edge and the off peg
Well fielded by Shakeel! Stoinis looks to make room once more as Shakeel follows him and darts in a yorker. Stoinis shovels it out hard, but Shakeel saves runs with a good low stop to his left
full and straight with a hint of swing, 122kph. Snuck out towards mid-on for one
Controlled pull for four! This was slightly short and it sits up in the surface. Mehran doesn't try to over play this, just guides it past the man at deep backward square
Stoinis is rolling! Insouciant flick as he walks across all the way to the offside and just flicks this full toss to the square leg boundary
fuller and angled in, strikes the front pad as he looks to heave this onside. They run the leg bye
Nearly another but can't beat the man at short third. This was full outside off, Stoinis opens the face and looks to run it past the man in the ring. Only a single
short ball from around the wicket, fended away well from around chest height. Does well to keep this down
Warner looks for the reverse lap pull into the space behind point, but can't connect. Well kept as well
skips down the track and slices this ambitious drive over cover. Just the single
full and down leg, Warner fails to get anything on this Skips down the track as Bilal drags it short. Ends up in an ungainly swipe on the bounce down to long-on
Short again, pace-off. Ducks into this in attempting the pull as the ball loops up off the batter's helmet through to Wade

Six and a no-ball! Oh dear, oh dear. This was a full toss above waist height and Stoinis just pummels it over deep midwicket. 50 up for Stoinis Full on off and hammered back at the bowler, who can only parry this towards midwicket
yorker just outside off, dug out towards point
length outside off, dragged on one knee towards wide long-on
full and straight, slapped down the ground but long-on collects
full on off, clears the front leg and slaps this down to long-off
Warner joins the party! Skips down the track, has to reach for this outside off but ends up levering it with ease over long-on. 50 for Warner now
good length on the stumps, leans back and swings through the line. Over the bowler, but while it was timed relatively well there are two men in the V to mop up
darted in outside off, as Warner misses on the reverse sweep
full on off, driven hard down to long-off. 100 up for Oman
full on off, hacked down to long-on along the ground
Clears deep midwicket! Short and pace-off outside off, but Mehran waits for it and pulls it cleanly and all the way
darts in a yorker that Stoinis leans back and digs out towards backward point. It's a tight single and a direct hit might have had him at the non-striker's end
wide yorker, but too wide says the umpire full and wide once more, squeezed in the air through cover for a couple
Swing and a miss! Warner gets on one knee and looks to hoick this over deep midwicket but the ball zips under his bat and past the off peg
It's all going Stoinis' way! Full and wide, Stoinis swings and swings hard. And that's good enough as a thick outside edge sails over short third
full outside off, carved in front of deep point for a couple
Bang! Full and straight, and this was struck as clean as a whistle. Swings right through the line and it goes all the way, arrow straight
Lovely shot! Short and wide, sits up and Shakeel cracks this behind point. In the air but well safe
Slower one on middle and leg, forces Stoinis to wait for this as he chips it gently down towards long-off
full and very wide wide yorker, squirted out towards deep cover
short of a length on the stumps, pulled towards deep square leg. They hustle for two. Expected with Warner at the crease

Lovely work from David in the deep sees the end of Mehran! This was a low full toss that Mehran lofts, seemingly for six, but Tim David hustles back and to his right from long-on grabs hold of the catch before popping it back up, going over the rope and back in, and then completing it. Top work, made it look far easier than it was

And finally Oman break the stand! This one is bowled into the pitch, and Warner just can't generate the power he wants. Ends up slapping this one from outside off straight to long-off. Warner walks off in a huff, clearly wanted to see this through to the end
David in action once more, another that's heaved wide of long-on. This time the ball dribbles towards the ropes as David mops up
David wastes little time! This was a slower one, 98kph, on his pads. But David gets inside the line and slaps this down to the fine leg boundary with interest. That really did race away
full on off and carved over cover. Marsh puts in a dive to grab this but can't hold on, as the batters run two
slower one, full on off. Driven down to long-on. Stoinis turns down the single actually opting to keep the strike. Shows the value placed on the set man on this surface
full on off, leans back and muscles this down to long-off
Drops a sitter! Leading edge goes straight up in the air, but the man running in from long-off just lets this bobble out. They manager to scamper two in the meantime
Dropped by Stoinis at short third! Slashes at a wide one and gets a thick edge, one that Stoinis can only get fingertips to as it dips over him
full on the stumps, flicked in the air but on the bounce towards deep midwicket
But no mistake here! This was a cutter banged into the turf. Shakeel looks to carve it high over point but only finds Warner in the deep. He takes it smartly to his left
full and wide, swing and a miss
Slower one outside off, Bilal with a wild swing and a miss
Flicked behind square leg! Length ball, sticks in the surface, but David waits for it and flicks his wrists to great effect
attempted yorker, eased straight down the ground
full on off, clobbered down to wide long-on. They look for a second that's never on as David is run out off the final delivery
Low full toss that Kaleemullah looks to work onside but ends up getting a leading edge, safely towards cover. Australia win by 39 runs
drifts in a tossed up delivery on middle and off, defended with soft hands
Looks for swing but overpitches outside off, driven to point
taps it to short cover, looks for a single but is sent back
Rares up from a length, line is outside off and Taylor shaped to cut before pulling out halfway into the shot
lovely hit!  Walks across the stumps to get inside the line of the delivery as he sweeps him up and over to clear the long leg boundary.

Lot of swing but that takes it outside the tramline. Length was fullish and Taylor went for the big drive through cover Yorker missed and Taylor lays into the full bunger. Fifth-stump line offers enough room for the drive through cover
lunges forward and defends back to the bowler
Best ball of the over so far. Yorker at 139ks not far from the crease, was at the stumps and Taylor handled it well. Stayed in the crease and squeezed it gently towards cover for a quick single
slaps it into the gap at wide long-off as they hare back for a second
Another full toss, Shaheen not landing them yorkers. This full toss was around thigh-high. 137ks. Monank may have been overwhelmed but managed to pat it towards mid-on
shortish on middle and leg, punched towards deep midwicket

Shaheen is confident, not sure if that was for lbw but looked to be going down leg. There wasn't a woody sound, so the chances of a strangle down leg were slim. Not given and the decision won't be reviewed after a chat.
Down leg, goes past the flick A wide to the off side this time. Length ball kept going away, let go WIde on a length, inside the tramline this time, let go. There was shape away.
floats it full and across Rizwan as he defends into the off side
Taylor connects with the square drive and Shadab dives at point to save three. Flung himself to the left and stopped it on the bounce. That was driven on the up really well

blinder at slip! Very, very reminiscent of Dwayne Leverock's from 2007. Take a bow, Steven Taylor. Netravalkar bowls a pearler, Rizwan is squared up by the line and length, the hint of away movement helps get the edge as Rizwan jabs at the delivery and the ball flies low to Taylor who puts his right hand out to pluck it sensationally.
Into the pitch, on a length and angling away. Monank is on the back stool, looking to slap it square. Misses
flayed on the up through extra cover, lovely timing and placement. Terrific way to get off the mark

Third wide of the over, second down leg. Goes past the flick again. Naseeem and Babar have a chat as Amir walks back. He's swinging it but the direction's off At the stumps this time. Fullish length at 132ks, Monank's footwork was a bit tentative, but he managed to clip it to midwicket
gently worked into the leg side as Netravalkar bowls a tight line on middle and leg

Will the extra balls cost Amir? Monank takes the charge and flays him through backward point. Was a length ball that was turned into a fuller one. It was angling away and Monank went with the cross-bat, got it off the bottom and got it in the gap to the right of backward point. His bat might've cracked.
gets this to jag back in from length on middle, defended
Pitched up outside off, Monank plinks a cover drive. Bat-face turns inwards and the ball dribbles to the bowler's right
gets the edge as Babar is squared up, the ball rolls down to third man
whips this to deep midwicket
Defends the length, ball at the stumps, in front
drifts in from around the wicket, Usman is squared up a hint but manages to defend.
Shaheen swings it away to beat Taylor's attempted flay over cover. 139ks. Fullish length got great bounce

what is happening?  Usman sees the ball tossed up and decides he's going down town, but the ball spins away to have him slicing high to long-off. The noise is deafening. Nitish Kumar was cool and calm underneath the high ball.
Pitched up just outside off, middles the off-drive and a misfield by Amir allows the single

sensational way to get off the mark!  What nerves? Down on one knee as he brings out the slog sweep, clobbers it over deep backward square leg. Was a safe hit as he went all in, was also hit towards the shorter boundary.

Back to wides. Length ball is down leg and goes past the flick Slip was wide but was that a chance? Iftikhar there didn't go for the catch. It was closer to him than the keeper. From the first replay, it looks like that was Iftikhar's chance.
punched to point, a half-stop means they get a single
Hey salt, here's injury... Monank gets an overpitched ball, takes a nice stride forward to get it on the low full toss actually, and nails it through cover
drifts in and skids through low on off, defended back

Shaheen is convinced with his appeal again, this for an lbw looked tight. Not given, Pakistan review. 143ks length ball looked to have kept a bit low. Monank was back in the crease and tried to defend with a slightly closed bat. Got beaten and hit just below the knee-roll? Where did it pitch though? Just outside leg.  Allahuddien Paleker's call is vindicated.
Taylor was lost a bit there. Took a couple of steps down after inside-edging the cover drive to short fine leg.
beauty! Shapes away nicely from outside off, Fakhar plays and misses
Nails the cover drive but finds the infielder. Pitched up by Naseem
works it wide of mid-on
Brave of Monank to make room early. Gets a fullish ball that is flogged back down the ground, Naseem stops it in follow-through. Not middled and Monank is disappointed
driven on the up but can't pick the gap, mistimed to mid-off
Tries to go downtown but inside edges the fullish length ball around the corner through backward square leg. Wasim Akram, on comms, unhappy with Pakistan not going for bouncers
hits the deck hard as he angles one in on a length from around the wicket, defended back
Quick single to cover. Pitched up around off, gently defended by Taylor and he called early. Great response from Monank
cuts back in to beat Babar's inside edge as he gives him the charge. That nipped back in considerably

Naseem goes into the pitch and the ball balloons up... but goes well over midwicket and lands safely. Shortish length and at the body, might've bounced more than Monank expected and he was late into the semi-pull. Looked to popped off the sticker. Ends up trickling to the edge of the ring
works this straight to midwicket
pitched up outside off, Fakhar leans into the drive as he creams this into the gap at point
He goes short too but is not as spicy as Naseem. The pace is manageable for Monank, who swivels and pulls with ease to pick up four to long leg
attempts the short-arm jab, timing not quite right, hits it wide of midwicket for a single
Three-quarter length on off, opens the face on the front-foot defence. Shadab runs in and... misfields to allow a single to deep third

struck high on the pad as Babar plays all around the incoming length delivery. As the ball deflected into the off side, he took off for a run. By the time he was sent back, there was an attempted direct hit at the striker's end. Babar was wandering away and could've so easily been run out. They get one for the overthrow
Fullish ball at the stumps, clipped to the leg side

what on earth has Fakhar done?  Attempts a paddle and ends up hitting it straight to short fine leg. Was in no control of the stroke, was completely off balance, so didn't get the amount of bat he would've liked. USA are all over Pakistan here in the powerplay.
Beats bat with 144ks. Nope, inside edge actually. Taylor tried to pump the three-quarter length ball down the ground but got it onto pad
stands tall and punches straight to point
Smart two to midwicket. Taylor charged and got followed by a length ball, he adjusted and managed to bunt it towards the outfield. The batters hared through for two

goes after a short and wide delivery, misses. Ali Khan sprayed it too far wide outside off beats him with one that nips away off a length from fifth stump or thereabouts. Shadab went for a flashing cut but missed
Length around fifth, tries defending it straight. Inside edges it towards forward square leg for a square leg
Naseem (handshake) jaffa. He nicks off Taylor with the perfect length ball in the channel.
firm push off the front foot but mid-off does well to come around and stop that

Edged, beats Iftikhar at slip! Looks like it didn't carry. He came forward and got on one knee but the ball half-volleyed him to the left and popped through the fingers. Was a three-quarter-length ball around off that Gous tried to drive down the ground. Ifti was standing wide and 20 metres away, shows the graphic on TV
gently defended into the off side as they scamper a quick single
Opens the face and pats the length ball through cover
shuffles across to defend this incoming short of a length delivery
Pitched up outside off, driven to cover
square driven to backward point, a half-stop allows them to take a single
Helps it away with a pull, four just in front of square. Not a bad ball at all, 137ks on a length. Bail-trimmer but Gous stood upright and cleared the infield with a bat swing indicating conviction
driven firmly but can't pick the gap as he hits it straight to cover
Low fully outside off, lunges into the square drive and finds point
mistimes this slap to cover
Shortish ball with all that pace has Monank hopping. Does well to fend it from just in front of the body, to backward point
lunges forward to defend, the ball rolls off the pad onto the leg side
Hard length, 136ks, at the stumps. Tucked off the back foot in the gap to square leg's left
drifting into middle and leg, worked into the gap at midwicket as they take two
Overpitched on fifth, opens the face to drive to the left of deep point for a couple
turn and bounce!  Shadab beaten as he jabs at this in-drifter

To the other side and this is glorious, deserves four despite the excellent chase to the right from Usman. He raced from deep point but the timing on that cover drive was just too pure. Rauf overpitched again and Gous held his shape to perfection.
the leading edge  nearly lobs back to Harmeet.  Shouts of catch, excitement from behind the stumps
Pulls his length back but still on the fuller side, it's tapped from just outside off and defended to cover
gently tapped with soft hands for a single
Much better. Three-quarter length on fourth at 149ks, defended without much weight transfer, to the right of Rauf. Gous maintaining his balance well though
gets well forward and turns it into the midwicket region, Harmeet runs across to stop the ball
hit on the thigh pad as he attempts a short-arm jab, the ball deflects into the off side and they scamper a leg bye. There was a stifled lbw appeal
Bad start. Loops it too wide and too full, Monank takes a big stride and pings it through cover. A bit of football from the fielder at the boundary saves two
defends to point
Full at the stumps, clipped to midwicket
advances down the pitch, the bowler does well to follow him and Shadab gets a thickish inside edge towards long leg
Ooh, did that hold in the pitch a bit? Fullish and flat outside off, 90ks, Gous checked his shot and managed to keep it on the ground. Goes to cover
driven on the up to extra cover
A bit of spin but Gous handles it well. Length ball just outside off, worked off the back foot to long-on
backs away and thrashes this straight to mid-off
Similar ball, shot and same result. Monank cleared the front leg and used his hand-speed to no get hurried
attempts to flat-bat that down to long-on, mistimes it to the man there
Chance? No, no edge. Pitched up outside off,
Drives the length ball from the top of the bounce. 149ks too. Gets it to the cover outfield to pick up two. Positive running as well
sees the batter advancing and fires this in, Babar is cramped for room as he defends. Harmeet does well to hare across and prevent the single
Bumper at pace has Monank try the ramp over third. Look like a mid-ball decision but couldn't lay bat on it. Proactive nonetheless.
worked towards the man coming in from deep midwicket. Looks for two but the boundary rider does well to cover ground and fire a flat throw
Length at the stumps, clipped through square leg
shortish on middle and leg, tucked to Netravalkar at short fine
Williamson-esque drive to cover. Three-quarter length on fifth, no movement off the pitch whatsoever. Middled it while playing on the up
steps out to whip it up and over but can't get bat to it, the ball deflects off the pad into the leg side as they scamper a leg bye
Change of pace? Yeah, not a bad ploy. It's on a length and at the stumps, clipped to deep square leg
backs away and chops it wide of cover
Haris kept it tight but can't finish the over off. Gous beats Shadab, at point, with a lovely square drive. It's on the up again and off the middle again
no timing whatsoever on that as he pulls that towards deep midwicket
sees Jasdeep drop short and Shadab gets inside the line slightly and uses the pace to pull him high and handsome over long leg.
Down leg. Fullish ball goes past the attempted sweep. Keeper manages to stop it Backs away and slaps the length ball around leg, through cover

make that two-in-two!  This is banged in short again, Shadab imperious on the pull as he clears the ropes at deep square. It was almost as if he was expecting it.  Sashayed down the pitch and absolutely clubbed it.

Tom Moody says Shadab has to be brave, 'toss it up'. Shadab does and gets pumped downtown. Works against him this time. Was too full and Gous' bat swing was clean. His style really does resemble Williamson, effortless...
spears in a length ball wide outside off as he sees the batter move around the crease. slashed away to deep point
Yorker is darted and jammed back to the bowler
takes him on with the pull but it's mistimed down to long leg
Tossed up, full and at the stumps. Drilled to long-on
onto the pads, flicked away to deep backward square leg
Length on leg, clipped to deep square leg. Went back in the crease and got inside the line this time

whips it from outside off and picks the gap at deep backward square. Loaded with risk, but once he got bat on it, that was headed just one way. Will take some pressure off Babar as Pakistan are finally on the move.  Is this the over that turns the tide for Pakistan?
Keeps a bit low but managed easily. Gous goes back and clips it to midwicket
ohh, tight line from Naseem! He bowls on a length around fifth stump, and gets it to shape back in to finish closer to off, as Gous lets it go
full and angling into leg. Clipped off his pads to short fine leg's right
pulled to deep square leg! Naseem bowls it short, and gets it to climb to waits height around off. Gous plants his front foot forward, and clubs it to deep midwicket's right
full again, and this is on middle and off. Pushed to cover with the full face of the bat
much fuller length, and a slower ball too on off. Driven to mid-off
launched over the bowler's head! He skips down the pitch, and converts this into a fullish ball on the stumps to push the momentum further
backs away, and looks to slash at this length ball on the stumps, but gets it off the bottom edge back behind the bowler
nudges this length ball on middle aerially to long-on
punches at this length ball on off, and bags another single to deep point
backs away, and Kenjige goes on the shorter side of a length on middle. Punched to deep point

a slower-ball bouncer, but wide called. Naseem banged it on a good length around off, and got it to angle in and jump off the surface. Gous let it go swats at this length around off, and the ball drops well short of the long-on fielder running forward
fullish ball angling into middle and of, and whipped to deep midwicket
flung away over the bowler's head! He advanced down the track, and reached out at this length ball which was wide of off, before ramming it back down the ground
length ball outside off, and punched to long-off
stands after getting across, and the ball is fired quick and full on middle. Clipped wide of long-on
ohh, well bowled! He saw Monank make room, and tossed it up to bowl fullish and just outside off. Monank went pushing, but missed
slogged to deep square leg! He goes low to swipe at this full delivery angling into middle and off, and heaves it away for four more

Rauf, placed at long-off, runs and tumbles to his left to pull the ball back. And replays show his hand has touched the rope. The ball was on a length outside off, and Monank punched that hard through extra cover to raise the fifty stand
very full and flat, and just outside off. Squeezed out towards point for a hurried single
swatted over cover again! He backed away, and launched at this length ball on the stumps, having given himself the room to attack
full and on off. Driven to deep point
again gives himself room, as Iftikhar bowls fullish on leg. Chipped towards long-on

thumped just over the long-on fielder! The man on the boundary moved to his left and leapt, but the ball barely beat his hands. Shadab got a low full toss angling into middle and off, as he went deep in the crease to thrash it back
bowls full and straight, and it is driven back to the bowler
again steps out, and tucks this length ball on the stumps to long-on off the inside half of the bat
ohh, Monank skips down the pitch looking to loft, but is beaten. It was bowled on a length, and was angling across from over the wicket, and finished around fifth stump
makes room, and Kenjige goes on the shorter side of a length outside leg. Clipped towards deep midwicket, and they pinch two
swatted over mid-off! Short of a length from Afridi, and again the ball was moving away towards off. But he rode the bounce and bashed it away from the higher side of the bat
on a length on the stumps, and nudged to deep midwicket for two more rapid runs

cleanly lofted down the ground! That is also Monank's fifty! The length was much fuller from Afridi this time, as he bowled fullish and on off. Monank planted his front foot forward, and went through the line

good catch at short fine leg! The break takes Shadab's momentum away. Netravalkar placed on the edge of the circle jumps slightly to his right, and grabs the ball. Kenjige angled this length ball into Shadab, who had backed away early. The ball finished a few stumps outside leg, and Shadab ended up swinging it straight to the fielder
yorker length, and angling across towards off. Jammed back to the bowler's left

given out first ball! Azam has a chat with Babar... and reviews. Kenjige bowled on a length on middle, and the ball seemed to have skidded through to middle and leg. Aza went pushing at it with a closed face of the bat, and missed as he was beaten on the inside edge. Replays show no bat involved, and it is umpire's call on hitting the top of leg stump. Kenjige on a hat-trick
again bowls on a very full length, and in the channel outside off. Monank looks to slash, but is beaten
full and slow on middle and off, and defended down
very full, and angling into off at 141kph. Squeezed back to Afridi's right this time
short of a length, and wide of off. Slapped to deep backward point, with Iftikhar sending Babar back after an attempted second

gone, bowled him! Gous is beaten by pace. Rauf angled this in, and bowled on a length around fifth stump. Gous was deep in the crease, and looked to chop at this ball, which shaped in slightly. It also hinted to stay a little low, and found the gap between bat and pad to hit off stump
on the shorter side of a length on off, and tapped down off the inside edge. The ball rolls past the stumps for a single
fuller side of a length on off at 136kpj, and shaping in. Tucked down with his bottom hand off
ah, good pace at 135kph, and shortish length in the channel outside off. Babar slashes off the top edge towards a straightish deep third

ohh, this is three bonus runs for USA! Rauf switches his length to much fuller, but slides this ball down the leg side. Jones wanted to flick but missed, and Rizwan dived to his left and got a glove too. But the ball still rolled away on a length around sixth stump, and slashed on the bounce to point
well played, and well fielded. The man at deep third runs and slides to his right to keep it to a single, as Iftikhar dabs this shortish ball outside off to play pretty late
and again he bowls on a tight line, hardly giving Jones any room. On a length and slanting in to finish just outside off, as Jones chops to point again
good bounce off a short length around seventh stump. Flashed to deep point
ahh, some luck for USA! He went pushing tentatively at this good-length ball bouncing nicely outside off, but the ball went past the stumps and the keeper

outside edge... but four! The keeper dived to his right, but the ball was too far away from him. Ali Khan went much fuller this time, with the line being around sixth stump. Iftikhar went driving, but got an outside edge rolling away for four
ohh, beaten outside off! He goes flashing at this length ball which is wide of off, but doesn't get bat on ball
full ball angling into leg, and hits his pad as he looks to clip

tickled to the keeper! This is turning around already. Amir bowled an offcutter on the shorter side of a length around middle and off. The ball moved away, and Monank skipped down the pitch to try and slash. There was a faint outside edge off the bat, though, and Rizwan went low to complete the grab
on a length this time, and angling down to finish wide of leg. He looks to clip but misses again hits his front pad as he looks to whip off a length
ahh, well bowled! Rizwan and Amir think there might have been bat. Short of a length on middle, and angling across to finish just outside off, as Nitish poked and missed
pulled hard and flat to deep square leg! He finds the gap between two fielders in the deep, as Harmeet bowls short on the stumps for Babar to go deep in the crease to ram it
slower ball, and much fuller on middle. Dabbed towards point to get off the mark
punches this length ball outside off to long-off
extra bounce for Amir! He bowled on a good length, and the ball angled across to end pretty high and over off. Jones looked to ramp, but missed
much slower, and tossed up. This is full on off, and pushed back to the bowler
short of a length, and angling away to end outside off. Punched to deep backward point
ahh, again slows it down to bowl full and just outside off. Poked to point this time
length ball on middle at a change of pace. Pushed to deep point to keep ticking
Babar's strike rate passes a hundred! Very nicely lofted. He saw this shortish ball which was wide of off, and launched at it late to go over backward point
tossed up, and full on the stumps. Driven to long-off
on a length, and around sixth stump. Punched to point for a quick single
loopy and full on off, and chipped towards long-on

ahh, gently guided for four! He just about finds the gap between point and short third, with the former fielder tumbling to his left in vain. Iftikhar spotted this slower ball, which was on a length and slightly wide of off, and opened the face of the bat to pierce the gap
this full ball dips on leg, and Jones slog sweeps to fine leg for two. The man on the boundary was at a straightish fine leg
pushes at this length ball angling in, and gets a single towards cover
clubbed over deep square leg! The man on the boundary turns around and sees the ball flying over him. Full and tossed up from Shadab, as Jones gets down to slog sweep

loud and confident appeal for lbw, and given. But predictably, Babar reviews! Jasmeet bowled a length ball angling in and pitching just outside off. It angled in and hit Babar's front knee seemingly on middle, as he looked to clip but missed. Replays confirm there is no bat involved, and that the ball would have hit the leg stump. So Babar's struggle ends at just above-a-run-a-ball 44
ahh, this turns away late off a length on leg, and ends on middle to almost catch him by surprise. Dabbed down late
on the shorter side of a length on top of off, and dabbed to deep third
on a length on middle, and turning into leg. Punched to cover
on a length just outside off, and clipped to short fine leg
length delivery just outside off, and slashed hard towards the man at deep backward point
slashed behind point! Sees this length ball which is pretty wide of off, and flat-bats it between point and short third
shorter side of a length on middle and off, and he opens his stance up to dab it down on the pitch
change of pace, and Iftikhar is beaten! The length is much fuller, with the ball angling into off. Iftikhar looked to push, but missed
fullish length on middle and off, and heaved across the line to deep backward square leg
slower ball again, and full ball angling into off. Driven to long-off's left amid initial calls of two

ohh, the extra bounce means it is a wide. Naseem bowled a slower bouncer on off, and it jumped off the surface, as Jones looked to pull but missed very full and straight, and driven off the inside half of the bat to deep square
fullish length on off, as he bends down to tuck it back to the bowler
yorker on leg, but Nitish is standing deep in the crease, and with his front leg out of the way. Driven to long-on
ahh, he looked to swat-pull this short-of-a-length ball, but bottom edged it close to his legs
good over for Pakistan! Only six off this one. Naseem bowled another near-yorker on the stumps, as Jones swung to deep midwicket off the inside half of the bat
this yorker-length ball is angled across, and ends around sixth stump. Iftikhar slices this to deep third
superb ball! Fires in a yorker while angling it in, and bowls around sixth stump. Jones looked to slash, but missed
on a fullish length outside leg, as he looked to whip. But the ball hit his front pad outside leg

flung away over extra cover! Jones hit that almost as if he expected that low full toss - or rather that missed yorker. He is deep in the crease, and has his front leg out of the way, as he lofts that over the in-field
heaved to deep midwicket! A full toss landing at a comfortable shin height on middle, and he swings across the line with his front leg out of the way

ahh, a run-out chance at the striker's end! And the square-leg umpire asks his TV colleague to check. Afridi and Pakistan don't look all that bothered, though. And replays show Nitish is well in, before Afridi hits the stumps at the striker's end. He bowled a yorker on leg, as Jones jammed it down, and the two batters took off
length ball just outside off at rapid pace, and drilled to long-off
another dot ball for Nitish! This is angled in at a near yorker length, and lands just outside off. It moves away after pitching and landing on the seam, as Nitish looked to loft but missed
another yorker just outside off. Jammed to deep backward point
low full toss angling into middle and off, and chipped towards deep point
an inswinging yorker o off, and driven back to the bowler's left
ahh, he gets across early, and Afridi bowls a low full toss on middle and off. Jones looks to scoop, but gets it off the toe end of the bat
bowls on a fullish length, and at a change of pace on a wide line outside off. Flung away towards long-on with his bottom hand off

ohh, an animated appeal for lbw... and it is given out! But Iftikhar reviews! It was a slower ball which was dipping rather sharply. It hit Iftikhar's front pad seemingly on leg, as he looked to swipe this to the on side. He was standing deep in the crease, and was beaten by the change of pace. Replays show it would have landed right on the base on middle and leg stump, and of course, hit them too. So Pakistan lose Iftikhar right when it mattered most

loud and confident appeal for lbw, but not given. That seemed to have struck outside leg, though. But Babar reviews! Amir fired a dipping yorker, and indeed the first replay confirms that Nitish was struck outside leg, as he looked to whip this after opening his stance up. But he was beaten on the inside edge. There's no bat involved, with the ball trickling way off his pads towards the off side
full on off, and driven towards extra cover for a quick single
ahh, superb bowling! He angles this across, and lands a yorker on middle. Squeezed back to the bowler

hoicked wide of long-on! Memories of all those runs Afridi got against India at MCG in 2022. This time he is deep in the crease, and slightly across the stumps. He gets a full toss outside off, and dumps it into the crowd for six
another very full ball on the stumps, and jammed to long-on
on a length, and wide of off. Again Afridi is across the stumps, and swats it to long-on
shapes to scoop, but Amir bowls on a length, and wide of off while angling it across. Nitish is beaten eventually, and it is another dot ball for USA
another full toss, but this is pretty low. It angles across and ends outside off, and is heaved wide of long-on

great bowling, and great fielding! Iftikhar, the man at long-on, runs and rushes to his left to pull the ball back last moment to keep it to three - or so it seems. Yup, it is confirmed as three. Amir launched another yorker on off, but this time Nitish managed to drill it back down the ground. It was timed well, only for Iftikhar to interfere and stop a run
ohh, this is ballooned... but lands in the gap halfway towards deep point! It was a fullish length a bit wide of off, as Afridi looked to slice it but ended up sending it straight up in the sky

ahh, a bouncer at 144kph! Ali Khan bangs it hard on a back of a length around off, and the ball zooms up, with Afridi looking to pull but missing. There is a throw from the keeper towards the bowler, who missed it, and the batters ran two. But this is called dead ball!
bowls a yorker on middle and leg, and Nitish swings towards midwicket off the inside half of the bat
short of a length again, and missed
dropped by Afridi! He was at mid-off, and tumbled to his right to try and catch it. Rauf bowled quite full on off, as Jones lofted down through the line
a yorker on off, and jammed to point. Superb execution from Ali Khan!
slower ball, and a dipping low full toss on off. Sliced to deep point
fullish ball angling across and ending outside off. Hoicked to long-on on the bounce
hoicked over wide long-on! Jones keeps USA's hopes alive with a timely six! Rauf angled this in, and ended up bowling a full toss which landed on leg. Whack it went for six!

another bouncer, and this is called wide. Afridi looked to pull but missed, and the ball was too high deposited deep into the crowd! On a length, and angling into middle and off. Afridi presents the full face of the bat in dumping it nearly out of the ground
ohh, this is another yorker on the stumps, which is squeezed back to long-on
ahh, well bowled! A yorker swinging in at 140kph into middle, and helicoptered to long-on with his front leg out of the way

this goes into a Super Over! Lofted over mid-off like a hero, and the game is tied! This will be the second Super Over of the tournament already, as USA keep their hopes of an upset alive. This was lofted beautifully under pressure, with Nitish making room and standing outside leg. Rauf went for a yorker, but it ended up as a low full toss. He chipped it nicely over mid-off, leaving Babar with a sour face
Full, swinging in... not out. Almost the perfect start, but not enough swing to bring the ball into the stumps. Great start from Wheal to the left-hander
back of a length, Munsey hops into line on off stump and survives one ball more than he managed in that aforementioned contest!
Full, across the left-hander, driven to mid off. This has been a great start for Wheal
pushed a touch fuller, tidy shape away from the left-hander, left alone
And now it's a brilliant start! Shorter length, into the pitch - which slows it down a touch - and Kotze cloths a pull shot straight to midwicket
full toss, Munsey is a touch surprised and pokes it back politely as it swings away outside his eyeline
Full, on the money again, into the pads of this left-hander. Pitched outside leg stump, though

overcooked, and swings away down the leg side! Munsey gave it the charge, never got close, but nor did the keeper! big outswinger, and overcooked in the other direction now. Six runs from zero balls might have been wide again, but instead Munsey meets it on the charge and drives wristily to short cover, who dives well
Edged... and beyond first slip! Right through where second would have been. Scotland do have a gully, but no second means Namibia are off the mark with a boundary
better length, but dug out well on the crease, meeting the outswing with a full face back past the bowler

Shorter, skiddier, into the hip. Frylinck tries to work around the corner but ends up wearing it for a leg bye.... and it's a no ball! Poor end of a brilliant over from Wheal. Free hit incoming... Full, lifted down the ground... but no real connection as it plugs and mid on comes around to field
full toss, swinging onto the pads, nudged to square leg. Trumpelmann started well but seemed to lose faith in his footing after the sawdust break
Bit of swing, bit of grip off the pitch as Currie runs his fingers down one side, worked into the leg side
tight lines on the full length, pushed back down the pitch
More of that shape, away to the left-hander - straightening, really, after angling down, defended back to the bowler on about middle and off
stabbed with high hands, off the off-stump line, down to deep third
round the wicket to the left-hander, beaten off the pitch, on a fourth-stump line
Driven on the up.... just short of cover. Berrington was there diving forward, and it landed just half a foot in front of him at extra cover
has a waft outside off, and sounded like a snick as the ball went by. No-one is moved though, as the keeper gathers
Angled in, curving away, taken well by Cross up to the stumps as Frylinck wafts
full length, bending in at off stump, punched into the covers
Makes room on the leg side, but Currie follows Davin who ends up settling for a pat to midwicket
pace off, tight line in at the stumps, nudged back down the pitch and that could have been curtains had Wiese's long reach managed to gather, as they set off rather early for the single. It couldn't
On the money again, into middle stump from over the wicket, full, pushed out to mid on
flapped out to point for another single

Short, lifts off a length and flies over the keeper! Thankfully, it's not all the way to the boundary, allowing first slip to collect. Wided by the umpire and rightly so Angled into the right-hander, just full of a good length, pushed to the side of midwicket
drags his length back and zags a tight inswinger back into Jones' stance. Comes down the wicket and though to the keeper
Driven handsomely but straight to mid on
slower delivery, a big wind-up through the slap into the on-side, plugs safely in the deep

Makes room, drives on the up through cover! Not quite timed and the fielders almost chased that down, but some necessary intent from Frylinck, even if he only makes contact with the outside half of his bat

shaping past the legs, a dive from the keeper cuts off a second set of five wides he's lost his line a bit at the moment, down the leg-side once more better line, offcutter, stopping in the pitch as Munsey pushes through the off-stump line to mid-on
Into the hip, worked nicely to the fielder in the deep at midwicket
round the wicket, sharp bouncer fizzes past a flashy pull
Punched wide enough of mid on to get the fielder scampering to his left  to field
two steps down the pitch and slammed heartily up and over mid-off! Good use of the feet from Jones, sensing Trumpelmann's lack of certainty and climbing down the pitch to meet his in-between length
Lovely shape away from the left-hander once more, Frylinck goes for a booming drive and misses completely
good line and length, through to the keeper, past the outside edge

Dragged on! Frylinck tries to hack across the line in a bid to, well, ignore the swing, but ends up under-edging onto his stumps! Awful shot, but a deserved dismissal for Currie. Scotland are up and about!
shuffles to the pitch, cracks a firm drive into the gap in the covers
Driven powerfully... brilliantly stopped by mid off, diving to his left to save three
shaping onto the hips, flicked to backward square. It's a low-octane powerplay so far. Namibia are off-colour but Scotland choosing not to rush
Bit of width, length delivery, gorgeously driven down to the third boundary! Davin's playing this off the back foot and opens the face at the very last minute to get down to the fence
on the legs, clipped to the on-side for another single
Same length but straighter this time defended into the pitch

driven in the air to mid-off! Lungameni's introduction does the trick as Wiese's bucket hands serve him well, diving forward. Looking to launch the wide line up and over the off-side, but he didn't quite get to the pitch and couldn't find the elevation

Slapped in the air... and dropped by Chris Sole diving full stretch to his right at mid on! Difficult, difficult chance as yet another Namibia batter duffs a pull shot. Would have been a catch to rival the one we saw in USA-Pakistan earlier.
swinging past the legs for a gentle welcome to the wicket better line to finish, outside off and shaping away. Left alone
Thick, thick edge... away for four! Unconvincing, but they all count, as the ball races away fine of third
lovely straight-lined drive, punched with power back past the stumps, but mopped up at long-on
Back to back boundaries - and this one is skewed down inside third again! This one is fuller, almost yorker length from Sole, and Davin digs it out with the end of his bat and gets four more
width outside off, but that kicks wickedly off the seam as McMullen leaps into a drive and is startled for his sins
Straighter, dragged back length, pushed to mid on
fuller length, tighter line, dabbed back down the pitch
Carved away for four! Finally, an intentional boundary as Sole offers width and David frees his arms, opening the face upon contact, and hoists over point
onto the front foot once more, fenced back to the bowler. The lack of width is keeping the batters honest at the moment
Slashed hard again... and into the hands of Currie at deep third! It's the best connection of the lot. Silly game, this
inside-edge, but doesn't carry Slower ball, sticks in the pitch and leaps at the splice, as McMullen is confounded
Big appeal as Sole angles one into the pads of Kruger from wide of the crease... are they going to review it? Nope, they decide not to. An eventful over!
opens the face, guided to backward point, nearly a run-out as Lungameni pounces and fires in a return. Wiese is strangling what little momentum Scotland had
Bang! Erasmus immediately makes room and slap-shots a full delivery from around the wicket over wide long off! Not a clean connection, but powerful enough
round the wicket, in the slot outside off, Jones slams a full-blooded swing back through the line Down the ground through long-on
More room, Watt follows and Erasmus goes with the angle and heaves to midwicket!!
forward, to the in-between length, presses the drive into the covers
Darted in, clamped down on bat and pad, shooting out behind point
onto the front foot, fizzes through point off a thick leading edge. And they hustle back for three, with the ball in no-man's land
Big appeal as Erasmus moves across to sweep. It looks like Watt has struck him in front... Berrington calls for a review... nope, great call from Umpire Menon - there was glove
round the wicket, an ugly swipe across the line, and an under-edge past the stumps! That's not a pretty shot, the ball was both too full and too straight for the pull. But it's runs...
Darted down the leg side, just past leg stump, taken by the keeper but not cleanly
well, that's more like it! Down the pitch, not entirely to the pitch, but his eyes and his commitment did the rest, rifling his hands up through the ball, high over long-off!
Length outside off, cut with an open face but straight to backward point
full, and on the pads, Jones can't connect on his swing to leg. 18 off the over
round the wicket, looped onto a good length, tapped into the off-side
Sharp, into the hip, worked around the corner
leg-stump line, angled in from round the wicket and straightening. Nudged to leg

Off cutter, from deep in the hand of Sole, Erasmus walks forward and works it out to deep square leg... and the sirens are going! No ball! Wide of the crease, wide yorker, Erasmus can't jam down on it and it goes through to Cross. Great delivery
sliding down the leg side, into the hip, tucked behind square
Length this time, Erasmus offers the face to deliberately edge down to third
on the back foot, flogged firmly out to mid-off
Kruger steps to leg, Sole sends it down wide of off stump off a length to keep it out of his reach
good line, tight to middle stump, back and across to push back to the bowler
Length again, this one scuttling into the batter off the pitch. Kruger guides from close to his body down to third
guided out to the deep off the back foot, but just another single
Wide, played down to third once more
Short, maybe even a googly, follows Erasmus who forces the ball down to long on
round the wicket, back of a length outside off, cracked into the off-side
Another googly, Kruger tries to dab it off the pitch down to third but doesn't make very good connection
on the back foot, meeting the restrictive leg-stump line, nudged to the on-side

Good length, swung down on the charge and excellently taken by Michael Jones out at wide long on! As casual as you like, couple of strides towards the boundary before taking it over his shoulder and ensuring his momentum did not taken him anywhere near the sponge.

driven but it's too tight to the body! Snicked to the keeper! Crafty work from the offspinner, sliding it across Jones' bows with the arm-ball, he was committed to the stroke and it's a sharp take from Green too. Big wicket, Scotland's only source of momentum is gone
Short again, skips up, pulled into the leg side
nudged off the pads, to the leg side, up comes the 50
Googly has Greaves exclaiming thinking Erasmus is late on getting bat on that. Not so, as he pockets two away to midwicket
takes an age to reach the batter, that was bowled from behind the umpire's standing position, but Berrington wasn't fooled, and cracked a firm sweep through square leg
Played out to long off... will they come back for two? They do, as the fielder scampers around to cut off a potential boundary
fumble at point allows a thick edge to fly along the turf for more runs. A loose end to a good over
round the wicket, leaning forward and poked to point
Over the wicket to the left-hander, full length, played off the pitch and away into midwicket for a single
on the back foot, and lumped back down the ground McMullen was waiting for that, weight anchored in the crease and applying the muscle
Delivered almost level with the umpire, cut low and beyond backward point for four!
Faster, into the pitch, off the inside edge as Erasmus presses forward, bagging a single into square leg
Wider, sharper into the pitch, Green gets himself in a tangle as he tries to pull around the corner
Oops, we've lost our feed for the moment. Bear with us
Flighted this time, worked with the spin down to long on
Fullish ball darted around off, inside edge off the full-faced bat takes it to the left of the keeper
Wide of the crease, pass on, Erasmus waits in his crease and pats it on the head to long on
Bit of turn off a length, pitching on about middle and leg, worked out into the leg side
opens the face on the back foot, stabbed to point, a terrible run and a very poor piece of fielding too
Flighted, met on the full by Green, who flicks it out to deep midwicket along the floor
width outside off, has a crack with flat feet, can't connect
Short, sits up, slapped through point! It's a favoured area for Erasmus and he punches his ticket once more

swings into a sweep, down the leg side, Erasmus is a bit miffed, might have been glove on that skids through, Green fumbles then whips off the bails anyway. He seems optimistic. The original was a clear stumping chance, but is McMullen's foot back down by the time of the second attempt? I don't think he's managed to get his studs down! He's got to go, and that is a dreadfully dozy piece of batting, reminiscent of Gooch after a plate of dodgy prawns in 1992-93!
Straight, hammered into the gap on the leg side... and brilliant stopped by Leask, who skids along the turf to save two
skids down the leg side shapes for a sweep, then opens the face to meet the wider line with a dab down to deep third

Flighted, crunched through the covers... and brilliantly saved by cover by Berrington! In fact, there'll be a slightly delay after the ball ricocheted off the skipper's hand and into his face! Physios on...
squared up on a leg-stump line, nudged to the on-side
Big drag down, powerfully struck by Green but one bounce straight to deep midwicket. Got away with that one
firm push back down the pitch. Scotland are struggling to get anything going here, as the umpires call for drinks
round the wicket, back of a length, slugged into the leg-side with a cramped pull to midwicket
Pushed out into the vacant greet as Currie returns
on the back foot, meeting the angle into the pads with a nudge to the on-side
Scuttles off a length, well taken by Cross as he was obscured by Erasmus' attempt low pull
open face, guided to point
Cut out to deep point, back for two
tossed up, good chance of pace, dipping on a good length and tapped to cover
Driven down to wide long off
firmly forward to the good-length ball, another push to cover
Big lift off a length! Big enough for Cross to jump to collect and wear that one on the thumb. He's not happy about it

wild sweep, that's plumb! The pressure tells on Cross, after a constrictive over, there's a discussion about a review but it would have been futile. Wicket to wicket line, straightens past a hard whirl of bat, and stone dead
Length, short, punched out to cover where Berrington dives to collect and throw, but not before the single is secured
on the legs, and tapped to the on-side
Bit of turn off a length from around the wicket, duffed out into the covers
lines up another sweep, a bit of glove prevents another raucous lbw appeal
Shorter, into the pitch, straightens and punched down to long on
fraction of width, lifted up and over gully, and only just! Open face and gets away with it
Leask sticks around the wicket to the right-hander... and Erasmus hits this in the air down to wide long off... but well short
kneels into another sweep, timed well but to backward square
Attempted reverse misses and Cross does brilliantly to gather cleanly given all the movement in front of him
firmly onto the front foot, to meet the round-the-wicket line. Back to the bowler
Big appeal as a full dart pins Green as he attempts a slog sweep. Are they going to review it? Nope... sliding down
a fraction of room outside off, Leask rocks back well to increase his room to swing the arms, and picks off two to deep cover
Leask can't get out the over as a short deliver is clobbered back over the bowler's head for four!
Worked away as Watt over pitches, followed by good running from these two
back of a length, tight line, hops into line, tapped to the off side
Short ball worked out to deep square leg for one. Watt deliveried that from the umpire's toes! Ludicrous human. Hasn't got his notes out just yet
bowled into the pitch, outside off, cracked hard to the leg-side but the sweeper is well positioned
Hung wide, fuller, dabbed down but straight to third who is up in the circle
on the back foot, flapped into the covers, a misfield allows a slight release of pressure
Flatter, out wide and Erasmus uses the pace to profit through point once more!
smashed hard off the back foot, but the cover sweeper denies any value for the shot
Straighter and flatter this time, defended
hoisted mightily over midwicket! Down on one knee, sweeping hard up into the width outside off, hung in the air for an age, but plopped into the front row, just beyond anyone's reach
Erasmus tries to bang one through point again but the pace is off this time and he can only find backward point
back-to-back boundaries to get Scotland moving! Punched firmly through the line, up and over the covers. A 16-run over is more the ticket for this chase
round the wicket, full and leg-sided, flashed into the on-side
Sits up and turns off a length, cut out to deep midwicket
forcefully lifted off the pads, up through midwicket to be mopped up in the deep
Erasmus gives himself room on the leg side so Leask - around the wicket - deliveries this just outside leg stump. Powered down the ground by to wide long off
Massive! The hundred comes up in style! A rare glimmer of width outside off, and Leask latches onto it with a mighty mash high over midwicket! It's lodged on the roof of the groundsman's shed!
Attempted big drive down the ground, thick inside edge out to square leg. That's the Namibian' century
forward, and punched down the ground for one more
Slog-swept over wide long on! Biggest part of the boundary as well, and that's Erasmus' 50 from 30 deliveries!
flashed back through the line, the bowler gathers

50 and out! That's an excellent comeback from Leask, pulling his length back and asking Erasmus to come at him. The opposition skipper duly obligies and finds nothing but air, leaving Cross to complete the dismissal by removing the bails. A bit of rush of blood to the head, but a fine innings comes to an end
very full length, driven into the off side. Scotland add another over of good progress to their tally
Into the pads, tucked around the corner - no bat, mind - and Wiese keeps the strike
stump-to-stump line once more, nudged away for the single
Full of a good length, into off stump, driven off a thick outside edge to deep point
on the back foot, waiting on the ball as it straightens from round the wicket, tapped to the on-side
Short and slapped cross-batted through cover, but no timing whatsoever. Green has to settle for the single
tight line again, eased back past the bowler on the front foot
Wide of the crease, attempted yorker ends up as a low full toss but only punched out to deep cover
on the back foot, jabbed to the on-side, no width to work with
Another low full toss, this one brilliantly saved by Berrington at cover. The shiner under his right eye is coming on nicely
swept, but well controlled, getting the front leg outside off as a precaution and watching the ball into a firm slap to midwicket

Slower ball out the side of the hand... well, well wide. Bowl it again, Chris Banged in short, well-directed, Green ducks into a pull and makes a decent connection but again finds the fielder out at deep square leg
eased off the pads to finish Scholtz's spell. It's been a humdinger. But is it enough?
Another attempted yorker turns into a full toss, albeit pace off, which is perhaps why Wiese holds back and settles for a single out to deep midwicket

How has that missed the stumps?! It's a short ball that sits up and, really, Wiese should smash that for six to the leg side. A huge swing misses and somehow his middle stump remains standing. Single taken as Cross misfields
round the wicket, hint of width, slapped out to deep point
Worked down the ground as Green plays this off the pitch
round the wicket again, angled into the pads, Leask swings into a big hack to leg, misses, but it's going over the stumps
Wiese tries and fails to pierece the off side
angled into the bat, a wristy chop to point. A valuable dot
Shot of the day! Full, allowing Wiese to press into a lofted straight drive that flies high and true into the stands!
pace off, a hint of width, cut at the top of the bounce to deep point
Flatter, wider, cut out into the off side
violent crack across the line! Pace off, and picked well by the batter, but it took a smart tumbling stop at deep midwicket to cut that off
Googly? Maybe a little bit of one, skips off a length through to the keeper as Green duffs yet another shot across the line. He's struggling out there
another slower ball, chopped into the covers. Tidy enough from Trumpelmann, to take Namibia's challenge deep
very full, swinging into the pads, Wiese is up for the lbw, as the ball deflects through short third. An enthusiastic appeal, but missing leg
Wide, just short of a full length, driven edgily out to point
mashed into the stands! A good take in the crowd at midwicket, as Leask takes no half-measures against the dangerman! A touch of width, and clobbered to bring up the fifty stand from 32 balls
Green finally gets one out of the screws! Boy he needed that... swings away a slog sweep into the Greenidge and Haynes stand as Watt spears one into leg stump
smashed into the off side for the single
Lovely shape, flighted outside off, Green strikes this cleanly but out to deep midwicket on the bounce
in the slot, on the pads, Berrington heaves across the line and through the gap! Bissects two leg-side boundary riders to take Scotland ever closer
Fuller, on about off stump, open-faced drive into the covers but there's a man there lurking to prevent the single
drops all the pace off, outside off, cuffed to cover
Watt holds this one back, Wiese goes to charge and reacts to the lack of pace with a push to midwicket for a single
full toss, deposited high over deep midwicket! That might just have been the over. 18 runs pour from it, almost half the previous requirement. Scotland need 21 from 18 now
Now Green is ticking... Watt hangs the ball outside off, so Green reverses his hands and flips him over third (up in the circle) for just his second boundary
Was that a knuckle ball to start? Grips off the pitch as Wiese tries to use the pace to drive down the ground. Skewed to mid on
hits his length but Berrington gets away with it! Hard length from round the wicket, driven on the up into the covers, and loops over the in-field
Test match length outside off from over the wicket, driven out to deep cover off the back foot
Leask is off the leash! Seizes on the slower ball, and piledrives it 101 metres, into the prevailing wind, over wide long-on!
Width, full outside off and Wiese goes for the big shot... and loops off the outside edge down to Watt at third! That's a big, big wicket heading into the final throes of this innings
the wheels are coming off now! Another big wind-up, but Trumpelmann has overstepped as well free hit ... full length, attempts a cutesy sweep/ramp, loops behind square on the leg side
Short, edged off the underside and into the leg side by Trumpelmann
steps into the length, lumped back over the bowler's head, without much timing, but the placement is good enough for the single
Width, across the left-hander, who looks to clear mid off with some footwork down the pitch and to the legside... but straight to the fielder! Outstanding over from Wheal.

holed out to long-on! Leask climbed into another mighty wipe down the ground, but this time the pace off, allied to a touch of width, leaves him reaching a touch too much. Wiese stoops low to gather, and ends a game-breaking knock

Another variation into the pitch, spits up at Smit who manages to get it away to square leg. The first single is comfortable enough for the pair to consider a sceond, but a tartan shirt is quick on the scene and puts them off
round the wicket, pace off on the yorker, clipped uppishly to the leg side. Scotland need only to hold their nerve now
Straights with a good length delivery on about middle and off, driven down the ground to long off
pace off, back of a length, lifted to the on-side
Scotland turning the screw at the death! It's a valiant attempt at a six to the leg side, but the wind holds it up and allows it to drop just inside sponge, into the hands of Wheal
leg-sided, a very delicate flick and the keeper does well. That was four all the way
Back of a length, Scholtz plays this with his weight back, dabbing into the covers and pinching a single
Berrington seals it in style! A muscular bosh across the line, seizing the width and pumping it hard and flat over wide long-on. Scotland march to the top of Group B!
Outside off, pace off, Smit tries to guide but ends up dead-batting the ball to cover
Sharper, skids on off a length, driven nicely but straight to cover
On the pads, slower again, Smit waits and wrists it away to the vacant square leg region
And Smit starts with a biggie! Pits the length ball, holds his shape and launches it over straight midwicket. Helped by the breeze, but it was a well-judged and well-executed shot
Short, no pace on it though and the pull shot skips away to deep square leg
Full, straight, just short of a yorker length and punched down the ground, beyond the grasp of Wheal
Similar delivery, dug out to long on. Comfortable single.... hold up, Smit wants two... and now he's decided against it and Wheal has the bails are off! The intention was sound, but that was poor
Into the pitch, off cutter, pulled to square leg and two scampered... and it's eventually confirmed as two as it looked like Scholtz' bat was jammed before it could break the line. But he's good
Short and slow again, hacked out to midwicket and they do get a couple. And now it has started raining as both sets of players make their way off the field. Hard rain, too, with the covers coming on.
Starts confidently does Balbirnie. Length ball angling across from the batter, who gets a good stride forward and drives but straight to cover-point
Slight bit of movement first up, not a lot. Also sort of a tennis ball bounce. The ball pitches on a good length and shapes away from Johnson who feels for it outside off.

Short and wide outside off, Balbirnie throws his hands at it but can't get a connection gets ample movement on the length ball right across Balbirnie, who chases the ball well outside off. Wide called WHAT A JAFFA! Similar to the Dhaliwal delivery from Little. Length ball that pitches on off and swerves right across Balnirnie's outside edge. Steep bounce for Sana
And he is away. Dragged down on his thigh pad and Johnson gets across, swivels and helps him over short fine leg for a four

Oh, he's completely lost his radar there. Looks like he was forcing the wide outswinger, ends up spraying it even past where the wide line is for Test matches Lovely drive to get off the mark from Balbirnie. Fuller in length outside off, he prods forward and drives crisply on the up and through cover. The sluggish outfield means he can only get three runs
Ah, hits him in the midriff. Was a back of a length ball that pitches on middle and shapes just a touch away from Johnson beating his outside off and hitting him
Very full, almost yorker length on middle. He pushes towards mid-on
Too straight on middle and leg, he gets across and ticks it the on-side
Length ball outside off, around the seventh stumps line. He punches towards cover-point
Sharp in-dipper but the line is on legstump. The ball strikes his pad and goes to the keeper's left, who does well. Dhaliwal will be filthy with himself to not get some bat on that
THUMPED! Half-volley outside off, he bends his back-knee and absolutely laces the square drive on the up through point. Top shot and that is not a great over from Sana to start off
On a length on middle and leg again, Dhaliwal glances it to short fine leg for a run.
Hard length to start off around off and middle, the ball hits high up on Balbirnie's blade as he pinches a quick run
Beats him first up. On a length veering across the batter well outside off, who reaches for it and is lucky to not get a bat on that
Ooh, the lifter almost gets rid of Stirling. Short of a good length just outside off, Stirling feels for it but the ball gets big on him and he is lucky to not get an edge on that

Huge, huge appeal for caught behind, but the umpire stays unmoved. Little is convinced, the keeper and slips not so much. Not out and no review taken. Was an absolute jaffa that pitched on middle and shaped away. Oh, hang on. Looks like he did get some glove on that through to the keeper. No wonder Little was sure.
Sprays the length ball well outside off, wide called On a length with a hint of movement away from Stirling outside off. He shoulders arms
Poor line down leg, called a wide Good length ball shaping away from Dhaliwal outside off who once again can't make a connection
Gets it on a length well outside off. Stirling reaches for it and opens the face of the blade to guide to deep third
Picks four now. Length ball down leg and these are easy pickings for Dhaliwal who gets across and works him past short fine leg
Back of a length 130kph on middle stump. Balbirnie stays back and defends
Low full toss outside off, he drives firmly but straight to mid-off
Short of a length ball that does not rise as much as Balbirnie was expecting it to. Was wide and he looks to go after it only to get a thickish edge to slip. The ball goes the fielder on the bounce
Fullish length again outside off, he drives to the right of mid-off and takes a run
Homes in on off stump as Stirling prods half-forward and pushes towards backward point
Length ball on off, he stays leg side of the ball and tips towards cover point looking for a quick run. Is sent back by Johnson
Good length ball just outside off, Stirling hacks it but straight to mid-on

And he's gone now. So he can't cash in on the reprieve from the earlier over. Short of a length ball outside off, he looks to carve it over point but does not get enough elevation and backward point takes a simple catch
Throws his bat at the fuller length ball outside off, but makes no connection. Sana has started this over well
On a length well outside off. Adair was looking for the inswinger but that started very wide. Pargat leaves it alone
Very well fielder by Kirton at backward point. Was a length ball outside off. He slashes at it hard and the ball travels quickly to Kirton who does well to his right
Back of a length ball around Pargat's waist on middle and leg stump. He shuffles across and works towards midwicket
