PUMPED but mid-off gets a hand to it and saves a run. Fuller just outside off. He absolutely tonks it to the right of mid-off, who does really well
Short of a length just around off stump. He pulls it down towards deep backward square leg for a run
Swing and a miss! Fuller in length and shaping away from Balbirnie, who throws his bat at it but only connects at thin air
Play and a miss! Good length ball shaping away late from Johnson outside off stump. He feels for it and is lucky to not get an edge on that
Length on off stump, he stays legside of the ball and pushes towards backward point for a quick run

Oh, miscommunication but short fine leg can't get the throw back in time. Was a length ball on middle and leg, he clips it to the right of short fine leg and sets off. But Johnson wasn't going anywhere.
Short and wide, Balbirnie is too early into his cut and all he can manage is an under-edge that goes to the keeper on the bounce
Fullish in length outside off, he squirts it down to deep third for a run
Banged in short outside off, he pulls to deep backward square leg's left for a couple of runs

Almost a chop back on and as it turns out, he gets four to his name. Was a fuller-length ball just outside off, Johnson has an uncertain feel at it, the ball catches his inside edge and goes perilously close to off stump. Short fine leg dives over the ball to concede a four
Good bowling this. Hard length ball on off stump that hits the splice of Balbirnie's bat and pops close to the bowler
Up and over! That's so much more authoritative. Good length ball angling across Johnson who punches it over covers for four more
Good length ball outside off, he opens the face of the bat and glides towards deep third for a run
On the fuller side again but on middle and leg and he effortlessly flicks it to deep backward square leg
Hard length again on middle and leg, he bunts it towards cover who sprints in quickly and prevents a run

Full and down leg, called a wide Sliced over cover point! Little gives Pargat a lot of width outside off and he cashes in by freeing his arms and just clearing cover point. The ball plugs into the outfield and they get three
Juicy full toss on the pads to start off but Pargat can't take full toll. Flicks it neatly but can't beat short fine leg
Flatter on middle and leg, he sweeps but straight to short fine leg
Length ball just outside off, punches towards cover
Huge appeal for lbw, but think he got some bottom edge on it. Was the quicker ball off the front of his hand. Balbirnie just about gets some bat on the sweep fine for two
Similar length ball outside off, he pushes towards backward point and there is some indecisiveness again with the running
Flatter outside off, pushed towards cover
Good delivery again. Length just outside off, he defends back towards the bowler
Another attempted sweep to the flatter ball on the stumps. He gets it fine past short fine leg for two more
On a length outside off, he pushes towards backward point and sets off only to be sent back
Pushed through on the stumps, he eases it to long on
Four dot balls and a wicket! Back of a length ball on the pads of Johnson, he heaves it away but straight to deep backward square leg.
Jumps down the track and belts the fuller length ball but straight to mid-off
Short and wide, he stands tall and cuts it past backward point for an impressive four
On a length outside off, he opens the face of the and guides to deep third
Another poor delivery from McCarthy . Length on his pads and Pargat clips it to the left of short fine leg
Big swing and a miss! Was that hard length again on the middle stump. He goes for a huge across-the-line swipe and makes no connection
Good length ball outside off, he tips it with an open face of the bat to the left of backward point for a run
Another play and a miss! Stirling is getting impatient. Back of a length ball outside off, he looks to force it through the offside but doesn't connect
On a length just around off stump, he defends

Stirling throws it away! This is excellent pressure applied from the Canada bowlers. Back of a length ball on the stumps. Stirling goes for the hard pull, gets a top edge that balloons straight up. The keeper gets across and takes a comfortable catch
On a length on leg stump again. He looks to work this fine, but can't bat on it. The ball catches his pad through to the keeper
Fuller in length on middle stump, he gets across and flicks to mid-on to get off the mark
Hard lengths again just on off, he stands tall and pushes towards backward point
Wayward delivery to end the powerplay. Full and way down leg, he glances it past short fine leg
On a length on middle and leg, he tips it the onside and sets off for a quick single
Fuller on middle, he pushes to long on
Hint of movement away from the batter, who squirts it off the outer half of his bat past backward point

As easy as they come and Canada are all over Ireland. Bowls this from the front of the hand on off stump. Balbirnie was looking to clip that away, gets a bit of a leading edge and Siddiqui takes the simplest of catches.
On a length just on off, he defends towards backward point

Oh, yes and no situation but the fielder dives over the ball. Fuller outside off, he pushes to the right of extra cover and sets off. Only Tucker wasn't going anywhere. But the captain can't collect cleanly.
Goes up and over, but does not time it as well. Was a length ball outside off, he jumps down and the bat turns in his head as he he goes over cover
Fuller on the stumps, pushed back to the bowler

Banged in short, but that was too short and too wide down leg Sliced high and Little has taken a lovely catch running to his right from deep third. Length ball outside off, with just a hint of away shape. Pargat looks to go over cover, but the bat turns in his hand again, and he ends up skying the ball. Little sprints across, settles underneath the ball and completes a good catch. That was a wobble seam delivery from Young.
Slower through the air, he eases it to long-on
Length ball angling across the batter, who shoulders arms.
A bit slower on middle and leg, Tector clips with soft hands towards long-on and some excellent running gets them two
Up in the air but the ball falls short of the incoming deep fine leg. Was a back of a length ball on his hips. He looks to pull, gets a top edge and is lucky the ball does not go to hand
A little short outside off, he stays back and ticks towards long on
Fuller on the stumps, he digs it to mid-off

A big, big dive to make it to his crease but is Tector home? Oh, that dive has saved him. Was very short and very wide, Tector gets an under-edge past short third. Gordon released the ball quickly and Tector had to really put the skates on to make it home
Fuller in length on middle and leg, he ticks it to the right of midwicket who does well to not concede a run
Another edge! The ball pitches on off and catches Tector's outside edge that flies past the keeper's right. He gets two more
That is a top shot! Length ball on middle stump. Bajwa extends his arms, straight down the ground and the ball goes over mid-on for four

And he gets his man now! What a big wicket this is for Canada and Ireland are in deep trouble now. This one went on straight with the arm pitching on off and going on to beat Tector and clipping the top of his off bail
Good length ball just outside off, he opens the face of the bat down to deep third
Flatter on off stump, he gives himself just a bit of room and punches towards deep point
That Caribbean flair out in full glory from Kirton. Good length ball on his hips, he gets across and whips it with authority and there is not much deep backward square can do
Angled in on middle and leg, he gets across and whisks it towards deep midwicket

Easy peasy! As nonchalant as it gets. Bit of a drag down on middle stump, Bajwa was looking to work it to the onside, gets a leading edge and Delany plucks a catch one-handed to his right with minimum of fuss. Bajwa can't quite believe what's happened.
Shimmies down the track and pushes towards long-on
Pushed through outside off, he pushes to cover
Tossed up generously outside off, 69kph, he pushes to long off
Tossed up on middle, he goes forward and takes it on the full to ease it to long on
Very slow through the air again outside off, he cuts it to point
Dragged down again on off, he ticks it to midwicket
Jumps down the track and pushes the quicker ball back to Siddiqui
On a length on the stumps, he gets across and works it towards deepmidwicket for a couple of runs
Darts this one in at 92.4kph on leg stump and almost gets a leading edge back towards the keeper
A touch slower and fuller outside off, he drives to deep cover
Flatter again on leg stump, Tucker stays back and flicks to deep midwicket for a run
Starts off with the fuller-length ball on the pads of Kirton who clips it to deep backward square leg

Big appeal for a catch at slip, but the umpire stays unmoved. The keeper is absolutely convinced. Length ball just on off, Tucker goes for a reverse, and on first glance looks like the ball has missed the bat and glove, hit the pad and popped to slip. Yep, no connection with bat or glove and Tucker survives
Length around off stump, he pushes towards backward point
Flatter on the stumps, he flicks to deep midwicket

Excellent fielding from Tector, but think Movva is safe. Indecision with the running again. Was a length ball outside off, he pushes to Tector's right at backward point, who throws down the stumps at the striker's end. Movva , however, was back
Gives himself a lot of room but the captain follows him and he can only punch to extra cover
Good lenngth ball outside off, Movva opens the face of the ball slightly past the keeper for a couple of runs
Slower good length ball on leg stump, he backs away again and cuts to extra cover's left who does really well
Back of a length ball on the stumps, he pulls to deep midwicket
Gets the sweep out to the length ball on off, gets a decent connection but deep backward square leg dives to his right and saves two runs
Back of a length ball on Kirton's hips, he glances it to the left of deep fine leg for a couple of runs

Oh, indecision with the running. Has Tucker run himself out? Looks like he has. Where was he running off to? Gives himself room to the length ball outside off and cuts to backward point. Sets off even with the ball in Kirton's hand. He fires in a good throw and Saad just about holds on to run Tucker out. This is slipping away quickly from Ireland.
angles this in, and bowls full on leg. It takes his pads as he looks to clip
tossed up, and dipping of a full length on off. He leans into a drive to long-off
full again, and slanting into middle and off. Pushed to cover
short of a length, and turning away towards off. Whipped towards deep backward square, and they pinch two hurriedly
short of a length, and slightly wide of off. Slashed to deep point away from his body
on a length, and flatter on off. Slashed to deep point
ohh, the extra bounce into play again! Short of a length from Heyliger, and just outside off, as Campher skips down the pitch after making room. He looks to hack, but is beaten
this is fullish and straight, and quicker too. Blocked towards cover

nicely taken at fine leg! Ireland unravelling here in pursuit of 138. Johnson placed at a straightish fine leg moved to his left, before diving forward to grab this low. Heyliger again went on a short of a length, almost cramping the batter for room this time. Campher still went ahead with the ball, and the extra bounce meant the ball took off from the top edge for a good catch by Johnson
skips down, and lofts this length ball just outside off over extra cover. The man at long-off gives the chase to his left
Heyliger continues to bowl on the shorter side, going just outside off this time. Delany shapes to play, before swaying out
length ball on off, and swatted to cover
short of a length on top of off, and punched to deep backward point
on a shortish length, and wide of off. Flashed to deep point
flashes at this short-of-a-length ball on fifth stump, and gets a single to a straightish deep third
on the fuller side of a length, and dipping on middle stump. Punched to cover
ahh, this will hurt! Some extra bounce off a length on middle, as Kirton is hit on his stomach off the inside edge, as he looked to half-clip it
much fuller, and angling into his pads. Clipped off the inside half of the bat towards square leg
tight line again. Short of a length bang on middle and off, and he can only dab it to point
fuller and straight, and driven to long-off from the full face of the bat

ahh, short of a length, and this takes off from middle stump. Kirton sways out of the way, and it is called wide on height on a good length on middle and off, and swatted towards mid-off from the higher side of the bat
ohh, this skids through off a fullish length on middle and off. Pushed hurriedly to point
another one which is on the shorter side of a length on middle, and it shapes in, as Movva dabs it towards short midwicket
fuller length on leg, and nudged towards deep midwicket
on a good length on middle and off, as Movva gets across and taps it down on the pitch
on the shorter side of a length, and angling into middle and off. Stabbed to deep third after staying leg side of the ball
on a length this time - bit fuller than the last one - as the ball lands on fifth stump. Movva attempts to loft, but is beaten
makes room and hints to skip down the pitch. The ball is shortish on middle and off, and is slammed to long-on

ahh, not entirely in control, but he does get a boundary! He went heaving at this length delivery and lost his bottom hand in the process, with the ball flying off the inside half of the bat over midwicket

tickled to the keeper! Somebody listen to the Canada players' jubilant voices on the field. Heyliger bowled on a length on fifth stump, angling the ball into the right-hander. Delany waited for the ball to come to him, and poked at it after it came back in. He played with a flat bat, and the top edge went to the keeper, who Movved to his right while going a bit low to pouch it
fuller length, and skidding through on off. Pushed to cover after bending a bit

on a length on middle and leg, and heading down. Left alone after getting across ahh, this is not called wide. Again Adair was across the crease, as Heyliger banged it on the shorter side while getting it to angle in, and the ball finishing outside leg after Adair left it alone
backs away, and drills through extra cover! The ball was on a fullish length just outside off, and Movva reached out to drive that wide of mid-off
fuller side of a length outside off, and tapped to point for a hurried single

ohh, just short of the point fielder rushing forward! Young hits back with a sharp short delivery which rises outside off, and ha Movva hopping in the crease. The ball takes off from his glove, and balloons towards point
shot of a length, and shaping in towards leg. Dabbed to point for another quick run
fullish ball on fourth stump, and pushed to mid-off for a quick single. Little, meanwhile, fell on the pitch after his run-up
he sees Dockrell make room, and angles it in full on middle and leg. Driven to long-off
on a length on middle and off, and punched towards deep point to keep ticking
full and dipping on middle. Clipped towards midwicket, with Adair sending Dockrell back after an attempted second
gets across, and whips this length ball around off aerially to deep square leg. The man on the boundary runs to his right to cut that off, but the batters pinch three hurriedly
full and flat on middle and leg, and swung down to long-on
makes room this time, and Little bangs it in short on middle and leg. Movva is forced into a tennis-batted swat, with the ball dribbling past the bowler's left
ohh, outside edge but there's no slip! He makes room and slashes at this length ball finishing outside off after turning away a bit. Two runs towards deep third
fuller side of a length on off, and tapped to cover. They rush for another single, with Movva even diving to complete the run
backs away, and the bowler follows by going on a length outside leg. Punched to point
outside edge to deep third, as Canada keep going for the shots. This time a fullish ball angles across towards off, as Movva drives after making some room
skips down, and Zafar tosses it up. The ball ends up becoming a low full toss, as Adair has a heave and gets the ball rolling off the bottom edge to beat short fine leg to his right
short of a length just outside off, and tapped to point after riding the bounce
on a length, and angling into middle. Punched towards long-on
hacks at this length ball in the channel outside off, and gets it off the top edge towards deep point, as he makes room to play

ohh, the ball nearly rolls on to the stumps! Heyliger bowled on a back of a length, getting it to angle in towards middle and leg. Adair looked to pull with a swivel, but had the ball dropping off the bottom edge
ohh, great effort by the point fielder! He dives to his left to stop at least one run, as Kirton punched at this length ball on off
ahh, some pace and bounce here! Short of a length outside off, and the extra bounce beats Adair, who looks to pull
ahh, extra bounce this time! Shorter side of a length all right, but the ball still zooms up from middle while angling away. Kirton pokes by opening the face of the bat, but is beaten
shorter side of a length on fifth stump, and hacked to deep backward point
zip off the surface again! The ball races through off a length after angling away towards fifth stump, as Kirton looks to swat but misses
the keeper misses, and that allows Ireland byes. Shortish length from Heyliger, with the ball angling in and finishing outside leg. Dockrell looked to pull after making room, but missed
short of a length on off, and he stabs to deep third after getting on top of the ball
again backs away, and swats at this short-of-a-length ball outside off towards mid-off
lofted down the ground! Kirton has been after the boundaries for a long time now, and this time he a bit of room at this length ball on the stumps, and launches over the bowler's head
thumped over the man at deep midwicket, who was a good few steps inside the field of play. Short ball from Siddiqui, as Dockrell rammed the pull for four
clipped off his pads! Canada pumping the runs now. On a length just outside leg from Young, and Kirton waits before gliding it to the keeper's right for four
on a length, and coming into middle and leg. Pushed off the inside half of the bat towards long-on
angles this in, and bowls a slower ball on a full length on middle and off. Whipped towards deep square to raise the fifty stand
makes room... and Siddiqui really slows it down to bowl on a length outside off. Slashed towards point
taps at this length ball straightening away towards sixth stump, and gets a single behind point
bashed over long-on! Dockrell shaking Canada up in this over. He saw this ball tossed up and dipping on a fullish length on the stumps, and went launching down the ground
ohh, cramped for room there! Short of a length, and angling in from around the wicket, as Young gets it to move in towards middle. Kirton looked to ramp, but had to sway out of the way in the end
ohh, really slow! Fuller side of a length on sixth stump, as Dockrell waited to push at it, before missing it

fired over mid-off! Kirton smashes 16 off the over. Young shifts his length to much fuller this time, but Kirton is deep in the crease, and waiting. The ball angles into the stumps, and Kirton, after backing away a bit, goes over the in field for six more

short of a length on leg, and slog swept to fine leg. Great effort by the man at wide-ish fine leg running and diving to his right. And in the end, he does manage to pull the ball back last moment to save two runs
yorker length on the stumps, and squeezed out towards mid-off
Adair gets across, and sees this length ball angling into off. He chips it towards square leg in the end
flays away over extra cover! He makes room and gets his front leg out of the way, lofting at this length ball outside off with the full face of the bat
ahh, well bowled! This yorker swings in to land just outside off, and Dockrell gets an inside edge towards short fine, as he looked to heave
gets across, and quickly tucks this fullish ball outside off towards midwicket. They rush back for two to keep the pressure on Ireland
swiped over short fine leg! That was sent up sailing in the air, before it went for a one-bounce four. Again Adair went across, and swung his bat at this length ball angling into middle and leg
short ball to keep Kirton on his toes. Little bangs it into the pitch just outside off, and has Kirton ducking
full toss dipping on middle and off. Hoicked to deep midwicket for two more
a nicely-executed yorker, which swings into middle and leg. Kirton has his front leg out of the way, but only manages to jam at it off the inside edge

swung over short fine leg! This went off the top half of the bat, but still cleared the rope. And the Ireland supporters are in full mood now. On a length, and angled into middle and leg from Sana, Adair went pulling and bagged six to keep pushing Ireland
swatted without any control, as Little bowls short while angling it across towards off. The ball takes off from the top half of the bat towards deep point
much fuller length, and just outside off. He looked to heave across the line, but got an inside edge
ahh, he sees Dockrell back away, and goes on a length on fifth stump. Dockrell reaches out to try and slash, but is beaten
length ball angling into off, and driven to mid-off, as they rush for the single. There is a throw at the non-striker's end, but it is wide even as Movva gives up
ohh, beats mid-off! Short of a length outside off, and Dockrell swatted back down the ground. The ball landed just short of the mid-off fielder moving to his right, and so he couldn't get his hand
fullish ball at a change of pace on off, and tapped towards point to keep ticking
shorter side of a length on the stumps, and pushed towards wide mid-off
change of pace, and on the shorter side of a length just outside off. The ball angles in, and his swatted towards deep third
ahh, again there is the extra bounce which beats the batter! On a length just outside off, and Adair went hacking only to get beaten

short of a length around off, and the ball takes off. Movva had shaped to pull but gave up seeing the extra bounce. Wide called ohh, tries the reverse scoop, but is hardly able to execute. The ball is fullish and outside off, and Movva gets an inside edge dribbling towards the leg side

great save by mid-off chasing it back! But Ireland still nab three, as Adair swatted this shortish ball outside off to launch it aerially and wide of mid-off. Dhaliwal there went back and pulled the ball back
angles this in, and lands a yorker on middle. Jammed towards midwicket with his front leg out of the way
on a length on middle and off, and pushed to cover
now he tries the scoop, but is beaten. He gets across the stumps early, and Adair bowls a slower ball on a length outside off
hacks at this short-of-a-length ball on the stumps, and gets it on the bounce to deep point
a high-ish full toss on middle, and swung away towards midwicket
slower ball, and on a length just outside off. He opens the face of the bat to push to point
yorker length angling into off, and dragged to long-on after making room
ahh, this is on the shorter side of a length, and angles across to finish wide of off. Kirton looks to slash, but is beaten

ohh, some luck going Ireland's way! Another high full toss angling in and ending outside off, as Adair swung his bat but got an outside edge which went past a diving short-third fielder, who moved to his left

taken at short fine leg! Almost a collision and mix-up between Balbirnie there, and the wicketkeeper. McCarthy banged in a sharp short ball, which rose considerably on middle and leg. Kirton jumped in the crease and took his eyes off, with the ball taking off from his gloves as he looked to raise his right hand up. Simple catch in the end, though
fires a yorker, which angles across to finish just outside off. Adair pushes at it, but gets an inside edge to the keeper
short of a length just outside off, and he looks to pull but he is beaten

four more for Adair, who keeps Ireland alive! He got across the stumps early, and Sana launched a yorker on leg stump. Adair went clipping, but replays show the ball went off the inside edge to beat the keeper diving to his left. Four more, and more Irish luck there

taken at long-on! McCarthy breaks Canada's momentum in the closing stages. Heyliger was standing outside leg, as McCarthy bowled on the shorter side of a length outside off. Heyliger went through with the free swing of the bat, but ended up pulling straight to the fielder on the boundary
low full toss angling across towards middle and off, and heaved to short fine leg
ahh, dot ball for Canada! Short of a length just outside off, and Adair went to pull but missed, with the extra bounce coming into play
ohh, bowls an inswinging yorker on leg. He squeezes it down towards mid-on

caught and bowled! Gordon comes back into the attack, and checks Ireland straightaway. He banged it in on the shorter side of a length once more, with the line being around sixth stump. Adair went ahead with the pull shot, but ended up ballooning the ball. Eventually, Gordon ended up very close to where the striker is, and took it with a reverse cup
bowls a slower ball on the fuller side of a length just outside off. Stabbed to point to get off the mark
shortish length, and pulled off the top edge towards square leg
ahh, well bowled! He spotted Movva making room, and went for a yorker which was wide of off. Movva let it go in the end
dot ball! On a length just outside off, and McCarthy's attempt to deposit it across the line doesn't pay off
a tennis-batted swat over extra cover! Short of a length from Adair, and just outside off, as Movva thrashes it over the in field by making room
this time they go for a bye! Good bounce off a length outside off, as McCarthy is beaten again after attempting a pull
sliced barely over mid-off. He opens the face of the bat at this full ball outside off - it seemed like a slower one too - and mistimed the loft
Canada win by 12 runs! Their first win in a T20 World Cup! Short of a length outside off, and flung to long-on off the inside half of the bat after skipping down the pitch

Movva is run-out attempting a second! They had to go for the run, with nothing to lose, though. Adair had mid-off back on the boundary for this ball, and again went for a slower delivery on a full length around off. Movva opened the face of the to loft, and got it aerially towards long-off, who raced forward to collect and throw the ball at the striker's end

leg stump out of the ground! A dream start for Farooqi! Full on middle stump and this curves into Allen late. Without any footwork, he looks to deposit this into the ocean and plays down the wrong line completely. The ball breezes past the bat and leg stump flies away. Farooqi is pumped, Afghanistan are pumped; NZ a little shell-shocked!
length delivery in the fifth stump channel. Threatens to shape in before going on with the angle. Gurbaz plays and misses after advancing
very full just outside off. Williamson comes forward and prods it towards extra cover
very full on leg stump. swinging into the batter. Gurbaz clinks his flick uppishly, getting it just past Santner at mid wicket. Gets a couple of runs for his toil
fullish outside off. Williamson gets a good stride in and drives it neatly through cover. The sweeper cuts it off and saves a single
shot! Shorter on off and Gurbaz is all over it. Gives himself room early, stands up on his toes and crashes it to extra cover's left!
full and swinging into leg stump. Conway is late on the flick and the ball brushes the pad, bobbling away past the keeper for a couple of leg byes
back of a length on middle and leg. Gurbaz gets behind the line and defends

back of a length outside off. Conway has a swish at it and misses. Too wide outside off, though, and some exercise for the umpire beaten all ends up! Full in the channel just outside off. Swerves away late and Conway is opened up like a deck chair. Tried to flick it but missed the ball by a fair distance
peach! Length in that probing corridor just outside off. Does not shape back in, instead continuing with the angle. Gurbaz feels for it and is beaten
full just outside off. Conway presses forward and pushes it towards mid off. Nabi misfields and that allows Conway to get off the mark
length on middle and leg. A hint of shape back into Gurbaz and he defends with soft hands
length on off. Pitches and straightens just a touch. Ibrahim jabs at it and slices it through the cover point region for a brace
edged! Tossed up on a length outside off. Conway throws his hands at it but the ball holds just enough in the surface to take the outside edge. Flies away past slip for a brace
fuller, angling into leg stump. Ibrahim looks for the flick and misses. Gets rapped on the pads but the angle was taking it down leg
back of a length outside off. Grips even more this time and spins away appreciably. Defended into the off side
edged and four! Back of a length on middle and leg. Ibrahim gives himself room and has a massive swipe across the line. Gets an inside edge that flies to Conway's left!

big appeal, not given! Fullish in and around off. Conway gets down on one knee and swipes across the line. Misses completely and gets struck on the left shoulder. Afghanistan are very confident and once Kumar Dharmasena says no, they go upstairs. Couple of things to check here. Did the ball spin enough to take it past off stump and did it strike Conway in line.  No bat involved but the impact is outside off. Conway stays and Afghanistan lose a review!
four more! Much more in control this time! Half-volley on the pads and that is easy pickings for a batter of Ibrahim's class. Holds his shape and clips it over mid wicket!
darted in on a back of a length on leg stump. Conway tucks it off his pads towards deep square leg

was that a chance?! Dug into the track just outside off. Ibrahim gets into a bit of a tangle trying to sway out of the way. Kisses his right shoulder and Conway, diving to his right, grasses it. Given a leg bye, and it did look as if it missed the glove
shortish outside off. Williamson stays back and dabs it enough to short third's right for a single
four to end the over! Back of a length outside off. Gurbaz takes a step down the track before nibbling at it. Gets a thickish outside edge and it beats short third to his left!
floated up full just outside off. Conway scuffs it back to the bowler

slides this shortish delivery down leg. Williamson does not make contact and the umpire has no qualms in calling it a wide angled in on a length just outside off. Nips back into Williamson and he chunks it off the inside edge into his pads
fullish outside off. Ibrahim scuffs his drive towards extra cover
another appeal! Fullish, pushed into middle and leg. Williamson walks across and then plays all over it. Gurbaz is very interested in the lbw but that was possibly heading down leg
hard length, slanting into leg stump. Ibrahim is cramped on the pull and splices it into the vacant mid wicket region

slower ball that boomerangs down leg. More exercise for the umpire streaky but they all count! Width outside off and Conway goes after it. Does not middle it but gets enough of an outside edge to clear short third!
shortish outside off. Zips off the surface and Gurbaz, looking for the cut, is beaten for pace

soft dismissal! Farooqi has two! Full outside off and this seems to stick in the surface ever so slightly. Conway pokes at it but the lack of pace means he cannot keep it down. Chips it straight to short extra cover, and NZ are two down inside three overs!
back of a length just outside off. Nips back in with the angle and keeps a tad low. Gurbaz plays all over it and the ball pings off the thigh pad into the off side
back of a length on leg stump. Mitchell tries to work it fine but is late on the stroke. The ball clips the pads and is stopped by Gurbaz, diving to his left
off-pace on a length on middle and off. Ibrahim presses half forward and tips it to mid off for a quick single
off the mark! Fullish on middle and off. Mitchell goes searching for it and the ball races away off the inside edge, beating short fine leg comfortably!
slower delivery dug into the track on leg stump. Gurbaz is early into the pull and gloves it down to short fine leg
huge appeal! Fired in full on middle and leg. Slides on with the arm and Gurbaz plays outside the line. Strikes him on the pads but that was possibly heading down leg

that looks very adjacent, but it is not given! Full and zipped into middle and off. Williamson, having walked across his stumps, misses his flick. Gets pinned right in front but Kumar Dharmasena is unmoved. Afghanistan, unsurprisingly, go upstairs and if Williamson has not hit this, he could be on his way. Clear gap between bat and ball. Ball Tracking up now, and it shows the ball would have clipped leg stump. Umpire's Call, and Williamson survives. Wow, that jagged back considerably. Afghanistan cannot believe it!
oh! Fizzed through on a back of a length on middle and leg. Sticks in the surface and spins away, squaring up Gurbaz. He taps it towards point for a run
dug into the track outside off. Mitchell gets up on his toes and turns it into the mid wicket region
floated up full on middle and off. Driven down the ground to long off
slower ball on a length outside off. Williamson waits for it and meets it right under his eyes
very full on middle and off. Gurbaz digs it out towards the bowler
fullish outside off. Williamson accounts for the inward angle and defends
slanted down leg. Gurbaz lets the ball come to him before helping it gently past the keeper for a couple of runs. Might have come off the pad actually
first boundary for Williamson! Slow, short and wide outside off. Williamson hangs back in his crease and flays it over backward point!

the bails do not come off! Flattens it out on a length on middle and leg, after seeing Gurbaz advance. Gurbaz does not get to the pitch but swings at it anyway. Seems to miss it and the ball grazes the leg stump before running away past the keeper. What a moment in the game!
another cutter on a length outside off. Williamson advances and dabs it behind point
full outside off. Mitchell gets onto the front foot and punches it straight to extra cover
back of a length outside off. Ibrahim gets up on his toes and pats it into the off side

what a beauty, and Mitchell has feathered it through to Gurbaz! Back of a length on middle and off. Seems destined to angle in from around the wicket but the ball holds its line after pitching. Mitchell has no option but to play at it and all he manages is a faint tickle through to the keeper. NZ are in all sorts of trouble now!
safe! Hard length, pushed into the batter on leg stump. Ibrahim is tucked up for room and cannot free his arms on the pull. Pops up but falls just in front of Ferguson at short fine leg
almost another for Farooqi! Shortish outside off. Phillips goes feeling for it away from his body and chops it past his stumps

dropped! Off-pace and into the track on middle and leg. Ibrahim winds up and has a huge swipe at it. Hits it straight to Allen at deep backward square leg, who seems to lose it in the lights. The ball hits him on the chest in the end
back of a length on off. Phillips gets behind the line of this one and plays with a straight bat
back of a length on middle and leg. Ibrahim stabs it to mid on for a single

just evades Rashid at mid off! Full on off and this seems to shape away very late. Phillips, looking to work to leg, gets a leading edge and fortunately for him, Rashid cannot hunt it down, moving to his left
cutter on a shortish length on leg stump. Gurbaz bunts it between deep mid wicket and deep square leg and hurtles back for two
full and wide outside off. Phillips wafts at it without any footwork and squirts it off the inside edge into his pads
fuller on the pads. Gurbaz comes forward and works it towards deep square leg. Just a single this time

oh dear, another missed opportunity! Back of a length outside off, as a response to Gurbaz shuffling across early. He dabs it to short third and wants the single, only to be sent back. The throw is accurate enough but Conway cannot gather, with Gurbaz sprawling to regain his ground
length ball hung outside off. Zips off the surface and flies past the outside edge of Williamson's flailing blade
darted in quicker and fuller on middle and off. Gurbaz advances, takes it on the full and plonks it to long off
angled in on a back of a length on the stumps. Williamson helps it round the corner for a single

big appeal, and given! Santner with the breakthrough for the Kiwis! Angled in on a length on middle and leg. Ibrahim gets down on one knee and swipes across the line. Makes no contact and gets rapped on the back leg. Kumar Dharmasena has a think about it before raising his finger. Ibrahim has reviewed this, though. No bat involved. All eyes on Ball Tracking now. It comes up and...reckons the ball would have missed leg stump. Ibrahim survives!
off-pace on a back of a length on off. Phillips taps it gently towards backward point
lovely! Tossed up into the slot on middle and off. Ibrahim gauges the flight nicely, gives himself room and caresses it over extra cover!
back of a length outside off. Phillips gets up on his toes and jabs it towards deep point. Has enough time to get back for two
very full on middle and leg. Ibrahim plays it back to the bowler
cutter on a hard length on off. Phillips gets behind the line and dabs it towards backward point
length on middle and off. Holds just a little in the surface as Ibrahim jabs it towards extra cover
peach! Length delivery slanted into the channel just outside off. Nips away against the angle and squares Phillips up completely. Sneaks past the outside edge and off stump
length outside off. Gurbaz plays for the turn but the ball goes straight on, fizzing past the outside edge. Conway messes up his collection again

straight to slip! Rashid gets his opposite number, and NZ are wilting! Fizzed through on a length outside off. Williamson waits for it and then opens his bat face. Not sure that shot was on with a slip in place and Williamson ends up guiding it to Naib. A sharp catch low to his left, and Afghanistan are all over NZ like a rash in Guyana!
given a bit of air outside off. Gurbaz skips down the track and powers it past the bowler for a single
very full on middle and leg. Chapman knocks it down the ground to long on to get off the mark
hung up fullish outside off. Ibrahim has a swish at it and shanks it back to the bowler
gets this away! A bit of a drag-down outside leg. Phillips lets the ball come to him before helping it past short fine leg!
slower and fuller just outside off. Ibrahim comes forward and knocks it to long on
short outside off. Phillips hops back and jabs it towards deep cover point
back of a length on the pads. Gurbaz helps it round the corner and Ibrahim is alert enough to sneak in another single

length just outside off. Chapman hangs deep in his crease and drops it into the off side for a single. The initial throw is wayward and that prompts Chapman to look for the second. Phillips, though, is not interested and sends him back. Chapman has to bring out the dive to regain his ground at the bowler's end
length outside off. Ibrahim waits for it and dabs it down to short third
fired in on a length on middle and off. Phillips stays back and defends
full, angling into middle and off. Gurbaz gets behind the line and defends
flighted up full on off. Chapman stretches forward and blocks

an event-filled ball! Full on middle and off. Gurbaz plants his front foot and drills it back into the stumps at the other end. Ibrahim is well out of his crease and Ferguson, sensing this, decides to uproot the stumps. By then, though, Ibrahim gets back via a dive. Had Ferguson got a toe to it on the first go (off Gurbaz's stroke), Ibrahim would have been out! The third umpire wants to check again if the ball scraped Ferguson's boot somehow but Ferguson seemed a little late in jamming his right boot on the floor. And the third umpire agrees with that assessment. Ibrahim stays!
length on off. Holds in the surface and spins away a shade. Chapman, trying to work to leg, gets a leading edge towards point
full on the pads. Gurbaz flicks it straight to the fielder at mid wicket
short outside off. Phillips cuts it towards deep point

appeal! Back of a length on middle and off. Decks back and keeps low. Gurbaz seems to play all over it and the ball rolls away off the pads into the off side. Given as runs, so maybe Gurbaz got a scratch on it
floated up full outside off. Chapman brings out the reverse but cannot get it past Naib at slip
slanted into the stumps again. Ibrahim knocks it down the ground to long on
slower on a full length on middle and leg. Chapman nurdles it into the on side and picks up a single
dug into the track, following the batter outside leg. Gurbaz is cramped for room and cloths his pull towards mid wicket
back of a length on off. Punched straight to extra cover
fullish just outside off. Ibrahim comes forward and stabs it back to the bowler

Middle stump has been flattened, and Rashid wheels away in celebration! Shortish on middle and leg, and this skids off the surface. Keeps a little low too and Chapman, trying to dump it over cow corner, only connects with fresh air. Hears the death rattle soon after, and Afghanistan are delighted. NZ, devastated!
flighted up full outside off. Ibrahim reaches out for it and drives it towards deep cover point

two in two for Rashid, and NZ are falling like a pack of cards! Back of a length on middle and off. Does not spin back in and goes on with the arm. Might have either been a googly or a slider. Bracewell, because he has not read it off the hand, stays back. Cannot bring his bat down in time and gets pinned on the back leg. The finger goes up but Bracewell wants to have another look. More in hope than anticipation, you'd reckon. No bat involved, and Ball Tracking returns with three reds. NZ, well, nothing is going right for them!
back of a length on off. Skids onto Gurbaz and he jams it off the inside edge into his pads
length on leg stump. Santner seems to miss it and the ball trickles off the pads into the on side
fired into the pads. Gurbaz sweeps it away towards deep backward square leg
Phillips finds the fence! A half-tracker on leg stump and it gets the treatment it deserves. Phillips rocks back and hammers it between deep mid wicket and deep square leg!
length just outside off. Ibrahim presses half forward and dabs it towards short third
back of a length outside off. Phillips goes back and jabs it towards deep cover point
length on off. Ibrahim comes forward and punches it to long on

googly on a length outside off. Santner goes nibbling at it away from his body and is beaten on the outside. But hang on, Gurbaz thinks there is bat involved, although he is not able to convince Rashid to review
full just outside off. Ibrahim backs away early and drills it straight to backward point
length on middle and off. Phillips gets down on one knee and swipes it towards deep backward square leg
back of a length on the stumps. No room to work with and Ibrahim defends
back of a length on off. Keeps low but Santner accounts for it, punching it down the ground
into the blockhole on middle and off. Ibrahim digs it out towards the bowler
edged! No slip in place for Phillips when Nabi is bowling. This is on a length on off and does not spin back in. Phillips, stabbing at it, gets an outside edge that trickles away fine past the keeper
sharp bumper outside off. Kisses the surface and zips through, whistling past Ibrahim's swinging blade

catch it, Gurbaz says, and Rashid catches it at long on! Wicket no.7 goes down! Floated up full just outside off. Phillips' eyes light up and he looks to smash it downtown. He is beaten in the flight, though, and has to reach out in front of his body, meaning that he clinks it off the toe-end. Rashid settles himself right on the fence and completes the catch!

almost a screamer! Yorker that goes wrong and ends up as a high full toss. Ibrahim tries to muscle it over mid off and does not get a good piece of it. Williamson, back-tracking, flings out his right mitt but cannot make it stick
back of a length outside off. Henry pokes it down the ground to long on

back of a length just outside off. Gurbaz drops it towards backward and calls for the single. The fielder picks it up, fires a throw at the stumps and the fielder backing up then misfields, thus allowing the second. Sums up the first ten overs in the field for New Zealand

ripper! Slowed up on a length outside off. Grips in the surface and spins sharply past the outside edge of Santner's bat. To be fair to Santner, he was not in danger of nicking it because he was so far away from the ball...
very full on middle and leg. Ibrahim squeezes it out to long on
fizzed in on a length just outside off. Henry comes half forward and defends

taken by Phillips but he ends up beyond the ropes! Darted into the slot on leg stump. Gurbaz opens up his stance and heaves it towards deep mid wicket. Phillips tracks it all the way, holds onto the catch but his running motion takes him beyond the boundary!
googly on a full length on middle and off. Defended back to the bowler
much fuller on the pads. Swept away towards deep square leg
length outside off. Skids off the surface and beats Henry for pace on the cut
second six in the over! Another slot ball on middle and leg, and Ibrahim climbs into it. Plants his front foot and thumps it over wide long on!
googly that slides down leg. Does not make any contact with the bat or the thigh pad and given as a wide wrong'un on a length outside off. Henry has a massive waft at it and is beaten on the inside
length just outside off. Ibrahim waits for it and runs it down to short third
back of a length on middle and off. Henry goes back and blocks
Gurbaz is not holding back now! A bit of a drag-down on leg stump. Gurbaz picks the length early, camps deep in his crease and pounds it over deep mid wicket!
darted in on a back of a length on leg stump. Henry plays it towards short mid wicket
fullish outside off. Ibrahim gives himself plenty of room and throws his hands at it. Slices it over backward point for a couple of runs
back of a length on middle and leg. Santner goes back and turns it into the vast open spaces in the mid wicket region for a brace
right out of the screws! Marginally short on middle and leg, and Ibrahim pounces. Snaps his wrists into the stroke and whacks it high and long over deep square leg!
slower on a length outside off. Santner, in trying to hit it too hard, scuffs it towards extra cover
knuckle-ball on a length just outside off. Ibrahim chops it into the off side and Gurbaz scampers through to complete the single
shortish outside off. Santner eases it out to deep cover point
off-pace on a length just outside off. Gurbaz presses half forward and taps it towards backward point
length just outside off. Henry comes half forward and prods it towards extra cover
shortish on middle and off. Gurbaz backs away and jabs it towards backward point
length on middle and leg. Henry works it behind square on the leg side
back of a length outside off. Does not get up very high and Gurbaz drops it into the off side for another single

castled! Full on middle and off. Does not spin and comes in with the angle. Santner goes fencing at it without any real footwork and just misses it. The ball flicks the pad and then thunders into the stumps. NZ sink further, and are on the brink now!
googly on a length on middle and off. Henry lunges forward and chunks it off the inside half of the bat towards deep square leg

hard length just outside off. Gurbaz eases it out towards deep point. Afghanistan threaten the second and that forces Chapman to throw it at the bowler's end. The throw is a little erratic and Boult cannot rein it it. Afghanistan eventually get the second
another googly, on a length on middle and leg. Ferguson prods it into the on side
that is a shot and a half! Banged into the track outside off. Gurbaz marches down the track, stands tall and flat-bats it over Boult's head!
fuller on middle and leg. Ferguson comes forward and pokes it towards short mid wicket
hard length on middle and off. Gurbaz stabs it back to Boult, who gets a hand to it and parries it close to the stumps. That is enough for Gurbaz to pinch a single, though
short outside off. Does not get up as much as Ferguson expects, though, and goes under his cut
short on leg stump. Ibrahim gets on top of the bounce and pulls it towards deep backward square leg
sprayed down leg, and called a wide googly on a back of a length on middle and off. Stays very low and Ferguson does well to help it round the corner for a brace
slow and short on leg stump. Gurbaz waits for it and hacks it towards deep square leg. Brings up his second fifty in as many games at this T20 World Cup!

simple catch for Rashid, and the Afghanistan skipper finishes with a four-for! Tossed up devilishly on a length just outside off. Ferguson plants his front foot and plonks his bat in front of his pad. The ball hits his willow and then pops up for the easiest return catch Rashid will ever take! Afghanistan just one wicket away from an astonishing victory!
off-pace and dug into the track outside off. Ibrahim cannot come to grips with the slowness and scuffs it towards extra cover
follows the batter outside leg with a full ball. Gurbaz works it between deep mid wicket and deep square leg, and hares back for the second
full on middle and off. Driven down the ground to long off
back of a length on middle and off. Sticks in the surface and Gurbaz stabs it towards Santner, who misfields and allows a single
floated up full outside off. Boult gets fully forward and drills it to long off
fullish outside off. Ibrahim stretches forward and pushes it towards deep cover point
clean strike! Given a bit of air but this lands in the slot outside off. Henry winds up, goes through the line and clubs it over long on!
slanted in on a back of a length on middle and leg. Skids on with the arm and hurries Gurbaz on the pull. Chops it into his pads
length outside off. Henry clears his front leg and hacks it to long on
slowed up a little and darted into the pads, after seeing Gurbaz advance. He cannot do much with it and the ball pings him on the thigh pad
googly fizzed through on a length just outside off. Boult has no clue about it and plays down the wrong line. Goes past his bat and past off stump too!
fired in on a length on the pads. Gurbaz tucks it away into the mid wicket region. Santner tears after it and prevents the second
full on middle and off. Boult lunges forward and works it towards deep mid wicket

it is just not happening for New Zealand! Hard length outside off. Gurbaz has a swing at it but the ball gets awfully big on him. Slices it up and the ball loops up. Backward point, third man and the keeper go after it but it falls bang in the middle of the three
angled in full on off. Boult moves across his stumps and knocks it to long on
ouch! Banged into the track on leg stump. Ibrahim gets cramped for room and cannot get out of the way as the ball keeps coming back into him. Thuds into the grille and that will have shaken Ibrahim
length outside off. Henry hangs back and jabs it into the off side

chops on the very next ball! NZ finally have a wicket! Dug in shorter and this is just a hint outside off. Ibrahim backs away, trying to muscle it over extra cover. Swishes at it too early, though, and the ball skews off the bottom edge into leg stump. Ibrahim throws his head back in disappointment. No real celebration from NZ, but they have something to show for their toil tonight!
off-pace on a fullish length outside off. Henry drags it towards long on
shortish on the body. Omarzai uses the pace, gets inside the line and glances it down to fine leg for a brace
leg-stump yorker that causes Boult all sorts of problems. He plays all around it and gets hit on the pads, although the angle is taking it well past leg stump
jaffa! Back of a length in the channel just outside off. Nips away a smidgen and breezes past the outside edge of Omarzai's bat
off-pace on a length just outside off. Boult comes half forward and pats it back to the bowler
short outside off. Omarzai gets on top of the bounce and cuts it towards deep cover point. Retains strike
slower yorker on middle and off. Boult gets his bat down in time and keeps it out
slower ball hung up on a length outside off. Henry has a wild slog at it and misses the ball by a mile
fired in full on middle and off. Omarzai lunges forward and pushes it to long off

Chennai, Delhi, Nagpur, Pune and now Guyana - the latest addition to Afghanistan's greatest World Cup hits collection! A truly professional performance to grab this group by the scruff of its neck and tell the rest of the world they are here to dominate! Off-pace and dug into the track outside off. Henry swings like a rusty gate again and gets a top edge. Fine leg circles under it and does the rest. Afghanistan are all smiles, and they deserve every bit of this win. They have thoroughly outplayed New Zealand and Farooqi, who set the ball rolling in the powerplay, fittingly finishes it off!
full on off. Gurbaz advances and perhaps gets too close to the ball. Shanks it down to long on
some turn! Tossed up on a length outside off. Drops on the batter late and then rips away past the outside edge as Omarzai looks to go inside out
fullish on middle and off. Straightens off the surface again and Omarzai edges it towards short third
up and over! In the slot on middle and off. Omarzai is now aware of what Santner is trying to do and gives himself room. Goes through the line and crashes it over extra cover!
angled in on a back of a length on leg stump. Omarzai bunts it to the edge of the ring in the mid wicket region and has ample time to complete two
off-pace and into the track on leg stump. Gurbaz hangs back and pulls it towards deep square leg
length on middle and off. Omarzai has a swing at it but ends up jamming it off the inside edge into his pads
fetch that! Banged in short outside off and Omarzai is waiting for it. Stands up tall and pummels this over the deep square leg fence!
cutter on a back of a length just outside leg. Omarzai backs away, trying to access the off side but only swishes at thin air
six more! Fractionally short on middle and leg. Omarzai reads the length like the morning daily and dumps it over the deep mid wicket fence!

Henry gets rid of Omarzai! Seems like a slower ball, bowled at around 127kph. Pitches on a full length on middle and off, tempting Omarzai to go inside out. The bat face, though, opens upon contact and he cannot generate the power he is after. Slices it towards deep cover point, where Ferguson holds on. A useful cameo, though, and it has given Afghanistan the continuity they needed after that opening stand!

four to start the over! Back of a length on off. Gurbaz dances down the track and lofts it over the bowler's head. Mitchell did put in the dive, running to his left from long on, but cannot stop the boundary!
back to back fours! Juicy full toss outside off and that is not great bowling. Might have been a leg cutter that went wrong, although it does not matter to Gurbaz, who just pops it over mid off!
into the blockhole outside off. Gurbaz shuffles across and tucks it off his toes towards deep square leg

stop the press, New Zealand have taken two catches in two overs! Another attempted yorker that ends up as a full toss just outside off. Nabi tries to turn it to leg but closes his bat face too early. Spoons up off the leading edge and Williamson does the rest at mid off. Very soft dismissal!
flies away for four! Sharp shortish delivery outside off. Rashid throws the kitchen sink at it and slashes it away fine past the keeper!
short and wide outside off. Rashid has another swish at it but is just a little late on the stroke this time. A fresh-air shot
into orbit! In the slot and guess what happens to those - they go miles! Gurbaz sits deep in his crease, swings through the line and launches it over long on. A 93m six!
slower delivery dug into the track outside off. Gurbaz nearly swings himself off his feet and miscues it towards deep square leg. Gurbaz is livid with himself
another off-pace delivery into the track on middle and leg. Rashid waits an eternity for it before swiping it off the top edge into his helmet
in the slot just outside off. Gurbaz tries to hit it into next week and drags it towards deep mid wicket
slower full delivery outside off. Rashid, because of how slow it is, cannot get the timing he is after and shanks it to long on

pick the bones out of this one! And watch out on the road too! Mitchell goes for a yorker outside off but ends up bowling a slot ball. Gurbaz bends his back knee to get under it and clatters it onto the roof over long off. Holds the pose too after that 105m six!

Rashid sacrifices his wicket! Nails the yorker outside off first up. Rashid cannot jam his bat down in time. Gurbaz is hell-bent on regaining strike and almost runs past Rashid before the Afghanistan skipper decides to sacrifice himself to keep the set batter on strike. Easy relay to Boult and he takes off the bails at the bowler's end!

Gurbaz gets cleaned up by Boult! Sizzling yorker on off stump that Gurbaz does not have a riposte for. He is late in picking it and the ball whistles past his bat before it comes down. Looks on in disbelief at what Boult has produced but he is not the first (or the last) to be castled by Boult. A passage of play Afghanistan might not look back at too fondly, although this innings was of the highest order!

appeal! Very full delivery that seems to pitch just outside leg. Naib plays all over it and the ball rolls away off the pads. Boult, though, is interested in the lbw and convinces Williamson to go upstairs. The key question here is where this ball pitched. If it pitched in line, it could be curtains for Naib. Ball Tracking confirms the ball pitched outside leg and Naib survives. Afghanistan get the leg bye too!
full and zipped into the pads again. Janat swishes and misses and Afghanistan have to settle for another leg bye

holes out to deep mid wicket! Banged into the track outside off. Naib has a massive mow across the line but has to fight the angle from over the wicket. Cannot control the pull and he skews it towards Phillips at deep mid wicket, who gobbles up the chance!
low full toss speared into leg stump. Najib has a swing at it and squirts it off the inside edge towards fine leg. Just a single to end the innings!
Off the mark straight away. Full and straight, worked through midwicket for one
good length to start, nice and straight. Defended watchfully by Nissanka
good length, angled in. Soumya goes for the sweep and misses. Stifled appeal as this strikes the front pad, but clearly sliding down leg
Picked up over midwicket! Sakib strays on the pads and Nissanka picks this up with ease, one bounce and over the ropes. That nearly went all the way
Perfect start for Sri Lanka! Soumya goes back and looks to work this onside. But he goes hard at this and ends up top edging a simple catch to Hasaranga at mid-on, who pops off in his celebration
fuller on off, defensive forward push towards extra cover
full on the pads, clipped through midwicket
back of a length on off, drop and run
good length on the stumps, defended on the front foot
back of a length, nips in a touch. Stays back and defends this towards cover point
length on off, back foot push in the V for one
Full and a little wider, shapes away late. Close to the wide line as this is left alone
full but wide outside off to start full again, pushes at this but only finds the man at point
good length on off, defensive push to cover
back of a length on the pads, goes back and tucks this towards square leg

Overthrows! Good length on middle and leg, tucked towards square leg for a quick single. Midwicket hares in for a pickup and throw but the backing up is not well organised and they ball runs away for four
back of a length, stays back and drops this towards backward point for a quick single
fuller on the stumps, stays in the crease and defends

Deja vu for Bangladesh as Thushara strikes! This was full and swinging in late, comes back from outside off to clatter into the base of off stump! Tanzin looks for the drive but is beaten all ends up. Sri Lanka can see a hint of light through the door
This time comes forward and turns it to the right of mid-on for one

wide yorker, very close to the blue line but the umpire says this was too wide Nearly sneaks through again! Good length, keeps low and and swings and seams in. Shanto gets the bat down just in time as the inside edge goes for a single
length on the stumps, goes back and taps this to mid-on for a quick single. Man in the ring caught on his heels there
good length on off, 141kph, movement away from Litton as he's squared up. Beats the edge and goes through to the keeper on the bounce
shorter and pulled towards deep midwicket for one
Ripper to start! Pitches on off and zips away from the left hander. Some bounce too
Clobbered to the midwicket fence! This was short and just sat up to be dispatched, Mendis doesn't miss out with the pull
slips this one down leg good length on the stumps, skids through as Shanto goes back to work this through midwicket
Short again and same result! This time outside off and Mendis flings this cut over backward point. No chance for third man, despite having to move just a few feet to his right
good length, some drift in towards off. Litton backs away early and cuts this late past short third. Ball slows up in the outfield though

And now Mendis is gone! This one was not quite as short, just back of a length as it catches Mendis in two minds over whether to come forward or stay back. Ends up just poking at this outside off and chops on to the stumps
full on middle and leg, chipped towards mid-on for one
Lovely start of Kamindu! This was back of a length, angling away. Kamindu just guides this away behind point, and this outfield is rapid as this races away
full on off, steps forward and clips this towards midwicket
fuller on off, opens the face on the drive. Straight to point
slides in on the pads, no bat as this is deflected behind square leg for one. Half-hearted appeal for leg before but they decide against the review
good length on middle and off, stays in the crease and defends with a full face
length on middle and off, nipping in. Defended from within the crease
Rushes him! This one skids from a back of a length, as Nissanka is slow on the pull. Ball deflects off the glove on to his grill
good length, 139kph, swinging in. Shanto looks to defend as the ball ends up somewhere near his feet. They run the single
Wowza! Sends this sailing back over the bowler with disdain. This was a fuller one, and Nissanka leans into this and swings right through the line
full on the stumps, stays in the crease and works this towards deep square leg
Swing and a miss! Rears up again off a back of a length outside off. Nissanka is beaten on the cut
full on middle and leg, gets forward and turns this behind square on the leg side for another single
Appeal for caught behind now, but not a confident one. This was in that channel outside off and has Nissanka pushing at it away from his body. They opt not to review
attempted yorker on middle and leg, played with soft hands towards mid-on for a quick single
good length on off, pushed to cover for one
full and swinging in once more. Shanto shows the gap between bat and pad, but catches this drive with the inside half of the bat. Straight to mid-on
good length on off, 142kph, defended towards cover
good length off break on off, defended back towards Theekshana
Smacked through the covers! This was tossed up on off and was enticing Nissanka into the drive, and he obliges. No chance for short extra
fuller just outside off, steps across and works this down towards long-on
Short and pulled now! Nissanka is quick on the pull and sends this soaring towards the vacant midwicket region
back of a length, angled in towards middle and leg. Goes back and tucks this around the corner for one
Nearly a run out! Kamindu calls for the single to midwicket, but Nissanka wisely sends his partner back. Direct hit might have been tight there
good length on the stumps. Litton waits for it and works it square on the onside with some breezy wrist work
Picked up over backward square leg! Gets low and just sweeps this in the air over the infield
full just outside off, gets a good stride in, pushes and runs
Nissanka is rolling! Another sweep and this time it's in front of deep midwicket!

First boundary of the innings! It came pretty fortuitously but Bangladesh and Litton will gladly accept. Goes for the sweep and gets a top edge that goes straight over the keeper and bisects both short fine and third man
Could've been another boundary this, but Nissanka strikes this drive straight at wide mid-off
And he strikes straight away! This was slightly full on off and Kamindu goes for the drive, but he doesn't get all off it. Ends up chipping an easy catch straight to mid-off
back of a length on off, looks to drop and run but point rushes in to save the single
full on off, driven briefly in the air towards cover

Straight to short extra! This was wide and full, inviting the drive. Shanto is standing well out of his crease and reaches for this drive. He gets a good connection but it's straight to Asalanka, who completes a sharp catch
Carved behind point! This was very full and wide, as DDS just hangs is bat out and guides this behind a diving backward point
full on the pads, glanced fine. Either side of short fine would have been a boundary, but he finds the man
back of a length and nearly squares up DDS, as this seams away a touch. Defended towards point

good length, but this one is pretty far down leg Nearly another! This was a good length, but Towhid stays in the crease. Big inside edge to Theekshana at short fine. His throw to the non-striker's end would have been close had it hit
back of a length on the stumps, defended on the back foot
pace-off yorker, 112kph, defended watchfully towards square leg
good length on the stumps, goes back and tucks this towards square leg for one
Ends the powerplay with a boundary! Shot of the innings as Towhid just holds his bat to this and times it perfectly through the covers. That will give him and Bangladesh a lot of confidence
full on the pads, inside edge onto the pads and they take a single
good length googly on the stumps, goes back and tucks this square on the onside
back of a length on off, back foot punch into the covers
floated up on the stumps, worked to square leg once more
back of a length on off, drop and run towards cover. It's a tight single that requires a dive at the striker's end, think he might have been safe had the fielder hit
good length googly, goes back and punches this straight to short extra cover. Briefly in the air
Walks across the line and flicks this past short fine but it's too square so backward square leg collects
good length leg break on the stumps, goes back and nudges this towards midwicket for one
Well fielded by Taskin. This was a low full toss driven straight back, but the bowler dives low to his right and saves at least one
good length googly, just outside off. Litton chops this towards point for one
full on off, driven straight to mid-off
Nearly chops on! Another googly, and it skids on as Towhid looks to cut it. Gloves it into his pads

Starts off with a wide. Back of a length well outside off Much better. Good length, right on the stumps. And this one keeps low as well. Defended watchfully by Towhid, who gets the bat down just in time
Guided past short third! This was a length outside off, and it's edged/placed very fine
good length and straight once more, this time it's flicked nicely in front of deep square leg. They run well to come back for the third
good length on off, defended off the back foot
good length on off, looks to push and run into the offside but point is on this in a flash
tossed up on off, squirted out towards deep cover point
low full-toss on off, pushed to mid-off for a quick single
Lovely leg break. Good length outside off, grips and turns past the edge as DDS is drawn forward
Full and another one that is just far too wide Full on the stumps, whipped through midwicket for a couple more. Hasaranga hares back to keep this to two
skids on the pads, tucked towards deep square leg for a single
Timed exquisitely! This was full and quick on off, but Towhid is equal to it as he produces an excellent on drive that beats the man in the ring
short of a length outside off, leans back and cuts it to deep backward point
pace-off and very full, squeezed out towards deep cover point
tossed up on the stumps, gently pushed towards midwicket for one
full and wide, flowing drive into the covers. The sweeper is in place though to keep this to just a single
good length on the pads, goes deep in the crease and tucks this in front of square leg
length ball, angling a touch away from off. Opens the face to guide this fine, but can't beat the man at backward point
Appeal for leg before as Litton fails to read yet another googly. Goes back in the crease but is struck well above the knee roll
Short and pounces! Nissanka has been excellent on the shorter stuff today, and this one is no exception. Just wallops this pull to the deep midwicket boundary
another googly, goes back and defends this

And NIssanka throws it away! This was fuller angled away from off, Nissanka looks to drive at it hard but ends up slicing it straight up towards the man at cover. There might have been some pace taken off on this one as well. Nissanka is livid with himself, Bangladesh are thrilled
tossed up on off, eased down towards long-off
full on off, defensive push towards mid-off
Absolutely hammered! Towhid had seen enough. This one was tossed up outside off, he gets on knee and it and absolutely clobbers this slog sweep over deep midwicket
good length on the stumps, worked straight to midwicket
full on off, carved down to deep point
full and straight, driven back but Theekshana does well to go low to his right and get a strong right hand to this
full but slides on the pads, tucked behind square leg for one
slips down leg And again, even wider down leg this time. Litton misses the sweep full toss on the pads, swept well towards deep square leg but well fielded in the deep by Nissanka
full on off, eased down to long on
good length on off, punched down to long-off
Skids on to the pads! Appeal for leg before, but the umpire thinks it's going down leg. Asalanka was caught on the crease a touch there. No review from Bangladesh
good length outside off, backs away but misses the cut. Nearly falls over in the process
good length on off, stays back again and pokes this straight to point
good length on off, steps across and works this to the right of mid-on
full on the pads, push and run to midwicket for one
Length ball outside off, left alone by Hridoy as it flies through to the keeper
Length ball tossed wide of off, Asalanka looks to cut but gets an inside edge towards the leg side
Length bal outside off, Hridoy meets it with an open face to steer it to deep third
Darted fuller and quicker outside off, left alone
On a length around off, Litton runs it down to deep third
Flung full and wide, Asalanka drives it uppishly through covers to the left of the sweeper
Back of length delivery outside off, dabbed to deep third
Tossed up in the slot, de Silva backs away and lofts it down the ground. But long-off running across is able to keep it down to just a single
Pathirana bangs it in short and Litton is onto it in a flash! Swivels and pulls this into the stands over deep square leg
That's massive! This is overpitched outside off, Asalanka clears his front leg and pumps this into the crowd over midwicket
Pitched up outside off, Litton drives it to the cover fielder
Length ball, tapped square on the off side for a quick single
Beauty to start the over! Length ball, cross-seam, angled across Asalanka. The ball pitches around off and zips away past the outside edge
Slog-swept with authority! This is in the slot and Hridoy powers it over midwicket
Length ball on off, he runs it down to deep third for an easy single

Back-to-back sixes! Hammered over deep square this time. It's in the slot again and Hridoy nails the slog sweep two balls in a row. Into the stands there, and the last four balls of this innings could have done the job for Bangladesh!
139kph length ball outside off, seams away past the outside edge as DDS looks to play at it
Hat-trick of sixes! Full outside off again, this time Hridoy goes inside out and finds a six over cover

Length ball on off, DDS cuts it hard to gully where the fielder takes a second to pick the ball up. Asalanka was a goner at the striker's end but the throw is not on target. Good fielding to not let it go past him though

Tossed up around leg, he misses his sweep and is struck in front. Not given and Sri Lanka review. No bat involved and he was struck low on his front pad. This looks plumb. And yes, that's shown to be crashing into middle stump. Hasaranga gets the wicket, but maybe Hridoy has already done enough?
Length ball angled into the body, Asalanka looks to swing across the line and misses
Tossed up full on off, Shakib eases a run to long-on

Direct hit. All sorts of confusion here. Asalanka taps a length ball in front of point and takes off for the single. He is sent back. The throw is on point, but Asalanka put in the dive as he made his way back. And he managed to get in safe. The deflection off the stumps saw the ball race away to the boundary, so Sri Lanka get the bonus runs here
Length ball outside off, Litton hangs back and defends
Full on leg, flicked off his toes to long leg for a single
Full on leg, clipped square to the fielder in the deep
Full on off, Litton drives it down the ground to mid-on
Bit of a drag down outside off, Asalanka pulls it away along the ground but it's hit to the deep midwicket fielder
Dug in short outside off, Litton plays an upper cut over point and picks up a brace
Length ball around middle and off, floated up slower in the air, de Silva taps it in front on the leg side for a quick single
Bouncer outside off, Litton wanted to pull but has to abort last minute
Length ball angled down leg, Asalanka looks to paddle it but only picks short fine on the bounce
On a length on a fifth stump line, Litton looks to fend and gets an inside edge onto the ground and the ball bounces past the stumps to the keeper
Full on the pads, tucked square on the leg side for a single
Full outside off, left alone by Litton
DDS dances down the track and almost yorks himself. Manages an inside edge past the leg stump and they scamper a single
Tossed full around off, played back to the bowler
Length ball angled across him, Asalanka eases it through point for a quick single
Fired in quick and full on off, Shakib eases it through cover for a single
Nearly chops on! Length ball angled in from wide of the off, de Silva looks to cut but gets an inside edge just past the off stump
Dragged down on off, Litton rocks back and pulls past the short midwicket fielder
de Silva done in by the slower ball! Length ball grips in the pitch as DDS looks to tuck it leg side. The ball pops up high towards backward point, but drops safely
On a length on off, eased to cover
Length ball on leg, tucked to deep backward square
Length ball angled across him from around the wicket now, Shakib nudges it to short fine leg and gets a single
Length ball around off, DDS drops it towards cover and takes off for a quick run
On a length outside off, punched down the ground to long-off

Asalanka misses the flick on this full delivery. The ball pops to the off side off his pads. Mustafizur goes up in appeal, but the umpire says no. Did that pitch outside leg? Likely so. The Bangladesh players have a quick chat and decide against the review

And he gets a breakthrough! Asalanka goes for the big slog sweep, but it's the longer boundary and he's picked out Shakib at deep backward square. Shakib nearly spills it as the ball bobbles up after his first grab, but he is quick to grab it right back. This was tossed full outside off and Asalanka got it off the toe end

Is there room for more twists here? Hasaranga traps Litton in front. The finger goes up but Bangladesh review. This is tossed up on off and goes on with the angle, and past Litton's inside edge. Hits him on the back thigh. And that's hitting the top of middle stump. Litton has played an important knock here, but he will not be able to take Bangladesh over the line today.

Is that two-in-two for the leggie? The umpire thinks so and Hasaranga is walking back with a golden duck! This is full around leg, Hasaranga looks to tuck it leg side and closes the face. The ball takes the edge and pops to the slip fielder who makes no mistake
Wrong'un on a length around off, Mahmudullah goes back and whips it away to deep midwicket. 100 up for Bangladesh
Wrong'un outside off, Mathews leans forward and smothers it
Length ball outside off angling in, Shakib defends
Tossed full on leg, Mathews flicks it away through to deep midwicket
Tossed up full outside off, driven to cover
Googly outside off, de Silva taps towards point for a quick run
Fired full and flat on middle, Shakib gets a bit of a leading edge as the bat face closes. the ball doesn't carry to Hasaranga though
Length ball on middle, Mathews drops it square on the leg side for a quick single to finish the over. But Rishad Hossain has given Bangladesh a massive boost here
Hasaranga goes wider and Shakib is drawn into a drive. But the batter misses. Good over from Hasaranga, and with that he bowls out
On a length outside off, Mahmudullah works it to the leg side for a single
Length ball angled into Mathews, who fends it to the leg side and gets a single
Works a length ball through midwicket
On a length around off, steered to deep third
Full on leg, squeezed out to long-on
Offcutter outside off, Mathews is able to tap it through midwicket for a brace
Angled full on leg, Shakib reverse-sweeps behind point and gets a brace
On a length outside off and it goes past the outside edge as Mathews looks for a drive
Length ball angled down leg, clipped square on the leg side for a single
Length ball clipped off his pads through square leg. Two more for Sri Lanka
Length ball fired across him is too wide Full on leg, eased out to deep midwicket
Full outside off, driven straight to cover. That's now five overs without a boundary for Sri Lanka
Fired full around off, squeezed out to the leg side for a single

What a ripper! Beautiful legbreak, drawing the batter forward. On a length around middle, the ball spins away sharply as DDS gets forward looking to slog. Litton is on the money behind the stumps and de Silva's back foot is outside the crease. And an odd innings from de Silva comes to an end and it's thanks to that man Rishad again!
