Theekshana takes an excellent catch running to his left from deep third! This is dug in short and across Shakib, who looks to play the ramp. Theekshana not only has to move to his left, but also dive in front and take it low. Not always the safest fielder, he has made sure to grab this one, Theekshana! This match is well and truly on, still!
Full on off, drifting in, Shanaka brings his bat down with an open face to run it to short third
Almost picks out mid-off! Length ball outside off, Rishad looks to muscle it over cover but miscues it. The ball pops up and mid-off is running to his left, but it lands safe
Full around off, eased square on the off side for a quick single
Very full on middle and off, flicked to midwicket
Legbreak on a length around middle and off, Mathews gets it off the outside half as he looks to play it to the leg side
Slower ball, full on off, clipped away to deep square leg
Length ball punched towards cover for a quick single
Length ball outside off, chopped to backward point. Good over from Pathirana
On a length on off and going in with the angle, Shanaka works it down the ground to long-on. Rishad finishes with career-best figures of 3 for 22
In the blockhole on off stump, fended back to the bowler
Back of length slower ball, pulled through midwicket for a singe
Length ball outside off, Mahmudullah is able to turn it square on the leg side
Length ball outside off, parried back towards the bowler

Bouncer outside off, Rishad looks to ramp but can't connect. And the umpire brings his arms up to signal a wide Through him! Thushara gets his third. Rishad looks to come down the track and misses, and loses his stumps! Thushare goes full length around middle, not quite in the slot, and Rishad was looking to back away and hit it over cover. But he is cleaned up, and Sri Lanka smell an opening!
Banged in short around off and that goes over Mathews' head. Wide called Length ball around off, flicked away to deep backward square

Huge appeal as a very full delivery hits Taskin on the foot. Or did he get bat on that? Not given out, but Sri Lanka review. Wait, that's hit Taskin full on the toe. Brilliant yorker. Pitching on leg and that's hitting the stumps! Sri Lanka have two in two, and suddenly, this game has turned on its head!
Shanaka is done in by the drop in pace. Taskin bowls a length ball at 114kph. Shanaka was already through with his shot, looking to bosh it over the leg side
Fires one down leg, and it's a wide! Back of length outside off, Tanzim hangs his bat out as he tries to chase the ball but is beaten
Another pace-off back of length delivery, Shanaka goes to pull and again fails to make contact
Very full just outside off, squeezed out to cover. Thushara finishes an excellent spell and he has given Sri Lanka a chance to pull off a heist here

The pressure tells. Follows up two slower balls with a quicker one dug in short outside off. Shanaka was late on the cut this time and gets a thick edge. Litton with a regulation take and that's the seventh wicket gone for Sri Lanka

Mahmudullah is not missing out on those! Shanaka starts off with a low full toss and you just can't do that here! Mahmudullah moves across and deposits it over deep square leg. Freebie at this stage, and Bangladesh move to within five runs of victory
Slower ball on a length on leg, Mathews blocks
Length ball flicked through square leg. And that brings Tanzim on strike
Length ball angled across Mathews, punched out to deep point
Full outside off, it stays low as well, as Tanzim goes for a wild hoick looking to go downtown. No connection made. That one kept quite low there!
Mustafizur angles a 135kph delivery across Theekshana, who can't connect as he prods at it
Full on leg, he flicks it away to deep square and gets the single. Mahmudullah back on strike now

Goes for the wide yorker, but this is too wide Length ball on middle, Theekshana fends at it and the ball goes to the bowler's left. Fizz does well to dive full stretch and stop the ball from going past him
Short and wide. Will that be called a wide? Mahmudullah gives a long look to the umpire, but he isn't interested. Dot ball it is

Theekshana swings for the hills, loses his shape and loses his wicket. Length ball angled across Theekshana who was looking to go big on the leg side. Gets a top edge and Tanzim does well coming in from deep third to take that

Kusal Mendis with a huge appeal for caught behind. Sri Lanka review. It's all happening. This is dug in short outside off, Mahmudullah has to jump as he looks to cut it. But there's no bat on that. And to make matters worse for Sri Lanka, it's called a wide Overthrows! Bangladesh have done it! They have somehow dragged themselves over the line! Mahmudullah drives a full ball to mid-off and takes off for the single. The throw came in at the non-striker's end but was wayward and allows Bangladesh to run a second
Leading edge lands safe. Length ball angled into Pathirana who ends up chipping it to the vacant mid-on region. They don't take the single

Pulled away for four! Dug in short and Mathews hits it straight of Rishad Hossain at deep midwicket, who was not on the ropes and has to be moving back. It just goes over him and lands short ofthe boundary rope for a one-bounce four

Good yorker on off, Mathews jams his bat down to squeeze it to short third, but the fielder lets the ball go through him with the ball bouncing in front of him and spinning away. Sri Lanka manage to run two
Very full just outside off, Mathews can only ease it down the ground to long-on. They don't take the run
Mathews misses out on a full toss! It's a low full toss outside off, Mathews swings for it but can't get bat on ball

Sliced to short third and Tanzim Hasan Shakib gets his first World Cup wicket. On a full length outside off, Mathews looks to heave it leg side. Gets a top edge and Bangladesh's mostly excellent fielding today continues

Sri Lanka manage a leg bye to finish it. But Bangladesh have reviewed for lbw. This was a pace off full toss following the batter who was making room leg side. He failed to get his bat down and the ball struck his outstretched back leg. They are checking to see if there's any bat on that but there isn't. Impact anyway looked outside leg and that's what ball tracking confirms. Sri Lanka finish on 124
Pitches it up, swerves it back in from leg stump to beat the flick. Hits pad but that's going down leg, no appeal

Three-act run out hands QDK a diamond duck. He took off as the ball was rolling to van Meekeren at short fine leg, Hendricks took a couple of steps but was tentative and ball-watching, QDK stopped halfway but took a couple more steps. In the meanwhile, Hendricks turned back and ran towards his crease. QDK was three-fourth of the way down now, the throw went to the bowler's end, where a couple of guys were standing. One player ran across but O'Dowd managed to collect the gentle throw cleanly and caught QDK short by miles. Was a fullish ball that was glanced fine.
Length on the pads, comes back in again. Doesn't lay bat on the flick
Fullish on middle, 129ks, clipped to midwicket

Levitt seemed like he was walking down but Jansen keeps him rooted with a bounce There's a sound as Levitt slashes, QDK is sure he's been nicked off. Jansen isn't and doesn't appeal. Umpire doesn't give it, SA review. Yep, 'there is a clear spike on the inside edge,' says the third umpire. On-field umpire accidentally signals not out, but Levitt is walking back. So the right decision has been made. Ball was around the fuller side of length and swung in a bit, Levitt tried to go square and the bat was mostly horizontal while lunging on one knee. Feathered it to the keeper
Chipped aerially but falls safely in front of midwicket Fullish ball at the stumps, Hendricks went for the flick but not with much power
Full on off, 139ks, defended in front
Full around off, defended to cover
Moves away sharply to beat bat. Might have been off the seam. Vikramjit wanted to guide it behind square, off the back foot
Full around off, defended to cover
Nips away more apparently this time. Beats a similar shot. Jansen hitting the 140kph hour mark and a good length, this one didn't get as much bounce
Slapped on the up. Hendricks uses a mostly horizontal bat to work a length ball through cover point. Back-foot shot. Ball was stopped by de Leede close to the boundary. Outfield is sandy and not fast
Fullish ball on the pads is nudged towards midwicket for a single
Wobble seamer swerves away a bit. Around a yorker length, Hendricks tries jamming it square, misses
Length on fifth, opens the bat face and pushes it away from the body. Middles it though, and finds backward point
Full around off, defended to the bowler
Length on fourth, good angle in at 133ks, defended to cover
Fullish ball zips into the pad. Flicked to midwicket
Lifts it over cover, who was a proper close-by catcher. So, Rabada going full and giving a bit of width was the invitation Vikramjit wanted, he went on one knee, arched back and drove it sweetly

Pace - 128ks but this is like Cummins to Root in Old Trafford 2019. Fullish ball angled in, looked to be heading for top of middle but straightened to beat Hendricks, who tried to cover the line with the full bat face, and trimmed the top of off. Absolute delight for van Beek. Could this actually happen again?
Change of length, Vikramjit is ready for it and tries hoisting the ball across the line. Misses. It was on a length and went away around the fifth-stump area
Fullish ball is defended in front
Goes for another booming cover drive but edges the low fully to deep third
Fullish on leg, blocked towards midwicket. Might've kept a bit lower than Stubbs expected, but he got low in time
Length leg, clipped through backward square leg
Full outside off, left alone
Length on leg, not much room for Vikramjit to work with. Defended back to the bowler

Swings away, Markram tries jamming it. Did he get bat on it and was it a bump ball? Umpire review will answer.It was on a fifth-stump line and Markram's bat was angled and had a slightly open face. Slow-mo replay shows he smushed it into the ground and Edwards took it on the second grab

Gets big on Vikramjit and Jansen has two-for. Well, he did momentarily, he has overstepped. Nothing behind the line and celebration turns to despair, as Pommie Mbangwa puts it. It wasn't short, back of length at best, and Vikramjit tried to pull it from outside off, got the edge and everyone was convinced. Celebrations begun but stopped soon Free hit is almost a replay. Don't think there was a nick on this. Vikramjit went to launch a pull square of the wicket from a length. Had to drag it across too

Netherlands are convinced Markram has been strangled down leg. Sent upstairs by the ump again. Markram curses and shakes his head as the replay loads. The length ball was going down leg, Markram tried to help it fine... and has nicked it. Now the tricky part, Edwards went low to the left, tried taking it with both hands. He caught the ball with the the left glove but it basketed in the flaps? Did that have the ball make contact with the ground? It's close but the third umpire says fingers underneath the ball. The roar among the fans is as loud as can be as OUT comes up. Late replays show that seamed in a bit. 3 for 3 in a chase of 103!
Pitched up outside off at 138ks, not overpitched but driven through cover with grace. Easy swing, gets it into the outfield
Length outside off, runs it to deep third
Backs away while driving the fullish length ball square. Miller dives to the left and half-stops it
Very full on leg, 130ks, clipped through midwicket. Deep square runs to the left to stop it
Length outside off, steered off the back foot to deep-backward point

Too wide. Late swing from a fullish length, got much more pronounced as it went low to the keeper's right. Good take by Edwards, who was flat on the ground by the end Length on leg, goes back and clips it to square leg
Length on leg, clipped to deep square leg
Nails the drive on the up, fielder at cover is on the wrong direction but sticks his hand out and the ball does the same
Klaasen shows why his presence for an extended period could close the game for SA. Sees the full, wide ball and drives it late and sweetly. Deep third runs to the right to stop it
Clips it leg side
Full around off, defended to cover off the front foot

Wide called, looked a tight call. Very full ball was swerving away and O'Dowd shaped to drive with an open face before withdrawing O'Dowd takes a risk, it doesn't come off. Rabada held onto the fuller side of length
Tight single to cover, the left-handed Pringle had the ball in his direction and threw it flat. No direct hit though, would've been out had it hit the non-striker's-end stumps

Marco Jansen uses his wingspan brilliantly, takes a stunning one-hander at first slip. He was diving to the left but was a bit late on the ball, nonetheless he went down like a lanky Ozymandias, and the ball stuck. He might've even started looking to take it with both hands but reflexes took over. Was a length ball outside off that swung away, O'Dowd tried cutting it but got an edge that took the ball flat and low.
Defended to cover off the front foot
Fullish ball on off, defended to mid-on
And again. Stubbs getting behind the line really well. This was a length ball around off again
Defends a full ball to cover
Bit of room offered and the length ball is driven from the top of the bounce, with an open face, to guide it through backward point
Leading edge but goes along the ground to cover point. Fullish ball on leg, Klaasen tried to push it towards mid-on
Fullish on leg, squeezes it towards cover. Played against the line there
Firmly punched with a vertical bat, to mid-off. Fullish ball was just outside off. 128ks

Jansen made amends for the no-ball in the field and now does it with ball. He went full and angled it in towards leg stump, Vikramjit didn't move his feet and went for an agricultural thrash across the line, may have got a thin edge, but the ball smashed the stumps

Klaasen won't break the back of this chase, he falls early in the pursuit! Dutch fans are ecstatic, pensive faces in the SA fan group. Klaasen tried doing a pacer what he does so well against spinners - pull a length ball. Tbf he did have pace and angle to work with, but didn't middle it and got it aerial. Pringle zoomed to the left, to the deep-backward-square-leg area, and slid across to take a low catch. He ran from deep square leg, the graphic shows, and 19 metres far
Length on fourth, defended towards point
Fullis length ball outside off, lets it go.

Leg slip was in for de Leede and Jansen looked to bowl to that field. Went into the pitch, around the armpit, the batter handled that well. Helped it into the ground, wide to the left of said leg slip
Pitched up outside off, angling across, let go
Bumper right over the ducking Engelbrecht. Good lines
Miller steers clear again. Kingma finishes with a wicket maiden. Was a full ball angling away again, let go
Defends the fullish ball back to the bowler
Fullish length ball around off is defended to the bowler
Full on off, pushed to mid-on. 134ks. De Leede went across, towards the line of the ball, to get behind it
Three-quarter length on fifth, back-foot square drive to point
Wide and full, de Leede drives aerially but safely to deep third. Slightly on the up and played it late
Stubbs tries to break the shackles but is beaten comprehensively. Wobble-seam on a length landed around fifth and decked back in a bit. Went below the cross-bat heave

Drives with the full follow-through and takes off. No direct hit from Markram at cover, Engelbrecht would've been long gone had it hit. Was a full ball that wasn't middled but went quick enough to the fielder for it to be a risky run.
Stubbs continues to attack, gets it away this time. Not far to the right of point but enough to race into the outfield. Was a length ball outside off that he drove with a full follow-through
Dances down and pushes the full ball to cover
Overpitched, Stubbs lays into the drive but can't beat mid-off to the left. He seems confident for now
Length just outside off, cut to point

Bumper. Handled well by Miller. 132ks ball was angling through fifth, Miller got upright and windscreen-wiped it from just above the ground, bat-face was looking down and the ball, thusly, went into ground
Pitched up on leg, pushed well. Along the ground through mid-on for a couple
Full on off, clipped to midwicket
Cuts him in half with a length ball that lands around off and jags back in. Ball went over middle, Engelbrecht tried defending straight
Fullish on fourth, defended to cover
Length outside off, pushed to point
Shortish ball is slapped through cover. Miller has had enough sighters and is now happy to go after a bit of width. Ball is stopped in the outfield
Stands upright while punching this length ball on leg to mid-on
Length on fourth, 128ks, waits for the ball to pass him and knocks it on the head to run it to deep third
Pitched up on off, 135ks. Engelbrecht tries the off-drive and gets a thickish edge through point
Defends the three-quarter-length ball on off to point

De Leede taken aback by the extra bounce there. It reared up from a slight back of length and all de Leede could do was hang his bat in front, bottom hand came off. Ball lobbed up but landed safely on the infield. No one at midwicket and bowler had too much to do
Length outside off, slapped to deep point
Risky run to cover but they make it. Full ball was outside off

There's a sound as the ball passes bat. Netherlands appeal for caught behind. Not given, Edwards doesn't review. Ultra-Edge shows it grazed the trouser. Very close to the inside edge though. Was a length ball that looked to have moved in. Miller tried to defend it straight and tried to snake his bat in late
Engelbrecht has a poke but the ball moves away from a shortish length to beat him
Length around off, defended in front

Is the pitch starting to play more tricks? This might've held up a bit, de Leede was early into the push towards cover. Had to check the shot and spooned the fullish ball a bit. It landed safely though
Length on leg, clipped to square leg
Beaten on the inside edge this time. Length ball just outside off, de Leede shaped to cut but noticed there was too little room and tried bunting. Couldn't adjust in time
He's right behind the length ball at the stumps, defends back to the bowler
Bumper around the helmet, de Leede goes for the swivel-hook. Doesn't connect
Pitched right up this time, Stubbs punches it with the straight bat. Ball bounces high off the pitch, clears the bowler but doesn't pick up pace after landing behind. Mid-off stops it
This is like attacking Test batting. Mid-on was close and a bit wide, so when de Leede saw this pitched up, he punched the ball firmly. Went with the full face but doesn't middle it
Fullish ball around off, defended to cover
Length outside off, cut through the point region for a couple
Full just outside off, pushed to cover
Fullish length ball straightens a bit to go towards off, de Leede checks the nudge. Gets it to the bowler's right

Miller goes over cover and brings up the first four, fifty legal balls into the innings. 138ks and pitched up, angled across and gave just a bit of room, Miller took a small step across and went through with the booming drive. Cleared the man with ease
Pushes it to cover to tick along
Fullish ball is defended to cover
Full on leg, 88ks, pushed to long-on
Miller's opening up, looks for another boundary shot. Saw the short ball angling towards fifth and pulled hard, didn't middle it but cleared the infield at midwicket to get two
Goes back and pulls it from just outside off, to long-on
Slow on a length from around the wicket, defended to cover
Full on off, driven to long-off. 84ks

Bumper gets tennis-ball bounce and goes way over the batter's head. Line was a bit outside off, Miller shaped to pull, even hopped, but decided he didn't have to and let it pass Slower one sticks in the pitch to beat Miller's poke. Slight back of a length just outside off, he tried to punch it firmly, with an open face, and got beaten.

Whoa, this one's exploded off a back of length and de Leede can only balloon it to point. De Leede made room but got followed. He jumped and got his bottom hand off, the ball went up off the shoulder of the bat and the fielder leapt across to take it. SA celebrate, Nortje might have another good day
Fullish outside off, opens the face and pats it to point
Zips past the edge. Length just outside off, Edwards tried to push it towards cover
Slapped to deep cover
Clips the length ball to deep fine leg
Defends the fullish length ball, at the body, 90ks, to midwicket
Length outside off, goes for the booming cut. Underedges it onto the ground below
Goes back and punches it from outside off to cover
Goes for the pull, gets beaten for pace. Bumper was around off stump and got the perfect height - around the head. Engelbrecht had to swing his head out the way while swiping
Good reverse sweep but finds short third. Looks for the single but the fielder keeps him in check. Was a full ball right on middle, Stubbs got his wrists real low and got the timing right
Engelbrecht's back leg collapses as he pulls this 146ks ball through midwicket. Looked to have bounced lesser than he expected but he controlled it well
Stays in the crease and tucks it off the pads, to midwicket
on a good length on middle and leg, and a tight line. He leaps to dab it down towards square leg
tossed up, and dipping on a full length wide outside off. Cut away with the turn to deep point
ohh, this escapes past the man close in at midwicket! He skips down and heaves at this length ball, and gets off the inside half if the bat to beat the in field
this is angling into middle and leg, and is flatter on a length. Punched towards long-off

ahh, a bit lucky for Miller! He pokes tentatively at this short-of-a-length ball angling into him, and rising sharply on top of middle and off. But the ball goes over the keeper off the outside edge. There is a discussion among the umpires for a potential no-ball... and indeed it is! change of pace, and short of a length again. This climbs on to Miller too, who pulls off the top edge, and the ball drops short of the deep square-leg fielder
he squats to reverse sweep this low full toss, but finds short third
shorter side of a length, and angling into leg. Takes his pad, and dribbles towards the keeper, as he looks to nudge
ohh, slower pace, and dipping on a full length on off. Poked behind wicket
on a length, and angling into off. Defended back towards the bowler with his head down
short of a length on the stumps, and pulled on the bounce to deep midwicket
shorter side of a length, and shaping into middle and leg. Clipped to deep backward square leg
slower again, and loopy and full on middle. Pushed to long-on
on a length around fifth stump, and there is good bounce again. Dabbed to point
on a fullish length, and wide of off. Left alone by Miller
wow, reverse scooped for six! Almost like a mirror image of Rishabh Pant. Edwards uses Nortje's pace to switch over and deposit this length ball angling into middle and leg over deep third
on a shortish length just outside off, and clipped towards deep midwicket

a run-out opportunity at the non-striker's end! Great agility by Markram, and he finds Edwards short! Markram was placed a few steps close in at mid-on, and went low and dived forward to have a go at the stumps. He hit the top of the stumps, and found a diving Edwards clearly short. Edwards had earlier pushed a length ball towards mid-on with his bottom hand off
slower, and on a fullish length on middle and leg. Whipped behind to a straightish fine leg for two
short and wide of off, and Engelbrecht slashes to deep point
short of a length, and around sixth stump. Slapped to deep point

short and sharp, but wide called. Again there is considerable bounce off a shortish length on middle, as the batter leaps to try and poke, but misses spooned to deep third! Wow, even a leading edge travels as far as that. Nortje's pace, and the extra bounce available on the pitch, combine to send Nidamanuru back. Klaasen, placed on the shorter boundary, took a few steps forward and went low to complete the grab. Nidamanuru had closed the face of the bat to try and clip this short-of-a-length ball angling nicely into middle, but seemed to have done it too early. So the ball took the leading edge and flew off
ahh, just six! It barely went past the man at long-on, who was placed a few steps inside the boundary. Full and tossed up on middle, and Miller went lofting down the ground
ahh, this zips through off a good length outside off at 144kph, as van Beek sways out of the way
length ball turning into middle and leg, and tucked towards midwicket to keep ticking
full and tossed up on middle and off. Driven to long-off with the full face of the bat
he angles this in, and bowls on a length in the channel outside off. Miller drives, but gets an outside edge to deep third
goes for the sweep at this fullish ball angling into middle and leg, and places it towards fine leg
fuller side of a length on middle and off, and dabbed down from deep in the crease
angling in on a length on leg, and clipped off his pads to short fine leg's left
on a good length on middle, and nudged to midwicket
loopy and dipping to become a low full toss on middle. Jammed back to the bowler
fuller length on middle and leg, and whipped to mid-on for a hurried single
this skids through off a good length on the stumps, and is swatted to cover
on a good length, and there is sharp bounce from around off stump, as Miller ducks. First bouncer called
ohh, goes for the roundarm, left-handed Kedar Jadhav action, and bowls full outside leg. Left alone, and wide called on a length on off, and dabbed back towards the bowler
on a length around sixth stump, and dabbed to point. Stubbs sends Miller back after an attempted second
on a good length on middle, and this rises through at the batter. Tapped back rather uncomfortably
bowls full and slowish on off. Driven to long-off
on a short of a length, and shaping back into leg. Takes his pads as he looks to clip, and the ball dribbles behind towards a straightish fine leg
ohh, he went pushing at this fullish ball angling across towards off, and got it aerially off the inside half of the bat to long-on
much fuller, and angling into middle and off. Pushed off the inside half of the bat towards midwicket
hoicked wide of long-on! Finally Stubbs gets one away, as South Africa keep the pressure on Netherlands. It was a length ball angling into middle, and Stubbs went through with the movement into him
short of a length around sixth stump, and slapped to deep point
good comeback, as he bowls an inswinging yorker on middle. Dragged to long-on

ohh, just short of Jansen at slip! He was initially moving to his right, before realising the ball was coming to his left. Van Beek was squared up by this length ball, which straightened away and finished around sixth stump, as he got the outside edge
on a length on off, and whipped to deep backward square leg
short of a length on middle and off, and way too high, as he lets it go. Wide called looks to flick this length ball angling in, but gets an inside edge rolling towards the keeper's right
short of a length outside off, and swat-pulled to long-on to round off a successful over for South Africa
full and flat on middle, and driven back, as Maharaj dives to his left
launched over mid-off! Now Stubbs is in the mood. He skips down the pitch after making room, and goes through the line of this length ball around off
slower, and angling into a full length on off. Hacked to deep point
fuller length on off, and tapped towards cover for a quick run
skips down, and gently chips this length ball outside off just over the bowler's head. And it is placed well enough to beat a chasing long-off to his right
on the shorter side of a length on off, and he rises with the ball to tap to point
short of a length this time, and pulled towards long-on
ohh, just short of long-on! He went heaving at this fullish ball outside off, which was bowled at a change of pace, and played off the inside half of the bat
on a length on the stumps, and punched to deep point. There is a fumble by Stubbs, and that allows the second
short of a length, and angling into off. Dabbed to deep third
loopy, full and slower on off, and driven to long-off again
on the shorter side of a length on middle and off, and clipped to deep backward square
on a length, and angling into middle and off. He dabs it down with a hop in the crease
angles this in, and bowls on a length just outside off. Miller gets across and blocks down
on a good length on off, and clipped towards deep square after riding the bounce
fuller length, and a slower ball on middle and off. Pushed back towards the bowler
fuller length, and stays a bit low as it shapes in towards leg. He backs away, and nudges to cover

three dots in a row to start the 16th over. This one stays low off a shortish length - the first real instance of that today - as van Meekeren bowls at a change of pace again. Miller goes slashing, but is beaten
he moves his back leg around, before pulling at this short-of-a-length ball outside off towards deep backward square leg
ahh, this is a tight line. This good-length ball is angled into middle and off, but straightens away, and is blocked down after he opens his stance up
another one on a short of a length, and this is pulled almost hurried over the at midwicket, as if the ball seemed too quick for him
now he backs away and advances down, only for him to try and chop at this length ball angling into leg, and getting a bottom edge towards the keeper

this one skids through off a length on the stumps, and is swat-pulled to mid-on. And, and... it's a late call of this being a no-ball gets across, and Nortje bowls on the shorter side just outside off. Swung away to fine leg
wow, the 16th over is a maiden! Good work by the man at midwicket, as Miller pulls hard at this shortish ball angling in. The ball goes on the bounce to the fielder
follows the batter, as Stubbs makes room. De Leede angles this in, and bowls on a length outside leg. Clipped towards deep midwicket for two
he makes room, and Jansen angles this across by bowling on a length. It lands just outside off, and he is beaten in trying to loft

gone, are we in for a late twist?! A well-judged catch by van Beek at deep midwicket, given the ball was in the air for a long time. He kept his eyes on it throughout, and took it in front of his throat. Again Stubbs backed away, and this time de Leede shortened his length to go on a good length. The ball shaped back in, and Stubbs pulled. But the ball travelled only high, and not quite the distance he had hoped for

ohh, dropped by Jansen! He stuck his left hand up, and even had a second attempt at it after the ball fell into both his hands, but still missed. Length ball on middle and leg, and chipped back by the batter
on a good length, and there is good bounce even for someone as tall as Jansen. Dabbed down after getting across
fuller length, and driven back down the pitch. The ball goes on to the hit stumps at the other end, though
on a shortish length on middle, and clipped behind to fine leg

another missed chance, but this was difficult! Hendricks was at deep backward square leg, and he moved and dived to his right. But the ball fell beyond his reach, as it was hooked high off a short of a length on leg
short of a length on middle, and whipped to deep backward square leg
on the shorter side of a length, and nudged towards square leg

ohh, just short of Edwards trying to rush forward! And Jansen is down on his knees after what seemed like a harsh blow. On the shorter side of a length on middle and leg from de Leede, as Jansen looked to pull, but the ball ballooned up and went behind the wicket after taking an inside edge on to his body

off the top edge, and four! It seemed like a slower ball, and it was on a short of a length on middle and leg. Van Beek went for the pull, but was beaten by the lack of pace. The ball rose up, and took the top edge over the keeper
on the shorter side of a length on middle, and pulled towards midwicket after making room. But the fielder slides to his right to stop the ball
short and wide-ish of off, and it is slapped to deep point
swung away over fine leg! Again he backed away, and the length of this ball was shorter as it angled into leg. It was the longer boundary there too, but Miller sent it hard and flat
lofted down the ground! Fuller side of a length from Baartman, and angling into off, as van Beek gets his front leg out of the way to chip that back
again bowls on the shorter side, but this is on off. Hacked to deep point
short of a length on off, and swat-pulled towards deep midwicket

good work by Pringle at deep square leg, as he runs and dives to his right to pull the back. Yup, replays show he did it pretty cleanly. Jansen whipped this length ball behind the wicket, even as it come off the inside half of the bat
another one climbs sharply off a good length around sixth stump, as he looks to hook but is beaten

bowled him! The roar from van Beek and co signal what this means for Netherlands. It was a length ball all right - and in the zone to attack. The ball landed on off after being angled in, and shaped back in further to hit the middle stump, as Jansen looked hoick across the line but missed. Big blow for South Africa late into the game
ohh, this zips through off a length after landing on middle and seaming away, as he sways out of the way after shaping to poke at it
shorter side of a length, and angling into leg. He clips to fine leg and takes off, but Miller sends Maharaj back
much fuller length on the stumps, and driven wide of mid-off
thrashed over a straightish fine leg! On the shorter side of a length, and shaping into middle and leg, as Miller swivels full throttle to send this flaying for six
on a length in the channel outside off, and he gets across to try and swipe it. But it hits him on his pad, and dribbles away to the off side
two more for Miller! Short and wide outside off from de Leede, and Miller slashed it hard to deep extra cover
on a length on middle and off, and shaping away late, as van Beek looks to hoick, but is beaten
ahh, well bowled! It is a slower-ball bouncer outside off, as Miller sways out of the way to let it go
slower ball, and on a length on off. Slapped to deep backward point
lofted over extra cover! Miller brings up fifty too! On a length and angled into off, as he presented the full face of the bat to go over the in field
six over long-on! He is almost beaten by the change of pace, but still manages to swat-pull this short-of-a-length ball rising sharply over middle and off. Well timed in the end

crashed over deep square leg! Miller takes South Africa home after Netherlands nearly did it. The South Africa fans breathe a sigh of relief, as does the dugout. A length delivery from de Leede, which angled in at perfect height towards middle and leg. Pulled hard and deep into the stands for six

swatted over point, and that is great work by the deep-point fielder running and diving to his left. It was Stubbs there, as he pulled the back last moment. Shorter side of a length outside off from Rabada, and Engelbrecht launched at it late

another boundary, and another teaser for a South Africa fielder! These two target Rabada, whose slower balls are being read well. He bowled at a change of pace on a length around off, as van Beek chipped it late to just beat mid-on to his left

leading edge to extra cover! He backed away early, and Baartman angled this in to bowl on the fuller side of a length outside leg. It was another slower ball, as Engelbrecht looked to clip this to the leg side, but seemed to have closed the face of the bat too early. A late boost for South Africa
on a length just outside off, and chopped to cover. Pringle takes off, but is sent back by van Beek

good catch by Markram! He was pretty close in at midwicket, and leapt to take it with a reverse cup. Shorter side of a length from Baartman, as Pringle went pulling at it from middle and leg. He hit it forcefully, but couldn't time or place it all that well, with the ball seemingly rushing off his bat
much fuller length on the stumps, and pushed down the ground
ohh, change of pace, and van Beek is fooled. He backed away early, and this fullish ball angled in to go past leg stump as he looked to push

well taken by Nortje! He was placed at cover-point, and moved to his left while looking up at the sky. The ball dropped, and into his hands as he took them while tumbling to the ground. It was another slower ball from Baartman, who bowled on a fullish length and into leg. Van Beek made room and went for the loft, but was beaten by the change of pace again. In the end, his attempted loft went only as far as halfway towards deep point
full inswinger, jammed through fine leg for four! Salt looks relieved to have got bat down on this but he picks up a boundary first ball into the bargain
round the wicket, looped up at 81kph/52ph outside off. Defended to cover point
full bunger wide of the stumps, 140kph and no swing. Salt swipes, think there might have been a tickle of bat, then bounced through to Wade
gives it some air again, Head is forward and clips a drive in front of deep extra cover, the short boundary... they scamper back for two
flung full again, swinging towards leg stump, swatted through square leg
straighter line, 90kph/56mph and prodded back down the track
length in the channel, 143kph/89mph and Buttler is beaten feeling for it outside off! Didn't swing, just went on with the angle
turn and bounce, clears off stump! Head beaten trying to play off the back foot, inches away from being castled
fullish on off stump, 147kph/91mph. Punched back to the bowler
tossed up around off stump, Head swats it away half forward
whoosh, big swing but misses everything! Curling behind the pads as Buttler shuffled across pitched up, another dot as Buttler jabs towards mid-off
angled in and worked off the pads into the leg side - just three off the opening over
back of a length, 139kph over the top of off. Driven to the point sweeper
nails the slog-sweep for six! Tempts the big shot against the spin but Head gets it right out of the middle
back of a length, shoots through a touch low outside off. Leaden-footed prod from Buttler, beaten
floated up and hammered! Back-to-back Dorothy Dixes from Head, taking Jacks to task over the shorter boundary. Absolutely mullered into the crowd
skips down and slams through backward point! Attacks the length ball, punishing swing of the bat. Short boundary, gives deep third no chance
fired down flatter outside off, Head throws the hands and carves up and away, a thick edge down towards deep third. Mark Wood throws himself valiantly to prevent another boundary
pitched up straight, 139kph and tucked off the pads through midwicket
too full, too straight, creamed over the leg side! Warner takes the aggressive option and Jacks again has he head in his hands. Smacked into the concrete at deep backward square leg
back of a length, hoicked through midwicket! A cutter but it sits up nicely as Buttler steps down again and forces past the diving man in the ring
brings out the reverse, not where he was aiming but it loops over Buttler for one
length on off, 142kph and punched to mid-on
pushed through and Head punches a drive straight to cover
round the wicket, full on the stumps, chipped... but it lands safely wide of mid-on
full and tempting, 143kph/89mph wide of off stump but swinging back. Buttler throws the hands but misses
fired into the pitch, Head dabs it to the off side and calls his partner through. Warner has to put in the full-length dive as Archer hares across and has a shy at the stumps
goes very full, again angled across the bows. Buttler chops down on it for one into the point region
length ball, 148kph/92mph on middle and off, Warner is looking to make room, jabs it square
goes big, big, BIG! Salt lands one right in the smackeroo, sailing into the stands at deep midwicket. Just a punch off the pads, 106m in distance. Does for his KKR mucker
full on the stumps and clipped through midwicket in front of the sweeper for two
fired full and fast into the pads, deflected behind square
short, 143kph/89mph and heading down leg shortish again, 146kph/91mph and slashed over the cover ring. Again looking to back away but not in control
sprayed wide of off again, away from the short side. Plinked to cover
pace off to finish, hits Warner on the gloves and they take one into the leg side
143kph, flung out into the tramlines. Too wide short-armed into the boundary cushion! Another chip to the short side of the ground, just bounces short
flicked off the pads, sails all the way...! It's a short hit out there, and Warner has pinged this high and handsome. Only a 78m six but it disappeared out of the ground
slams this into the deck, 137kph/85mph as Salt looks to advance. Flies through past the top edge

short and heaved away, another sixer! Wood tries to tuck him up but Warner, just as he promised in the build up, uses the pace to his advantage and nails a pull into the stands at deep backward square leg
smashed through point! Room to free the arms and Salt connects
banged into the pitch, shifting the line slightly across to off stump. Defended
hard length, Salt swings to leg, deflects off the pocket towards backward point
full toss, Wood gets another toweling! Just a flick of the wrists, the ball soaring into the Greenidge & Haynes Stand at deep midwicket
back of a length and guided away, rides the bounce and slices across the ball to pick up four more out to deep backward point
short and hammered! Warner rolls his wrists on a brutal pull, picked the slower one and slammed it in front of square
pace off, Salt nudges via his pads into the leg side
another change-up, 133kph/82mph and Warner prods it towards point
floated up and slapped down the ground! Seemed to come off the toe of the bat but Head swings malevolently through the line, beats the dive of mid-on
full on off stump, 142kph/88mph. Salt digs it out powerfully in front of the cover sweeper for two
floated up and butchered over long-on! Back-to-back boundaries to start the over for the third time. Head takes a step and blasts the ball back towards the sightscreen
back of a length, boffed over the man in the covers. Warner hares around the boundary to save a couple
flatter and jabbed into the covers for one
fired in full, 140kph almost yorker length. Salt flicks across it but can't beat short fine leg
darted on the stumps, 96kph and Warner advances aggressively, flips the ball short of mid-on
slower ball now, wide of the stumps and Salt swipes ineffectively
mauled through midwicket, dropping back this time and clattering four more past the diving Jordan!
misses the yorker, sliced through third! Just too full, 143kph and Salt just needs to stretch out and get some bat on it. Beats the two men inside the circle and races for four

bowled 'im, stays low and skids on! England finally have a moment to breathe. Warner caught on the crease when he perhaps should have been forward, the ball grips and scuttles into middle and off halfway up
pace off, sits up wide of off, Salt chops a cut to backward point
slower ball, chopped down into the covers
fullish in the channel, Buttler punches to cover
another cutter, Head is back and swipes, a thick edge bobbling low through to the keeper
skips out and honks four over cover! Not a clean hit by any stretch but it just needs to clear the ring and bounce away to the short side
short and blasted through point! Archer persisting with the offcutter but this one disappears as he rides the bounce
Buttler steps outside leg, Stoinis follow him. Length ball, 129kph/80mph and swung away to fine leg

gone, stumps out of the ground...! Another offcutter, much fuller and sliding under the bat to crash into middle and off - Head is lopped off, Archer hits back again for England! What a high-octane start this has been
length ball into the pads, tucked for one
over the wicket, 149kph/93mph and banged into the pitch, Maxwell hops into line
steps away again, Stoinis goes wide blockhole, 133kph. Dug out to cover, Salt has to scamper back
short with pace on again, 148kph and searing through into Buttler's gloves as Maxwell swings blindly
dug in as Salt scurries down, deflected off the body... Wade grabs it flying to his right. Nitin Menon isn't interested, no bat involved, it seems. Actually, it came off the helmet
over the wicket, floated up outside off. Marsh gets off the mark with a punch through cover
taken at deep third... Head steps on the rope with the ball in hand! He knew straight away, even though he tried to relay it to himself. Don't see that sort of mistake very often these days
googly, I think, wide of off and swatted uppishly through mid-on stretching on to the front foot
full length, bunted into the off side for one
tossed up straight, Marsh slams a sweep through square! Shorter side of the ground and he bisects the field perfectly
munched over the short leg-side boundary! Slower ball from Starc but it goes the journey as Buttler's bottom hand takes over, on to the concrete at deep midwicket again
slower legbreak, outside off and dabbed off the back foot
full toss, slammed down the ground! Beats mid-off to the right. Stand and deliver from England's captain
tucked off the pads, Maxwell thought about one but seemed to lose his footing
full and slapped into the leg side, just one out to cow corner
flighted, on the stumps, whipped away through midwicket
high full toss, 142kph/88mph and Salt completely mistimes it, plinked into the midwicket region... lands safely in no-man's land

strikes first ball! Bail-shaver does for Salt! He looks disbelieving, as if wondering whether Wade had nudged them off - but he has to go. Skiddy legbreak and it beats a cross-batted swipe playing back, flicking the off bail on its way through
back of a length, angling in from over the wicket. Thick-edged down to fine leg
pushed through, 89kph on off stump. Jacks platys straighter and works it down to long-on
similar line and length, tucked towards midwicket
quicker legbreak, spinning outside off. Buttler dabs into the covers
flung full in the channel, 133kph/83mph. Marsh marmelises a drive straight to mid-off
tossed up on middle and leg, tucked through midwicket
Wood continues with his change-ups, 134kph and nudged to leg. They manage to pick up two into the gap at midwicket
into the pitch, 94kph and spinning a smidge, Jacks picks out cover
short of a length, tapped down coming across on off
gives it a little but more air, clipped through long-on. Picture-perfect first over from Zampstagram

skiddy length, Marsh flicks across it, Wood appeals... was there any bat involved? Looked to have smacked the back leg in front of middle and leg. But Buttler decides it's not worth a flutter on the DRS
tossed up and rammed through midwicket! A whipcrack of a slog-sweep in front of square, into the gap and skips across the boundary marker
length ball, shovelled into the leg side
flatter and cut away to deep point
goes for the wide offcutter, just inside the tramlines as Buttler reaches out and swipes to point
flighted googly not sure Marsh reads this. Tries to cut from outside off as the ball comes back in, almost drags on
pace on, 143kph/89mph and into the body. Jacks aims a blow across the line but only gets an inside edge into his thigh pad
floated up and Marsh attempts to sweep, under-edges behind his pads again
boshed through the covers! It was in the air but Head couldn't get his right hand to the ball. Jacks muscles his first boundary

pounded for six... ROOFED IT! Marsh rocks back as Rashid drops short and obliterates a pull high over deep midwicket. He's smashed one of the solar panels up there, damaging not just England but the fight against global warming!
low full toss, clipped back through mid-off
looped up, can't get under this one, swept flat through square leg
full outside off, pace on and Buttler prods it warily to the man in the covers
length ball spinning away outside off, Jacks cuts to the cover sweeper
back of a length, fourth stump. Marsh chops it through point
goes for the reverse-sweep, big old wind up but only manages a top-edge over the keeper for two
pace off, straight line, nudged towards midwicket
flighted, 86kph, reverses again, nailed... but straight to backward point
full and dipping, 116kph/72mph on the stumps, flicked off the toes. Australia bring up the 100
crunched over long-off! Fractionally too full from Zampa and Buttler bludgeons it down the ground. The boundary rider thought he was in the game, right until he wasn't
goes for the yorker, 139kph/86mph and well directed. Maxwell makes room and picks out cover

reversed... straight to backward point! Buttler's strength becomes his weakness and Zampa is cock-a-hoop! Another big wind-up as he looked to heave this away but didn't time it, allowing Cummins to set himself for a head-height catch. Australia have hooked the big fish
short into the hip and tucked around the corner
spooned wide of extra cover! "Caaaaaaaaaaaaaaattttccchhh!" was the cry as Bairstow was beaten in the flight, but it didn't go to hand
back of a length, pace off and swatted out to the cover sweeper
back of a length, pace off, a big heave across the line and under-edged into the leg-side
full on the pads, clipped in the air once again by the hard-handed Bairstow. But safe at midwicket again
slow bouncer, Maxwell sets himself for the pull, opening his stance on the back foot,  but can't get much welly behind it
tugged out to the leg-side, no great timing but into space in the deep
another cutter, fuller length, a big attempted pick-up off the tight line, but cue-ended back to the bowler
steps into a mahoosive front-foot wallop, meeting the wide line outside off, but that ghosts past the inside-edge
he was set for that one! Deep in the crease, anticipating the extra pace and lofted up and into the leg-side. Didn't nail it but out of the reach of deep midwicket
back of a length, Bairstow swings into a pull to leg, can't connect cleanly
pace off again, into the pitch, wide of off stump, clubbed firmly out to deep cover

smashed to long-off, Starc clings on brilliantly! Jacks threw the kitchen sink at that, but it was a slower ball, a touch high on the blade, and Starc judged it wonderfully, flinging himself forward to scoop it inches from the turf!
lovely bowling, pace off once more  but swinging from back of a length this time. Opens the face on the back foot but can't get any bat through the wide line
bouncer first-up, but that's too high. Will have to bowl that one again guided elegantly out to deep cover, a full-faced push off the back foot, eludes short cover and is swept up in the deep
rocks back to the tight line, can't connect cleanly off a cuff into the covers
full length, into the pads, pinged up and into the leg-side, Livingstone's shy from the deep is pinpoint, but unfortunately it ricochets away for more runs
a touch of width, Bairstow rocks back for a slap to deep point. Moeen on strike to the offie...
makes room to leg, cracks a firm cut through the back-of-a-length delivery, mopped up at deep cover
round the wicket, tidy dart, drawing a hasty stump-defending block
flogged through wide long-on! Full length, angled in at the legs, makes room and lumps with a closing face, beating Jordan on the rope
a touch less pace, met on the back foot with a flick off the pads
huge hack, not quite the stroke he was looking for, clothed into the leg-side off a fuller length
makes room to leg, but can't carve that past short cover. England are sinking a bit in this period
fizzes through this time! Pace back on for Wood, only 85mph on the clock, but beats the attempted flap off the back foot
magnificent dot-ball. Line, length, fizz off the pitch, Bairstow can only block it back down the line. That's a momentum-wrecking over
fuller length, shaping onto the toes, clipped behind square and Rashid grabs well at short backward square. Flings a shy in and Wood tumbles well to cut off the overthrows
strangulated appeal, but that pitched outside leg before thumping the pads
full length, bashed into the off side, just the single
tossed up, gripping on middle and leg, pressed into the off side. This is lovely bowling
very wide of off stump, Maxwell chases it with a chaotic pull-sweep, tumbling into the stroke... top-edged to midwicket where Bairstow can't reach it! All that for a dot
cracked into the covers, but just a single
outside off, and blatted flat over deep third! Wow, that's Maxi's angles, opening the face on the full length, and nailing it with wristy timing, all about the bottom hand there!
very full, dipping into the leg-side blockhole, YJB sweeps himself off his feet, but not the ball

fired through to the keeper, that's a harsh call of wide... similar margins to Archer's in the World Cup super over even wider, Maxwell chases it, and times it! Reaching uppishly, levering into the space at deep cover. Lovely timing once more
flighted, outside off, a real tempter, Jonny loses his shape on an ugly inside-edged hack behind the keeper
wide yorker, that's the perfect line and length, toe-ended into the off-side
fizzed into the pads on the full length. Another muffed sweep from Bairstow, and England have managed five runs in 12 balls... Australia are tightening their grip here

no doubts about that wide... clearly the wrong side of the guideline. Reload! nailed through point! Jordan serves up width from back of a length, Marsh cuffs firmly, straight through the gap in the field that Liam Livingstone vacated moments earlier. England continue to bleed boundaries
round the wicket, crashed up and over the leg side! Moeen knows there's no time to wait, and connects massively!
instant reverse from Maxwell, looped up outside what was his leg stump, can't connect properly out to cover/midwicket
in the slot again, launched over long-on! That's more like it from Moeen, it's been pitched up, into the arc, and deposited!
on the pads, tapped square for a single
width on a full length, a flat-footed hack, can't connect. Well hidden outside off
tight lines, just back of a length, poked into the off side off the back foot
outside off again, dragged behind square for the single
tossed up, onto the toes, another nudge off the pads to midwicket
similar line to Zampa, over the wicket and into Bairstow's pads, a cramped sweep ends up at backward square

lovely loopy legbreak! Is this a stumping? Marsh was initially walking. Beautiful shape from Livingstone, a hint of drift to leg to open up the batter, then sharp spin past a big hack. Buttler reaches the bails before the toe can get back into the crease, albeit at the second attempt. Critical breakthrough for England!
flicked off the pads, mighty over midwicket! That's the over England desperately needed! Full enough to take on the short side, and it's a 20-run over, the best of the innings
thrashed hard off the front foot, to long-off. Excellent over to check Australia's surge
tossed out outside off, instant sweep from Stoinis, in front of square

into the pitch, Bairstow holes out at wide long-on! A wipe from outside off, and so ends a non-starter of an innings from YJB. Maxwell gives the England fans behind him a wave after presumably taking some bird for his previous over

leans back, nailed to deep midwicket! Salt didn't have to move! Maxwell was right back in his crease, creating length that didn't exist, and he couldn't get the requisite elevation. A double-whammy dents Australia's surge
tight lines from Hazlewood, angling in on middle and off, a solid front-foot block
skids on outside off, rocks back and cuts to the off-side
backs away, Hazlewood sees him going and follows him down the leg-side, a cramped pull to midwicket
too wide outside off this time, out of the front of the hand from Rashid lovely flight and dip, pace off, and sharp spin to beat an attempted slog sweep. Traction for England now
good length, just outside off, and that doesn't get up much. Brook jabs his bat and can't connect
pushed through to the right-hander, a non-turning googly, met on the back foot
lines up the ramp, but can't connect down the leg-side. Hazlewood gets away with the wide due to the premeditation
top-edged on the sweep, but it's the short side! Nothing much Rashid can do about that, as the ball plops into the stands at backward square. Stoinis is away, with a one-handed six!
outside off, back of a length, through to the keeper past a loose wipe. Another dot ball, and that 20-run over feels a long time ago again
tight lines from Livingstone, gripping on off stump and pushed to the off side
round the wicket, back of a length, wristily cuffed into the covers,  no way through there
looped into the blockhole, leg-stump line, open-faced push to mid-off
walks to the off-side, seeking the uppercut through the long off-side boundary, Cummins hides the ball wide, one bounce to deep cover
good lengths once more, leg-stump line, looping into the blockhole. Met with a solid punch back down the pitch, but a fine piece of footwork from the bowler to deflect the ball to mid-on
slower ball, sits up from back of a length, flashed out to deep cover. No timing in sight for England
reverse-sweep, off a tight line, can't connect properly to point

slashed in the air to deep cover! Warner tracks around, staring into the sun, but the ball hangs up in the breeze, it's sliced out into the off-side, and England's dangerman is gone! Super bowling from Cummins, hiding the ball outside off, demanding that Moeen took on the long side, and he failed
firm lines on a bosh to mid-on, but Livingstone is holding his length well so far

pace off, down the leg side. A bonus run for England hits the pitch, line and length from Cummins, and all Livingstone can do is defend from deep in the crease. Dare one say it, England aren't looking much different to the 2023 World Cup outfit at the moment
right underneath this one! A huge hoist back over the bowler's head, hitting right up into the ball, and that's vast! Onto the concourse!
swivels on a pull, no clean timing, deep backward square gathers

width on the full length, creamed over extra cover! It's the long side, into the breeze, and David loses one hand on his bat, but still mashes it into the stands! Jordan gesticulates... what else can he do?
width on a good length, outside off, thrashed to long-off. All very conventional lines in England's hitting. Can't beat well-set fields
dropped by Jordan in his followthrough! A collector's item that, but that was properly nailed, and at thigh height too, couldn't get his hands down in time
climbs into a pull, again, it's just a single out to midwicket. Nothing to get any leverage through
lashed through the length ball, Jordan sticks out another hand but can't intercept as long-off mops up
low full toss, wide of off stump, thumped to long-off. This is ponderous from England, but so canny from Australia. They have their plans and they are nailing them
width outside off, an open-faced steer, there's a short third in place but the ball falls short
line and length, outside off, cuffed to deep point, Warner tracks round on the boundary's edge. This chase has flatlined

this time the long boundary is David's downfall! More width from Jordan, forcing Australia to take it on, but David's uppish thrash is into the wind, and Livingstone is well placed inside the rope at deep cover. England continue to nibble away through the back end
better ambition that time, walking across the stumps to lift the ball into space behind square, but there's not enough timing to beat the sweeper
slower ball but down the leg-side. Reload! Wade nails the pull through deep midwicket! Archer tumbles on the rope but can't collect. Another last-ball boundary to keep Australia ticking
pounds the pitch, back of a length, outside off, another swing and a miss. Livingstone wants a wide but he's not getting it. There's no way back for England now
makes room to leg, meets the full length with another pushed single
on the reverse, can't connect properly as Rashid tosses it up at the legs
rocks back to the length ball, cracked hard off the back foot, wide long-off gathers. This is pedestrian
lots of width, too much width! Wade steps into the ball, meets it on the full, and strokes it effectively through the gap at extra cover
so tidy from Zampa, another ambitious cuff through the good length, but no timing or placement, gathered in the deep
A loud blast of music kicked in to distract Wade, who tried to pull out of the shot, but he blocked it off the back foot, and so the umpire says he played at it!

steps into the length, mashed over the bowler! The first boundary for 21 balls, and it's a well-picked googly. Too late surely, but two more of those in this over, and this chase has a pulse. We have a delay for a new ball, that one has travelled outta here
width outside off, carved uppishly out to point
follows the batter as he makes room to leg, has a hack and that's wriggled past the keeper too. Doesn't reach the rope, so significantly less than the requirement
lumped through the line, not timed, as Jordan motors round at long-on to clean up
tossed right up into the blockhole, slashed into the covers, Zampa's game-breaking spell is done! What a white-ball bowler he has become. Every ball a coconut
another reverse sweep, through the gap at backward point! Double tea-oot from Rashid, that was picked up well from a formerly leg-stump line, and bissected Archer and Bairstow perfectly!
round the wicket, squared up, but through deep third! Pace off as the cutter grips, Rashid was standing at a wide short third and couldn't intercept
full length, wide of off, cracked off the toe out to deep point
pace off again, on the pads, nudged to the leg-side
back of a length, another ambitious swing, but the pace is off and Brook can't time that at all. Out to the leg side
back over the wicket, pace off once more, outside off, luring Stoinis into a drive, but he can't find the timing
yorker, that's lovely bowling, squeezed off the toes to the leg side. England are adrift now
back of a length, toe-ended to Brook at mid-off! He does brilliantly to save the boundary, full length dive to his left, might have been a catch but saving the runs was the priority
huge hack, big edge, Zampa almost holds a worldie! Fires out his right hand, high above his head, but can't control it as he lands. It won't matter
short, pace off again, no timing on the pull, plugs in the deep
back of a length, pace off, flogged through the line, straight to Starc at long-off! An ugly innings ends, and England are already in need of snookers

Wade is given out on a reverse-pull, but instantly reviews it! He switched his stance, but was met with a full-pace short ball from Archer, comprehensively beaten for pace, but yes, that's missed the gloves and kissed his biceps!
rolls the fingers, another wide cutter, Jordan slaps with flat feet and can't connect. Cummins is done, another mighty effort
lifted very straight, beats the sprawling Brook! Full length into the toes, Stoinis accessed it well and found the gap at long-on. A fine leap to no avail from the fielder
flat feet, outside leg, can't reach the wide line outside off where's that shot been hiding! Full length, Brook opens the face and lifts a one-bounce four over extra cover
follows the batter to leg with a short ball, rolls the wrists on a pull to leg
back to pat-ball, as Brook opens the face and guides a push into the covers
Jordan fires in the wide yorker, but it's too wide hits the pitch hard outside off, a firm pull to the leg-side, but straight at deep midwicket. The 200 is up
clipped to the on-side, another single

spliced to Brook at wide long-on! Jordan strikes in his final over for his 100th T20I wicket! Hitting the pitch on a leg-stump line, Stoinis was cramped on the pull and couldn't get the leverage. Still, an important hand
back of a length, thrashed to the leg side, sticks in the pitch and doesn't get up much. This has been a deeply flaccid second half of the chase from England

slower-ball bouncer, Cummins turns down the run! Wade rushed through, determined to get on strike for the final ball, but the lob from Buttler behind the stumps found Jordan who did the needful at the bowler's end
another cutter into the pitch, grips and thumps Jordan in the chest as he misses his pull

cuffed hard into the off-side, a good leap to intercept, the shy comes in but Jordan breaks the stumps before he has the ball, then uproots the stump as Wade tries to sneak another... it's academic with the initial run in the bank... but it could technically be an extra wicket. If this was a critical moment, it would be thrilling! Wade's toe was stretching back into the crease, but the stump wasn't completely out of its hole
width on a full length, a futile boundary to finish! Flashed away through deep third, but it's immaterial. Australia have turned up, England have not!
big turn! Flighted up on a length just outside off. Drifts in before gripping and ripping away past the outside edge
floated up full on off. King comes forward and plays it back to the bowler

huge appeal, and Mukasa has three ducks in a row! He cannot buy a run at this T20 World Cup! Arm-ball, slanting into middle and off. Mukasa, having seen the last ball turn, thinks he can reverse sweep this. Does not account for the ball swerving in and gets rapped right in front. The finger goes up, and Mukasa's horror T20 World Cup continues!
flighted up again, full on middle and off. King gets to the pitch of the ball and drives it to long off
back of a length outside off. Shapes back in and Obuya scuffs it into the off side

goes through everything and everyone! Given a bit of air on a length on middle and leg. Charles goes searching for it well in front of his pad. The ball goes on with the arm, beats him on the inside and goes past leg stump (and the keeper)!
length delivery that starts outside off and swings back into Obuya. He looks for the drive on the up and inside-edges it onto his back leg
very full on middle and leg. Charles squeezes it out towards the bowler
gets it through! Very full outside off. Obuya lets the ball drop and opens his bat face to guide it past cover point!
oh! Given plenty of air on a full length on leg stump. Charles has a huge mow at it and seems to get an inside edge that thuds into the keeper's pads
more turn! Fizzed through on a length outside off. Grips in the surface again and spins appreciably past the outside edge
slow and short outside off. Charles stays back and knocks it to long off to get off the mark
length just outside off. Charles presses half forward and defends
length just outside off. A hint of curve back into Ssesazi and he squirts it off the inside edge towards short fine leg
hard length just outside off. Charles clears his front leg and hacks it down to mid on
Ssesazi off the mark with a boundary too! Short on leg stump. Ssesazi waits for it and swings it away past deep backward square leg!
full toss outside off and Charles will feel he has missed out there. Pushes it straight to extra cover

soft dismissal! Fullish just outside off and buoyed by the last ball, Ssesazi goes after this. Plants his front foot and swipes at it but the extra pace and bounce means he cloths it. Easy catch for Joseph at mid on, and Uganda are two down early!
length on middle and leg. Holds in the surface just a little and Charles taps it gently towards mid wicket. Might have been a cutter
full and swinging into the pads. Ramjani glances it down to fine leg to get off the mark
length on middle and leg. Charles gives himself room and jabs it towards cover point
back of a length on off. Obuya drops it into the off side and Ramjani calls him through for the single
that has been laced! Fractionally short outside off and there is width on offer too. Charles backs away to create even more room and crashes it over cover!
length outside off. Ramjani comes forward and punches it towards cover
floated up full outside off. Obuya plants his front foot and drills it to mid off
shot! Shortish outside off and King cashes in. Stands up on his toes, gets his hands through the ball and cracks it past extra cover!
almost! Back of a length delivery angling into middle and leg. Obuya gets his bat down just in time and squirts it away towards short fine leg
very full just outside off. King digs it out towards mid off and dashes across to the other end
full just outside off. This swerves away and Ramjani makes no contact with his wild slog

peach! Back of a length in the sixth stump channel. Pitches and leaves the batter, beating Charles comprehensively on the outside. But hang on...looks like Miyagi has overstepped, quite comfortably too... Charles capitalises! Slower ball on a full length outside off. Charles plants his front foot and mows it over mid on for four!
gets this away! Fired in on a length on middle and leg. Ramjani brings out the sweep and nails it behind square!
into the blockhole on middle and off. Charles gets his bat down in time and defends
full just outside off. A hint of shape away and Ramjani plays it back to the bowler
does not miss out on the full toss this time! This is outside off and rather than trying to hit it too hard, Charles focusses on timing it. Picks the gap between extra cover and cover point too!

that is adjacent! As plumb as it gets! Darted in on a length on middle and off. Ramjani gets down on one knee and hacks across the line. Swishes at fresh air and the ball pins him on the back leg, right in front of middle. That might have been missing leg stump and off stump....because that was crashing into middle!
dug into the track on middle and off. Rushes onto Charles and he helps it into the square leg region

oh my word, that is an absolute peach! Length ball that starts on off stump and seems destined to angle in. Until....it pitches and decks away a smidgen. That is enough to make Obuya play down the wrong line and he hears the death rattle soon after. Russell can do no wrong tonight!
full and following the batter outside leg. Charles flicks it towards mid wicket
goes for the magic leg-stump yorker but strays down leg. Called a wide fullish just outside off. A hint of shape away and Riazat defends towards backward point
Charles goes big! Off-pace outside off but this is in the slot. Charles has to reach out a touch but gets enough muscle behind it to clear long on!
angled in on a length on middle and off. Straightens a touch after pitching and squares up Riazat as he defends
very full outside leg, designed to cramp Charles for room. He pushes it to mid off and is not happy with himself
back of a length outside off. Riazat hangs back and runs it down to third man for a brace

dropped, oh dear! Fullish just outside leg. Charles has backed away early again and looks to go over mid off. Does not get enough power behind it and Riazat, running back from mid off, is in the game. Gets both hands to it while trying to take it in front of his face but can only palm it over the bar
hard length just outside off. Riazat gets up on his toes and dabs it to third man

that would have been out with a direct hit! A very risky single and King has gotten away with one here. Drove this low full toss straight to mid off and set off for the run. Would have been comfortably short, even with a dive
into the blockhole on middle and off. Waiswa gets his bat down in time and jams it into the his pads
into the blockhole on leg stump, denying Charles the leverage to get under it. He digs it out towards extra cover
tossed up on a full length just outside off. Drifts in before spinning away sharply, past the outside edge
darted in on a length on middle and leg. King advances and pops it over the bowler's head for a couple of runs
floated up further outside off. More grip for Hosein and this rips past the outside edge too
brilliant! A bit of a drag-down but it was intended to tuck King up for room. He stepped so far outside leg, though, that he still had some room to work with. Drilled to mid off's left!
angled in on a back of a length on middle and leg. Riazat is all at sea and gets cut in half, getting rapped on the pads

knocks him over! Darted in on a length on middle and leg. King opts to stay back, possibly playing the trajectory rather than the length. The ball skids on with the arm and King is hurried into his stroke. The ball goes past the bat, kisses the pad and then disturbs the furniture. Big wicket for Uganda!

hot knife through butter! Another arm-ball and Riazat is the latest to fall to it. Does not pick it at all and tries to cut. Has no room whatsoever as it swerves in from outside off and the ball breezes past the bat before knocking back middle stump. Uganda in all sorts of trouble!
length just outside off. Pooran comes forward and plays it back to the bowler
flighted up on a length just outside off. Nakrani lunges forward and plays it with the turn into the on side. Might have come off the pad actually
fullish just outside off. Pooran stretches forward and pushes it down the ground
length just outside off. Waiswa gets down on one knee and sweeps it towards deep square leg
that is going to bring rain! Given a hint of air and this is in the slot on middle and off. Pooran gets down on one knee and slugs it high and long over deep mid wicket!
back of a length outside off. Swings away late and Waiswa is beaten on the outside as he fences at it
angled in on a length, following Charles outside leg. He swings at it and cloths it down to long on
back of a length outside off. Waiswa takes a step down the track and defends
back of a length delivery angled across the batter outside off. Pooran goes fishing at it and is beaten for pace
sharp bumper just outside off. Waiswa does well to duck under it
clean as a whistle! Fractionally short on middle and leg, and Pooran climbs into it. Picks the length in a flash, rocks back and dumps it over the deep square leg fence!
short ball that slides down leg. Waiswa does not get bat on it and the umpire has no qualms in calling it a wide hard length on middle and off. Waiswa gets behind the line and defends
full on middle and off. Pooran presses forward and pokes it towards mid wicket
back of a length on off. Nips back into Waiswa and beats him on the inside. Cops a blow on the thigh pad
fuller just outside leg. Pooran has a swipe at it but misses. Gets pinged on the pads in the process
length delivery outside off that shapes away nicely. Waiswa wafts at it but misses it by quite some distance
full on the pads. Pooran comes forward and turns it towards mid wicket

classic left-arm spinner's dismissal! Floated up on a length outside off. Plenty of revs on this and the ball drops very late on Nakrani. He stretches out, trying to smother it but is nowhere close to the pitch of the ball. The ball grips in the surface too and bursts through the gap between bat and pad. Beautiful bowling!
length on middle and off. Charles stays back and stabs it towards mid wicket
length ball angled into off stump. Masaba looks for the paddle sweep but makes a hash of it. Gets struck on the front pad
length ball on the pads. Charles helps it round the corner towards short fine leg
flighted up full on middle and off. Masaba comes forward and pushes it to long off
fullish outside off. Pooran lunges forward and tips it to extra cover for a quick single
full and wide outside off, shaping back into the batter. Waiswa fishes at it and is beaten on the inside
fuller on middle and leg. Driven straight to extra cover

five of the very best for Akeal Hosein! Another arm-ball that starts outside off and zings back into Waiswa. Like many before him, he has no idea about this. Plants his front foot and then plays outside the line. The ball sneaks past the inside edge and thumps him on the front pad. Kumar Dharmasena gives it out, and even though Waiswa has reviewed, this looked out. Clear gap between bat and ball. Ball Tracking coming up now and it returns with three reds, with the ball thudding into the inside of leg stump!

goes all the way! Fullish just outside off. Charles gets down on one knee and tugs at it. Does not quite middle it but gets just enough to clear deep mid wicket, who was not stationed right on the fence. Had he been, he might have been in the game a little more!
an arm-ball to finish his spell. On a length just outside off and Miyagi, prodding tentatively at it, manages to keep it out
full toss on the pads. Charles glances it towards deep backward square leg
hard length, slanting into leg stump. Masaba is late on the pull and the ball trickles off the thigh pad behind square
off-spinner on a length on off. Pooran advances and defends
shortish outside off. Miyagi lets this zip through to the keeper
back of a length on middle and leg. Pooran hangs back and prods it towards the bowler
hard length on middle and leg. Miyagi tries to get away from the line and manages to fend it down to third man
another massive hit! Slowed up a shade on a length on middle and off. Pooran dances down the track, gets close enough to the ball and launches it over long on!

gloved through to Pooran! Another one bites the dust! Banged in short on middle and leg. Masaba wants to have a crack at this but he is awfully late on the stroke. The ball gets big on him too and he can only feather it through to the keeper. Joseph in on the wicket-taking act now!
fired in shorter on leg stump. Pooran uses the pace and pulls it towards deep backward square leg
brutish short delivery on middle and leg. Kyewuta gets inside the line and sways out of the way, just in time
short down leg and Masaba gets away with it. Charles helps it straight to short fine leg
back of a length just outside off. Kyewuta has a flat-footed poke at it and is beaten, unsurprisingly
floated up full outside off. Charles has an almighty swish at it but only connects with fresh air
very full on middle and off. Pooran comes forward and tucks it off his toes towards deep mid wicket
fired into the toes. Miyagi tries to work it away but does not make contact. Hits him on the pads
length on leg stump. Charles works it away towards mid wicket
tossed up on a length just outside off. Miyagi aims for the moon and misses it by a mile
very full outside off. Pooran squeezes it out towards extra cover
back of a length outside off. Miyagi opens his bat face and dabs it behind point for a couple of runs
length just outside off. Pooran lunges forward and nudges it towards backward point
back of a length outside off. Miyagi goes back and defends
shortish on the pads. Charles is cramped for room and stabs it towards mid wicket
fuller on middle and leg. Miyagi clears his front leg and drags it towards deep square leg
fired in full just outside off. Charles plants his front foot and powers it to long on
fired in full on off. Kyewuta pokes at it and chunks it off the inside edge into his pads
short and wide outside off. Charles sits back in his crease and jabs it past extra cover
back of a length just outside off. Miyagi continues swinging like a rusty gate and is lucky his off stump is not pegged back

miscued, and Masaba strikes! Fired in on a back of a length on middle and leg. Pooran looks for the big heave over cow corner but the ball seems to skid on just a shade quicker than he expects.
