Cannot complete his swing and the ball skews up off the top edge. Masaba calls for it early and completes the catch. Massive moment in the game!
back of a length outside off. Miyagi dabs it down to third man
loopy low full toss on middle and leg. Powell turns it towards deep mid wicket to get off the mark
dug into the track just outside off. Kyewuta picks up the length early enough and sways out of the way
a proper drag-down outside off and Masaba gets away with it because the ball does not bounce a great deal. Charles pulls it towards deep mid wicket and has a wry smile on his face
length on middle and off. Kyewuta comes half forward and pokes it past extra cover for a single

flighted up full just outside off. Powell has a poke at it and squirts it off the outside edge towards short third, who misfields and ends up conceding two extra runs. Nakrani was the fielder in question
shortish outside off. Miyagi wafts at it and only grabs a handful of fresh air

oh dear, another bad misfield by Nakrani! This is short and wide outside off. Charles cuts it straight to short third, who produces his rendition of the Sydney Harbour Bridge. Not a minute Nakrani will want to re-watch!
length outside off. Miyagi gets forward and punches it to deep cover point
four more! Strays onto the pads and gets punished. Powell waits for it, uses the pace and tickles it neatly past short fine leg!
slanted in full on the stumps. Miyagi stabs it past mid wicket and has enough time to get back for two
length on middle and off. Powell comes half forward and pushes it just past the bowler for a single
floated up full on middle and leg. Miyagi presses forward and defends
fuller on middle and leg. Charles knocks it to long on
full on middle and leg. Miyagi has a slog at it and jams it off the inside edge into his pads

watch out on the road! Tossed up a shade on a length on the stumps. Powell comes out of his bunker and seems to not be to the pitch of the ball. Goes through with the swing, though, and smokes it a 107m over long on. That was effortless!
full on middle and leg. Flicked straight to short mid wicket

very full on middle and off. Powell jams his bat down in time and keeps it out. Uh-oh, Nsubuga has overstepped... darted in full on middle and off. Powell clears his front leg and drills it down to long off
nearly! Tossed up on a length outside off. Miyagi reaches out for it and jabs it uppishly, just past the diving Powell at short extra cover
fullish on middle and off. Charles gets forward and flicks it to long on

another big appeal, and another batter falls to the arm-ball! This has been WI's biggest bowling weapon tonight. The ball starts just outside off before coming in with the angle. Kyewuta does not get a big enough stride and does not pick the variation either. Plays all over it and the ball clips the flap of the back leg right in front of middle stump. Kumar Dharmasena raises his finger, and Kyewuta does not bother with the review!
full and slanting into leg stump. Charles pats it back to the bowler
angled in on a length on middle and leg. Miyagi pushes it past the bowler and is happy to run the single. Motie did hit the stumps from mid on but Miyagi had made his ground by then
angled in on a length, cramping Charles for room. He has a swipe at it and misses, getting pinged on the body in the process
short outside off. Nsubuga watches it go through to the keeper
full on leg stump. Charles, standing well outside leg, tugs it towards deep mid wicket
hard length, angling into the batter outside leg. Nsubuga is late on his stroke and the ball rolls away off the thigh pad towards point
shortish just outside off. Grips in the surface and spins away. Powell taps it gently towards extra cover
shortish just outside off. Miyagi gets on top of the bounce and punches it towards deep point. Puts on his skates thereafter and picks up two
fired in fuller on middle and leg. Powell advances and digs it out towards long off
speared in full on middle and leg. Miyagi is squared up and the ball trickles off the leading edge towards deep cover point
oh! Slightly slower on a length outside off. Charles tries to hit it into the ocean but only swats away a few flies

there it is, a whopping 134-run victory for the West Indies! And this is also the joint-lowest team total in the men's T20 World Cup! Length ball in and around off stump. Nips back in a shade with the angle and beats Nsubuga for pace, who anyway had a half-hearted poke at it. Top of off stump is rattled, and that sums up what has been a terrific bowling performance!
fullish, slanting into the pads. Powell bunts it with enough pace towards deep mid wicket and can saunter back for the second
off-pace on a full length outside off. Powell reaches out for it and chunks it off the inside half of the bat towards long on
full on off. Charles pokes it towards extra cover

Charles' struggles come to an end! Sort of summed up by the fact that he has gotten out to a full toss. He could have hit it anywhere but he is almost taken by surprise. Gets it high on the bat and plonks it straight to long on. Intent was not an issue for Charles tonight, but execution was!
slower ball on a length on leg stump. Rutherford does not quite pick it and gets squared up. Pings into his pads
fullish, pushed into the pads. Rutherford works it into the mid wicket region and gets off the mark
full on middle and off. Rutherford comes forward and defends
slides this down leg. Rutherford lets it go and the umpire has to indulge in some exercise length just outside off. Rutherford opts to stay back before jabbing it towards deep cover point
shortish outside off. Powell skips down the track and slaps it to deep cover point
Rutherford gets his first maximum! Half-tracker on middle and leg. Rutherford cannot believe his luck and rocks back to pound it over cow corner!
angled in on a length on leg stump. Rutherford goes back and pushes it towards long on
leg-spinner on a back of a length just outside off. Keeps a touch low and goes under Powell's attempted cut
starts off the over with a boundary! Off-pace but this is too short on middle and leg. Rutherford picks it, delays his stroke and pulls it past deep backward square leg!
slower ball on a length outside off. Rutherford taps it off the front foot towards backward point
into the blockhole outside off. Rutherford squeezes it out towards backward point
length outside off. Powell presses forward and pushes it into the off side
cutter on a back of a length outside off. Rutherford jabs it towards point
low full toss just outside off. Powell knocks it down to long off and retains strike

missed stumping chance! Flat and dragged down after seeing Powell advance. He swishes at it anyway and the ball trickles off the toe-end towards the keeper, who cannot gather and misses a very presentable chance
shortish and following Powell outside leg. He can only jam it off the inside edge into his pads

back of a length delivery way outside off. Left alone by Powell and called a wide Masaba gets the WI captain! This is also shortish outside off and Powell looks to go up and over extra cover. Cannot quite get under it, though, and fails to get the elevation he desires. Obuya leaps up at extra cover and snaffles up a sharp chance above his head!
back of a length on leg stump. Russell waits for it and eases it to deep mid wicket to get off the mark
full outside off. Rutherford stretches forward and nudges it into the cover region
darted in full on middle and leg. Russell knocks it down the ground to long on
off-pace on a length outside off. Russell gets forward and nurdles it to backward point's right
full on off. Rutherford tips it to extra cover and scampers across to the other end
full toss outside off. Russell clears his front leg and hacks it to deep mid wicket
shortish outside off. Sticks in the surface and Rutherford jabs it towards backward point
slower ball on a back of a length outside off. Keeps very low, and Russell misses it by a fair distance
deft touch! Another off-pace ball on a back of a length outside off. This time, Russell holds his stroke and opens his bat face to steer it between backward point and short third!
full and wide outside off. Driven straight to extra cover
four more! Width outside off and Rutherford pounces. Flashes hard at it and scythes it past backward point!

cleans him up with a cracker, and gives Rutherford a send-off too! Sizzling yorker on leg stump. Rutherford, it seems, is not expecting it and even if he was, that was just too good. Awfully late in getting his bat down and the ball thunders into leg stump. WI keep losing wickets!
full toss on middle and off. Shepherd pats it back at the bowler, who in trying to collect and throw it back at the stumps, misfields. No damage done and Kyewuta gives Shepherd a stare as well

speared way down leg. Shepherd leaves it and the keeper cannot gather cleanly either. Two extras added to WI's total oh! In the slot outside off. Russell plants his front foot and tries to tonk that into next week. Only connects with fresh air

edged and four! Full outside off. Russell swings his blade like an axe again and gets a thick outside edge that flies past the keeper!  And it looks like Kyewuta has overstepped too... oh dear! Thigh-high full toss on leg stump. Russell almost seems to lose the trajectory. Swings at it anyway and the ball trickles off his back thigh into the off side
top yorker on middle and leg. Russell jams his bat down in time and the ball rolls away off the toe-end towards the keeper
very full on off. Shepherd plants his front foot and whips it back past the bowler. Bags a brace for his toil
low full toss just outside off. Shepherd cannot get under it but powers it enough to long off's left for a couple of runs
low full toss wide outside off. Shepherd reaches it but cannot beat the fielder at backward point
perfectly-executed yorker on leg stump. Shepherd digs it out towards long on
pin-point yorker on off. Russell can only drag it towards deep mid wicket
Russell finds the fence! Goes for the wide yorker but misses by a smidgen on the shorter side. Russell, sitting deep in his crease, can get under it and blasts it past deep cover point!
superb yorker on middle and off. Russell cannot do anything worthwhile with it and blocks it back to the bowler
four more! Full and wide outside off. The width allows Russell to throw the kitchen sink at it and flay it over backward point!

full and wide outside off again. Too wide, in fact. Beyond the tramlines and some more exercise for the umpire flies away to the fence! In the slot outside off. Russell almost swings himself off his feet and while he does not middle it, the outside edge hurtles away past the keeper!
four more! Russell has that wide yorker line figured out now. This falls short of a yorker and Russell, flashing hard at it, slices it over short third!
just a bye to end the innings! Gets the wide yorker right and Russell cannot make contact. Perhaps a little late in jamming his bat down, and WI have to settle for a bye off the last ball
full and wide. Rizwan leans into a drive. Hardik has a chase on his hands as the pair run three
full and straight, searching for the yorker. Rohit clips it to square leg for a couple. The outfield is very, very slow
full once more, and sliced through the covers from Babar as well. A pair of threes to start off the innings
drags his length back. Rohit defends towards the offside
thick inside edge, nearly chopped it on. Runs down to fine leg and the pair exchange ends
picked up beautifully over the onside. A length ball that he dispatches way over the midwicket boundary. Caught it sweetly out of the middle and it flies away for a huge six
gets his line wrong and the keeper can't collect cleanly, so they come through for an extra wide tailing back into the pads, driven to mid-on
wider outside off at just under 137kph. The batter watches it through to the keeper
back of a length delivery, Rizwan dabs it to backward point
shaping away, this one. Slightly fuller. Rohit prods it to the offside
bit of shape in, and it's driven to cover-point, where Kohli collects smartly
huge appeal from the bowlers, but Babar reckons there's a faint inside edge, and doesn't review. If there wasn't one, that was probably plumb in front
driven down the ground and it sneaks underneath a diving mid-on. Classy drive from the Pakistan captain, and it brings up the Pakistanis' first boundary
a bit of outswing, but it's a half-volley, and the swing only gives Kohli width to free his arms and drive sweetly to the right of cover. Travels quickly even on this outfield
thick outside edge runs down to third man for a single
length ball, top of off, gets his weight moving nicely into the ball to defend it back to the bowler
what a beauty! Landed on length and seamed away, inches away from Rizwan's outside edge. The batter was opened up but doesn't get the edge

width again, but Kohli has slapped this straight to cover point! On the shorter side of a length, a bit of shape away, and Kohli ends up having to reach for the ball, and toe-ends it to Usman, who catches it two-handed over his head. Don't know if the ball stuck in the pitch a little, or if it was just the wide-ness of the line that made Kohli hit it not quite off the middle
punched to backward point for no run

Lovely delivery, slanted across the stumps but finishing close to off, on a good length. Pant presses forward to defend, playing for swing into him, and it keeps going with the angle, or seams away, and beats his outside edge
clipped to midwicket, where it's fielded sharply. Decent comeback from Siraj after the first ball

full, swinging down the leg side. Pant misses the flick, and the diving Rizwan stops the ball - which bounces again in front of him - but lets it run away from him a little, allowing India to steal another run overpitched, too straight, ends up right up at Rohit's toes. Fine leg is in the circle, and Rohit clips it neatly into the big gap to his left
driven back to Siraj, who collects and then wallops Rizwan with the ball in his attempt to run him out. Rizwan doesn't look especially pleased, but they hug it out
length ball close to off stump, lets it come and steers to deep third
sliced past the infield. Jadeja gives chase from point, and they scurry back for a couple
fullish, slanting across Rohit, gets forward and defends towards midwicket
length ball from Bumrah at just under 143, Rizwan defends
fullish, not quite up for the drive, slanting away from off stump. Rohit looks to drive on the up, possibly playing for a bit of swing into him. Keeps going with the angle and beats him
looked to pick it up outside off stump to smear it towards cow corner. Gets a thick inside edge onto his body
length ball slanting across, finishing in the close corridor. Looks to defend with soft hands, gets an edge that bounces well short of slip diving right
Rizwan slapped it straight to Dube at fine leg, where he puts down an absolute sitter! How costly could that be! He didn't have to move, but ends up shelling it

there's that pick-up shot again, but this time he's picked out the fielder at deep square leg! I think Rohit has been done in again by the lack of swing. It was quite full, quite straight, but I would think Rohit was aiming to hit behind square, but it ends up coming off the face of his bat a little awkwardly, and goes to the man on the boundary, who moves a few yards to his left to take it. The ball may have stopped on Rohit too
thick outside edge to third man
full, wide outside off, left alone. Wide signalled. Ended up just beyond the tramline length ball close to off stump, punched to cover
driven down to mid-off for no run. Bumrah unlucky that over
length ball finishing close to the top of middle stump. Stays a little leg side of the ball and defends with soft hands towards backward point
fullish, swinging away fairly wide of off, left alone
slapped back to Siraj, and it's popped out of his hands! Those are the kinds that sometimes stick in the follow-through, but it didn't, and then lands harmlessly from Pakistan's point of view

full, angling in, finishing close to off stump, and Pant gets his head on top of the ball and flicks it to the left of mid-on. The slowness of the outfield allows Shaheen to chase back and pull it back in front of the boundary
back of a length, defended into the onside
swing! Nice length in the corridor, and it leaves the left-hander pretty late. Looks to drive on the up through the covers and is beaten
clipped off the pads and they come through for a single
swing again, but from a shorter length. Axar is beaten again, this time he's looking to cut
length ball again, hits the inner half of the bat as it rolls to midwicket

beaten for the third time in a row. Extravagant swing this time, from a full length that's not quite a driving length. The line is outside off, inviting the drive, but Axar isn't putting bat to this one. Swung a LOT
back of a length, Rizwan dabs it towards first slip, but no run. India have managed to apply something of a squeeze here
very full outside off, opens his bat face and squeezes it down to third
tucked into the onside and they scurry through for a single
back of a length, cross-batted steer from Rizwan to get off strike
length ball outside off, and Axar looks to get low for a flat-bat square drive. Ends up getting a thick edge that races away wide of slip
crunched toward point, but it's straight to the fielder
shot. Shaheen goes short now, and he gets it to climb steeply just outside off. Axar lets it come, and ramps it smartly over slip, an d gets it to carry all the way for six. Lovely bit of timing
back of a length ball. Babar read the length early and slapped it over long-on; the ball runs away to the boundary
full outside off, Axar doesn't quite gets his weight forward into the drive, hits it a little uppishly, but it's in the gap to the right of cover

Bumrah strikes! Sensational catch in the slips. Length ball that shaped back in; Babar wasn't sure whether to play or leave, ends up dabbing it to Suryakumar Yadav at first slip, where it looks like the catch is taken. They're double checking though, but the fingers do look like they're underneath the ball. It's officially confirmed, and India have their first
full outside off, a bit of away-swing. Driven to cover point
nearly had two in two. Whizzes past the outside edge as Haris drove unconvincingly
length ball close to off stump, and it nips back into Pant off the pitch. Looks to dab it square on the off side, and gets a thick inside edge past his leg stump
beats the outside edge once again. Muffled appeal from the Indians, but it missed the edge again. Usman thankul to get out of the over
length ball outside off, gets down on his back knee for a back-cut to the left of deep third. Good, aggressive running to pick up two
driven towards long-off. Usman looked for a run but Rizwan sent him back

thick edge, and it just eludes slip! Full outside off, swinging away, and Pant goes hard at the front-foot drive. Iftikhar throws himself to his left at slip, and it's going quite high too. Can't quite get his hands to it
clipped to long-on as Rizwan fell over slightly

it's all happening. Now Usman Khan puts down a tough chance. Full again, starting on the stumps and swinging away from Pant. Was looking to whip it over the leg side, ends up sending a leading edge ballooning over the off side. Usman turns around at cover point and chases with the ball dropping from over his shoulder, and he gets his hands to it but can't hold on
dances down the track and slaps it over extra cover for a 74m six. That breaks the shackles somewhat for Pakistan after India had begun to dry the runs up
Amir is bowling beautifully here. Length ball nips in from just outside off. Presses forward to defend, and it sneaks through the gate but bounces over the stumps
nudged off the glove into the onside. Rizwan seems to be in a little bit of discomfort and the physio comes out
length ball close to off stump, gets forward and dabs to backward point
short and a touch too high for the umpire's liking. It's called a wide length ball from Pandya, clipped towards mid-on. Pakistan scurry through for another one

four more, and again it's off the edge. What a bittersweet over for Amir. Again it's full, swinging away from the stumps, and again Pant goes hard, looking to whip over the leg side. This time the edge flies high over slip
prodded towards short third. A nervy Usman once more set off before being sent back by Rizwan
fullish outside off, Pant goes for the drive, and it swings away and beats him. No luck at all for Amir. Not much bounce this time, bounces again before reaching Rizwan
comes around the wicket, defended back to the  bowler
struck him slightly high on the bat to mid-off
angling in flat, eased through to point for a single
angling back in and Usman misses once more. It's an uncertain start from him here
tries to pick it up over fine leg but misses. Perhaps it clipped the pad because it's not called wide
bouncer that Usman took eyes off and worked to midwicket to get himself off strike
inside edge nearly chopped onto the stumps. Pant tried to pick it up over fine leg but the shot was never really on
bounces up and hits the hapless Rizwan on the glove once more. He takes it off and may receive a bit more treatment
flat and wide down leg came down the wicket so Iftikhar drags his length back. Eased to long-on
wonder what Usman was doing there. Just looked to hang his bat out away from his body, and nearly set off for a bye for some reason. Gets back in time and Rizwan comes down to tell him to settle down
finishes the over with a boundary. Dances down the track and drives him over his head for four. Gun barrel straight, and he rescues the over for India somewhat
thick inside edge to midwicket and they come through for a single
around the wicket, steered to square leg for a single
length ball outside off stump, driven on the up to mid-off
length ball, defended to extra cover
length delivery once more, defended back to the bowler
nudged into the onside and gets a single

cleans him up! Axar danced down the wicket but misses a straight one which crashes into the stumps. The pressure had built after a good over and a half from Pakistan since the PP and this shot was never really on. Pakistan have the wicket they'll feel they deserve
went deep in his crease to nurdle it to short fine
length ball, SKY prods at it towards the offside
rapped on the pads and Rizwan nearly set off for one before Usman wisely sends him back

splits mid-off and mid-on with a crackling straight drive! Ends the over with a boundary once more, and they salvage something from it. It was slightly overpitched, allowing SKY to lean into that drive
worked to long-off and Rizwan keeps the strike
nearly a run out as Usman set off for a run that wasn't there, and Pandya got in his way as he attempted to make his way back. He would have been run-out if Pandya had hit the stumps, though
topedged and an inrushing Usman cannot take the catch! Didn't get to the pitch of the ball, Pant, and sent it straight up, but gets lucky as it's just far enough away from Usman
eased to fine leg for one
grips and turns, SKY pokes it to short third and gets off strike
comes down the track and slaps Pandya over cover for four. Flat-batted this one and caught it out of the middle as it races away for Pakistan's first post Powerplay boundary
whipped off the pads to midwicket for another couple
Pant trying too much. Attempts another reverse pick-up that's never on and gets nowhere near it
bouncer from Pandya which is pulled away for another single
heaved into the onside and they race through for a couple
slower delivery, but Rizwan read it. Nudged towards midwicket and he keeps the strike. Nine off the over
slaps it to mid-on, doesn't time it yet again, and it falls short of the fielder
comes around the wicket, length delivery. Defended back to the bowler
carved to short third uppishly. Well fielded there
slower ball, and Pant waits for it. Hits it through the line up and over extra cover, and it runs away for four
punched past point. Pakistan thought about two but Dube in the deep was sharp enough to dispel that thought
falls over as he laps it past fine leg, using the pace of the ball to help it to the boundary. That shot is not in the manual, but Pant finds a way of steering it into the precise gap he wants
a bit of grip and it beats Rizwan. The keeper whips off the bails but Rizwan's in his crease
comes back over the wicket but it's on the pads, and Pant flicks it past fine leg once more Haris's pace means he can't afford to err in line
loses his balance as he defends back to the bowler
carved it towards third man and they come through for one
carved to point, but it's cut off
decent delivery to finish off the over. Over 142 kph, and it beats the limply hanging bat of Suryakumar

lovely inside out drive. Came down the wicket and lofted it over the cover region, just wide enough of long-off. Breaks the shackles as the teams break for drinks. Pakistan in charge at the halfway stage, and I leave you with Karthik for the rest of this game

there's that Axar slider going with that big inward angle from wide of the crease. Goes on the back foot, presumably looking to play through the off side, and it hurries on with the angle and he hurriedly jams his bat down. Can't connect, and it beats the inside edge to hit the back pad. Huge lbw appeal, not given, and India have reviewed... It's struck him in front of middle stump, he's on the back foot, the ball doesn't have a long way to go, and HawkEye says it's crashing into a good chunk of leg stump. Axar has struck first ball!!!
smeared towards square leg and they ease through for a single
a bit of flight outside off, and he stretches out to sweep to deep backward square leg
drags it down leg and they come through for the extra run
full, angling into the pads, clipped to the right of midwicket
bottom handed jab attempted but it kept slightly low

and he charges out and smacks him into the stands! A bit of air, and he's out of his crease in a flash. The line is outside off, and that allows him to free his arms and absolutely wallop it over straight long-on
reverse sweep picked up over the man at 45 at it races away. After that early fortune, he's now settling into his trademark, ominous self
back of a length outside off, driven into the covers
comes down the wicket and clips it towards cow corner
length ball turning in towards off stump, clipped through midwicket
punched down to long-off
they need less than a run a ball now. Poor ball, full and angling down leg, and Fakhar flicks and gets just enough bat on it to get it into the gap fine of short fine
tailed in and rapped him on the pads. Muffled appeal from the bowler but it was clearly heading down leg
length ball straightens towards off stump, squares up a little while defending into the covers

scoops it up straight to Amir at mid-off! Yadav never really appeared to catch that as he spliced it into the air, and he can't clear mid-off. Pakistan have a breakthrough, if not the man they desperately want
full outside off, weight not fully forward to drive, plays it in the air but in the gap to the left of backward point
length ball outside off, hung his bat out, no feet,beaten.
back of a length, slower ball, 111kph, finishes on off stump or thereabouts. Defended back to the bowler, off the back foot
length ball to Dube, who defends it back to Rauf
back of a length just outside off, looks to dab it down to third and nearly inside edges into his stumps. Chops it into the pitch off the inside edge and it bounces behind the wicket
back of a length from Haris, reared up slightly. Defended into the offside
shortish, gets up to Rizwan's hip. Swats it round to long leg
carved away through to point and it's a single that prevents a wicket maiden
slower ball, fairly full and angling into the stumps, clipped towards deep square leg
eased into the onside to get Pant back on strike

got him, Hardik gets a big wicket, and Pant takes a terrific catch! Steps out and Hardik bounces him. Well directed, at the front shoulder, cramps him for room, and he only manages to glove his pull. It loops up over Pant's right shoulder, and his weight is initially moving left, because of Hardik's angle. He does so well to turn around, run backwards, mindful of the helmet behind him, and then complete a terrific falling, tumbling catch
spun sharply back in as he steers it to square leg
length ball on leg stump, clipped to square leg
slapped back to the bowler
goes into the pitch, hard length finishing on middle and leg, keeps a bit low. Defended watchfully towards mid-on
grips off the surface once more as its whipped into the inside

keeps low again. Slanted across the stumps this time, finishing outside off, and Imad looks to stand and deliver, punch through cover point. Ends up straightening past his inside edge and beating him. Bounces a second time before reaching Pant
tried to lob it over short third but it hits the pad and they come through for a legbye
shortish, angling in to finish over off stump. Stays leg-side of the ball and carves to backward point. Wicket and just one run off the over
skids this one through and it's driven back to the bowler
back of a length, straightens into the thigh pad with extra bounce. Looks to hop and flick, only manages thigh pad into the off side
opens the face and runs it down to third man
edged, and it runs away. Fullish outside off, straightens off the deck. Throws his bat at a drive without moving his feet an inch. Thick edge flies away wide of Pant, no slip in place

grips in the pitch slightly and it's scooped up to Naseem Shah, who has his third wicket! he did not read that slower ball, got stuck on the crease and just shovelled at it with his hands. Naseem will never have an easier catch off his own bowling, and Pakistan are suddenly rampant
steps out now and Arshdeep bangs in the bouncer. Swivels to hook but can't connect
shortish at the hip, tucked away to fine leg
comes down the wicket and slaps it uppishly towards the general direction of mid-off, but it bounces before it gets there
length ball straightens a touch, in towards off stump. Punched off the back foot to long-off
length ball defended back down the ground
makes a lot of room and Arshdeep follows him with a shortish ball on leg stump. Looks to cut, and bottom-edges into the pitch. Could have easily played on

drags this one down leg and the umpire calls it wide. Oh, wait, it's a no-ball! Naseem overstepped, and India have a free hit Pandya swings like a rusty gate and misses. Naseem gets away with it, and it's a phenomenally good over - two runs and a wicket

bowled him! That shot from Rizwan is going to come under a lot of scrutiny. Swings across the line at a length ball angled into the stumps, and misses. Did it keep a little low? Maybe. Did it pitch fuller than Rizwan expected? That can happen with Bumrah's action and release. Puts a lot of backspin on the ball so it can pitch fuller than it appears. Whatever it was, what a moment!

straight up in the air and Pant falls too! Babar takes an easy catch. India are imploding here  It stuck in the pitch and Pant went high rather than long, and Babar came across from mid-off to take a simple catch
back of a length close to off stump, opens his bat face to try and steer to third, and backward point moves quickly to his left to cut it off

Jadeja goes first ball! This is carnage. Pakistan fans are making all the noise in New York. Just dabbed at one that floated up to Imad at short mid-off, and Amir is off and away! He'll be on a hat-trick and India's middle order has been cut to ribbons
length ball in the corridor. Jabs at it with hard hands and the thick edge bounces well short of slip
length ball, Arshdeep gets in line and defends

looks for the yorker, bowls a low full-toss on off stump. Hits the bat hard as Shadab pushes towards mid-on. They take on the quick single as the fielder, SKY, attacks the ball and does the swooping pick-up and flick. Doesn't hit the stumps
gets across and clips it to fine leg for a single
nice shot. Back of a length, slanting across to off stump. Stays leg-side of the ball and steers to the left of deep third
slower ball, and Hardik lets this one go
fullish, angling away from off stump, gets forward and pushes towards mid-off
lets another one go. Two wickets and one run in that over. On that note, I hand it to Karthik to finish the innings off
Shadab looks to get the left-hander on strike but Rohit at short extra cover moves quickly to his left to cut off the front-foot push. Length ball angling in towards off stump
length ball slanting across, a little late getting forward to defend and it slides past the outside edge
similar ball, gets forward and pushes to long-off instead
back of a length, angling away into the corridor, opens the bat face to steer to deep third
slanted away from off stump, back of a length, no turn back in, and he goes hard at the cut and misses
fullish, close to off stump, steps across first and then gets forward for a push towards mid-off, who's on the edge of the circle
Action replay of the previous ball. Literally
banged in short, angling across the left-hander. Late on the hook, and he doesn't get any bat on it
wow, beaten three times in a row. Skiddy length ball slanting across, though much closer to off stump this time. Looks to punch off the back foot and misses
and there's the yorker, slower one too, 116kph in the blockhole. Dug out square on the off side
now it's shorter and wider, and he slaps it to deep point
shuffles across to this length ball slanting into the sixth-stump channel, and clips it wide of mid-on
looks to make room and Hardik follows him with a fullish ball, swiped down to long-on

Arshdeep heaves one away. Length ball slanting in towards off stump, and he just stands there, opens up his hips, and clubs it away over wide mid-on. Doesn't quite nail it, and it lands and slows down in the outfield, but enough impetus on the ball to pick up four
now Shadab makes room and Hardik follows with a hard-length ball into the hip. Tucked away into the midwicket region, no one inside the circle there
length ball just outside off, hangs back and defends into the covers

steps leg-side again to make room, and Hardik nails the bouncer, angles it in, gets it up to shoulder height, and it gets big on Shadab. Only manages to top-edge the hook into the air, and Pant, sprinting to his left, gets nicely under it. Started with two expensive overs, but Hardik has taken two big wickets since then

did that carry? Doesn't matter, because Rizwan hasn't held on. And it's hurt Arshdeep. Cross-seam bouncer, and Arshdeep gets into an awkward, cramped position while trying to hook. Jams his right glove into his bat handle, and then loops up behind the wicket, teasingly. Rizwan has to throw himself forward to try and catch it, and I don't think it carried. Can't catch it on the bounce either
shortish outside off, cut towards deep point
full, angling in towards off stump, opens his hips and swipes it away through midwicket. Deep square leg moves to his right to stop it
looks to create room and Hardik denies him room, goes into the wicket on a leg-stumpish line. Looks to cut, and the ball bounces over his bat
again, an edge doesn't carry. Steps out and Amir bowls a cutter into the pitch, the line just outside off. Swings across the line, gets an edge to it, but it falls well short of the keeper
2-6 now, and he'll finish with 2-24. What an effort. Looks to make room again, and Hardik bowls a fullish offcutter that finishes around off stump. Swiped along the ground to long-on

wow. Arshdeep takes stance outside leg stump, a long way outside, exposing all his stumps, then jumps across before the bowler delivers. Ends up going full but outside off, and Arshdeep swings and misses, aiming leg side

shortish, angling into the stumps, and Hardik makes room, exposes all his stumps, and rolls his wrists over a back-cut. Thick edge, flies very fine, and the diving deep third, moving to his left, can't cut it off. Naseem seems to hurt his right knee while diving there
length ball finishing on top of off stump, makes room and slaps to deep point
back of a length, nips in to hit the thigh pad as Hardik misses the tuck off his legs

full, angling into the stumps. Almost a yorker. Wristily drilled back down the ground, and it hits the stumps at the other end. And... uh oh, Siraj has overstepped. Not by a lot, but a no-ball nonmetheless. back of a length outside off, flat-batted to the right of deep point

another thick edge, and this time Shadab is back at deep third, and he stops this from reaching the boundary. Similar to the previous boundary, shortish ball that Hardik makes room against and flashes at. Not quite as short as the previous one, and a terrific bit of work from Shadab, throws himself full-length to his left
back of a length outside off, chopped to the right of backward point

taken, Ifti on the leg-side boundary! Length ball angling into the stumps, and Hardik shuffles across and looks for the pick-up flick. Hits it pretty well, but Iftikhar, sprinting left from long leg, intercepts it nicely
looks to make room again and Siraj slants an attempted yorker out towards off stump. Low full-toss, steered to deep point
and he's gone first ball. Full and wide, and Bumrah gets a nice stride in to drive, and he hits it well, but hits it in the air, at chest height, straight to Imad at short cover. India nine down

slower bouncer, ends up looping down the leg side, as Iftikhar pulls out of the pull hard length, angling in towards leg stump. No room at all, and Iftikhar pushes with a straight bat into the vacant midwicket region. Siraj does the chasing himself
looks for the yorker, ends up angling slightly down leg. Steps across and clips to deep square leg

good ball to finish the over, low full-toss at the base of the stumps. Driven back down the ground off the low part of the bat, and Siraj, falling down in his follow-through, can't quite prevent it from rolling down to long-on for one

offcutter grips like an offbreak. Into the pitch, pitches well outside leg stump and ends up the other side of Imad's  body as he tries to make room. Then ends up jabbing at it and gets a thick edge that rolls towards short third
in the blockhole, slanting across to finish jusy outside off. Jabbed to the right of backward point, where Shadab sprints to the ball and throws at the keeper's end, conceding an overthrow

slower short ball, and again it turns like an offbreak. Amazing. Starts outside the tramline, and it's well within it by the time it reaches the crease. By this time, Iftikhar has just left it alone, playing the initial line. Amazing stuff
fullish outside off, plays a checked drive to the right of deep point
into the pitch again, seam-up this time, outside off. Sneaks under the bat as Iftikhar attempts to pull

low full-toss outside off, jabbed towards that deep cover fielder again, and Siraj sprinted out for a second, so the fielder throws at his end as he hurries back that way. Not the best of throws, and the bowler can't collect cleanly either - he may have been unsighted by Siraj running across him - and India get another overthrow
full-toss at thigh height, angling into leg stump. Swiped down to fine leg. Oh, only thigh pad on it.
now Siraj steps across his stumps, aiming for a scoop/deflection over short fine leg. Shaheen goes on pace, length, at the stumps, and beats the batter but it bounces over the stumps

looks to make room again, and slaps this length ball - which is just over the top of off - to the man at extra-cover, right on the edge of the circle. Late to take off for the single, and he ambles in as Bumrah collects the throw and back-flicks into the stumps, and he's juust in when the bails glash

looks to step across and scoop again. This time it's fuller and outside off, and he misses again, or does he get a little touch on it? Pakistan appeal for caught behind, and it's not given. Babar has reviewed... Cross-seam ball, and did it brush the face of the bat as it went? Close, but no contact. Nothing on Ultra Edge

gone, Bumrah strikes with a full-toss, and Arshdeep takes a terrific catch despite almost running into Suryakumar Yadav! Full-toss angling into the batter, about thigh high, and he swings hard at it while cramped for room. Top-edges it high into the sky, and Arshdeep, from fine leg, and SKY, from deep square leg, converge towards the ball, and almost, almost collide. Arshdeep keeps his eyes locked on the ball and catches it nervelessly

ooh, driven in the air, but it doesn't carry to mid-off. But Pakistan get their wicket anyway, because there's a mix-up. Full, angling in towards leg stump, following Siraj's attempt to create room. Drives and almost yorks Babar at mid-off. He picks up and throws to the keeper's end, because while Siraj set off immediately, Arshdeep was slow to respond. Nowhere in the picture as Rizwan collects and whips off the bails. India are bowled out with an over to spare

what's happened here? Arshdeep followed Imad's movement towards the leg side with a blockhole ball, and it goes through to the keeper. It's given out on field, and Imad has reviewed it. Let's figure out what happened here. Yorker slips between bat and back pad as Imad jams his bat down. Did the ball hit the inside edge? Did the bat hit the ground? Ultra Edge suggests it's inside edge, and there's daylight between the toe of the bat and the ground. Well, then, Pakistan are seven down!
full, slanting across, driven to the left of long-off
bit of reverse? Looked to veer in late. Yorker, hits the back leg on the full as Shaheen looks to step leg side and somehow whip it away. Rolls away into the short leg region

wow, Naseem Shah! Terrific shot from the No. 10! Steps across, expecting the attempted yorker at the stumps, and Arshdeep delivers what he expects. Meets it on the full, and scoops it over the keeper, and it runs away despite Siraj's chase from short fine

and he slices it up in the air, and briefly it seems as though it may carry all the way... Full, slantin g away from off stump, and he slices it up and away, to the right of Kohli at deep backward point. Dives to his right, but can't stop it, but all India will worry about is that it bounced before it reached the boundary
and he does his bit. Low full-toss on off stump, jabbed back down the ground, past the other end, and India have defended 119. What a performance, and what a match this has been
back of a length, hint of outswing, timed with confidence as Munsey leans out of his crease, gathered in the deep
round the wicket, hits a good length outside off, pushed off the back foot to point
good line, across the right-hander, bends back in a fraction as Jones holds his bat inside the line
solid loop and grip from Watt, round the wicket again, pushed off the front foot to mid-off
good shape, tighter in at middle stump, Jones hops into line and punches into the covers
out comes his 24-yard delivery, bowled from behind the umpire, chopped to point
lovely length, bending in at the toes with that left-armer's trajectory, punched back down the pitch
clipped off the pads as Oman open their account
stops in the pitch a touch as Bilal holds it back outside off, Jones checks his shot into the covers
top-edged sweep, just over the head of short backward square! Not remotely in control as Watt finds some extra bounce. That shot might be shelved for a while after that!
dangled outside off, just back of a length, Jones cuts but under-edges into the pitch. Very tidy opening gambit
chipped off the pads to the on-side, just another single as mid-on gets down well to gather. Tidy
line and length first up, just a hint of shape on the ball, met with a high-handed block into the off-side
round the wicket, pushed across the left-hander on a full length, clipped to the on-side
cracked back through the line, very high on the blade, it wasn't really there for the shot, with Wheal finding extra bounce to hit the stickers. Swept up behind the umpire
probing line, around the wicket again, met under the eyes with a push to the off-side
gives it the charge, can't connect with a cross-batted wallop
lovely line, darting in at off stump on the angle from round the wicket. Defended into the covers
zip and nip, carries well through to the keeper as the batter bails out and draws his bat inside the line
lifted languidly over the ropes at long-on! Jones has had a look, recognises that Shakeel is skidding them through, so takes it on with style!
an inelegant thump to deep square, again no timing but plenty intent. Hangs in the breeze as the sweeper comes in to gather
flatter trajectory, back of a length, blocked
cracked into the covers, can't beat the ring. Scotland will be very content with this start

makes early room to leg and launches magnficently over long-off! He went so far, it initially looked like he was pulling out of his stance, but he saw the door was open on the off side and clambered through it!
chipped off the toes, and back for the second, might have been close with a direct hit
definite bounce in this deck, good wheels from Sole, wide line, through to the keeper from back of a length
shape through the air from over the wicket, Munsey meets it with a step down the track and picks off an auto-single to cover
more lively carry! Sole thrashes his length and that takes over, over a wild swing across the line
pops at the splice, fenced into the off side
extraordinary six! I've no idea how that carried! A massive leading edge on a lofted drive, miles in the air, three fielders pursuing, and the breeze just launches it way over the rope at deep cover!
a touch of width on a full length, Jones has a massive wipe and the thick edge does the business! Rushes away through deep third. If it's up, it's in his arc
rocks back, cuffed up and over Safyaan at mid-off who rushes back but can't reach it
good riposte, extra nip off the deck, on a good length, Jones gives it the charge and is comprehensively beaten by the extra bounce

whoops, ramped straight to short backward square! A simple plopped catch as Khushi tries to get innovative, sauntering across his crease to access the leg-side, but doesn't quite manage the full Jos Buttler.

hoisted high to mid-off, a splendid back-pedalling catch from Mehran! That's the extra bounce that Bilal produced one ball earlier, forewarned was not forearmed for Jones. Gets right underneath another slash down the ground and Scotland's opening partnership is broken
outside off, clobbered on the up over the covers! The best shot yet from Oman, certainly the most authoritative. Clean through the in-field
crashed up through the covers! Hint of away movement from Wheal but Athavale was equal to it, seizing on the original width!
slung onto a good length, long lanky levers from over the wicket
stump-to-stump response, trapped on the crease but no danger of an appeal
half forward to the good length, pushed across the left-hander
attempted hack across the line to a shorter ball, thumped on the back hip as the ball deflects to point
slashed outside off, a top-edge sails high over deep third! It's against the wind this time, but it matters not, that travelled as if in the moon's atmosphere!
full length, into the toes, nudged behind square
hacked off the pads, no timing on the lofted stroke across the line, and it falls short of deep midwicket
slapped aggressively across the line, taking on the shorter ball with a lofted hack... eludes the in-field but doesn't have the timing to roll away
tight line, full length, half-forward and squeezed to the leg-side
much better strike! Rolls through a leg-sided short ball and cuffs it through backward square
bottom-handed chunk, into the leg side, another single to keep the strike
superb pick-up off the toes! Full and sliding into the pads, Ilyas gets underneath his stroke and uses the breeze to lift it all the way!
round the wicket again, fired in at the right-hander, who pats back up the pitch
good adjustment, angled in at middle and off on a full length, clipped to mid-on
flogged on the front foot, and through the gap in the covers. Right under the eyes on impact, forcing it square of the fielders. Lovely
back and across, right in behind the short ball, pushed to cover
under the eyes once more, another push to cover, this time for a single
hits the deck outside off, good carry to the keeper, past another hopeful wipe
so nearly bowled round his legs! Munsey lines up the reverse paddle, he misses out as Shakeel spears it in, and it wriggles past the stumps and the keeper too
swiped across the line, gathered at deep midwicket
crunched straight and hard, past long-on! Meeting the full toss with fierce timing
fuller length, crashed uppishly through midwicket, Greaves sprints, dives, and does brilliantly to keep both himself and the ball inside the rope
met under the eyes on the back foot, picks off another single into the covers, Munsey keeps the strike
punched off the pads for another single
genuine edge, but there's no slip! A dive from the keeper, I suppose on reflection he played for that... but still, closer to the keeper than he perhaps intended!
enthusiastic appeal for lbw, but McMullen was a long way down the track as that thumped him high on the knee-flap

Nailed on the pads, up goes the finger! If there's no bat this looks plumb, but Ilyas has sent it upstairs... not sure it was an instant review though... there is no bat... it's angled in at leg stump, very full and probing length, and umpire's call is the call! Fair enough from the umpire, one of those that definitely looked to be hitting, and sure enough, the bails would have come off!
cracked at short cover, out it pops! That's a flying attempt from Zeeshan, grabbed with both hands in the air to his right, but dropped!
squeezed away for a first-ball single
flogged out through the covers again, changing the length with a shimmy out of the crease, and drilled past the in-field
right up to the toes, and clipped with oodles of timing through backward square. Perhaps a touch more leg-sided than the Ilyas dismissal but similar intent from the bowler
crashed on the up to bring up the fifty! Scotland are finishing the powerplay with intent, makes room to leg and lets the hands do the rest!
cramped on a leg-stump line, fended down into the crease
another step down the pitch, thuds the pads, deflected behind square
smashed on the up, over extra cover! A feisty end to Oman's powerplay, a confident step into the length and cracked firmly to the rope
cuffed out into the covers
tight line, shovelled off the legs to midwicket for a single
rocks back, and that's rifled through the covers! Skids on from back of a length, made room early, nailed the timing
round the wicket, looped onto a good length, tucked behind square
back of a length, pace off, tucked into space at midwicket
back over the wicket, tight lines to Zeeshan, tucked with the spin to the on-side
extra air this time, dipping on the crease, punched to mid-on
poor fielding from Scotland! Munsey at backward point can't intercept a dinky open-faced dab to deep third
reverse-sweep, pinged over backward square! That's magnificent, into position early, solid base, the ideal length from the bowler, and hoisted up and over, onto the grass banks!
nudged off the legs, they wanted two, but Athavale is sent back! The shy goes to the wrong end, he was toast!
two in a row! Even with the fielder back on the rope, Munsey trusts his timing to clear the ropes and he does so brilliantly!

extra bounce and Cross grabs the edge! Lovely line from Watt,kicking off a good length from over the wicket, Zeeshan opened the face but couldn't get enough bat on his attempted glide. The keeper did the rest
outside off, back of a length, flogged out to cover
full length outside off, pushed to the on-side for a single to mid-on
sets himself early, outside the line of off, meeting the wide line with a toe-ended lift, straight as you like, not timed but placed so well, and into the rope
skids through outside off, just eludes the edge! Loose from Kail, opening the face to an outswinger, and misjudging that extra bounce
the wheels are coming off now! Fired down the leg side, Munsey's angles messing with the bowlers, the keeper has no chance of cutting that off outside off, chopped out to the off side
taken on the splice again from a good length, low hands out to point where McMullen pounces
blatted across the line! Munsey wants to finish this in a hurry! Steps into the length, swings into a sweep, hoisted onto the grass again!
short ball, swished off the helmet out to midwicket to get Kail off the mark

leading edge on another hack, and Munsey goes! Caught in the wind, swirling at short backward point, Shakeel watched it well as it swirled down, and clung on. The end of a feisty knock that has set Scotland firmly on course
attempted yorker, fired in at the toes, clipped to the on-side
good length angling in on the stumps, Berrington taps it back down the track
hits the pitch from just back of a length, soft hands on the back foot to pick off a single to the on-side
round the wicket, angled in at off stump, pushed into the off side
looped up and battered through cow! All along the ground but hit with scintillating power, leaves the two men in the deep standing
a touch of width, gets on top of a chopped cut out to point, mopped up in the deep
flighted from round the wicket, this grips a touch and McMullen defends
increases the angle into the legs, attempted sweep but no contact pace off from back of a length, poked out to cover for another single, reaching for the extra width
stretches on to the front foot and dabs one through backward point
clipped to the on-side
tossed up, 84kph outside off. Berrington drops deep and cuts into the gap at backward point. Good running brings them three, though the Oman fielders rather dawdled in pursuit

That will be a deeply satisfying dismissal for Scotland! Kail punches a single into the covers, completes his first run, is sent back for the second, and the shy comes in for Watt to ping down the bowler's stumps with glee!
patted away towards point
on the back foot, outside off, whipped to the on-side for another single
biggedy-biggedy bonged! McMullen greets another flighted delivery with a mighty mow down the ground, straight and true over the ropes. Brings up the Scotland hundred in fine style
smoked through extra cover! Little bit of air and room to swing the arms outside off. Berrington crunches his first four
round the wicket, fenced off the back foot to the on-side
tossed up straight and dabbed back towards the bowler
fired in at the pads, clipped to the on-side
uses the feet, clobbered all the way! Berrington saunters down and dumps his opposite number over long-on
down on one knee for a slog-sweep, not totally timed but finds space in the deep
googly, beats him on the inside, a good comeback from Ilyas
pressing forward and mopped up at long-off

another wrong'un, slides through the gate and hits middle! Ilyas exacts a measure of revenge after an expensive start to the over. Flighted delivery outside off, Berrington done by some drift and just enough turn to beat his expansive drive
faster and flatter, skidding in at the stumps and defended
tossed up, possibly another googly, hits the front pad... heading down, I think. Cross doesn't look too perturbed, and no review forthcoming from Oman
tight line across the right-hander's bows, met on the back foot with a push to point. That will be drinks
round the wicket, back of a length outside off, 136kph/84mph. Ayaan tucks it down towards backward point
boshed over cover! The fielder in the deep should probably do better but can't prevent it skipping away for four
pitched up and pushed to mid-off... they pinch one, despite a direct hit at the non-striker's end
dropped in the deep! McMullen gets another life, despite picking out Rafiullah pretty comfortably on the midwicket fence. Running chance but he should have held on
short ball from over the wicket, Athavale completely miscues his pull but it loops over the head of Sole and lands safely short of mid-on
angled in and pushed down the ground
length ball angling in, flicked away through backward square leg
flattish outside off, defended square
shortish into the hip, Ayaan nudges it square for one more
angled in and dragged away on the sweep for one
short and biffed on to the grass banks! Athavale pops his head up to take on the short ball, and gets it away emphatically over deep backward square leg. Oman need a few more of those
flat on the stumps, McMullen drips back and picks out short cover
tossed up, spinning away and dabbed into the covers
round the wicket, flighted and dipping, clips a leading edge... but lands short of Leask in his follow through
swiped down the ground as McMullen stretches on to the front foot. Kushi makes a bit of a meal of it at long-on
stretches out and drives back to the bowler
steered to backward point
length ball, defended coming across on off
floated up and belted through long-off! Strong bottom-handed thrash through the line, Ilyas can't get a hand to it and the ball races away
pushed through quicker, up at 98kph and defended to leg. Leask scampers across to prevent one
crunched over cover, the fielder's dive is in vain! Fifty up for McMullen, from 27 balls, he raises the bat to the team balcony. Been a fine knock since coming in during the powerplay
flat on the stumps again, 93kph and turned to the on side where the bowler again cleans up. Five dots now
oof, beats the outside edge! Some grip and turn, McMullen plays down the Bakerloo. Wasn't far from hitting the top of off, either
loses his clean sheet by pushing one down leg full and chopped down into the ground, back past the bowler for a single. Just two off the over, though
round the wicket, looped up at 89kph. Cross nurdles it towards point
round the wicket, angling in and tapped down... there's another direct hit at the non-striker's but Athavale was back
down on one knee, hoicked with the breeze! Firm slog-sweep from McMullen for a 76m six over deep backward square leg
short ball with pace off, 120kph and rising around the ribcage. Ayaan defends from the crease
drops back and slaps one past the diving Ayaan to long-off
back of a length and heading down leg, another slower ball, swatted fine for a single
targets the leg side, slogged all the way! Cross plants the front foot and heaves heartily across the line
Athavale looks to come down so Wheal bowls full and wide, pace off again. He has to stretch and guides it past cover for one more to the sweeper
repeats the dose! Using the wind, it's not a long hit to that side, plops over the boundary boards at deep backward square leg again
full and fast, 134kph/83mph and skids into the pads with Ayaan attempting to flick across the line
quicker and flatter, beats the edge as Cross aims a cut
slower ball banged into the pitch, tucked off the body for a quick single to finish
short ball, swung away through square leg, Scotland smash their chase to win by seven wickets! And that will do wonders for their net run rate, too
slashes and gets enough on it, skewed past the keeper and short third won't be cutting that off!
tries to come down, Leask drags his length back. Defended
fired wide of off, 101kph and Ayaan rocks back to steer a cut behind square
pushed through, 95kph offbreak on fifth stump, stabbed to backward point for a quick single
stays round the wicket, angled across the right-hander, who dabs to short third

dropped over the rope at long-on! Munsey the fielder, and he thought he had it...! Looked like Athavale had fatally underclubbed his swipe down the ground, Munsey got both hands to the ball, but somehow shelled it for six
round the wicket, angled across outside off and pushed away

missed stumping! Scotland not putting these chances away... Cross was unsighted, to be fair, as Ayaan stepped out and Watt fired it down the leg side. But the keeper fumbled the chance floated up and tapped back watchfully
tries to swing to leg, takes it on the body
reverses the stance, hoicked for four behind point! Lovely invention from Ayaan and he nails the shot into the wide open space
speared in full, 104kph and shovelled into the leg side for two
looped up this time, pace down to 80kph. Ayaan uses the feet and whips through midwicket
over the wicket, pitching on off and tapped away
full toss, but Ayaan doesn't put it away. Clubbed through midwicket for one
floated up and Athavale is across to prod it away

holes out to deep midwicket! Greaves has burgled a wicket and it's a big one, that of the set opener, Athavale. Shuffled across and forced to hit into the wind, never got hold of it. Well held by McMullen running in
length ball, 96kph and skidding into the pads
tossed up a bit slower and Mehran gets off the mark but bundling one into the leg side
short outside off, 130kph and sliced rumbustiously down to deep third
round the wicket, goes full and targeting the stumps, 122kph/76mph. Flicked through square leg
length ball angling into the right-hander, deflected up and away to the left of the keeper
whipped away through midwicket
some tonkage for the Oman cause! Goes deep in the crease and picks the change-up, battering it back over the head of mid-on
full, straight, pace off again, flicked out to deep backward square leg
over the wicket, pace off outside off, the ball sits up but Mehran can't time his pull across the line
full, 129kph/80mph outside off, slapped down to long-on
low full toss, pumped down the ground! Sharif misses his yorker and Mehran connects with a lofted straight drive
short ball with pace off, 109kph. Swatted away to deep square leg
wide blockhole from over the wicket, squirted away to deep backward point
short ball, tickled behind! Sharif hits the deck outside off, Mehran aims a swing across the line but can only manage a faint top edge through to Cross. Scotland chip out another at the death
round the wicket, pace off and back of a length, worked through square leg
slower ball in the channel, swing and a miss from Rafiullah
goes pace on this time, 131kph/81mph and beats another almighty swing

full and wide, boshed down the ground... straight to long-off! Rafiullah clearly understood his brief but slices across it slightly aiming an almighty slog. Picks out Sharif for a straightforward catch a few yards in
pace off from round the wicket, dinked into the backward point region
length ball, another change-up, glanced fine for a single. Ayaan will keep the strike for the final over
goes full and wide from over the wicket, scuffed towards mid-off... a direct hit would have been gone, but they pinch another on the overthrow!
chopped past the keeper! Big ole inside edge defeats the leaping Cross and brings Ayaan another boundary
full and slammed through midwicket! Pace on from Sharif and it disappears off the bat with interest
full, 128kph and right up in the blockhole, but Ayaan digs it out into the leg side and they scamper two as the boundary rider runs in
goes for the yorker again, dug out down to long-off
full and bunted down the ground, they'll come back for two. Oman raise 150 from the final ball, but Scotland will be pretty happy with their work
Sighter for Tanzid. He got room and the length was too full but the swing kept it taking away and he didn't look to play it
on a good length on middle, and angling across towards off. De Kock dabs it down on the pitch
Whoa, that rises sharply after going past the batter. QDK has to take a full ball above the head. Was outside off and Tanzid let it go

whipped over deep backward square leg! The typical pick-up shot from de Kock, as he gets fuller delivery from Sakib, with the ball finishing around off after angling away. De Kock took a step down the pitch, and swung deep into the stands
Pitched up on leg, helped away to deep fine leg. Leg glance is a gift for a batter today
crashed to deep midwicket! Sakib pulls his length back, and goes on the shorter side of a length. Again this one ends around sixth stump, as de Kock pulls forcefully
Swing away offers Tanzid room, but he reaches out with bat far away from the body and is beaten.
hints to step down the pitch, and pokes this good-length ball on off towards cover
Shortish ball around off has Shanto hop and defend it towards point
ahh, slower ball already, as he bowls fuller on middle and off. Clipped to deep backward square leg
Sharp away movement again, 137ks, on a wide-ish length, Shanto takes a big stride across and tries defending to cover, ball zips past the shoulder of the bat to the keeper

just half an appeal for lbw, and given out! A deafening roar from the Bangladesh supporters shakes New York up. Sakib angled this in and bowled on a length on off. The ball just about hinted to straighten away, as Hendricks defended on middle stump. But he was hit on his back leg, with the ball also seemingly staying a little low. A first-ball duck for Hendricks
He might've looked for swing but if it's that far wide and overpitched, Tanzid will go after it. This time he nailed the drive through cover, bulleted along the grass
bowls very full, while angling it across towards off. Driven to mid-off from deep in the crease

Uppish, catchable height but in the gap behind point. Tanzid threw his bat again, this ball was just as full and a little less wide. More suitable for the booming drive but he got it slightly off the edge. Can't fault the intent, which is on point
swung away over deep backward square leg again! A length delivery from Taskin which angles across and lands around middle and off, only for it to barely straighten in. Swiped for six more
Length around off, defended to cover
bowls on the shorter side of a length just outside off, as this one angles in. Stabbed to deep third by de Kock, as he plays late
Length outside off, defended to cover
fullish length, and angling into middle and off. Pushed to mid-off as he leans into the shot
Rabada's finding his radar now. Hits the fuller side of length, around off, Tanzid ducks a bit to defend it to cover
ahh, nice line and length. He angles this in, and lands this on a length on fourth stump. It goes on straight after pitching, as Markram lets it go

Big sound as Tanzid tries to flay it square. Don't think all fielders were sure but Rabada was and the finger goes up. Tanzid has a long chat with his partner and decides not to review. He wasn't sure, but Ultra-Edge shows the sound came with ball taking the edge. Was a fullish 142ks ball that was angling away wide of off. Not a great ball but luck and extra bounce was on Rabada's side
goes fuller this time, and on middle. Driven to mid-off again
Length on middle and off, zips in at 144ks to hurry Tanzid. But he manages to tuck it to short fine leg
short of a length, and a bit wide of off, as Sakib bowls from wide of the crease. De Kock looks to slash, but is beaten
short delivery outside off, and he pulls with a swivel to deep backward square leg. It goes to the longer side of the ground, and they pinch three
ahh, another slower ball, and de Kock can't read it. On the fuller side of a length in the channel outside off, as the ball seams away after de Kock looked to push
ahh, beaten! On the shorter side of a length on middle and leg, and angles across nicely to beat his attempted poke on the outside edge. Again there is some extra bounce

some extra bounce off a fullish length, and called wide. It even landed on a 12th-stump line, as de Kock let it go bowled him! The ball just about clips the side of off stump, as de Kock looked to pull but missed. Sakib bowled on a length in the channel - it was around sixth stump - as the ball angled in from around the wicket. De Kock pulled, perhaps expecting more bounce than what he got, and he missed. Another early strike for Bangladesh
another one on the shorter side, and this pitches outside leg. Litton gets across to look to hook, but is beaten again, as the ball goes over his gloves
on a good length on off, and defended back on the pitch

this is wide outside leg. Shorter side of a length outside leg again, and Litton lets it go ohh, past the outside edge! He looks to defend this length delivery pitching on middle and shaping away considerably to go away from his bat as he looked to block
short of a length in the channel again, and dabbed toward point, as he sends Markram back
shorter side of a length on middle, and shaping away to finish outside off. Pushed to point
on a length on middle and off, and clipped to square leg
six over the bowler's head! He skips down the pitch, and lofts this length ball angling across towards middle and off. The ball just cleared the boundary

beaten! Taskin tests Markram from this end after wickets by Sakib from the other. The ball again got some extra bounce, as it went over off stump after shaping in off a length from outside off, with Markram looking to push but getting beaten
fuller length, and shaping away towards off. This keeps low, as Shanto squats to block it down
driven through extra cover! Another length delivery by Taskin, but this lands on fifth stump, and Markram beats extra cover to his left after leaning forward
full delivery angling across and finishing on off. Driven to mid-off
short of a length on middle and off, and shaping in sharply to hit his front pad outside leg, as he looked to clip

ohh, a run-out chance! Confusion between Shanto and Litton, as the latter sends the former back after Shanto is more than halfway down. Shanto tapped at this full ball on middle and off towards cover and took off, by Litton didn't seem interested
good bounce off a shortish length on fourth stump. The ball angles in towards middle and off, and Markram goes deep in the crease to block
full again, and slanting across to end outside off. Driven to mid-off

ahh, gone! Bowled Markram, too! The stadium in New York is trembling after those moves from the Bangladesh fans. Taskin angled it in, and bowled on a length around off. Markram went for the drive, and played it from the middle stump. But the ball went on straight after pitching - there seemed to be no movement - and hit the inside half of the off stump
on the shorter side of a length on middle and leg, and dabbed down on the pitch, as the over ends with five dots in a row
short of a length just outside off, and angling in. He skips in the crease to dab it down
backs away and looks to heave, but is beaten. A length ball just outside leg from Jansen, as Litton went to attack with his front leg out of the way, but couldn't connect
shortish length just outside off, and blocked down towards point
ahh, Litton is hit on the box off the inside edge! There is an ohh from him after being hit! Short of a length on middle and leg from Jansen, as Litton went to pull but got an inside edge

spooned to short cover! Looked like the ball stopped on to Stubbs. Well taken by Shakib diving forward, as he went low while the ball died on to him. A short-of-a-length ball from Sakib in the channel outside off, as Stubbs went pushing at it by riding the bounce. He presented the full face of the bat there, but I think the slowness of the pitch played a part in the ball just chipping off his bat
flung away to long leg! The man at fine leg is at a straightish position, though. Again short in length from Jansen, and finishing outside leg after angling in. But Litton swivels to pull it hard
good line there. Bowls on a length on middle, and gets it to angle across towards off, as Miller blocks back after opening his stance up
on the shorter side of a length on middle and leg, and clipped to fine leg
short of a length on middle and leg, and he hints to get across to nudge to fine leg. The bounce on the pitch contiues to be true
looks to push at it tentatively, as the ball is on a length and wide-ish of off. He ends up dabbing it down on the pitch, though, with the ball stopping on the pitch
on a good length just outside off, and seams back in towards middle and off. Punched to mid-off
bowls a bouncer just outside off, and Shanto has to sway out of the way to let it go
goes slightly fuller than the previous ball, and bowls on a length on off. Pushed towards mid-off, as he leans into the shot
fuller side of a length, and angling into off, as Litton opens the face of the bat to loft over cover. It isn't all that well timed, but the ball still dribbles away
fullish again, and angling in from over the wicket. Pitches just outside off and shapes to come in, as Miller defends after going low
ahh, almost bowls him! Rabada goes on a fullish length outside off, as Litton got across to swipe. But the ball hit his front leg and popped up, only to drop close to the leg stump
ohh, slower delivery from Mustafizur, who bowls on a length just outside off. The ball comes in towards off, as Miller defends off the inside edge, with his bottom hand off
short of a length, and shaping into middle, as he clips towards mid-on
ohh, nearly dragged on! He goes slashing at this length ball around sixth stump, and gets a bottom edge running wide of leg stump. A single to fine leg
shorter side of a length on sixth stump, and stabbed to point away from his body
angles this in on a length on fifth stump, as Klaasen dabs to point
now manages to guide this length ball around fifth stump, and places it to deep third
short delivery rising sharply on middle after angling across from leg, as Klaasen skips to tap it down
ahh, the inside edge goes past the off stump! He looks to drive at this fullish ball just outside off, but plays early. The ball rolls away past short fine leg
change of pace, as he goes for the offcutter on a length on leg. It angles away towards middle, and is blocked

flung to extra cover! A simple catch arriving in front his stomach. Maharaj tossed this one up, and got it to dip on a very full length on leg stump. Litton had made room, and went to drive hard, but ended up chipping straight to Miller. Clearly beaten by the flight and the dip, even as he played it as a half volley
full ball angled across from over the wicket, and pitching on off. Blocked on the pitch
ohh, Maharaj slows it down, and bowls full just outside off. The ball turns in, and is swept to fine leg
goes heaving across the line, and gets four between long-on and deep midwicket! Fullish ball angled across towards off, as he risked going to the leg side, and just found the gap
full and angled into off, as he leans forward to push to Maharaj's right
slows this down, and bowls full on off. Tucked back to the bowler's left
excessive turn, and this is called wide! Lands fullish on leg, and ends up wide of  leg, as Shanto lets it go quite full on middle and leg, and paddle swept to fine leg
ahh, this one turns in off a length on middle and leg, and is clipped behind square
he skips down, and jams down at this length ball on off for a single to long-off
ahh, sharp turn and bounce! Dipping on a fullish length on off, and turning away and rising nicely, as Klaasen looked to poke but withdrew his bat in the end
reverse sweeps this full ball angling into middle and off, and gets two to deep backward point
short of a length, and turning into middle and off. Punched to wide long-off, as the man at extra cover dives to his right in vain
goes wide of the crease, and bowls on a length on middle. Clipped to deep backward square leg
angles this in, and bowls fullish on off. Driven to mid-off
goes a touch fuller than the previous ball, and bowls on leg. It shapes away a bit - and with good bounce - and Shanto nudges it back
fullish length, and angling across to land on fifth stump. Klaasen looks to drive, but is beaten
goes on a length this time on leg, and is clipped to a straightish fine leg
driven just past mid-on's left! Slower ball on a full length, and angling away to off. Klaasen reads it and plays late to beat the man inside the circle

chipped to short midwicket! Nortje bangs it hard and into the pitch, and Shakib ends up with a tame attempted hook. The short ball on middle angles across and finishes outside off, even as it also gets big on him. Shakib went ahead with the shot, but ended up getting the ball off the higher side of the bat. Seemed beaten by pace there
short of a length this time on leg, and shaping away towards middle and off. Dabbed down from deep in the crease
ahh, an overthrow allows the third! Short of a length on off, and clipped to fine leg by Hridoy. The throw comes to de Kock, who can't collect it to his right, and lets it go
flies towards deep third, but lands well short! He goes slashing with a flat bat at this very full ball angling across and finishing wide of off. The ball took the top edge and was flung away
short of a length, and rushing through at middle and leg. He hops and dabs it down
on a length on off, and hinting to shape back in, as Miller clips this to fine with his bottom hand off
wow, this turns away! Drifts in on a length on middle and turns away, as Hridoy looks to push but is beaten
fullish length around sixth stump, and flashed to deep point
bashed over long-on! Backs away, and pumps this fullish ball angling into middle and leg with the full and free swing of the bat
on a length on middle, and angling in towards leg. Punched to long-off

ohh, this again turns away off a fullish length on middle, and is pushed to point. The throw at the keeper's end is wide - de Kock himself ran towards point - and there was no one collect, as Bangladesh get two
Fuller side of a length on off, and keeping a little low. Miller looked to clip, but ended up nudging to cover off the outside half of the bat
very full on middle, and nudged to midwicket
turns in slightly from a full length just outside off, and is flicked to deep midwicket
this turns away from middle and leg, and is clipped to fine leg
on a length on the stumps, and punched to long-off
full and just outside off, as Shakib pushes it back. Maharaj dives to his right to stop this
length delivery wide of off, and slapped to deep extra cover to keep ticking
on the bounce to Jansen at slip! Hridoy goes to drive at this cutter on a fullish length in the channel outside off, and gets an outside edge
on a length on the stumps, and punched to cover
on a good length just outside off, and tapped down on the pitch
ahh, nice turn! On a fullish length on off, and goes away sharply, as Klaasen thought of poking but let it go
another dot ball, as he taps at this good-length delivery shaping into off. Played to point
launched deep into the stands! He goes over the bowler's head, as Rishad tosses it up and bowls full on middle and off, but Klaasen presents the full face of the bat to club it
has Hridoy hopping at this sharp bouncer rising on middle. Hridoy gets it to fine leg after leaping, and getting his front leg out of the way
bam, six more! Short of a length on middle now, as Rishad pulls his length back. But Klaasen shifts his weight back, and pulls hard over the longer boundary at the ground

taken at a shortish square leg position! Markram, placed towards midwicket, scampers towards square leg and grabs this. Another bouncer gets a wicket for Nortje. Shanto went hook - like Shakib had - but the pace of 146kph had him struggling, as the ball jumped on to him, and went off the top half of the bat
on a length on off, and turning away. Hacked to deep point
short delivery on off, and shaping in to finish on leg. Wide not called, even as Mahmudullah ducks
