ohh, this turns in off a length just outside off. Miller slashes to short third after being cramped for room, and takes off. The throw at the non-striker's end is wide of the stumps, even as Miller dives

Edge and Litton drops it, Mahmudullah's hands are on the floor in disappointment! Was a sharp deflection off the bat and Litton got hurried, it hit his left groin as the gloves went low. Got nothing on it in the end. His knees weren't bent as much on his stance, which might have cost him. Was an 82ks fullish ball angling into leg, Miller played for the line - tried defending towards cover - and the bat angled away further, leading to the edge
angles this in, and bowls full on fifth stump. Driven to short cover
Full ball is pushed to long-off
heaves at this fullish ball angling into middle and off, and gets if off the inside half of the bat to deep backward square leg
Smart play from the Klaasman. Goes back and tucks the length ball to midwicket for a quick couple. No one in the ring there
fuller length angling into off, and pushed back towards mid-on
Klaasen tries something similar but Mahmudullah, probably thinking like a batter, darts it in at 90ks on a fullish length. Beats the close-faced flick and hits pad

flashed off the outside edge! Some lick goes Mahmudullah's way, as he advances down the track after making room. The ball is on a short of a length outside off, and he hacks, and gets it off the outside edge to beat deep third
Pushes the fullish ball outside off to deep point
the man at point dives to his left, but can't get a hand. Mahmudullah had tapped at this length ball angling in, and got two wide of deep third
Defends it forward
fuller length, and shaping into off. Driven to mid-on
length  delivery just outside off, and nudged to mid-on. And it is a no-ball bowls this on a length on sixth stump, and from the back of the hand. Swatted to mid-off
Clips the length ball to square leg
shorter side of a length on off, and finishing on middle. He skips in the crease to block it down
Clips a length ball through the leg side
again goes on the shorter side on middle and off, and it is clipped to midwicket

Taskin straightens the ball from around the wicket to beat the edge. 133ks on a length, went through around the fifth-stump channel, Miller tried defending with a straightish bat. Litton keeps him in check by shaping to underarm and run him out a la Carey to Bairstow
on a good length on the stumps, and flicked to midwicket again, as he has to leap in the crease
Guides the length ball from outside off to deep third

through Jansen's hands! Mahmudullah had swayed out, and guided at this short-of-a-length ball rising on middle and off. He opened the face of the bat and let it go, as Jansen moved to his left and missed the ball
Taskin keeping it simple. Bowling length and trying to let the pitch misbehave. This was in the channel too but went straight, Klaasen opened the face and patted it late. Found backward point though
back of a length, and angling into leg. Clipped to fine leg
Goes further up and a bit wider but Klaasen doesn't go for the big hit. Instead, he pushes across with the front foot and pushes it to the right of point
Fullish ball just outside off, holds up in the pitch a bit. Mahmudullah had to check the straightish blade, guides it to mid-off
Not short by any means but Klaasen stays upright and carves it to the left of deep-backward point. In fact, he hopped leg side to make room after the ball was delivered. Luckily, the bounce was even
Fuller side of length outside off, guided towards cover
Punches the length ball around off to long-off. 90ks
On the pads, clipped to deep square leg
Full and a bit down leg, 90ks, Miller happy to clip it between deep square leg and deep-mid for two
Slower one on a length, clipped off the pads to deep square leg
Pitches up on leg peg, clipped to square leg's left. 89ks but seemed slow
Length in the channel, defended with an open bat face

Extra bounce has Klaasen pull out of the cut, big turn too. Klaasen tried to hop across and cut it like he did in the first ball, but the slightly fullish ball ragged away to keep the bat from going through with the swing
Shortish just under the armpit, Hridoy hops as he rides the bounce well and glances it to deep fine leg. 138ks

Turn again, beats bat again. Litton takes off the bails, not sent upstairs by the ump. Was a fullish ball that landed outside off and went away (legbreak), Klaasen tried pushing to cover with a straight bat
Hridoy makes room ample room but Maharaj gave it air while following him. Ball landed around middle and leg and straightened a bit
Driven to the stumps at the non-striker's end. Fizz might've got hands on it but Miller backed up well, slid the back early.
Tucked to the leg side
Bumper just outside off at 135ks got good pace and bounce, whizzed past around head-height. Let go
Full on leg, straightens again. Hridoy closed the face and tried nudging it, leading edge took it in front of point
A bit of room on the length ball has Miller crash a cut, but he finds cover
Pitched up and Hridoy is able to get under it. The line is on leg stump and he walloped it flat over forward square leg for a 77-metre six. Big cheer from the crowd
Pitched up on leg, 129ks, beats the flick and goes off the pad towards forward square leg. Single brings up fifty partnership
Full and flat at the stumps, defended to midwicket
Heart of a length, angles outside off, looked like he rotated the fingers on it. Yep, cutter at 113ks. Cut to deep-backward point
Length outside off, cut with the spin to deep point

Fizz pitches it up to look and burgle a wicket at the end of a tight over, but it's overpitched and Miller's instincts were trained well enough to pick it up and hold the balance on the lofted off-drive. Sails past long-off and a spectator might've taken a spekky reaching out forward
Length just down leg, clipped to short fine. Leg bye actually
Tries to push the fuller ball in front, inside edges it onto pad
Clears the front leg and gets followed by a length ball, clipped to midwicket
Test stuff. Fullish on off, 135ks, big stride forward as he deadbats it to the bowler
Good spot by Mahmudullah, who went shortish and very flat after seeing Miller try and make room. It's at the stumps and is punched to long-off

Line on the bumper goes wrong. Too far down leg, let go Hridoy's picking boundary balls to perfection. This was a half-volley at the stumps, he took a front-foot stride and held his shape while driving through the line. Mid-off and mid-on were in, and the crowd are buzzing again
Hits the sweeper at cover with a back-foot square drive
Length on leg, beats the flick, does it? Yep, leg bye called. Ball deflected off the pad to the leg side
Miller ticks along with a swept single to deep-backward square leg. Full on leg at 90ks, good defensive bowling from the part-timer again
Shortish at the body, rises with the bounce and clips it to deep square leg

Darted again, 93ks, inside edge onto pad. Was a length ball that landed around middle and may have spun in a bit, Klaasen tried to punch to long-on off the back foot but got his feet jammed and, thus, cramped for room
It hummed along as Hridoy tried pinching two but quietened as they settled for one. Was a length ball on leg that was clipped off the back foot. Jansen had run because the area was unmanned
Fullish ball around off, Hridoy tries to defend straight with low hands, gets an outside edge that goes wide to point's left. Stopped at deep third.

Line on the cutter goes wrong, fullish ball is well down leg. Goes past the flick and half-volleys the keeper, who deflects it to the left. Bye taken Shortish at the stumps, pulled to deep square leg. Bounce not great
Opens the face to guide it to cover point's right for a single. Was a length ball around off, looked like Mahmudullah was poking, but no, played it under his eyes. Bit fidgety, Steve Smith style
Length on leg, clipped to the infielder at midwicket
Shortish outside off, guided to deep third off the back foot
Bumper doesn't come at pace, beats the pull and hits around the neck. Was a slower one angling in and Miller looked to hit it in front of square
Slow and full outside off, driven to cover
Ooh, Klaasen misses out on the yorker gone wrong. Tried to lump the full toss through the line but couldn't get the power into the backlift and ended up finding long-off
Ducks under the bumper around the stumps
Quick single to mid-off, who's slightly back. Pitched up by the bowler, punched with a check to Shakib there. Direct hit did come by but no harm
Down leg, beats the flick and is called wide Duly done. Shortish around off, defended towards point
Back of length, 131ks, cramming in above leg stump, Klaasen has to tuck the open-faced blade back towards him to dink it to backward point. Tanzim ends his day with 3 for 18, impressive figures
Cut to cover, not much room or flight. Smart utilitarian bowling from Mahmudullah
Length on leg, clipped to midwicket
And again, it's like he might offer a bit of room but the angle comes back in and Miller finds cover on the cut

Mahmudullah goes across and misses the flick, it hit the front pad and the lbw is given! He reviews. The line is the only thing that can save him. Looked close in real time but from the slow-mo replay, it looks like it's going down leg. Yeah, the angle on the full ball was too sharp. Down leg it is, decision overturned, but the ball did go to the boundary off the deflection. Because it was given out, the runs won't count
Pitched up and given air, not taken on. Miller drives to long-off instead, along the ground
Full on leg, clipped to midwicket
Klaasen ain't missing out on the step-hit! Mahmudullah apologises to the skip for missing his length immediately

Overpitched and that's lashed through cover! He's kept Bangladesh, and the crowd, chugging along on a slow deck. Took a stride in front and used the bit of room to swing freely. Raced along the ground. 21 needed off 20 now
Back to stump-to-stump darting, it's tucked leg side. The contact is gentle enough for a quick two
Fuller side of length on leg, clipped to square leg
Klaasen tries a repeat but times the dink a bit too well and deep midwicket is able to run in quickly and deny the second. Was a full ball again
Pitched up around off, punched to mid-off

Bangladesh might be denied another single here. LBW is given but that looked like it was going down leg, even on first view. Could it be clipping through? Hridoy went across and tried to clip the length ball off the back foot. He was deep in the crease and was hit on the top flap of the front pad. Ooh, it is clipping leg stump. The silence subsumes the ground again, huge wicket. Hridoy was the danger guy but the slight wobble and in-movement on the ball costs him. Big smile on KG's face
Chops the length ball to point
Length around off, defended to point

Slower short ball does not rise, Klaasen's almost through the pull but manages to almost freeze last second and bunt it through forward square leg. Keeper yells but the fielder running in can't stop two
Hard length in the channel, guided to point off the back foot

Klaasen slogs across the line and this pitch swindles him like it has many other batters, the bounce is low and the seam movement takes it further in to dink top of leg stump. No pace off the pitch at all. The crowd find their voice again. Miller has his arm around Klaasen and has a word. Excellent stand this btw
Pitched up at the stumps, pushed to mid-on. No single
Jansen was ball-watching and almost run himself out, but he uses his long reach and there is no direct hit

He does try to get the boundary but plinks it to mid-off's left. They hare for a single. Was pitched right up at pace, he cleared the front leg and tried to go downtown, but the bat face opened on impact
Pulls the shortish ball to deep square leg
Pitched up again, Mahmudullah happy to knock it to long-on for a single. Ball ricochets into a gap after a direct hit but they won't go for the overthrow
Opens the face and guides the length ball to deep third
Mahmudullah tries to take him on, can't lay bat on it. He got the width and the fullish length he wanted but the pace and bounce took the ball above the bat swing. Grimaces in frustration
Jansen brings Miller back on strike. Length ball clipped to midwicket
Into the pitch, at the hips, clipped to midwicket which is open. Baartman gives it all to chase the ball, slides and keeps it to one

And Rishad turns on brave mode and knocks him over, continues his rise at the international level after being thrown in the deep end!. This was the topspinner, the seam was upright and it was delivered like a slinky - coming from the back and springing up after hitting a full length. But the extra bounce beat the bat and Miller is furious. He took the chance as he had to and it doesn't come off
He can't but will pinch two. Length ball at leg stump was flicked into the midwicket pocket again
Paddles the full ball fine
Has a hack but it's mistimed. Bottom hand comes off as he tries to drag the length ball from just outside off, finds deep midwicket
Full just outside off, pushed to cover. Fielder's close, crowd cheer. Bangladesh closing this innings well
It was there to hit around the corner, Mahmudullah tried doing it with a help-along heave. Can't do it. Wonder if it was double bat
Tries the booming cover drive. The line and length were in the batter's favour but the turn meant it went off the edge to short third
Mistimes the pull but gets two to that midwicket pocket again. The bat has been busted, Jaker - to check if the bat was broken - whacked it face-first onto the knee and it was broken proper.
Jansen tries to manufacture something but doesn't connect with the reverse sweep. Went with force but the length ball hit him on the wrist after beating him, and it rolled towards point
Mahmudullah loses balance but manages to sneak a wide. Tries to carve the length ball square but inside edges it into the pitch, single to square leg
Takes it away, offers no pace and the Fizz beats the cut. Length ball through fifth

Low full toss is thrashed downtown, the slow outfield gives an extra second for the fielder and the batters but the second isn't on. Maharaj can't collect the throw on the bounce and Mahmudullah, who was falling short, made it

Keeps it away from the arc to beat him again. Maharaj tries dragging it across with a splashy heave but didn't move across and the reach wasn't enough. Litton is standing wide off side, so this is bowling to a plan
The rising cheer doesn't hit crescendo as Jaker elevates the full ball but can't clear long-on. He got close to the pitch but the impact was from too far low and Markram took a bread-basket catch
Shortish ball looked pacy and beat the pull. Maharaj went on the front tool and tried heaving over midwicket. Went next to his shoulder

Close lbw call. Not given, Maharaj signals for it right away, batters run a single to short third. He went across early, back foot well outside off off stump and front leg outside leg, he tried to smack it across the line - go over midwicket but missed the slog sweep. Impact the only issue here for SA and it is outside off.
Maharaj does go across but still can't make contact. Tried to drag it over midwicket but the fullish ball beat him for pace

Mahmudullah connected but can't clear the long-on boundary. The crowd are stunned back to silence again. The veteran batter is in disbelief, has hand on head and has to walk back. It was in his favour - full toss looped outside off, he clubbed it with a flattish bat and got a lot of height. Markram ran to the left, timed his hop and took a brilliant catch

Maharaj has finally caught up. Leaves the full ball with the sharp angle and the crowd quiet up after a noisy little period. He was standing just outside off but didn't get the bat down due to the angle He will have to run this time. Bumper is pulled from just outside off and finds midwicket

High full toss, will it be a no-ball? No, and Maharaj's praying. His prayers have been answered, in fact, as SA sneak a four-run win It was wide and he tried to heave it across the line. The line was outside off and he couldn't drag it, spliced it to cover and the celebrations followed.
Jansen flat bats it, hits Maharaj on the bounce as he ran forward, the ball deflects and loses pace. Fielder has to come to mid-off, there's enough time to sneak back for two.
Full, just outside off stump, skewed off a thick inside edge into square leg for a single
full on the pads and whipped away, four off the first ball - just as he did in the opening match of the tournament! Not a great ball, and crunched past midwicket
Full, outside the left-hander's off stump, driven out to backward point
dug out down the ground, this will run away, too! Afridi overpitches slightly, didn't look like more than a defensive push from Johnson but it trundles through long-off

Fired way, way, way down the leg side! Movva had no chance. That would have been two keepers! Full, quite the appeal, but thick inside edge from Ayub saves his front pad after a bit of movement into middle and leg
pitched up, looking for swing. Again Johnson is positive, punches a drive that holds up this time as mid-off gives chase
Good length, jagging back, almost played on to the stumps by Ayub who was reluctant to get off the front foot to play that until the last moment
fullish again, tapped into the covers
Fuller length, handsomely driven by Ayub into the gap between point and cover. Sounded good but not quite timed allowing the ring fielders to chase it down
gets some swing here, 141kph/88mph and skidding into the pads. Afridi appeals but looked like it pitched outside leg. Probably doing too much, even if it did land in line
Beats the outside edge to finish! Good bounce there to cap off what - that honking wide aside - was a decent start from the left-arm seamer
full length outside off, bunted towards cover by Dhaliwal
Length, shape away, Rizwan goes searching but can't find anything through to the keeper

scurries in and drops short, fading away wide off stump... starts with a wide slashed energetically through backward point! Back of a length, 138kph and it sits up for Johnson to throw the hands through a back-foot punch, flies over the infield and away
Corker! Leaps off a length - just 80mph - but Rizwan hops back and almost wears it on the glove.
fifth stump and holding, touch short. Left alone this time
Another away-shaper, this one sharper - 85mph - but doesn't bounce at all, through to the keeper on the bounce

beauty from Naseem, beats him playing back... in fact, Naseem thinks he's nicked it, but I'm not sure any of his team-mates agree. Babar is canvassing for supporting views but eventually decides not to review. Which is a good call, because Johnson missed it by several inches
Short, wide-ish, Rizwan finally lays bat on one but into the man at cover
back of a length and shaping away again, played more comfortably this time
Fuller, swinging away, left alone
appreciable seam movement for Naseem, 134kph/83mph outside off. Johnson shoulders arms
Gordon's grunting as he thrusts this down, full, banged into the pitch, worked away towards mid on and a single pinched
perfect length again, jack-knifes through to the keeper! Johnson can't get forward and is left groping at thin air as the ball decks away from him
Full outside off, driven by Rizwan but he was reaching far enough to mean his bottom hand comes off the bat. Pierces the ring but without that power, has to settle for a single
full and drilled through point! Dhaliwal gets in on the act now, crouching low into a flowing square drive for his first runs
Decks in a touch off a length, Ayub right behind it, defending towards cover
still over the wicket and angling across, 137kph/85mph in the channel. Left alone
Garbage running! Ayub lifts well over mid on but holds the pose for too long. It subsequently plugs and they're so late setting off for the first than they don't even get two!
good length, nipping away and staying a touch low as Dhaliwal sits back and is beaten
Bit of width, cut but off the under edge and balloons over the keeper. Luckily for Canada, third is set back on the sponge and scurries around to tidy up
another ripper, sizzling across the right-hander from back of a length. Wobbles past the outside edge and then nearly wrongfoots Rizwan, too
Short, wide, Ayub flails and misses! Misses out, too - that was there for carving
pitched up, shaping back in this time! Dhaliwal drops his bat on it in time
Full, onto the stumps, picked up to midwicket but only two as the heavy outfield sucks the life out of the shot

bowled by a snorter! On a length, 141kph/88mph and jagging straight down the line of middle stump, slicing through Dhaliwal. Amir sprints off arms outstretched, the Pakistan fans in the ground finally have something to celebrate. Off stump is flat on the ground. That was some beautiful fast bowling from Amir
Bit of width, not that much bounce but Rizwan stays low to cut through cover. Chased down to keep them to two
clubbed over point! Johnson continues to go about his merry way, throwing the hands at width
Full, arrowing into leg stump, played down to mid on
pitched up and chipped, manages to clear the man in the covers! Didn't get it much beyond the circle in the end
Full again, a little more on leg stump, allowing Rizwan to tuck away through square leg
134kph/83mph outside off, Johnson duck the bouncer
Full from over the wicket, just outside off, defended into the off side
fullish in the channel and Johnson has a dip, thick-edged down to deep third

Down! Ayub goes on the hook but is undone by the lack of pace off the pitch this time around. Ends up swivelling it over to short fine leg - Navneet Dhaliwal - who leaps and then gets the ball into his left hand on the way down before it bounces out. Should have been taken
touch short, 135kph/83mph on the stumps and nurdled through midwicket

Chaos here, as Rizwan drops his back after getting pinned by a throw at the nonstriker's end after he wears a delivery into square leg before scarpering down the other end as the keeper runs around and throws
a quiet finish, steered down to backward point
Full length, outside off, Rizwan offers the face and opens it at the last second to guide down to third
length, fourth-stump line from over the wicket. Pargat is forward and defends. The curse is broken

Heyliger strikes with his second ball! It's been coming... bit of width Ayub pulls across the line off the back of the length... but there's not as much bounce as expected and the left-hander ends up under-edging through to the keeper, who takes a sharp low catch going back to his right
angling across, 140kph/87mph in the channel, beats a tentative prod
Loose down the leg side, banged into a length but very wayward Full, into off stump, driven back to the bowler
looking for the nip-backer again, slides down the leg side
Beats Babar on the inside edge! Scurries in off a good length, Babar plays off the back foot but misreads it off the deck completely
pitched up, curling in towards middle and leg, Pargat flicks it late through backward square leg
Angling into a fourth stump line, punched back to the bowler
digs this one in short, Johnson is across on off and ducks

Is that out?! Babar advances and seems to flick around the corner through to the keeper. Umpire says not out - there was definitely a noise - and it's been sent upstairs... but it's pad, not bat. And the check for LBW is not out too.
length ball, looking for swing back in, jabbed watchfully towards mid-on
Banged into a length, no pace off the pitch, cut to cover

and now the first ball brings a wicket! Fast and nasty, rising from back of a length, kisses the glove and flies to slip. Afridi strikes with his seventh ball, after an indifferent first over, and Canada lose their second in the powerplay. The ball kicked at Pargat and he was caught between trying to play and leave
A boundary! A real boundary off the bat! And the first of the Pakistan Powerplay! Banged in short again, but a bit of pace to work with and Rizwan clouts it through midwicket. The crowd erupts!
back of a length, was there a touch through down the leg side? No... in fact, it's a wide shortish and jabbed down into the covers
Dabbed down to third as Gordon goes slightly fuller and tightens his line. Third comes around to gather at the sponge but these two run well to nab two
banged into the deck and Kirton lines it up coming across on off
Banged in, straighter, Rizwan gets on top of the bounce to defend down the pitch
back of a length, 131kph/81mph on the hip. Kirton flicks and misses, the ball dribbles into the leg side
Rizwan on the charge as Gordon hits that short length but toes it so hard he's going to need a new bat! Big chunk taken out of the bottom left corner
short and steaming through outside off, Kirton sways underneath
Dabbed down towards third
beats the edge, half an appeal for caught behind from Afridi. But already Pakistan's players are racing round for the next over
over the wicket, short of a length, tapped down into the off side
Starts full and down the leg side Full, straight, defended back down the middle of the pitch
short and slapped... extraordinary six, all the way over deep cover! Johnson showcases his belligerence and skill once again. Just clocks Rauf's pace over the rope, well in front of square
Looped, drifting onto leg stump, flicked away to backward square leg
dug in short, 141kph/88mph, Johnson ducks... and it clears the keeper! Pace working against Rauf here in the channel, Johnson slashes an outside edge down to deep third
Length dragged back, decent flight, worked out into a vacant midwicket
round the wicket, goes full and angling in, 141kph. Kirton drives, scuffing the toe of his bat on the ground. Gets one wide of mid-off
First delivery outside off stump, Rizwan leans into a drive away to deep cover
back of a length, Johnson swings and misses! Not far from hitting the top of leg stump on its way through
Flighted, drifting into leg, worked away to square leg and a good second call gets them two

dropped into the covers, Kirton is sent back... Imad throws down the stumps! Superb bit of fielding, Pakistan are delighted, and it's curtains for Kirton! He wanted one but Johnson wasn't keen. Imad swooped and turned to pull off a direct hit at the non-striker's, leaving him half a yard short
Flatter, picked off squarer than the previous delivery but the fielders on the deep have been tweaked slightly and backward square leg tidies up
Flights on onto middle and leg, tucked to square leg where the bowler has to reluctantly field
length ball, tucked to the leg side
Full, into middle stump, punched into the covers
back of a length, 133kph.83mph outside off, Movva stabs it towards backward point
Flighted, just outside off, shovelled out to midwicket
Similar line, worked away into midwicket with a straight bat by Rizwan this time
round the wicket, 136kph/84mph back of a length. Movva pulls without timing but picks up his first run to midwicket
Fired down the leg side. Keeper's got the bails off as Babar goes to sweep, but no dice Full, worked away to deep midwicket. Probably could have been two, but Rizwan declines
slower ball, this grips and hits Johnson on the back leg as he looks to defend. Afridi is begging the umpire for an lbw... no review from Pakistan. Imad gestures that height was an issue
Googly? Hint of one anyway, well spotted by Rizwan, who pushes to cover

miscued, high into the air... and all the way over long-on! Afridi looks bemused, having foxed Johnson with a slower ball. He was aiming somewhere over cover but somehow it swirls back down the ground and over the ropes
angled in from round the wicket, clipped into the leg side
Looped full, Babar skips down and again profits from an empty region in the circle at midwicket. One to plug?
96kph on off, defended back to the bowler
Bit of pace off this one, Rizwan adjusts his movements and defends back to the bowler
tapped in front of point by Johnson, this time they push for a tight single... think Movva would have been home, even with a direct hit
Into off stump, driven just beyond the reach of cover, with long off up to field
tossed up, this one spins sharply away. Left alone
Babar skips down looking for the big shot, but ends up yorking himself and digs one off to cover
darted on off, 97kph/61mph and pushed into the covers
Darted in, not much bounce off a length, pushed back to the bowler, towards mid off
flighted again, pace down to 82kph. Movva goes fishing as the ball turns away from the blade. Manages to keep his back foot anchored as Rizwan whips off the bails
Full ball... full toss... swept away for four behind square leg! A vital boundary to ease the pressure among all the singles. Saad was going for a quicker delivery but got it wrong
slammed in back of a length, doesn't get up that high. Johnson swivels and attempts to pull, plays over the ball outside off
Boooom! Pakistan's fifty comes up in style, as Babar finally gets his dancing shoes on the right feet, skips down the track and clouts straight and true for six!
shortish in the channel, jabbed down to deep third
Googly, very slow out of the hand, watched off the pitch and punched out to cover

bowled into the pitch but flying down the leg side short of a length, Movva cuts... nicks behind! 100th T20I wicket for Rauf, who gets his radar working and makes the breakthrough. Movva didn't look happy but that was perhaps more at the shot. Big deflection behind, Rizwan takes it without fuss
And the same this time, only now Babar opens the wrists a touch to find the gap
short of a length in the channel outside off, beats the bat as he comes across
Out the front of the hand, sharper, Rizwan reaches out to meet this on the full and finds two through wide mid off

beastly line, flies off the edge! Rauf goes bang-bang. Bit of a wonky shot from Ravinderpaul, closing the face as the ball homed in over the top of off. Skewed off the shoulder of the bat straight to Babar at slip
Slider, but full-ish and wide outside off stump, dabbed out to the boundary rider on the off side
over the wicket to the lefty, shortish and tucked off the hip
Out the front of the hand again, punched down to long off. That's 11 from the over - and drinks!
Beats the outside edge immediately! Leaping off a length, Babar unsure as he prods at it
skips in, tossed up outside off. The arm ball skids past the outside edge into Rizwan's gloves
Not as much behind this one, full into off stump, driven down the ground, fielded by mid off running across to his right
floated full, Saad is forward and punches a drive
Wide of the crease, angled into middle and leg, worked out to deep square leg
slows his pace, tapped away into the off side
Wide length, Babar dances down and thrashes away through the covers, out to the boundary rider
monstered down the ground! Touch full, Johnson shuffles and then heaves with all his might, sends it 76 metres over long-on
Full of a length, outside off, Rizwan guides down to third
flatter, prodded into the covers
Short, whipped away out to deep square leg, but straight to the fielder
tossed up, 83kph and played off the back foot, clipped through cover for a single
low full toss, 145kph/90mph. Johnson swats it down to long-on
Babar uses his feet again, gets hold of this one but has to dig it out a touch, allowing long on to shift left to field the ball along the deck
round the wicket, pitched up and then nibbling away at 144kph, beats the bat through to the keeper
Slightly wider from the skipper, turn off the surface, too, as Rizwan blocks in front of middle
banged in back of a length, defended from the crease
Full, scuffed off the under edge. Shreyas Movva is so keen to try and catch Rizwan short of his ground that he accidentally knocks into the stumps!
full length, Saad pushes a drive, gets a thick edge into his pads for a single
Darted into leg, manoeuvred through midwicket

short, top-edged... but Fakhar misses the chance! Not sure he even got a hand to it, the ball dropping over his shoulder as he ran back from midwicket. Flicked the fingers, I think. Should have been taken, even if it wasn't the easiest catch
Length, but very slow, Babar waits and cuts this out to deep cover
dug in, 142kph/88mph and Saad crouches low
Darted into leg, blocked but worked enough into the leg side for a single
round the wicket, arm ball from Imad, heading towards the top of off. Stabbed into the covers
Starts full, outside off, pushed down the ground
constricting line, Johnson defends towards point
Babar gives himself room on the leg side, Kaleem goes full on off stump, dug out
bit more air, 84kph and spinning as Johnson steps into a forward defensive

Loose, full on leg stump, worked away for a couple as the fielder at deep backward square leg meets the ball a foot inside the boundary. That brings up the fifty partnership between these two, from 49 deliveries

put a donk on it, son... Fifty up for Johnson, via his fourth six! Soft-shoes to the pitch and flips it down the ground, lots of hang time but the ball drops safely over the head of long-off coming around. He raises his bat to the crowd. Proper Bannerman territory for Johnson now

Into the pads as Babar advances. The ball dribbles out into the leg side and he looks quizzically at Rizwan about the single, but the bowler fields sharply off his own bowling to end that conversation
fired in on the stumps, blocked to the off side

Flashes beyond point and away for four! Babar uses his feet again and it looks like backward point is in the game there, sprawling to his left. Too much on the shot, though, and that's Babar's second boundary
dabbed down behind point and they scurry one
Full - very full - dug out outside off stump with a drive and a single scampered as mid offtries and fails to gather and throwdown the nonstriker's stumps
dug in short, swing and a miss
Length, on leg stump, met more than halfway by Babar, punched out to deep cover
back of a length, 129kph/80mph outside off. Johnson defends into the covers
Pulls the length back even further, outside off, Rizwan irked as he was looking to advance and ends up hitting the ball into the ground in front of him

backs away, swings hard - and misses! Johnson's one-man show is over. Looked a tired shot, that... he trudges off slowly, just a brief wave of the bat to the crowd. Naseem hit back of a length and the ball skidded on, cramping Johnson as he looked to mow through the off side. Smack into the top of leg stump
Worked out into deep midwicket once more
digs this in short, flies through past the gloves
Outside off, charged and driven nicely, but deep cover fields with ease
short again, 135kph/84mph, snaking back a the body, helped away through backward square leg
Panged out to midwicket on the charge to... brilliantly saved by the subfielder at deep midwicket, who claws it back and saves two
stays over the wicket, thick-edged down to deep third
More footwork, more driving, but straight to cover
Another shot on the move, but no great timing as mid off intercepts and chucks to the keeper's end prevent the single
over the wicket, Imad slides his first ball past the outside edge
Full bunger, punched down to mid off again, who manages to take pace off the ball with a strong right arm from a dive, allowing long on to tidy up
pushed down the leg side fired down wide of off, 91kph and punched to extra cover coming forwards
Ouchie! Babar smacks the ball into his front knee after running down and trying to pull a short ball away. Shake it off skipper...
length ball, played off the back foot with the turn, can't get it past midwicket this time

Gone! Babar falls to the delivery that nips away on the fourth stump line - the same one he's had trouble with throughout this knock. Tries to just guide down to third but can't get the right connection. Babar is furious and smashes his bat on the ground in disgust!
punched into the covers for one
Starts outside off to the leftie, pushed into the covers to get off the mark
undercutter, sliding into the front pad... heading down leg, I think
Wide of the crease, full, worked down to mid on
tossed up on off, pushed away coming across
back of a length, jabbed away towards cover

Excellent shot! Because it wasn't a particularly well-constructed lead-up to the shot. Rizwan skipped down, wasn't to the pitch of the ball, but lets his hands and wrists go, lifting gorgeously over extra cover for six!
low full toss, creamed through point! Usman put in a fantastic diving effort in the deep but couldn't prevent it getting past him
Pushes into midwicket - first run hard, likewise the second, as Fakhar commits early to coming back
good length, 142kph/88mph, blocked watchfully towards mid-off
Loopy googly outside off, played off the pitch to third, who is up in the circle
banged in short outside off, Saad swings at a pull, gets a bottom edge into the pitch through to Rizwan
Looped outside off again, tip and run to the covers has the Canadian ring fielders scampering in vain
short and sliding down the leg side, another to the extras column length ball, Saad attempts to club it down the ground. Doesn't really connect but gets one to the right of mid-on
Another googly, on a length, Fakhar plays late and dabs a single into cover
goes full and wide, Kaleem slices a drive into the gap at backward point for two
Slider, Rizwan reaches out and pats this through the off side
Full, pushed out to mid on
length ball delivered from over the wicket. Saad is forward on off and defends
Swing and a miss! Fakhar tries to boom one into the leg side but you can't trust the bounce off a length on here, and this one goes under the bat

leading edge, but Amir can't get there! Seem to stop on Saad as he flicked across the line, Amir had to turn and run back towards mid-on, but the ball stays just out of reach. Needed a full-length dive, I think
Full, across the left-hander who slices this one-handed out to deep point
slower ball, dinked into the gap
Short, this one bouncing up as expected, pulled across the like to deep square leg
short ball, Saad ducks it
Fuller, wide, slapped out to deep cover to bring up the Pakistan 100. Just three fours and two sixes... but they're winning I suppose

swipes a big top edge, and Rizwan circles under it! The Canada captain falls trying to swing late runs. Into the pitch, Saad hoicked across the line but it got big on him, Rizwan tracking the ball all the way to the edge of the circle around short third

Moves wide of the crease, tucked to the leg side... and they end up nabbing three! The fielder running in forgets to collect and has to go back. That's 52 from as many deliveries for Rizwan, who salutes the crowd. It's the slowest fifty by a Pakistan men's batter in all T20 internationals...
back of a length, nudged off the body
Rizwan charges a length ball outside off, tries to pull it away for a boundary to win the game there and then, but ends up clothing into square leg
full, pace off and clipped... lands safely in the vacant mid-on region

Full, larruped into the off side... and caught! Fakhar takes his turn to finish this one off, but ends up scything the ball high rather than far, taken excellently by subfielder Bajwa running back to cover from point
round the wicket, full length and driven to mid-off on the bounce

Short, over the shoulder of Usman Khan who decides not to hook. Wided There it is - Pakistan finally get the job done... Slower ball worked out to that profitable midwicket region to huge cheers from the stands. Babar Azam's side are finally up and running after two defeats, winning this one by seven wickets.
pitched up, 139kph/86mph around off stump, patted into the covers by Kaleem
back-of-a-length slower ball, popped into the off side... but again it doesn't go to hand
122kph cutter, fourth stump and played late towards backward point. Would have been gone with a direct hit! Shadab the fielder
low full toss, 133kph/83mph on off. Slashed off the outside edge to deep third
angled across, pace off in the channel, draws a swing and miss
top-edged to fine leg! Amir had the man up but still went short, Heyliger was tucked up but swung hard and got enough to clear the circle
slower ball wide of off, another swipe of thin air
full at the pads, 137kph/85mph and Heyliger can't connect again
pace off again, worked out to deep midwicket for one
fired into the blockhole, Kaleem tries to clamp down on it. The ball skids through to Rizwan past leg stump. There was half an appeal for caught behind but I think it flicked the pad
pitched up straight and dug out
misses down the leg side but they scamper a bye
length ball, carved all the way! Pace on and Kaleem uses it to his advantage to dump the ball over deep backward point
goes to the change-up, heaved without timing into the leg side
fired in full, scuffed back through mid-on
nails the yorker, 139kph/86mph and dug out to mid-off... who sets himself and has a shy, misses! So a single off the final ball, and Canada have scraped together something from the depths of 55 for 5
hard length on leg stump. Pitches and skids on, meaning that van Lingen is late on the stab. Wears a blow on the thigh pad for his troubles

would have been out with a direct hit! Back of a length on middle and leg. Warner drops it into the off side and calls Head through. Head was not quite ready for the single and would have been well short had the fielder's under-arm throw hit the stumps
shorter and wider outside off. van Lingen throws his hands at it but only swishes and misses
full on middle and off. A hint of shape away and Head squirts it off the inside edge towards deep square leg

sprays this a mile down leg and Wade does brilliantly to get his right glove to it. Saves three runs hard length on middle and off. Davin shapes up for a swipe but the ball hits him before he can complete his swing
shot! Short, wide and Warner puts it away. Too much width on offer and Warner stands up tall before crunching it to extra cover's left!
short outside off. Davin waits for it and cuts it past backward point to get off the mark
back of a length just outside off. Warner plants his front foot and has a yahoo across the line. Only connects with fresh air, though
back of a length delivery hung up well outside off. van Lingen has another swish at it but gets nowhere close to the ball
length just outside off. Sticks in the surface a shdae and that forces Warner to check his shot. Shanks it towards mid on
edged and four! Back of a length outside off. Pitches and nips away against the angle. van Lingen, wafting at it, gets a thick outside edge that flies over slip!
banged into the track on middle and leg. Head hops up onto his toes and fends it into the on side
gets it through! You cannot give width to Warner and that is exactly what Wiese does. This is on the shorter side too and Warner threads it between cover point and extra cover!
back of a length on middle and off. Davin goes back and defends. Just a hint of shape for Stoinis
back to back boundaries! This is possibly the best of the lot. Full enough outside off. Warner leans into the drive and caresses it between extra cover and mid off!
safe! Hard length just outside off. Davin opens up his stance and hacks at it. Miscues it but luckily for him, it falls between mid on and mid off
goes all the way now! Half-tracker on leg stump and that is very ordinary bowling. Warner is expecting it and rocks back to dump this over the deep square leg fence!
length just outside off. van Lingen stands up on his toes and jabs it towards extra cover

Warner falls! Full outside off and Warner was in that kind of mood where he was going after everything. Looks to go downtown but the bat face opens upon contact. Slices it way up and Trumpelmann snares the chance at mid off. Some respite for Namibia!
shortish just outside off. van Lingen waits for it and pulls it towards mid wicket. Got a decent piece of it but could not find the gap
fullish in the channel just outside off. Nips away and that squares up Marsh, who defends with soft hands
shot! Over-pitched on off and van Lingen pounces. Springs forward, accounts for the inward movement and cracks it to mid on's right!
sprayed a mile down leg. Green does well to get behind it and collect cleanly. Called a wide full on off. Marsh comes forward and blocks
short on leg stump. van Lingen swivels nicely and pulls it away towards deep square leg
full delivery that finishes just outside off, after shaping away a great deal. Head pushes it down the ground
back of a length just outside off. van Lingen tips it to mid off and hares across to the other end. Marsh could not gather cleanly and that made the single easier
lovely! Back of a length just outside off. Head waits for it, uses the pace and opens his bat face to steer it to short third man's left!
hard length just outside off. Davin, without any footwork, swishes at it and only connects with fresh air
up and over! Length just outside off. Head plants his front foot and goes through the line, pumping it flat over mid off!
hard length, slanting into middle and leg. Davin looks for the slog again but is awfully late on the stroke. Pings away into the off side off his body
four more! Half-tracker outside off and that is never going to trouble Head. He clears his front leg and swats it through mid wicket!

Davin perishes swinging! Slightly shorter and wider outside off. Davin gives himself room, trying to carve it over backward point. Makes contact but does not get the elevation he desires. Picks out Maxwell at backward point and he was never dropping that. Early breakthrough for Australia!
shortish outside off. Head gets up on his toes and cuts it towards cover point, who misfields and ends up conceding a single
back of a length just outside off. Frylinck gets up on his toes and taps it towards backward point
Marsh is off the mark too! Full outside off. Marsh shimmies down the track, gets close to the ball and lifts it nonchalantly over mid off!
length just outside off. Frylinck stays leg side and runs it down to third man to get off the mark
short and slanting into middle and leg. Head stabs it off the back foot towards mid on
length delivery angled across just outside off. Frylinck comes half forward and jabs it towards cover point
onto the grass banks! Not sure Head needed the breeze for this. It was a drag-down on middle and leg, Head rocked back and smoked it over cow corner!
back of a length on off. Frylinck is cramped for room and pokes it towards extra cover
length on middle and leg. Head opts to stay back before playing it towards the bowler
hard length on middle and leg. A bit of shape back into Frylinck and he hacks it towards mid wicket
much fuller outside off. Head drives it down the ground to mid off

Cummins has his first! Full on middle and off. There to go over the top but Frylinck does not quite get the purchase he is after. Steps outside leg, goes through the line but hits it straight to Marsh at mid off. Namibia lose their second and they are now in a spot of bother!
short outside off. Kisses the surface and bounces extra, going past Head's attempted cut
shortish outside off. Erasmus gets up on his toes and defends
fuller and flatter outside off. Head comes forward and pokes it towards cover. A very tidy over by the Namibian skipper
hard length just outside off. Erasmus sits back in his crease and pushes it towards mid off

another for Hazlewood! Hazlewood keeps badgering that hard length outside off. A hint of extra bounce and that means van Lingen cannot keep his jab down. Slices it towards Maxwell at backward point, who juggles initially but manages to hold on. Namibia slide into further trouble!
off-pace and into the track outside off. Marsh hangs back and jabs it towards cover
fullish outside off. Smit comes forward very tentatively and dangles his bat. Squirts it off the toe-end towards third man
slower ball on a length on leg stump. Marsh will feel he missed out there. Swings at it and the ball trickles off the pads into the on side
back of a length just outside off. Nips back in and Erasmus accounts for it, blocking it solidly off the back foot
another boundary for Head! Dug into the track on middle and leg. Head stays leg side and that gives him the room he needs to ramp it over backward point!
back of a length just outside off. Erasmus waits for it and punches it towards extra cover
four more! Back-of-the-hand slower ball that lands right in the slot on middle and leg. Head winds up and smacks it over mid on!
fullish on middle and off. Erasmus comes half forward and pats it down the ground to mid off
shot! Back of a length just outside off. Head rises with the bounce and crashes it on the up between extra cover and mid off!
back of a length outside off. Shapes back in slightly and Erasmus, having advanced, jams it off the inside edge into his thigh pad
oh! Back-of-the-hand slower ball on a length on leg stump. Head tries to hit it into the ocean but only swats away a few flies
hard length on middle and off. Marsh presses half forward and defends with a straight bat
slanted in on a length on middle and leg. Smit plays all over it and the ball thuds into his thigh pad
gorgeous! Marginally short outside off and Marsh is all over it. Gets on top of the bounce, gets his hands through the ball and creams it through point!
shortish on middle and leg. Smit hops up onto his toes and turns it behind square towards long leg
fetch that! Slower ball that sits up to be hit outside off. Marsh has all the time in the world to clobber this over deep mid wicket!
banged into the track on middle and leg. Erasmus sizes up the length early enough and ducks under it

that will be that! The Australia captain finishes it off with another supreme stroke, and Australia rampage to victory inside six overs! Length outside off. Marsh marches down the track menacingly and crunches it to mid off's left. Seals the deal, and Australia are now through to the Super Eight!
hard length on middle and off. Erasmus tries to give himself room but is unable to do so. Stabbed back towards the bowler
back of a length on middle and off. Erasmus advances and drops it into the off side
swish and a miss! Hard length on middle and leg. Erasmus looks to force it through the off side but only connects with fresh air
slider on a length just outside off. Smit walks across his stumps and pats it gently towards mid wicket
back of a length on off. Skids on and Smit works it enough to mid wicket's right for a single
floated up full outside off. Erasmus digs it out towards short extra cover
googly on a back of a length on off. Erasmus reads it off the pitch and plays it towards short extra cover
back of a length just outside off. This grips in the surface and spins away, going past Erasmus' cut. A bit of extra bounce too
shorter and wider outside off. Erasmus hangs back and dabs it towards backward point. The Namibia skipper still not off the mark
zipped in full on middle and off. Smit comes forward and pokes it towards mid off
off-pace on a back of a length outside off. Smith swishes at it and misses. Might have been the back-of-the-hand slower one
peach! Back of a length in the channel just outside off. Sharp movement away from Smit, both in the air and off the deck. Smit nibbles at it and is beaten all ends up

huge appeal, not given! Back of a length on middle and off. Jags back sharply and cuts Smit in half. He seems to play all around it and gets rapped on the back leg. Australia discuss and then decide to go upstairs. Did Smit hit it? Looked a touch high too. Okay, so there is no bat involved. The ball did strike Smit on the flap of the back pad, though. All eyes on Ball Tracking now, and it shows the ball would have smashed into the top of leg stump. The decision to review vindicated, and Namibia are four down now!
fullish on the pads. Green misses his flick and the ball trickles off his thigh pad behind square on the leg side
full on middle and off. Erasmus comes forward and flicks it to mid on, who is well inside the circle, anticipating the quick single
very full on leg stump. Green moves across his stumps and paddles it towards long leg to get off the mark

big appeal, Nitin Menon is unmoved! Fired in full just outside off. Erasmus shuffles across and looks to paddle it away. Does not make contact and gets pinned on the front leg. The impact seemed a little outside the line but Australia have reviewed nevertheless. No bat involved but the impact, as expected, is outside the line. It was also beyond 3m and Erasmus stays!
finally off the mark! Low full toss on off. Erasmus gets down on the sweep and helps it round the corner. Wry smile on his face as he completes the single
beauty! Googly fizzed through on a length just outside off. Green hangs back rather than coming forward and does not pick it either. Rips past the outside edge of his prod

that is plumb! Fuller, faster and flatter on middle and leg. Green looks for the sweep again but the ball is too full to be playing the stroke. Sneaks under his bat and pings him flush on the back leg. Zampa goes up, and the umpire's finger goes up just as quickly. Half of the Namibian side is now back in the shed!
googly on a back of a length outside off. Wiese picks it off the pitch and pokes it towards extra cover
the runs are flowing for Erasmus now! Back of a length just outside off. Erasmus gives himself ample room and crashes it between extra cover and mid off!
hard length on middle and leg. Nips back a shade and cramps Erasmus for room, who can only dab it towards backward point
banged into the track on middle and leg. Erasmus is terribly late on the pull and splices it towards fine leg
very full on middle and off. Wiese looks for the flick and chunks it off the inside edge into his boot
bumper on middle and leg. Wiese watches it till the last moment before ducking out of the way. That was sharp
fullish, angling into middle and leg. Wiese presses forward and tucks it off his pads towards fine leg
was there a nick?! Flighted up full outside off. Wiese throws his hands at it and seems to miss it. Catches the outside of Wade's right glove and beats Marsh at slip too
angled in on a back of a length on the stumps. Defended by Wiese

Wiese bites the dust too! Googly bowled a little shortish on middle and off. Sticks in the surface, spins into Wiese and comes off slower than he expects. He was shaping to work it away into the mid wicket region but the lack of pace means that he can only chip it towards long on. Hazlewood makes up ground to his right, slides across and completes the catch!
back of a length outside off. Trumpelmann goes back and jabs it towards deep point
googly floated up on a length outside off. Erasmus has no clue about the variation and dangles his bat. Squirts away off the inside edge into the on side
very full on middle and off. Trumpelmann digs it out towards the bowler
off-pace on a length just outside off. Erasmus tries to hit it into next week and gets just enough to evade Marsh at mid off
shorter and wider outside off. Keeps a tad low and goes past Erasmus' flailing blade
dug in short on middle and off. Zips off the surface and Erasmus, aiming to slash it over backward point, is beaten for pace

safe! Banged in much shorter just outside off. Seems like a change-up and Erasmus has to wait an eternity for it before flat-batting it on the bounce to mid on. Survives a run-out scare at the bowler's end too
full and wide outside off. Shapes away late and Trumpelmann misses that by a significant margin
back of a length on middle and off. Trumpelmann lets the ball come to him before meeting it right under his eyes
length just outside off. Erasmus goes back and pushes it into the point region for a single
back of a length outside off. Trumpelmann pokes it towards extra cover
Trumpelmann hits the scoreboard! Juicy full toss outside off and Trumpelmann cannot believe what has been dished out. His eyes light up and he thumps it over deep mid wicket!

six and out! Zampa with the last laugh! Shorter outside off and this seems to skid on just a smidgen. Trumpelmann shapes for the pull but because the ball rushes him, he cannot get enough on it. Maxwell settles under it at deep mid wicket and does the rest!
floated up full just outside off. Scholtz presses forward and stabs it towards short mid wicket

finishes his spell with an absolute ripper! Beautifully-disguised googly on a length outside off. Drops on the batter late and zings back in off the surface. Scholtz does not read it and has a huge waft at it. Leaves a gap between bat and pad and the ball sneaks through, crashing into off stump!
back of a length just outside off. Erasmus gets up on his toes and jabs it towards backward point
shortish just outside off. Erasmus cuts it towards deep cover point and then decides against taking the single. Well, Namibia could do with every run
hard length, slanting into leg stump. Erasmus gives himself room and slaps it towards deep cover point. Calls for two immediately and Brassell rushes back to make it
banged into the track on leg stump. Erasmus makes room, looking for the upper-cut but is beaten for pace
up, up and away! Short and wide outside off. Erasmus backs away to create further room and smashes it over extra cover. Lands just inside the ropes!
shortish outside off. Erasmus goes deep into his crease and bunts it powerfully past mid on. He was intent on the third but decided against it. Had he gone for it, it was a run-out waiting to happen
slower ball on a full length on the pads. Brassell glances it down to fine leg and gets off the mark
full and hung up well outside off. Erasmus throws his hands at it but is late on the stroke. Fails to make contact
oh dear! Full toss on the pads. Erasmus gets inside the line and heaves it towards fine leg, where Hazlewood lets it go through for four!
off-pace on a length outside off. Erasmus has a massive swing at it and shanks it towards mid on
back of a length just outside off. Erasmus uses the pace and dabs it towards backward point

four to end the over! Shortish outside off. Erasmus seems inclined to run this down to third man for a single but the extra pace means that he glides it well over the keeper's head. Does not retain strike but does get four!
full toss outside off. Brassell comes forward and stabs it towards deep cover point
cutter into the track outside off. Erasmus is early into the stroke and scuffs it back to the bowler
off-pace again, and shortish outside off. Erasmus winds up while sitting deep in his crease and slices it over extra cover for a brace
pick the bones out of this one! Dug in short outside off and Erasmus is waiting for it. Picks the length early, opens up his stance and clubs it clean over deep mid wicket!
short again outside off. Erasmus rolls his wrists over it this time and pulls it towards deep square leg
Cummins tests out the middle of the track again. This is outside off and that allows Brassell to comfortably sway out of the way
full delivery hung up way outside off. Erasmus shuffles across, looking for the sweep but does not lay bat on ball

shorter this time and perhaps wider outside off. Erasmus holds his ground and swishes at it. Misses it but the umpire calls it a wide nails the wide yorker but this is just a tad beyond the tramlines. More exercise for the umpire goes straight up, and Erasmus' stay comes to an end! In the slot just outside off. Erasmus gets into a good position after moving across but gets too much under it. Clinks off the toe-end and goes a mile up. Maxwell runs in from deep mid wicket, tracks it all the way and snaffles up the chance. Namibia nine down now!
fullish, angling into middle and off. Shikongo comes forward and prods it towards short mid wicket
fuller, pushed into middle and off. Shikongo gets forward and defends
banged into the track outside off. Shikongo gets under it easily

a superb catch to end the Namibian innings! Australia have rolled them over for 72! Zipped in full on middle and leg. Seems to hold in the surface and Shikongo, trying to work to leg, gets a tame leading edge. David calls for it early, sprints to his left and takes the catch with a slide across the surface. A professional end to a professional bowling display!
pinned on the kneeroll! That's a magnificent loosener! Curling in from off to middle on a perfect length, nothing the batter could do to cover the initial line and his pads too. Plumb!
A bit of extra bounce as it angles away from a back of length, guided to deep third. But Rohit was taken aback and had to adjust
pushed out wider, looking for big inswing but this one shapes straight across

Netravalkar turns into left-arm Anderson to nick off Kohli. Perfect three-quarter length in the channel,  lands just outside off and keeps going away with the angle. Kohli went back and across, big step, and felt for it. The push with the full bat-face was firm and by the time he realised the angle was too far and tried withdrawing the bat, it was too late. There was the first-ball rust in there. No foot movement, all hands, and like in Nottingham 2021, he falls for a goldie
big in-dip once again! That's such a tricky angle to negotiate, bending back in at the pads once more, but this one is doing just too much ... probably!
Full outside off, pushed to cover
pushed across the right-hander again, a pair of two-card tricks so far. But this one is just the wrong side of the line up on the toes, cracked out to deep cover for two runs, first off the bat

Jags back in sharply to beat bat. Wobble ball on a length lands around fifth stump, might have hit a crack, and beats Pant on the cut. He was pulling out but could've easily dragged it back onto the stumps
shaping back at the batter again, but from outside off on this occasion, Skims past the inside-edge as Gous flashes outside the line
Full outside off, pushed to cover

high on the splice, flashed high in the air! Oh dear, this is going down the pan for USA! Drags his length back, but Gous failed to do likewise with his weight. An off-balance pull was the upshot, Hardik hared across from mid-off and grabbed the ball at the top of the bowler's run-up!
Full on the pads, clipped to fine leg
A bit short, a bit of width and Pant's all over it
tight lines on the yorker, squeezed away for a first-ball single through square leg
Tucks it off the body to the leg side. Back-foot shot
full length, shaping into the blockhole and dipping away late. An open-faced push out to point
Length ball keeps a bit lower than he expected, Rohit collapses a bit to defend it to the leg side
soft hands on the back foot, waiting for the length ball to arrive and poking the single to point
In Pant's half and he looked for a Gilchrist-esque heave down the ground. He had a bit of width but couldn't connect, ball rolled along the pitch and mid-off stopped it
shaping away from the left-hander, good hoop from Siraj but left alone
On the fuller side. Middle-and-off line, defended with a straight bat
attacking the top of off from over the wicket, blocked with an angled bat into the covers
Wide on a length, guided to deep third
driven off the full length, squirts out to point who can't gather cleanly. Bonus runs to end the over
steps out to the length, on a wide line, shaping past an upraised bat
Full on sixth stump, Rohit takes a big stride towards the line and defends to cover
elegant drive on the front foot, but straight at short cover

Netravalkar wins the battle of Borivali too, keeps the length up and the line tight. Ball may have held in the pitch and Rohit, who tried to push it towards mid-on from in front of the body, got a leading edge. In face, he rolled his fingers across, that's what deceived Rohit who probably expected it to come in. Ball went high and slow, Harmeet from mid-off went back and took a great running catch
on the back foot, nudged with an open face out to point
Fullish outside off, pushed to cover
hitting the splice hard from round the wicket, tight lines into the left-hander, who defends on the back foot

Extra bounce catches SKY on the gloves. Bat comes off right away, replay shows it hit right on the thumb and shook it badly. Physio comes out to tend to him. Was a length ball at the stumps that jumped up, SKY tried to punch it with a straight bat. He tried to get upright to adjust but the ball had wedged between the bat handle and the back hand
wafty on the back foot, hint of width as Arshdeep drags his length back. Through to the keeper
Full and Surya follows it despite the wide line, tries to go over cover but gets an edge. Falls safely outside the ring and rolls to deep third
good curl out of the hand on a full length, inside-edged into the pads as Taylor chops down late outside off
Fullish on fifth, 126ks, guided to deep-backward point
Pitched up on leg stump, whipped away to deep-backward square
very full, good bend through the air, leg to middle, blocked with a closed face to the leg side
Full and too straight, clipped to deep square leg
firm drive, on the front foot, not timed but better intent, eased back through the line for mid-off to give chase and gather
Length just outside off, guided to deep third. Stood upright and jammed the bat down on it, not much bounce, so had to play it right beside him
lovely line and angle, in from wide on the crease, zips past a tentative front foot block, so close to the stumps as the keeper scoops up low
Length around off, 134ks, defended to the bowler off the back foot
rolls the fingers on an excellent cutter, this grips from back of a length and nips past a flashy drive
Clips the fullish ball on middle to deep-backward square
makes room to leg, and has a hack through the off-side. Misses out
Length on fourth, defended back to the bowler. 131ks but Jasdeep sure does bang the ball into the pitch
short, and hoisted over fine leg for six! That's more like it from Jones. Climbing through the length, hitting up into the ball, a bit top-edgy but it does the needful
hits the pitch hard, as is his wont, angled across the left-hander, jabbed to point
Full around fourth, pushed to mid-off
pounds out his length, wide of off stump, climbing past an aggressive cut and into the keeper's gloves

And SKY uses the angle, goes across and gets low to wristily ramp it behind. He was upright for most of the journey of that length ball coming towards him, stood deep in the crease and crouched right as the ball was in his range. The feet hopped a bit and the wrists flicked and raised at the right time to elevate the ball. Amazing shot
attacking the stumps, angled in at the body, met with a respectful hop into line to defend back to the bowler
Length outside off, punched through cover
so close to the inside-edge! Zippy pace and inswing, kicks off the turf, slaps into the keeper's gloves as Jones is cut in half
Pushes the three-quarter length ball to cover
a shuffle to the pitch, nudged off the legs, no single to midwicket
Fuller side of length outside off, guided to deep third
hops into line, forced right back on the stumps to defend. Relentless pace and accuracy and USA's innings remains in a hole
Netravalkar sure is getting his processes right. Cliches aside, he's held onto a length or the fuller side to challenge both edges. This one's full and just outside off, pushed towards cover
pushed across the left-hander on a full length, chopped at the top of the bounce, down into the crease

Heart of a length, around off, defended to cover point off the back foot. No-ball being checked for and it's tight but Jasdeep's foot is on the crease, nothing behind. Tries to keep it away from the arc and deny him pace, he goes across and tries to carve it off a length. Follow-through has a flurry but the contact isn't perfect, ball rolls to cover
pulls his length back, angled in at the left-hander's body, cramped on the crease as the ball thuds to the turf
Wobble ball beats the cut. It landed around off and Pant perhaps expected the ball to go wider, went hard and square, gets cramped for room. Beaten
on the back foot, just a hint of width to flash through a cut, mopped up at deep backward point

Deep-backward square leg runs back and watch the ball fly over his right shoulder and into the cushion. Not sure if he misjudged it or was standing too near. Was a length ball just over the pad, which Pant hopped across and helped along with the pull. Went flat
tight lines from over the wicket, thumping the bat on the back foot, short cover swoops to join another dot
Full around off, pushed to mid-off
angled in at off stump, full length, met on the front foot, tapped back to the bowler
Wide and fullish, tries to hoick it downtown. Bat turns in the hand and the ball blobs into the pitch in front
swings across the short ball, wide line, it was a rare chance to swing with impunity but it's an air-shot to end the powerplay. All India at the moment
Full outside off, pushed to cvoer
full length, leg-sided, thumps the pad, deflects to the off side
Three-quarter length around off, pushed to mid-on
jabs the bat down, inside-edged past the legs, to backward square
Slow on a length, clipped off the top of middle and off, to square leg
tip and run, a sharp single to midwicket, but there was no fielder nearby. Good running
Length around fourth, clipped to midwicket
fires out the wide yorker, that was utterly pinpoint as these things go, more akin to a tennis serve right into the corner of the box
Length around fifth, may have straightened a bit, tapped to backward point

bouncer, flashed up and over Pant's leap In fact, there wasn't even any bat on that, it just climbed and kept climbing, out of the reach of everyone! stabbed out to point, Kohli sprints round from cover to gather, unleashes the shy as Taylor was sent back and slipped! But the shy was to the wrong end
Length around the stumps, clipped to midwicket
oof, too good! Round the wicket, angled in at pace, straightening off the pitch, climbing past the splice! Can't lay a bat on those!
Jumps up off a back of length, 123ks, to cramp up SKY. He jumps to tuck it to midwicket

Jumps off a length and flies off the shoulder of the bat over where first slip would've been. Goes to deep third. Was a fullish length ball around off that SKY tried to defend, had to remove the bottom hand and flinch back as ball rushed onto bat
pressed into the off side
Rocks back and pulls the shortish ball through midwicket

bouncer, pulled, top-edge, straight to Siraj at fine leg! That's the crucial wicket! Jones has been magnificent in this campaign so far, but this attack is a cut above. He tries to step up the pace but Pandya is onto him too quickly. Siraj pocketed a lobbed chance at belly height

Pant can do nothing about the shooter from around the wicket, Middle stump is bent halfway back. Ali wheels away and the batter has to walk back in resignation. Was a length ball that landed well outside off and angled back in sharply, looked to have gone under the bat and deflected off the pad and back onto the stumps. Pant's instincts had him on the back foot for the straight-bat punch, the bat was much higher up too. Not much he could've done about it.
back of a length to the new man, keeps a touch low as Kumar presses back to the bowler
Length on off, defended to cover.
poked into the covers to open his account
Close to the edge, oohs among the crowd. Length ball angling sharply at fifth stump, Dube tried to run it to third with an open bat face and no footwork. Hand-eye co-ordination didn't suffice there
fuller length, pushed across the left-hander, flashed to point off the back foot
Fullish wide ball at 140ks skids low. Dube shapes to guide it to third but is tentative and beaten. Puff of dust as the ball lands before the keeper
gives it the gallop, can't connect on the drive to mid-off. The shy comes in and there's half an appeal at the bowler's end as Rohit backhands a casual flick onto the stumps. Cheeky but safe
Fullish ball on off, defended to cover
banged into the pitch, there's no slip this time, and away to the deep third rope! A genuine edge
Three-quarter length on fourth, defended to point.
loses his line a touch, into the pads, nudged to the leg-side
soft hands on the front foot, tapped to cover
Fullish on top of off, hits high on the bat as Dube defends to cover
line and length, met on the front foot, solid defence to the off side. Diligent but it's not getting USA out of this hole in a hurry
Back of length from wide of the crease, 129ks, tapped on the head rather late. Short third/gully is close-by, so the single is not on
now that's more like it! Dube drags it down, on the pads, Taylor climbs through a rifled pull through midwicket! Hard, flat, into the chest of an unexpecting security guard! Ouch
Shortish ball at the body is tucked off the back foot to the bowler's left, van Schalkwyk flings himself but can't stop the single
back on a better length, poked to the off-side. An odd experiment, but maybe the sense that the pitch is nibbling encouraged an extra seam option
firmly onto the front foot, pushed back down the pitch
Length just outside off, guided to deep third
clipped off the toes to the on-side

Pitched up and SKY tries to go inside out but doesn't middle it, off the bottom if fact. Ball goes to the left of mid-off, who leaps across and palms it in on the bounce while falling. Parries to the left, saves two. Line of the ball was just outside off and SKY might've been early into the shot
round the wicket, leaning onto the front foot, pushed to the off-side
Length on the pads, clipped to deep square leg. 108ks
tapped with the angle from round the wicket, out to mid-on

Wide and full, Dube reaches out for a slash but can't meet the cutter that's past the tramline Into the pitch, looked pacier than before - 114ks, and beats the cut. Was shortish and Dube tried to muscle it
stops in the pitch, across the left-hander, cuffed hard but without timing off the back foot to backward point
Full on the outer-half of off, opens the face and dabs it to short third
opens the face, pressed out to cover for the single. Time for drinks with India in firm control
SKY yells 'no' as the ball trickles to point's right. Was a full ball around off that was defended late
Length just outside off, patted to poine
swing on a full length but into the pads, deflects out to point as the batter is squared up on the attempted clip
Length on middle and off, defended to cover
lovely strike, clean through mid-on... it takes a super sprawling stop from SKY at long-off to intercept. Firm lines, up into the stroke, and too straight for the man at mid-off
Length on leg, clipped to midwicket
full, on the toes, clipped to midwicket

Makes room and tries to clobber it with a flat bat but splices the length ball into the pitch and then to mid-off's left. Dube went halfway down for the single but SKY didn't move much, no run in it. Signs of pressure?
leans back to the shorter length, carved up and over the off side, solid contact but gathered in the deep
Dube makes room again, this time he gets followed by a length ball. It beats the flick and hits the pad
onto the front foot, solid on-drive, down to the boundary sweeper

Edged but doesn't carry to the keeper, angle takes it away and deep third can't cut it off. The keeper was moving to the left as the length ball was angling in towards off, Dube opened the face late to run it fine. Got it too fine but all safe. Four crucial runs to end the boundary drought
rocks back to the short ball again, another open-faced cut to deep third
chopped out to the off side, finds space in the covers
Full around off, 112ks (110-120ks seems like Anderson's range generally) pushed to cover
fuller length, on the pads, swings into a slog-sweep, gets in a tangle

Loud lbw appeal from Anderson but impact seemed outside off. Not given. Panicky running from Dube again, came forward while SKY didn't move much. Got back in time. Was a cutter on a length that spun back sharply to beat the flick. Went off the pad to the keeper's left.
donked through the line! Wonderful strike, Taylor's second boundary and his best yet, seizing on the over-pitched delivery to dump it down the ground
Clips the full ball through midwicket

inside-edge onto the stumps! Oh woe is Taylor, his beans were going, looking for another firm strike through the off-side this time, but Axar hauled his length back just enough and induced an under-edge. A gutsy knock from the depths of 3 for 2, but he's done for now

Keeps lower than SKY expected and has him on the floor. Ball was around the fuller side of length and reached him just under knee-roll height, SKY jammed his bat last second and managed to make contact
on the back foot, hacked out to the off side
Length outside off, cut to point
fired past the legs, good take but the umpire stretches his arms squeezed into the leg side, bat and pad together

SKY tries breaking free with the sweep and almost gets out, ball ballooned off the glove and landed a few feet behind the stumps. Keeper ran in front but the ball bisected him and the stumps. Was a pre-meditated shot. Got forward to take it on the full length and wanted to go square
makes room to leg, crashed hard on the up, into the covers, plugs in the deep
Drives the full ball to long-off
tight lines, rolling the fingers on the cutter, blocked on the front foot to the off side
Goes for the lofted square drive, doesn't middle the full ball and it pops up. Deep cover runs to the diagonal left, gets it on the bounce.
makes room to leg, yawned into the sightscreen! Effortless lift, freeing his arms and trusting his eye to muscle Pandya off his length. Lovely
Misses out on the full one. Dube tried to clobber it across the line but plinked it to long-off
bouncer, as well he might. Kumar ducks

Right up, deep Netravalkar runs back from short third... and drops it! Has been a dream day for him so far but not there. He was looking right up, got under it and started to squat while taking it. Got fingers on ball but it burst through. Was a fullish ball around off that SKY seemed to go for the pendulum drive (a seemingly straight drive that goes behind the keeper)
full length, scorched back past the bowler! Wonderful timing and raw power, picked the length and the pace, and nailed it through Pandya's followthrough
Tucks the length ball to square leg
poked out to point to end a 12-run over, USA's best of the innings
Length outside off, punched to cover
Back of length around top of middle and off, clipped to midwicket
chipped off the toes to the on-side
Back of length just outside off, guided to deep third
pushed across the left-hander, lashed out to point
Pulls the shortish ball to deep-backward square leg
tight lines outside off, tapped to short third
Tries to pull the bouncer angling in. Height on it is good and Dube doesn't make contact
round the wicket, gripping on a leg-stump line, thumps the pads
Back of length tucking him up. Tries to whip it through midwicket but is hurried by pace, manages to work it to the edge of the ring
Corey clears the front dog! That's a sublime pick-up, and a familiar one. Long levers, hitting up into the length, clean over deep midwicket!

Helped away in front of square somehow. That was an instance of reading the length early if there ever was one. Saw it was on the fuller side of length and outside off, stood upright and rotated his wrists to generate the power. Played it early too, to get it in the gap. No one there in front of square
cramped on the back foot, but another single as the ball deflects off the thigh. USA are making headway. Who said 137 was out of the question?
