pushed back onto the defensive despite attempting to make room to leg, fenced to the on-side
Beats the pull and hits him around the thigh
bouncer, but gets away with it, the right length skimming through at shoulder height as Kumar ducks

Finally connects, sound is sweet and looked like a second-tier hit. 87 metres. Was a length ball at the stumps, rose only to knee-roll height but didn't skid much. Anderson's pace isn't high and that came evenly enough for a cross-batted heave executed without fuss. Big pop from the crowd. Asking rate was nearing eights but two boundaries have lowered it again
has a wipe to leg, but can't connect, Arshdeep hitting a teasing in-between length, across the right-hander
Tucks it to the leg side for a single

wonderful grab at deep midwicket! It's a big, big square boundary but Nitesh nailed his pull, up into the stroke. It looked to have the legs but Siraj backpedalled well, timed his leap backwards, and clung on high above his head before slumping to the pitch inside the rope! Arshdeep has three and the USA are back in the soup
SKY shapes to go across and waits for the delivery, Anderson decides to stay on a length and hold a fourth-stump line. Pats it in front
over the wicket to the left-hander, keeps low and squeezed to leg
Drags the full ball from outside off to deep square leg with a sweep
hits a probing length from over the wicket, soft-handed block into the off side
Goes for the yorker and doesn't miss by much. Whipped to long-on
Clips the length ball through midwicket
full length, round the wicket, Corey opens the face on the back foot and burgles a boundary through deep third. Handy!
Clips the length ball off the back foot through midwicket
hits the pitch, cramping the left-hander on the crease from round the wicket
Hard-length ball has been pulled to deep midwicket
nudges another single to keep USA ticking
Shortish ball angling down leg has been pulled to short fine

flicked off the hips, top-edge over fine leg! Bumrah is going the journey in this over! Cramped on a leg-stump line, but Bumrah's pace and lift do the work for him! The first six he's conceded all tournament
Tries to burgle two but bowler chases back to midwicket to keep it to one. Was a length ball that was clipped gently and SKY started running right as it made contact
fuller length, drilled through the line, confident intent on the front foot, in the air and into space at deep cover
Taps the length ball outside off to the backward-point area
pushed into the off side. A rare double-figures over from Bumrah. USA closing in on their 120-130 target
good cutter, bites the pitch and climbs into a hard pull, can't connect
Full ball has been flicked over the vacant midwicket infield, they look for two but it's not on

another short ball, lobs to Pant behind the stumps... there's a distinct lack of excitement, but Rohit is reviewing. Is there a suspicion of glove before the ball clearly clipped the shoulder. It was mighty close to top-edge as Harmeet swung through his pull, but nothing doing
Tries to cuff the length ball down the ground with a flat bat. Gets it along the ground, long-on runs to the right and stops it
yorker, lovely bowling, and very well dug out too. Jabbing the toe of the bat down into the blockhole

Launched but is it too high? No enough distance too, clears the extra-cover boundary and brings the Indian supporters back ti life. Was overpitched and seemed like the slower one, it was in his half and he seemed to wait an extra second to middle it. Held his shape well
pace off on the short ball, Harmeet shapes for the pull, is completely deceived by the variation and wears it on the shoulder again. The deflection flies square for a bye

SKY has effectively cleared the game with these two boundaries. Went orthodox first and then funky. Lunged low and helped the length ball over the shoulder with the ramp. Cleared short fine with ease and gets a one-bounce four

hacked high, high, high in the air! Anderson makes room to leg, Hardik followed him with the short ball, the ball soared miles in the air to square leg, and Pant demonstrates once again that he is fully match-fit with a wonderfully judged sprint from behind the stumps, calling early and ushering his outfielder out of the way to take it at full tilt over his shoulder
And this time, he gets a quick two
another short ball, shaping away outside off, Hardik's work is done, and it's been excellent work. A wicket maiden to finish!
Slow and shortish just outside off, miscues the pull but gets it to midwicket

hoisted high to deep midwicket but a horror drop from Siraj! An excellent bouncer, following the batter, Siraj has one super catch to his name but he misjudged that badly, throwing himself forward at the last second and letting it through his hands
Shortish ball lifts to around waist-height, it's helped over short fine with an aerial pull. Amazing wristwork again, deep backward square runs right to stop it
cuffed into the off side for the single
Length around off, clipped to deep fine leg

that's the ticket! Arshdeep persists with his short-ball policy, Harmeet has a swish across the line, gets a thin edge off the shoulder of his bat, Pant times his leap behind the stumps and Arshdeep does have four after all!
Length on middle and leg, flicked through forward square leg
round the wicket, attacking length to the right-hander, cautious block on the front foot
Length just outside off, seemed slow, worked to the bowler's right
full length, attacking the stumps, punched through the line to long-on to bring up the 100. It's something, can they make it something more?
Length outside off, late cut to backward point's left
back of a length, nearly the five-for! A cramped slap into the covers, but reaches the man on the bounce. The end of a wonderful spell from Arshdeep
Cutter on a length, flicked from the channel to long-on

SKY gets fifty with an edged glance. Crowd, team-mates, WaGs applaud and he raises his bat high. He's had to rein himself in but has managed a couple of flamboyant shots on a tough pitch. Was a low fully that went to the keeper's left. Half-stopped but single taken
full length, whipped off the pads, behind square to fine leg

Wide and full, let go to collect the extra Drills a very full ball down the ground. Long-on runs across and stops it with a dive. Looks rough on a sandy outfield, that allows time for the batters to take two and help India complete the win
rolls the fingers, back of a length, hops through to the keeper with all the pace off the ball
wide on the crease, fires in the blockhole ball, bashed into the covers
right back on the stumps, dragging a flat pull to the leg side as the ball skids low. Backward square gathers
slower ball, pace off again, another urgent wipe but that hops low past the off stump
inside-edge, off the pads to backward point. Bumrah goes wicketless but gives nothing away in that final over
pace off again, dies in the pitch on the wide angle across the left-hander, no contact on a flashy cut
finds the gap at wide long-on! Siraj hits the pitch outside off, inviting a launch to leg and SvS connects sweetly!
slower bouncer, wide of the batter in his stance, can't connect on a thrashed uppercut
hoisted off the pads, in the air but not timed, deep square rushes in but it's two more
full length, outside off, makes room to leg again and crashed back past the bowler. Another single to mid-off
good finish, pace back on, beats a wild wipe to leg, the batters sprint for the bye, but Pant lobs to Siraj, whose direct hit at the bowler's end is true. Out by three metres. 111 will be the target
tossed up on a length on middle and off. Conway plays outside the line and gets pinged on the back thigh
length delivery swinging into the pads. King plays all over it and the ball trickles away into the on side for a leg bye
fuller outside of and this shapes away just a shade. Conway closes his bat face early and the leading edge bobbles past extra cover
well well! Full in the channel just outside off. Swings back in and goes past Charles' massive swing. He was probably looking to hit that to Guyana
starts off with the one that shapes in. Allen hangs back and pats it into the off side
full toss shaping into middle and off. Charles comes forward and turns it towards mid wicket
fuller outside off. Swings in again and Allen carefully defends
oh! Back of a length just outside off. Does not swing back in and goes on with the angle. Charles goes feeling for it and is beaten
back of a length just outside off. Conventional off-spinner and Allen pulls it down to long on
shortish outside off. Charles lets it go. That bounced again before reaching Conway
back of a length on the stumps. Conway tucks it off his hips towards deep backward square leg

chopped on! A Boult from the New Zealand blue! Length just outside off that might have just held in the surface a shade. Charles gives himself room, trying to force it through the off side. The bottom hand takes over too much, though, and he tugs at it, eventually dragging it onto his stumps. Just the start NZ would have been after!
fires it way down leg. Pooran does well to gather to his right. Called a wide hard length on middle and off. Conway hops up onto his toes and fends it into the on side for a quick single
peach! Length delivery that pitches in the channel and decks back sharply. King goes searching for it and is cut in half. Sails over the stumps!
Allen is up and running! Marginally short outside off and Allen makes the most of it. Stands up on his toes and hammers it past deep square leg!
full on middle and off. A hint of shape away from King. He comes forward and tips it to mid on to get off the mark
full just outside off. Allen drops it into the off side with soft hands and Conway is alert enough to sneak in a single
length delivery pushed across the batter outside off. Pooran comes forward and watches it go through to the keeper
oh! Back of a length on middle and off. Climbs onto Conway and he has to take his bottom hand off to ride it. Trickles off his pads into the off side eventually
length just outside off. Curves back in and takes the inside edge as Pooran wafts at it. Trickles away into the square leg region
almost! Length outside off. Allen tries to force it through the off side and nearly chops it back onto his stumps
hard length on middle and off. King advances, trying to manufacture something but can only scuff it to mid off

short and wide outside off. Swings away further from Allen, who swishes and misses. Called a wide, though peach! Back of a length in the channel just outside off. Threatens to angle in before nipping away. Squares Allen up and he is beaten on the outside
back of a length on middle and leg. King skips down again and hacks at it. Does not make contact and the ball brushes the back thigh on its way to Conway
length outside off. Conway gets down on one knee and sweeps it towards deep square leg
streaky but they all count! Fullish, angling into leg stump. Pooran, having advanced, has a wild slog at it and the ball flies off the leading edge, beating third man
length outside off. Allen opts to stay back and jabs it towards backward point
back of a length on middle and leg. Pooran tries to smash that into next week and cops a blow on the body for his troubles
goes all the way! Arm-ball that swerves into the slot on off stump. Allen plants his front foot, goes with the swing and thumps it over cow corner!
much fuller, pushed into the pads. Pooran jumps outside leg, swings at it and chips it over mid wicket. The bottom hand came off and he could not get the timing he was after
back of a length on middle and off. Allen waits in his crease and knocks it to long on
back of a length just outside off. Pooran goes back and runs it down to third man
tossed up on a length on off. Conway comes forward and defends
shortish just outside off. King stands tall and swats it straight to mid on. Calls for the single immediately and makes it comfortably enough

Conway perishes, and it is that man Akeal Hosein again! Slowed up a smidgen on a length on off. Conway looks for the sweep but this seems to be the arm-ball. Holds in the surface, bounces extra and loops up off the top edge. Chase makes no mistake at short fine leg, and that is a vital breakthrough for the West Indies!
full on the pads. Pooran gets forward and works it towards deep square leg to retain strike
Allen greets Russell with a boundary! Shortish on the pads and Allen is never going to miss out. Uses his wrists and whips it behind square!
back of a length just outside off. Not a lot of pace off the surface and Pooran inside-edging his slog into his back thigh
cutter on a full length on middle and leg. Allen comes forward and pokes it towards mid on
up and over! Shorter and much wider outside off, giving Pooran the room to free his arms. He holds his shape too and crashes it over cover point!
hard length on middle and off. Allen gets up on his toes and defends. Gesticulates that the ball bounced higher than he expected
dropped! Back of a length just outside off. Pooran opens up his stance and absolutely smacks it. Hits it straight to Mitchell at short extra cover, who puts down. That was travelling...
back of a length on middle and off. Allen meets it right under his eyes with a straight bat
four more! Slower ball on a length just outside off. Pooran picks it early, plants his front foot and bashes it past mid on!
angled in on a length on off. The cutter grips in the surface and Allen prods it past mid wicket for a single

goes straight up, and Southee gets the better of Pooran! Banged in short outside off and this gets awfully big on Pooran. He tries to swipe it away but the extra bounce means that he cannot control the stroke. Skews off the top edge and Conway, after circling under it for a bit, completes the catch. West Indies have been rocked again! Hang on. Just hang on...there is a check to see if the ball touched the wire of the spider-cam. If it did, it will be called a dead ball and Pooran will survive. The third umpire is happy that is not the case, and Pooran's dismissal has been confirmed!
dug into the track on middle and leg. Rachin hops up onto his toes and drops it into the off side. Another example of tennis-ball bounce
full on middle and off. Chase lets the ball come to him before poking it towards mid on
back of a length on middle and leg. Allen goes back and punches it uppishly towards long on
back of a length just outside off. King dangles his bat and the ball rolls away off the inside edge towards short fine leg
length just outside off. Rachin hangs back and scuffs his cut into the off side
fullish, angling into off. Chase presses half forward and pushes it to mid on
darted in on a back of a length on off. Rachin hops back and eases it to long on to get off the mark

Chase bites the dust too! West Indies are faltering! Dug into the track just outside off and Chase thinks he can deposit this in front of square. The ball seems to hold in the surface a shade, though, which means Chase is slightly early into the stroke. Clinks it up tamely and Rachin, running back from mid on, does the rest. Three wickets in the powerplay, and NZ well on top!
finds the gap! Short outside off and that provides the width Allen is after. Uses the depth of the crease and cracks it to cover point's left!
back of a length on middle and leg. Powell tucks it off his hips towards deep square leg
angled in on a back of a length on off. Keeps a little low and Allen pushes it towards short mid wicket
back of a length just outside off. King hangs back and meets the ball right under his eyes
shortish outside off. Another arm-ball and Allen plonks it towards mid off
shortish outside off. King throws his hands at it but because he is early into the stroke, he chops it perilously past his stumps

dropped by Rutherford! Length just outside off. Allen swishes across the line but gets a massive leading edge. Rutherford runs back from cover point, gets under it but cannot hold on. Perhaps Rutherford overrun it a little, and that could be a big moment in the game. The ball might have actually slipped through Rutherford's hands
hard length on middle and off. Powell gets behind the line and taps it gently towards mid wicket
hard length on middle and leg, cramping the batter for room. Allen defends off the back foot
length just outside off. Powell comes forward and defends
short on leg stump. Allen gets inside the line and helps it straight to the fielder at short fine leg
angled in on a length on middle and off. Powell gets onto the front foot and blocks

taken this time! Joseph breaks the game open further! Sharp back of a length delivery on middle and off, and this gets onto Allen quickly. Up to his chest and the lack of room means he cannot free his arms. Splices it straight to Russell at deep square leg, and he was never going to drop that!

edged and gone! Southee strikes again, and West Indies are in all sorts of trouble now! Back of a length in the sixth stump channel. Powell looks to guide it fine but the ball climbs onto it. He cannot get on top of it and all he manages is a nick through to Conway, who stoops down low to snare the chance. This has been a dream start for the Kiwis!
back of a length on off. Williamson runs it down towards slip and Rachin calls him through for the single
back of a length on leg stump. Rutherford helps it round the corner and gets off the mark
back of a length on off. Rachin gets on top of the bounce and dabs it down to deep backward point
slanted in on a length on middle and leg. King plays all over his flick and the ball thuds into his thigh pad
flighted up full outside off. Drops on the batter late and then spins back, taking the inside edge and thudding into the pads
full outside off. Rutherford presses forward and drives it towards deep cover point
shortish on middle and leg. Rachin hangs back and pulls it towards deep mid wicket for a couple of runs
King counter-punches! In the slot outside off and no half-measures from King. Springs forward, extends his arms and lofts it cleanly over mid off!
back of a length outside off. Rachin goes back and punches it to long on

six and out! The crowd are stunned, and half of the West Indian side is now back in the shed! Fullish outside off. Perhaps a bit of nip away and King is drawn into a poke with an open bat face. Almost guides it to Conway's right, who dives smartly and holds on!

edged and gone! The crowd erupts, and Williamson has to walk back! Fizzed through on a back of a length outside off. Williamson thinks it is short enough to cut and shapes for the stroke. The ball, though, spins just enough to graze the outside edge and Pooran, after a slight juggle, completes the catch. Massive moment in the game!
edged! Full and wide outside off. Hosein goes nibbling at it and edges it down to third man
full on leg stump. Mitchell gets down on one knee early and paddles it fine to get off the mark with a brace
fullish, angling into off stump. Rutherford comes half forward and prods it back to the bowler
goes through Chase! Full outside off. Mitchell unfurls the reverse this time and helps it towards backward point, where Chase dives over it!
short outside off. Rutherford waits for it and cuts it past backward point for a single
hard length on middle and leg. Rachin gets up on his toes and glances it down to fine leg
shortish just outside off. Rutherford rides the bounce and runs it down to third man
dug into the track on middle and off. Mitchell helps it round the corner towards fine leg. Rachin wanted the second but Mitchell was not as interested
length on leg stump. Pitches and nips back in, going past the inside edge of Hosein's bat and thudding into his thigh pad
back of a length on middle and leg. Rachin comes half forward and defends
back of a length just outside off. Hosein stays back and defends
shortish on the pads. Rachin tucks it off his hips past mid wicket and gets back for two
full outside off. Hosein comes forward and pushes it towards mid off. Williamson misfields and that allows the second. First real mistake NZ have made in the field tonight
risky running! Back of a length on the stumps. Rachin bunts it to mid off and sets off for the single. Has to scamper and a direct hit might have made things interesting
back of a length on off. Hosein stabs at it and chunks it off the inside half of the bat towards deep square leg
back of a length just outside off. Mitchell gets a half stride in before blocking
fuller, slanting into middle and leg. Rutherford pokes it back to the bowler
very full on leg stump. Hosein digs it out towards the bowler
full on middle and off. Rachin flicks it towards King at short mid wicket, who gets a hand to it but cannot save the single
slowed up on a full length on middle and off. Hosein stretches forward and knocks it to long off
back of a length on off. Mitchell lets the ball come to him before patting it towards extra cover
full toss down leg. Rutherford does not get bat on it and the ball scraps the pad, running away past Conway towards fine leg
length just outside off. Mitchell skips down and places the ball perfectly between deep mid wicket and deep square leg. Brace completed comfortably
full on middle and leg. Rutherford flicks it down the ground to long on
shortish outside off. Mitchell goes back and pushes it towards backward point. A slight misfield but no damage done
clean as a whistle! Tossed up into the slot outside off and Hosein climbs into it. Plants his front foot, swings through the line and pumps it over long off!

Motie has another! And Russell has another catch too! Fired into the slot on middle and leg. Rachin thinks he can whip this off his pads and into the stands. Gets a decent chunk of it but dos not get the elevation to clear deep mid wicket. Russell barely has to move, and NZ are four down now!
back of a length on middle and off. Hosein waits in his crease and punches it to long on
full on middle and leg. Phillips gets forward and works it past short mid wicket to get off the mark
floated up full outside off. Phillips knocks it down the ground to long off
back of a length just outside off. Hosein goes back and works it towards deep square leg
flighted up full just outside off. Straightens off the surface and trickles off the outside edge towards backward point
shortish outside off. Comes off a touch slower than Rutherford expects and he scuffs it towards extra cover
full on middle and off. Driven down the ground to long off
hard length on middle and off. Rutherford stays back and pulls it towards long on. No real timing on that either
length on off. Mitchell comes forward and defends
off-pace on a length just outside off. Deviates into Hosein and he is beaten on the inside as he looks to defend. Gets struck on the thigh
given a bit of air on a full length outside off. Mitchell lunges forward and smothers it
length in the sixth stump channel. Holds its line after pitching and Hosein, feeling for it outside his eye-line, sees the ball sneak past the outside edge
length on middle and off. Mitchell nails the reverse sweep but cannot get it past backward point
oh dear! Back of a length just outside off and that almost rolls along the floor. Hosein cannot get his bat down and that is another sign of variable bounce
full outside off. Phillips drives it towards deep cover point
Rutherford welcomes Santner with a six! A bit of a drag-down on middle and leg. Rutherford rocks onto the back foot and whacks it over deep mid wicket!
angled in full on the pads. Mitchell tucks it away towards deep mid wicket
another shortish delivery on middle and off. Rutherford goes back and pulls it towards long on
back of a length on middle and off. Phillips goes back and taps it towards backward point
back of a length just outside off. Hosein turns it towards short mid wicket
fired in full outside off. Phillips gets to the pitch of the ball and drills it past extra cover for a brace
floated up fuller outside off. Hosein comes forward and plays it back to the bowler, who dives to his left and stops it one-handed
back of a length outside off. Phillips jabs it towards deep cover point
given plenty of air on a full length outside off. Hosein gets down on one knee and drags it to deep mid wicket's left

cleans him up with an absolute corker! Floated up deliciously on a fullish length on middle and off. Drifts into Mitchell, which makes him think he can go over Motie's head. Drops on him late, though, and then rips past the outside edge, knocking back off stump. Mitchell cannot believe what has happened, but he has to walk back. West Indies continue to tighten their grip on this game!

taken sharply by Neesham! Back of a length on middle and off. Holds in the surface and spins back into Hosein. He tries to work it past short mid wicket but hits it uppishly. Neesham snaps to his left and gobbles up the chance. Just as a partnership was building, WI lose their sixth!
back of a length on off. Rutherford jabs it towards deep cover point

slides this down leg first up. Phillips does not get bat on it and the umpire has no qualms in calling it a wide back of a length on middle and leg. Keeps a tad low and Phillips prods it hurriedly towards short mid wicket
oh, hello! Ferguson goes full on middle and leg, and Russell is waiting for it. Gives himself a touch of room and lifts it over the bowler's head!
shortish on the pads. Phillips hops back and tucks it off his hips towards deep square leg

shortish delivery that slides down leg. Russell gets inside the line and lets it go. Called a wide another back of a length delivery that strays down leg. Russell does not get bat on it and the umpire has to indulge in some more exercise oh! Sharp bumper on off. Russell seems to pick it a little late and has to hurriedly duck out of the way
length on middle and leg. Neesham nurdles it into the on side and gets off the mark
length delivery angling into leg stump. Russell clears his front leg and has a massive yahoo across the line. Only connects with fresh air. That was not far away from leg stump either

oh dear, what have you done, Nicholas Pooran?! Back of a length on the stumps. Phillips drops it into the on side and sets off for the single. A bit of yes and no between him and both batters are stranded mid-way. Pooran gathers, takes an age to take aim and then fires a throw at the stumps. He could have run up to the stumps and still gotten the batters out but he went for the glory throw, and failed!
first six for Russell! Ferguson goes fuller but this is outside off, which gives Russell the swinging room he desires. Clears his front leg and smites it over long on!
length outside off. Neesham advances and plays it back to the bowler
four to end the over! Shortish on leg stump. Russell knows that length is coming after the six the previous ball. Sets up for it, opens up his front hip and swats it past deep backward square leg!
darted in full on middle and leg. Neesham comes half forward and plonks it back towards the bowler
angled in on a length just outside off. Comes in with the arm and Phillips, nibbling at it, almost drags it back onto his stumps
length just outside off. Rutherford comes forward and pushes it towards extra cover for a single

Phillips breaks the shackles! In the slot on leg stump. Phillips plants his front foot, gets under it and muscles it just over Charles at deep mid wicket. He was hitting with the wind, and that helped Phillips massively!
back of a length just outside off. Russell has another mighty whoosh across the line but makes no contact. Russell tried to hit that too hard

huge appeal, not given! Back of a length just outside off. Skids on with the angle and keeps low. Phillips seems to swish at thin air but Pooran is interested in the caught-behind. They deliberate and then decide against the review. Nothing on UltraEdge either

Boult outwits Russell! And the crowd goes silent again! Off-pace and into the track outside off. Russell, like the last ball, almost swings himself off his feet. Loses all shape and spoons it up off the outer half of the bat. Ferguson settles under it at short third and makes no mistake. This could impact how many WI eventually end up with!
shorter outside off. Phillips looks for the cut but scuffs it towards extra cover
bumper to welcome Shepherd. On middle and off, and Shepherd ducks under it
full outside off. Phillips stretches forward and pokes it back to Motie
hard length on middle and off. Shepherd gets into line and stabs it behind square on the leg side
fired in full outside off. Phillips digs it out towards extra cover. Dot to end the over
slower ball on a back of a length just outside off. Jabbed out to backward point
length just outside off. Shepherd presses half forward and pats it gently towards extra cover

bursts through the hands! Length ball on the pads. Neesham plants his front foot and clips it straight down Charles' throat. But somehow, Charles lets the ball go through his hands. Hits the rope on the full as well to add to his and the West Indies' misery!
fullish outside off. Shepherd gets forward and pokes it enough to extra cover's left to pick up a single
dug into the track on middle and off. Neesham rides the bounce and fends it into the on side for a single
full just outside off. Rutherford leans into his stroke and drives it crisply past extra cover for a couple of runs
back of a length just outside off. Jabbed out towards extra cover
lifter outside off! Back of a length, laced with width. Rutherford thinks about the cut but has to pull out because of the extra bounce
cutter on a back of a length outside off. Phillips stands tall and punches it towards deep cover point
back of a length on off. Rutherford tips it to backward point and sets off immediately. Has to scramble to the other end but makes it via a dive
full outside off. Neesham comes half forward and dabs it towards backward point
back of a length outside off. Seems like a leg-cutter and this squirms past the outside edge of Shepherd's bat
length outside off and this cuts back in with the angle. Neesham has a wild waft at it and is beaten on the inside
back of a length just outside off. Phillips gets up on his toes and eases it towards backward point
length on middle and leg. Rutherford lets the ball come to him before knocking it to long on
back of a length just outside off. Skids on and Neesham, looking for the dab, is late on the stroke

palmed over the bar! Short ball on leg stump. Shepherd gets inside the line and heaves it away towards fine leg. Boult leaps up into the air on the fence but can only push it over the ropes. He was not right on the fence and that may have proved crucial
length on middle and leg. Neesham camps deep in his crease and helps it behind square on the leg side. Good fielding by short fine leg to prevent the second
back of a length on middle and leg. Shepherd tucks it off his hips towards deep square leg
length outside off. Phillips presses half forward and punches it towards deep cover point
hard length, angling into off. Rutherford wants to tip and run to backward point again but this time, Shepherd sends him back
off-pace on a length on off. Neesham tips it towards backward point and Phillips hares across to complete the single
back of a length on off. Rutherford drops it into the off side and gets the single he is after
hard length on middle and leg. Phillips seems to have poked it past Russell, until he brings out the superman dive to his right and saves the single
shortish on middle and off. Shepherd sits back in his crease and swings it away towards deep mid wicket

this has gone so high up and this is going to bring down the clouds with it. Still in the air...still in the air...and eventually taken by Brandon King! Fullish and angling across the batter outside off. Neesham tries to smoke this into oblivion but only gets elevation. King has to wait an eternity under it, running to his left from extra cover and when it does, he is on top of his game. Clean catch, and NZ sink further into trouble!
very full outside off. Shepherd squeezes it out towards backward point
dug into the track on off stump. Santner gets up on his toes and defends. Phillips wanted the single but the fielder at backward point was sharp enough to prevent it
full on the pads. Rutherford uses the angle and flicks it away towards deep square leg
shortish on middle and leg. Denies Santner any room and he can only drop it into the off side

short ball that slides down leg. The square leg umpire has his arms stretched out too, indicating it may have also been higher than what is allowed fuller on the pads. Shepherd glances it towards short fine leg
back of a length outside off. Santner slaps it towards extra cover, where Hosein misfields and allows Santner to get off the mark
swung away for six! Half-tracker down leg and that is easy pickings for Rutherford. He gets inside the line early and helps it over the long leg fence!
length on middle and off. Phillips can do nothing productive with it and blocks it towards the bowler
full outside off. Rutherford gets forward and drives it towards deep cover point
slower ball on a length outside off. Phillips plants his front foot and drills it to long on
full on the pads again. Shepherd works it away slightly uppishly towards deep backward square leg
starts off the over with a boundary! Slower ball into the track outside off. Sits up to be hit and Phillips smears it past deep mid wicket!
slower ball in the slot outside off and Shepherd will feel he missed out there. Drills it straight to extra cover
back of a length just outside off. Phillips drives it on the up but straight to extra cover

a Ferguson celebrappeal, and the finger goes up. That looked pretty plumb! Shortish on middle and off. Decks back in off the surface and keeps low too. Shepherd, swiping across the line, misses it by a margin and the ball pins him on the back leg, right in front of middle stump. Shepherd has reviewed it, but it looks more in hope than anticipation. No bat involved and Ball Tracking has it smashing into middle stump, two-thirds of the way up. West Indies are eight down now!
just clears the fence! Off-pace on a back of a length outside off. Phillips stands up tall and with all his weight on the back foot, he muscles it over long on!
full outside off. Joseph comes onto the front foot and punches it towards deep cover point
angled in on a length on the pads. Keeps a little low and hurries onto Phillips. He plays all over it and gets hit on the pads
off-pace on a full length on off. Rutherford pushes it to extra cover and saunters across to the other end
short outside off. Phillips throws his hands at it and drills it towards deep cover point. A bit of hesitation on the second initially but then eventually get it via an overthrow
back of a length just outside off. Keeps very low and Joseph does well to stab it towards mid wicket
very full on middle and leg. Phillips digs it out towards the bowler, who gets his right hand to it and parries it to long on
back of a length on middle and leg. Rutherford eases it down the ground to long on
banged in short on leg stump and this does not get up as high as Phillips expects. Misses his pull and wears a blow on the back thigh for his troubles
back of a length just outside off. Sticks in the surface and Rutherford pokes it down to long on
finds the fence this time! Similar length but this is a change-up. Phillips picks it, reads the bounce and pummels it between deep mid wicket and deep square leg!
gets it away! Slower delivery dug into the track on leg stump. Joseph gets inside the line, rolls his wrists and tickles it past short fine leg. Southee cannot catch up and those are four vital runs!
back to back boundaries! Joseph keeps badgering that hard length, but Phillips now seems ready for it. Opens up his front hip and pounds it past deep mid wicket!
length outside off and this barely gets up. Joseph has a waft at it and sees the ball squirm underneath his bat

miscued, and the West Indies captain completes the catch! Is that the game? Banged in shortish on middle and leg. This is a little shorter than the previous deliveries and gets bigger on Phillips. He cannot free his arms fully and he shanks it towards long on. Powell comes charging in and snaffles up the chance. Hops up in delight, and the West Indies know they are almost there!
hard length on off, angling into the batter. Joseph is cramped for room and hacks it towards extra cover

Southee departs first ball! Back of a length just outside off. Southee pre-meditates his shuffle across his stumps. By the time the ball arrives, he is cramped for room and all he can do is spoon it up. Joseph calls early, runs back to his right and takes the catch. Joseph has four, West Indies have eight, and the finish line very much within sight now!

cleans him up! Back of a length just outside off. Skids on low and comes back in with the angle. Joseph is late to get his bat down, beaten by the inward movement and the lack of bounce. Kisses the outside of off stump, and the Kiwis are just one wicket away from bowling West Indies out!
edged! Speared in full on middle and off. Boult backs away and throws the kitchen sink at it, slicing it down to third man
back of a length on middle and off. Motie gets behind the line and defends
hard length on leg stump, skidding onto Santner and rushing him for pace. He misses it and the ball rolls away off his thigh pad into the off side
slower ball on a length outside off. Rutherford reaches out for it and drags it towards deep mid wicket. Single turned down
length on off. Boult sits deep in his crease and tugs it towards deep mid wicket
watch that ball fly! Slower delivery that sits up to be hit outside off. Rutherford reads it like the morning daily, opens up his stance and thumps it over long off!
off-pace and into the track outside off. Santner has not picked it and swings way too early. Only connects with fresh air

back to back sixes - this is even better! Right in the slot on the stumps, and Rutherford is not going to miss out. Snaps his wrists into action and launches it over long off. Almost like a short-arm jab but that carried 86m!
into the blockhole outside off. Santner digs it out towards long off
fires in a yorker on the pads. Rutherford cannot work it away and the ball strikes him on the front pad
fetch that! Slower ball that lands right in the slot on middle and leg. Boult backs away and clobbers it over deep mid wicket!
or, maybe not! Why run singles when you can hit sixes?! Another half-tracker, this time on leg stump. Rutherford picks it up and dumps it over the fine leg fence!

Russell has the last laugh! Cutter into the track outside off. Boult continues swinging at it but does not pick the variation. Swipes too early at it and the ball skews up off the outside edge. Chase settles under it and hammers the ninth nail into the New Zealand coffin!
length on middle and leg. Rutherford pushes it to long on and keeps strike for the start of the next over. Brings up his fifty too, and the crowd is up on its feet!
short outside off. Rutherford winds up and powers it straight to long off. Dot to start the over
six number one! In the slot outside off. Santner stays leg side and goes inside out, creaming it over the deep extra cover fence!
short outside off again. Rutherford cuts it towards deep cover point and is hell-bent on the second. The throw is not great and Rutherford can make it back
two sixes in a row! Oh, hello! Shortish on middle and leg. Santner picks the length early, clears his front leg and smokes it over deep mid wicket!
that is a stunning shot! Shortish outside off. Rather than trying to drag it, Rutherford holds his shape. Goes through the line and crunches it over extra cover, off the back foot!
dot ball! Slower ball dug into the track outside off. Santner tries to hit it too hard and drags it into the on side
safe! Given a bit of air on a length outside off. Rutherford dances down, trying to go downtown. Slices it but luckily for him, it falls in front of deep cover point. Races back to retain strike
third six of the over! Slower ball on a length outside off. Santner plants his front foot and boshes it clean over long on!
pick the bones out of this one! Santner tries to hide it outside off but Rutherford has read his intentions. Walks across, gets down on one knee and slugs it over wide long on!
slow, short and wide outside off. Santner swishes himself off his feet but only swats away a few flies in the process

four to finish off! Rutherford ends with 68 off 39, and WI finish on 149! Back of a length outside off. Rutherford sits deep in his crease, brings his wrists into play and bludgeons it to deep cover point's left. A sensational shot to cap off a sensational innings!

There it is! A Trinidadian tale of triumph to tell for Rovman Powell and his team! Dug in short outside off. Santner has another mow at it and heaves it towards deep mid wicket. Does not matter, though because it is the West Indies that march on to the Super Eight, and they are smiles in the dugout, even as the Kiwis wonder what next is in store for them!
Big swing first up, inside edge saves Levitt. Was a full ball that swung late, Levitt was hurried and in a last-second move, jammed it down
Hint of shape into Tanzid but the line is down leg. The ball flicks Tanzid's pads through to the keeper.
Length on leg, clipped to the bowler's right
Back of a length ball on middle. No swing but the speed went up from 126 to 135kph. Tanzid defends back to the bowler
The Fizz overpitches in the pursuit of swing and offers a bit of width, Levitt capitalises by smearing it along the ground through cover. Bowler slaps his hand in disappointment
Shimmies down the track now and gives himself room as well. Kingma keeps the lines tight though cramping the batter for room. The ball thuds into his thigh pad to the off side
Length at the stumps, defended in front
Ooh, lot of bounce and carry but the line is well outside off. Called a wide. On a length with a hint of batter on off, he opens the face of the blade and gets it to deep point
Walks down and has an ungainly flat-bat, splices the shortish ball a few feet left of the bowler. The call for the single is early
Swing again, but Kingma is struggling with his line for now. On leg stump, raps into Tanzid's pads as he looks for a flicks. The ball rolls to short fine leg
Long bat-lift from O-Dowd as he blocks the length ball in front
This one keeps low now. Back of a length ball just outside off. The ball does not rise as much as Tanzid was hoping. He looks for a wild hack, and the ball goes under his bat
Rushes in on off stump, he defends off the backfoot
Fullish ball around off is run down to deep third with an open bat-face

Oh, dear me! Shanto has revere-swept Dutt straight to first slip! That is such a soft dismissal. The ball lands well outside off and drifts away. Shanto looks for a reverse, does not connect cleanly and Vikramjit takes a simple catch.
Angles it back in for a bat-pad hit. Was a fullish ball that swung towards off, Levitt tried defending straight
There's that bounce because of his height. On a length on off, he gets across and works it towards square leg.
Square drives it sweetly. Used the away movement well and munched it on top of the bounce, found cover point though
The ball pitches outside off, and bounces steeply as Tanzid gets on top and cuts to backward point
Tanzim misses the line and O'Dowd helps the fullish ball fine. Bonus four to fine leg

Oh, miscommunication but Tanzid just makes it back because the fielder slipped. Was shorter and slower, Tanzid goes back and pulls to midwicket's right who does well. Tanzid is halfway down the pitch, but because the fielder slipped, he made it back
Late movement to beat bat. Lands on the heart of a length and straightens. Line around sixth stump and O'Dowd had a tentative poke towards cover
Very flat but the line is down leg. The balls flicks Tanzid's pad to the keeper. They pinch in a quick leg-bye
Punches the length ball to cover

Huge shout from Taskin for caught behind. Not given. LItton has a long chat with the bowler, they won't go for it in the end. Looked like an outswinger off the hand, seam was pointing towards first slip but that hit the seam and jagged back in. Levitt tried to defend straight and was cut in half. Close to the inside edge but no contact. Ultra-Edge shows the sound was off the bat flicking the pocket

Short, pulled and he does not get a clean connection. But the ball falls in no-man's land. Short of a length ball outside off. He looks to pull but the ball gets big on him and results in a slight top edge. The ball past midwicket's grasp.
Levitt takes a chance, connects with a slog sweep over square leg. Ample bravado in that shot, was a pre-meditated hit. Got on one knee and under it
Gets a good connection this time around. Back of a length ball on his hips, Tanzid swivels and helps this over short fine leg

Direct hit from mid-off, has Levitt run himself out? Coin-toss decision, so very close but a tiny fraction of the bat seems to be in as the bails were dislodged. Was a full ball that was driven, Levitt took off for a very tight single. He leapt into the dive with sheer desperation, and it saved him

Oh, that's a tremendous shot from Tanzid! Length ball on the stumps, he shimmies down the track, gives himself room and slaps it hard over covers. The ball flies flat and hits the advertisement hoardings on the full
Into the pitch, over the stumps. Defended in front
Back of a length ball sliding across Tanzid, who cuts it past backward point. Deep third gets across well, and even though his spike gets caught on the turf, he saves a couple of runs
Goes across, outside off, to cut the line but Taskin keeps it around sixth stump to beat the straight-bat defence

Oh, the ball gets caught in Tanzid's helmet grill. Wow, have never seen that before, I must admit. Bouncer aimed at his body. Tanzid looks for a pull, and ends up top-edging the ball into his helmet grill. The ball gets lodged into the visor and stays there. Off comes the helmet, and he will have a concussion test. Talk about keeping the eye on the ball.
Hard-length ball beats the cut. The shot was on as there was a bit of room but the 138ks ball got good bounce

Cracked away through cover-point and he gets four more. 18 off that over, just what Bangladesh would have wanted. Short and wide, he stands tall and slaps it through the fielder's legs. Deep third can't do much

Oh, my God! What a stunning catch by Engelbrecht! How has he caught that? Length ball on the stumps, Litton goes for a sweep, gets a top edge with the ball going towards square leg. Engelbrecht was placed behind square. He sprints across, covers a lot of ground, puts in a full-length dive and plucks the ball inches off the turf. Stunning!
Length outside off, punched to cover
Length on middle and leg, he tips it to short fine leg
Not that short but sits up. Shakib looped it but that works against him, Levitt cleared the front leg and pulled far over midwicket. Middled it despite the turn away.
Shortish length just outside off, he pats it to cover point
That one skidded through. Length on off, 91ks, defended in front.
Nicely done. Short of a length into his body, he stays back and pulls wide of long on. Logan van Beek hares to his left, puts in a big dive but can't rein the ball in
Fullish on leg, backs away and pushes it to cover point
On a length on the stumps, Tanzid pushes to long on
Makes a lot of room very early, Shakib keeps the line at the stumps. The length ball is delivered at 90ks, slapped uppishly and with limited control, goes to long-off
Length on the pads, he nudges it to the right of short fine leg
Cuts the length ball to point
On a length just outside off, he drives but straight to covers
Makes room and Taskin, smartly, offers a bit of width to go away from Levitt's range. Was a length ball on fifth, Levitt shaped to cut but let it go in the end
Fullish in length on off, he digs it back to the bowler

Top edges a cut and the fielder at point takes it. Shortish ball in the early 140ks, Levitt made room again and tried to carve it over the infield. Taskin got good carry and the pace had him hit it high on the bat.
Shortish outside off, he cuts it neatly to the right of that man Engelbrecht, who dives to his right and saves a few runs
Length on middle and leg, worked around the corner
Top drive from Shakib. Overpitched outside off, he drives on the up through covers. Four all the way
Taps it late, almost too much as the ball rolls back. One bounce and goes through the fifth-stump line. Was a length ball he played with an angled bat
Poor line now on the pads of Shakib who clips it nicely to deep fine leg
Goes across for a heave-pull, misses the shortish ball outside off
Short of a length outside off, he mistimes his cut to backward point
Awesome cover drive on the up. Fullish length but not far from length, 140ks, fifth-stump line. O'Dowd stood upright and creamed it through the line and along the ground
Up and over! Not the best of starts from van Beek, Short, wide, he stands up on his toes and cuts it over backward point.
Fullish on fourth, pushed through cover, past the diving fielder
On a length outside off, he pushes to mid-off and sets off. A shy at the stumps from the fielder, who misses and not so great backing up from the fielder allows and extra run
Cross-bat delight, while on the move. Dances down and carves it in front of point
Short and wide again outside off. Not as much bounce though as Shakib unfurls the cut again past backward point and the outfield is a stunner
Length around fourth, defended in front
Length ball down leg, called a wide Fuller in length on middle and leg, Shakib pushes to mid-on

Excellent catch by Tanzim in the follow-through. He delivered the cutter into the pitch and was falling away to the left. O'Dowd made room and tried to flat-bat it as hard as possible but got it high off the bat. The visuals almost looked incongruous as the contact was high up off the bat. So, the pace wasn't at its peak and Tanzim stuck out his hand to the left and took it close to the body

That one flies over short fine leg! A bit of a top edge but Shakib won't mind. Banged in short just on off. He looks for a pull but with fine leg in, that was a safe shot even though it didn't go where he intended it to
Tries to drive on the up and misses. Was a length ball on fifth

19 off that van Beek over and that is a top powerplay for Bangladesh. Length ball outside off, he throws his hands at it, gets it off the outer half of the bat past short third and there is nothing deep point can do
Pulled through midwicket. Engelbrecht happy to go after anything he sees fit despite the early wickets. Shortish ball was at the body and he timed the extension of the hands well.
Aggression straight away! Gentle length ball outside off, he jumps down the track and pummels it past mid-off.
Fullish ball on leg, turned to backward square
Two in two! Back of a length ball on Tanzid's hips. He gets across and pulls to the left of deep backward square leg, where the fielder dives over the ball
Shortish ball around off is pulled to deep midwicket
Oh, after all the Engelbrecht praising, he lets one through his legs. Back of a length ball on his hips, he pulls straight to Engelbrecht, who lets the ball through but recovers fairly well
Length around off, clipped with the closed bat-face, to midwicket
On a length outside off, he pushes towards cover
Stands outside leg and defends the length ball at the stumps. Slightly away from the bounce
Almost a chop-on. On a length on off, he looks to force the ball through the off side, is lucky his stumps aren't rattled
Slog sweep launched over long-on. Vikramjit got onto one knee and smoked the full ball high and far
Shortish in length into his body, he pulls to deep backward square leg
The breeze helps out Vikramjit in clearing the deep-midwicket boundary. Shakib looks in resignation as the batter didn't seem to get all of it on the powerful shot. Still got it 75 metres far
Did he get a tickle on that? Nope. Flatter down leg, he was looking to tickle it fine, misses Cuts it right from the stumps. Was quicker on middle, he gets it to point

Mix-up, should have been a run out but the Fizz misses the direct hit at the non-striker's end. Fielder from midwicket was running to the left, the bowler - to the left of the pitch, three-fourth of the way down - looked for a moment to see if he can throw to someone but decided he didn't have the time. Tried getting it on the bounce but missed. The ball was defended with an angled bat and Vikramjit was three-fourth of the way down and Engelbrecht was hesitant.
Extra lift for Shakib on off stump, he stays back and pushes towards cover
Length just outside off, opens the face and jabs it to point
Keeps it on a length on middle, he shimmies down the track and tips it to the on-side
Low fully on leg is helped to deep-backward square
Keeps it wicket to wicket on middle and leg, worked to the on-side.
Back of length at the hips, 136ks, tries flicking it. Gets an inside edge onto body, ball pops to square leg
Ooh, almost another wicket for Dutt. Was fired just outside off, Shakib looks to cut it fine and is lucky he did not get an edge on that
Length in the channel, defended with the open-faced vertical bat to point. More a back-foot shot
Jumps down the track again, and pushes aerially but away from the outstretched left hand of Dutt
Goes across early and inside the line of the length ball on fourth stump. Clips it leg side
Slower offcutter outside off, was on the fuller side. He drives on the up to deep cover
Vikramjit takes him on right away. Legbreak on a fullish length just outside off gets mauled by a slog sweep, high and far over midwicket
On pace length ball darted in on off and middle stump. He opens the face of the bat towards point and sets off only to be sent back
Nudges the full ball to deep midwicket

He's hit against the wind and perished! The cross-seam ball does the job for van Meekeren and Tanzid has thrown away a good start. Was back of a length into his body. He looks for a pull, does not get a clean connection and deep backward square leg has to come in for a simple catch.
Flatter and fuller, it's on top of middle and Engelbrecht punches it to the bowler's left while backing away
Length ball that kicks off a length and hits Hridoy on the knee. Was bowled at 137kph. Van Meekeren has a chirp

This is a bit too full and Engelbrecht pumps it downtown. They are taking Rishad down. He stood slightly leg side of the ball and swung through the line, bat went well behind the shoulder in follow-through.. Did that hit the cushion directly or on the half-volley. Actually a yorker, very close but it's given four
Almost a similar ball and shot. He looks to flick, gets hit higher on the thigh pad
Full just outside off, pushed with an angled bat to backward point's right
Back of a length ball, he pulls to deep midwicket.

They pinch a two to deep midwicket. Direct hit from the dude running in. At first it looked like Engelbrecht's bat might've been in the air but no, he slid it along the ground with the head in the opposite direction.
On a length outside off, he drives on the up but can't beat cover
Reverse swept with a flamboyant follow-through, is a bit late on it and the ball dribbles through the first-slip area and then to short third. Was a length ball darted just outside off
Fullish in length but on his pads, he clips to deep backward square leg
Length outside off, cut to cover
Fuller in length outside off, he drives to covers.

Mahmudullah foxes Vikramjit in flight. Looked like the batter decided to go down the ground after it was looped up above the eyeline, there was width but also a bit of extra bounce. Bat swung to go over cover but got nothing on it
Slower bouncer around shoulder high, he pulls towards deep backward square leg
Punches the length ball just outside off to cover
Length ball on middle and leg, he gets across and turns it towards deep backward square leg who is a touch in from the boundary
Takes a step to the left to manufacture room. Was a seam-up ball angling in on top of off, sat up enough for Edwards to carve it through cover
On a length on middle and leg, he pushes back to the bowler
Sweeps the full ball to deep-backward square leg
Well, Netherlands will be through if Edwards times em like this. Waited for the length ball on fourth to go behind him and chops it, beats backward point and there's no one behind
Tossed up just outside off, he sweeps to deep square leg
Quick single to the left of mid-off. Was a fullish ball that was punched off the front fot
Low dipping full toss on Hridoy's pads who can't get it away cleanly. Gets it down to deep backward square leg
Shortish ball has been lifted up with a square drive, lands just over the ring and deep point runs to the right to stop it. A combination of a square drive and a cut from Engelbrecht
A touch quicker on a length on off, he works it to deep midwicket
Heavy ball on a length at 145ks, pings off the bat as it's defended back to the bowler
Ooh, there's a bit of purchase for Pringle. Slows it down on a length on off, Hridoy looks for a sweep, misses and gets caught on the pad. Was struck outside off, though
Back of length just outside off, 135ks, caressed off the back foot to deep point's right... and the batters sneak back for two. Agile running
Scythes this one over backward point for a run.
Top of a length just outside off, punched to cover
Dragged down on middle, but Shakib has placed it so well. Stays back, does not try to hit that too hard and pulls almost with a straight bat breaching the gap between deep midwicket and long on
Flatter outside off, he pats to short third
High-release on the legbreak. Looped over the eyeline, 90ks, around the stumps. Edwards makes room and drives straight to cover
Dragged down on off, but Hridoy only pushes to long on
Big risk, no reward for Edwards. Goes square-on and tries to launch the reverse sweep with the spin on the length ball ripping outside off. Doesn't have the pace to work with or the timing
Length on middle and leg stump, he gets across and works behind square
Steals a single by pushing the fullish on off towards point and calling early
Flatter on off stump, he gets across and ticks it with soft hands towards deep midwicket for a couple of runs
Belted over the bowler with a flat bat. Tanzim runs to the left from long-on and dives to save two
Hint of turn and some bounce as well. Was bowled at 97kph on middle and leg as Hridoy works it to square leg

Almost a catch and a run out! Was an overpitched ball that was chipped just over the leaping fielder at cover, seemed to not get a hand on it. Ball was rolling to the deep and Edwards took off for the second. Engelbrecht had just gone out of his end as the threw left the fielder's hand. But the throw was awry. Keeper had to run too far down the pitch, was never a two there but Netherlands get it and evade the run out
On a length on middle, he works it to deep backward square leg. End of Dutt's spell, wonderful figures of 4-0-17-2
Makes room and Rishad goes wider to get it out of his arc. Engelbrecht reaches out for a square slash, the low fully dips and beats bat
Beaten on the cut. It's wide on a length and Edwards looked to go hard and square

Flattens Hridoy's leg stump with a flat, quick ball! That was bowled at 93kph and the ball skids through after pitching. Hridoy gives himself room, probably too much of it, misses the ball and sees his leg pole go splat.
Crouches a bit and effectively sweeps a length ball from top of the pad. Gets it to deep-backward square leg, they thought of two but it's not on
Slower through the air with the line down leg, clipped to the on-side
Slapped down the ground. Cutter on a length, top-of-off, and Engelbrecht stood leg side and munched it with a vertical bat, gets it straight of mid-off
Flatter outside off, Shakib can only push it back to the bowler
Great comeback from Taskin. Yorker at the stumps. Nailed with pace. Jammed out in front
Oh, what a stunning shot from Shakib. Tossed up outside off, he jumps down the track, takes it on the full and screams it all across the carpet to the right of long off

Pulled out of the ground. 92 metres over midwicket, it hits the roof and bounces away like it was a good length ball delivered by a giant. The sound on that was exquisite. Was a back of length ball around off that was smoked while staying upright. New ball to be brought in
Flatter outside off, he slaps it to long-on
Taskin one-ups after a boundary ball again, this time beats bat. Was a well-directed bumper around head-height which Engelbrecht tried to pull
Fuller on the stumps, Mahmudullah digs it back to the bowler
On a length on middle, he works to the on-side
Length around off, beats the sweep. Appeal for lbw not given, impact might've been the issue
Massive swing and a miss! Gentle length ball around leg stump. He jumps down, and looks to deposit that into the sea. Misses and the ball just misses his leg stump
Pulls the length ball between midwicket and long-on well enough to pick up two. Netherlands bring up 100. Just 76ks
On a length on middle and leg, he works it towards deep backward square leg
Spins away to beat the slog sweep. 82ks but this seemed slower. This was full, landed around off and got extra bounce to hit high on the pad
Short of a good length on middle, pushed back to the bowler
Backs away and cuts the length ball from leg stump, to cover
Slower back of a length ball, at 106kph, he gets across and works it towards deep midwicket
Length on leg, backs away again and cuts to long-off
Nails the pull! Banged in short, shoulder-high. Mahmudullah gets inside the line, rolls the wrists and places it so well between deep fine leg and deep square leg
In the aiir... clears cover who was running to the right. Mahmudullah the fielder at cover, Shakib not pleased. They take two again as the throw comes in from long-off.
Sharp length ball on middle and leg, he whisks it past midwicket
Wide ball sits up, Edwards went away and waited for the ball to reach the top of the bounce and cuts it hard through cover. Hridoy is the sweeper running to the right, dives full length to save two
Back of a length ball just outside off, he slaps it to the left of midwicket who does well and does not concede a run
Goes across to fifth stump, gets inside the line of the length ball straightening. Hits it deep into the outfield and well to the left of deep fine leg. One-bounce four
Length outside off, he whips it but can't beat midwicket
Sweeps the full ball around the corner
Sharp bouncer that took off after pitching. Mahmudullah was eyeing a pull, but the ball evades him at pace

Clothed. Tanzim takes the catch despite taking the eyes off in the last second. Was looking into the sunshine, the head went away but after the hands were positioned in front of the face as he was falling down. The ball was basketed and he managed to hold on. Was a full legbreak, tossed up generously, that turned away sharply and Engelbrecht tried to swipe it down the ground. It bounced more than he expected as well, taking the top edge. The leggie has been expensive but ends a handy cameo that was threatening to take Netherlands through
Another quick back of a length ball on off. He gets a leading edge towards backward point and they take a quick run
Full outside off, driven to cover
Length ball on middle, he works it to deep backward square leg. Think about a second, but the fielder came in quickly.

Keeper confident with the stumping. Sent upstairs.. Was a legbreak - full ball that landed around off and spun away to beat the straight drive. Litton took the ball well in front of the body and swept his hands right onto the stumps without letting the momentum take him back. MS Dhoni-esque keeping. De Leede lost balance momentarily, fell forward, took a second or two to pull the foot back but it was too much time
On a length outside off, he takes a couple of steps down and drives to extra cover
Goes across first before getting back. punches it straight
Another play and a miss! Good length ball outside off, he stays leg side of the ball and looks to cut it fine. Makes no connection.
Tossed up outside off, full ball is driven down the ground
Sharp back of a length ball on off, he mistimes his pull to short midwicket

Full on fifth, makes room and tries to cuff it with a semi-horizontal bat. Bowler runs to the right and dives, can't stop it in time. Shakib unhappy, perhaps feels that the non-striker, running back to make his ground, was in the bowler's way. But the worry doesn't carry for long
Banged in short, he follows the batter but the ball is down leg. Should be a wide. Oh, it's not. Shakib is not impressed, has a word with the umpire.
Full on middle and off, worked to long-on.
On a length outside off, he drives to cover and sets off only to be sent back.
Edwards goes for that reverse launch again, the full ball from around the wicket is darted outside off and beats bat
Overpitched, right in Mahmudullah's slot and he has not missed out. Slower offcutter right in his wheelhouse and he whacks this over wide long-on. 200 sixes for Mahmudullah in T20s.
Shakib's towel falls off as he delivers the length ball outside off, Edwards makes room and cuts to deep point

Edwards goes across and is beaten on the sweep. Fizz saw him and went really wide and fullish. Given wide by the ump. Was dicey with the batter's movements but oh well Edwards looks to cut the angle and go across the line but top edges it back onto shoulder and to third. Was a length ball that he tried to heave, got low but couldn't cope with the bounce
Deceives Shakib in the flight as he shimmies down and then has to adjust. Can only work it to the on-side for a run
Back of length, angling across, Pringle goes down and gets beaten as he tries to punch it
Oh, that's beaten everyone. Fuller on leg stump, beats Mahmudullah's attempted whip, and Edwards misses it as well.
Length outside off, angle on it is sharp. Pringle tries to push it towards cover and misses it
Slog-swept over deep midwicket and he juuust clears a leaping Vikramjit. On middle and leg, he does not get all of it, but enough to clear the fielder
Offcutter on a fullish length goes away with the angle, it's just outside off and beats the heave across the line
Tossed up outside off, he jumps down, gives himself room and lofts over extra cover. No fielders deep in there.
Looks for a quick single to cover but doesn't get it. Was a cutter on a fullish length that was patted
Flatter on middle stump, he pushes back to the bowler
Another slower one. This on a back of length, spits up and bamboozles Pringle.
Slower through the air on off, he pushes towards cover
Oh, he misses out on a scoop and gets hit on the helmet grill. Was a back of a length outside off, he shuffles across and can only manage a top edge onto his visor.

Van Beek falls now. Had to take on the leggie, tries going across the line with the slog sweep. But top edges it and Rishad goes back to complete the catch. He used his height to his advantage again, got extra bounce off a length. Wheels coming off for Netherlands
Fifty for Shakib! A welcome return to form for the maestro. Gets to his 13th T20I fifty with a flick to deep midwicket
Excellent ball, beats the edge. Was a length ball that landed around off and spun away sharply. Dutt tried to punch to cover

Picked up, and Engelbrecht has taken another lovely catch. Back of a length back on Mahmudullah's hips. He gets inside the line of it and heaves it but Engelbrecht's is stationed right on the ropes. He leaps and sends Mahmudullah packing.
Rishad is the Fizz now. Beats the slog sweep with a length ball that rags away with spite
Falls in no-man's land. Banged in short, and hurries the batter. The top-edge goes straight up but away from O'Dowd at mid-on
Dutt gets the pull away somehow. Clears the deep-midwicket fence. Ball on the shorter side of length, 93ks, it was rising steeply again but not at pace
Good length ball outside off, he gets across and was looking to held it over short fine leg. Does not get a decent connection though
Bravery meets skill as Rishad tosses up outside off, turns it away sharply to beat the slash aimed over cover
Back of a length ball that does not get up enough. Hits him high on the pad as the ball rolls to deep fine leg
Full and wide, slapped to long-off
Length ball outside off, he heaves it to deep midwicket. Jaker wanted two, but is sent back by Shakib
Length ball angles away outside off, Dutt hops for the cover drive but has to collapse due to the lack of bounce. Doesn't make contact
Fuller on the stumps, he backs away but is cramped for room. Can't get past mid-off though
Full, slow and around off, Dutt clears cover with a miscued lofted drive. Manages to get it halfway into the outfield for two
Crrrrrrunched! Low full toss outside off. He stays legside of the ball and absolutely belts this past mid-off
Into the pitch, at the thigh, beats the pull and the ball deflects towards cover point
Big swing and a miss! Slower fuller ball well outside off, he almost swings himself off his feet
Slow on a length, angle away is sharp again. Beats the bat swing again. Lands around off and finishes around sixth stump, Pringle's arc was horizontal almost
Banged in short and that's such a clean connection. The line was well outside off. He fetches it, feet off the ground and places it so well to the right of deep midwicket
Does him again with the angle. Offcutter is cupped out the hands with max revs from Fizz, this is fuller and beats another heave
Four more to end the over, and Bangladesh are going big. Slower low full toss well outside. He throws the kitchen sink at it, gets a thick outside edge just past Edwards' right

Pringle has been bamboozled about eight times in his stay so far, can't lay bat on ball. It's because Fizz and co have used the pitch and the slower variation to full effect. Beats another heave with a fullish ball. Keeper didn't collect it and in fact, ball went to short third. Pringle was sent back after looking for the run
Slower length ball well outside off. He lofts it to the right of deep cover for a couple of runs
There it is. Dot to make it 33 off 5. Slower bouncer outside off beats the pull
Slower back of a length ball outside off, he looks for the pull but is deceived by the pace of it.
Hugs among the fans as the slower bouncer is pulled from just outside off to deep square leg
Oh, lucky runs but they all count. Slower fuller ball well outside off. Shakib looks to go through covers, gets a thick outside past a leaping Edwards
Backs away and cuts the length ball to cover
Slower short of a length ball well outside off again. He gets well across, and pulls it over short fine leg

On-pace bouncer finds the edge but the ball sails behind the keeper for a one-bounce four. Dutt went full-throttle with the pull, swivelled after hitting it off the top edge, and Taskin yelled in frustration
Nails his yorker on middle. He jams it back to the bowler
Close to a yorker. Tad behind the mark, Dutt can't get under it though. Jammed to long-on
Fuller in length on middle and leg, he gets across and flicks to the right of deep backward square leg. Gets back for two or does he? Yes, he does. Shakib ends on 64 off 46 and Bangladesh reach 159.

Slower one ends Pringle's misery as well as the game. Leg stump has been floored. Was a fullish length that angled back in. Pringle lunged far forward and tried to heave over midwicket. Missed it and there are big smiles among Shanto, Shakib et al
full and launched! I think England are going for it... Salt opens the shoulders and drills his first ball over the extra cover rope
Short, skidding on and bouncing - Athavale goes to pull and ends up edging into his gut. Gets a run into square leg as Oman get going
pitched up and clattered for six more! Pace off from Bilal, too full and room to swing the arms again. Salt obliges, dumping the ball over the covers again. He's getting 'em in sixes...
Fuller, swinging in, played out with bat jammed firmly next to bad by the right-hander

much better length, flattens off stump! Salt's stay is brief, six-six-out. But that part of the ledger doesn't matter for England's pursuit of a healthy NRR bump. Skidding on from over the wicket as Salt swings across the line, gets a thin inside edge that takes the ball smack into the top of off
Quicker, also nipping in but starts on a straighter line and ends up in the hip of Prajapati
...and defends his first ball! What's this nonsense? It was a good length, 127kph on off stump, very respectable, to be fair
Not as much movement, good carry thought, defended on the hop towards backward point
touch shorter on the pads, worked out to deep midwicket for one
Straighter, still length, dropped into the leg side
full with pace off, Buttler clips off his toes through square leg
Short enough to pull, but no real timing as midwicket scooches low to gather. Solid start
Starts with a wide down the leg side On the charge! Great intent, skipping down, throwing hands through the ball and getting it through extra cover
back of a length, Buttler pokes at it and gets an inside edge for one

Ah well... Archer hits a length - hard - and Athavale mistimes a slap straight to cover, who has to get low to gather. There's a momentary query over whether it carried but the umpires are more than satisfied

driven crisply down the ground! Jacks steps into an on-the-up thrash past mid-off, in the air but safe. And Kaleemullah overstepped, too goes full, Jacks swipes without moving his feet. Thick edged to short fine leg and there's no extra damage
Oooooof rapid bouncer, swished at by the skipper, taken above the head by Buttler!
length ball, hint of away swing, Jacks shuffles forward and looks to cart him down the ground... misses
Bit of width, into the pitch and cut expertly through backward point! Uses the pace, waits for the ball to come on, goes through with the shot. Tidy
banged into the pitch outside off, 127kph/78mph and Jacks throws the hands, beaten past the top edge
Fuller, Aqib goes for the drive and ends up getting a single into square leg as the ball nips in off the pitch

short and skied to point! England have come out in a frenzy of shot-making, and Oman bag another. Good bounce from Kaleemullah, the ball got big on Jacks as he looked to swat over the off side, only managed a big top edge to the man in the ring
Fullest of the lot, in with the arm, defended into cover point
short and boshed! Pace off, I think, but Bairstow lumps it unceremoniously over cover point
steps down and hammers through mid-off! Beats the man on the edge of the circle to his left and it races away
Pace off? Looked it. Certainly held back and holds up in the pitch, defended into the off side
low full toss, 127kph/78mph wide of off, Buttler slams it straight to cover
Sharper, hits the splice of the bat as Aqib thinks about a tip and run at his toes
short ball, sits up nicely, spanked behind square! Buttler sits back and eases away his second boundary
Almost yorker length, dug out beyond cover and a run is scampered
slot ball, pace off, dumped through long-on! No timing whatsover on Buttler's flail across the line but still it sails away to the rope, just short of six
Scoop attempt! Prajapati moves across, outside off stump, and tries to get a full ball over the top but ends up nutmegging himself to fine leg, who is up in the circle
banged in and blapped! Buttler goes up and over, with the wind out towards the longer boundary at deep midwicket. An 89m six, brings the target in sight
Driven out to mid off
full, wide and slashed up and over, but bounces some way short of the cover boundary. So this chase is going to a fourth over!

Oooooo that's a hell of a shot... only one for it, but Aqib gets down on one knee to sweep Topley over to deep square leg, where there is a fielder lurking. Bit more timing and that's a boundary into a very exposed region
short and swung away for the winning runs! Bairstow finishes with a strike rate of 400, England have got the job done in record time - and the World Cup defence is back on!
Bit of a leg cutter, into the top of off, dropped well in front of point for a well-taken single

Another attempted scoop, this one the worst of the lot. The length and line are right, but Prajapati ends up wearing it on the pads, away to fine leg. A muted appeal for LBW but he got well outside the line there

Another sharp grab low! Or is it? Archer is cut to Jacks at backward point who claims the catch but the umpires want to have a look at this... "Fingers are clearly underneath the ball," says the umpire.
Archer around the wicket to the left-hander, into a length, pulled but poorly timed, gathered by midwicket
Shelled at first slip! Full, late movement, booming drive, straight to Moeen Ali, who can't claim. Really, really bad drop
Leg cutter, leaps off the surface and raps the glove of Zeeshan as he tries to pull down to fine leg
Corker! Full of a length, angling in, nipping away, beyond the right-hander's outside edge
Wide, driven not all that convincingly but beat a weak hand from Jacks and allows two
Bunted in the air towards midwicket... but just out of Jofra Archer's reach, who have to move to his left to field
Short, doesn't get up all that much, and cut tamely to Jacks

Wowzer! It's a length delivery going across the right-hander who drives and lets his arms go to lift it high and away for six over backward point! It's a 54m hit that side. Expect to see that in play for the rest of the afternoon...
Full, straight, dug out
That's not a bad way to start... Around the wicket, sharp and full of a length, squaring the batter up enough to offer a leading edge back to the bowler
Wide of the crease, into the top of the stumps. Kail's feet were very leg-side there...
Bit of width, Kail has a hack and top edges over the cordon, to Topley on the bounce at deep third
Snorter! Sharp - 91mph - leaping off a length, almost taking the glove with it through to Jos Buttler
Angling into the pads, chipped in the air but short of midwicket
Too quick! Length into the batter, Prajpati swishes a pull more in hope than expectation, clothing in the air to Livingstone at midwicket.

Big leggie, big sweep - misses completely. Buttler goes way out wide to gather and comes back to remove the bails at the second attempt... and Kail's foot is in the air! Great work from the England skipper - even if he did botch the first go - but terrible game awareness from the batter!
Flight into middle and leg, conventional leggie, defended back down the pitch
Out the front of the hand... and wide. Close to the line but the right call Leggie off a length, Shoaib prods at it to point
Beats the edge! Loops, grips, spins sharp, Shoaib no chance
Good intent, and well executed! Didn't try and overhit a ball that sits up nicely off the pitch, but good footwork gets Shoaib back and in a great position to lace through point
Yowser! Another edge-beater, probably the best delivery of the over from Rashid. Could have trimmed the off bail
Full, into off stump late, just about kept out
Dug up, rapid, ducks under it early
Again into the left-hander, this one nipping away and beating the retreating batter, passing over the top of off stump!
Nicely played, bit of a wristy flourish to a length ball on a fourth-stump line, beats the man at gully
Jumps wider, angled into the stumps, lovely-looking straight drive to wide mid on
