Dragged on! And that's Mark Wood's 50th T20I wicket! Pace does it again, over the wicket to the leftie, who tries to use the pace across him to find something down to third. Alas, finds himself walking back to the hutch
Hack across the line from Shoaib... and it goes absolutely nowhere after he loses his shape to a tempter and scuffs in front of himself
Punched down to long on
Top-spinner? Maybe. Either way, left alone outside off stump
Moeen holds this one! Big leg spinner, drifting onto a full length just outside off, enticing the drive and finding the edge to a wide first slip.
Full, on middle stump, defended out to cover
Driven on the up... but beyond cover - Will Jacks - who didn't pick that up, actually. Archer runs around from long off to tidy up
Attacks the stumps, well-defended by Shoaib who gets right behind the delivery
Full, outside off, defended into the covers. Thinks about a single, almost sells himself down the river, but is able to abort in time
Defended well once more from Shoaib as Archer goes full and at him
Stings the glove! Archer drags his length back, gets one to lift and bite the bottom hand of Shoaib, who immediately takes his hand off the bat and gives it a shake. Ok to continue
Length outside off, stands tall, defends out to point
Loops up off a length, Shoaib can't resist having a little swipe at it. Archer thinks there was a nick, but no one else does. And that's drinks!
Full, on off stump, bit of turned but defended into the off side
Beats the edge - drift in, good turn, past the full face of Butt's bat
Sharp side spin... but too much spin and wided as Fayyaz reaches out for a sweep Out the side of the hand, skidding on, defended back down the pitch
Googly pins the batter in front... totally misread but it's spun a bit too much that it would probably have slid down leg. No review taken
Got him this time! Googly again, this one wider, fuller - perfectly pitched, really - and scuttles through a very loose push from Fayyaz to light up the stumps
Full, dug into the ground by Kaleemullah who aborts a drive mid-shot
Chipped away through midwicket, just out of the reach of the fielder! Scamper a much needed two
Shoaib on the hop, playing this down off his toes and away for a singlein front of square leg
Carved down the ground! Front leg moves out the way, flat-bat shot hacks a precious boundary back past the bowler! Have that!
Tries to repeat the shot... but Wood puts a little extra behind this and pulls back the length.
Top edge... but no boundary as Topley gets across from deep third to save three
Length into the hip, worked behind square. Decent over for Oman, all told. And Shoaib Khan becomes the first Oman batter to reach double figures this afternoon...

Another big turning delivery... and another wide from Adil Rashid as the leggie is the wrong side of the off side line Stunted appeal as another big leggie traps Shoaib in front. Too big, mind, squaring the batter up but turning down off stump
Left outside off stump
Defended back to the bowler
Short, allows Shoaib to rock back and work to backward square leg. They think about two, but they'll have to settle for one as Bairstow comes around to field
The googly has another victim! Outside off, asking the right-hander to come forward, then turning him inside out.

One-handed sweep... on the bounce to Liam Livingstone out at deep square leg. For a moment, it looked like Adil Rashid might become the second Englishman to take a T20i five-for after Sam Curran. He'll have to settle for four...
Full - full toss, in fact, worked out to deep midwicket. But Shoaib doesn't want the single.

That's all she wrote! Short ball gets big on Shoaib as he tries to step across and manufacture something into the leg side. The ball balloons in the air towards fine leg where Buttler tracks well and take the catch. Clinical stuff from England.
back of a length outside off. Gurbaz advances and then watches the ball go through to the keeper
very full just outside off. Shapes back in and Ura digs it out towards extra cover. Ura wanted the single but his captain sent him back
back of a length outside off. Gurbaz hangs back and stabs it into the off side to get off the mark
full and swinging into the pads. Ura stabs at it and squirts it off the inside half of the bat towards fine leg. Off the mark with a brace

full and speared down leg. Ibrahim does not get bat on it and the umpire has no qualms in calling it a wide length delivery way outside off this time. Swings away further and some more exercise for Alex Wharf beauty! Length outside off. Shapes away beautifully and draws Ibrahim into a poke. Beaten all ends up
length just outside off. This does not swing back in and Ura is happy to let it go. Does not carry through to Gurbaz, though
back of a length just outside off. Ibrahim takes a step down the track before punching it towards short extra cover, who sprawls to his right and stops it
length on middle and off. A hint of curve back into Ura and he defends off the front foot

oh dear, that is the last thing PNG need! This is almost comical! Back of a length on middle and leg. Nips back into Ibrahim and raps him on the thigh pad.  Rolls away towards point, who fires a throw at the bowler's end. No one backing up that throw and Afghanistan initially get three over-throws. That throw is then also fumbled by the keeper and despite four fielders, apart from the keeper being in the vicinity, it rolls away for another run
back of a length on middle and leg. Ura lets the ball come to him before meeting it right under his eyes
hung up outside off. Gurbaz lets it go
full and wide outside off. Ura plants his front foot and drives it neatly towards deep backward point
Ura welcomes Nabi with a boundary! Short outside off. Drifts away from Ura and that gives him the room he desires. Hangs back in his crease and cracks it through point!

big and long appeal, and given! Full delivery that curves in late and raps Ibrahim on the pad. He fell over a little and that caused him to miss the line of the ball. Kamea gives his vocal chords a proper run-out and the umpire eventually agrees. Ibrahim, though, reviews. Did this pitch in line? Was this doing too much? No bat involved but the ball pitched just outside leg. Ibrahim survives!

slower on a length outside off. Grips in the surface and spins back in. Pings Ura high on the bat and trickles away into the on side. He scrambles across for the single and would have been out with a direct hit at the bowler's end
shortish outside off. Comes off slower than Ibrahim expects and his back-foot punch only meets fresh air
length on middle and off. Vala drops it into the off side and calls his partner through
full on the pads. Ibrahim comes forward and flicks it to mid on

full on middle and leg. Ura is a little late in jamming his bat down and the ball rolls away off the inside edge towards short fine leg. A bit of hesitation initially but the single is completed in the end

hot knife through butter! Hard length on middle stump. Shapes back in a smidgen and that does the trick for Kamea. Ibrahim walks down the track, looking to mow it over cow corner. Misses it completely and his middle stump is pegged back. First time Afghanistan's opening stand has not gotten more than 100 this T20 World Cup, and this is just what PNG would have hoped for!

back of a length outside off. Vala stands tall and punches it past cover point. PNG decide late that they want the third and Vala looks like he has made it comfortably enough. But hang on...hang on...He did not drag his bat and when the ball hits the stumps at the bowler's end, his bat is actually in the air. Not the greatest bit of running, and PNG lose their skipper early in the piece! Good work by Gurbaz too. He collected the throw from the deep and then rifled it into the stumps at the other end!
back of a length on middle and leg. Naib stays back and tucks it off his hips towards deep square leg
floated up full just outside off. Ura looks to go downtown but ends up shanking it towards short mid wicket
gets it away! Length ball on the pads and that is easy pickings for Gurbaz. Glances it a little uppishly but well past the fielder at short fine leg!
full toss on the pads. Naib works it away towards deep square leg and picks up two

edged and taken beautifully by Gurbaz! Length in the channel just outside off. Does not swing back in, instead going on with the angle. Siaka nibbles at it and the ball hurtles off the outside edge, almost off the shoulder of the bat. Gurbaz flies to his right and shows excellent athleticism to snare the chance with two hands. Afghanistan have their second in the powerplay!
fullish on middle and off. Naib comes forward and flicks it towards deep square leg

proper peach, and Farooqi has two in two! Length in the channel and this decks back sharply after pitching. Bau has to play at it and can do nothing as the ball grazes the inside edge. Gurbaz flies to his right again and snaffles up another smart chance!

Gurbaz goes big! Full outside off. Gurbaz has had enough of the pushing and prodding and dances down. Has a mighty swing at it and while he does not middle it, he manages to muscle it over the deep mid wicket fence!
back of a length delivery angled into middle and leg. Hiri, having advanced, is late on the flick and the ball races away off his thigh pad. Beats the keeper and fine leg
hard length, angling into middle and off. Gurbaz, having advanced, defends into the off side
length ball that starts outside off and boomerangs back in. Hiri goes for the booming drive and cloths it into the point region

timmmbbeeerrrrrr! And it is the big wicket - the one PNG would have really wanted. On a length on off, nipping back in with the angle. Gurbaz hares down the track and has an agricultural swipe across the line. Misses the ball by a mile and hears the death rattle soon after. The intent was right but the shot and the execution went awfully awry. PNG have another in the powerplay!
back of a length just outside off. Bounces extra and Ura does well to fend it into the ground
full and wide outside off. Swings away beyond the tramlines and Nao will have to reload very full just outside off. Omarzai comes forward and defends
yorker swinging into off stump. Ura picks it just in time and defends

and Naveen among the wickets straightaway! Length outside off. Comes back in with Naveen's natural angle and Hiri, like he did last over, tries the expansive square drive. The inward movement does not make that stroke feasible and all he does is chop it back onto his stumps. PNG four down now, and in a lot of trouble!
shortish outside off. Naib goes deep into his crease and scuffs it towards backward point
full and angled into the batter just outside off. Soper comes forward tentatively and pokes it into safety
length delivery sprayed down leg. Easy decision for the umpire back of a length just outside off. Naib goes back and across before running it down to third man

back of a length delivery well outside off. This went the other way but was too wide to be troubling the batter. Some exercise for the umpire full outside off. Shapes away a shade and Soper, hanging back in his crease, prods it towards backward point
in-swinging yorker on middle and leg. Omarzai spots it just in time and jams it off the inside edge into his pads
full and slanting into off stump. Soper gets a much more confident stride in and defends

short and well outside off. Some more exercise for the umpire. That is the tenth run PNG have given up as extras low full toss outside off. Omarzai drives it to mid off and ambles across to the other end
back of a length just outside off. Soper gets squared up but manages to tap it towards backward point
back of a length just outside off. Naib goes back and defends
back of a length outside off. Leaves the batter late and Soper, feeling for it, is beaten on the outside
shot! Leg-stump half-volley and Naib climbs into it. Gets his hands through the ball and with a straight bat, creams it past mid wicket!
length on leg stump. Sticks in the surface and Omarzai closes his bat face too early. Pops up off the leading edge into the off side

oh dear! Wayward delivery bowled a mile outside leg. Gurbaz can get nowhere near it and PNG get five extras. They will not mind it. Not one bit! back of a length delivery that starts outside off and cuts back in sharply. Ura is beaten by the inward movement and gets pinged on the back thigh
fullish, angling into middle and leg. Omarzai comes half forward and stabs it towards cover
angled in on a back of a length on leg stump. Ura is late on the stroke and the ball rolls away off the pads into the square leg region
fuller on the pads. Omarzai comes forward and nudges it enough to mid on's right for a single
full just outside off. Soper reaches out for it and shanks it down the ground towards mid on
length on off. Keeps a tad low and Naib chalks it off the toe-end towards the bowler
length on middle and off. Soper presses forward and pats it towards point for a sharpish single
short and wide outside off. Naib shapes for the pull and hacks it towards mid on. That came off the bottom of the bat too
shortish on the pads. Ura uses the pace and helps it down to fine leg for a couple of runs. Might have come off the thigh pad actually

dropped, oh my! Back of a length outside off. Nabi goes fishing at it away from his body and gets a healthy outside edge. Doriga gets both hands to it behind the stumps but cannot make it stick, despite having multiple attempts at it
back of a length on off. Ura tips it towards cover point and saunters across to the other end
full just outside off. Omarzai comes forward and drives it towards deep cover point

ouch! Back of a length just outside off. Ura tries to drop and run to point. His partner responds to the call but as Ura tries to make his ground, he wears a blow on the calf. Ibrahim with the throw but no real indication that Ura changed his line of running to get in the way
back of a length on off. Naib gets behind the line and pats it gently towards mid wicket
banged into the track outside off. Soper looks for the upper-cut but fails to make any contact
safe! Fortune favouring Naib! Back of a length on middle and off. Naib has a swish across the line and the ball spoons up off the top edge. Luckily for Naib, it just evades short third running back
off-pace on a length on middle and leg. Soper nudges it into the square leg region and picks up a single
shot! In the slot outside off and Naib does not miss out. Springs forward and cracks it to mid off's right. That was in the air but the fielder was nowhere near it!

knocks him over with a jaffa! Full on off and this seems destined to come in with the angle. Until....it pitches and holds its line a smidgen. Ura is caught on the crease and pokes at it in hope but the slight movement takes it past the outside edge, before cannoning into the stumps. Fifth powerplay wicket for Afghanistan, and they are well in the ascendancy!
length just outside off. Naib lunges forward and defends
back of a length delivery pushed into middle and leg. Doriga plays all around it and the ball pops up off the pads into the on side
length outside off. Naib presses half forward and pushes it towards short extra cover
fuller, slanting into middle and leg. Doriga presses half forward and pats it towards mid on
back of a length just outside off. Keeps low and squirms under Omarzai's attempted jab
leg-spinner on a length just outside off. Soper comes forward and defends
back of a length outside off. Omarzai gets on top of the bounce and guides it neatly past backward point for a brace
fizzed through on a length outside off. Grips in the surface and spins away, breezing past the outside edge
full on off. Driven down the ground to mid off

more extras! Goes for the googly but slips it down leg. Gurbaz cannot get around to it and Noor cannot pull it back into play either googly on a length outside off. Much better line and this spins back just enough to sneak past the inside edge of Soper's dab
back of a length outside off. Omarzai stands up on his toes and punches it towards deep cover point
back of a length just outside off. Soper stays back and defends
power! Marginally short outside off. Naib picks the length early, transfers his weight onto the back foot and belts it past mid wicket!
another wrong'un on leg stump. Soper does not get bat on it but the ball did brush the pad on its way through to Gurbaz
oh! Length outside off. Naib skips down the track and aims for the moon. The bat and the ball end up in different postcodes, though
back of a length on leg stump. Soper reads the googly off the pitch and tucks it away for a single
short outside off. Omarzai hops back and cuts it towards deep cover point
leg-spinner on a length on middle and off. Spins back and bounces a touch extra. Soper squirts it off the inside edge towards short fine leg
back of a length on off. Naib knocks it down the ground to long on
fuller on leg stump. Seems another leg-spinner and this goes past the inside edge of Doriga's bat. Strikes him on the pads but that was going down leg
four more! Shortish outside off. Omarzai sits back in his crease and flashes hard at it, slashing it past backward point!
very full just outside off. Doriga looks for the sweep and misses. The ball trickles off his back leg behind square on the leg side
floated up full on middle and off. Omarzai lunges forward and smothers it
length on leg stump. Pitches and skids on, hurrying Soper and beating him for pace. Pings the pads but this might have pitched just outside leg
back of a length on middle and leg. Omarzai works it towards deep mid wicket
fuller outside leg. Soper advances and digs it out towards deep mid wicket
back of a length outside off. A bit of hold in the surface and Naib plonks it towards short extra cover
floated up full outside off. Doriga lunges forward and smothers it
length just outside off. Omarzai comes half forward and defends
length on leg stump. Soper stays back and turns it into the on side
back of a length outside off. Jabbed out to deep cover point
flighted up very full just outside off. Dogra stabs it off the inside half of the bat towards deep backward square leg and scurries back for the second
full on middle and off. Naib has a huge yahoo across the line and squirts it away off the toe-end towards third man
length on middle and leg. Doriga tucks it off his pads towards mid wicket

castled! Fullish, slanting into middle and leg. Does not get up as much as Omarzai expects and the ball sneaks under his bat. In fact, on second look, that kept exceptionally low, barely getting up off the turf. Hits almost the base of leg stump, and Afghanistan lose their third!
full just outside off. Soper clears his front leg and tries to smash it into the ocean. Only connects with fresh air
full outside off. Naib pushes at it and chunks it off the inside half of the bat towards short mid wicket
googly on a length on middle and off. Soper dangles his bat and the ball squirts away off the inside edge behind square on the leg side
length just outside off. Nabi wants to drop and run but Naib says no. The fielder, sensing a run-out opportunity, shies at the batter's end and concedes an overthrow
back of a length on off. Soper drops it into the off side and hares across to the other end to retain strike
full just outside off. Soper has a swish across the line and sees the ball squirm under his bat
fullish outside off. Nabi comes forward and taps it into the off side
length on middle and off. Soper reads it off the pitch and meets it right under his eyes
full on middle and off. Nabi flicks it towards mid on and saunters across to the other end
full on leg stump. Soper takes a step down the track before defending
full outside off. Naib throws his hands at it and slices it on the bounce to deep cover point

that is catastrophic running between the wickets! Googly on a full length on middle and leg. Soper squeezes it out to the bowler's right. He takes a couple of steps down the track and his partner thinks Soper wants the single. Doriga ends up running past Soper, who has to watch in horror as Noor, who chased after the ball initially, relays it to Rashid at the bowler's end. Bails whipped off, Soper a mile short and PNG six down!
back of a length outside off. Naib fiddles at it away from his body and sees the ball sneak past the outside edge
short outside off. Doriga gets onto the back foot and punches it enough to deep cover point's right for a brace
back of a length on off. Nabi dangles his bat tentatively and jams it off the inside edge into his pads
googly on a full length outside off. Doriga stretches forward and pokes it towards backward point
very full on off. Nabi digs it to towards mid off and calls for the single immediately. Makes it comfortably
length delivery outside off that shapes away nicely. Vanua lets it go
back of a length outside off. Nabi nudges it towards extra cover and Naib responds to the call of the single
back of a length just outside off. Vanua gets up on his toes and defends
back of a length on off. Naib stays back and knocks it to long on
back of a length just outside off. Vanua gets up on his toes and defends
full on middle and leg. Nabi plants his front foot and chips it over mid on for a couple of runs
banged into the track on middle and leg. Vanua ducks under it
fuller on the pads. Nabi works it away past mid wicket. The sweeper running around from deep square leg misfields and concedes the second
back of a length outside off. More movement away from Vanua and he is beaten on the outside as he goes wafting at it

appeal! Low full toss that tails into leg stump. Nabi plays all over it and gets rapped on the pads. That seemed to be heading down, but PNG want to have a look nevertheless. Not just heading down, it might have hit Nabi outside the line too. No bat involved but as expected, the impact was outside leg!
beauty! Back of a length in the fifth stump channel. Zips off the surface and nips away, breezing past the outside edge of Vanua's bat. Maiden to start off for Omarzai
length delivery angled into off stump. Nabi stretches forward and blocks
full on leg stump. Naib comes forward and eases it to long on
length delivery hung outside off. Doriga goes fishing at it and is beaten
angled into the pads. Nabi does not get bat on it and the ball trickles off the thigh pad past the keeper
back of a length outside off. Doriga skips down the track and has a massive swish at it. Makes no contact whatsoever
now!
fuller, angling into middle and off. Doriga comes forward and pushes it to mid on
shortish outside off. Sticks in the surface and Naib hacks it to long on
back of a length on middle and off. Sticks in the surface a little and Doriga plonks it off the leading edge towards mid off
slowed up on a length on middle and off. Bounces more than Nabi anticipations and hits him on the glove
safe! Banged in short outside off. Doriga advances and swings himself off his feet (almost). Scuffs it but luckily for him, he manages to clear Nabi at extra cover
darted in on a back of a length on leg stump. Nabi pops it off the leading edge towards the bowler. On the bounce, though
back of a length outside off. Doriga charges down the track and swings like a rusty gate. Gets nowhere close to the ball

has Vanua been run out?! Back of a length on middle and leg. Vanua bunts it to mid on and seems to call for the single. Always looked touch-and-go, from the moment he called for it. Rashid is on his toes, swoops in and hits the stumps at the bowler's end. All eyes now on whether Vanua has made his ground. He seemed favourite to do so but his bat got stuck in the turf a centimetre outside the line. That is really unfortunate, but that is also the third run-out in this innings for PNG!
make that 24 needed off 47! Dug into the track on off stump. Sits up nicely for Naib and he rolls his wrists to pull it past deep square leg!
back of a length outside off. Doriga uses the pace and runs it down to third man
fullish just outside off. Naib walks down the track and flicks it towards deep square leg
hard length, slanting into leg stump. Nao is late on the stroke and the ball thuds into his thigh pad
length ball on the pads. Nabi glances it away towards fine leg
vital boundary! Omarzai strays onto the pads and pays the price. Nao uses the angle and just tickles it fine past the keeper!
into the blockhole outside off. Naib, in trying to dig it out, chunks it back into his pads
length in the channel just outside off. Nao has a flat-footed poke at it and is beaten all ends up
length just outside off. Naib pushes it towards mid off and dashes across to the other end
back of a length just outside off. Nao has a wild swipe across the line and is lucky to not lose his off stump
hard length on middle and off. Nabi shapes for the pull but ends up clothing it towards deep square leg
lovely! Tossed up outside off and this is into Nabi's hitting arc. He stretches forward to get close enough to the ball and caresses it over extra cover!

full and way outside off. Beyond the tramlines and called a wide four more! Back of a length on leg stump. Doriga does not get bat on it but the ball slides off the thigh pad, racing away past the diving Gurbaz!
floated up fuller on off. Nabi comes forward and pokes it towards extra cover
back of a length on off. Doriga nudges it into the mid wicket region. He seemed to call for two initially but then decided against it. Last thing PNG need is another run-out
given plenty of air on a very full length outside off. Nabi squeezes it out to deep cover point
fullish on middle and off. Nao comes forward and blocks
short and wide outside off. Naib chops it towards deep cover point
full just outside off. Nao throws his hands at it and edges it down to third man
full on middle and off. Nabi stabs it back to the bowler
slow and short on the body. Doriga advances and swings it away towards fine leg
into the blockhole outside off. Nabi chalks it back to the bowler
shot! Length on middle and off. Nao gets his front foot out of the way and razes it back past the bowler for four!
that is right out of the screws! Half-tracker outside off and Naib pounces. Opens up his front hip and whacks it over the deep mid wicket fence!
a big swipe and it falls safe! Given a bit of air on a length on middle and off. Doriga gets down on one knee and plays it uppishly. Well short of both deep mid wicket and deep square leg
full outside off. Naib comes forward and chips it over mid on for a couple of runs
googly on a back of a length on the stumps. Doriga knocks it to long on
full on middle and off. Nabi gets onto the front foot and flicks it enough to long on's right to pick up two
fizzed through on a length just outside off. Nao tries his luck with the slog sweep this time but fails to make contact. Not far away from off stump either
length outside off. Naib marches down the track and punches it past extra cover
googly on a length on off. Nao opens up his stance and slugs it to long on
low full toss on middle and leg. Nabi taps it towards short mid wicket, who misfields and ends up conceding a single
four more! Tossed up into the slot outside off. Doriga gets his front foot out of the way and slams it past long on!

that rolls along the ground! Slower ball on a length outside off. Naib advances and has a huge mow at it. Misses it by a distance because the ball barely gets up. The keeper then has a wild shy at the stumps and misses, giving up an overthrow in the process
length just outside off. Doriga stays back and jabs it towards backward point

Naib finishes it off in style, and Afghanistan are into the Super Eight! New Zealand, on the other hand, have been knocked out! Into Naib's hitting arc and he does not miss out on the chance to seal it with a six. Goes through the line and pumps it over the bowler's head. A seven-wicket win to further assert their dominance and Afghanistan have been full value for this win!
flighted up full on the pads. Looks like a leg-spinner and it spins past the inside edge. Trickles away off the leg towards short fine leg
googly on a back of a length outside off. Keeps a little low and left alone by Nao
full on leg stump. Nao plays it back to the bowler

googly tossed up full outside off. Nao looks to go downtown but does not seem to pick the variation. Swings at it and misses as the ball turns past the outside edge. Gurbaz takes off the bails and enquires for the stumping, and like it happens in most cases, we go upstairs to check. A part of his back foot is grounded behind the crease, and Nao stays!
full on leg stump. Nao plants his front foot and drives it down the ground to long on
googly on a length outside off. Doriga drops it into the off side and canters across to the other end
fullish on middle and leg. Doriga gets down on one knee and drags it towards deep square leg
length on middle and leg. Nao has a massive swing at it but only gets it as far as the edge of the circle. Long on mops up
googly on a back of a length on middle and leg. Spins back into Doriga and cuts him in half, rapping him on the pads
fuller on middle and leg. Doriga heaves it away towards deep square leg
another wrong'un on a back of a length on middle and leg. Nao has an ungainly mow at it and misses. The ball trikes him on the back leg
back of a length outside off. Nao tugs it back towards the bowler
shortish outside off. Doriga goes back and jabs it enough past extra cover

dropped, oh dear! Dangles the carrot outside off. Nao cannot resist the temptation and hares down the track. Slices across the googly too much and the ball skews towards Naib at short third, who makes a hash of it
shot! In the slot on the stumps. Doriga marches down the track and smacks it over mid wicket for four!
googly on a length outside off. Doriga goes feeling for it and is beaten all ends up

trapped in front, and the finger goes up! Beautifully-disguised googly that pitches on a length on middle stump. Doriga plays for the ball coming in but when it decks away, he is squared up completely. Plays down the wrong line and gets pinned on the back leg. Doriga does not even bother with the review, and that sums up how plumb it was. A useful knock, though, and PNG, courtesy of it, are within reach of a 100-plus score!

fires this googly well down leg. Gurbaz cannot gather but short fine leg is on hand to cut it off. Just a solitary extra back of a length outside off. Kariko thinks about playing at it initially before letting it go
off-pace on a back of a length just outside off. Nao has a nibble at it and is beaten by the lack of pace

holes out to long on! Hard length on middle and off. Seems to hold in the surface a shade and that meddles with Nao's timing, who is looking to swat this over long on. Clinks it off the toe-end and Rashid runs in, completing the catch well inside the fence!
dug in short on off. Kamea stays leg side of the ball and fends it down to third man
angled in on a length on leg stump. Kariko comes half forward and defends
fired in very full, following the batter outside leg. Kariko digs it out towards mid off
what timing! Hard length on middle and leg. Kariko gives himself room, opens his bat face and uses the pace to steer it beautifully past backward point!
cutter on a length just outside off. Grips in the surface and deviates away, which takes it past the outside edge of Kamea's bat
full and darted into leg stump. Kamea marches down the track and slogs at it, squirting it off the inside edge towards fine leg
length delivery that slides just down leg. Kariko, having moved across his stumps, looked for the lap but missed
this is slower and perhaps a touch fuller on leg stump. Kariko goes for the scoop again but does not make contact. Possibly a little early into the stroke

a run-out to end the innings?! Follows the batter way outside leg. Kariko, because he has no other option, swings wildly at it and misses. Kamea calls him through for a bye. That never looked in the offing and Kamea is caught short of his ground as Gurbaz throws down the stumps. That sums up PNG's innings. They finish with 95 and with four run-outs!
Fired in full around middle, Bhurtel digs it out towards mid-on
good length outside off to start, 132kph. Some nice shape away from the right-handed Hendricks. Left alone
Full outside off, 140kph, swinging into the right hander and Bhurtel squeezes it out to mid-off
back of a length, closer to off. Nicely off the middle of the bat as Hendricks stands tall and punches this straight to cover
Pitched up full around middle and leg, 140kph, and Bhurtel jams his bat down to keep it out
fuller on middle and leg, 133kph, presents the full face of the bat to push this to mid-on

Nepal are underway in streaky fashion! Bhurtel chases after a full delivery angled across him, gets a thick bottom edge past a diving Quinton de Kock and the ball races away for four. First runs for Nepal in their chase
First boundary of the day and it's off the pads! This one pitches middle and seams in, just clips the thigh pad and races past short fine leg
Full on off, pushed out towards mid-off for a quick single
full on off, front foot push to mid-off
Length ball on middle and off, Sheikh blocks and they get a single
back of a length, stays back and defends watchfully. Cover darts in to collect
starts off well wide of off, 103kph. Left alone, wide given Quick and flat once more, slightly fuller this time as de Kock slashes this square for a couple
Length ball outside off, shaping away from the right-hander, and beats the outside edge
Good length just outside off, push and run towards cover. Played with soft hands
Length ball on off, 135kph, Sheikh defends
good length off break around off, 95kph. Goes back and works this towards midwicket for one
Length ball outside off, 135.3kph, and it jags away just a bit as Sheikh sticks his bat out
back of a length on off, 90kph, cut towards point
Length ball seams away, Sheikh backs away and looks to cut but can't get bat on it
Nearly skids through. This is the arm ball and it shapes in towards de Kock, who looks to punch this and gets an inside edge towards backward square leg for a single. Airee has his hands on his head

Oh my word, Rabada shells it! Sheikh swings across the line as Rabada bowls another length ball. Gets a top edge that goes straight up in the air. Rabada gets under it, looks like he had it under control, but the ball just bursts through his hands
length ball on the stumps from over the wicket, tucked around the corner but cut off by backward square leg
Carted over cover! This time Sheikh makes use of the width on offer and slaps it over the infield on the off side
Beauty from Jansen. Full length around off, shaping in. Bhurtel looks to drive but the inward movement sees the ball go past the inside edge
full and straight to the left hander, hint of shape in from just outside off. Punchy drive but straight back to Sompal
Full outside off, goes between the inside edge and stumps again as Bhurtel looks to drive again
good length outside off, induces a false stroke from de Kock who looks to chop this and misses
Length ball around middle and off, blocked to the bowler's right
back of a length on off, back foot punch but only as far as mid-off

Big bounce on that one! Jansen bangs it in short around leg, Bhurtel backs away and looks to cut but is beaten by the bounce. Good take by QDK, sticking up his arm as he jumps up and just about plucking it out of the air. Saves a possible four runs there!
Edged and four! Streaky but they all count. This was full outside off, de Kock leans back and looks to flay this through cover but gets a thick inside edge down to the fine leg boundary
Length ball angled across, Bhurtel hangs his bat out and is lucky that he is beaten on the outside edge
short and pulled away in the air. On the bounce to the man at deep square leg
Cheekily done! Bhurtel moves across the stumps as Jansen bowls another length ball. Gets under the ball and scoops it fine on the leg side and it goes all the way! First six for Nepal!
Bouncer, but this is too short. Wide given as it loops over Hendricks sees Hendricks charging and drags the length back. Nestles in the batter's midriff as he looks to work this onside
full on off, slapped wide of mid-off for a single.
Sheikh is struck on the pad as he misses a flick. This is a full delivery around off. Umpire isn't interested in the appeal. Likely going down leg
Tonked down the ground! This was tossed up on off, and Hendricks needed little invitation to clobber this drive
Length ball around middle, Sheikh looks to work it leg side but misses. Hit on the pad again, and this was also angling down leg
short and pulled towards deep midwicket
Length ball around off jags away sharply as Sheikh looks to back away and slap it away on the off side

Chipped back and Nepal have the breakthrough! This one was the arm ball, on a good length and angling in. De Kock is a little early on the drive, perhaps this held up in the surface. He ends up checking his stroke and can only offer up a simple return catch to Airee
Flicked away gloriously! Great wristwork as he picks this full delivery around off and helps it along over square leg. One bounce and over the rope!
good length off break on off, 88kph, defended towards mid-on
Swings at a length ball that's jagging away and is beaten!
good length and on off once more, 95kph, defended back towards Airee
Length ball outside off, he chops it square on the off side
good length on off, defensive push towards cover
Bonus runs for Nepal! Length ball angled across Bhurtel who swishes and misses and the ball just goes under Quinton de Kock's gloves as he dives low to his right to try and stop that
back of a length, 131kph, angled in. Defended into the onside
Length ball on middle and leg, defended to the off side
Lofted over point! Hendricks makes room to free his arms and flays this up and over the infield. Marginally overpitched from Karan as well
Length ball, 140kph, steered to gully
Whipped through midwicket! Over correction in line, this one stray on middle and leg and Hendricks just eases this through the vacant space
Bhurtel moves leg side, Jansen follows him. The batter looks to swing it away leg side, but misses and the ball deflects to his left off his body
good length angled in on the stumps, push and run towards mid-on
Dug in short around leg, Sheikh pulls it on the bounce to deep fine leg
Crunched but straight to cover. This was a good length on off, Hendricks gets low and gets a sweet connection on this drive but can't beat the man in the circle
Length ball on leg, Bhurtel fends with an open face and the ball goes to gully
length ball angled on the pads, turned fine for a single. Well fielded by short fine
Banged in short and Sheikh is beaten by the bounce. Good take by de Kock behind the stumps
short of a length outside, goes back and flat bats this in the V but mid-off does well to dive to his right and cut it off
Full, straight and flicked away off his pads behind square leg in the gap! Nepal are ensuring they keep getting boundaries!
nearly skids through! This one kept low as well, as Markram just about got bat to it in front of the stumps
On a length on off, gets on his toes and punches it off the back foot, but straight to the cover fielder
full on off, driven down to long-off
Length ball seams in from outside off, Sheikh looks to swing it away leg side but misses and is hit on the right thigh. They get the leg bye
follows the batter down leg. Hendricks is early on the pull as this deflects fine off the pad
Pace off back of length delivery around middle and off, Bhurtel backs away but can't get bat on ball
Slapped through cover! Slightly shorter in length as Markram backs away and hacks this between cover and mid-off
Full around off, Bhurtel taps it through midwicket for a quick single
Full outside off at 136kph, Bhurtel goes across the stumps and looks to scoop again, but can't connect
Starts off with a ripper! pitches on a good length on middle and rips past Hendricks' back foot defence
Length ball around off, Bhurtel punches towards cover and they scamper for a single
And again! Another ripper, this one goes past the edge on the forward defence
148kph delivery on a length outside off, Sheikh chops it to the off side
fuller on the pads, tucked through midwicket for one
Full and angling into off stump, fended to the leg side
good length top spinner, 93kph, defended right in front of the stumps
Bangs it in short outside off, Sheikh can't get bat on it as he looks to pull
looks for the reverse sweep, and misses as this bounces off the forearm

Off the glove and just past de Kock! Nortje goes short again and angles it into Sheikh. He looks to pull and takes a blow on the glove. The ball bounces over de Kock who was also wrong-footed by the angle of the delivery
full on on leg, 87kph, worked down to long-on
good length angled in, goes back and chips this in the air towards long-on
Tossed up full around off, swept along the ground to deep midwicket
Thwacked down the ground! Not the prettiest of strokes, but extremely effective! There was a man at long-off but Hendricks goes back and forehands this with ferocity to beat the man

Spin does the trick! Bhurtel looks to reverse-sweep the second ball of spin in the innings. This is tossed up on off, and turning back into the stumps. Bhurtel doesn't get near it and the ball goes off the pads and onto the stumps. Was there really a need for that shot in the situation Nepal were in?
length ball cut to cover this time
Full around middle and off, pushed out to midwicket
Short and clears the man at deep square! The man in the deep thinks he's in it, but this soars past him. Ferocious pull
Ripper! That spun back in a mile! Tossed up full and wide of off, Paudel looks for the drive but the ball turns sharply and crashes into off stump. Shamsi has just brought South Africa back to life!
full on off, defended towards cover
Full ball around middle and off, Anil Shah punches it back and onto the non-striker's stumps
good length on the stumps, pushed back towards Malla
Full on leg, Shah whips it away to deep midwicket's right for a single to get off the mark
Back of length delivery at 148.5kph, Saah parries square on the off side
full and drifts on the pads, tucked towards deep square leg for a single

Oh, well played! Length ball outside off. Saah moves across the stumps and flick-pulls this over midwicket. He was on his toes playing that shot and he cleared Markram at midwicket easily and the outfield does the rest
good length on the stumps, this time it's the googly that skids through. Strikes Hendricks on the pads outside the line of leg stump
Length ball angling in form outside off, Sah works it to short midwicket
big turn away from off, misses the sweep
Length ball outside off stays low as Sah looks to drive and sees the ball go under bat. Change of pace from Nortje
Oof! Nearly edges on. This was the googly, and Hendricks pushes at it on the front foot not reading it. Inside edge into the back pad
Banged in short at 145kph and angling into Sah, who gloves a pull through fine leg
fuller on off, square drive for a single
Fires a full toss down leg side for a wide. That was close to 148kph Sharp bouncer around off, Sheikh ducks under it as de Kock plucks it out of the air
tossed up on the stumps, defended watchfully on the front foot.
short to start, pulled down to deep midwicket
Full around leg, it stays low but spins in to go down leg for a wide Tossed up very full around off, Sah drives it down the ground for a single
swing and a miss! Tossed up outside off, induces the drive but it rips past the edge
Tossed full around off, Sheikh manages to sweep along the ground behind square leg
good length on the stumps, goes straight this one. Back foot punch down to long-off
On a length on leg, Sah backs away and jams his bat down
short of a length on off, pulled down to deep midwicket
Tossed full and Sah clears his front leg and lofts it down the ground. Lands short of long-on
full on the pads, tucked around the corner but short fine cuts it off
Full on middle, he parries it square on the leg side for a quick single
good length, angled in on leg stump. Back foot punch down to long-on
Length ball on leg, Sah goes back and whips it away to deep backward square
raps the back pad as this skids on to Markram. Missing leg

Just beats the fielder at deep third running to his right. Or does it? Shamsi does stop it, but his hand does hit the rope before he parries it back the second time. Four given. This was a length ball outside off and Sah just steered it fine on the off side
full outside off, slashed away but straight to backward point
Fired down the leg side by Nortje Dug in short outside off, Sah arches back and looks to play a ramp but is beaten
Scorching drive! This was overpitched and Markram absolutely leathers this drive through the covers

Shot! This was full on the pads at 144kph, Sah flicks it over midwicket and it's a safe area to play his shots because Markram at short midwicket was the only one in that direction. Sah is looking good here
good length and straighter, punched into the covers for a single
Length ball angles in from outside off, Sah rises to defend

Dropped! Oh dear, oh dear. This was a good length on off, and Hendricks gets this lofted drive low on the bat. It's chipped straight to Bhurtel at long-off, who makes an absolute mess of this and what's worse it runs away for four
Back of length outside off, Sah runs it down to deep third
good length on the stumps, tucked down to long-on for one
Banged in short, Sheikh ducks and that's called wide for height Length ball angled into Sheikh, who chips it into the vacant region in front of square leg
back of a length on the pads, punched down to long-on
Floated up full outside off, Sheikh backs away and lofts a drive wide of long-off
And Bhurtel does make amends! This was a good length leg break outside off, that sits up a bit. Markram has to wait ages for this and ends up slashing hard at it only to chop on to his stumps

Just beats long-off! Sah continues to attack for Nepal. This is full and wide, gives Sah a chance to free his hands and loft it wide of long-off. The fielder almost gets there but Sah picks up the six in the end
drifts down leg, goes back and works this towards deep square leg
Full outside off, it stays low as Sah looks to reach for it. Shouts for caught behind. SA don't review
again slides down leg, goes back and looks to work it onside but only as far as backward square leg
Full on leg, Sah misses and is hit on the back pad, but well outside leg
good length around off, grips and turns away sharply as Hendricks draws the bat in late
Tossed up full and wide, Sah drives it through cover and picks up two
good length on the stumps, defended on the front foot
Full on off, Sah can't get his reverse-sweep past Nortje moving to his left from short third

And he is greeted with a boundary! It shouldn't have been one though. This is back of a length and Sheikh pulls it away sqaure on the leg side. Tristan Stubbs gets behind the ball but just over-runs it and ends up letting the ball slip through
Beauty! Tossed up on off, draws in Klaasen and rips it past the forward push
Length ball angles into Sheikh who drops it in front on the leg side for a quick single
Nearly another! Klaasen goes for the switch hit and chips it barely over backward point, who gets a leaping right hand to it. Tough, tough chance
Full on off, Sah looks to loft a drive down the ground but doesn't time it. The ball goes high in the air, Markram is running back from mid-on but the ball just clears him and drops safe!
length on the stumps, worked towards midwicket
Length ball around off, steered to short third
full on off, driven down to long-off
Shot and a half! Banged in short and Sheikh latches onto this in an instant. Nails the pull and he sends it out of the ground! Sheikh will remember this shot for a long, long time, you'd think!
tossed up slower on off, cautious forward defence as this takes the leading edge towards cover
Full around middle and off, he clips it down to long-on and finishes the over with a single
googly this time, and it finds the inside edge this time on Hendricks' forward defence. They run a single to backward square leg
On a length outside off, punched out to deep point
floated up outside off, driven into the covers. Just the single
Length ball outside off spins in, Sah tucks it square on the leg side

Bobble, bobble, bobble but he holds on! And they have the big fish in Klaasen! This was tossed up and Klaasen backs himself to take on the long boundary at extra cover, but he doesn't catch it as he would like and it's straight at Karan in the deep, who juggles this multiple times before leaping forward and holding on with his right hand
Full on off, turning in sharply, Sheikh works it square on the leg side for a single. He wanted a second, but Sah sends him back
good length, leg break that turns down leg good length on off, defensive push towards mid-off

Jansen takes a very good catch and South Africa get a breakthrough! Sah has been on the front foot and he takes on Markram. Full outside off and he looks to slog-sweep. The ball goes high, but doesn't go far enough. Jansen has to run in and to his left from long-on, but he gets under it and holds on as he tumbles.

Big appeal but think this might be pitching outside leg. Nepal review though. This was tossed up as Miller missed the sweep completely. It pitches and goes on with the arm to strike the back pad. Oh wow, it's pitching in line, and impact in line, but umpire's call as this is deemed to be clipping the top of the bails. Great review, but very unfortunate on the result
On a length around off, Airee tucks it square on the leg side for a quick single to get off the mark
full on off, driven down to long-off
Length ball outside off, punched to midwicket
short outside off, leg break. Pulled to deep midwicket
full on off, driven straight back to mid-off
Length ball outside off, blunted to backward point
wide full toss, chopped into the turf
Full around middle and leg, tickled down to long leg
back of a length on off, punched down towards long-off
Back of length delivery stays low, he pulls it away square on the leg side. Stubbs does really well to run across from deep midwicket and puts in a dive to stop the boundary
full outside off from around the wicket, thumped straight to the man at cover
Length ball outside off, Sheikh punches it to mid-off for a quick single
short and pulled behind square for a single
Full and flicked down to long leg
full and straight, chipped down the ground for one
Length ball outside off, chopped to backward point
Markram tosses it up outside off, pushed out to point
back of a length on off, swatted down to long-on
Floated full on middle, Sheikh pulls to midwicket
quick off break on back of a length, cut square for a single
Length ball around off, he knocks it towards mid-on for a single

Top edge and gone! Hendricks' frustrating innings comes to an end. This was back of a length and quicker, but it stops in the surface. Hendricks swipes at this and can only manage a top edge that loops straight back to Airee
On a length outside off, Airee pulls it away to deep square as the singles keep coming
good length outside off, Stubbs pushes at this tentatively as it goes past the edge
On a length and Sheikh clips it to midwicket. Good, sharp fielding by him to stop the single!
fuller on off, driven down to long-on
Length ball clipped through square leg
full on the pads, tucked square on the onside. Played softly and they run hard to come back for the second
Full on off, he gives it a gentle push past the non-striker for a quick single. Mid off raced in and had a shy at the stumps, but Airee was in safe
tossed up on off, outside edge on the drive to backward point
Full on leg, he ends up chipping it to the vacant mid-on region
Misfield goes for four! Stubbs powers this sweep as Karan at deep square leg overruns this and misreads the spin. Inexperience showing there perhaps
Full around off, squirted out to deep point
Reverse paddle sweep now, bounces this over slip for a couple
Goes short and takes pace off. Airee prods but is beaten on the bounce
tossed up on off, driven hard to long-off. Bit of a bobble leads to another misfield and a couple more
Yorker around middle and off, Airee manages to jam his bat down and dig it out to midwicket
good length on the stumps, nudged to the right of the bowler for one
Low full toss outside off sneaks under the bat as Airee looks to drive on the off side. Jansen closes the over well
good length, angled in from around the wicket. Tucked square on the onside for one
good length on off, backs away and chops this into the covers
On a length around leg, fended towards midwicket
full toss on off, driven down to long-off
Full on off, he skips out and drives it out to long-on

Sliced and gone! Airee's great day continues! This was tossed up on off, slows it up a touch. Miller goes hard on the drive across the line, but there's just enough turn to take the edge as this pops up straight to Lamichhane at short third

Late twist?! Shamsi gets a wicket with a ball fired down leg! Airee looks to sweep but misses. QDK grabs it and goes up in appeal. The umpire thinks so too and Nepal review immediately. There's a spike as the ball passes the glove and Airee will have to go!
full and straight, worked down towards wide long-on
Full on leg, clipped square through leg side and they get a single and 100 comes up for Nepal
full on off, walks across the line and looks to sweep but can't place it past short fine leg
On a length around leg, Sheikh looks to tuck it away on the leg side but only hits it onto his own pads
good length on the stumps, defended

Oh, Shamsi you magician! South Africa saved his last over for late, and boy has he given them a chance here? Sheikh was the set batter and he has to go! Full around off and it spins in sharply to go past the bat and hits pad and clips the off bail! Two double-wicket overs for Shamsi have given South Africa a chance of preventing the upset today!
wide yorker, looks to reverse paddle this fine but can't beat the man in the ring. 100 up!
Length ball outside off, punched to cover
Jansen now looks to paddle it as well, again a good yorker though. They run the leg bye

Bowled 'im! First wicket for a fast bowler in this game. Nortje digs it in on a length around leg, Malla looks to swing across the line and misses completely and that hits top of off! South Africa's leading wicket-taker in this World Cup has got a big one right now!
full and wide, swing and miss
Very full around off, Sompal Kami drives it straight to Klaasen at cover. Another dot ball. More pressure!
Whipped to deep square leg! No one on the boundary there and Stubbs, walks across the line and flicks it nicely into space
Sompal looks to cut this back of length delivery but is beaten by the pace. Nortje hit 142kph there
full and straight, slapped hard but straight back to the bowler

Hold your horses, there are twists still to come! Sompal Kami has hit this out of the park! Back of hand slower ball and Sompal picks it early, bashing it over midwicket. That's gone over 100 metres. Some cars in the parking lot may have been damaged!
full on off, looks to drive but ends up inside edging it towards backward square for one
Full on off, driven out through cover, they run very well to get two! Nepal keeping themselves right in it!
Tossed up and outta here! This was a risky from Bhurtel, as he floats it up on off, but Stubbs has the reach and he just clubs this flat over long-on. Just the second six of the innings
Length ball on off angled across the left-handed batter, who looks to cut but can't make contact
full on off, carved into the covers, misfield allows for two
Nails the wide yorker, inside the line, and Jha can't touch this either! Another dot from Baartman
looks for the reverse sweep but can't connect
Game on! Cracking shot! Baartman goes for the wide yorker again, Jha has moved across the stumps and he carts it over cover. Deep point stood no chance. Four needed from three now!
good length leg break, goes back and nudges this to the right of the bowler. They want to two but Bhurtel hares to the ball to keep it to one
Crashed through cover and they are just two away now! Length ball going across him, he backs away and slaps it away to deep cover's left. They get the brace.

Jansen holes out! This was slightly back of a length as Jansen goes back and looks to muscle this over long-on. It's off the toe-end on the bat as Sah rushes in from the long-on boundary and takes a good catch falling forward
Baartman bowls the dot! Digs it in short and beats the attempted ramp! Two from one, and one for a Super Over!

Bhurtel ends with a four-for! Rabada saunters down the track and looks for a big heave over long-on, but the googly beats him all ends up. Easy stumping to end the innings. South Africa end on 115 for 7

Is that a run out?! Quinton de Kock is all smiles! What a dramatic end this is. Jha can't get bat on the short ball but the batters take off for the single. QDK throws it and it deflects to Klaasen off Jha. Klaasen throws the stumps down at the non-striker's end and it's heartbreak for Nepal! Jha seemed to slow down just a tad in the end I think. He is on his haunches, hand on head. But it's celebrations for South Africa, who have again pulled out a win out of nowhere!
back of a length outside off. A bit of extra bounce and Allen watches it go through to the keeper
in-swinging yorker on off stump. Ronak picks it early enough and defends

slides this down leg and the keeper does brilliantly to sprawl to his left and get a glove to it. Just a wide back of a length on middle and leg. Nips back into Allen, goes past his flick and then rolls away off the thigh pad towards short fine leg
fullish on middle and leg. Holds its line and does not swing back prodigiously. Ronak plays it with an open bat face towards short third

wild delivery outside off, reminiscent of Steve Harmison all those years ago at the Gabba. Gathered by the keeper, though, albeit not cleanly back of a length on leg stump. Conway plays all over it and the ball pings off the pads into the off side

big appeal, and given! That looks very plumb! Another yorker, which starts on middle and leg and curves away. Ssesazi has no clue about it and is awfully late in jamming his bat down. Sneaks past the inside edge and hits him flush on the back leg, right in front of middle stump. Ssesazi does not bother with the review, and Uganda lose their first!
length outside off. Allen comes half forward and pushes it towards mid off

clean through! Full just outside off and this swerves back in devilishly. Obuya looks for the drive first up but does so without getting to the pitch of the ball. The inward movement takes it past the inside edge, through the gap between bat and pad, and smashes into the stumps!
back of a length outside off. Allen waits for it and dabs it towards backward point. First run off the bat for NZ!
out-swinging yorker just outside off. Ramjani gets behind the line and digs it out
classic Conway! Full enough outside off. Conway springs onto the front foot and creams it on the up past cover for four!
back of a length on middle and off. Ramjani gets onto the back foot and defends
short, wide and punished! Too much width on offer and Allen throws the kitchen sink at it, slashing it well over backward point!
full and swinging away outside off. Ronak comes forward and watches it go through to the keeper
length just outside off. Allen presses half forward and defends. A hint of away-swing
appeal, not given! Length in the channel just outside off. Decks back in sharply and seems to breeze past the inside edge. Strikes Ronak on the back thigh but that might have been a little too high
back of a length just outside off. Keeps low and Allen chalks it off the toe-end towards the bowler
length outside off. Goes straight through and Ronak lets it go
hard length on middle and off. Allen does not try anything funky with it and defends
full and angled into middle and leg, bowled from wide of the crease. Ronak waits for it and meets it right under his eyes
shortish outside off. Allen has a massive swish at it but fails to make contact
back of a length in the channel just outside off. Ronak goes feeling for it and sees the ball sneak past the outside edge
back of a length outside off. Allen hops up onto his toes and taps it into the off side
slanted in on a back of a length on leg stump. Ronak is a touch late on the stroke and the ball rolls away off the thigh pad past square leg

length just outside off. Conway hangs back and drops it into the off side for a single. Uh-oh, looks like Kyewuta has overstepped... back of a length way outside off. Allen sits back in his crease and has a mighty mow at it. Clinks it off the toe-end and gets caught at long on. But it will, of course, not count!
full on middle and leg. A hint of swing back into Ronak and he accounts for it fully. Defended with a straight bat
fullish just outside off. Conway presses forward and drives it to mid on
back of a length on off. Shapes back in sharply and almost cuts Ronak in half. Goes past the bat and strikes him on the pads but that was again a little high
length on middle and leg. Conway tips it towards point and saunters across to the other end
length outside off. Boomerangs back in with the angle and Ronak covers it all the way. Taps it towards backward point
back of a length outside off. A bit of movement away and Allen uses it to run it down to third man
length in the channel. Goes straight on with the angle and Ronak blocks it into the off side
hard length on middle and off. Conway dangles his bat tentatively and the ball squirts away towards short fine leg off the inside edge
back of a length on middle and leg. Keeps a shade low and Ronak hurriedly prods it towards mid wicket
length delivery hung up wide outside off. Allen has an enormous waft at it and only connects with fresh air

oh, a half-hearted appeal, and the finger goes up! Length ball on off that seems to continue with the angle. Ronak defends with bat and pad very close together. Boult thinks the ball has brushed the front pad first, and appeals. The umpire agrees and gives it out. Ronak reviews straightaway, though. It was pad-first but the natural angle might be taking it away from off stump. Well, the impact itself is outside off and Richard Illingworth has to reverse his decision!
short on leg stump. Conway gets inside the line and glances it off his hips towards short fine leg
full and hung up outside off. Ramjani leaves it alone
length just outside off. Allen punches it towards cover and canters across to the other end
full and swinging into middle and off. Ramjani picks it a little late but from his POV, does so just in time. Stabbed down the ground
peach! Length in the channel just outside off. Straightens against the angle and Conway, looking for the drive, is beaten convincingly. Nod of approval to Miyagi too
length just outside off. Shapes back in but Ramjani judges his leave well
back of a length on middle and leg. Conway advances and pats it gently towards cover point

Southee goes up, and so does Paul Reiffel's finger! Length on middle and leg, and this seems to curve back in. Curves back in enough and keeps low to graze the pad and then hit the bat as Ramjani looks to defend. Ramjani has reviewed, and don't think he will get as much success as Ronak did in the last over. Clearly pad-first and Ball Tracking reckons it is missing leg stump because....it is thundering into the middle of middle stump!
dug in short on off. Conway is a little late on the pull and splices it towards deep square leg
full just outside off. Waiswa comes forward and jabs at it, squirting it away off the outside edge towards second slip, who misfields and concedes the single
full just outside off. Allen is content to drop it into the off side and dash across to the other end
fullish outside off. More swing away from Ronak and he defends it behind point
and he starts off with a wayward delivery down leg. He will have to reload that one... in the slot just outside off. Allen plants his front foot and drags it to mid on
length just outside off. Waiswa comes forward and pokes at it, chunking it off the inside half of the bat into the on side

appeal, and given! Allen cannot believe it, and he reviews it! Sprayed down leg. Allen looks to tickle it fine and seems to miss it. The umpire, though, thinks otherwise and reckons bat is involved. There was a sound as the ball went past the bat, but did the bat hit the ground or his boot on the way? There is a spike but Kumar Dharmasena says there is a gap between bat and ball, and that the bat brushed the floor, only to then go back and have another look. Now, he says there is a spike as the ball passes the bat, and the decision stands! The right decision might have been made eventually!

another Boult appeal, but not given this time! Zipped in quite full, just outside off. Swerves back in and Waiswa, looking for the booming drive, seems to miss it. Clips the pads and then floats through to Conway, who catches it. New Zealand have reviewed this, with the umpire's decision being not out for the caught-behind. That could be out on two counts. If it has not hit the bat, lbw could be in play. No bat involved, and the impact is Umpire's Call, which is a very close call. Ball Tracking has the ball hitting the stumps thereafter but it does not matter after one parameter returns Umpire's Call! The original decision, just to reiterate, was not out on both the caught-behind and the lbw.
low full toss on the pads. Rachin works it away towards deep square leg and gets off the mark with a single
back of a length outside off. Whistles off the surface and whizzes past the outside edge of Waiswa's bat
shortish outside off. Conway flashes hard at it but cannot make contact
into the blockhole just outside off. Waiswa cannot jam his bat down in time and the ball sneaks under his bat
that has sped away to the fence! Half-tracker on leg stump and that is a proper buffet ball. Conway picks it and belts it behind square!
beautiful square drive! Full outside off and the width allows Waiswa to free his arms. Waits for the ball, uses the pace and beats backward point to his right!

drifts down leg again. Conway lets it go and the umpire calls it a wide fired down leg again, and some more exercise for the umpire. Richard Illingworth is going to have sore arms by the end of this over and this is a wide on height. This over keeps on going. Short on middle and leg. Too short, though. Nine off the over already banged into the track on middle and leg. Gets big on Conway but he manages to fend it away into the on side for a single
full in the channel just outside off. Waiswa, having taken a step down the track, nibbles at it and is beaten on the outside
gorgeous! Half-volley outside off and that is right up Conway's alley. Springs onto the front foot and crunches it to cover point's left!
full just outside off. Ronak comes forward and plonks it past cover for a single

that will be that! New Zealand get on the board and they have iced this run-chase inside six overs! Short down leg. Conway uses the pace and the angle to help it past short fine leg. NZ cruise to a nine-wicket win, and they have points on the board!
back of a length outside off. Waiswa lets the ball come to him before meeting it right under his eyes
peach! Back of a length in the sixth stump channel. Threatens to angle in before nipping away off the surface. Waiswa, prodding at it, is beaten all ends up
fuller, slanting into middle and off. Waiswa pats it towards mid on
length outside off. Waiswa goes fishing at it away from his body and is beaten on the outside edge
the nip-backer comes but Waiswa has it all figured out. Comes forward to this length ball and works it into the on side
shortish outside off. Grips in the surface and spins away. Waiswa jabs it past extra cover for a single
beauty! Fizzed through on a length on off. Drifts into the batter before ripping away. Ronak is beaten all ends up
flighted up even more and perhaps fuller outside off. Drops on Ronak late and then rags past the outside edge. Massive turn!
arm-ball on a back of a length outside off. Comes back in but the initial line is too wide to threaten the stumps

edged and taken! Stunning bowling! Looped up devilishly on a full length on middle and leg. Drifts into the batter before dipping and then snaking away. Ronak tries to knock it down the ground but the excessive turn means he can only feather it through to Conway. Smart catch behind the stumps, and Uganda are four down!
length delivery hung up way outside off. Beyond the tramlines and called a wide. Might have been an attempted arm-ball floated up full outside off. Riazat comes forward and defends
Waiswa welcomes Ferguson with a boundary! Dug into the track on middle and off. Waiswa picks the length, rocks back and rolls his wrists nicely to pull it through backward square leg!
safe! Hard length, angling into off stump. Bounces a touch extra and spoons up off the leading edge as Waiswa looks to work to leg. Luckily for him, Ferguson cannot get to it on his follow-through
back of a length on off. Waiswa gets behind the line and taps it gently towards mid wicket
length outside off. Looks like it will angle in before pitching and holding its line. Waiswa nibbles at it and is beaten comprehensively

castled! Much fuller, slanting into off stump. Nips back in a little off the surface too and Waiswa, trying the booming off-drive, leaves a massive gap between bat and pad, mostly because his feet had gone nowhere. The ball bursts through and he hears the death rattle soon after!
length delivery pushed across the batter just outside off. Nakrani has a flat-footed poke at it and is fortunate to not nick it through to Conway
back of a length outside off. More extravagant spin and Riazat misses the ball by a mile
tossed up on a length outside off. Rips away off the surface and Riazat is beaten all ends up
floated up full on off. Riazat comes forward and stabs it into the on side to get off the mark

darted down leg and that is a rare loose ball. Nakrani swings hard at it but misses. Called a wide back of a length delivery that pitches just outside off and spins down leg. More exercise for the umpire looped up on a length on middle and off. Nakrani comes forward to defend but sees the ball go past the inside edge, striking him on the flap of the front pad
back of a length outside off. Nakrani goes back and punches it enough to extra cover's right for a single
length outside off. Riazat lunges forward and watches the ball spin through into Conway's gloves
zipped in on a fullish length on leg stump. Nakrani gets squared up and nearly pops it straight back to Ferguson
shortish on middle and off. Nakrani hops up onto his toes and fends it into the off side
back of a length just outside off. Nakrani hangs back and jabs it towards backward point
hard length, angling into leg stump. Nakrani tucks it off his hips into the mid wicket region and picks up a single
length just outside off. Riazat gets onto the front foot and blocks
banged into the track just outside off. Riazat gauges it early enough and ducks under it. Called a wide on height length outside off. Riazat presses half forward and defends
tossed up on a length on middle and leg. Nakrani plants his front foot and drags it towards deep mid wicket
darted in very full on off. Riazat digs it out towards the bowler
length on middle and off. Riazat comes forward and defends
full on middle and leg. Riazat comes forward and defends again
fired in quicker and fuller on the pads. Riazat chunks it off the inside half of the bat towards deep backward square leg
lobbed up on a length on the pads. Nakrani misses it and the ball trickles away off his front leg
darted in full outside off. Riazat plays it towards short extra cover

beautiful bowling, and no Riazat rescue act for Uganda tonight! Fizzed through on a length on middle and off. Drifts in and then rags away after pitching. Riazat has not accounted for that much turn and tries to defend with an open bat face. Almost glides it off the face and Conway pouches it smartly behind the stumps!
shortish on off. Keeps low and Masaba stabs it off the back foot towards short extra cover

tossed up on a length outside off. Masaba jumps across his stumps, trying to swipe it away. Misses the ball by a fair margin after being defeated in the air. Conway whips off the bails too and the third umpire has been called into question to check the stumping. Masaba's back foot is grounded behind the crease, so nothing fruitful for the Kiwis on that front!
back of a length outside off. Masaba hangs back and prods it into the off side
length outside off. Comes off very sluggishly and Masaba misses his paddle sweep completely. Conway is nutmegged too and Uganda get a couple of byes for their toil. Not a great deal of bounce again
fullish on the pads. Nakrani uses the pace and glances it uppishly towards fine leg
banged into the track outside off. Masaba watches it go through to the keeper
hard length just outside off. Bounces extra and hits Masaba on the splice as he defends
hard length outside off. Nips back in sharply and pings Masaba very high on the bat. Almost near the handle
much fuller, slanted into the pads. Masaba works it towards mid wicket
back of a length just outside off. Masaba gets up on his toes and defends
given a bit of air on a length outside off. Spins back appreciably and strikes Nakrani on the pads
fuller outside off. Nakrani gets close enough to it and smothers any possible turn

taken brilliantly by Glenn Phillips! Dangles the carrot outside off and Nakrani bites. Looks for the big slog over cow corner but does not get the power, the placement or the elevation. Swipes it flat towards deep mid wicket, where Phillips hurtles in off the fence, lunges forward and snaffles up a sharp chance. Phillips was not right on the fence and that allowed him to get to it. Nakrani has to go, and Uganda are 26-7!
darted in on a length on middle and off. Straightens a touch and Achelam meets it with an even straighter bat
back of a length outside off. Achelam goes back and knocks it to long off
angled into the stumps. Masaba keeps it out without much fuss. Another dot, though
back of a length on leg stump. Achelam is late on the flick and the ball thuds into his thigh pad
sprays this down leg. Achelam lets it go and the umpire calls it a wide shortish outside off. Achelam gets on top of the bounce and runs it down to third man
bumper on leg stump and Ferguson gets away with this. Seemed to slide down leg but the umpire is happy with it
back of a length on off. A bit of extra bounce and Masaba plonks it back towards the bowler
length in the channel just outside off. Zips off the surface and breezes past the outside edge of Masaba's booming drive
length in the channel. Masaba goes feeling for it without any footwork and is beaten on the outside
shot! Full outside off and Achelam pounces. Gets down on one knee early and razes it to deep backward square leg's left!
loopy low full toss outside off. Driven down the ground to long on
length outside off. Masaba moves across his stumps and helps it round the corner towards deep backward square leg. Finally, off the mark
slowed up on a length on off. Achelam waits for it before patting it towards short extra cover
fuller on off. Achelam brings out the sweep and collects a single to deep backward square leg
slow and short outside off. Masaba hangs back and knocks it to long on
back of a length outside off. Kisses the surface and whizzes through, whistling past the outside edge of Masaba's bat
length outside off. Masaba has a massive waft at it and only connects with fresh air
fullish, angling into middle and off. Masaba stabs at it and chunks it off the inside half of the bat towards mid wicket
shortish just outside off. Masaba gets on top of the bounce and dabs it past backward point
back of a length outside off. Achelam advances before poking it towards mid on
full toss on the pads. Achelam tucks it away towards deep square leg and is content with the single
full and hung outside off. Achelam fishes at it away from his body and does not lay bat on ball
back of a length on middle and off. Achelam comes forward and pushes it towards mid on

trapped in front, and that is a no-brainer for the umpire! Back of a length on middle and off. Nips back in a smidgen and keeps low. Achelam, having moved across his stumps, plays all over it and gets pinned on the knee roll of the front pad. That was only heading one way, and that was into middle stump. No review from Achelam, and Uganda are eight down!

that is as plumb as it can get! Length just outside off, and this decks back in sharply. Keeps extraordinarily low too and smacks into the pad, almost up around the shins. Southee goes up and Paul Reiffel upholds the appeal. Miyagi has reviewed it because, well, why not. Clear gap between bat and ball, and Ball Tracking has it pummelling middle of middle stump. Uganda nine down now!
full and speared into middle and off. Kyewuta comes forward and blocks it with a straight bat
fuller on middle and off. Kyewuta pokes it to the right of the pitch and scampers across to the other end
flighted up full on middle and leg. Kyewuta advances and jams it towards short mid wicket
tossed up on a length outside off. Kyewuta plays and misses at it, and then gestures that he left it
oh! Flighted up full just outside off. Kyewuta tries to hit it into next week and only swats away a few flies in the process

that will be that! Uganda have been rolled over for 40! Looped up beautifully on a full length on middle and leg. Dips on the batter late and it is just too good for Kyewuta. He tries to flick it away but the turn takes the outside edge and Mitchell does the rest at slip!
An air-shot from Salt, back of a length from Wiese and sits in the surface while seaming away. Misses an ambitious pull

good line and carry outside off, bending from the left-arm line, and through to the keeper. But Topley has overstepped! Shocker Free hit... banged in short, outside off, very close to being too wide, but he gets away with it, hiding the ball well out of van Lingen's reach
short again, same result! Another flat-footed haul to leg from Salt, and he's beaten by the bounce and movement outside off
that's better from Topley. Hitting the pitch from that cloud-snagging release point, hint of away movement, a loose hack to leg, reminiscent of England's powerplay swinging
back of a length, Salt is into line and fends a single into the gap in the covers. England haven't quite got going, but early days
hits the pitch again, another shot to nothing across the line Back of a length, good carry, through to the keeper
hits the pitch again, stops on the surface, Buttler pokes back down the pitch off the splice. This is a super start from Wiese
Moeen straight into the action in his new position, as van Lingen pushes with hard hands, off an inside-edge
beaten on the walk! Wiese has the ball on a string in this over, a touch fuller, nipping away, Buttler falls into a loose drive and can't connect
softer hands, through the full length, pressed back down the pitch for a single
on the back foot, another swish across the line! No contact as the keeper gathers. It's a ten-over game for England now!
