tight line over the wicket to the right hander, a bit of bend back at the batter, who blocks to point off the back foot. After that nervy first ball, that's a super effort from Topley
big jag off the seam! Hits a good length across the left-hander, and zags away, through to the keeper
back of a length, Trumpelmann resists the temptation to swing it in Salt's arc, instead he induces a gentle back-foot poke to cover
just back of a length, pushed across the leftie again, a loose slap across the line, can't connect

bowled him! That is a simply huge moment for England's World Cup campaign! Trumpelmann bluffed Buttler there, he perhaps assumed he wouldn't risk that wicked full-length inswinger, but by jingo he did! Perfect line, length, shape, plucking out the leg stump as England's captain flaps loosely through the line! Crumbs!
bouncer, didn't know much about that! Swings up into the stroke, and in fact did better than it looked, committed to the pull, and ducking his head inside the line on impact
sticks on the pitch again, poked in the air into the covers, off the mark, which is something ...
another hoist across the line, huge edge over the keeper! Ten runs in two balls to get Namibia up and running
back of a length, wider line, Salt has a chance to thump down the ground! England have their first boundary, and it's all muscle
fuller length, wider line, chipped uppishly out into the covers
width outside off, and Salt's on the move! Sitting deep in his crease, crashing up into his stroke, a high hack over deep third. Nearly carries the distance
walks across his stumps, can't make the contact he's looking for, as that takes the body and deflects to the keeper. Good over for Namibia though!
w-a-a-a-a-y outside the off-side tramlines. No danger of nicking that. cramped on the back foot, another ball sticks in the pitch and is poked in the air, this time to the leg side

slower ball, nicked to the keeper! Now this is just wonderful bowling. Wiese turns off all the pace, but finds the ideal line and length, a knuckleball floats like a leaf down at Salt's hard hands, and a palpable nick loops gently to the keeper. England are in a world of bother now!
lovely line and length, and lift, from a tight line across the right-hander. Through to the keeper
full length outswinger, that's met with a respectful block into the off side. England are in a serious scrap now
shorter length but tight to the body again, Davin swings into a pull and under-edges to the keeper
on the back foot, soft hands blocked into the off side
fuller length, dug out from the blockhole with a drive to short cover. Topley is trading in dots and singles here
on the back foot, cuffed out to the off side
wider line, full length, lures the crashing drive but straight at cover. Missed out on a four-ball there
another knuckleball but Bairstow's bottom hand takes over, like a back-seat driver in a traffic jam. Forcefully back through the line, and over the bowler's head
walks to the off-side, Topley hangs it out wider, clipped off the toes to the on-side, chance of a run-out but safe
that is sumptuous bowling! Bairstow all but loses his off pole to a worldie of an outswinger, wide on the crease, full length, angling in and straightening past the edge
in the slot, slogged over Jordan's head at mid-on! Doesn't get full beans through the stroke, as Jordan tracks back to limit them to two. Topley's work is done, and he's done it well
round the wicket, probing length on the pads, tucked to midwicket
good lines from over the wicket, shaping away, and beating a slap to the leg side
slog-sweep but beaten by the spin! There's sweaty grip off the pitch there, Bairstow was eyeing up the short boundary, but didn't get close
well bowled, tight on off stump, a hint of away swing, lobbed in the air to the on-side, but short of wide long-on
another attempted slap across the line, beaten by the turn and bounce
makes room to leg, Curran sees him going and just dangles it out wide of off. Good nerve from the bowler
reverse-sweep, nailed! Excellent from Bairstow, premeditating the change-up stroke, up and over point for a precious boundary
another swish across the line, top-edged too fine for deep third! A profitable zone for Namibia

now he's on the move! Seizes on Scholtz's turn to blink, he tossed it up a fraction fuller, maybe anticipating another reverse. Instead he opened his stance deep in the crease and pummelled a launch over long-on!
cutter, all the pace off the ball, tucked off the pads to the on-side
another big hack across the line, is that off a top-edge? The keeper can't gather, and the bowler looks a bit crestfallen
lovely finish! Extra carry off the tight line outside the left-hander's off stump. Buttler gathers. One more over for this to constitute a game
hits the pitch, back of a length, angled into the body, a swish to mid-on, high on the blade
round the wicket, a real dart, back of a length and pushed across the right-hander, toe-ended out to cover
on the toes, full length, clipped out to midwicket for another single. The rate is pushing 3 a ball now
carved out into space in the covers
that'll help that rate! Full length, wide of off, and that's in the slot for a slap, up and over backward point!
launched high, back over the bowler's head! Not timed at all, three fielders converge, Erasmus included, but the ball plops just safe!
bouncer, sharp pace, and it's the right height to get away with the wide ... just! Davin flings his bat at the ball but is beaten
crashed violently across the line! Bairstow is doing the needful now, hanging back in the crease, targeting the leg side, nearly carrying the whole way
pace off, lovely length, stops in the pitch and beats a woolly whoosh through the line
speared in at the body, Bairstow swings across the line from round the wicket, deflects off the body
lifted up and over the leg-side ... this constitutes a game!
winds into another big slog, loses his shape on impact and lets out a groan as the ball skews out to square leg. Still, it's progress from England now, in what are still tricky conditions
looped up outside leg, blatted high over midwicket! Stunning strike, proactive footwork, taking on the long boundary and clearing by a distance
line and length with a high action, poked in the air into the covers
reverses the hands, nearly picks the gap at backward point, but Bairstow tumbles well
width, and crashed hard by Brook but the point sweeper slides well to cut off the four
slower, wider, tossed up and dipping, big spin past a bigger wipe
bottom-handed blat, high over the leg-side! That's Brook at his best, solid base, aggressive intent, dispatched over the ropes
big turn outside off, and that's gone too far lovely loop and grip! Tossed up, dipping below another slog-sweep, sharp turn with all the pace off the ball
drags the length back, cuffed past point! This is free-flowing now from England's Yorkies. Riding the extra bounce, and beating the diving fielder
wider line, toe-ended slap to cover, more big turn
good riposte! Very full length, seemed to be in the slot for Brook, but that takes a piece out of the pitch and flies past the edge into the keeper's gloves
big grip on the googly, strikes the pads as van Lingen gets in a tangle, Buttler shies at the stumps and misses
Hits the pitch again, more good carry, slaps the keeper's gloves. A brace of dots to regain control in that over
round the wicket, Bairstow pans a pull over midwicket! Just stopped in the pitch again but he's wise to the pitch now, waits on the stroke and launches it!
wide line, hint of away swing, clubbed hard on the front foot, but straight at cover
faster and flatter, speared in at an attempted sweep, deflects to point
sits back in the crease, solid contact on a bash across the line, out to deep midwicket
dips on the toes, and nudged to the leg-side... this could have been a run-out! Bairstow was struggling as they turned for the second run, but Erasmus couldn't gather cleanly!

gets on top of the ball, and cuffs a first-ball boundary through backward point! Opens the face at the top of the bounce, using the angle across the body. Four an over is the requirement, he's meeting it...
leg-sided, Brook makes initial room as the bowler follows him. Tucked off the hip to backward square
on the back foot, nudged off the pads, and up comes the fifty for Namibia
round the wicket, chopped uppishly through deep third! 108kph from Erasmus, zippy angle into middle and off, Brook rocks back and lifts it past the diving backward point
pace off, wide line, slapped with an open face out to deep cover
in at the toes, Brook can't get any elevation into his launch to the on-side, but the lack of timing allows them to get back for the second
tight lines, back of a length, Wiese gets in a tangle aiming a flick off the pads. Good finish to the over
googly, van Lingen steps into the length, climbs through a lofted drive, to long-on

width outside off, Bairstow toe-ends his slapped cut! The keeper calls early, jogs round to short cover and pockets a big top-edge. The end of a handy knock from Bairstow, one which began in very tricky circumstances
tight lines on the legbreak, chopped off the back foot to deep cover, Salt's shy slips out of his hand and they burgle an extra run
yanked across the line, off a good length outside off, into space at deep midwicket
sits back in the crease, hoisted magnificently over long-off! Waiting for the ball to bite, gets underneath the stroke, and lofts it sweetly!
Moeen goes long! In his arc, from over the wicket, he plants the front dog, takes on the longer boundary, and clobbers the camera at wide long-off
vast slog-sweep! Rashid over-compensates, right in Wiese's arc. Out come the long levers, belted massively over midwicket!
reaching for the width, and cuffed uppishly out to cover
up and over the off side again! Shades of Heinrich Klaasen as he anchors on the back foot  and lifts up into the legbreak. Bissects two men in the covers!
round the wicket, dipping on a good length, and eased into the covers
on the back foot, pulled to the on-side
wide line, slammed out to deep cover, a good slide to intercept...
into the pitch, hoisted to the leg-side, no timing on the pull as it plugs at midwicket. Wiese is off-strike, which England won't mind
hoisted around the corner, good contact on the full length, but deep square leg gathers
walks across his stumps, Jordan sees him going, aims full outside off, and long-on gathers on the bounce
very full, high hands from Brook as Brassell follows him down the leg-side, and lobbed to the on-side
attempted yorker, fired in full and straight, under-edged onto the pads and away for a single to cover
cramped on the pads, flicked in the air, good areas from Brassell, tight to Brook's body to prevent him from freeing his levers
wide yorker, this is an excellent over so far. Van Lingen can only toe-end a drive back to the bowler
wonderful contact on the ramp! It's a very flat ramp, a very full length from the bowler, and the contact is sweet and true through fine leg

rolls the fingers on a cutter, and gets launched! Too short, outside off, van Lingen checks his pull and almost dumps the ball into the back of a waiting ambulance. Which, in different circumstances, might have been an apt metaphor for England's campaign. Maybe not today after all!
slower ball, waits and waits, and muscles the uppercut! Hard over extra cover!
goes down-town once again, but picks out Brook at long-on! Hitting up through the line, Jordan strikes with his final ball, and England are home bar the snookers

over fine leg once more! Brassell fired it outside the legs, but Brook was walking all the way across his stumps, and just tapped it on the head as he went. Up and over fine leg to complete a damaging over, the hundred is up too
full length, on the toes, clipped to the on-side
over the wicket, slower ball, in the arc, Moeen latches on with alacrity! He held his stroke wonderfully, waiting that split-second for the ball to arrive and mashed over long-on
rolls the fingers well on the slower ball, very full, hopping past off stump as Erasmus misses his drive back over the bowler's head
seizes the short ball, but straight to deep midwicket! Sticks in the pitch, taking on the longer boundary. Trumpelmann strikes, but Moeen has made his mark
pace off, into the surface, Erasmus waits and waits on his pull and hauls to the on-side
lands the one-handed slam over backward square! Livingstone is set up outside off, hoists across the full length and pounds it onto the grass banks.

pace off once more, top-edged on the pull! Wiese swings for the hills, as well he might, but Brook is on hand once more in the deep, looking into the sun but judging it well. Is that the end for Wiese, his salute to the crowd suggests it might be. What a performer he's been. Handshakes from the England players as he left too, which is nice to see
over the wicket, launched gloriously over long-on! In the slot, plants the front foot, nails it over the ropes!
pace back on, zips up through an attempted launch to leg. Archer looks a bit miffed to be called wide, but it's academic now thuds the pads, deflects to the off-side

wider line, back of a length, Livingstone swings for the hills, cannot connect, should have been run out at both ends! Trumpelmann aimed an under-arm at the bowler's stumps, missed them all, and Livingstone stole the strike back!
pace off, back of a length, Erasmus tries a reverse paddle but can't connect. England have done their bit
wide yorker, clubbed down the ground, and run out looking for the second. No matter, England have posted 122, which will get a small bump for the overs-adjustment
over the wicket, full and straight, defended
round the wicket, slides on, driven off the back foot to cover
slides on at off stump, pushed through, defended back to the bowler
full outside off, left alone
first aggressive shot, a strong sweep off the stumps, out to deep backward square
full and straight, driven back past the bowler to long off
round the wicket, angled into the pads, deflects to the leg side
full at middle and leg, pushed towards mid-on
goes for a drive, skews off a thick edge backward of square on the leg side, not in control of that
worked off the hip into the square-leg area, has to get a shift on to complete the run
chopped on! Agar strikes. Angled in from round the wicket, Jones looking to play square, takes a bottom edge into the pad and back into the stumps
defended on the back foot. Very nice start from Leask
over the wicket, full outside leg, Warner falls over as he aims to work the ball way. Some swing
appeal for lbw first ball! A yorker speared in at leg stump, looked to be going down, Starc is pleading. No review from Marsh. Yeah, going well down

high the air, and taken! Huge wicket. Pushed across outside off, Warner tried to clear the off side but could only mistime it high into the high sky. The captain held his nerve underneath it. Scotland believe.
a full toss, late swing, McMullen taken a little by surprise, tries to drive and gets an inside edge into the pads
good delivery, full at off stump, defended
full at off stump, pushed to the left of mid-off to get off the mark
uses his feet, a short of a length delivery, misses and is taken on the thigh pad
what a ball! The best of Starc. Full at off stump, rapid late swing away, beats the edge of the drive and so close to taking off stump
back of a length, straight, punched into the covers
short of a length, looks to pull through the on side but plays over the top it
deep in the crease, drives square off the back foot and finds point. A superb start from Scotland
good length outside off, 138kph, driven into the covers. Tight start from Starc
round the wicket, drives a full ball to cover
super start! More late swing. Plenty of movement out there. Full outside off, goes for the drive and is well beaten
dragged down a fraction short, Marsh rocks back and pulls powerfully over midwicket
short at the body, nicely pulled backward of square
angled into the pads, deflects towards short fine leg...that was the long ball, from way behind the crease
a huge drive from Munsey, flies off a thick edge well over the slip and down to third
short outside off, can't beat the off-side ring as he square drives off the back foot
pushes this down the leg side great shot! First boundary for Scotland, and in some style. Lofts a full delivery over long-off with a drive on the up
short of a length outside off, driven over the off side, not perfectly timed and it gets hauled back
full at off stump, 129kph, driven back to the bowler
gets this one away, too short and too much width, cuts it over point
full at the stumps, squirts off a thick inside edge to deep square leg as he looks to drive
back of a length outside off, some movement, steered down to third
dragged into the leg side off another inside edge as the late swing makes it hard to drive
excellent shot, short at off stump, hardly any width but he's able to upper cut this over backward point
dropped at mid-off by Marsh! A very full ball, goes for the drive, it's quite a tough one for Marsh as he has to leapt and reach above his head. Perhaps could have moved a little better
good delivery, fuller around leg stump, Head giving himself a touch of room, plays to mid-on
full and wide, a thick-edged drive over backward point down to deep third
short outside off, gets a bottom edge on the square drive, into the pitch
short at the body, swings to the leg side, bottom hand comes off the bat
picks up a back-of-a-length delivery and pulls it high over midwicket...wasn't a bad delivery
fantastic! Brilliant from McMullen. Uses his feet, comes down the pitch, and drives high and handsome over the off side
pushed across outside off, Head tries to fetch it with a pull but swings over the top of it
another drop! A diving effort from Head, tough chance at cover. Full outside off, strongly driven and Head can't quite cling on leaping to his right
length at the stumps, Marsh heaves it over midwicket
round the wicket, clips a full delivery to mid-on
comes down the pitch, it's a short delivery, pulled to deep square leg
steps outside leg stump, opens the face and steers to short third
dropped by Jones! Round the wicket, launched miles into the air, mid-on tracks back, this was very difficult, bursts through the hands
flicked in the air, lands short of mid-on
slashes and misses outside off, over the top edge...Scotland building pressure
great shot! Munsey switches his stance and reverse sweeps over cover into the grass bank. Superb batting
full and straight, pumped down the ground, a very strong drive from Head...in the air, but perfectly placed
he's up and running...comes down the pitch and launches this over long-on. Challenge laid down
pulls a shorter delivery through square leg, the sweeper is able to get across
beats mid-on! Full at the stumps, a strong flick of the wrists sends this straight of the fielder inside the ring
full outside off, punches a drive to deep cover
taken at deep midwicket! He strikes first ball. Dropped in short, Marsh hitting into the breeze, can't get enough on the pull and it's a simple chance
full outside off, driven high in the air over cover, lands just in front of deep point running around
full and straight, worked into midwicket...nearly overthrows
short outside off, drags a pull powerfully through midwicket...pressure on Australia
a bouncer outside leg stump, Head ducks underneath, well directed and decent pace
back of a length, swings across the line and gets an inside edge into the pads
good length, straight, drives with an open face into point
low full toss wide outside off, square drives to deep point. Scotland's fifty up inside the powerplay
shuffling around the crease, was he expecting the short ball? Gets into an odd position as he plays to mid-on
nicely put away, swivels on a pull, a dragged down slower ball, places it backward of square
back of a length, gives himself a touch of room and drives to cover
short outside off, steps back and drives to deep cover
round the wicket, a short ball, Head tries to angle it down to third but is beaten
swings across the line, gets it wide of short fine leg, deep square is able to keep it to a single
short of a length into the pads, Head can't get it away
another strong shot down the ground, gets plenty of it to clear long off. With the wind.

this one is pushed down the leg side as it starts a little too straight gets this away, and all the way! Australia needed that. Short outside off, Head plays one of his favourite shots with a cut over deep point
good use of the crease, steps back to a slightly shorter delivery and square cuts through backward point
full at leg stump, clipped of the pad between deep square and deep midwicket
short again, this time cracked powerfully to cover
short outside off, a very crisp pull, doesn't land that far in front of deep midwicket
a googly, sticks in the pitch a little, McMullen manages to get it down to long on
works a full delivery into midwicket
round the wicket, pushed back to the bowler
round the wicket, tucked off the pads to deep midwicket
hammered, huge! A massive slog sweep and that's out of the ground. McMullen could be playing the innings of his life
just wide of cover! Was short and wide, Head drives off the back foot and nearly finds the fielder
driven off the back foot to deep cover
played square into the off side, pushed through by Leask
round the wicket to the left hander, way down the leg side outside leg stump again, worked off the pads to short fine leg
flicked off the pads to deep square leg
he continues to flay Australia! Another perfectly played lofted off drive, comfortably clears long off
short outside leg stump, whipped backward of square, good work by deep square leg
square drives to deep point and brings up a 26-ball fifty
dragged, and clears long on! For a second looked like he might not have got this, but Maxwell connects well enough
over the wicket, worked off the stumps into midwicket
worked through midwicket off the back foot
round the wicket, driven into the pitch and it runs towards long off

what a ball! Watt has produced a beauty! Oh boy. Round the wicket, pitches on off stump, straightens, beats the edge and takes the top of stump. In fact, Maxwell may have nicked that as well. Massive moment.
uses his feet, beaten by the turn, takes the pad into the off side
he's away straightaway, delivered from well behind the crease, Stoinis square drives and the fielder at point, Leask, dives over it. Rare mistake from Scotland
he's through the slog sweep early, takes the toe end into the off side
full at off stump, driven to long off
no problems this time! Sweeps from outside off stump and over deep square leg
punched down the ground to long off
tries again, finds deep midwicket! Touch wider from Maxwell, Munsey tried to drag it and couldn't connect well enough
slides on with the arm, pushed wide of cover
full and straight, driven back past the stumps, Zampa couldn't quite get across
round the wicket, very delicate from Stoinis as he brings out the reverse sweep and dabs it fine of short third. Lovely placement
skids on, defended on the front foot
pushed across outside off, drives and finds point
worked off the stumps straight of midwicket
short on the pads, worked through midwicket
short of a length, steered through the off side to the sweeper
driven off the back foot to cover who parries it away so allows the single
very full at off stump, drives and gets a thick edge to short third
beaten! Extra bounce, too. Goes across the right hander. Stoinis on the back foot
worked from outside off through midwicket. Tidy over from Zampa
driven carefully down to long off
Length ball turning a bit. Defended back
length ball on the stumps. Tucked away towards midwicket
backs away and carves it just over extra cover. Sweeper cuts it off. Marsh leapt and might have got fingertips on it
length but down the leg side. Needs to be bowled again length ball around off. Head arches back and smashes it through the cover region for four
length ball outside off. Dragged towards wide long-on
full around off. Head once again smashes it through covers but straight to the sweeper this time
length but sliding down the leg side down the track, gets to the pitch of the ball and lofts it over long-off, against the spin
length ball around off. Stoinis helps it towards square leg
length ball on the pads. Flicked behind square leg
length ball at the stumps. Head was looking to create room but had to defend it back towards the bowler
dragged short and Berrington forces it off the back foot through the cover region for four
length ball around off. Smashes straight to extra cover
full around off. Looks to go big but gets an inside edge onto the body
too short around off but he gets away with it as Stoinis hits it towards long-off for one

taken at short third. Tossed up wide outside off. McMullen looks to go big but gets a thick outside edge that goes behind the stumps. The ball was dying on Starc who had to dive forward to pouch it. The on-field umpire wants to confirm with the third umpire regarding the catch and replay shows it was a clean catch, comfortably
length ball around off. Head hits it towards extra cover off the back foot
length ball around off. Pulled towards long-on
length ball around off. Goes back and punches it towards long-off
length ball around off. Defended
short around off. Stoinis hits it back on the bounce but Greaves fumbles and allows a single
full around off. Blocked on the front foot
too short once again. Head was early into the pull and toe-ends it into the pitch
length outside off. Goes for the sweep but misses as the ball sneaks underneath the bat
short of length outside off. Head gets a single towards backward point
length ball outside off. Pushed towards cover-point
length ball on the pads. Flicked away for one
a thin outside edge that goes past the keeper. Short third puts in the chase to stop it just inside the boundary line
length ball around off. Pushed on the off side
length ball around off. Backs away and hits it over cover-point for a couple
long ball. Too full around off and for the second time in the match Stoinis hits that one for four. Through covers this time
length outside off. Backs away once again and hits it towards long-off. Was in the air for a bit
length outside off. Stoinis was early into the slog sweep and gets beaten
worked towards long-on for one more
goes for the fine reverse sweep and misses again
length ball on the stumps. Clears his front leg but fails to get the timing right. One more single to long-on
length outside off. Cuts it to the right of backward point where Leask makes a diving stop
another attempted reverse hit. Stoinis gets some bat on it for a single to short third
full outside off. Berrington goes for the drive but misses
full on the stumps. Defended back
full outside off and Berrington manages an outside edge, which is just enough to beat deep third
length ball. Worked towards long-off
once again on the fuller side around off. Cross hits it hard through extra cover but this one just slows down as it nears the boundary line
that's some timing. A length ball around off. Stoinis goes for the reverse again but this time focused on timing than power and sent over backward point
short of length outside off. Berrington arches back and uppercuts it but deep third makes sure there's only one run available
back-to-back sixes. Full around off and Stoinis goes straight down the ground, and all the way
full on the stumps. Backs away and pushes it towards extra cover
a length ball around off and Stoinis once again helps it over backward point with a reverse hit. Four this time
lucky to end the over with a six. Was a short ball from Starc that Cross pulled towards fine leg. Zampa dived to his left but not only he dropped the catch but also parried it over the boundary line
length ball on the stumps. Worked behind square leg
Another drop. Short of length outside off and spinning in. The batter goes for the cut but fails to keep it down. Marsh at extra cover dives forward but ends up grassing it
full around off and Stoinis goes down the ground. Not the power he intended but it bisected long-on and long-off for four

an appeal for lbw, denied. A late decision from Australia to review it. The batter had moved across to sweep it and replay shows the ball had brushed the glove. Nothing going Australia's way at the moment
another boundary. Full outside off and Stoinis throws his bat at it. Gets a thick outside edge between the keeper and short third

Finally a wicket. And off a full toss, too! Was a knuckle ball from Maxwell. Cross backs away but ends up hitting it to deep midwicket. Was hit against the breeze. The umpires are checking for the height and it seems fine
length outside off. Stoinis pushes it tentatively but just clears the cover fielder
short of length around off. Cuts it towards deep extra
length ball in the channel. Head goes for the cut and misses
full around off. Flicked towards deep midwicket
fifty for Head. Pushes a length ball down the ground
floated around off. Leask hits it back towards the bowler who makes a partial stop that is enough to prevent a single
Berrington slogs it over deep midwicket. Was full outside off but wind came to aid the batter as he went for the sweep
launched into the stands. A short ball on the stumps and Head helps himself to a six
length outside off. Cuts it towards deep point
another six. This could end soon. Full outside off. Head moves across and smashes it over long-on
a full toss around off. Hit along the ground towards long-on
full but way too outside off third six in as many legal deliveries. Full outside off and Head goes after it, clears the long-off boundary with ease. Head into overdrive
another full toss. Mistimed towards long-on
it's all happening. Full around off. Head looks for the fourth six of the over but ends up hitting straight to long-off. Couldn't really get under the ball for the required elevation
full outside off. Goes for the sweep but gets an under-edge towards short fine leg
short ball around off. Pulled in front of square for one
length outside off. Cut towards deep point for one more
short of length outside off and Stoinis helps it over backward point for four. A big, big over as Stoinis brings up his fifty, off 25 balls
full outside off. David drags it towards short fine leg
down the ground and hits it towards long-on for one
way too outside off even though David was moving across too full around off. Digs it out towards long-off
a slower length ball. Leask was looking to back away and work it towards the off side but fails to connect
length ball outside off. Stoinis fails to connect the reverse shot
full on the stumps. Hits it down the ground. Starc at long-on dives to his left to make the stop
full around off and Stoinis powers it down the ground for four. 150 comes up for Australia
a slower short ball. Leask was too early into his pull and gets beaten
reverse swept over backward point. Four more. Stoinis is making it look too easy
Ellis picks up his first. Full and straight. Leask goes aerial but doesn't get the required distance behind it. A simple catch for Starc at long-on
bowled 'im. Is there a twist here? Full and straight. Stoinis went for another reverse lap but missed and got bowled
a slower length ball. Opens the face of the bat to work it towards point
full around off. Driven towards long-on
starts with a dot. A length ball around off. David ends up pushing it back towards the bowler who dives forward but it lands just short of him
full around off. Slog-swept towards deep midwicket but will get only one
short at the stumps and David pulls it fine. Picks up a boundary to fine leg
was shaping up to play a slog sweep but Zampa bowled it wide outside off. Greaves had to change his shot, opens the face to work it towards short third
a full toss spraying down the leg side. Don't think David got any bat on it but it brushed the thigh pad and went for four
Gone with the wind! A length ball around off and Berrington slogs it over deep midwicket. A much-needed hit
wheels are coming off. A short ball at the batter. David backs away and forehands it over cover for four more. A run a ball required now
full on the stumps. Digs it out towards long-on
length ball at the stumps. Flicked towards deep midwicket
full around off. Nudged towards mid-on and they come back for the second as the fielder runs in from the boundary
full around off. Wade goes down and sweeps it towards square leg. He took off for a single only for David to send him back. The fielder attempted a direct hit but missed
full on the stumps. Berrington opens the face of the bat to work it square of the wicket
full outside off. David throws his bat at it and gets a thick outside edge. Short third makes a diving stop to his right
full but way down the leg side. Greaves was moving across to scoop it but fails to connect a full toss around off. Pushed towards extra cover
length ball down the leg side. Wade works it towards square leg for two
another low full toss. Pushed towards sweeper cover
a length ball angling across. Wade went for the reverse hit but missed
a slower length ball outside off. Greaves gets beaten by lack of pace as he looks to hit it on the leg side
short and pulled down towards deep-backward square leg

full on the stumps. Greaves backs away and hits it behind point, and he dives back for the second. We are going upstairs as it looked like Greaves dived too early but replay shows he just managed to get inside before Wade removed the bails
a juicy full toss but David fails to put it away. A fumble at deep square leg though allows him to come back for a second
a short ball to end the over. Greaves fails to connect the pull
full but way outside off. Left alone length outside off. Smashed straight back towards the bowler who gets a hand on it but cannot stop the single
in the blockhole. David works it towards long-on
that will help - full and way too wide outside off a slower length ball wide outside off. Berrington gets it towards short third off the toe end of the bat
length ball around off. Mistimed towards long-on
full around off. Flicked towards deep midwicket
length ball around off. David launches it towards midwicket. Sole moves to his right and get under it, but ends up dropping it. Was never steady but what a time to drop a catch. Score are level
a low full toss outside off. Dragged towards long-on and they sprint back for the second
That's it. Scotland have been knocked out. England are through to Super Eight. It was in the slot, full on off and middle and David smashes it over deep midwicket
a bouncer. Pulled down towards deep square leg
full outside off. Was a slower one. Greaves looked to smash it down the ground but missed

full and wide outside off. Berrington was always coming for a bye and guess what it's been called a wide too. So that's two runs to Scotland. Wade did throw it to the bowler but he fumbled the throw full and wide. Berrington takes it on the full and steers it towards backward point
beats the outside edge with a ripper! Lovely shape away that has Rizwan feeling for the ball outside off.
goes full, hint of swing back on off, Balbirnie pushes into the covers
chips down the track and belts him back past the bowler. Adair is lucky he didn't get a hand to that, it was struck really hard. Aggression straightaway from Rizwan
back of a length, snaking down the line of leg stump, beats him on the inside and hits the back leg. Shaheen likes but Chris Gaffaney isn't interested. Slightly high and leg side
pushed towards point, looks for a single but is sent back

vicious inswinger, castled! Shaheen strikes with his third ball, a peach of a delivery coming back in to beat Balibirnie's on-the-up drive and hit the top of off stump. Loose from the batter, but a lovely sight for a left-arm quickie
that is a corker again! Full and gets it to move late from a fourth-stump line, Rizwan's beaten by the late movement.
back of a length, chopped down past the leg stump... could have gone anywhere but Tucker picks up Ireland's first runs
hops back and across as he turns this short of length ball into the leg side

angling across, nicks him off! Two in the over for Shaheen, who turns and blows a kiss, arms outstretched. Pakistan have located their mojo this morning, never mind how dismal the campaign has been. Scrambled seam, pitched up and tempting the drive, brings an audible edge through to Rizwan
full on the pads, flicked straight to midwicket. Good comeback after going for a boundary early in the over.

fiendish line, jagging back again on off stump, ends up in the keeper's gloves. Big appeal for something - caught behind surely, lbw maybe - and Babar reviews. But UltraEdge shows Tector hasn't hit it, beaten on the inside edge, and the ball is missing the stumps on ball-tracking. So Shaheen is denied a third wicket in the opening over of the match!
full and shaping away from off-stump, shows the full face of the bat as he defends bsck
pitched up, sliding across the right-hander from over the wicket, Stirling dabs one into the covers
beaten as he looks to slash this up and over cover
Tector lets this one go in the channel
solidly defend this away-going length delivery to point
pitched up, shaping a touch, Tector flicks and deflects one off the pads. Amir appeals but I think that pitched outside leg

the nonchalance, the style and swagger - all very attractive. The no-look flick up and over square leg, ended up getting more elevation than distance, and on this slow outfield the ball plonks close to the boundary.

big appeal and Stirling walks! He charged down and just keeps going, as Amir runs off arms outspread. Tried to put some pressure back on the bowler, but Amir responded by dropping short. Stirling threw the bat anyway but could only manage a thin top edge through to Rizwan
chipped, but just short of mid-on. Checked his shot at the last moment.
excellent length, shaping back in, Campher inside-edges it fine for four! First boundary of the Ireland innings, although he had little idea about it
feels for a delivery that nibbles away off the seam from outside off, lucky not to nick that
Campher advances out of his crease this time, beaten by a big inswinger
tucked away neatly towards deep backward square
Afridi loses his run and then his radar to start the second, sprayed across towards the off-side tramlines good length, 135kph/83mph in the channel, this goes on with the arm past a tentative prod
beats the outside edge as he slants one across the left-hander. Excellent control from Adair. getting it to dart and zip away

big inswinger, 140kph on the stumps, Campher takes it on the boot... Afridi is pleading for a review and Babar grants him it, despite burning one already. Was it doing too much? No doubt it beat the bat and scudded low into his left big toe. Pitched outside leg, in fact! So not much going for it in any sense. And Pakistan have no more reviews
beaten as the ball keeps a tad low. Saim was looking for the short-arm jab through midwicket
pitched up, clipped leg side... Afridi gives chase as they scurry through
throws his bat at the away-going delivery, beaten again

full, wide line, invites the drive... Tector has a flash. Was there a sound? There's some discussion about reviewing, but obviously Pakistan don't have any. And UltraEdge shows a tickle, that one would have been overturned!
gets this length ball to nip back into middle and leg as Saim bunts it to cover point
full, doesn't swing quite as much, leading edge towards mid-off

the pick-up shot for six!  Adair lands a length ball on middle and leg, Saim had decided yesterday where he was going to hit that. Clean pick up, lovely wrist work to send this soaring over deep backward square leg.

pinned him again, bullseye! Up goes the finger, now Ireland are the ones contemplating the DRS. But Tector eventually decides it's not worth his while and walks off, leaving his side four down inside three overs. Curled back a long way and eventually hit him on the heel of his back boot. Probably clipping, at worst. Update: Ball-tracking shows this one pitched outside leg, too. Tector should have reviewed!
nips back into middle and leg off a length, Rizwan is struck on the thigh pad as he tries to work it square, they get a leg bye off the deflection
play and a miss outside off, another appeal for caught behind... That was an optimistic one, though
punched straight to point
big in-dipper, beats the bat and misses leg stump as he tries to give the bowler charge
backs away and steps out to go over point, but is cramped for room as he defends
back of a length on off, 133kph./82mph and Campher chops down towards his bootstraps
swivels back and helps the pull along to beat deep backward square. Picked the length early and timed it superbly.
pitched up straight, Campher punches a thickish inside edge through midwicket for a couple
strays in line again and gets picked away through midwicket. Saim with a lovely flick of the wrists to pick the gap. Wasn't all that full mind you.
back of a length and going across, 134kph. Campher pulls without much in the way of timing, picks out midwicket
works it wide of short midwicket for a single
full outside off, this time he's across looking to scoop. Doesn't connect, which is perhaps fortunate as the ball skips through to Rizwan

way too adventurous for his own liking and Saim has to perish! Looks to heave this short of a length delivery across the line, but gets a big, fat top-edge. Tucker does well to circle underneath that as he covers some distance and keeps his eye on the ball and pouches it safely as it descends.
length ball snaking away outside off as Dockrell hangs the bat out
worked down to long leg to get off the mark
in the channel, tapped down
on the pads and Rizwan neatly tucks it away towards deep square leg for a couple
pitched up, 136kph/84mph on fourth stump, Dockrell bunts it low to mid-on
slips this length ball down leg as Rizwan looks to tickle it fine, misses into the blockhole, dug back past the bowler
full and launched! Dockrell holds the pose, down on one knee, skelped over the infield in front of point for his first runs

lucky runs into Rizwan's kitty courtesy overthrows!  squirts this to mid-off as he's squared up by this full ball that curls away, the mid-off fielder fires an overthrow at the striker's end as the ball rolls to fine leg off a deflection. Trickles to the boundary.
overpitched, and smashed through cover! Dockrell collars him again, on to the front foot, high elbow and right over the top of the shot. Races away, never mind the soggy outfield
squeezed out to mid-off again
round the wicket now, full on the stumps and clipped nicely, beats mid-on and runs away down the ground. Abbas Afridi makes up for it by giving chase all the way, though
flayed to point where a misfield gives Babar a single
back of a length on off, jabbed down into the covers
takes a step across to get inside the line and swings through the line to pick this behind at deep square. The top hand came off the bat handle as he made contact.
length ball, 136kph/84mph and steered to point. Brings a sliding stop from Shadab, and a loud call of "No!"
slips it way down leg as Rizwan attempts another pick up shot, misses neatly worked off the pads to deep square leg
steps outside leg stump, Amir goes short. Misses with a big swipe across the line
steered straight to short third man

slower ball, Dockrell is completely duped! Amir rolls his fingers over it, gets the ball to drop on the batter as he pushes out and spoons up a simple return catch. Down goes the head immediately, Ireland lose their fifth wicket inside the powerplay

caught brilliantly at fine leg as Rizwan lives by the sword and dies by it. Picks up this length ball on middle and off and whips it high. He thinks the connection is sweet enough to sail over, but Adair leaps high and takes an excellent catch with the ropes just behind him.
fired across the bows, slapped for four! Delany shuffles forward and opens the face on a drive that flies through backward point
flicked to midwicket, good one-handed stop to save a certain boundary
better length, still angling across, dabbed off the back foot to the man behind square
punched to deep point
back of a length wide of off, 136kph;/84mph loosener. Swing and a miss from Campher
drops short and slips it down leg, Babar uses the depth of the crease to pul him over short fine. Absolute dragdown
dug in short, Campher swings wildly and doesn't connect
turn and bounce off a length to square Babar up, the leading edge rolls to the off side

banged in, and swiped straight up the chimney! Campher gets bat on ball but only manages to balloon tamely to the man circling under it at midwicket. Rauf strikes with his third ball, Ireland are swimming with the Florida gators
pulled away nicely but towards deep square where Adair cuts it off
back of a length, worked away fine
cuts to deep point
short, wide of off stump, Delany throws the bat and misses
bunts it wide of point for a single
banged into the pitch, 138kph/86mph and again Delany can't connect with an attempted carve over the off side
length in the channel, punched towards cover
hits hard length as Fakhar dabs it to point

goes fuller, 136kph/84mph and shaping in to rap the front pad as Delany steps outside leg. They pinch a leg bye into the covers, despite a direct hit at the non-striker's - and despite Delany not running his bat in properly
leans forward and drives this to cover
back of a length outside off, opens the face and runs one to deep third
beaten by a skiddy bouncer on middle and leg, just a tad late on the shot
shortish, 133kph/82mph outside off, carved down to deep third off the toe end
punched to sweeper cover for a single
full, straight and flicked out to deep square leg
squeezes this to mid-on off a thickish inside edge and scampers a single
dug in and heaved away in front of deep square leg, plugs in front of the rope but they come back for three
punched to deep point for a single

drilled straight to mid-off! Fakhar wanted to go over the top, appeared as if he was trying to hit it straighter but the angle took the ball away from him and ended up slicing it a bit to the fielder.
length ball, hammered back at the bowler... Rauf does well to get a hand near it, but it well technically go down as a drop! Think the ball hit him on the wrist. He looks to be in some pain
chops it down to third man to get off the mark
short ball, hooned into the stands! Steps to leg and uses the pace on the ball, swiped up and over the LED boundary boards at deep midwicket
mistimes the drive back to the bowler
banged in, 140kph/87mph and miscued back down the track as he steps away again
the short ball gets big on Babar as he pulls, it's a miscue that dribbles wide of midwicket
slower ball, short and looping up over Delany's cross-batted swipe. Bobbles through to Rizwan
drops and runs into the off side, neatly done
back of a length and slashed, comes off a thick edge down to deep third
whips it down to long leg
goes full and straight, 141kph/88mph. Adair is across his stumps but watches it closely and nudges to midwicket

the extra bounce has done the trick! Usman is glaring at the surface and wonderinf how it kicked up the way it did. Jabs at the ball and it pops off the shoulder to point where Tector takes a dolly. Ireland have come storming back.
flighted delivery... plonked down the ground! Full and nicely in the arc for Delany to absolutely kipper an 86m six over long-on

massive appeal for lbw as Shadab's struck on the pad playing around the front pad. McCarthy was convinced this was close but bailed out of a review the moment the umpire shook his head. Good call, would've missed leg.
grips a touch, squirted towards backward point

tickled down leg! Excellent take. Not the kind of delivery you'd think would fetch a wicket. It's a leg-stump half-volley all told, a delicious little delivery to tuck into but what does Shadab do? Tickle it gently for the keeper to grab that.  Are Ireland onto something here?
defended in front of point this time, they take one as the fielder runs up
attacks the stumps with a length ball on middle, kept out
flatter, hits the pads as Adair swing across the line
driven straight to short cover
tossed up, chopped into the pitch back to the bowler
play and a miss! Imad looks to run it down and opens the bat face as the ball shapes away to beat the outside edge.
dragged-down googly, slugged over deep square leg! Rauf was the man out there and again he got a hand to it. Tough chance leaping high to his left, but goes down as another miss
slower ball, dinked into the leg side
snorter that Babar somehow manages to bail out of! Surprised by the bounce on this back of a length delivery, tried to drop his wrists and evade that, lucky break
length ball, 134kph/83mph outside off. Adair swings hard and misses
works this gently into the leg side
dug in short, top-edged for four! Sails high and wide of the keeper, but fine of deep third
toe-ends a slog down to long-on
full, another change-up but straying down leg low full toss, 140kph/87mph and swung away to deep midwicket
hammered down the ground to beat mid-on, should take some pressure off. Campher overpitched and got picked away
fired down the leg side pitched up and smoked over deep square leg! Strong base from Delany and he targets the boundary with plenty of success
hops back and dabs it to point
back of a length outside off and he drops deep to deftly guide a couple more into the deep backward point region

he's slapped this straight to point! Imad can't believe what he has done. Short, had enough width and he went after it, but it's almost as if he forgot there was a fielder there. Superb from Tector, that was travelling. Pakistan are in real trouble now.
floats it full on off, defended back
length on the stumps, 84kph and cut in front of square, straight to the covers fielder
hits hard length on middle from wide of the crease, defended back
driven into the pitch, 95kph outside off. Adair slugs a cut to the sweeper
tucks it to the vacant space at deep midwicket, excellent running

grip and bounce, popped up to point! Imad makes the breakthrough, just as this partnership was reaching ticklish territory. Delany stares at the pitch, the ball seemed to stop on him a touch as he looked to work across the line. Loopy outside edge and Shadab makes no mistake running in
driven back straight to the bowler who stops it on his followthrough
straight line with lots of overspin, hits the inside edge and ricochets into the pads going back
punches straight to point
pushed through and steered away coming across
whips it to deep square leg. Top spell from Barry McCarthy as he bowls out
slower pace, 82mph on off, defended towards backward point
back of a length, 136kph/84mph wide of off and it doesn't get up. Rizwan wrings out his hand after taking the ball on the second or third bounce
drops short and angles into middle and leg, Babar pulls to deep square
snorter, climbing outside off, Adair attempts to fend at it and narrowly avoids steering it through to Rizwan
hops back and somehow manages to scramble some bat on this short ball honing in towards his ribcage
short, 140kph/87mph and coming back in, angled away towards deep third
steered down to third man
length ball, 143kph/89mph and sliding back in with the arm, McCarthy blocks into the off side
he's picked the bones out of this pull in front of square, comes back for two
bangs it on a hard length, beats the outside edge with McCarthy attempting to prop on to the front foot
squeezes this to deep square
full, straight, 143kph/89mph and clipped neatly off the pads through midwicket for a couple
looks to take him on with the pull, picks out midwicket as he toe-ends it
whips this short of length delivery from outside off towards deep midwicket
round the wicket, tossed up and gripping a touch, Adair defends
beaten as he tries to steer that rising delivery behind point
chopped into the covers going back
slash and a miss as he sees a hint of width on that

holes out to cow corner... where two fielders collide! Shaheen Afridi holds on even as Usman Khan clatters into him. This could have been nasty, and Usman has stayed down while Adair walks from the field. Ireland lose their eighth wicket, with more than six overs still to be bowled
dabs it to backward point, looks for a single but is sent back. Pressure building
pushed through, Little is hit on the pads attempting to reverse. Heading down leg, I think
pressure-releasing boundary! It's a wild heave across the line, ends up hitting it into the gap at midwicket. Campher may have erred just a bit in length by going too full.
angled in, tucked into the leg side
beaten as he jabs at this lifter in trying to steer it behind square

steps away, misses with a big swing! McCarthy exposes his stumps and Imad duly takes up the offer to hit them. Slower pace, definitely some turn as the ball straightens into leg stump. He hadn't taken a wicket at this World Cup before today - now he has three!
fired in straight, Little bunts it for one
looks to drive on the up but the ball angles back in from around the stumps, squeezes it back off a thickish inside edge as he has no room to work with
back of a length, 137kph/85mph, White lets it go outside off
more pressure on Babar. Looks to punch it into the gap but picks out cover as the ball nips back in from around the stumps
back of a length in the channel, swing and a miss
three dots in a row! Excellent from Little. Babar looks to pull but this keeps low, mistimed to midwicket
swipes fruitlessly  in the channel
drilled into the gap at extra cover! The timing is exquisite. There was a boundary rider who got around to try and stop that but the timing was stunning.
into the pitched, 141kph/88mph and White connects for a single through cover
tickled down to fine leg
short ball, moosed through the leg side! Little sits back and clobbers four to the right of mid-on
dabs it wide of short third as they squeeze in a single
just eludes the keeper as he runs across to try and catch. Abbas mistimed the pull as it got big on him
tossed up and ripping past the bat, ends up in the hands of slip... Shadab thinks it must have hit something, but Rod Tucker isn't of the same mind. Did too much, maybe hit the back leg on its way
punches to deep point
defended, comes off an inside edge into the leg side
squeezes the drive to cover as Campher bowls yorker-length
steps out and steers one through cover point
that should release some pressure. Heaves this into the deep midwicket boundary. Solid hit. Right off the middle.
sliced, in the air briefly, runs away wide of the diving Shadab
dabs it gently down to square third
tossed up on off and patted towards cover
chipped, but lucky this doesn't carry to mid-off. Babar hit this off the top part of the bat. Spongy bounce nearly had him there.
straighter line, White gets a tickle of inside edge and Shadab again has to give chase running across to the leg side

there's an appeal for catch and the third umpire is checking to see if the ball came off the boot and back to the bowler. Abbas' eyes lit up as he went for a booming drive to this tossed up delivery.  Replays confirm the ball bounced before it hit the boot, not out it is
over the wicket, length ball speared across the right-hander, through to the keeper
full on middle and leg, pushed to short midwicket
similar line, beats another little fiddle outside off
squeezed to backward square leg for a single

short ball, comes off the body, I think, Rizwan scampers forward and takes a tumbling catch... "How was that?" he askes twice, gesturing to the umpires to check (knowing full well that Pakistan don't have any reviews). They ruse doesn't work. Definitely no bat/glove involved anyway
eased down to long-off as Babar jogs the single
in the channel, White pokes and misses again

nearly had him! Abbas has a go at that tossed up delivery, there's some sound as the keeper collects. Maybe the sound was of the bat hitting the turf. Are they going up?  It's an umpire's review.  Not out it is. Replays confirm there's no spike as ball passed the bat.
pitched up, wide line and he has a thrash at it... no contact
hit back against the turn, down to long-on
beats the edge one more time, 132kph/82mph in the channel and White fishes unsuccessfully. Maiden over - not something you usually see at this stage of the innings

appeal for lbw as Afridi gets across the stumps to sweep. He's hit on the pad but the impact may have been well outside off. Third umpire checks as Ireland review. And replays confirm impact was way outside off
goes for the yorker, 134kph/83mph on off stump. Little chops a thickish edge through to Rizwan's left
looks to pull this long-hop over midwicket, ends up chipping it over the bowler's head
short ball, smeared through midwicket! Makes room and clumps well in front of square as the sweeper attempts unsuccessfully to get around
cut away to deep point
slower ball, full length and Little waits for it, punches through the covers

heaved straight to long-on! Babar smashes his pads with the bat in frustration at the non-striker's end. Generously tossed up outside off, Abbas stepped out to clear the straight boundary but ended up dragging it to the fielder. Adair was ice cool at the ropes as he took it comfortably.
round the wicket, 140kph low full toss. White prods it into the covers
the ball spins back in sharply off a length as Shaheen goes back to defend
full on sixth stump, White ushers it through to the keeper
the wrong'un bounces appreciably, Shaheen is right back inside the crease as he defends
dinked into the covers, White keeps the strike
back of a length, beats him as White dangles his bat in the channel
squeezed down to long-on for a single
dabbed to backward point, Little wants to get on strike... and White is struggling as Shadab shies! Would have been gone by a distance with a direct hit
wow, is that the blow that seals the game?  Shaheen read the googly and took a step across to get closer to the length and swung through cleanly to hit it way over long-on
slower ball, comes out as a full toss. Little clubs into the leg side, wants a no-ball but he isn't getting one. Looks a harsh call on the replay. He also declined a run so as to keep the strike

tosses it up wide outside his hitting arc, Shaheen swings and misses dropped!  Tough chance for Stirling. Shaheen swung across the line to get a thick edge off this wrong'un, Stirling leapt high and got his fingertips to it at szlip but couldn't hold on
pace off again, smoked over long-on! Little picks it and launches on to the front foot to batter six down the ground. Brings up the Ireland 100 in the process
eased down to long-on as they jog the single
pitched up straight, 135kph and slapped back to the bowler

seals victory with a six!  Shaheen has clobbered this way over wide long-on! Once again premeditates by taking a step across and then gets down on one knee to swing it with all his might. Got it right off the middle and it sailed away.
swiped through mid-on for one
tossed up, 82kph on the stumps, Little reverse-swipes it over short third, just enough on his top edge to clear the man in the ring and they hare back for two
pushed through, attempts to reverse again, hit on the pads. Imad appeals but I think you could see all three stumps as he stepped outside leg
looped up as Little shuffles across and looks to sweep, takes it on the front pad
darted in and chopped back to the bowler
flighted, turning and bouncing through to Rizwan as Little again looks to launch a slog-sweep, fails to connect
flat on the stumps, 95kph and swatted down to long-on. Little finishes on a T20I CB as Ireland bat out their overs - something that didn't look all that likely at 32 for 6 in the seventh

gone first ball! Dream start for Nepal, and their fans are dancing in the aisles! Banged into the track first up, on middle and leg. Tanzid hares down the track, trying to smash it over mid wicket. The ball rushes onto him, though, and he is awfully late on the stroke. Splices it tamely back to Kami, and he makes no mistake. Bangladesh jolted early!
edged and four! Back of a length just outside off. Bhurtel has a very tentative prod at it and the ball flies away off the inside edge past the keeper!
back of a length on off. Nips back in with the angle and raps Shanto on the thigh pad
peach! Length just outside off. Bhurtel advances, trying to force it through the off side. The ball, though, decks back in sharply and cuts him in half
short on off. Shanto picks the length, swivels nicely and pulls it to deep backward square leg's left. Off the mark with a brace
length delivery hung up wide outside off. Swings away further and some early exercise for the umpire length outside off again. Leaves the batter and zips past the outside edge as Bhurtel wafts at it
hard length on off. Shanto hops up onto his toes and works it towards deep square leg
length outside off. Bhurtel presses half forward and defends towards backward point
length in the channel. A hint of shape away and Litton covers that swing, defending it right under his eyes
full and wide outside off again. More swing away from Bhurtel and he fails to lay bat on ball

a delayed appeal, but given by the umpire! Fullish on middle and leg, and this seems to curve away late. Litton, having taken a step down the track, plays all around it and gets pinned on the pads. Kami is not overly convinced but appeals anyway, and his appeal is upheld. Litton, though, wants to have another look. Was it sliding down? It did swing away but it did not necessarily nip away. No bat involved but Ball Tracking reckons it would have slipped down leg. Litton stays!
length in the sixth stump channel. Bhurtel goes feeling for it and sees the ball sneak past the outside edge
back of a length on off. Shanto goes back and turns it into the mid wicket region
hard length just outside off. A bit of extra bounce and Aasif has to get up on his toes to fend it
shortish outside off. Litton stays back and times it sweetly through backward point. Kami gives chase, puts in a sprawling dive and pulls it back into play. Superb effort!
back of a length on off. Aasif gets behind the line and blocks. That hit very high on the bat, though

does him all ends up! Tossed up beautifully on a fullish length just outside off. Shanto is beaten in the air completely and goes searching for it way in front of his pad. The ball drops on him and then continues with the arm. Shanto played for the turn too and left a gap between bat and pad. The ball burst through to strike timber, and Bangladesh are now two down!
ouch! Shortish just outside off and this jags back sharply. Aasif does not account for the inward movement and the ball crashes into his helmet
off the mark in style! Tossed up on a length outside off. Shakib presses forward, stays on top of the bounce and cracks it to cover point's right!
hard length on middle and off. Aasif gets up on his toes and defends
shorter outside off. This grips in the surface and bounces extra, going past Shakib's attempted cut
back of a length outside off. Aasif has a massive mow across the line and misses the ball by a fair distance
back of a length outside off. This skids on and Shakib jabs it towards point
off the mark finally! Shortish on middle and leg. Aasif clears his front leg and swings for the hills. Muscles it away behind square for four!
hard length on middle and off. Sticks in the surface and Litton chips it into the vacant spaces in the mid wicket region
back of a length on middle and leg. Seams back into Bhurtel and he cops a blow on the body
slanted in on a length on middle and leg. Comes back in with the angle and thuds into Shakib's thigh pad as he misses his flick

cleans him up with a full toss! Full toss that starts on off stump and curves away. Bhurtel looks to drive but is beaten by the late movement away from him. Connects with fresh air and the ball kisses the outside of off stump. Bhurtel cannot believe he has missed it, but that is the early breakthrough Bangladesh would have been after!
dug into the track outside off. Shakib decides to get out of the way early and does so

thumped on the back shoulder! Back of a length just outside off. Sah goes at it with relatively low hands and the extra bounce means he wears a blow on the body. Tanzim with a few words of advice for Sah too....
shortish outside off, bowled from wide of the crease. Shakib advances and drops it into the off side for a quick single

goes straight up, and Tanzim has two in the over! Fullish on off and Sah, perhaps rattled by the previous ball, tries to smack this into next week. Clinks it straight up off the toe-end and Shanto does the rest, stationed at mid off. Tanzim is jubilant; Nepal are stunned!
length outside off. Shapes away and Litton plays with the movement towards cover
back of a length outside off. Paudel goes feeling for it away from his body and is beaten on the outside
oh! Back of a length outside off. Leaves the batter late and Litton, who goes fishing at it, is beaten on the outside
hard length just outside off. Paudel gets up on his toes and defends

short outside off. Shakib cuts it towards backward point, who dives to his right and stops it partially. A bit of hesitation between the batters but the throw is wild and Shakib can make it at the bowler's end

short and wide outside off. Another fresh-air shot for Aasif but his blushes are spared by the umpire shot! Goes full outside off and Aasif cashes in. Steps into the drive and crunches it back past the bowler for four. Great chase by Shanto but he cannot rein it in
back of a length just outside off. Litton taps it gently towards extra cover

edged, and it goes through! Back of a length in the channel. Aasif gets squared up and dangles his bat at it. Flies off the outside edge and Tanzid, diving low to his right, cannot quite grab it. Was touch-and-go on whether it carried
floated up fuller outside off. Litton comes forward and pushes it towards cover
banged into the track on middle and leg. Seems to sail over the batter's head as he looks to pull but not called a wide
swing and a miss! Tossed up full outside off. Litton stretches forward, looking to go downtown. Only grabs a handful of fresh air
fortune favouring Paudel! Sharp bumper on middle and leg, and this rushes Paudel considerably. He has a swipe at it and splices it. Luckily for him, it evades Jaker at square leg
goes high up, but it lands safe! Fired in full on off. Litton moves across his stumps and brings out the sweep. Top-edges it but deep square leg cannot get around to it
that should help ease some nerves! Short, wide and punished. Aasif throws his hands at it and flays it past cover point!
finds the fence this time! Length outside off. Litton gets across his stumps again and rolls his wrists to keep the sweep down. Beats short fine leg and the sweeper on the fence!
back of a length on off. Nips back into Aasif and goes past the inside edge, hitting him on the thigh pad. A polite lbw enquiry but that was heading down leg and over the stumps
peach! Back of a length outside off. Does not come in with the angle, instead holding its line. Shakib nibbles at it and is beaten on the outside
hard length on middle and off. Paudel hops up onto his toes and blocks. Stares Tanzim down as the ball trickles towards him
hard length, angling into leg stump. Shakib is late on the flick and the ball trickles off his thigh pad into the on side

Tanzim gets Paudel, and the Nepal skipper is livid with himself! Short, wide and there to be hit. Paudel gives it the lot and laces it. The only problem, though, is that he hits it straight to Rishad at backward point, and Nepal are now three down inside the powerplay!

goes straight up, and Litton falls too! Kami keeps badgering that hard length and reaps the rewards. This is on off and Litton thinks he can swipe it away. The ball, though, holds in the surface just enough to meddle with his timing. Skews it up and the keeper calls early to complete the catch. Kami is pumped; Bangladesh in a heap of trouble!
back of a length outside off. Kisses the surface and zips off, breezing past the outside edge of Jora's bat
off the mark with a boundary! Shortish and sliding down leg. Hridoy gets inside the line and uses the pace to tickle it fine past the keeper!
back of a length just outside off. Jora jumps up onto his toes and defends
length just outside off. A hint of shape away and Hridoy comes forward to defend
dug in short outside off. Jora watches it all the way and sways out of the line of the ball
back of a length just outside off. Hridoy opens his bat face and runs it down to third man

almost! Hard length on middle and leg. Sticks in the surface and Jora closes his bat face too early. Pops up off the leading edge but does not quite carry to Tanzim. A wicket-maiden for the Bangladesh quick - his second in succession
oh dear! Back of a length outside off. Aasif uses the pace and runs it down to third man. Tanzim seems to have it under control until he is not. Goes through his legs, and Nepal have four runs!
fullish on middle and off. Hridoy walks across his stumps and plays it towards mid wicket
back of a length on off. Aasif gets behind the line and defends
back of a length on middle and leg. Hridoy manages to get inside the line but cannot beat short fine leg
back of a length outside off. Aasif gets on top of the bounce and pushes it towards cover point
shot! Length on middle and off. Hridoy picks the length early, gets down on one knee and belts it behind square for four!

taken on the second attempt! Mustafizur in on the wicket-taking act, and Nepal are going down like dominoes! Full outside off and Aasif goes after it. Gets a decent piece of it but cannot keep it down, perhaps because he is not to the pitch of it. Smashes it straight to Shakib, who cannot snaffle it on the first go but does enough on the second try. Bangladesh are favourites now!

miscues the sweep now, and Nepal have another! Bangladesh are crumbling in Kingstown! This is fuller and perhaps a touch slower on off. Hridoy goes for the slog sweep, rather than the controlled sweep behind square. The slight lack of pace, plus the hold in the surface creates the miscue and Lamichhane, circling under it at short fine leg, makes no mistake. Nepal are enjoying themselves, Bangladesh, not quite!
back of a length outside off. Malla stays in his crease and defends
length on middle and off. Mahmudullah comes half forward and defends
length in the channel outside off. Malla comes half forward and dabs it towards backward point

tossed up on a length outside off. Mahmudullah comes forward and works it into the mid wicket region. Shakib was intent on the second but was sent back by his partner, just in time. A run-out is the last thing Bangladesh need...
back of a length outside off. Grips in the surface and spins away, going past the outside edge of Mahmudullah's dab
length just outside off. Jora presses half forward and taps it gently into the off side
shortish outside off. More spin away from Mahmudullah and he taps it with soft hands
that will sting! Back of a length on off. Snakes back very sharply and it hits Jora near the ribs
deft touch! Shortish outside off again and this is a touch quicker. Mahmudullah waits for it, opens his bat face and glides it to backward point's left!
back of a length just outside off. Jora opens his bat face and dabs it down to third man
looped up on a length outside off. Prodigious turn and Mahmudullah cuts it towards deep point
fullish just outside off. Malla comes forward and plonks it towards backward point

length on middle and leg. Spins back into Shakib and he misses his flick. Goes past the thigh pad and the keeper cannot gather either. Given as byes and Shakib lets the umpire know that he is not happy with that call. To be fair to the umpire, Shakib did shuffle across a little
full and wide outside off. Malla goes searching for it and chunks it off the inside half of the bat into the on side
fired in short on off. Mahmudullah stays back and turns it towards deep mid wicket

four for Tanzim, and he has caused mayhem tonight! Short and wide outside off, very similar to the ball that got Paudel. Jora tries to keep it down but is unable to do so. Hits it straight to Rishad, who makes no mistake. Tanzim is delighted, and why shouldn't he be. He has turned this game Bangladesh's way, almost single-handedly!

oh dear, what has happened here?! Pitches on a shortish length outside off and spins back a mile to go down leg. The batter lets it go and Litton cannot get around to it either shortish outside off. Malla waits for it and guides it behind point for a couple of runs
length on off. Mahmudullah comes forward and pushes it to the edge of the ring in the mid wicket region. Paudel tears after it and prevents the possibility of a second
back of a length outside off. Malla gets right behind the line and meets it under his eyes
floated up nicely on a length outside off. Dips on Shakib late and then spins sharply past the outside edge
googly on a shortish length outside off. Malla looks for the cut but misses it completely
another vital boundary! On the shorter side outside off and there is width on offer too. Shakib waits on it and knifes it between short third and backward point!
short outside off again. Malla goes back and cuts it towards deep cover point
short outside off again. This spins away and Shakib punches it calmly to long off
back of a length on leg stump. Airee has a swing at it but does not get the purchase he is after
floated up much fuller outside off. Mahmudullah dangles his bat and jams it off the inside edge into his pads

appeal for a stumping! Tossed up on a length just outside off. Drifts in before ragging away past the outside edge. Litton was quick to whip off the bails too but reckon Airee had his back foot grounded behind the crease. The back foot is behind the crease but might have been a brief moment when it was not grounded. When the bails were dislodged, though, it was grounded and that is all that matters!
angled across the batter on a length outside off. Dabbed to backward point
back of a length outside off. Spins back into Shakib a great deal and he plays with the turn, working it between deep square leg and deep mid wicket for a brace
awful delivery to start off. Short and down leg. Malla helps it past short fine leg for a couple of runs
attempted googly on a shortish length outside off. Shakib stabs it down to long on
back of a length on leg stump. Malla goes back and eases it into the square leg region
floated up full just outside off. Mahmudullah scuffs it back to the bowler
floated up full outside off. Airee tugs at it and squirts it off the inside edge towards fine leg
lovely! Given plenty of air outside off but this is just a little over-pitched. Mahmudullah reaches out for it, gets his hands through the ball and crashes it past extra cover!
back of a length just outside off. Malla stabs it past the bowler and picks up another run
fuller and wider outside off. Driven out to deep cover point
shortish outside off. Jabbed out to deep cover point

oh dear, disastrous running between the wickets! Low full toss on middle and off. Shakib pushes it towards extra cover and sets off for the single. He then realises Jha is very close to the ball and sends Mahmudullah back, selling him down the river in the process. Mahmudullah cannot get back in time and the bowler does the rest, whipping off the bails at the non-striker's end. A hand-on-head moment for Shakib and this is just what Bangladesh did not need at this stage!
back of a length on off. Malla turns it towards short mid wicket
hard length on middle and leg. Airee gets inside the line and glances it to fine leg
full on middle and off. Jaker lunges forward and helps it round the corner towards short fine leg
banged into the track outside off. Malla watches it go through to the keeper. Called one bouncer for the over
back of a length on the stumps. Jaker works it towards deep square leg
back of a length just outside off. Malla stays back and defends
darted in on a length on middle and off. Shakib stays back and nudges it towards deep square leg
length just outside off. Malla presses half forward and pats it gently towards extra cover
back of a length on middle and leg. Skips off the surface and pops up off the thigh pad towards short mid wicket
back of a length on off, bowled from very wide of the crease. Malla plays it back to the bowler
shortish outside off. Jaker rocks back and punches it crisply past extra cover. Malla runs across to his left, puts in the dive and saves two. Another brilliant fielding effort
length just outside off. Malla presses forward and tucks it away towards deep square leg
back of a length on off. Jaker plays with the turn and glances it towards short fine leg
beauty! Fizzed through on a length just outside off. Dips on Jaker and then rags past his outside edge. Kept low too
short outside off. Spins back into Malla and he guides it towards deep point
back of a length just outside off. Jaker hangs back and jabs it past backward point for a single
ripper! Flighted up nicely on a length on middle and off. Brings Airee forward and then snakes past his outside edge
ripper! Googly on a length just outside off. Shakib does not pick it and is caught on the crease. Prods at it and is beaten all ends up
back of a length on middle and leg. Grips in the surface and spins away sharply, rapping Airee on the back thigh
floated up fuller and wider outside off. Shakib has to fetch his sweep and miscues it towards deep square leg

more prodigious turn! Back of a length just outside off. Spins a mile and beats Airee all ends up. Litton takes off the bails too, and appeals, almost forcing the square leg umpire to go upstairs. Litton waited an eternity to take off the bails but even when he did, Airee's back foot was grounded behind the crease!
tossed up on a full length on middle and leg. Drifts in before turning away. Jaker is squared up but manages to defend
back of a length just outside off. Airee accounts for the turn and drops it into the off side
flighted up full and wide outside off. Jaker wafts at it and sees the ball spin past the outside edge
Airee breaks the shackles! Fired in fuller and quicker on middle and leg. Airee gets down on one knee and razes it behind square on the leg side!
floated up full on off. Malla comes forward and flicks it to long on
back of a length just outside off. Shakib waits for it in his crease and meets the ball right under his eyes
back of a length on middle and off. Airee lets the ball come to him before helping it round the corner
shorter outside off. Shakib punches it uppishly towards long off
length just outside off. Malla stays back and plays it towards short mid wicket
length on middle and off. Jaker lunges forward and drops it into the on side for a sharpish single
back of a length outside off. Malla dabs it towards deep point

trapped in front, and Shakib bites the dust! Fizzed through on a back of a length on middle and leg. Pitches and spins away significantly, opening Shakib up on the back foot. He tries to prod at it but is beaten by the turn, getting rapped on the pads in front of middle stump. Shakib has taken this upstairs but not sure if he will find any joy. No bat involved. Ball Tracking comes up and....three reds, with the ball smashing into middle stump. Shakib has to go, and Bangladesh are reeling now!
