back of a length on the stumps. Airee taps it back to the bowler, who misfields and parries it towards extra cover
full outside off. Tanzim comes forward and tips it into the off side. Jaker scampers across to complete the run
shortish outside off and this skids on with the angle. Airee wafts at it and misses. Punches his thigh pad in frustration
low full toss just outside off. Jaker comes forward and knocks it to long on

hung up full and wide outside off. Jaker has a massive swish at it and misses. Called a wide, though back of a length delivery that pitches outside leg and finishes outside leg. Keeps low too as Jaker helps it behind square on the leg side
full just outside off. Malla lunges forward and defends
slow and short outside off. Tanzim waits for it and jabs it out to deep cover point
full on middle and off. Malla gets forward and turns it behind square on the leg side. The throw is wild and Nepal get a buzzer
back of a length outside off. Skids on a touch quicker than Jaker expects and he is beaten for pace on the cut
back of a length just outside off. Malla goes right back and defends
length on middle and leg. Jaker plays the trajectory and hangs back. Stabs it hurriedly into the on side
back of a length just outside off. Malla meets it right under his eyes
slides this down leg. Jaker lets it go and the umpire has to indulge in some more exercise slower and shorter outside off. Jaker goes back and punches it to deep cover point

goes through everything! Tossed up wonderfully on a full length outside off. Malla looks for the drive but watches in disbelief as the ball rips past the inside edge. Litton does not read it either and Nepal get two extras
safe! Looped up full outside off. Tanzim does not quite get to the pitch of the ball and chips it, just past the fielder at short extra cover

appeal, not given! Back of a length on middle and leg. Grips and spins into Malla. He plays all around it and gets rapped on the pads but that might have been heading down leg with the turn. Replays indicate the ball would have clipped the top of leg stump, and it would have returned Umpire's Call had Bangladesh gone upstairs

another big appeal, and the finger goes up! Bangladesh seven down! Fizzed in quicker and on a full length on off. Tanzim has a huge swipe across the line and misses it completely. Gets thumped on the back leg, and that looks very out. But Tanzim has reviewed this because, well, why not. Does so just as the clock ticks down too. The only thing that could save him is impact or if the ball bounces exponentially, like it did in Miller's case a couple of days ago. Nothing on UltraEdge. Ball Tracking comes up and hang on....it shows the ball would have spun past off stump. Scratch everything that was written before because Tanzim is still around!
shortish outside off. Airee uses the pace and runs it down to third man

no need for DRS this time! This is beautiful, beautiful bowling! Superbly-disguised googly on a full length just outside off. Drops on Tanzim devilishly and he has no clue this is the wrong'un. Plays for the turn and plays down the wrong line eventually. Ball sneaks past his inside edge and thuds into the stumps. Bangladesh are seven down now, and those associated with Nepal (fans and players) are having a splash (literally in some cases too)!
back of a length just outside off. Malla waits in his crease and pokes it into the off side
full on middle and leg. Rishad has a swing at it and chunks it off the inside half of the bat towards deep square leg
shortish just outside off. Malla hops up onto his toes and glides it down to third man
fired down leg and called a wide by the umpire this is outside off and Jaker lets this go. Not a wide this time
finds the fence! Short, wide and put away. Lots of width on offer and Airee flashes hard at it, slashing it over backward point!
fuller outside off. Jaker stretches forward and smothers it
angled in on a length on off. Airee prods it just past the bowler and scampers across to the other end
full outside off. Jaker gets to the pitch of the ball and eases it to long off
hard length on middle and off. Malla gets behind the line and blocks
back of a length outside off. Jaker looks to dab it but is beaten by the fizz off the surface
short outside off. Airee cuts it towards backward point. Good stop by Rishad, diving to his right
big spin! Plenty of revs on this one and this drops on a full length on middle and off. Rips away thereafter and beats Jaker all ends up
back of a length on the stumps. Airee goes back and works it between deep mid wicket and long on. Canters back for the second
back of a length on middle and off. Jaker goes right back and defends

big appeal, not given! Darted in full on leg stump. Airee falls over while trying to flick it away and gets pinged on the pads. Seemed to be heading down leg with the angle but Shakib was quick with the "T" signal. In fact, he did not even wait for his skipper. No bat but Ball Tracking shows it would have only kissed the outside of leg stump. Umpire's Call, so Bangladesh do not lose the review!
shortish on middle and leg. Spins away and Jaker watches it right till the end, punching it off the back foot towards deep mid wicket
full just outside off. Airee plants his front foot and drills it to long off
floated up nicely on a full length outside off. Rishad has a wild slog across the line and misses. The keeper fumbles too and Bangladesh sneak in a bye
length just outside off. Malla hangs back and defends
back of a length on off. Jaker goes back and knocks it towards long on
shortish on leg stump. Malla has a swing at it but the ball only trickles off the pads towards short fine leg
back of a length on off. Malla goes back and stabs it towards short mid wicket, who puts in a dive to his right and stops the single
lobbed up full and wide outside off. Turns away sharply and rags past the outside edge of Jaker's prod

almost a run-out! Shortish outside off. Malla cuts it towards backward point. Airee wants the single but is sent back by his ball-watching partner. Airee has to bring out the dive and might have still been in trouble had Mahmudullah gathered and taken off the bails
googly on a back of a length on middle and leg. Jaker reads it very late and might have jammed it off the inside edge into his pads
Malla goes big! Given a bit of air on a length outside off, and Malla climbs into it. Gets into position for the slog sweep and smears it over wide long on!

knocks him over with the wrong'un now! 100 T20I wickets for Lamichhane, and Bangladesh sink further! Googly on a back of a length on off. Jaker, like the previous ball, does not pick it and tries to play it off the pitch. The ball, though, whizzes off the surface and spins back in, cutting Jaker in half. Pin-balls off his thigh pad into the stumps, and Nepal are just two wickets away from bowling Bangladesh out!
slow and short outside off. Malla waits for it and slaps it past extra cover. Jaker misfields on the fence but that does not cost Bangladesh
back of a length just outside off. Taskin gets behind the line and blocks
four more! Drifts onto the pads and Mahmudullah pays the price. Malla just uses the pace and glances it past Mustafizur at short fine leg!
googly on a back of a length outside off. Taskin, while staying deep in his crease, goes feeling for it and is beaten on the outside
well well! Tossed up full outside off and Malla's eyes light up. He tries to smack it into oblivion and perhaps tries to hit it too hard in the end. Only a fresh-air shot
back of a length just outside off. Taskin gets onto the back foot and pokes it into the on side

just clears the fence! Dragged down on off. Rishad sits deep in his crease and biffs it towards deep mid wicket. The fielder leaps into the air, trying to parry it back into play but fails to do so. Full marks for the effort, though, but six vital runs for Rishad and Bangladesh!
cutter on a length outside off. Airee has a huge waft at it but does not make any contact. Not sure he picked the variation either
four more!! Tossed up fuller outside off. Rishad gets down on one knee and pummels it to deep mid wicket's right. Runs are flowing for Bangladesh now!
just short! Hard length on middle and leg. Airee looks to pull but is cramped for room. Splices it towards deep square leg, where Tanzid comes hurtling in but just cannot get there
fired in very full outside off after seeing Rishad advance. He squeezes it out towards backward point and Taskin scampers through for the single
hard length just outside off. Tucks up Malla and he can only prod it towards extra cover
googly on a length on off. Taskin misses his swipe and the ball brushes the back leg, rolling away past the keeper for a leg bye

goes straight up, and Shanto holds on! Excellently-disguised cutter on a back of a length just outside off. Malla looks to go downtown but the lack of pace does for him. Shanks it and Shanto, running back from mid off, gobbles up a smart chance in front of his face. This is a massive moment in the game!
slow and short outside off. Rishad goes back and eases it to deep cover point
oh! Length just outside off. Cuts back into Jha and he gets the faintest of inside-edges onto his pads

another lbw shout, but the umpire is unmoved! Very full delivery that seems to finish on leg stump. Taskin plays all over it and gets rapped on the pads. Bhurtel is very interested and he has talked his captain into a review. This might have pitched outside leg, and the impact might have been outside leg too. No bat involved, but Ball Tracking confirms our original suspicion. Pitched outside leg, and Taskin survives!
back of a length just outside off. Skids off the surface and beats Jha for pace as he looks to cut

straight to long off! Darted in full outside off, and Rishad's eyes light up. He tries to pound it over long off but cannot get under it enough. Picks out the sweeper to perfection, and Nepal are elated. Rishad departs for 13, and Bangladesh are staring down the barrel!

Airee keeps fighting! Banged in short outside off. Airee, having advanced, jumps up onto his toes and carves it over the deep point fence. Eerily reminiscent of a stroke Airee's cricketing idol played back in the 2011 World Cup final!
arm-ball on a back of a length just outside off. Mustafizur jabs it out towards deep cover point
fullish and angling into off. Airee is squared up a touch and pokes it towards backward point
full and wide outside off. Taskin throws his hands at it and slices it towards backward point
dug into the track again, this time on middle and off. Airee swivels and pulls it towards deep square leg
back of a length outside off. Taskin has a hurried poke at it and chunks it off the inside edge into his pads
back of a length just outside off. Whistles off the surface and Jha cannot lay bat on ball
fullish just outside off. Taskin comes half forward and prods it into the mid wicket region

tame dismissal, and there will be no redemption for Jha tonight! Hard length, slanted across the batter outside off. Jha has a massive swipe across the line but the ball gets onto him much quicker than he expects. Spoons it up off the splice and Hridoy, stationed very close at extra cover, does the rest!
fired into the pads. Mustafizur misses his flick and the ball rolls away off his leg into the on side
length outside off. Kami presses half forward and laces his square drive, only to be thwarted by Rishad at backward point
into the blockhole outside off. Taskin jams down on it and digs it out towards the bowler
slower delivery on a length just outside off. Airee has an airy swish at it and gets nowhere close to the ball

banged into the track on middle and off. Taskin has a wild swipe at it and misses. Called a wide on height slips this down leg. Taskin swings and misses again but the umpire stretches out his arms for the second ball running off-pace on a length on middle and off. Taskin bunts it into the vast open spaces in the mid wicket region and dashes back for two
cutter pushed across the batter outside off. Airee continues swinging and misses for the second ball running
streaky but they all count! Yorker just outside off. Taskin stabs down on it and squirts it away off the outside edge past the keeper!
sharp bumper on middle and leg. Airee seemed to suggest he was lining up the scoop before trying to pull it. Very late on the stroke, though, and the ball whizzes past his ear
angled in on a length on the pads. Taskin misses his stroke and the ball trickles off the thigh pad towards short fine leg
another slower ball hung up on a length outside off. Airee has a wild slog at it, almost swinging himself off his feet but can only swat away a few flies
back of a length on leg stump. Nips back in with the angle and cuts Taskin in half. The keeper fumbles his collection and Mustafizur scurries through for a bye
another off-cutter on a back of a length outside off, and Airee is not learning. Swings like a rusty gate and misses
safe! In the slot just outside off. Mustafizur swings at it with all his might and gets just enough to clear the fielder running back from mid off

looks for the single, and nicks it through to Litton! A wicket-maiden. In the 19th over, and that could be that for Nepal! Sublime cutter on a length outside off. Airee has only one thing on his mind and that is a single. Tries to help it past the keeper but ends up giving Litton some catching practice. Bangladesh almost there!
four more! Length outside off. Taskin throws the plumbing at it and slices it over Lamichhane at short third man!

stumped by a country mile! Tossed up deliciously on a length on off. Kami hares down the track, aiming for the moon. Loses all shape and makes no sort of contact. Litton collects cleanly and then effects the stumping, with Kami well out of his crease. Nepal falling like a pack of cards now!
fired in full on leg stump. Taskin squirts it off the inside edge behind square on the leg side

there it is! Bangladesh march into the Super Eight, and they get to right where they want to be! A momentous day for Bangladesh, and it has come courtesy a classy bowling display in Kingstown! Back of a length on middle and leg. Skids on with the arm and traps Bohara on the thigh. He had walked across to work it to leg, and the umpire feels that is enough to give him out. Bohara has reviewed but this could be more in hope than anticipation. No bat involved, and Ball Tracking has the ball crushing leg stump!

a run out to end the innings, and that sums it all up for Bangladesh! In the slot outside off. Mustafizur sits deep in his crease and drills it straight to extra cover. Taskin calls him through for a non-existent single. Paudel fields it cleanly and then relays it to the bowler, who collects and throws it into the stumps at the bowler's end. Bangladesh bundled out for 106!
length ball outside off, shaping away, defended into the offside
good length outside off, hint of shape away. Confidently struck to the man at cover
cuts him in half with an inducker, This is in the channel, coming in off the seam, and Levitt plays at it but it misses, passing between bat and pad to the keeper

Ideal start for the Dutch! This one was a touch fuller outside off, and Nissanka goes hard at it. The shape away coaxes a big slice, which flies to the man at deep third. There's still a ton of work to be done though by the man running in, as the ball seems to hold up in the wind and go away from him late. A big dive forward though completes the catch
fullish ball on the stumps, flicked aerially to deep midwicket. They think about a second but the sweeper there gets to it smartly
back of a length on off, defended
length outside off, O'Dowd pokes it just straight of point and there's enough time to run two
short outside off, Kamindu flays at this and misses
length on about middle and off, pushed towards mid on
back of a length, but slips down leg Wide well outside off this time fuller, just outside off. Defended towards cover

back of a length in the channel, O'Down tries to clobber this over the legside, but gets only the top half of the bat to it. It clears mid on comfortably, but the fielder runs back and keeps it to two
shapes in off a good length, but just can't get the line right. Slides down leg back of a length on off, punched to the man at cover off the back foot
First runs off the bat. Turns this off break down leg, goes back and tucks it behind square for one
there's that swing first up. This is yorker length, just outside off, curving away from the right-hander. Levitt just digs it out
back of a length on off, punched back to the man at mid-off
takes a risk and it pays off. Levitt makes room, gets another delivery full on the stumps, and he carves this high over cover point with the wind, and fetches a four
length ball wide of off, eases this between cover and mid-off for one

juuuust clears fine leg! This is a full ball on the pads and Levitt flicks it, turning his wrists, and making a decent connection. It's going against the wind though, and that brings Pathum Nissanka on that boundary into the game. He leaps and gets a palm to it, but wasn't able to do anything more
short and pulled in front of square. There's a man stationed at deep midwicket
length ball, wide of off, Levitt flashes at it and misses
looks to make room as he clears that front leg. It's short of a length on off, and slapped straight at cover
length ball, a little tighter into the stumps, defended with the full face
Dutt just missing his lengths here, on the short side outside off once more. This is slashed away, but there's a man out sweeping so just the single
full, into the legs, straightening in the air. Levitt tries to whip through midwicket but doesn't connect. They run a legbye as the ball dribbles off towards point

big six with the wind firstball Full on the pads, flicked beautifully, And as it's with the wind it carries a good 1.5 metres over the rope this time. Levitt is making a charge here. fullish, outside off, Levitt tries to club it to leg, but is caught on the full at midwicket (it's a free hit though). There's a shy at the stumps, but O'Dowd has raced back after initially looking for a single.
Beats the edge! Goes across Kamindu and nips it away. Not much footwork as Mendis plays and misses
length ball just wide of off, Levitt swings and misses
short of a length outside off, cut behind point but there's a man patrolling the boundary there
shuffles down to this fullish delivery, and mistimes it to mid on, but they can run a single
very wide outside off, reaches for this and chops it into the turf for one

length ball quite wide of off, Too wide. The umpire spreads his arms boom! Netherlands are away here. This is just a powerful straight shot with that high backlift O'Dowd has. The ball was fullish and in the slot. The batter swings through the line and puts the ball 15 metres back past the rope
On the pads, but pace-off at 113kph. Mendis looks to pick this up over the onside but is way to early on the stroke. Deflects off the pads for one
length on off, driven back just past the diving bowler, but mid on collects
First boundary of the day! Short and down leg, Kusal looks to hook it and catches it high on the bat. Fine leg is in the circle though and this is well fine of him
shortish, wide of off, O'Dowd tries to chop it square but misses
good length outside off, left alone
full and straight, opens the face on the bat a touch as this drive goes to short extra cover
wide, outside off, and punished first ball. Levitt gets deep in his crease and crashes this through cover point
Top edge but safe! Nearly another! This was a short of a length, but rushed Kamindu who looks to pull this and gets a top edge that just loops over van Beek on the follow through. Close one
flat delivery, fired in at the stumps, hit right back to the bowler
fuller on off, carved towards point for one
a back-foot lofted cover drive. Levitt hops back in his stance, opens up the off side, and when he gets a flat one on the stumps, crashes it over the cover boundary for six. Spectacular shot
back of a length on the pads, tucked away through midwicket for a couple
length on the stumps, and offbreak I think. Played towards mid on for a single
good length, angled in just outside off. Kusal pushes at this as he's squared up a touch. Knocks it towards point
fullish on the stumps, driven down to long on
Short and pulled, but not timed at all. Just about clears mid-on but it doesn't have the legs to beat the man to the ropes
shortish ball, flat on the stumps, Levitt goes back and drags this to deep midwicket
full ball, wide of off, a slower one I think. Levitt doesn't quite read the pace correctly and swings and misses
Lovely drive! This was marginally too full on off, and Kamindu leans into the drive. Uppish but through extra cover
full ball on off stump, swinging away slightly. Levitt tries to blast throughoff, but gets it far enough away from the mid off fielder and gets a single
Shapes in from a good length and strikes the front pad, but crucially via the inside edge as Kamindu looks to pick this up over mid-on

O' Dowd tries the flick and he's gone! This was another slower one, I think, on about middle stump. Having seen Levitt hit a couple of boundaries with that pick-up shot, O'Dowd ventures one of his own, but he doesn't connect well, partly because of the pace. Kamindu Mendis on that deep square leg boundary , and barely has to move
good length but a little too straight, clipped through midwicket as the fielders give chase to the long boundary
fullish on the stumps to the left-hander. Flicks toward midwicket and gets a run
back of a length, pitching on middle and leg and nipping away. Opens the face and defends this towards point
fullish one on off stump, driven to mid off
short just outside off, leans back and cuts this away nicely. But there's a man stationed at the deep cover point boundary
slower one, dug into the pitch, just outside off. Levitt tries to sit back and pull it, but makes no contact with that. It bangs into his torso
Edged and safe! This was full outside off and Kusal has a swing at it. The edge is in the air but just wide of the man at short third
flatter one, lengthball, no feet movement from Vikram and he misses
Glorious! This was full and straight, and Kamindu just nonchalantly picks it up over deep square leg. With wind and 87 metres long

back of a length, slides down leg Finds the man! This was short and a touch wide, but Kamindu can only crash this straight to the man at point. He'll be very disappointed with that, but the Dutch will take them any way they come
fullish, fired in outside off, driven to mid off
full on off, punchy drive to mid-off for one
offbreak, pulls the length back and pitches outside off, turning away. Batter tries to slog sweep and misses
good length on off, pushes this towards point

stumped! Levitt runs down the track, and gets a Theekshana offbreak that keeps low, wide of off. His bat goes over the ball, and Mendis behind the stumps takes a nice low take and completes the stumping before Levitt can even bowl back
short and put away! This was a gimme, and Kusal does not waste it. Helps this on its way with a pull behind square
fullish on the pads, clipped through midwicket
full outside off, driven to the left of mid-off for one
short of a length outside off, cut into the cover
Hasaranga starts of with a flat lebgreak, which Vikram puts wide enough of mid wicket to get a single
fuller on off, again into the covers
flatter googly, Engelbrecht goes back and drags it to deep midiwcket
this one is on a good length on the stumps, comes forward to defend. Inside edge towards midwicket for one
tossed up outside the lefties' s off stm
length outside off, carved straight to point
fullish, on the stumps, flicked towards deep midwicket
full on middle and off, steps across and works this through midwicket
flatter one outside off, a googly I think. Engelbrecht goes back and clubs this back at Hasaranga, who misfields and allows a  couple
back of a length, angled in. Goes back to work this onside but only manages an inside edge on to the pads
tossed up, just outside off, and Engelbrecht brings out the big swing, striking it cleanly over long on for six. Threw everything at that, and nailed the shot
short and wide delivery to start, Vikram stands tall and crashes this over cover, and the offside sweeper has work to do, Makes a good diving save
good length on off, stays in the crease and defends this
length ball in the channel, opens the face and they get a single towards point
back of a length on off, dabbed down to third man

wow! One of the more interesting juggled catches from Kamindu Mendis running in from the deep square leg boundary. This was a short, chest-high ball from Shanaka, which Vikram tries to find a home for in the stands beyond deep square leg. Kamindu makes good ground and gets hands to it, but lets it slip through. But then it hits one thigh, then the other as he is running, and pops back up again for him to snaffle properly
short and over the shoulder, Kusal looks to hook this away but misses. One for the over signalled, very close to a wide as well
back of a length ball wide of off, opens the face and runs it to deep third
short again, this time pulled into the space at deep midwicket. Not timed though. They still manage to run three
fullish on the stumps, driven to long on
good length, slides down leg back of a length on off, slower one at 117kph, goes back and works this towards wide long-on
short ball on off stump that sits up for Scott Edwards, who hangs back and smokes it through square leg for four. A shot of authority there.
short of a length on off, but keeps low. Scuffs the pull into the onside for one
fullish ball into the pads. Engelbrecht makes room and swings but misses. It hits pad and bounces off toe the keeper
full outside off, driven past the man at extra cover for one
keeps making room to try to flay Pathirana through the offside, but the bowler follows him with a yorker and again the batter misses
straighter on a good length, pulls out the sweep. It's aerial but safe towards the man at deep midwicket

caught at long on. This was coming, you sensed. This is full, on the stumps, and Engelbrecht tries to bang him over long on this time. Doesn't get under it though, and it;s an easy catch for the fielder running in. Charith Asalanka takes it comfortably
good length just outside off, eased into the covers
fullish, swinging, right on the stumps from Pathirana. De Leeded just blocks it to leg and gets off strike, and off the mark
Delicate! This was quicker from Pringle, just outside off. DDS waits for it and deftly opens the face to guide it past short third
shortish ball outside off, slower one, with the fingers rolled over it. Edwards tries to pull but misses
back of a length on the stumps, tucked off the back foot through midwicket. They want two but the man from the deep rushes in well to keep this to just one
full, swinging in to Edwards, hitting him on the toe. There's a long, pleading appeal from Pathirana, but it's turned down. Maybe going down leg.
Short and put away! This was poor from Pringle and Kusal makes no mistake. Gets a good connection on the pull and places it nicely in front of the man at deep square leg
length on off, opens the face and punches this to the man at point
flat one, googly, outside off. Just prodded away
back of a length on off, looks to push and run but cut off by cover rushing in
legbreak, slows this down, pitches on off and beats de Leede's outside edge with the turn
short of a length, scuffed pull to the right of midwicket for one
flatter now, on off stump again, clipped to midwicket and they run two
short, as Mendis ducks under this. Wide called full outside off, driven to mid-off for a quick single

another one goes! Netherlands are nosediving here. This was a topspinner just outside off that de Leede tried to thump over the straight boundary. The overspin makes it dip and bounce, though, and it goes off the top half of the bat into the air. Asalanka, running in from long off, takes another good catch
Makes room down leg side, but van Beek follows him. Pulled down towards deep backward square leg

is that another one? I think it is! A run out or stumping? This is a googly tuning in to off stump, that van Beek tries to paddle around the corner. Gets an under edge to it though, and wickekeeper Kusal Mendis gets a pad to it, and as van Beek takes off for a single, and then turns back, has time to run the batter out. Great work from KM.
yorker on off, dug out back towards the bowler
flatter one on the stumps, hit back to the bowler
short of a length just outside off, hacked away down towards wide long-on
full delivery, but narrowly down the leg side. shortish, wide of the stumps, cut away straight of point and they take a couple
That man at long-on in action once more, this time to his left as Mendis muscles this drive down the ground. Long boundary means there's three for the taking
length ball, wide of off, Edwards thinks about throwing his bat at it and decides against last moment.
short of a length on off, mistime swipe across the line towards midwicket
stump seeking yorker headed to the base of middle, clipped through square leg for a single
Edged away for for! This was short outside off and Mendis has to reach for it, gets a thick edge on the cut that races away fine of the man at deep third
full, swinging into leg stump, dug out towards mid on
good length on the stumps, push and run towards point
full again, swinging in again, and though Edwards makes room on the off side, ends up clipping to leg again, and gets a couple to square leg
slower bouncer outside off, DDS can't connect with the uppercut
shortish, on off stump, pulls this time, again through the square leg region

And he strikes straight away! Mendis takes the bait. This was short, goading Mendis into the pull against the wind. Mendis takes it on but despite his decent connection, there's just not enough on it to clear the man at the deep square leg boundary who takes it well within the ropes
flat googly, pitching outside off and turning in, driven to long off
angled down leg, goes back and works it behind square leg for a couple
googly again, fast and just wide of off, Edwards plays at it and gets his inside edge beaten
back of a length on off, tucked towards mid-on for one
topspinner I think, slows it up and pitches it on the stumps, Edwards sweeps but can't connect. Going down leg
off break turns down leg length off break outside off, goes back and across and works it through midwicket
floated up on off, driven just wide enough of cover to steal a single
short of a length on the pads, pulled to deep square leg

stumped! Pringle runs at the bowler, who bowls a quick googly, gets the ball to dip and jive between the bat and pad. The batter is stranded way down the track, and Kusal Mendis cheekily delays the stumping a couple of seconds long enough for Pringle to look back at him. Probably could have just been merciful and sent the batter on his way there, without embarrassing him.
good length outside off, can only punch this back towards Dutt
floated up outside off, driven through cover
full ball, but fired way down leg full, swinging in slightly towards those stumps, clipped through square leg
good length on off, holds up a touch. Defended towards mid-off

length ball, on the stumps, defended back to the bowler after a shuffle down the pitch. Thushara picks it up and attempts to throw stumps down, but only hits Edwards in the body. Pretty good natured though.
back of a length, tucked off the hips behind square leg
short, slower ball, wide of off. Edwards waits for it and chops it to deep point
picked up over mid-on! This was a good length around off, but DDS stands tall and just lofts it over the man in the circle

had all three stumps to aim at and missed! Thushara had all the time in the world. Dutt had bunted this length ball just wide of the pitch, but Edwards had taken off and was two thirds down the pitch by the time Thushara collected. But the bowler missed with his throw. They take an overthrow
And now to deep square leg! Short and pulled with the wind, beats the boundary rider with ease
fullish on the stumps, flicked through square leg.
Oof, even better! DDS has woken up! Another short one, and this one pulled with disdain in front of deep midwicket. Flat six
fired down the legside again. short ball just wide of off, Dutt leans back and ramps it towards deep third, who fields it on a couple of bounces
short of a length, controlled pull down to deep midwicket
back of a length on off, goes back and nurdles this through midwicket
flat and fast outside off, stroked to deep cover
back of a length on the stumps, goes back and knocks this down to long-on
tossed up just wide of off, swept hard along the ground square of deep midwicket
back of a length on the stumps, goes back and eases this in front of square leg for another single
backs off to make space, but Hasaranga follows him with a googly, and Edwards can only hit that back to the bowler
Big, big six! Dutt misses the length, and Asalanka finds the wind! Pulls this with the breeze and it sails over deep midwicket
tossed up on the stumps, driven to long on
good length on off, defended into the offside
nicely-struck sweep. This was fast, and flattish on leg stump. Dutt gets low and sweeps behind square, making a nice connection

Leading edge for four! This one beats Asalanka but it's runs nonetheless! Angled in on middle and leg, the left hander looks to work it onside but the edge takes it fine past short third and it races away on this pretty quick outfield
runs at the bowler this time, and although he doesn't get to the pitch of this delivery, manages to drag it through deep midwicket

off stump is flat on the ground! This was a length ball, shaping in, pitching on off and coming in to take the top of the stumps. Dutt made room and tried to flay Pathirana through the offside, but couldn't handle the pace
full on middle and leg, clears the front foot and whips this towards deep midwicket
full ball, right into the heel, hits van Meekeren low on the pads and goes towards fine leg
full and very wide, sliced over point for a couple
fullish ball on the stumps, clipped nicely through fine leg for a single
back of a length on off, chipped to the left of Pringle for one
yorker, wide of off, swinging in. Batter tries to chop down on it and misses

This time DDS doesn't find the connection! Looks for the slog sweep, but there's just enough turn and bounce to ensure the timing isn't quite there. Ends up going high rather than far as the man at deep midwicket rushes in, circles under and holds on well
slower one, just on off stump, full. Pushed to cover
good length outside off, looks to push and run but Mathews turns Asalanka back
length ball wide of off, Meekeren throws his bat at it and gets an outside edge that runs to deep third
back of a length on the stumps, tucked onside for one
length outside off, leans back and punches this into the covers for one
flatter ball, but turning, a play and a miss outside off stump

Grassed! This was dug in and Mathews goes for a wild hack across the line. It's a top edge that the fielder at midwicket just can't hold on to despite the dive. It pops out as his elbows hit the ground
fuller one, fired down leg flatter again, turning in, and Meekeren gets and outside edge that squirts to point and they can take a single
length ball, tucked onside for one
offbreak again, which Edwards tries to reverse sweep but it goes off his under edge just past off stump and between Kusal Mendis' legs. They can take a run

Swings across the line and misses. Stifled appeal for leg before as this seemed to have struck the dimunitive Asalanka on the back leg. Umpire says too high but Netherlands review. Close one as it's umpire's call on the wickets.
fired in outside off, pushed to point again
On the roof! This one just keeps going, and going, and going! It was short and Asalanka pulls it high and far, as it keeps soaring with the breeze

Shanaka has misjudged that one. This is slog swept from Edwards, with the wind. Shanaka would have been in the game had he read the ball's trajectory, but ends up only making a late charge at the ball at the deep midwicket boundary, and couldn't get a hand on it. Clears the boundary rope by about 50 centimetres.
Full outside off, another one that's in the air but this time no timing. Comes off the toe-end of the bat but falls safe as the man at long-on has a long way to run in to reach this
flat outside off, played into the deep on the offisde

Not a lot for Netherlands to gain, but Edwards is playing a nice innings here. This is full, wide of off, and Edwards crashes his bat down on it and gets it to scream away behind square on the off side for four
full on the stumps, worked towards midwicket

slower bouncer, and that does it for Edwards. Nice bit of bowling from Thushara. This is dug into the pitch with fingers rolled over, and Edwards tries to pull, but is very early on the shot, and hives a nice catch midwicket, who takes it at chest height. Easy catch

Incredible work by Engelbrecht! This was a full toss that was destined to go all the way, but Engelbrecht has leapt one-handed at the deep midwicket boundary and dragged this one back in. Unreal, as he holds on and then flicks it into play behind his back as he himself plummets over the ropes
fullish outside off, just pushed into the offside, wide enough of the point fielder
No saving this though! Tosses up and dispatched down the ground and all the way

given lbw! But was there bat on that? Van Meekeren reviews immediately. There doesn't seem to be bat, and van Meekeren was only reviewing because they had reviews to spare. It looked plumb initially. This was swinging in to middle, was very full, and smashed the batter on what would have been his front pad, only he'd switched legs as he attempted to play a scoop. As plumb as it gets, really.
length outside off, chopped past the keeper into the turf for one
Swept with the wind! Gets under this well and wallops this over deep square leg. Sri Lanka have upped the ante here
Four more! This was tossed up, Mathews leans back and shovels this down the ground. Couple bounces and over the ropes, no chance for long-on
Wide yorker, but can't quite keep it within the lines Launched over wide long-off! This was a wide full toss and Asalanka connects with it sweetly
And again! This time it's wide and in the slot, and once more Asalanka just swings through the line and over long-off

But third time is not the charm! Asalanka's lovely innings comes to an end. Another wide one in the slot, but this time Asalanka slices it squarer and into the breeze. It holds up as the man at extra cover (who had just been moved there) comes in and takes a comfortable catch
Shanaka's dismal tournament continues! Back of a length on off, it nips in and cramps Shanaka for room. He looks to run this down to third man but only manages a faint tickle through to the keeper

back of a length on the stumps, goes back and tucks this to the vacant midwicket region. They run hard and come through for the second. They quickly check for a run out at the bowler's end, but Mathews is safe
carved over short third! This was full outside off and Hasaranga deliberately opens the face on this and carves it in the air. Just about clears the man as four more gets added to the total
back of a length on off, worked through midwicket for a couple
slower ball around off, dragged to deep midwicket for a couple more
short around chest high, gloves this pull into the ground but not past the keeper
Walloped over deep midwicket! This was short on off, Mathews stays on the front foot, flicks the back leg back and just tonks this pull over the midwicket boundary
slower and shorter outside off, Mathews waits and waits for this but only manages to chop it into the turf
wide full toss but slow, dragged towards deep midwicket for another couple
Smoked over cover! Pringle is on the ropes, but he initially runs in before realising that he's misjudged it completely. Sails over in the end
Clobbered down the ground! Clears that front leg, gets low and under it, and just launches this slightly fuller one straight back over the bowler
makes room once more, but van Beek gets this full on leg stump. Low full toss in fact, as Hasaranga carves this into the covers
full on middle and leg, whipped in the air to deep midwicket. Almost a miscommunication but they settle on a single
slower length ball outside off, picked up over point for another single

Picked up towards cow corner! But Vikramjit running to his right from long-on does extremely well to flick this in before he himself ends up over the ropes. Saves two runs there as Sri Lanka end on 201 for 6
tight line, hint of inswing, a respectful block on the front foot to launch the chase
Full, swinging, front pad in the sights but defended out into the covers - and they even pinch a sharp single

caught behind! Wow! Finn Allen throws the bat at a hint of width, there's an audible snick as the ball keeps low outside off, and the keeper scoops it up! Umpire Reiffel waits for a beat and sticks up the finger. The third umpire confirms it's carried off an under-edge!
Bit of shape away from the left-hander, but no real bounce through to the keeper, who has to go down to claim on the second bounce
full length, shape through the air, Ravindra blocks with an angled bat to the cordon
No real swing, into the pads. Chance of a leg bye? Nope, Ravindra swoops from forward square leg
attacking length from over the wicket, hits the splice and deflects out to point. This is a very tidy start
More swing, very full, defended back to Boult
back of a length, nips away outside off, Ravindra drives but can't time his stroke into the covers
Shorter length, catching Vala unawares as he defends into his pads and falls over a touch to the off side. Almost plays on
steps into the length, drags a single out to square leg with a full-blooded swing through the line. Very tidy start!
Another straighter one at the hip - Boult not quite got his radar to the leftie - and a leg bye is taken to square leg
full face of the bat, punched into the covers, good sharp fielding keeping NZ honest
Movement through the air but very wide from Southee. Vala has a flourish at it but can't quite reach
width, from back of a length, under-edged on the cut. It's proving hard to line up the medium pace on this surface
Late movement into the right-hander from over the wicket. Too much, as it happens, allowing a leg bye to be taken into midwicket. A quick one, by the way - smart calling from these two
tighter line, keeps low as it zeroes in on off stump. Fended back to the bowler with a jab of the hands

Skewed high and into the hands of Phillips at backward point! Late swing again, by which point Ura has already decided to target that leg side boundary. Alas, a leading edge sends it skywards in the opposite direction.
genuine edge, and just wide of the keeper! Leans forward, there's half a bat's width of wobble off the pitch, and so close to the outstretched glove!
Outside off, left alone as Amini has a sighter
on the back foot, punched back down the pitch with one hand coming off the bat
Thick inside edge... and that's PNG's first boundary of the innings! Very lucky considering that almost shaved leg stump with Amini looking to drive through cover
nip from a very good length, drawing an awkward block back down the line. NZ not having things their own way in the powerplay
That's a better drive, but straight to the fielder at cover
round the wicket, punched off the back foot to long-off
Full, Boult-esque, takes a thick outside edge along the deck to point
poked into the leg-side, pops a touch off a good length as Conway leans forward
Play and a miss! Lovely shape once more, Vala offers the bat but gets nothing but air as the ball dies on its way through to Conway
beats everything! Lovely length, angling in, gripping and bouncing off the pitch, through the stance and past the keeper!
Same again, this time movement off the seam as Boult hits his length a little harder
chopped into the off side off the back foot
Driven down the ground! Gloriously so by thePNG captain, who steps at Boult and drives on the up over the other set of stumps
slides back and across, punched into the covers with a high elbow
Top edge... and safe. Very safe, as Fine leg trots in to collect on the floor. Well-directed bouncer from Boult, flapped at by Vala
head over the ball, nudged to the on-side
And now no bounce whatsoever! Outside off, into a good length, two bounces through to the keeper...
tight lines from over the wicket, just back of a length, tapped off the pads to the on-side
Vala on the charge again, trying to hack a Southee length ball across the line. No dice...
uses his feet emphatically! Flicked on the up over midwicket, NZ are ahead on DLS!
Length across Vala, into a fourth stump line. Attempts a cut but gets his timing all wrong and ends up skewing the ball into the ground
flashed on the up, out through deep third, chasing a touch of width

Similar delivery, this time Vala opens the face and guides a single to third. There's a whiff of a run out chance as gully - Phillips - fields but he ends up taking a chunk out of the outfield as he tries to turn and can't keep his balance to throw at the stumps
high elbow, poked back down the track, past the bowler
Full, pushed back to the bowler
full length, driven off an inside-edge to midwicket
Wide down the off side as Southee tries to get one to hold its line across the leftie. Starts it too far across though Driven nicely, though not quite out of the screws, straight to cover
head over the ball and blocked back down the pitch
Bit of width, thrashed through the off side but no dice once more, hitting the first of two fielders stationed in the ring at cover

lofted out to deep midwicket! Ravindra took the aggressive route, stepping down the track, looking for the launch off the pads, but he didn't get enough of it, and that plopped invitingly into Kamea's grasp!
... and he strikes first ball! Vala's keen to drive, and the length is there but not enough convinction. Edges to a wide first slip! Bit of extra bounce in there, too
on the pads, deflected behind square with half an appeal for lbw. Pitched outside leg either way

Full and on the stumps, skewed out into the off side where Phillips swoops from backward point and almost catches the nonstriker short of his ground! Throw just misses but would have been very, very interesting...
loopy slower ball, right up to the blockhole, draws a measured drive into the covers
Big bounce again, this just full of a good length, through to the keeper
attacking the pads on a full length, clipped to mid-on on the front foot
Play and miss! Gets big off a length, across the left-hander, who follows it
pops from a good length, Conway comes forward but is rapped on the gloves as the ball deflects down into the off side
This one leaps at Bau, who does well to get his hands up to his throat and keep the ball down
steps into the length ball but Morea sees him coming and drags it back a touch. Another wonderful over. New Zealand are being made to sweat it out for the moment
Flashing drive! Was there a noise? Maybe my speakers are playing tricks on me. Either way, no un
back of a length, wide line, a toe-ended cut into the off side
Driven out into the covers, and this one has found one of the few gaps in the region allowing Amini to pocked a single
soft hands on an off-stump line, fended down to deep third off a thick edge
Full, late movement, slapped towards mid off for a run
one-handed wallop, up and over long-on! Conway wasn't entirely to the pitch, but committed to his stroke with the straightest of blades and hoisted it up and over
Test match length and line from Southee, leads Amini at the last moment, through to the keeper
back of a length, inside-edged to backward square
Full, just outside off, defended into the off side. Amini takes a couple of steps down with a view for a single but his partner says no
wide line again, another cut down into the off side, gathered at cover
Wide, slashed but straight into the ground. Conway gasps from behind the stumps - very close to playing on there
line  and length, left alone with the respect of a Test match. Well well...
Into the stumps, flicked to midwicket, collected on the bounce
looped up on a good length outside the left-hander's off stump. Poked out to point
Another play and miss brought on by the bounce of Ferguson
full length, a touch more width, driven with a flow of the arms to deep cover
Straight, full, thick edge onto the pads. PNG going nowhere fast...
chipped off the toes, to long-on
Big lift across the leftie, who slashes wildly at another
guided with an open face on the front foot, out to cover
Fifth stump line, Bau has another go but cannot connect
gets on top of the cut to cover
Into off stump, resolutely defended down the pitch
on the back foot, open face, guided out to backward point
Tennis ball bounce through to keeper this time, but perfectly fine as it passes the batter at a cut-able length. For the umpteenth time, Bau cannot oblige
Over the wicket, full, worked away behind square
fired in full, on the toes, flicked around the corner for a single
He's bowled him! No wait, he hasn't. Is that an appeal for LBW? IT was... but they're not reviewing it. Big sweep to a googly comes and goes. Phew, that looked very close
lovely line, just back of a length, straightens at off and keeps low. Blocked a touch awkwardly
Shorter length, Bau on the charge but nowhere near the pitch of the ball and ends up wearing it as it bounces up
full length again, blocked into the off side
Down the pitch and drives a single down to long on
fended off the toes, out to square leg
Quality sweep this time for Amini... and it's beaten Mitchell Santner at deep square leg! He had made up the ground from deep midwicket but the slide and gather went awry

round the wicket, classy drive! It needs a misfield at deep cover to reach the boundary but that was Williamson at his most sumptuous. Full length, a touch of width, drilled. And the skipper is hobbling a touch after tumbling on the rope there
Big googly... too big, in fact, as it's wided down the off side Tucked off the hip, and that's good running
on the back foot, advancing initially then forced back by the length, blocked to the on-side
very full length, wide of off, Conway stabs with an open face and point gathers
Starts over the wicket, loopy and full, worn on the pad by Bau who can't flick it away down to fine leg
bludgeoned down the ground! Not a lot of width but he climbed into it all the same, straight enough to beat mid-off. Good placement
Drops on a length, defended into the leg side
on the back foot, open face, guided down to deep third
Similar length, this time Bau plays it off the pitch on the back foot, tucking a single into the leg side
tossed up on a full length, driven with placement over timing, out to wide long-on, where it is hunted down with a long chase
Full, outside off, Amini tries to wrist this one away through midwicket but can't impart enough force in the shot
round the wicket, fizzes through with good lift past the left-hander, the keeper juggles, standing up to the stumps

Ooooo bit of a contentious single here, as Amini drives down the pitch, Santner can't dive across to stop it because the nonstriker's in the way, who ends up deflecting the ball down to long on. New Zealand don't seem that bothered to be fair
lofted down the ground! Conway's on the move now, bringing up the fifty with a high-handed swing of the blade, through the full length
Worked away behind square, but the man on the 45 is on it to prevent a single
Lovely straight-on delivery from Sodhi, out the front of the hand, beating the outside edge
on the legs, tapped out to square leg for another single
Amini picks this one better, jumping back to cut out to the man patrolling the leg side fence

pinned on the pads! Speared in on a fuller length, angled in at the left-hander, didn't get up much and this looks plumb! Just a nibble of seam movement back into the pads to miss the inside-edge. Smashing middle and leg!

Looped high - almost a moon ball - outside leg stump. Bau does to meet it on the full but ends up half-volleying it with his right foot as he dances down for the shot, and gets a leg bye away to third
round the wicket, drawing the new batter forward with a full-faced block
Flicked away into extra cover for a sharp single
short, lifting past a swish across the line!
Short and carved away through midwicket! Powerful and expertly placed by Bau, who rocks back as soon as he sees Sodhi's gone short
hits the pitch once more, good aggression to the new batter, Mitchell takes his medicine and blocks with high hands
A repeat of the shot but the ball's not quite there and Bau settles for one to wide long on
round the wicket, fended off the pads, out to backward square
Turn but into the pads, allowing the leftie to work away to square leg
wicket to wicket line, keeps a touch low, and dug out on an off-stump line
Satner slowing his action right down, looping it down off a length. Amini works it away to the leg side but mid on's lurking
stabbed back down the track once more, lifting off a good length, tight line
Bit more pace on this one and Bau plays it nicely, contorting his wrists to paddle down to third. It requires a bit of chasing from two fielders allowing the pair to come back for a third
more pop from a good length, Williamson is startled by that one, raps his gloves as he plays with a straight blade
Flatter as Amini comes down the pitch and has to make do with a bunt towards midwicket, who is up in the circle
too short and banged through square leg! Rides the bounce well
Leading edge... but safe, ballooning into point where the fielder is set far back
width, cuffed out to deep cover for a single
Another one plopped in the air... but out of harm's reach on the leg side this time
on the back foot, under-edged cut on the wide line, another single to backward square
Cutter to start? Looked it. Off-cutter to be exact, from around the wicket. No real bite off the surface as it's left alone through to the keeper
full on the pads, lofted through midwicket! Aggression from Mitchell, picking the gap well as the sweeper tracks round, but can't intercept

Ooooo that looks out... Ferguson goes at the stumps and pins the front pad low down. Umpire says not out but we're having a review...and it's confirmed - hitting middle and leg three-quarters of the way up.
fired in at the pads, chipped with the angle to the on-side
Full, on off stump, driven but with the toe of the bat, out to cover
swivels into a pull to the leg-side, one more chipped off
Swing and a miss! Decent pace - 85.2mph - skidding off a length and just past the top of off stump
misdirected, helped off the pads! Too full, angled down leg, a rare bad ball in a gutsy bowling display. Mitchell takes it down to single figures
Hacked away unconvincingly. Hiri was backing away a touch there, most of all three stumps visible...
clubbed aggressively over the covers! An over-correction from Kamea but in truth that was always going. NZ want to finish this off quickly now
Hiri on the charge! But in vain, as he gives himself too much room on the leg side while Ferguson just keeps his line outside off. A third maiden for Ferguson...
full and on the toes, clipped firmly but this time backward square is waiting to intercept
full length, round the wicket, dipping on the toes, clipped to midwicket
Bit of bounce as Bau tries to sweep. Loops in the air towards the keeper but just short
smashed up and over long-on! A big yahoo to finish, he didn't get hold of it, but it plugged out of reach of mid-on tracking back, and back they come for the winning second run
Charge and launched... straight to long on! Easy as you like for Finn Allen, and Santner, who just had to drop that on a length and wait for Bau to mistime down the ground.
Darted into the pads... just kept out!
Down leg, well-taken by Conway who wasn't helped by the lack of bounce Full, at the stumps, defended back down the pitch
Gives himself room to cut... but no dice. Weight was all over the place
Short, no bounce and cut off an inside edge to fine leg, who is up in the circle
Arrowing into off stump, just about kept out by Soper
Another dot ball for Ferguson... and he's finally hit the stumps! Does Soper for pace, angling into the stumps, bit of shape and then a helping hand from an inside edge makes a mess behind the batter
Runs in a Ferguson over! But it's leg byes as Doriga strides down the pitch and ends up wearing it on the knee roll and down to third!
Mistimed pull... but lands short of mid off!
Angled into the pads off a length, Doriga gets bat on ball but into his stumps, away into backward point
Doriga on the charge... and he can only wear it back to the bowler, And there it is! Four maidens for Lockie Ferguson!
Floated outside off, dips and turns off a length, Hiri goes to play late and misses completely
Played off the back foot, full face, into the off side
Hit high towards deep cover - nicely played, inside-out
Worked away behind point, but straight to the fielder
Attempted big heave clothed towards mid on, but the lack of timing allows these two to cross for a single

Swept high and towards the two fielders at deep midwicket... but it beats them both to reach the sponge! Almost got there on the full but lands just short. And with that, I'll take my leave and hand you back to Andrew Miller!
steps away, and laces a drive through the covers! That's magnificent hacking, away though the gap with alacrity!
splats the stumps! Boult strikes in his final T20I. Round the wicket, angled in at the top of leg, Hiri Hiri retreats to no avail
beaten with a loose drive on the up, outside off
back of a length, angled in at the top of the stumps, pressed out to point
fired in on a fuller length, round the wicket, inside-edged down into the crease. A single to complete the over
gives it the gallop, can't connect with a hack through the line, legs outside leg stump
tucked up on the hips, another deflection into the off side, a sharp single as the shy comes in

bouncer, down the leg side. A bit loose, but they all count for PNG length ball, slaps the top of leg! A nothing shot from Doriga, a swat across the line, feet sliding backwards as the bat swung through. No contact, as the stump is uprooted
tight line, blocked back down the line, right in behind the ball
cut in the air, close to point but down to deep third, reaching for a touch of width from back of a length
tight line to finish, tucked off the pads to the on-side. Southee's work is done, is it for the final time at an ICC World Cup? We can only wait and see, but what a career either way!
back of a length, on the pads, swung away through backward square! A precious boundary to PNG. Every little helps
more loop outside off, dipping on the crease and blocked
wonderful slap down the ground! Sodhi tossed it up, Vanua's eyes lit up but his base remained strong, watched it onto the blade and clean off it again!
wider line, hint of turn, can't connect on the cut
steps to the off-side, flicks to leg, a good over of progress so far
dipping on an off-stump line, open-faced push to backward point. PNG's most productive over of the innings!
round the wicket, swinging in at the toes, can't connect on a flick to leg
attempted ramp! He does well to get bat on it in the end, had he missed that would have been the most plumb lbw of all time, dead in front of middle on a yorker length
back over the wicket, pushed off the back foot to cover for a single

a swat across the line, a steepling top-edge, and Mitchell swallows the catch at midwicket! A knuckleball into the pitch, Vanua was deceived by the change of pace and the extra bounce. Boult has his second, and his 83rd in T20Is. Time for two more?
round the wicket, attacking the stumps, fenced to the on-side with a swish of blade
round the wicket, attacking the base of the stumps, poked out to point. Boult is done. He takes the plaudits from his team-mates, as one of the great champions of NZ cricket exits the world stage
A skip to the pitch, a big hack, and an edge flies past the keeper!
stumped! Tossed up outside off, dips past an aggressive charge, grips and turns past the edge, off come the bails with the batter stranded. Regulation, and PNG are all but done
tight line across the left-hander, straightens off the pitch, chopped to the on-side off the back foot
huge hack across the line, picks out Mitchell at long-on! PNG are all out for 78, a decent recovery in the end. But this won't be a significant challenge, you wouldn't think
one slip, coming around the stumps. Length ball on middle. Tapped towards the off side

Just the perfect start for West Indies and King! A delectable shot to get things going in Gros Islet. Farooqi bowls it full and tries to swing it into the right-hander. King's balance is perfect as he flicks it wide enough of mid-on. Fast outfield does the rest
Gurbaz backs away a bit. Hosein bowls a length ball on middle and leg. Sliding into him. Punched towards cover

And Farooqi returns with a wide yorker that swings in past King's jammed bat. But, uh oh, Farooqi has overstepped King moves back and across his stumps, Farooqi nails the yorker on off and middle. King can only squeeze it towards mid-on for a quick run

scuffs it straight to mid-on! Hosein bowls a fullish ball and Gurbaz comes down the track. But the ball drifts in, dips late, and Gurbaz's aggressive shot only finds the bat's toe-end. Easy catch for Russell at mid-on

What King does, Charles does too! Poor delivery to be honest. Length ball but bowled on the pads. Tried the outswinger there All Charles has to do is get enough bat, and he does that to deflect it well past short fine leg
full ball outside off but drifting in and landing on off stump. Fended carefully off the front foot
Shaping away outside off, glided to deep backward point
flatter, quicker. Short of length around off and skidding into middle. Surprises Naib. Blocked back to Akeal
Shaping in on the pads on a length, tucked away to deep midwicket. It is the bigger pocket and that allows them to rush back for the second. A direct hit at the striker's end but King is well in
a wicket maiden! Quite the way to start off in defense of 218. Length ball around off stump, and Naib tucks it back to the bowler to see the over off. Pooran runs across to Hosein for a quick chat
Slower one on a fullish length on middle and leg, King defends it back uppishly. An expensive start from Farooqi
good length ball on off stump. Blocked towards mid-on, down the v

Edge, thanks to the outswing! Charles gets away and gets four. Full and well outside off, he has a tentative poke at that. Fortunately for him, the outside edge flies away from short third and is wide enough for backward point to get to
good length ball on off. Solid followthrough for Russell, spring in his step. Ibrahim punches this towards cover point but can't beat the infield
Full and swinging away just outside off, defended from the crease
first runs for Afghanistan after nine balls. Full ball on middle, and clipped away to deep midwicket where there's lots of space

Another edge, another four. Charles makes room by backing away slightly early. Omarzai lands it on a length around off and middle, and swings it away. He goes hard at that and gets a thick outside edge to the left of short third this time
tests him with the short ball. Bangs it short around off and Ibrahim sways out of the ball's line
Angling in on the pads, tucked away through backward square leg
slower ball, rolls his fingers over this one. Fullish on off and caressed to mid-off

Knocked him over, Omarzai the King! Such a beauty to bowl early in the spell. Bowls it on a length with a wobble seam, King is unsure of coming forward or staying back. The ball goes straight on, King's half-stride works against him. He is still on the move as the ball ricochets off the inside edge to peg back middle. Afghanistan on the board early and Omarzai has his arms stretches as he runs in celebration
just three off that over. Full toss just outside off and Ibrahim knocks this mistimed drive towards mid-on for a quick single
Length delivery angling away outside off, he comes forward and defends it to cover, who dives and stops that. A successful over to start for Omarzai

first boundary of the Afghanistan innings! And this Akeal Hosein over starts in a more promising fashion for Afghanistan. Full ball outside off and still drifting in, but he keeps a steady base, lets the ball land, and then drives through the off side
Full and drifting away outside off, he places it to short cover. It was the slower one
length ball sliding into his pads from off stump. Ibrahim knocks it to the leg side, in the region of mid on's right for a single

A third four for Charles via the outside edge. Angling away on a length at 131.4kph, the width was too enticing to let go of. Charles goes hard at it away from his body again, gets a thick outside edge that beats backward point rushing to his left
full ball on middle. Bit of drift into his pads. Hurried onto a clip off his pads to square leg. Ball stays low too
A quick run. Places the length ball to Omarzai at backward point, he half-stops and they pinch a run. A direct hit at the striker's end could have been interesting...
full ball around off, and knocked off his pads to midwicket. Gently played, one collected
On a length around off, 135.3kph, opens the face to glide it towards wide short third for one
full ball outside off. Pushed to cover, one of four infielders on the offside between backward point and cover

Sprays this wide down leg from around the wicket Smartly done this time. Farooqi goes for the change-up and bowls a slower one full outside off. Charles plays the check shot, opening the face of the bat to get it between backward point and short third. The protection deep is on the leg side
quick run as Naib drills a drive to mid-off's left, forcing Russell to grab with his left hand, and delaying his release, thus allowing the single

Drilled back down! Full and straight in line of the stumps, Charles never bothers to get his front foot towards the pitch of the ball. Keeps an open stance and belts it between the non-striker and mid-on. Matt Roller had written about the time for Charles to shine, and at a venue where he has a stand named after him, he sure is putting on a show.
full ball outside off. Bit of outswing. Ibrahim reaches out to drive but misses. Through to the keeper

Goes the distance. Off the outside edge. Length ball outside off from around the stumps, Pooran goes hard and looks to heave it across the line. But gets a thick outside edge that carries well over third. The six was into the breeze, says Roller

launches it over mid off! And sends Powell for a futile chase. He makes some room and when Joseph bowls a full ball on middle, Ibrahim finds himself in a good position to loft it over the infield. Just has to be careful about the swing, as this was a touch mistimed

Pooran in his elements early. Length ball angling in at 130.3kph, he stays back, swivels and pulls it all along the ground through midwicket. What's worse, Azmat has overstepped It goes from bad to worse for Afghanistan. He goes for the bouncer but it is too short. Passes well over Pooran as well as the keeper's head The perfect yorker! But it counts for little. Omarzai nails the yorker on middle and leg, Pooran swings and misses
full ball just outside off. Bit of shape away from Ibrahim, and he misses connecting with the drive
Full length ball on leg, Pooran swings and misses. But the ball deflects off his pads and runs away to the fine leg fence
full ball on off. Ibrahim shapes up to tonk it over the bowler's head but the ball jags away after pitching. Misses it altogether

Length ball angling across Pooran, 122.4kph, he slices hard at that. Gets a thickish outside edge towards the vacant deep backward point region. Once again into the wind. It is the shorter boundary too
slices a shot towards backward point for a single
Fetch that! Full and in the slot on middle and leg. Pooran clears his front leg and thwacks it well over deep midwicket. 89m hit, thanks to the breeze
clobbered! Full ball, on the stumps, and Naib doesn't have to do much. Just relies on his hand-eye co-ordination and swings across the line to deep midwicket

Pooran power punishing Afghanistan in Gros Islet! Omarzai bowls the slower one, 119.9kph, on a length around off. Pooran just belts it over the non-striker for a maximum. The boundary there is 77m, not the shortest one but it cleared it easily. 36 runs off the over, the joint-most in T20 World Cups!
catching chance? Ibrahim gives the bowler a charge and Hosein bowls it quick, wide and full. Throws his hands at the ball, slicing a drive that whizzes just over Johnson Charles at cover point
Length ball on off, he goes back and tucks it through midwicket
slows it down. Full ball on middle and off stump. Pushed towards cover, but to the fielder
Lofted over mid-off. Floated full on middle and leg, 94.5kph, Pooran clears his front leg and only times this
Ibrahim makes room and Hosein follows him with a length ball sliding beyond leg stump and into the batter. He tucks Ibrahim up successfully, and the batter can only push it gently to cover
Tossed up again, outside leg, Pooran goes for the reverse hit but misses and it lobs off the pad
in the slot, and punished! Full ball just outside off. No real drift this time, and it's not turning either. Inside-out loft over the bowler's head

Flatter and quicker, turning down leg, he misses the flick No slip, edged away for four! Flatter and quicker, the slider perhaps that angles away. Pooran is deep in the crease and goes for the cut, but gets a thick outside edge for four
flatter, length ball on middle. Sliding into his hip. Clipped to midwicket for a quick single
Clears his front leg and hacks it to wide long-on

full ball on mdidle and leg. Tries to clip it fine, aiming for fine leg, but misses. Pooran gets a pad behind the stumps to keep it down to just one run plus the wide punchy shot through the off side, but stopped at cover point. Length ball around off stump
The googly on a length, whipped away with the turn through square leg
good length ball on off. Tries the pull but mistimed. Towards midwicket
Starts off with a length ball, angling in from wide of the crease, he misses the flick and wears it on the thigh
short of good length ball. Misdirected, sliding down leg and Ibrahim doesn't let the loose ball go. Swivels and gets an attempted pull to dribble away to fine leg for four
Sprays this wide Poor ball again. Goes wide of the crease and angles it in on a length, Charles only has to swivel and pull it wide of short fine leg
short ball, true bounce, Ibrahim gets in position early for a pull. Mistimed, as it lands behind square leg
Yorker on off, dug out towards mid-on
deposited! Easy pickings, length ball angling into his pads, and comfortably flicked off his waist, using his wrist and the bowler's pace to smack it towards fine leg
Full and outside off, lofted over covers for two
changes his line. Keeps it outside off, and Ibrahim cuts towards deep backward point for one
Full and straight on the stumps, belted straight back onto the stumps at the other end

Afghanistan 45/1 after the powerplay. Back of a length ball outside off, and Naib swings the bat across the line. Top-edge towards deep third but the ball lands a few metres short of the fielder running in
Length ball outside off, defended to the off side.
short of good length ball outside off. Solid bounce off the deck. Misses the cut. Through to Pooran
Flatter length ball on middle, he goes back and wrists it through wide mid-on

goes full on off stump, and Naib gets forward to defend, but the ball snakes past the inside-line of defense, and crashes into his pad. LBW appeal given out but Afghanistan review. The fans have already given their verdict with their fingers raised in the stands, but what does the TV umpire say? No edge, hits the back peg, and clipping the top of leg stump. Umpire's call on nicking the bail, and that's enough for Naib to continue walking back.
Flatter and angling away, 89.3kph, Charles goes back to open the face and glide it to short third
back of a length ball to welcome Omarzai. He bunts a shot off the back foot towards mid-on for a couple

Is there a tickle? Gurbaz and Noor chat for long, Rashid gets involved and then asks for the review. There was a noise as Pooran went back to tuck a length ball. But it was of the ball clipping the pad
full ball driven towards cover, but gently
Floated fuller on off, 89.4kph, flicked to long-on
length ball around off and angling in. Smartly punched through the off-side region to deep extra cover for two
Tossed up full on middle and leg, Charles takes on the longer side. Hits it on the bounce to deep midwicket
full ball around off. Ibrahim attempts to push at it, but plays it awkwardly by making his hands reach out in front. Mistimed past Motie's left
Goes back to turn it across, but only manages to get a soft leading edge back towards the bowler
Full and outside off, bowled from wide of the crease, 131.6kph, Charles goes hard at it but misses

through the batter, past the keeper! Back of a length ball around leg stump, and shapes into the batter further. Cuts the batter in half, and the late deviation forces the miss from Pooran. Four byes to start
Length ball around off, only 110.9kph that, Charles is done in by the lack of pace and is early into the shot
length ball angling across the right-hand batter, and Omarzai pounces on it, cutting it between backward point inside the circle and deep third on the boundary line
Dropped! Charles gets a life. Full and wide outside off, the slower one again, Charles reaches out and toe-end it towards cover, where Nabi leaps and only gets a hand. Hands-on-hips from Rashid there
brings the line closer to off stump now. Omarzai rises on top of this length ball to tuck a shot towards point
Powers the pull. Short ball, angling in to Charles, who backs away and pulls it in front of square on the leg side. It is the shorter side and into the breeze
full ball just outside leg stump. Ibrahim flicks it off his feel, but perhaps too languidly. Easy catch for the man lurking at deep backward square leg.
Very full outside off, once again toe-ends it to cover. Pooran was a long way down from the non-striker's end but the fielder does not throw, since there is no back-up
starts off with a length ball pushed wider outside the left-hand batter's off stump. Tries the cut but misses
Naveen strikes and Charles' charmed life ends. Another slower one around off, Charles is yet again early into the shot. Chips it towards cover, where Naib takes a good, low catch diving forward

Johnson Charles, hello there! Makes acres of space by running in at rapid pace from deep point and smartly dives forward to take a sliding catch. Najibullah chases at this short and wide ball, and goes for the cut. But he can't keep it down. Duck for him and McCoy has two in his first over
length ball outside off. Cut smartly to the off side for a single
Tossed up wide outside off, Pooran powers it to deep cover
squirted away to backward point after slicing a drive
Flatter and on a length outside off, punched to deep cover-point
full ball just outside off. Mistimed cut in front of square
Full on middle and leg, 89kph, driven to long-on
full ball on off. Quicker one and Omarzai manages to get a cut away to backward point for a single.
Deceived Pooran! Slower through the air, on a fullish length outside off and spinning away. Pooran looks to turn it across but gets a leading edge to short third
full ball on middle and leg. Nabi fends it towards the non-striker
Fuller, he gets down on his knee and sweeps it through midwicket
full ball on middle. Big stride forward and carefully blocks, ensuring the bat is behind the line in case it turns
Goes around the wicket across, and bowls it on a length, he goes back and pulls it down to long-on
cutter to start off. Length ball angling across and the ball takes the shoulder of Omarzai's bat en route to deep third. Surprised the batter there with the change of pace
On a length in line of the stumps, Hope goes back and across and flicks it through square leg

McCoy making a strong case to be a permanent member of this World Cup XI! Fullish ball on off and middle. Ball jags in this time, instead of angling across the right-hander. Nabi is in no position to play any shot, and his late attempt at a cut is totally futile, chopping the ball onto his own stumps.
Full on the pads, flicked to short third for a quick one
back of of a length ball on middle and leg. Knocked off his chest region to square leg for a quick single
Flatter and on off, presses forward and defends it to cover
full ball pitching just outside leg stump. Flicked off his heels towards midwicket for a quick single
Flatter and on a length on middle and leg, 97.5kph, goes back and wrists it through midwicket
good length ball on middle and leg stump. Worked off his waist to the leg side for a jogging single
Angles it away on a length, slower through the air at 89.9kph, punched to deep cover
back of a length ball on leg stump. Omarzai sways away from the ball's line as it goes past his helmet grille. Time for drinks
Fuller and quicker, the googly, turned to square leg
full and wide ball and cut towards point. King at point gets a hand to stop the ball's pace, and Hosein chases after the ball from backward point
Flatter and on a length outside off, 88.7kph, spinning in a touch, punched to cover
into the breeze... and all the way over wide long on. Full ball around off, and it sat up well for the strong man. Hammered across the line
Floats it up, and Hope needs no second invitation. Gets his front foot to the pitch of the ball and slogs it high and long over deep midwicket
full ball around off stump, pushed past the bowler's left to long off

Nabi comes around the wicket, it does not matter for Hope. Angled across him, it was the length ball. Hope clears his front leg and slogs it over deep midwicket again. The longer side, with the wind and it sails over
short and wide outside off. Smacked in front of square, cutting it to Powell at cover, but the captain gets his body behind the ball to intercept
Full and outside off, drilled to cover

shot of the day! Holds his pose as he lifts this checked drive over cover for six. Full ball on middle, and Omarzai got outside the ball's line to execute that shot, using the spin away from him to aid his direction
Back over the wicket, bowls a full toss on off, smashed through midwicket. Najibullah in the deep does really well to dive and stop with his left hand
full ball on middle. Omarzai lets the ball turn across him before nudging it towards cover point
Floats it fuller, low full toss, Hope toe ends it through midwicket. 15 runs off the Nabi over, is that all for him tonight?
The googly around middle, Hope makes room and eases it through cover
short ball just outside off. Cut to deep extra cover where Hope takes a tumble and roll to intercept the ball
Fuller and quicker on middle, goes back and hurriedly gets his bat down to place it through mid-on
full ball outside off stump. Angling across the batter. Tries to hammer it over cover but misses. Through to cover
