Thick inside edge. It was the one that turns in, but Hope looks to push it through cover and gets it past leg stump
back of a length slower ball. Surprises the batter as the ball ends up near his face but with almost no pace. Bunted awkwardly to the off side for a single
The googly from outside leg, Hope goes back and clips it to deep square leg
good length ball angling across and Janat tries to run it towards deep third with the bat's open face. But misses
Floated fuller around off, again the wrong'un that Pooran picks and clips across the line
slower ball again. Full on middle. Janat moves to the off-side, exposing his leg-stump in the process, and nurdles a gentle shot to the leg side for a single
Full on off and middle from around the wicket, driven down to long-off
good length ball on middle and leg stump. Pace on this time. Blocked back to the bowler
good length ball on off. Bit of turn away and tapped to the off side for a quick single. Pooran wants his fielders to up their energy

Najibullah takes a screamer and Naib strikes with his first ball. Najib made good ground to his right from deep midwicket while running in a bit, dives full length then to grab this slog sweep to end Hope's stay. Naib begins with a legcutter outside off at 100.9kph, which Hope looks to hit with the wind. But it was the longer side and he pays the price. The signature biceps pose from Naib
full ball on off stump. Driven towards cover for a single, but Powell attempts to throw the stumps down with a quick pick-up-and-release. Can't get the direct hit though
Fuller on off and middle, driven down to long-on to get going

easy catch at cover as Omarzai is out in a soft manner. Full ball on middle, and sliding into leg. Omarzai closes his bat's face to work it towards the leg side, however, that brings about his demise for the night as the ball pops up high in the air in the opposite direction.
Just short of short third as Pooran looks to cut the length ball that is angled away. Noor gets a bad bounce there and allows a run
arm ball. Good length outside off. Cut towards backward point where an acrobatic effort saves runs
Shortish and outside off, mistimes the pull through mid-on

unforced error! Full ball around off. Rashid gently taps it towards backward point and Janat is off the blocks quickly in search of a single. Rashid takes a step but turns Janat down because the single is unlikely. However, Janat has over-committed and he is too slow to turn around and return. King carefully lobs it to Hosein, and the bails are quickly dislodged at the bowler's end
Slower one, shortish as well, pulled through midwicket
length ball cut away to backward point. Akeal finishes with 4-1-21-2
Shortish, off-pace ball outside off, Powell waits a touch and delays his cut to get it wide of sweeper, as a result gets a brace
Russell returns, and starts with a slot ball just outside off. Rashid doesn't need a second invite as he scythes his bat to send the ball over cover for a one-bounce four
Floated full on the pads, whipped to short fine. Pooran comes down for a run but is sent back well in time
slower ball, full on middle and leg. Rashid clears the front leg and attempts a big shot down the V, but mistimed towards long on
Quicker legbreak, on a length around off. Pooran is unsure and gets a thick inside edge onto his back leg and towards short fine leg
length ball, fourth-stump line. Opens the bat's face and runs it down to deep third
Goes back and punches this through midwicket, Rashid himself does the fielding
pace-off delivery, fullish just outside off. Gently tapped towards the off side for a single
Lands it on a length, 90.2kph, spins away a touch, Powell goes back and clips it to deep square leg
full ball just outside off. Noor offers minimal footwork in his attempted flick from outside off stump. He's lucky his off stump is still upright
The googly on a length on middle and leg, he goes back and plays it through midwicket with soft hands to bring up his first half-century in T20 World Cups off 31 balls
full ball, yorker length on off. Noor manages to nurdle a shot towards the leg side for a single
Tosses it up full, easily knocked down to long-on

holes out at long on. Full ball around leg and Noor backs away slightly before trying to launch a big shot down the V. He doesn't have the timing to find the distance and Rutherford runs square from wide long on to complete the formalities.
Flights it full on middle, flicked to deep midwicket

bouncer?! Naveen, with no helmet, gets a rude welcome in terms of a testing line first up. He somehow manages to get his bat near his face, and manages to guide a shot awkwardly past first slip for four! Replay shows this was a back of a length delivery that zipped off the deck, generating extra bounce and surprising the batter.
Flights it full outside off, the one that spins away, Pooran goes for the slash away from the body. Gurbaz appeals and is the only one doing so
played to the off side
Quicker and fuller just outside off, Pooran looks to hack it across the line to the shorter side but only gets it off his leg to the off side
full on off. Ball stays low. Fended to the off side
Now he presses forward and pushes it towards cover-point for one
full ball darting in and Naveen presses forward to defend. Inside edge onto his pad and that saves him from an lbw
Fuller around off and middle, gets it off the inside edge through midwicket. Noor hares behind it and keeps them to one
full ball around off and fended to see the over off. Motie's figures: 4-0-28-2
Flatter and fuller around off, Pooran sits deep in the crease and defends it towards short third. Solid spell from Noor, West Indies have seen off four boundary-less overs on the trot
over the keeper for four! Short ball around off. Rashid swings his bat like a ninja and gets something - enough - off his bat to get it for four. Batter and bowler share a smile
Disdain! Such a cruel greeting from Powell. Full and in the slot from Farooqi, he does not need another invitation. Short-arm jabs it straight over the sight-screen
hits Rashid on the body as he ducks to this short ball that didn't bounce as much. Ball dribbles away  to Pooran
Around the wicket, full outside off, hammered down to long-off
length ball around off. Rashid is a tad late on his attempted pull, and mistimed to deep midwicket
Short and outside off, 112.6kph, pulled through square leg for two

the bouncer does the trick! Joseph digs it in short, and Naveen tries to duck, but doesn't really. He tries to get his glove and bat in front of his face, and the ball kisses the glove before going towards Pooran. Pooran has to put in an acrobatic jump to ensure the grab is secure.
Another slower bouncer outside off, Pooran is caught by surprise and cannot get bat to it
no run
Very full on off, steered to backward point. Good comeback this from Fazal
short ball aimed ta Fazalhaq as he backs away. Given wide but Alzarri is showing that he wants to pepper batters with the short ball fullish ball around off stump and blocked back
Very full on off again, squeezed through cover
Rashid won't go down without putting up a fight! Always intent on hitting the big shots, and he does so against Russell now. Short ball around off and crunched over deep midwicket
Bowls it wide outside off to Pooran, who lofts it to long-off on the bounce

game, set, match. West Indies win by 104 runs. Full ball around off, and Rashid tried to helicopter a six down the ground. But he ends up slicing it, and Powell at long off takes a tricky catch. West Indies finish as Group C toppers, while Afghanistan finish second. Not that it matters for the Super Eight, but definitely does for bragging rights and team morale.
Angling in on a length, swivel-whipped to deep backward square leg

A first boundary for Pooran since the fifth over. Takes full toll of a full toss angled across him. He moves back and across early and slices it through cover. Naib gets across from sweeper cover but fails to keep it in play despite the dive, and Naveen is not pleased
Deceives Pooran with a slower one, 111kph, he gets a top edge towards short third
The short ball does not take Powell by surprise. It was well directed by Naveen, but he swivels and gets a top edge over short fine leg. 124.3kph
Slower one outside off, Powell swings for the hills but misses

Floated full on leg, Pooran goes for the slog but gets hit on the back leg. Rashid appeals for lbw, but did it pitch outside leg? Rashid takes the most low-key and belated review. It did pitch outside line and spun in ever-so slightly for it to miss leg
In the slot, out of the park. Floated full on middle, Pooran clears his front leg and sends it sailing into the deep midwicket stands

A horrible misjudgement from the fielder at deep midwicket. Rashid goes full again, Pooran heaves it after clearing his front leg. Ibrahim perhaps ran in a touch while moving to his right, stretches his right hand out but makes no contact
Fifty-stand up with a massive 87m strike. Quicker one on a shortish length, allows Pooran to go back and hammer it over wide long-on
Full again, Pooran wallops it through midwicket for two

Huugggeee strike to end a 24-run over! The script going wrong for Rashid, who continues to bowl it in the slot. This is full on middle and leg, and Pooran once again clears his front leg and slogs it high and long over long-on. Is this the over that swings the game back in West Indies' favour?

Powell's power on show now. Naib goes slower one again, turns into a low full toss just outside off. But the West Indies captain manages to get underneath it and sends it sailing over the bowler's head
The legcutter comes out well now, fullish and just deviating away from Powell's arc
Skied high, taken safely! Naib's legcutter does the trick. Powell looks to tonk it long but gets a top edge. The substitute Kharoti is settled under it at backward point and makes no mistake
Just misses leg stump! Another slower one, 102.9kph, following Russel who backs away to swing across, but misses
Slower bouncer, Russell had to wait for it a bit and pulls it to deep square leg. 200 up for West Indies
Comes around the wicket and bowls another slower one, 96.4kph, full outside off, Pooran can only reach out and squeeze it to deep point

Digs it in, the slower bouncer at 114kph, but it lobs well over the batter's head. The highest total this T20 World Cup, and the highest for West Indies across editions Walloped! Full and in the slot, Pooran waits for the slower one, gets it, hammers it over the bowler's head
Pooran nears a ton, St Lucia erupts. Naveen misses the yorker, delivers a juicy full toss that is sent into the deep midwicket stands
Goes wide of the crease and bowls a slower one, full outside off, Pooran goes for the sweep but misses

A rocket throw Omarzai ends Pooran's blitz! What a throw that, flat and on the full at the striker's end. Pooran belts the slower full ball to deep cover and wants two, but it was the shorter side and Omarzai has rocket arms. Pooran stretches and dives and lies on the ground for a bit, for he knew his fate much before the big screen confirmed it. Walks back to a deserving standing ovation
Full and wide outside off, looks to go over cover but gets it off the inner edge through mid-on

Rashid grasses Russell, West Indies finish on 218 for 5. Hard length from Naveen, Russell looks to smack it over deep midwicket but gets more height than distance. Rashid covers good ground to his right from long-on but fails to hang on
Short, wide and dispatched. The intent is there from the get-go. Taylor lines Jansen up and slaps this past backward point
Hint of shape away from De Kock just outside off, he opens the face of the bat and guides to deep third
On a length on middle and leg, he works it towards midwicket and sets off
Holds its line outside off. The ball pitches on a length and continues to move straight and beats Hendricks
Hint of shape coming into Gous and strikes him high on the pad around middle
Fuller outside off, he presents the full face of the bat and drives solidly but Jones at short extra cover intercepts really well to his right
Fuller in length outside off, he drives on the up but straight to mid-off
A hint of shape into Hendricks this time around. He is up for it though as he gets half-forward and defends back to the bowler
On a length angling across Gous who shoulders arms
Through covers! Fullish in length angling across the batter who drives neatly and gets two for his efforts. The outfield is a little sluggish and Hendricks hit the ball into the wind.
Well watched again. Gets it on a length outside off. Gous watches it closely and lets the ball go through to the keeper
On a length on middle and leg, he ticks it to midwicket
Short and wide, he cuts it but straight to cover-point
On a length outside off, he drives to the right of mid-off and sets off for a quick run
BANG! Floated on off and middle. Taylor gets down on one knee and wallops him miles over deep midwicket for a six
Fuller in length on middle and leg, he works it to the left of short midwickets, who moves nicely to his left
Six and now a four! On a length on off, he sweeps, this time to the left of deep midwicket

Ooh, some steep bounce for Ali. That rears up from a length outside off. Hits the splice of Hendricks' bat as he fends it towards backward point. He sets off and I guess de Kock was caught on his heels a bit. A direct hit and he was struggling
Short, wide again, and Taylor misses out. Pummels the cut but straight to backward point

Length way down leg, he does not connect Holy moly, what a stunning save by Jahangir at backward point. Short, wide, he absolutely muscles the cut to the left of Jahangir who reacts like a gazelle, with minimum of fuss.
Flatter trajectory on the off stump, he slaps it down to long on
Fuller down leg, he clips it aerially to deep backward square leg
A hint of turn as Gous backs away to the leg side. Markram follows him, as Gous works him to the right of deep midwicket for a couple of runs
Crrrrrrunched! On a length outside off, he backs away, gives himself a little room and wallops it flat over covers for a six
Banged in short, but the line is just down leg. Called a wide Back of a length ball angling into Taylor who is rapped into the thigh pad as he looks to work this through the on-side and misses
Good length just outside off, he cuts it to deep third
Slammed up and over! Was a length ball outside off, he stands tall and thrashes this over the mid-off
Some swing for Netravalkar just outside off, Hendricks gets across and pushes towards covers
On a length down leg, called a wide Ooh, look at that carry and bounce! Banged in short outside off, the ball flies away to de Kock as Taylor misses the pull
Heaved away, not far away from Jones at midwicket. 124kph on off, he jumps down the track, is cramped for room and ends up mistiming his heave just past the fielder
Goes full now just outside off, Taylor looks to dig it out, gets a thick inside-edge past the stumps for a four

Straight up....goes miles in the air and Anderson takes a steepler. That was on a length on middle, Hendricks jumps down the track looking to go up and over. The ball catches his top edge and balloons straight up. A swirler for Anderson around the mid-off region and he holds on
Slower bouncer now, down leg and not called a wide. Got lucky there, I reckon, Jansen.
Length ball shaping away from Markram who gets a thick outside edge down to deep third
Low full toss and Taylor misses out. Was on middle and leg, he flicks it straight to midwicket
Fuller in length with a hint of movement away from the batter, who pushes back to the bowler
Pitched up right in Markram's slot well outside off. He frees his arms and smacks the drive through cover with authority
Gets a length ball on the stump, but Gous is ready for it. Pumps him straight back on the up for a four to start off
On a length on the pads of Markram who clips it neatly to the right of mid-on for a quick run
Gets his pace up and smacks Gous in the midriff. The batter gives himself room and backs away but Rabada follows him and cramps him for room
PUMPED! Back of a length ball angling into de Kock who shuffled across and slams the pull to the deep midwicket fence with the wind

The back of a length ball does the job for Rabada! Was pitched around middle as Taylor backed away and looked to go up and over. The length does him in as the ball catches the splice and balloons feebly towards mid-off who dives forward and takes a good low catch

Similar length, similar line, just add two to the result. De Kock didn't time the previous one as well. He did it this time around and sends the ball soaring over the deep midwicket fence. And, what's worse, Jasdeep has overstepped Nah, can't bowl there to de Kock. Back of a length ball on his pads, he gets across and helps this over the deep fine leg fence for six more
Hard length again that hits him on the thigh pad very close to the pitch. They scamper through for a leg-bye

Top-edge, top-edge but he has got enough bat to clear the deep backward square leg fielder. Thought that went straight up, but de Kock had enough power on it. The change of angle almost did the trick. Back of a length ball on middle stump, he swivel-pulls as the ball catches his top edge and goes straight. As it turns out, clears the fielder
Ooh, almost pops a catch back to Rabada! Length ball that stopped on the batter who plays a defensive shot. The ball hit the high part of Gous' bat
Ends the over well. Fuller in length outside off, drives to cover
On a length on off and middle, he goes for a wild heave, only to mistime to midwicket
Good length ball angling across the batter, who mistimes his cut towards backward point
Fuller to start off outside off, he pushes to long off
Picked and how! That has gone miles into the stands. On a length on off, he keeps his head down and sends it 95m over wide long-on. Hit with the wind, but that was going for a six on any ground
On a length on off, he nudges to the on-side and walks through for a run
Back to the hard lengths on off, he pushes towards mid-off and sets off
Flatter in length outside off, was short as well as he rocked back and thrashed it but couldn't beat cover
Low full toss outside off, he backs away and scythes to the right of deep point who sprints across and saves two
Shimmies down the track and works the length ball to the onside
Gous' turn now to go the maximum city. Back of a length ball on the stumps, he jumps down and hits the shot with the wind over wide long-on
Swept hard and over the in-field. Length on middle and leg, he gets inside the line of the ball, on his knee and dumps him over short fine leg
Low full toss on the pads of Gous for a couple of runs. Was the slower ball that was picked early. The fifty is up for USA in five overs.
Too short, and punished. He gives himself a bit of room by backing away and Kenjige makes de Kock's job easier by shelling up a half-tracker. De Kock cuts it hard and flat past point
Length ball on of stump, he mistimes his drive towards mid-off
Slower offcutter on the pads of Nitish who works it to the right of short midwicket for a run
Another quick length ball just around off stump, he miscues to mid-on and takes a quick run
Backs away, quite a bit but Rabada sees him and follows with a slower offcutter. Gous is deceived and just about defends to the offside

Ah, misses out there. Ali goes around the wicket and sends down a low full toss on middle. De Kock backs away and is probably a bit surprised by that full bunger. Fails to pierce the gap through the off side

Up in the air and that's a second wicket for Rabada! On a length on the pads, he flicks but doesn't get a clean connection. The ball hits the high part of his bat and Stubbs at deep square leg isn't dropping those. Nitish clipped that into the breeze and that was another reason the ball didn't travel as much as it should have.

Fuller and angling well down leg. Gous does really well to his right Inside-edge that just misses the leg stump. Angled in on off and middle stump. He throws his bat at it and is lucky the ball didn't thud into the stumps
Fuller on middle stump, defends back to the bowler
Slower ball into the pitch and de Kock has picked that up nice and early. Waits for the ball and tonks him miles over deep midwicket for a six
Good length ball on off stump, he gets across and defends
On a length on the stumps, he backs away again and connects well but can't beat mid-on
Hard lengths just outside off, he opens the face of the blade but can't get it past backward point
Fullish on off stump, drives to long off
Slightly flatter and shorter outside off, he cuts to the right of deep point for a couple
Angled across de Kock who gets across and can only nudge it to the on side
Gets the length ball to drift into the batter who pushes to long on
Flatter at 94.6kph on middle and leg, he works it towards deep midwicket
On a length just outside off, he stays back and pushes to cover
Again flatter length on middle, he stays back and flicks to the right of long-on for another run

Jones is a goner and that is a massive wicket for South Africa! Floated nicely from Maharaj on the fuller side outside off. A hint of turn away from Jones, who pushes at it with an angled bat and only manages a thin edge to de Kock.
Backs away but Harmeet keeps it fuller on leg stump. Works it to deep midwicket
A touch flatter on middle and leg, he works it behind square for a run
Fuller ball to end the over. On middle, he pushes to long on
Drifted into Gous sharply and on the fuller side. He pushes back to the bowler
Starts off with a sharp back of a length ball on the middle stump. Anderson leaves the ball off a length
Shorter in length on the stumps, he goes right back and cuts to deep cover
Anderson gives him the charge trying to throw Nortje off his length. But all he can manage is a thin inside-edge past his leg stump
On a length on the pads of the batter who works it to short fine leg
Fuller outside off, he digs it to mid-off
Super pickup from Markram! Fuller and flatter outside off, he gets the revers out and pumps him over short third
Slower back of a length ball, on middle and leg, he works it towards deep midwicket. Was the back of a hand slower ball
Lovely shot! Tossed up on the stumps, he jumps down the track, reaches the pitch of the ball and deposits him over long-on
Another back of a length ball on leg stump, Anderson gets inside the line of that and helps to deep fine leg
Gores flatter and shorter outside off, he cuts it hard to deep cover's right
Banged in short shoulder-high. Gous tries to pull it away, gets a bottom edge perilously close to the of stump
Quicker through the air outside off, he pushes towards cover for a quick run
Fuller on leg stump, he backs away and digs it to long on
On a length just outside off, he stays back and pats to the right of backward point for a run
Flatter on middle and leg, he tips it to wide long on for a run again
Slower through the air, but the length was marginally short. He hops back and cuts to deep point for a run
Yorker on off stump, he backs away but the length is such that de Kock can't get under and can only push to long-off
A tad short in length on middle and leg, he rocks back and hammers the pull but straight to long-on
Slower through the air, shorter and very wide. He reaches for it and somehow cuts to deep cover
Shimmies down the track and works the length ball on his pads to short fine leg

Fifty off 26 balls for de Kock. Welcome return to form for the opener. Fuller down leg, he sweeps it hard to the deep backward square leg fence Very full outside off, he goes for another hard sweep, misses and is stumped. But of course it won't count as it is a no-ball
Reverse sweep, he misses and is rapped on the pad as a loud appeal ensues. Think the angle would have taken the ball past off stump. SA do not review. Was fuller just on off.
Eases to long-on to end the over
On a length just outside off, he eases it to long-on
That's really well done by de Kock. Fuller length ball outside off, he gets a thick bottom edge to de Kock's right who does really well
Flatter outside off, he pats it to point
WALLOPED! Back of a length ball right in his arc. He backs away, exposes his stumps and hacks him over deep midwicket for a huge six
Excellent placement from de Kock. Floated just outside off, he reaches fetches it sweeps between deep square and deep midwicket

Excellent riposte from Nortje. Goes full and sends the leg pole splat. Don't think Anderson was expecting that. He stays rooted to the crease and Nortje goes full. He misses, Nortje doesn't and USA's job gets tougher.
shorter and wider, he cuts but can't beat thefielder
Spears the full-length ball on the stumps that crashes into his pad. But he got a thick inside-edge to go with it. Was bowled at 143kph
Fuller outside off, he looks for a drive, gets a thick inside-edge past the keeper. Anderson gives chase and keeps the ball inside the field of play
Fullish length outside off, he drives to extra cover
Another play and a miss! Floated outside off, he looks for a sweep, misses and the ball hits the keeper on the shoulder. They take a bye
tests him with the bouncer, but that was too short. Called a wide. Pacy back of a length ball into his body, he swivels and pulls to deep midwicket
Fuller on the stumps, he works it to the onside for a quick run
comes around the wicket, picked up over cover elegantly, but there's protection in the deep
Rapped on the pads. Enthused appeal but it's sliding down leg
flatter and fuller, de Kock can't get underneath it
has a heave-ho, but there's extra turn and he doesn't connect. Well taken by de Kock
once more, it's yorker length. Carved out and they exchange ends
Chipped into a vacant mid-on area to turn the strike over
low full toss, Markram reverse sweeps but Taylor puts in a dive at backward point to save a boundary
guided towards sweeper cover for a single
length ball wide this time. Markram waits for it and slashes it through point, and it's placed well enough to run away for four
wider and flatter outside off. Jahangir tried to guide it to past short third but misses
low full toss, whipped to long-on for a single
chipped off the leading edge up and over Maharaj. Miserly over from Keshav as the asking rate climbs above 13
eased down to long-off for a single

that's adjacent, and he's given! Shamsi strikes first ball Jahangir reviewed but it landed on off and spun back to crash into the pad in front of middle, and was going to hit middle and leg. USA lose a wicket as well as a review, and South Africa are closing in here
misses the yorker, and when he does, QdK is good enough to punish him. Comes across and whips it over cow corner for a 90m six
back of a length, Harmeet chips uppishly to long-off
goes wider outside off, allowing him to carve it to deep point
slightly overpitched, allowing him to lean into the drive and loft it over extra cover for four
follows him as he backs away. Nudged into the onside
eased down to long-off
this is just bad bowling. Wide full toss. Qdk opens the face of the bat and directs it perfectly into the gap between backward point and short third for the easiest boundary he'll score today
radar was off with that delivery. strayed onto leg, letting him sweep into a vacant fine leg area to pick up four handy runs
ahhh, he's at his best right now. Anticipates the full yorker, and reverse laps it over the keeper's head for another boundary. He's unplayable in this mood, is the South African wicketkeeper
slapped to long-on as he keeps the strike
slapped down to long-off for one
comes around the wicket again, whipped down to long-on for a single

full toss, but he doesn't fully connect this time. Powered to cow corner, but doesn't have the legs to clear the rope, and a sharp catch is taken. The umpires are having a look at whether it was higher than the waist, though I think he won't survive this. He doesn't! And the USA finally break through again
extra flight made Gous wait for it before carving it to deep cover for a couple

two in two, Miller chips it to Harmeet first ball! Innocous delivery, really, but Miller, not set yet, just pushed at it, straight into the gleeful hands of Harmeet. Do the USA have their foot in the door again?
helped down to long-on
angling back in, defended into the onside
in the slot, and Harmeet punishes him. Picked up off a half-volley length and shovelled over long-on for a 75m six. The worst area you can bowl to him at that pace
defended towards the offside
slows it down and drags it back. Prodded to cover for a single
times it to long-off for a single
whipped to long-on for another handy over for the USA
carved to deep point from around the wicket for a single
drives it down to long-on for a single
pushed down the ground for a single
strays down leg once more
defended to cover for no run
bottom handed shovel over Shamsi's head for a single
sends this in quicker, and it's cut away for another single
backs away and Shamsi follows him. Cramped for room, he can only whip it to an onside fielder
nurdles it into the onside and smart running fetches them two
restricted for room once more but manages to guide it to long-off
eased into the onside to keep the strike
short from Shamsi, chipped over long-on. Shamsi squeezes in a tight over and the asking rate rises once more. Nearly 16 now
too close to cut and is beaten for pace when he attempts it
slower delivery. He waited for it and carved it behind square for four
mistimes an onside slog, and it's cut off at midwicket for a single
pushes it into the offside and the pair exchange ends from one more
low full toss and a misfield at mid-off means it tickles along to a much-needed boundary for the USA. I think Markram's the bloke who made the error there
opens the face of the blade to sneak it past short third, but the fielding's sharp and they only get a single
slower ball at 109 kph, slaps it to sweeper cover

punishes the full toss this time, slapping him straight over his head for six! That was fast and relatively low, but great bottom-hand strength from Gous to dispatch him over his head and find the strength to clear the rope
and another six! Is this the over that's the catalyst for an astonishing comeback? Probably not, but it's muscled over midwicket for six more, ending a phenomenally productive over for the US

But he doesn't miss it! Markram reached out to the full delivery to try and help it over backward point, but instead times it too well, and an onrushing Ali Khan takes a superb catch diving forward. The USA are beginning to drag this back quite effectively now
long hop, Klaasen on the back foot and powers it over long-off. The fielder gets fingertips to it but can't prevent it sneaking over the rope for six
in the slot from Shamsi, this is poor bowling. And he smears it over midwicket for six more!
whacked to cow corner once more, but there's a fielder there who collects on the bounce
flatter through the air, nudged into the onside
picks it up and slaps it over his head, splitting the two fielders at long-off and long-on perfectly
prodded into the onside and the pair exchange ends
googly outside leg stump that's guided to midwicket for one
slapped through the offside once more. The spinners are sticking with that wider line for now
clips it into the onside, calls two early and gets there easily. Excellent running and a 12-run over to break the shackles
carved to backward point where the fielder picks up after a fumble, but Shamsi just about gets out of that over
juicy full toss, Stubbs could have gone after it but opts to place it to long-on for a couple
another full toss, and he can't get on top of it. Muscles it to the long-on fielder
runs down the track and goes up and over mid-off! Slapped over cover and the boundary region is vacant
goes a touch too wide this time and the umpire calls it another one that's a touch too wide tries to heave it over the onside but mistimes it and can only manage one
slower bouncer as he saw the batter charging. He can only prod it into the offside for a single
wide half-volley, driven to wide long-off
slower ball, high backlift and drilled down the ground. Jasdeep does well to get out of the way, and the fielder in the deep cleans up
wide once more, but this one's just within the line and he misses the cut
wide outside off, but it's much too wide and the umpire gives it this time bottom edge to extra cover for a single as the asking rate creeps above 16 now
that was in the slot, and Klaasen looked to heave it into next weak, but he catches the inner half of the bat
picked up over and behind midwicket and Stubbs cuts it off in the deep
another half-volley, and he doesn't miss out this time. What power, picked it up and drilled it for a huge six over cover. Very few in the game could hit that shot as well
goes across but Shamsi goes wider. The umpire thinks it's too wide though, much to Shamsi's displeasure wide outside off again, but this one's just within the guidelines
bouncer that Klaasen tries to pull and misses
goes wide again, but errs by also going full. That means when Harmeet picks it up and uses a lot of bottom hand, he successfully drags it over wide long-on all the way for six
well-executed yorker this time, and he can only dig it out for one
goes too wide once more gets a top edge and it flies into the air, but into a gap as David Miller at long-off is unable to get there in time

Cheeky! Set himself up for a slog to cow corner, readjusted when he saw it was a full toss and attempted to reverse lap it over the keeper's head. Does not get the distance, but comes through for a couple
long-hop gets the treatment it deserves. Swivels and clobbers it over midwicket. It splits the fielders but flies over the rope anyway!
yorker outside off he can only nudge for one

six more! Six more! Is this actually happening then? Poor from Shamsi again, another long-hop, and the pull just about clears a leaping cow corner fielder. 22 off the over, and the US are suddenly in a position of near-parity

full toss that's timed very well. Too well, in fact. It flies to midwicket, where Stubbs comes across to complete a simple catch. Harmeet puts his hands on his head before he has to depart after a knock that breathed life back into the USA's chances
slower ball. Stubbs was waiting for it, but in the end got lucky. Thick edge that evaded a diving keeper and ran away for four
slower ball wide outside off that he pokes at and misses
wide outside off, drilled to wide long-off, where the fielder had a chase on. Does well diving to his left to keep it to two
High pace from Rabada again. Wide outside off and full, and another swing and a miss from Jasdeep
wide line again, inner edge through to the keeper
offcutter picked up over midwicket for a single
nails the wide yorker again. Excellent death bowling from Netravalkar
slapped to backward point and they ease through for one
Stubbs anticipated it but still couldn't do much about it. Wide yorker and Stubbs' sweep doesn't connect with the ball, which thuds into his pad
change of pace from Rabada, a swing and a miss, and a phenomenal over ends. Just 2 off it and a wicket. It's undone all the damage Shamsi did, and South Africa breathe easy again
slapped back to the bowler, and he signs off with four dot balls in a row. Absolutely world-class death bowling from Netravalkar
makes room and carves it to cover, and they do decide to take the single, weirdly
pulled away to midwicket for a single
pace and back of a length, slapped to deep cover for a single

short ball that Klaasen thrashes into the wind. It wasn't great timing, but the power and the assistance of the wind allows him to clear that short boundary for a 69m six. Harsh on Ali Khan but South Africa continue to push towards 200
backs away but Nortje follows him at pace, and Gous can only slap it back to Nortje. Mathematically impossible now if South Africa bowl no wides or no-balls
dug out and driven back down the ground and they scurry back for a couple. They're checking if he got back at the striker's end for good measure but there are no issues here
thick outside edge that bounces just in front of short third. He can't properly collect and it flies over him and away to the boundary
nails the yorker. Dug out back down the ground and Stubbs faces the final delivery
wide outside off and it's guided down to deep point
gets underneath it to scoop it over the keeper's head as South Africa sign off with a boundary. It brings up the 50-partnership and means South Africa end with 194.

full and straight, smacked to mid-off and they don't even bother running as South Africa seal an 18-run victory. The USA gave them a scare, but South Africa were the dominant side for much of this game, and are now five in five at this World Cup
Off the mark straightaway. He lands it on a shortish length outside off and gets it to spin away, Salt goes back and wrists it through midwicket to get going
full, 132kph/82mph and shaping back in towards off stump. King watches it closely and drives in front of mid-off for a single off the first ball
The inswinging arm ball on a length, moves slightly in and Buttler keeps it out

length ball, there's swing for Topley - but that takes it down leg for a wide full and hit on the pads, Topley likes it... Nitin Menon walked away immediately, and Buttler isn't convinced. Pitching in line a question, maybe doing too much. No review
Fuller outside off, pushed to cover
length again, 135kph/84mph and curling behind Charles' pads as he looks to swat leg side hits a length and keeps the ball on the stumps, Charles shovels to leg
Quicker on off and middle, flicked to deep midwicket for a couple
full, swinging outside leg again. But Charles had stepped across and ends up being nutmegged as he tries to get the bat down
Fuller outside off, the arm ball again, looks to go through off side but gets it off the inner half to mid-off
shorter, 131kph/81mph and skidding into the thigh pad as Charles flicks across the line
Goes back and across, gets a length ball that turns a touch. He is in position to punch it to long-on. Steady start
pitched up and driven square, not timed and Livingstone tracks it down in front of the rope
angling back in, flicks the back leg, Wood goes up now! There's some discussion but again no review. Looked high to me
Starts off with a very full ball, 132.3kph on the pads, Salt misses the flick and gets it off his boot around the corner

banged in and veering down the leg side pitched up and tucked towards mid-on, they scamper through... and the throw to the striker's end was a direct hit, which ricocheted away to deep third. But they don't manage a second
Flicked away for England's first four. He angles it in on a length, ends up delivering it on the pads, down leg. Buttler does well to deflect it well past short fine leg
length ball wide of off stump, big ole swing and a miss from Charles
\Quick single, after he blocks the length ball to the off side. One look at his partner and Buttler was off in a sprint
fired in full, 147kph/91mph, Charles gets a ballooning leading edge but it lands safely between mid-off and mid-on!
Angles it down leg, Salt misses the flick Better. Length ball on middle and leg, Salt can only defend it back towards the bowler
short and steered away, Charles sits back and uses the pace on the ball, opens the face and checks his shot through point. First boundary of the night
Anticipates Salt backing away, follows him with a length ball that he swivels and heaves to deep square leg
fired in full, Charles backs away and pings a drive... picks out cover
Too straight, pays the price. England have two fours in the over with minimum risk. Fuller than good length, on the pads, Buttler once again beats short fine leg to his left
On a length outside off, 95.6kph/56.9mph, driven to cover
fullish length and swinging down leg as King aims what looked almost like a slog-sweep but doesn't connect length ball, 131kph/81mph outside off. Mistimed towards extra cover
Swings it in from a length, 99.9kph/62.1mph, Salt punches it to cover-point
short and angling away from the right-hander. King swings hard but plinks his pull back towards Topley in his follow through
Leading edge past Hosein. And he can't believe how much time Joseph took to move to his right from mid-off. As a result, the edge has the most pristine timing and runs away down the ground

now that's why he wanted a new bat... smashed on to the roof at deep midwicket! Full and in the arc, King plants the front foot and hammers the ball clean out of the ground, 101 metres. And now we'll need a new ball, too!

Dropped? There was a definite noise. Pooran does not hang on. Shortish and spinning away outside off, Salt looks to heave it over the on side. The ball does deflect and it was the toe end, confirms Snicko
full but pushed out wide this time, nudged for a single
Fuller on middle and leg, knocked down to long-on
pitched up, 135kph/83mph on leg stump, Charles biffs it to mid-on
Lands it on a length, just outside off, 98.5kph, Buttler opens the face and gets it to short third
full toss, flicked away fine! Think Charles has inadvertently played the Nat-meg here. Big inside edge but no one back and it races away for four more
Length ball on middle, clipped to deep backward square leg
on the stumps and tucked into the leg side
Back of a length on middle and leg, gets it off the inner half towards midwicket
banged in, 141kph/88mph outside off. Charles leans back and swipes a pull for one
A touch fuller on middle and leg, Buttler backs away and wrists it between midwicket and mid-on and gets two

slower ball, carved away through backward point, Salt hares around from deep third, can't cut it off on the slide! He palmed the ball away but then threw himself in vain into the boundary cushion trying to claw it back
Buttler backs away early, so Russell bowls it on a length outside off. He can reach out and bunt it to short cover, who dives and stops
short and clubbed down the ground! King rocks forward and muscles Archer over the head of mid-on
Carved through point. Length ball on off, Buttler makes room, and then adjusts to curve his hand and find the gap between backward point and cover-point. Three taken
pace off again, tucked leg side coming forward
Clubbed! Top tier stuff. Russell goes for the slower one, the legcutter at 115.5kph, full on middle. Salt stays leg side and hits it straight over
dug in short, 142kph/88mph, Charles sits back and attempts to up-and-over it, doesn't connect
Buttler takes a step to leg before coming in line, clips the fullish ball on leg through square leg
slashed over the leaping fielder at third! Big top edge but it clears the man and skips away
Length ball on off, defended back towards the bowler
goes full and wide, King jumps out and drills to cover... and now he's down on his back. He looks to have knacked something playing that shot
Powered away through covers. Shortish and just outside off, this time Salt is up to the task. Goes back and punches it through the gap in the off side
stays over the wicket, good length on middle and off, defended
Bowls it into the surface, the inswinger, pulled away through forward square leg. Hetmyer has work to do in the deep, and allows them time to get back for two
ghosts past the edge, lovely shape on the ball from Curran, beats Pooran's flat-footed drive
Looks to hack it to the on side but mistimes it to midwicket. That allows him a run, Shepherd misses his shy at the bowler's end. Safe
fuller with pace off, Pooran jabs at it and gets a thick edge towards short third
Flat and quicker, 100.9kph, length ball, punched back to the bowler
width on offer and crashed through point! Curran finishes with a poor ball, on a length and room to free the arms. Pooran slaps his first runs in front of the sweeper
Welcomed with a shovel over midwicket! He steams in and bowls it full on the pads, Salt clears his front leg and flicks it aerially. Against the wind to the longer side
banged in and slammed over cover point! Slower ball and Charles was waiting to swing it up and away

Short and angling in, pulled away through midwicket. Rutherford rushes across to his left to keep the ball in play. But ends up over-running because of his momentum after palming the ball in. Saves two
pitched up, possibly pace off again, prodded to cover
Angling in on the pads, flicked towards short fine leg
full outside off, slashed through the ring! Uses 145kph to his advantage, opening up his bat face to steer between backward point and short third
Buttler is standing well outside leg, Joseph follows him with a length ball that is clipped to square leg
tighter line, dabbed into the off side
Looks to pull but is through early with the shot, gets an under-edge past off stump to the wicketkeeper
banged in short, 143kph/89mph. Charles swings at a pull and misses
Soars over short fine or half a dozen! Perfect end to the powerplay. Once again Joseph angles the short ball in to Salt, who gets inside the line, swivels and sends it sailing

slower ball, Charles moves across and doesn't connect again. Signalled wide, though England think the batter's movement should have been taken into account short and into the body again, Charles flat-bats one out to deep square leg
Fuller on off, clipped wide of short fine leg
angled across, pushed the ball out wide... too wide slower ball, almost comes out as a beamer but dips in time. Charles flicks it off his body into the leg side
Bowls it full down leg, flicked to deep square leg for a couple
length ball on off stump, tapped back down the track
Quicker and fuller on off, punched to sweeper cover
full and slapped on the stretch, just one through the covers
Full on off, wrists it through midwicket with soft hands and sprints back for two
pitched up, 130kph/80mph on middle and leg, Charles clips through midwicket
Goes wide of the crease and lands a length ball well outside off, 102.3kph/63.6mph, cut straight to backward point
drops short and gets clubbed! Sits up nicely for Pooran to swat well in front of the deep midwicket sweeper, bouncing away to the rope

Beauty! Slows it down, lands it fullish on off and gets it to spin away a touch. Buttler is slightly off-balanced, Pooran whips off the bails in a flash after the ball beat his outside edge. But his back foot never lifted off the surface
full outside off, 136kph and lashed over the infield, just one to the man in the deep
full, fast and donked into the stands! Pooran coolly chips a 147kph/91mph rocket off his pads, 95 metres over deep midwicket. Woof!
Tossed up full on off, eased down to long-on
drags his length back a touch, beats the swing in the channel
Slower through the air, 91.5kph, outside off, knocked through cover
slanted across the bows, 149kph/93mph and draws another unsuccessful poke
Fires it through, full on leg, flicked to deep midwicket
length ball, 148kph/92mph, Pooran heaves at it and squirts a thick inside edge out to deep backward square leg

Lbw? Given! Buttler asks for the review. Chase spots Buttler charging down early and fires one in at 108.9kph/67.7mph! Buttler gets into a tangle and is not in a position to even flick it away. Wears it full and low on the front pad. Cooked! Three reds and West Indies have their breakthrough
back of a length band sliding down the leg side steps away to leg, Wood goes full at the spot where he was standing, 149kph/93mph. Whipped away to deep midwicket
Around the wicket, arm ball, fullish outside off at 95.5kph, goes for the drive and gets a thick outside edge to short third
shortish on a wide line, possible a change-up. Swing and a miss from Pooran
Tosses it up and lands it on a length around off, punched to the bowler. Excellent over from Chase in the chase.
pushed out full on the stumps, Charles prods it back
Full on leg, flicked to midwicket
quickish legbreak, 91kph outside off stump. Punched down to long-off
Fuller and quicker on middle, 97.8kph, driven down to long-off
googly, Pooran sits back and plays to leg. Rashid scampers after it
Moeen sweeps it away with disdain. Motie bowls it on a length outside off, flatter and quicker too, but Moeen picked that up quickly and nailed it through square leg
out the front of the hand, I think, 94kph on leg stump, Pooran clips it down to long-on
Fuller and quicker on middle, flicked through midwicket
big-turning leggie, slower pace and it has Charles groping at thin air outside off
Slows it down, flights it outside off, pushes at that and gets an inside edge
another googly, launched through midwicket with a plant front foot. Think he was aiming straighter but gets away with it, just a single to the boundary rider
A reverse sweep from Moeen Ali! And off the back of the bat that. Flatter and on a length just outside off, spinning in a touch. Moeen outsmarts the bowler and beats short third to his right
over the wicket, flat on the stumps, 98kph and nudged leg side for one
Floated outside off, fullish, driven to cover
dragged down, wide of off and cut away through point. Just a single to the sweeper
Fuller and quicker on off, powered away to cover.. 106.3kph
lobbed on the stumps, nudged down the ground for one more
Fired it full and wide down leg, he misses the flick Slower this time, 92.5kph, on middle, eased down to long-on
zipped in from round the wicket, 90kph and turned to leg. Placed into the gap and hard running brings them two, despite a direct hit at the non-striker's end

Another drop, Pooran again. Shortish and outside off, Moeen goes back for the cut. But gets an inside edge. Pooran fails to hang on. How costly will this prove, considering Moeen's ability to play spin?
tossed up, Pooran is forward and dabs one into the covers now
Moeen dives full length, has he made it in though? Moeen turns this through midwicket and takes on Rutherford, who fires a flat throw on the bounce to the keeper. The dive saves Moeen though.
Charles drops back to cut for one more
Full and just outside off, squeezed through covers
tossed up outside off, Charles winds up for a slog down the ground. Doesn't connect

Moeen backs away early, Russell sprays it wide on a length Moeen picks out deep midwicket! Russell strikes upon return. Bowls it on a shortish length despite the shorter boundary on leg. Moeen takes him on with a pull, but cannot time it clean. The wind blowing against the shot also played its part. Finds Charles stationed in the deep to perfection

but this one does go the journey! Tossed up full and Charles sets himself to muller the ball a long way back over wide long-on. His first six of the innings, and coming with a sense he wants to put the hammer down now
Angles the length ball down leg, JB lets it be Length ball outside off, 135.6kph, looks to slash but chops it via the under-edge
shuffles across, Rashid tries to aim for the tramlines, but gets it too wide flat legbreak, into the pitch, bunted down to long-on
Length ball on off, 137.9kph, goes for the drive but gets an inside edge onto his back pad
tossed up wide of off, Pooran drops back and cuts, picks up two into the green space at backward point
Full and swinging in a touch on off, flicked away through midwicket. The longer side allows them a couple
pushed through, 93kph on the pads and tucked through backward square
Back of a length just outside off, 137.9kph, looks to chop it to deep third but does so just wide of the keeper
flattish and spinning away, Charles shovels one more down the ground
Shortish again, gets an inside edge to short fine leg. The fielder fumbles and that passage of single was easier

goes big... not big enough. Charles holes out to long-on! He was standing outside leg and Moeen simply looped it up wide of off, made the batter fetch his shot. Clubbed down the ground but needed just a little more oomph. Held safely by Brook as it dropped in front of the rope

Fires it full and down leg, Salt lets it be. Deflects off Pooran's pad towards short fine and allows a bye too Tossed up on off and middle, he goes for the slog but gets a thick inside edge onto the pad
angled out wide of off stump, Powell cuts without success
Shortish and angling in, heaved away to deep square leg
slides this one through just inside the tramlines as Powell plays no shot
Sees Bairstow back away and fires a full ball on his pads. He whips it away to short fine leg, and takes him on for a run because of the half-stop
flat offbreak, chopped behind point going back for his first run
Low full toss on the pads, knocked down to long-on
tucked into the leg side, Moeen gives chase

Chipped over the bowler. Bairstow looks to shuffle across but then goes back to his original stance. Chase tries to york him up on leg, ends up dishing out a low full toss. The bottom hand comes off as Bairstow hits it, and beats long-off
cleaned out over long-off! Powell shows Charles how to do it, setting himself for the flighted delivery and boshing it into the top tier. A fine way to bring up the Windies 100
Fuller and angling in, swept to deep backward square leg
pushed across the bows of the lefty, Pooran dabs behind square
Fuller on off, carved just wide of cover
floats up the wrong'un, Powell presses out to block
Holds in a touch on middle, on a length, and Salt nearly chips it back to the bowler

flatter legbreak, Powell reaches out to try and paddle sweep... Rashid asks loudly for lbw and England will review Nitin Menon's not out. Maybe spinning and bouncing too much? In fact, it's hit Powell in the chin! They'll take the impact from where it brushed his upper arm, though. Yes, umpire's call on impact and bouncing clear of off stump. No England burn that one
Goes back to the length ball and punches it wide of long-off
tossed up, spinning away and hacked down to long-on going back
Tossed up outside off, Bairstow goes inside out over extra cover. Joseph gets around from long-off and saves two
googly, worked behind square on the leg side
Top edge clears short third. Lands it on a length on off, he gets plenty on the edge and no chance for the man chasing
Powell goes back and clips another single to long-off. Another good over for England
Full on middle and leg, flicked through midwicket to keep strike
Hammered away over the longer side. Joseph goes with the slower short ball, allowing Bairstow plenty of time to swing it away over deep midwicket
over the wicket, full and skidding into the pads
Smartly done now. Short and just outside off, 128.7kph, Bairstow backs away and ramps it just over the right of the wicketkeeper
short and bludgeoned into the crowd! Powell is quick on the bouncer, stepping into a ruthless mow over midwicket, 89 metres off the middle
Continues with the hard length, just outside off, 143.2kph, he misses the slash after backing away
pitched up, tickled down the ground
Shortish again, on middle and leg, pulled through forward square leg for a couple. Was the slower one at 116.5kph
wide full toss, Pooran picks the unguarded spot at deep square leg! England had just brought that man up in order to send point out, but Nicky P spots the devil in the detail and swipes four
Digs it in again, but gives the batter almost no pace - 119.4kph, Bairstow is a tad early into the pull and gets a soft leading edge towards fine leg
into the pitch, bottom-edged looking to pull
Salt backs away, Joseph follows him with a shortish one, heaved away on the bounce to deep midwicket. 14 off the over
full outside off, 132kph/82mph and Pooran is late on his drive, chides himself loudly
Quicker arm ball on a length on middle and leg, goes back and punches it through cover-point
dragged down and slapped away to deep midwicket, who has to run around allowing them to come back

Huge appeal for lbw! Not given. Meanwhile, Pooran spots Salt halfway down for a single, gets to the bowl and misses his shy at the bowler's end. Powell wants Hosein to convince Pooran for a review, but he isn't. Looks like it came off the glove. Bairstow went for the reverse shot but did not connect well
charges out and rams six straight back over the bowler's head! Powell isn't going to let Livingstone sneak through one here. Skips a couple of steps out and smokes through the line
Quicker and fuller on leg, swept away through backward square leg, No chance for the fielder in the deep
honked over long-off! Looked as if he'd mishit this one, but it's six more! Down on one knee, sliced high... but long enough
"Catch it!" is Pooran's call, someone in the crowd will have to! Tosses it up and lands it on a length around off, Bairstow gets a top edge on the slog sweep but goes 76m over square leg
fired flat outside off, 95kph and chopped square

Hosein cannot believe it. Walks back towards his mark and is down on his haunches. Fires in an almost perfect on middle and leg at 100kph, Bairstow looks to go over off and gets an inside edge past leg stump
biggedy-biggedy-bonged once again! Tossed up and Powell opens up to crunch it down the ground for a 93m six
Fires it down leg, he misses the flick Spins it away from a length, Bairstow blocks it from the crease. 15 off the over, is that the game for England?

got him this time, top-edged to short third! Powell attempts to thrash Livingstone for his fourth six in the over but miscues it, Mark Wood plunging forward to get his fingertips under the ball on the edge of the circle. The third umpire checks, but they're happy he didn't ground it. Powell's cameo is curtailed, but he walks off having given his side the hurry up
full-length ball, hung out wide, Pooran can't connect
Brings up fifty in style! Full and outside off, clobbers it over covers
pitched up, 143kph/89mph outside off, another swing and a miss
In the slot, out of the ground! Full on off and middle, he clears his front leg and smacks it high over the sightscreen
full, wide and skewed for four! Pooran gets low and throws the hands, takes it on the full and clears the leap of backward point to pick up four
And now uses the bounce of the bowler and the surface. Shepherd bowls the slower one in the middle of the pitch, Salt arches back and ramps it over the wicketkeeper
full outside off, beats the bat through to Buttler
This one is even bigger! Length ball outside off, in the slot again. Salt clears his front leg and hits it 93 over wide long-off
goes full outside off again, and once more Pooran fails to connect
Some assault this! Short and angling in to Salt, he gets inside the line, swivels and pulls it wayyyy over deep backward square leg. It was the slower one but made no difference

Archer nicks him off! Pooran could not get to grips with what Archer was doing that over, and eventually tickles an edge through to Buttler. Full, 140kph/87mph outside off, Pooran flashed at it and Buttler heard the nick. So too did Ahsan Raza and England have another
Full toss outside off, Salt goes inside out over cover for four more. 30 runs in the over, the most by a West Indian in T20 World Cups. What a time for that to happen
full outside off, googly, I think. Russell jams down on it, the ball bobbling towards mid-on and there's nearly a mix-up, before Russell slopes up to the non-striker's end
Fuller outside off, eased through cover
tossed up on off from over the wicket, pushed into the covers
Cuts it through the gap. Short and wide outside off, flatter and quicker too. Salt stays deep in the crease and gets it between short third and backward point
flighted outside off and Rutherford prods to mid-off
Goes back and works this away through mid-on
flatter on the stumps, clipped leg side
Full outside leg, drives it inside out to cover

BIGGIE! Russell holes out to deep midwicket! It was the googly and that made him drag the shot leg side. The hit never looked clean and it ended up picking out the man on the rope perfectly. West Indies wavering after a strong start
Flatter and quicker just outside off, cuts it to short third
tossed up and dinked to the on side, Rashid scuttles across. He finishes his spell with excellent figures of 1 for 21
Backs away to the length ball and punches it to cover
Follows Salt with a back of a length ball, which is heaved away through midwicket. Did not time it well and hence gets two
short and slugged all the way over backward square! Crisp pull from Rutherford, hitting with the wind to the longer part of the ground
Digs it into the surface, Salt top-edges the pull. But it lands safely, well short of deep square leg running in
short again, muscled in front of square! Scything short-arm jab from Rutherford, finds the fence again!
Shortish again, outside off, Bairstow pulls it to deep midwicket to seal a commanding win for England
low full toss, 149kph/93mph outside off, Rutherford punches a couple out to the cover sweeper
another bumper, 135kph/84mph and this time plinked out to deep square leg
banged into the pitch, Shepherd hit on the pads as he hangs back

145kph/90mph, short and sliding down the leg side again fired down leg. Wood getting it wrong as he looks to make Shepherd hit into the wind length ball, shovelled for four! Into the wind but it's a short hit off the pads down to deep backward square leg
over the wicket, full on off and dinked down the ground
round the wicket, full length in the channel. Shepherd clubs a drive to the cover sweeper
pace off, the ball spins up and beats the bat as Rutherford tries to hit the cover off it
low full toss, 130kph/80mph and slogged, not a great connection and it bounces out towards deep midwicket. Bairstow has ground to cover and they get back
length outside off, pace off again. Rutherford smashes it to the sweeper and races up and down for two more
another cutter in the channel and this beats the bat. Superb over from SCurran
goes full at the pads, 142kph/88mph. Shepherd flails across the line and gets a leg bye into the off side
short and clobbered, all the way! Picked the offcutter, I think, and it's a short hit, 69 metres over deep backward point
full toss outside off, 143kph/89mph. Slapped over the infield and they get back for two despite some miscommunication between the batters
full outside off, 149kph/93mph and drilled down to long-off for one
bumper, 138kph and Shepherd swings unsuccessfully at it...  but they steal a bye to the keeper, and then another as Archer attempts to underarm into the non-striker's stumps and misses
back of a length, 148kph/92mph and Shepherd misses again! This time Buttler fires in the throw and they don't chance one. England will have to chase 181, and probably the happier at halfway

slants one too far wide outside off, left alone. No swing back in that time clean strike down the ground, one bounce for four! Gave him the charge and went dead straight. Lovely followthrough of the bat as he made contact
floats it full outside off, gets a hint of inward movement, Rohit drives straight to cover
good comeback. Bowls a touch ahead of length and gets it to nip away from outside off, left alone
good, clean strike down the ground for four! Steps out and goes straight down the ground as Arshdeep went full on the stumps. Lovely timing, one bounce to the ropes.
gives Arshdeep the charge to try to slap this over cover, but bails out as he slants it outside his swinging arc.
full on off-stump, Rohit leans forward and drives back to Fazal who stops it on his followthrough
slower ball into the pitch but it's angled too far wide outside off, wide called peach! Hits the seam and nips away a hint from off stump to beat Gurbaz's tentative poke
has a big heave but misses! Rohit was looking to hit this wide of mid-on
walloped for six! Comes down the track and disdainfully pulls him in front of square to clear deep midwicket. Made it look ridiculously easy.
streaky boundary to get India off the mark! Rohit closes the bat face to try and work this through midwicket, gets a thick edge that rolls through Zazai's hands at short third.
good stop by Bumrah at short third! Saved three runs. This got big on Gurbaz as Arshdeep bowled into the pitch, he tried to angle it fine but got it high on the bat.
gently tucked towards short midwicket as they amble a run.
hits hard length on off from wide of the crease, punched to cover point
drifts a tossed up delivery across Rohit from around the stumps, drilled straight to mid-on

who else but that man, Jasprit, with the breakthrough. And it's the dangerous Gurbaz.  Incredible change of pace, rolls his fingers over the ball, the cutter lands outside Gurbaz's hitting arc as he tries to go leg side of the ball to belt it over cover, can only get a thin edge through to Pant who takes a regulation catch. Gurbaz was in no position to play the shot, got into an awkward position where he was reaching out to waft at the ball.
swept hard to deep backward square leg
goes full on off-stump, defended to cover
off the pad, tries to tickle it fine as this one drifts in, they'll scamper a leg bye
big movement back in. This one beats Zadran's inside edge. Ooohh, lovely
makes room and mistimes this slap to mid-off. Nabi bowled length, Rohit didn't quite get the room he would've liked
steered down to third man as he hops back to defend
tucked into the gap at midwicket as they jog the single
off-cutter on a length again as he slants this across, defended. Just one of that over along with a wicket
flatter one that Kohli punches back to Nabi. Good, tight over.
slants a length ball across the batter, punched to sweeper cover

big appeal for lbw, massive appeal. Not given by Paul Reiffel. Afghanistan have gone for a review. Bowls slower and fuller, Rohit is looking to heave this up and over deep square, but is struck on the pad. The only point of doubt was if the ball pitched within the stumps and going by the replays, it seems that it didn't. Ball tracking confirms as much, just pitched outside leg.  Not out it is  There was no late swing back in for Fazal that time either
floats it full on off, pushed to mid-off for a quick single
taps it gently to the man coming in from point for a quick single
crashed between backward point and short third. Just a hint of width from Arshdeep and Zadran latched onto it.
slants this too far wide outside off as Kohli leaves, wide called and rightly so driven straight to cover point. Fazal bowls short of a length as he slants it across, doesn't quite come on
Kohli puts that down at point!  Must say that was a regulation catch. Zadran punched it uppishly, this one bursts through as he leapt high to grab that over his head.
waits, waits and then steers this between point and short third, Kohli is off the mark
takes pace off as he bowls full on the stumps, dabbed into the off side for a single

dolly of a catch for Rashid at mid-on! Pulls his speed back from 134kph to 119kph. Bowls full and on the stumps, I suspect it was a  back-of-the-hand delivery  a cutter, Rohit toe-ends a heave and Rashid takes the skier quite comfortable. India have been rocked early.
punched to deep point
slips this down leg as he goes searching for swing perhaps, wide called. Good grab slips another one down leg and Pant merely lends direction by neatly tickling it to the fine leg boundary
tucks this straight to short fine as Axar fires this back in from around the stumps
shortish on off, Kohli punches it into the gap between deep midwicket and wide long-on. Thought about a second for a while
eased back to Axar, who does well to run to his left to stop that
tossed up outside off and Pant throws his hands at that and picks the gap at cover. They manage to come back for three as the ball stops on this heavy outfield
drifts a length ball back in, extra bounce off a length as he defends
swept firmly in front of square, Kohli will come back for the second quite comfortably

picks out extra cover!  The dots just got to Ibrahim. Moves leg side of the ball to go over the infield, but because Axar follows him, he doesn't quite have the room and he ends up hitting it straight to Rohit. Afghanistan in early trouble.
backs away to open up the off side and slap this through cover and point but is beaten
fired full on the stumps, defended back
plays the slog sweep, was in the air for a while and Gurbaz went 'caaaaatch' instinctively, but there's no one at deep square. They get two more as the ball plonks
gets a leading edge as this one doesn't turn, rolls to short third. Maiden to start for Axar
whips this to deep midwicket as they jog the single
looks like Zazai is foxed by Bumrah's cutter! This one grips the deck and takes off, Zazai is looking to work it to the leg side but ends up getting a leading edge to point. Dolly of a catch that.
backs away and slices this length delivery over point, square third quickly comes around to cut that off.
angles one full and at a furious pace from wide of the crease, dug back
advances and punches this short of a length delivery straight to cover
another off-cutter outside off from wide of the crease, Omarzai lets it go
takes pace off as he bowls length into the pitch from wide of the crease, Kohli punches straight to cover again
thick outside edge between keeper and slip! Rolls between the two as he looked to dig out this yorker-length delivery

slapped down the ground! Naveen bowls short and into the pitch but offers Kohli a lot of width, he could've hit it over cover if he wished, but Kohli decides to flat-bat this downtown. Waited for it and went boom. How many of you remember ' Kohli goes down the ground, Kohli goes out of the ground'?
gets behind the line as he defends solidly
squeezes one off a thickish inside edge to deep square. Kohli was looking to hit that over cover
shows the full face of the bat as he defends it past the bowler, they attempt a single that wasn't on, sanity prevails in the end
gently defends this slower length ball on middle
has a big heave at that, beaten as the ball drifts in and spins away.
turns this to backward square leg. They take off for a single. There's a direct hit at the striker's end but Pant seems to have made it comfortably. Yes, replays confirm as much.
lunges forward and defends back
reverse-swept over point! Tremendous hand speed and hand-eye. Nabi fired this full into the stumps and Pant still had the audacity to take him on. Hit it sweetly.
jabs it away as Axar bowls length on off. Gets it to turn away a hint

Naveen, what have you done? Not only has he dropped the catch at fine leg, but has also let this into the boundary. Completely misjudged this. Pant takes him on with the slog sweep but miscues it. Naveen did well to cover ground as he ran around the ropes, but missed it completely as the ball hit his chest and deflected to the boundary.
fuller on the stumps, eased down past the bowler
too much flight and Pant drills this over the infield at cover, races away to the boundary.
eased with the spin to long-off
lunges forward and drives straight to cover
a backfoot punch for six! That's an incredible stroke. Tremendous forearm strength to hit it up and over. Went deep back inside his crease and lofted it straight over long-on.

hits this back really hard, Kohli sees the possibility of this smashing into the stumps and drags his bat back quickly, even as the ball deflects off Nabi's fingers. No one's terribly excited and replays tell us why.
Loosener first up, punished. Overpitched outside off, Omarzai gets on one knee and slaps it through cover.
driven hard to long-off
Has to check his shot but ball goes mostly along the ground and in the gap to deep point. Was a full ball outside off
worked neatly towards deep square
Hardik focusing on length now. Hits that good length at 126ks. Beats the flick and hits high on the pad. Rolls towards point
shortish outside off. flays this straight to short third. Kohli was looking to bisect point and short third
Bumper around the armpit at 133ks. Was there an underedge as Naib went for a pull? Ball popped off the flank and hit grass. Point ran in but it was too far for him
rocks back and pulls this wrong'un to deep midwicket. Read that off the hand
Short and slowish, Naib is too early on the pull. Had to drag it from outside off too
attempts to sweep, but the ball deflects off the pad for four. The keeper couldn't have done much either as he was blinded by the line. It was a wrong'un
Slower bumper doesn't rise much but comes back in rather sharply. Naib pulls his arm back close to the chest while trying to get out the way. Manages to just about leave it

attempts a reverse-sweep but appears to be stone dead. Given out on field but Pant goes for a review. I suspect he's going to find out that wasn't a very good decision. This is a legbreak, almost full enough to hit his boot straight up. Pant got himself into a tangle attempting the shot, was in no position to play the shot in the end. Ball tracking confirms this would've smashed into the off stump.
Length around fourth, very little air given. Cut to backward point
bowls full'ish on off, dug out to long-off.
Full and looped up generously. Angles in towards off stump, Omarzai has a heave, gets it off the bottom of the bat. Ball lands safely in the cow-corner outfield and is stopped in the deep
whips this to deep midwicket to get off the mark
Length on fifth, punched to long-off
fired full but loses the line, slips it down leg. Wide called shortish and angling away, Kohli cuts hard to deep point

Chops the 94ks length ball outside off through backward point. Kuldeep runs to the left and tumbles over 360 degrees as he pulls the ball back in. The towel was tucked on the back of his trouser and it was flying close to the cushion. Third ump says he's good
reads the wrong'un off the pitch and dabs it to the man coming in from point.
Tucks the length ball to the bowler's right
chops the cut to backward point, they scamper a run

Given air again. On a fullish length and it's slog swept with limited timing. It was travelling along the grass, Arshdeep runs to the right from deep midwicket and splashes the ball to his tag-team partner running in from the other side. Did well to do it before his feet hit the cushion
reaches out to slap that short ball to sweeper cover

Full on fourth, worked to long-on. Umpire checking about the no-ball. Kuldeep's stride is over the crease, no-ball it will be to start Kuldeep's spell Darted on the pads, delivered from really close to the stumps. Naib's left leg makes room and he uses the hands thrash the ball across line for a four through square leg
too much flight outside off, Kohli reaches out to drill that into the gap at deep extra cover
Full outside off, 85ks, slog swept to long-on. Kuldeep flighting it this time
slaps this on the bounce to cover, a half-stop by Noor means they don't even get the run
Length on top of off, good bounce, 81ks. Azmat backs away and cuts to cover

looks to go inside-out, hit it wonderfully well but picks out long-off. Rashid has his second and Afghanistan are jubilant. Kohli saw this tossed up and hit it cleanly with the spin. He's distraught. Felt as if Kohli wanted to go deep extra cover, perhaps the lack of turn on that made him hit it a lot straighter.

Length on leg, Azmat stays legside of the ball and clips it to midwicket. Two bounces on the square before going to the keeper. Ump tells SKY, the fielder, not to do it. Simon Doull, on air, not a fan of that. Says reverse swing is a great skill and teams should try and get it as long as sandpaper isn't involved
wrong'un off a length, defended back
Full on leg, clipped to long-on
eased down to long-off as he gets off the mark
Fullish just outside off, cut to deep point
shot of the day! Fetches this from way outside off as SKY sweeps Rashid off his length to pick the gap at deep square.
belts this full toss into the gap at sweeper cover
...and taken down first up. Full ball on off from around the wicket, Azmat stood leg side of the ball and got a bit of room and walloped it over long-on for a 100-metre six
reaches out to slap this tossed up delivery straight to cover
Dinked to the side to turn strike
clobbered over long-off! Into his hitting arc, enough width on it as well and Dube climbed into it. Superb hit, used his reach to good effect. Smashed into the outer part of the sightscreen
Length on fifth, punched to long-off. 99ks
full on the stumps, worked to deep midwicket
Even more of a dart. 102ks on a slight back of length. Azmat makes room and works it to long-on
flicked into the gap at deep midwicket, aggressive running to come back for the second
Change-up. Given air, keeps it wide and full, gets big spin away. Naib has a heave across the line, misses
flicked to deep square as they jog the single
Fullish on off, taps it towards point but can't find the single. Drinks

Slow on a length, goes away with the angle outside off. Pulled to deep midwicket. Omarzai went back for the second and Jadeja almost got a direct hit from the deep. Lucky for the batter he didn't, but it wasn't far. Bullet throw though
Rashid errs in line and length, gets punished. Too full, down leg and all SKY had to do is help it fine, did so with a powerful sweep

Kuldeep gives the googly air and Naib skies it to the keeper. Pant went to the right and called to ensure he and Rohit didn't collide. Big smile follows from Pant as Rohit seems to say 'it is yours'. Was a full, wide ball that Naib tried to hack across the line. Might've expected it to be a stock ball but the turn away meant he hit it off the bottom of the bat

Tries to sweep him off a length, misses. 96ks leggie lands around off and spins away a bit, topspin on it gives the extra bounce. Ball beats bat and parries behind, off the wrist. SKY is alert and kicks the ball away from the stumps as it was rolling
Shoots it wide on a fullish length, beats the attempted push towards cover
Two out of three in favour of SKY with the sweeps. This is full enough for him to get to the pitch with a nice stride forward, wallops it across the line, square over the leg side
Full on leg, dinked to midwicket
Quick single to cover, fielder half-stopped it and the batters took off early. Was a full ball that was punched
Another googly but the spin works against Kuldeep. Fullish ball landed on middle and leg and beat the full-faced defence. Tickled the pad and beat Pant

Is that pad first? LBW not given, Rashid reviews almost immediately. I thought out, Shashank says bat first, let's see. Legbreak lands on a length around off, 94ks, a bit of drift in and spin too. Looks like pad first - back leg, top of the flap of the pad - as Dube tried to jam it down. Yeah, he's a goner. Three reds - hitting top of middle and off. Dube looked unsure whether to play off the front or back foot and in front of the body or under his eyes. In the end, it was an indecisive jab close to the body that was just over the pad, not close enough to ball to make contact.
Full around off, defended in front
Gives it a bit of air, well so it looks to me but that's 94ks. On the heart of a length, at the stumps, defended in front
Length on leg, clipped to midwicket
dolly at long-on, Afghanistan are unravelling very quickly. Jadeja gets this to turn off a length, it's an ugly hack against the turn from Omarzai but only managed to toe-end it.
Pitched up, arrows in towards middle and off - 127ks - Pandya's slightly inside the line and pushes it with soft hands towards cover point
cut away to deep point, Nabi off the mark
Leading edge but softly played again, goes past backward point's dive to the left and to deep third. Was a length ball around off that SKY tried to nudge with a closed bat-face
flatter one on a length from around the stumps, punched to long-off
