Hardik showing the virtues of powering the ball along the ground. Dances down and crunches it through cover after holding back a little, as the length ball was turning into a fullish ie. Did it with control and used his fast hands to good effect
beaten by the fizz and bounce off a length. Also got that to turn to beat the outside edge

Is SKY out backing up? Third-umpire referral made. Naveen was falling to the right and deflected the ball in his follow-through but SKY reached back fully and the bat was low at the start. He placed it well inside the crease in quick time. Not out
flays this to deep point
Pandya dances down again, (worthwhile tactic?) and clips it off a length to deep midwicket
turns this behind square as they jog the single
Length in the channel, taps it under the eye with an open bat face. Single to backward point
drifts one into middle and leg from wide of the crease, defended

Ridiculous shot from SKY. How on earth do you sweep a wide full toss through square leg? It seemed like a pre-meditated shot as his weight went across for the stride. But that had to almost double in length as the line of the ball was outside the off-side tramline. His body obliged, his reach was great too and he swept it without losing balance.

tossed up outside Najibullah's swinging arc, he goes after that one and is beaten. Wide called as it spun away sharply fired full and into the stumps, he's swept him over cow corner. Lovely hit. Off the middle of the bat. Kuldeep gave him pace and Najib only had a short leg side boundary to contend with.
Overpitched, close to the body too, SKY crunches it through cover. Finds the gap but deep extra cover manages to run to the right and stop it
chopped away into the off side, wide of cover for a single

Flair deluxe. SKY thumps the overpitched ball through cover and holds his pose. Didn't move his feet, got explosive power upon impact, and the gap to the left of mid-off. India look to be targeting Azmat.
driven straight to cover, excellent diving stop by Axar, saved a couple at the very least
Wide and full, driven to deep point, who's a bit straight
eased down to long-off
Pandya tries to drive the fullish ball outside off. Misses. Looked like he wanted to go square, went with power
breaks away sharply off a length. Najib looks to flat-bat that through cover but is beaten by the turn
Works it off the back foot to long-on
shortish outside off, cut away to sweeper cover
Beaten. Length ball outside off, lands around fifth and gets a bit of spin away to beat the push with a fully open bat-face
tucked to the man coming in from deep square, food running to come back for the second
Full on leg, 94ks, Pandya slides his back foot leg side to make room and drives to mid-off
nudged wide of short midwicket for a single
Pandya might be looking to see off Rashid but the leggie's pouncing. Bowls a fullish length, lands it just outside off and gets a bit of turn to beat the full-faced front-foot push
cut away to deep point
Fullish on leg, Pandya is able to get behind the line and blocks it to the right of the bowler
shortish on middle, there's a hint of turn and bounce, worked into the midwicket region

Rashid looks to finish with a tempter but errs and Pandya capitalises. Was a loopy, wide length ball that was delivered from behind the stumps but Rashid signals that slipped out a bit. Pandya is able to cut it hard along the ground through cover point
driven with the spin to long-off
Back of length, into the pitch just outside off. Pulled along the ground to long-on
cutter on a length around off-stump, steered straight to point
Punches it in front. Another dot

has it come off the helmet? Pant runs back to take the catch. Pandya enquires but umpire Rod Tucker signals leg byes. Nabi looks to pull this 129kph bumper, but was way too early into the pull. The ball lobbed off the back part of the helmet as they took a leg bye.

SKY looks to sweep it off a ridiculous line again, realises the full wide one is too far despite another split-like lunge. Opens the face last second to guide it to deep third. Good adjustment all around

Smoked over square leg. Pace-on length ball was going towards fifth stump, got a bit of extra bounce but Zadran swung across from the waist and got it off the bottom-third of the bat but enough for it to sail over
Wide and fullish, Pandya tries to reach out to lash it over cover. Rotates while losing a bit of balance but manages to hit it along the ground to deep cover

Change of plan from Hardik almost ends up as a no-ball. Went for the wide yorker and it didn't land that far from going away into the grass. Let go LBW call from India. Not given, Pant not confident but Rohit goes for it. Did it land outside leg? Seam-up ball was full and beat the flick, hit low on the front leg. It is indeed pitching outside leg. India's fielders are back in position as the call is made

Easy game for photographers when SKY's batting, says Kass Naidoo as he holds the pose again after nailing a drive. This was too, Azmat's pace is easy enough for the batter to pump it through the line with a full flourish fuss-free
Back of length outside off, pulled across. Long-on runs to the right to keep it to one
Wide on a back of length. Too wide. Let go, keeper fumbles Guides it to deep third with good wristwork
Low full toss is clothed to mid-off. It was on middle and hurried Zadran a bit
Length around off, Nabi stays leg side and belts it across with a flat-bat. Off the upper-half of the bat, so it balloons off into the grass and rolls to long-on
Wide on a fullish length, sharp angle. 89ks, slapped to long-off

Excellent catch from Arshdeep, Bumrah - as often - can do no wrong. He saw Zadran back away, was almost at the return crease as he reached out to the 141ks full ball zooming in towards middle, whisked it away but found short third to perfection. Ball hit Arshdeep's hands hard but he clung on before he wrung his palms right after
A bit of drift on the fullish ball just outside off, SKY opens the face and checks the punch. Stopped at point

Nutmegged past the keeper. No bat on it in fact. 140ks yorker at the feet, as block-hole as it gets. Rashid looks to whip it across, misses. His front leg was out the way and the ball snuck through the gap between the feet

SKY takes the risk, doesn't middle it but ball lands in the outfield. Deep cover, running to the left, takes it on the bounce. Was a length ball that he turned to a full one by dancing down, the bat-face opened on impact which meant he didn't middle it. Not too far though
Hits midwicket and Nabi wants a run. Not on, the throw comes in. No direct hit, so he's safe

Great smarts from Pandya. Noor stayed around the wicket and bowled it in his direction. Got a length ball that he lofted over cover. Forced a bit as it seemed to hit higher than on the middle but still cleared the infield easily
Slow and into the pitch. A bit of room but extra bounce means Rashid has no chance of connecting with the cut despite a massive wind-up

That's almost hit the comm box, this is vintage Pandya. Felt like 2017 as he took a step towards the line and pumped it off a length. Flat-bat, fully stable base and step-hit it with a rotational arc. 88 metres, hits the glasslike thing above the stand. 'i could have caught this six if not for the glass,' Sid Monga, who is in the press box, says.
Goes for the helicopter shot but can only drill out the full ball to long-on
Full and a bit leg side, beats the sweep and hits the pad
Slow and back of a length, goes away with the angle through fifth stump after beating bat
Makes room and gets a shortish ball at the stumps that doesn't rise. Cut to deep extra cover
Tries to launch it downtown. He bends his knees to get a bit lower and cloths a through-the-line swing. Looked like he was in trouble but the ball landed a few feet in front of long-off
Very high... but clears long-off. Was a full ball just outside off at 81ks, Nabi got the high-backlift out and launched it
Wide yorker. Looked pace-on. Driven to deep point

Nabi goes high again but can't clear the long boundary. Hit against the wind too and it means a shot that looked to be sailing into the stands ends up in Jadeja's hands at deep midwicket. Despite the last ball going for six, Kuldeep went full and slow. Knew the equation was in his favour. Line was a bit too straight and Nabi seemed to have gotten a good chunk on it. But the air wasn't in his favour.

High six, far six. Amazing how he does it. This was a vertical-bat shot to a back-of-length ball hit from deep in the crease. Maybe the ball was slower, I'm not sure, which allowed him a bit of time but then he'd have had to manufacture pace, which was still a tough ask. He did so by standing still as ever and mowing it
Reverse carted well over backward point. It's on the up and goes for a one-bounce four
SKY brings up an enterprising 27-ball fifty. Fulish ball outside off, he hacks it over wide long-on, wide of the fielder
Noor tries to go for another reverse, goes well across which is too much room in the end. The full ball down leg beats bat

This shows why the six two balls ago was so good. SKY tried to launch it from a back of length again but toes it right up. The cutter was going away from his body, the line - that was the difference, and he couldn't whack it across the line. Nabi runs in from long-off and takes the skier. Excellent innings though
Pushes the full ball around off to mid-off for a quick single
Length on fifth, Noor opens the face to guide it. Can't keep up with the pace
Shortish ball outside off is cut to deep point
Wide and full, Noor tries to heave across. Gets nothing on it
Wide and full, Jadeja takes a big step towards the line and tries to sweep it. Doesn't middle it but gets it to midwicket
Length ball in towards fourth stump, tries to belt it with a flat-bat. Cloths it to long-on
Slower one on a shortish length is bunted late. Backward point doesn't collect it properly, communication between batters is a bit muffled and they don't take a run

Wide and fullish, 138ks, lands around sixth stump and went well outside the tramline. Rashid has a slash and misses Skied, taken at deep third. Full and close to the tramline, Rashid tries to reach it to whip it but can only get it off the bottom of the bat

Bonus. Down leg on a length, goes past the attempted shovel Slot ball has been smacked on top of the terrace. This was on leg, angling into him from a wide-of-the-crease delivery from Pandya. The pace was there and Pandya cleared the front foot and clubbed it.

Naveen comes in, and goes right away. Tried to pull a shortish ball from Arshdeep across the line. The seam-up ball came around rib-height and took the top edge as Naveen tried to muscle it into the neighbouring town. Easy catch for Pant, Arshdeep on a hat-trick

Down leg? No, Paul Reiffel gives it. Pandya reviews. Was a 133ks full ball that Pandya tried to clobber across the line again. Front foot made a bit of way, back foot right in front of leg peg. Ball beat the inside edge and hit him around the shin. Hawk-Eye projects that Naveen's angle is too sharp and it'd go down leg.

Edge saves Farooqi, earns him four too. Was a full ball around middle that he tried to defend in front. Was a tentative push with low hands and it took the outside edge and scooted between keeper and slip
Pandya misses out, falls to the wide ball that sat up. He tried to carve it on the up, got it off the bottom of the bat and found the sweeper. Gets a warm reception from his team-mates
Tries to drive down the ground, gets a thick inside edge to the leg side. They steal two
Full around fourth, pushed to cover
Yorked proper. Jadeja danced down and Farooqi hit hit boot after beating the attempted flick. Ball is close enough to deny the single
Misses the yorker, Noor punches the full toss on off stump firmly. Finds cover
Jadeja hits the gap skilfully. Was walking down but stopped after noticing the length of the ball was shortish and that it was angling in. Pulled it between deep square leg and deep fine leg
Fullish ball around fifth, pushed to cover. 123ks

Death-overs dismissal. Very whacky. Was a slower one that was as short as it could get, gripped and popped up like a tennis ball. Seemed to be going above head but the room had Jadeja try to upper cut it over short third. But there was no pace to work with and it ends up like a forehand gone wrong
Length on off, looked like another cutter, Noor tries to work it across the line but chipped it. Managed to clear the non-striker, who doesn't want the single
Pitched up, clipped leg side and they sneak two
Length just outside off, beats the cut. Noor not having much of a clue and who can blame him
Makes room and gets followed by a low fully, all he can do is jam it to midwicket
Length down leg, beats the flick but may have flicked the trouser on the way to the keeper. They sneak a leg bye, which is all that cost India in the penultimate over
Length outside off, tries to clobber it. Edges it to the sweeper on the off side, Farooqi doesn't want to take strike

Starts with a wide yorker, misses the line. Let go Nails it this time. Pace-off, Axar takes a small step across and jams his bat over the ball and meets air. Looks like a tighter call on second viewing, might've been wide
Slower one is fullish and wide. Noor tries to have a hack over long-on, misses by a mile
Axar takes a step across and Naveen looks to go wide. Yorker attempted, full toss arrives. Axar carves it off the top edge, gets two to cover
Shortish pace-on ball around fourth stump, 132ks, beats the pull and goes to the keeper
Sweeper moved straighter and Axar crashes the wide full toss where the fielder was. Another yorker gone wrong, Axar needed to move very little and timed the slash well
Whoa, that came from nowhere. Noor stands upright and pulls the shortish ball from just under the shoulder. Flat six, 69 metres far.
Cuffed down the ground, one of long-off and long-on cuts it off but can't stop two. Good running
Arshdeep nails the fourth-stump yorker. Noor has hit feet out the way and tries to jam it leg side. Plays well inside the line
Slow and wide, Axar tries to guide the full ball behind square. Toes it and gets it much finer than intended. Luckily it ends up ballooning over short third

Last ball... has to be rebowled. The full ball is well outside the tramline Take three needed. Same line off a fullish length beats the heave. Pant has to jam his knee to collect it Sliced, Rohit takes it. Arshdeep lunges with a big smile as India complete a 47-run win. Full at the stumps, Noor tried to pump it through the line and got a thick outside edge. Found cover.

Second wide of the over. Fullish ball was well outside the tramline, let go Slower one into the pitch. Very short, wide-ish line, beats the pull. Keeper lobs it really high but Naveen is able to collect it run back and beat Axar on the race to run him out
round the wicket, on the stumps, pushed into the covers
starts with a very full one at off stump, some swing, jabbed into backward point
brings out the reverse sweep, gets a big top edge that flies in the air down to deep third
again, a yorker around off stump, comes out as a low full toss, defended square into the off side
short of a length, worked into the on side for a scampered single

through him! Starc strikes early, as he so often does. Full at the stumps, Tanzid caught on the crease as he defends, takes the toe of the bat, bobbles into the crease and back into the stumps. Perhaps didn't bounce as much as Tanzid expected, but was full and he wasn't really forward
goes for the drive, gets a thick inside edge that isn't too far away from leg stump
full at middle, defended to the on side
pushed firmly into the covers
another yorker at off stump, not sure if entirely by design, defended back to the bowler
steps outside leg stump, the bowler follows him, plays up to mid-on
gets this away! Dragged down a little short and wide, he takes advantage with a square drive over backward point
short of a length, straight, defended to the on side
did that carry? Short outside off, a slashing square drive reaches point in the blink of eye. Yes, that's a drop. Low, but a clear chance
outside off, back of a length, punched square of the wicket to point
short of a length, straight, square drives to backward point
tight line, angling in at off stump on back of a length, defended into the covers
slammed through the off side, stays leg side of the ball, drives through cover, not perfectly timed
fuller outside off, he gets forward and drives to mid-off, 133kph
short of a length, gets underneath and pulls very high over the leg side, lands safely before deep square leg can get there
hangs back in the crease and punches nicely square of the wicket but can't find the gap. Five dot balls.
pushed across outside off, Head throws everything into a drive and misses...142kph
back of a length at off stump, played to the bowler. Immaculate stuff from Hazlewood. He starts with a maiden
width outside off and he's laced that square of the wicket, a very powerful cut through point. One of Head's strengths
moves to leg and drives strongly into the covers
pushes this down the leg side at 141kph full at off stump, driven straight, doesn't beat mid-on
now he goes leg side, down on his back knee and slog sweeps miles back onto the grass banks
keeps it full outside off, basically yorker length, steered square into the off side with an open face
outside off, drives to cover
low full toss outside off, drives square but finds the fielder at point
pushed into the stumps, driven past a diving cover, long off gets around
full and wider outside off, he stretches for it, drives again and again picks out Stoinis. Nine dots for Das
nearly dragged on! Head went miles outside leg, was a very full ball, takes a thick inside edge into the pad and trickles towards the stumps
drags the length back outside off, steered down to third with an open face and opens his account
exposes the stumps again, drives into the off side. Good little contest
this is sweetly driven, parried by Starc in his follow through, a tight single as it rebounds towards mid-off
there's some aggression! Great strike. Gives himself room outside leg and advances at Hazlewood, launches him down the ground over long on
over the wicket, 140kph, full outside off, driven into the covers
outside off, back of a length, steered into backward point
hammered! Short of a length outside off, stand and deliver from Warner as he pulls it past mid-on
good length outside off, 135kph, pushed into the covers
tucked off the pads in front of square

tries to invent something, walks across his crease and plays the scoop, doesn't connect as Hazlewood pushes it well down the leg side tries the same again, walks across, this is back of a length around off stump and gets taken on the body via some edge
more power! Crunched. Just back of a length, perfectly good ball, really, and Head flays it wide of mid-off, on the up
short of a length at the body, pulls and doesn't get much timing. A little cramped for room
round the wicket, follows him with a shorter one, Head is cramped on the pull
full outside off, driven into the cover ring
over the leg side! Back of a length outside off, Head rocks back and pulls it massively over deep midwicket. Brutal
full at the stumps, gets a leading edge towards mid-off as he closes the face
over the wicket, full at the stumps, driven to cover and there's a misfield. That's poor from Shakib
good length at off stump, 142kph, defended
on the pads as he follows him, flicked in the air to deep square leg
takes this on...that's an excellent shot. Short of a length outside off, drags the pull in front of square
worked off the stumps into midwicket
low full toss outside off, nicely driven through the covers, doesn't have the legs to go all the way
a short ball, 133kph, cramps Head for room as he pulls, finds mid on
just past short third! Short outside off, played with an angled faced, Warner leaps full length to his left and isn't far from it. Good hang time!
launched down the ground! Lofts through the line, straight down the ground. Served up nicely from the Fizz
143kph, driven into the covers. Better over for Bangladesh
short outside off, again gives himself room, goes up and over backward point. He's on the charge
swept from around off stump to deep square leg, brings up the fifty stand
full and down the leg side, a diving stop from Wade back of a length at off stump, 140kph, driven into the covers off the back foot
pushed into the pads as Head sweeps, deflects past the stumps and the keeper
strongly flicked off the pads, good use of the wrists, sends it over wide mid-on
defended off the stumps to the covers
gets back outside off, driven square into the covers
tucked off the pads through square leg
a bouncer, flies over the batter and the keeper...given wides. Ballooned off the surface uses his feet, drives a short-of-a-length delivery towards mid-off without much timing
leans back and straight-pulls this through mid-on, think he was aiming a touch wider
back of a length, straight, takes a thick inside edge and dribbles to the on side
dragged down short and that's a freebie, Warner rocks back and pulls over deep midwicket
pushed across wide outside off, Shanto doesn't connect with his drive. Close to a wide.
full at middle and leg, turned through midwicket
over the wicket, flat-bats a drive down the ground
over the wicket, touch short outside off, he latches into this quickly, pulls powerfully through midwicket with perfect placement
the reverse sweep, gets it behind point and into the gap, races away down to deep third
full at middle, flicked off the pads through midwicket
tossed up just outside off. Turning into Warner. He tries a slog sweep but misses it altogether
pushes this into the pads, worked to short fine leg, probably missed out there
full ball on middle. Stays on the back foot and worked off his waist to the leg side
a legbreak which spins, dabbed towards short third
beats Head! Slows it down. Length ball just outside off. Turning in too. Head tries to drag a shot across the line, from outside off, and he misses the swat. Off stump pegged back.
on leg stump, looks to flick it away, takes the pad behind square on the leg side
one slip in place. Full ball outside off. Solid turn away. A confidently delivered ball, and Marsh lets it go
around the stumps. Length ball around off. Skidding through. Pushed to cover
round the wicket, very wide outside off and called short outside off, flies over the top edge as Shanton flays at it off the back foot
length ball on off. Pushes Warner onto the back foot with this skiddy ball. Knocked to the non-striker's left, and Mahedi runs across to intercept
edged, wide of the keeper! Short outside off, angling in at the left hander, not sure if he was entirely in control of that but he was aiming roughly that direction. Fifty stand
length ball outside off and cut to deep point for a single
pushed square into the off side
full ball on middle, and he punches it off the back foot, with the full face of the bat. To Mahedi
short of a length, pulled out to deep backward square
length ball, fourth-stump line. Makes some room to cut but misses. Mahedi groans
that's nicely played this time, more in control as he glides this from outside off down to third who gets around the boundary
full ball on off stump. Back-foot punch to the off side and the throw from cover hits the stumps at the batter's end. But Marsh was in as they never attempted a run. Mahedi finishes 0-22
fuller outside off, drives in the air over the off side out to deep point
full outside off, steps forward and drives to long-off
full ball on off. Dip and turn. Warner presses forward and fends to the leg side
wider outside off, drives into the covers
tossed up on leg and he drills this through the leg side, with the turn, to Shakib at cow corner
misses the sweep! Goes straighter this time, Litton aims across the line and plays over the top of it. Deflects off the back leg into the stumps. Lovely variation from Zampa
short ball around off. Straightens. Marsh gets down on one knee and sweeps towards backward square leg for a single
big sweep first ball, taken on the back leg, appeal for lbw but missing leg
full ball on middle. Warner opts to stay on the back foot and pushes a shot through the on-side to long on
outside off, leans back and drives square to deep point

appeal for lbw and given right away by Illingworth! Full ball on the stumps, but perhaps sliding down leg with Marsh missing the sweep? Marsh reviews. Replays show Marsh is struck on the knee-roll after the ball pitched on middle and slid towards leg. Ball-tracking confirms it is clipping the outer half of leg stump, so Marsh will have to keep walking, albeit on an "umpire's call."
a shorter delivery, a googly, pulls to deep square leg
full  ball around off. Brings out the reverse sweep, and well timed, but straight to backward point
round the wicket, tapped away from off stump into the covers
full ball, wider outside off but not wide enough, and that allows Maxwell to play a punchy drive, through the covers for four
worked off the pads behind square
full ball on middle stump, and pushed to long off for a single. Mustafizur takes a tumble on the followthrough while trying to stop the ball
gets forward, pushes to the off side, can't find a gap
around the stumps to Warner. Full ball just outside off and the slap from Warner is stopped smartly by point. Warner grimaces, perhaps he thought he should've put it away
shorter and wider outside off, onto the back foot and cracks a drive wide of the cover sweeper. Terrific shot

short ball on middle. Warner drops his knees and gets his head out of the ball's way. Mustafizur bowled that into the wicket while also rolling his fingers over. Like Cummins these days, although Mustafizur has always had this ball
fuller at the stumps, flicked into the on side, Wade chases from behind the stumps
short ball on middle, but this time the bounce is more spongy. Warner hangs back and absolutely clatters a pull in front of square for four
taken at short third! Maxwell strikes, and he's pumped. Rishad charged down the pitch, lost his shape on a hoick to the leg side, takes a thick outside edge and it's neatly taken by Zampa
slower ball, full just outside leg stump. Gently knocked to square leg for a single.
Starc's back to bowl out. Short and wide ball, and Shanto attempts a cut by reaching out but misses
fullish ball on middle. Solid bounce. Warner looks busy, pressing forward but then stepping back, and then nudges the ball towards point
full ball outside off. Pace off. Caresses a drive but can't beat cover
reverse sweep for four! Full around leg stump, and Warner is quick to get in position. Hammers it over conventional point, and there's nobody in the deep
short ball on off. Bounce isn't prolific. Attempts a pull, but hits him on the body before rolling away to deep third. Appears to have been a slower ball
tossed up, lands just outside leg. Warner lifts his back leg and caresses a flick through the midwicket region to the deep
full toss around off. Bunted to long on, but you can say Shanto missed out on a solid opportunity off a loose ball

ridiculous! Flat six over wide long on. Full ball, outside off stump. Maxwell stretches his arms out, and then brings the bat down with such precision that his checked leg-side swat flies over wide long on
short ball on middle and leg. Angling down the leg side as he raises his arms around the stumps. Full just outside off and driven towards cover
once again to wide long on but Tanzim at long on runs around and gets a hand to it. This was a tossed-up full toss outside off, and Maxwell once again swatted a shot away to the wide-long on region.
short ball around off stump. Rides the bounce and knocks it away to deep third. Finishes with 1-21
expensive over although this one is a dot. Full toss wide outside off and Maxwell is disappointed not being able to clear cover
good length ball outside off. Bit of turn in. Shapes to cut but can't put it away. Hit to the off side

a 34-ball fifty! Gets there in style with a six. Full ball on his shin, and Warner absolutely hammers a flick over deep square leg. He was so sure it was going for six that he didn't even look at the ball's direction
around the stumps. Full ball just outside off. Bit of turn away. Shanto throws his bat at this and clatters a shot towards deep cover
length ball on middle and leg, and he pulls with disdain. In the air, and deep square leg can take a catch, but the ball lands just a metre short. Team 100 and play is interrupted by rain again.
good length ball outside off. Slaps a cut, in the air, but lands just beyond the cover point fielder. Man in the deep scurries across to keep tit down to two
full ball outside off and driven along the carpet to deep extra cover where the outfielder has to cover a lot of area
full ball around off, and clipped towards square leg for a single
full ball around off. Najmul attempts a reverse sweep but misses. Hits him on the pad and squirts away. They appeal for LBW but not given out. Was impact on pad outside off stump?
googly. Length ball around off. Bit of turn in. Uncomfortably cut to the off side. That had Wade excited!
length ball outside off. Bit of turn away. Hridoy's cut is mistimed, hit towards point
mowed across the line! Slightly fuller from Zampa, but still outside off stump. Hridoy gets down on one knee and drags this legbreak to deep midwicket
knocked away to long on for a single
good length ball on leg stump. Tries to pull off the back foot. Hits his body

plumb! Shanto's fifty against Australia will have to wait. Full ball on leg and middle. Sliding across a bit. Shanto gets low to sweep but misses. Hits him on the knee roll and given swiftly out. Shanto does not bother reviewing, but you wonder if he should've atleast considered one? Bounce could've been a factor as well as whether it was hitting off stump. Replay confirms that's crashing into off. Good review saved.
back of a length ball on off and knocked off his body to square leg for a single
good length ball on leg. Shakib moves slightly off side and works it off his hip to deep backward square leg
full ball, wider outside off. Pace off this time. Hridoy sticks the bat out and bunts a shot towards the off side
rolls his fingers over this ball. Fullish ball around leg. Fast offspinner turns towards middle. Knocked to the leg side, with soft hands
short ball, this time full pace. Around leg and middle. Ducks under it good length ball around off stump. Moves to the off side and tries to play a late cut. Can't play it perfectly.
full ball just outside off stump. Opens the bat's face and glances a shot to cover point
full ball on leg. Turning down leg. Shakib closes the bat's face and guides a shot delicately to fine leg for a couple
full ball around off. Slow through the air. Toe-ends a drive to long on
good length ball outside off.Extra bounce. Cut to the off side but he was surprised with the bounce. Did that land on the seam?
length ball outside off and cut in front of square for a single
length ball on middle. Sliding away from Shakib. He muscles a cut through the off side for a single
slog swept and beats two outfielders on the leg side! Full ball just outside off. Hridoy gets low and smacks it between the fielders at wide long on and deep midwicket. Zampa finishes with 2-24
good length ball around leg stump. Pace taken off.  Shakib backs away but he ends up cramping himself with the bowler's line. Tucked to the leg side
full ball on leg stump. Makes a bit of room, then breaks his wrists while flaying an inside out drive through the off side
full ball around off and worked off his shin to midwicket. Team 100!
back of a length ball on middle and off. Shakib tries to back away and slap a shot over the infielders on the off side. But it is mistimed and very nearly carries to cover point for a catch
good length ball on middle. Hridoy attempts to use his wrists and play a leg-side flick. Mistimed towards short third
rolls his fingers over this ball. Fullish around off and tucked off his pads to square leg. Slowly played, so enough time to call for the second run

another Shakib failure at this T20 World Cup. Overpitched straight ball on leg. Shakib's hands are cramped, and he tries to adjust and play over mid-on instead. However the ball pops right up and the bowler Stoinis himself calls for the catch. Smart cutter delivered from the medium pacer
full ball on middle, and clipped smartly to the leg side for a single
much needed! Half a dozen through Hridoy's favourite area of cow corner. Length ball just outside off. Sits up at a comfortable height, and he waits on the back foot before depositing it
strong wrists on offer! Fuller ball, on his toes, and Hridoy uses his wrists to flick it exquisitely, playing it behind square. The Bangladesh fans find their voice again!
toe-ends an attempted yorker to cover. The drive can't beat the infield
Hridoy will keep strike as Stoinis concedes 14 in the over. Full and wide ball caressed to Warner at cover
good length ball around off. Bunted gently to square leg, where there's acres of space for two
full ball around off. Cutter this time. Hridoy drives to long on for a single
full ball just outside off. Pushed to left of mid-off for a quick single
full ball on middle stump and clipped to deep midwicket. Only a single, but the throw from the deep is a direct-hit!

dragged onto his stumps! Short of good length ball outside off. Mahmudullah attempts a pull, but it takes the bottom-half of the bat and crashes into his poles. Cummins rolled his fingers over the ball on this occasion

guided straight to deep third! Back of a length ball outside off, and Mahedi hangs back and tries to play an upper cut, but the ball flies off the bat's face and goes straight to Zampa lurking at deep third. He'll be on a hat-trick if he bowls the 20th.
attempts a yorker, ends up as a low full toss outside off. Sliced to deep third where Starc cleans up

full ball around leg stump,  and Taskin plays a smart clip off his legs, sending the ball to fine leg. But Starc is committed, running around the boundary line and then putting his body on the line by sliding. Saves the boundary

caught? Or just fell in front of Wade? Or maybe there was no edge at all! Let's see what happened here. Back of a length slower ball on middle. Taskin tries to pull, but it hits his shoulder, and pops up for Wade who dives forward to grab. They don't review, and save it
spongy bounce on this short ball on off stump. Taskin pulls in front of square and the ball is smacked towards cow corner. Stoinis and Zampa are in that region

yorker length ball on off. Taskin knocks it to the off side and they scurry for one. Hazlewood runs across, picks the ball  and aims at the stumps at the bowler's end with a quick release. But he misses and that allows Bangladesh to take a second run
gets it away! Hazlewood tries for the yorker. Ends up as a dipping low full toss. Taskin slices a shot by backing away and has just about enough to get the ball between cover and mid off

Hat-trick for Pat Cummins! Slower ball, just outside off. Hridoy moves to the off side to play a scoop over short fine leg but he has lobbed it right to that fielder. A wry smile from Cummins, and his team-mates congratulate him. The seventh hat-trick in T20I World Cups. The second Aussie since Brett Lee, also against Bangladesh
full ball on off and Tanzim bunts a shot past the non-striker to Starc at long on
back of a length slower ball around off stump from around the stumps. Drags a mistimed pull to the leg side. Enough time to pick up two, all crucial runs
cutter, length ball wide outside off.  Mistimes a cut to point and they jog across for one. Could they have attempted a two?
good length ball on off stump. Tanzim commits to a shot and lifts it over the leg side. In the air but lands well short of David at deep square leg. Two more
Bangladesh finish on 140/8 as this full ball outside off is slashed to Zampa at deep third. Bit of shower coming across the ground as the innings comes to a close.
Starts on the hip - and Kagiso Rabada takes a wonder grab at leg gully! False alarm - it flew off the thigh pad
over the wicket, good length around middle and leg, hint of shape and tucked to midwicket
Full and across, Salt tries to hit the white off the ball and misses completely. Taken at head-height by Quinton behind the stumps
touch shorter, Hendricks attempts to work off his pads, can't get it through
Short... and bang! The sound off the bat was like a bullet from a gun, as Salt picks the length quickly and smears it over the square leg fence
on a length, angled across the bows and steered to backward point
Length, into the top of off, timed well, but straight to cover
full and inviting, 133kph/82mph and not much swing. Hendricks stretches into a drive but picks out cover
Into leg stump, movement early from the hand, worked through midwicket for a single
fullish, Hendricks just opens the face this time, pushes through point for a couple to get going
Outside off, pushed tidily down the ground but well-intercepted by Aiden Markram shuttling across from mid off
touch shorter, 132kph/82mpg outside off, tapped down into the covers. Watchful start from Reeza
Hung outside off, Buttler reaches for a drive and almost gets it to cover on the full...
round the wicket, lobbed on a length around the line of off, de Kock leans into a forward block
Into middle and leg, looked like it might have stopped in the pitch. Buttler almost falls over himself playing into the leg side but keeps his balance to nab. a single to wide mid on
flighted, spinning away a touch, chopped into the point region going back for a single
Lifted down the ground! Not timed, but well struck from Salt, elevating a drive as Rabada goes for that neither full nor short length
full, 86kph/54mph, drifting in with the arm, Hendricks is forward and works through midwicket
Straighter, punched back to the bowler
tossed up and pushed into the covers looking to come forwards

Shorter, and a cutter, but skids down the leg side as Salt lets out an "oi" as he swivels far too early on an attempted pull Another down the leg side, this one a straight up-and-down off a length attempting to cramp Salt for room Salt goes to a stunning catch at over! The hero of St Lucia just two days ago has to depart, tempted into an aerial drive that is plucked out of the heavy air by Reeza Hendricks, sprawling to his left - feet off the ground - for the Proteas first wicket of the morning! Game on
comes down the track, clumps past mid-on! QdK uses his feet and gets a decent chunk of it, Archer unable to get across. First boundary of the day for SA
Attempted yorker ends up as a low full toss, pushed away through the leg side and Bairstow is off the mark
goes again, smoked beyond the reach of a leaping long-off! Not quite to the pitch, not quite out of the screws... but enough on it to clear Brook running around, SA get their first six!
Wide outside off, knocked on the head down to deep third, wide of the fielder for a couple
length ball, 129kph/80mph on leg stump, Hendricks tucks it past midwicket
Carved away... but stopped well by Miller at backward point
back of a length and carved through backward point, Salt has work to do tracking around the rope
Into a length, played on top of middle stump, into the covers for a single
full length, hint of away swing, de Kock drives and gets one into the leg side
Beauty! Shape in, movement away with a bit of lift, leaving Buttler's outside edge for dead!
shortish on the hip, blocked to the on side

Yorker, just outside off stump, dug out to cover by Buttler for a scampered single. Oh my... Jansen's overstepped! Low full toss, skewed away for four! It's an ugly, ugly shot - Bairstow's bottom hand comes off the bat as he reaches low for the attempted yorker and gets a thick, thick inside edge to the fine leg boundary
full on the pads, clipped out to deep backward square leg
Short, clothed to backward square leg, where the fielder is out
short and cramping him for room, tucked off the body through square leg for one more
back of a length from over the wicket, 139kph/86mph and nibbling back a touch. De Kock gets an inside edge into his groin, I think

Take back your beer South Africa, that's a horrible drop! Bairstow lifts inside out to deep third, where Klaasen runs in to meet. It's in his big bear hands for a moment before spilling out! He got there in good time, too. Costly miss
fuller, de Kock uses the pace, swishes it over fine leg! Just whipped off the pads, 141kph/88mph and it soars over the left hand of Topley as he attempts in vain to get around
Squared up, defended down the pitch
munched over midwicket! Full and belted, de Kock on the charge after a quiet-ish start. Hit in front of square this time, flies 88 metres out towards the stands
Same again, only Rabada is a bit lax going after the ball which lands into the leg side and Bairstow charges through - bumping shoulders with the bowler - to pocket a cheeky single
uppercut now, four more! Archer keeps pace on the ball, dug in but slightly wide and de Kock plays it insouciantly up and over the ring down to deep third
Slower delivery off a length, pushed one-handed out into the covers
pace off, dabbed into the covers for one
Bairstow steps to the leg side, Rabada follows him, limiting the room he has to swipe, scuffing down to mid on
drops short and gets banged through midwicket! Hendricks in on the act now, pulling his first boundary. Archer's first over disappears for 21
An attempt to run the ball down to third meets the fielder up in the circle behind square. Excellent over from Rabada, which could have been so much better...
Drifting onto off stump, Buttler shapes inside out and punches two through cover
back of a length, steered away behind square, QdK playing late and angling the ball down into the gap for another boundary
Buttler gets the ol' reverse out! Picks the line - outside off - early, flips the hands and swishes over the ring down to third
fifth stump, good length and de Kock knocks it on the top of the head towards point for one
Punched down to long off for a single
pace off, full and sliding down the leg side angled across the right-hander, Hendricks is forward to drive, won't beat the cover ring
Bairstow hands the strike back to Buttler, cutting down to wide long off as Maharaj is a touch short
slower ball, tucked off the pads towards midwicket
Flatter, bit more round-arm, with drift from the breeze, defended into the off side
back of a length, another slower ball down at 121kph. Hendricks runs it down to deep third. That's the SA 50 up, inside five overs
Same again, this one a touch shorter forcing Buttler to adjust as the ball rears up a little more
lentgh on the stumps, tickled through backward square leg for one more
Starts full, outside off, Bairstow swings and gets another inside edge, away through to fine leg for a single

length ball, just enough room for de Kock to cut, staying low and he forces it between backward point and cover. Livingstone nearly manages to slide into the rope with the ball, but tosses it behind him before doing the dosy-do and throwing it back in
Length, into Buttler, who is running down the pitch and wearing this on the hip, into square leg for a leg bye
round the wicket to Hendricks, who defends back down the track
Wide, bit of shape away, missed by Bairstow, who swings hard
115kph cutter, sliding on to the pads, nurdled around the corner for one

Over the top, but no timing whatsoever from Bairstow as he gave himself room and tried to find a boundary to long off. The field is up, but Markram at mid off was able to catch up with that one just before it plugs
short ball, slammed flat over midwicket! Picks the back-of-the-hand slower ball and ab-so-lute-ly wallops it for his fourth six
Muted appeal as Bairstow is almost undone by a yorker that scuttles between bat and off stump. Was there a noise there? Nope, umpires unmoved and South Africa aren't fussed about a review
pitched up and dinked into the covers coming across
Driven, but Baartman gets a hand on it in his follow-through to keep it to one. And with that, England have their lowest six-over Powerplay of 2024...
another slower ball from round the wicket, worked leg side
pushed through outside off, Hendricks drops back and punches through cover
Slow delivery - 50.5mph - Bairstow tries to impart his own pace on the ball with a wristy reverse, but finds the fielder at short third
tossed up from over the wicket, 86kph outside off, de Kock defends
Bit more on this delivery, Bairstow gets this reverse out of the middle but straight to backward point
steps out and clips one off his pads, that's de Kock's half-century! From just 22 balls, the joint-quickest in the tournament so far. He's provided the perfect platform for SA so far
Ugly hack across the line - a third one-hander of this Bairstow innings - out to the fielder at deep midwicket
flighted, drifting slightly leg side, nudged off the pads behind square
Shorter and straight to Buttler, who plays the ball off the pitch, gets on top of the bounce and works a single around the corner
flattish legbreak, de Kock plays with the spin through midwicket for two more

Goneski! Smart stuff from Maharaj - throws the delivery up there slower and wider having seen Bairstow getting tetchy. Goes for a cut but ends up guiding it straight to Jansen at backward point, who dives to his right to take a smart catch
sliding on outside off and cut away to the point sweeper
Just outside off, tidy length, defended by Mo. Brilliant over from Maharaj
Full of a good length, angled into middle stump, worked. away to the leg side boundary rider
angled in a touch quicker, 90kph on off, defended
Into the hip of Moeen as Nortje stays over the wicket to the leftie. Mo works this around the corner
lands it on a length, slightly slower. Punched down to long-on
Full, late movement in, Buttler stays honest and defends back to the bowler
gives it some air, dropping outside off, Hendricks is forward and works with the turn through midwicket
Short - pace off, actually - pulled away through midwicket
round the wicket, de Kock backs away and exposes his stumps, slaps firmly through backward point. Two there as the sweeper tracks around the rope
Buttler steps to his left just before Nortje gets to the crease. The bowler responds by sending a length delivery a little more in his direction, which Buttler swats down to deep third
looped up and de Kock comes down, chipped without great timing but into the gap at extra cover for two more
Scuffed to cover... no, just over the fielder at short-extra cover! Very lucky shot from Moeen, but he'll get one with it
straighter line, nudged to leg. Moeen scurries across to prevent one
floated up on the stumps, Hendricks nudges one more off his pads
Maharaj lands this one on about middle and off, good length, reverse-swept well but straight to deep cover

googly, slog-swept... straight to deep backward square leg! De Kock had been the aggressor for SA but this time he sends the big hit straight to the man back. Although he wants this checked - Wood had to stretch forward at the last moment as the ball dipped on him, and the third umpire is going to have a look. And Joel Wilson reckons it burst through his fingers to touch the ground, rather than Wood having them firmly under the ball! England are very unhappy about this, but the decision is not out!
Outside off, decent length, Moeen reaches and gets it very square on the leg side, forcing Klaasen to cover a decent amount of ground to field just in front of the sponge
another googly, this time played conservatively towards square leg for one
Wide, back of a length, loopy. Moeen waits and then times well but not well enough to beat the fielder at deep cover
pushed through on the stumps, Hendricks can't get it away

Headloss, Buttler? Buttler tries to use the breeze to launch Maharaj into the stands at deep midwicket, but the left-arm spinner has slowed his pace meaning Buttler can only sky to Klaasen, who makes no mistake this time. Simple as. South Africa turning the screw, England circling the drain...
floated up and flicked into the midwicket region for a couple coming forwards
Almost sneaks one through with a flat one! Brook gets it away for a single through the off side
slows his pace, drops a touch short. Hendricks drops back and slaps a pull to deep midwicket
Into the pitch outside off, driven through cover to keep the strike
Around the wicket to the left-hander, out the front of the hand, full, into middle and leg - pushed into the covers
worked away through the leg side
Dragged down, but dragged across to the leg side by Moeen instead of being struck with any real malice. Missed out on a boundary, there...
charges down and lofts into the gap, de Kock picks his spot at deep extra cover and collects a welcome boundary
Bit of turn, worked off the pitch by Brook, out to deep midwicket
Bite off the surface, thick edge of the bat but in front of point for a single
chopped through backward point going back
Drifting into Brook onto a full length, defended

Hendricks gallops down, flubs to mid-on! England finally have their first wicket, and no doubt about the catch being clean this time. A big skier from Hendricks ad Moeen pushed the ball wide and asked him to fetch it. Brook settles under it after coming in off the rope. To be honest, that might be a better wicket for SA than England
Tighter to the stumps, turn into off stump, worked through midwicket. Tidy start from Markram, and it's time for a well-earned drink for the Proteas.
flat outside off, Klaasen drops back and slugs a cut to deep cover
legbreak, flat outside off, Klaasen punches square going abck
Length, just outside off, run off the face down to third
tossed up and this spins, loops up off the bat/gloves to the leg side

Game over? Short ball - you know, not even that short - pulled away to Maharaj out at deep midwicket, some 15/20 yards in from the fence. Smart bowling from Baartman, who knew Moeen Ali needed to take on the shot to the longer side, against the breeze...
switches his stance, Rashid pushes it outside leg... de Kock goes for the reverse anyway, the ball squirts past Buttler. No bat on it, but not given as a wide either

Full bunger almost traps Livingstone first ball! It's a missed yorker, from wide of the crease, that Livingstone wears on the front pad. Sliding down comfortably, but both a miss and a bit of fortune for Livi first up
tapped into the covers
Timed down the ground, but Baartman fields well to his left
googly, this veers back and cramps Klaasen as he looks to cut. Forced to cover
Into the pitch, no real pace off it, pushed back to the bowler
lands it on a length, 83kph and punched warily to the man in the covers again. Just two off the over

Full outside off, the bat turns in Brook's hands as he tries to impart some muscle into the ball, but is only able to force it away for a single through midwicket. Another excellent over from South Africa
Angled into the pads, tucked away to backward square leg
gets this wrong, tries for a slower ball wide of off... almost misses the cut strip back of a length, pace off again, I think, and chopped through point
Onto the toes of Livingstone, who whips this around the corner. He thinks about coming back for a second but his feet give way on the turn and he has to abort. Probably not there anyway
banged into the pitch, Klaasen rides the bounce in defence
Fired down leg stump again, worked away but straight to the fielder stationed wide at deep fine leg
goes short, 145kph/90mph and it clears Klaasen's languid attempt to pull
Finally, a boundary! The first since 4.2 overs, as Livingstone smears a length delivery over to the leg side, in between the two boundary riders
pace off, low full toss on the stumps, shovelled away to deep backward square leg
Yorked punched out to Rabada at mid on... who nails the nonstriker's stumps with a direct hit! TV umpire checking... but Livingstone's dive has saved him comfortably. Play on

short with pace off, edged... and swallowed by the leaping Buttler! Brilliant one-handed take, and there won't be any hanging around this time. Buttler gets to his feet and exchanges a business-like high five with Archer. The cutter did for de Kock's timing, but a phat top edge could easily have flown for four. England's captain ensured otherwise
Into pitch, outside off, Brook reaches and gets a single down to deep midwicket
round the wicket, dug in short at 141kph/88mph and Miller ducks the challenge
Flighted, slower through the air, on leg stump, worked out to deep square with a late turn of the wrists by Brook for a sharply taken two
pitched up and blapped through mid-off! Possibly the cutter, but it was an inviting length and Klaasen rattled it back so firmly that long-off stood no chance of getting across in time
Length dragged back, Brook reaches but can't beat cover with a drive
touch short outside off, thumped off the back foot, but picks out cover
Flatter, fuller and swept hard just behind square leg ! Great timing

131kph/81mph and hit on the pads coming across his stumps. Curran thinks this is out, and Buttler assents to a review. Klaasen was rapped on the knee roll looking to whip leg side. Was he in line with off stump? He was, but the bounce means it comes back as umpire's call on hitting the top of the wicket! Close but no cigar for England
Back on the money, teasing pace, almost getting a return catch off a leading edge as Brook tries to manufacture something into the leg side
pitched up, Miller flicks across the line, gets a low edge to short third

Punched hard off the back foot to deep cover. The first is taken sharply, but the second needs to be even quicker as the throw comes in from Klaasen. Brook's running to the danger end and just makes it! Direct hit and he'd have been a goner...
back of a length, 129kph/80mph and dabbed down towards cover

Reverse sweep in the air... but well inside the fielder in the ring at third, who follows the spin off the outfield and keeps it to one. And outstanding spell of 2 for 25 from Maharaj, featuring nine dot balls in his four overs
tight line on off, Miller shuffles across and turns a single out to deep square leg

Around the wicket, wide of the crease, full into the toes, flicked away to backward square leg. Brook had initially moved to the leg side and Jansen was a tad risky following him with no cover down at fine leg, but gets away with it
fired full across the bows from over the wicket, 144kph/89mph and driven out to the cover sweeper
Length, held back a touch, but at Livingstone, who wants to heave this to the leg side but misses completely and ends up having to wear it on the inside thigh
sprayed slightly leg side, gets a touch off the pad... but he's saved by the flying Buttler going to his left
On the charge, forehand smashed away to the cover fielder as Jansen drags his length back with the first delivery of the over outside off stump
short ball, veering down leg as Klaasen pulls and misses. Signalled wide, brings up the SA 100 full and straight, clipped down to long-on
Brook makes more room, opens his hands but can't beat backward point with a bit of finesse
shortish, 146kph/91mph and pushed across the southpaw, Miller chops through cover point
Full, outside off, hammered through backward point! Brook finally gets the chance to free his arms as Jansen fails to follow the initial movement to leg

steps to leg, Wood follows him with a dipping bouncer, Buttler has to scamper after it after the ball hits his pads... but he then pulls out a bullet throw to run out Klaasen at the non-striker's end! Miller called for the run, his partner was perhaps guilty of ball-watching. But that was another superb piece of work behind the stumps by Buttler back of a length, 148kph/92mph and tucked down to leg
This time Brook rushes to the off side for the scoop as Jansen goes to leg once more... but no dice! And no wide, either, as Brook's movements were so late. The bluff almost worked for the batter
skiddy length, edged through gully! Miller was looking to close the face but ends up squirting four to deep third, past the dive of Topley
floated up outside off, Markram cuts his first ball and gets one as backward point half stops it
That's a great start for England! All of 143km/h into the pitch lifted high and with the breeze, over square leg
reverse-swept and finds the gap! Turns the hands around and chops down on it to beat point and the man back
Short length again, pace off, pulled out to the fielder at deep midwicket
tossed up, 83kph on the stumps, worked out to deep midwicket
Full, outside off, driven out into the covers, beating the initial dive of the fielder in the ring. Two pocketed as the deep fielder comes to tidy up

lovely loopy stuff, Markram drags on! Slow and inviting on a wide line, 76kph/47mph and Markram can't time an aggressive thrash through the off side, ends up getting a thick inside edge that bobbles back into his leg stump. England chip out another, strangling SA after a strong start
Width, flashed away through backward point! Great hands from Brook to get the ball down through that region at pace
legbreak, jumps up in the channel, Stubbs is back and across and punches through point
SCOOOOOOOP! Cutter into the pitch outside off, met by Brook who fronts up to the delivery and lifts it high over third up in the circle
flighted, worked from off stump through midwicket, Rashid hares after it
Into the pitch again, not as short, worked away into midwicket

Brook on the charge! Nortje starts with length and is pumped back over his head by an advancing Brook! Great hands, great ticket. Made a difficult shot - and a difficult surface - look very easy on that occasion
short and clouted through midwicket! Gets on top of the bounce, uses 146kph/91mph to his advantage and slams a timely four
Powered through cover! That's the shot of the innings, without question. Brook stands tall, hits the ball on the up, wide of Markram at mid off. Stunner...
pitched up, 145kph outside off, Miller pings a drive to cover. Struck so firmly there's no time to run one
Gives himself room, Nortje follows him with a toe-crusher which Brook digs out to deep midwicket. Hits it too well to get two, though
into the pitch, possibly a slower ball. Miller swings at it and misses
Yorker again, into leg stump, dug out by Livingstone who keeps his balance to push it to deep square leg for a single
dug in and swiped down to fine leg! Pace on and Miller again rolls the wrists, tucks it to the left of the man at deep backward square
Wide of the crease, but wide of the blue tramline... just! Harsh call, actually, as replays show the ball passing over the line Straighter, into the right-hander, worked away square once more
slower ball, pitched up and driven out to deep point
Powered down the ground, but low on Livingstone's bat, as long on comes around to field
short again, tickled fine! Stubbs doesn't have to do too much to pick up his first boundary. Good over for SA, almost doubling the number of boundaries since the end of the powerplay (seven)
And Livingstone starts with a boundary! Wide full toss, slapped to deep cover in the vicinity of Tristan Stubbs who can't get anywhere near the ball as it crashes into the sponge on the half-volley
pitched up, pace off from over the wicket, Miller nurdles through square leg
Another full toss slammed through cover! Horror start from Baartman, but Livingstone's cashing in...
slanted across the right-hander, but too close to the tramlines for the umpire goes for wide blockhole, 135kph/83mph. Stubbs drives to cover
Another full toss... and six over square leg! Three full tosses, three boundaries. Horrendous from Baartman, pace on for all three deliveries, missing his yorker every time!
back of a length and Stubbs cuts for a single
A fourth full toss! But Livingstone can only get this off the toe away to deep midwicket.
full and skidding into the pads, worked for one more
Finally, Baartman lands one this one, into a length, slapped out to deep cover
pitched up and bunted down to long-off

And Brook finishes the over with its fourth boundary! Another full toss, with mid on up, allows Brook to lift down the ground without really taking a risk. That's 21 from the over and suddenly England need just 25 from 18 deliveries!
loopy slower-ball bumper, the classic from England's 2010 title success. Miller is flummoxed and misses with an attempted pull
full, tailing in towards leg stump, Stubbs wanted to make room but ends up blocking back to the bowler
Finally, a dot ball for the Proteas. But it's a full toss again from Rabada, very straight, driven back to the feet of Rabada
pitched up again, not quite yorker length, 142kph/88mph. Clipped out to deep midwicket
Another full toss... but Livingstone's lifted it straight to Stubbs at deep backward square leg! Rabada celebrates right in front of Livingstone - he is pumped! Is there a further twist in this?
round the wicket, full, straight... and launched over deep backward square! Sits up nicely for Miller to drop-kick it with the wind, crunched 77 metres flat over the boundary boards
Full, into the pads, flicked out to Klaasen at deep square leg
short with pace off, 117kph, Miller cuts at it and misses
Brook gives himself room, Rabada follows him with one into the surface. The shot across the line isn't timed out to deep midwicket, but there's only one available
short ball again, swung away to deep midwicket
Slower ball - off cutter - into the top of middle stump, worked into midwicket. Curran wants two, but South Africa are up in the field
banged in and Stubbs is left in a tangle as he attempts to revers-ramp a head-hunting 147kph/91mph delivery! Brave strategy. Nearly took that one right in the mush!
Another slower ball into the pitch, Brook times nicely but straight to one of the leg side boundary riders. Keeps the strike but that is an excellent over from Rabada
Full, touch wide, across Brook, who is too early with the shot down the ground and ends up scuffing it back to the bowler
good length with pace off, Miller swats it through the covers and charges off looking for two. He'll get them

Straighter, worked out to deep midwicket... and they manage to pinch two! That's Harry Brook's fifty from 34 deliveries. His first half-century in World Cups. But as Kobe once said, job's not finished...

full toss, swatted out towards deep square leg... where Livingstone throws himself full length to prevent four! Palmed back into play at full stretch. Miller wanted a no-ball called there, but it looked like it was dipping in time
Tries to ramp, followed by Jansen. Ends up wearing it just in front of the keeper and takes the leg bye on offer with a strong early call from Curran
slot ball, hammered! Misses the yorker by a yard or two and Miller butchers it back into the (empty) seats at long-off! Brutal hit
Into the pitch, rearing up outside off, pulled out to deep midwicket once more...
slower-ball bouncer, but Miller turns away as it loops through outside off. Too high short with pace off again, Miller stretches and slaps one to the cover sweeper
Into the pitch, scythed into the breeze on the off-side... but that saves Brook from the fielder running in from deep cover, who has to gather on the deck after the ball plugs
round the wicket, back-of-a-length cutter, Stubbs swings hard and bottom edges one into the leg side

Curran gives himself room... and Jansen follows him brilliantly to restrict any leverage. The ball squirts out into square leg and Curran just makes his ground back for the second to give Harry Brook the strike for the final over...
over the wicket, another change-up, top of off and Miller can only punch it down to long-off

Brook goes! And it's a stunning catch from Aidan Markram over his shoulder running back from mid on! Clutch play from the Proteas skipper after Brook inadvertently skies the first ball of the over down the ground. It did not look like a variation, but Brook did not get that as intended.

full and slapped... but Brook intercepts at long-off! Pace on and Miller hit it cleanly, but England had a man back there and he takes an excellent low catch diving to his left. Decent knock from Miller but Archer will now have a new batter to target in the final over
Full into the pads, whipped away to deep midwicket and Curran has the strike with 13 needed from 4, hitting to the short side...

and another one, chipped to cover running back! Pitched up, Jansen sliced his shot leaning back, looked like probably being safe - only for Curran to skeddadle back from the edge of the ring and take a full-length diving effort over his shoulder
Four to Curran! Awful delivery from Nortje, full and outside leg stump, helped on its way beyond fine leg - up in the circle - and away to the boundary
short ball, uppercut wide of deep third, Wood scrambles around to palm it back... but connects with the rope at the second attempt and concedes four!
Low full toss, worked out to deep midwicket.. and Curran refuses the run!
full and straight with pace off. Maharaj dinks it in front of point for one
Outstanding from Nortje! Wide yorker, just outside off, Curran hits it well but all along the ground to long off
goes for the yorker, 145kph/90mph. Dug out through midwicket

And South Africa have won it! Fires one through Archer, who swings and misses, though to Quinton de Kock! An excellent finish from Nortje after Baartman had let England back in it with a horrible 17th over. But South Africa kept their nerve - first with the bat, then here at the end with the ball - to secure their second win of the Super Eight stage, moving top of Group 2!

short with pace off, Stubbs swipes at it and gets a bottom edge into the  leg side. Buttler gives chase and keeps them to one. So England, having squeezed superbly after a leaky powerplay, will have to chase 164 to win
orthodox left armer's delivery to start, a bit of turn after pitching on a length, played back to the bowler
Full outside off, hint of inswing into the right hander, Hope leans into it and eases a drive to cover
turns the other way, a bit short, and quick. Hits Taylor on the body as he misses a sweep but the appeal is short
On a length around off, Hope punches it down the ground to mid-off
full, darted in around off, dug out towards mid off and they sprint through for the first run, with a bit of a stutter
Full on leg, swinging in, Hope looks to flick and misses but West Indies get on the board as the ball pops to the off side off the pads and they get a leg bye
slows this one down a bit, a regular orthodox ball, pitching on about off. Pushed down the ground for a single
Full outside off, Charles drives along the ground to mid-off
shorter one, quick again, was that the arm ball. Taylor tries to club through midwicket but only gets an under edge to it
On a length on off, going across Charles, who opens the face of the blade to steer it to deep third
makes a good connection with the swipe to leg this time, but Hosein has cover at deep backward square. This was to another length ball fired in on the stumps
Full on leg, Hope clips it wide of mid-on and gets the single. First run off the bat for him
a little shape in to the left hander, the batter can do little more than to poke this out towards the backward point region
Quick and straight, clipped through square leg

good catch at point from Roston Chase, clinging on to a low one, just centimetres off the turf. This was shortish and wide from Russel, and Taylor slashes it right to Chase. He'd hit it well though, so the fielder has to react quickly. He completes the catch, keeps his hands above the turf, and Kensington Oval celebrates
Kenjige sees Charles backing away and follows him, Charles fends to mid-on
more swing for Russel, but Kumar is up to playing it first ball. This is wide of off and going away and he prods this through cover point for a couple
Full and following Charles again, who backed away leg-side again. Charles gets down and sweeps to fine leg. The fielder misfields and allows the single
straighter ball on the stumps, clipped square on the legside for one
Onto the roof! Kenjige just goes a touch too short and Hope rocks back and hammers a pull over midwicket
more movement, just outside off, length ball, poked to point who has a bit of work to do but the batters decide against a run
On a length on middle and off, tucked wide of mid-on for a single

lovely timing. This is back of a length just outside off. Gous stands tall gets on top of the bounce and punches this behind square on the offside, Three fielders give chase including the deep third, but can't cut it off
Length ball angled into Charles, who clips it towards deep midwicket
seam-uo arm ball to start to Kumar. This swing in to Kumar and he defends back to Hosein
Glorious! This is full around off, and he just lofts it down the ground. Couple of bounces and over the rope
slower one, a little loop, turning away from Kumar, who just drops it square on the offside
Length ball, punched to mid-off
arm ball again I think, but a bit wider of off. Kumar gets low and chops it to point
Another cracking drive! Full around off and Hope pierces the gap between extra cover and mid-off with a perfectly placed drive. Hit it on the up, and it races away
floated up, wide of off, driven to extra cover where a misfield allows a single. Should have been easily stopped.
Length ball angles in from outside off, Hope whips it wide of mid-on
down the track to a looped up stock ball, but he doesn't get to the pitch and just flicks through the leg side instead. Finds space behind midwicket and gets one
Length ball around middle and leg, Charles punches it square to point

flatter ball outside off, Kumar pushes towards point and calls for the single. Roston Chase is all over it though and makes a diving stop and then a shy at the stumps, but doesn't connect with the throw, which didn't have a lot of power in it. USA scramble one.
On a length outside off, Charles looks to back away and slap it down the ground, but can't beat the mid-off fielder to his left. Another dot ball for him
A swing and a miss! Length ball outside off, Hope looks for an expansive drive but can't connect
a bit of a beamer to start - a thigh-high full toss outside off. Kumar had made room and misses out
Fuller on off, Hope manages to clip it to midwicket's left, but the fielder gets there, preventing the single
inside out. Backs away again, and gets one exactly where he wanted it, on the stumps and pitched up. Smokes this over cover with a classical lofted cover drive
Bouncer on off, Hope ducks under it. Good start by Ali Khan here
stays put this time, and Kumar tries to whip this through mid on. Comes off the inside half of the bat and goes past midwicket, who has chasing to do
Excellent riposte by Hope! This is a length ball that sits up nicely and Hope latches onto it, heaving it over cow corner!

shortish, and sits up nicely for Kumar, who crashes this over midwicket for four, with excellent shape. Kumar's looking good here. He stayed in his regular stance, picked the length early, and controlled the shot to perfection
Full toss on the body, Hope clips it fine on the leg side and it just beats the fine leg fielder!
fullish on about off stump, carves this through cover point to the offside sweeper
Full length around off, fended to the leg side

play and a miss, and that takes off from the surface. Length ball angled across the batter by the left-arm bowler. It bounces and explodes out of the surface. Kumar is back trying to blast this over cover, but doesn't connect.
arm ball, coming in at Gous, and he goes deep in his crease, opens the face and carves this through point for four with excellent timing. Has been good through that region
Charles finally gets one away. This is in the slot on off and Charles thrashes this over mid-on. It's been a frustrating knock for him so far, and that shot will help get him going
full, darted in, on about off stump, driven to long on
Backs away and Harmeet makes him stretch with a length ball outside off. He manages to reach out and flat-bat it to mid-off
slower this time, but another run to long on results, as Kumar goes back and pushes at this length ball
Full and driven down to long-off
another tossed up ball, on the stumps this time, turned to deep midwicket for another single
Full on the stumps, Hope backs away and goes inside out over cover. Doesn't get all of it and that's a good job by the fielder to stop it from reaching the ropes
tossed up, pitched just about on off and turning away, tries to knock it to long on again, but can't beat the bowler who darts to his right and stops it
Full delivery eased to long-off
shortish, quick one outside off, and cut hard. But it's straight to point. Kumar throws his head back in frustration at finding the fielder
On a length around middle, Charles clips it wide of long-off for another single

shortish ball, wide of off, slashed to deep backward point. And oh dear, Alzarri has overstepped Kumar backs away massively, and Alzarri follows him with a yorker that lands about a metre outside leg stump. Kumar has to play at it though, and pokes it past midwicket for a single
Full all on leg, dipping late, dug out to long-on
Gous plays a big legside shot now. This is fullish, on the stumps, whipped beautifully square on the leg side, between square leg and midwicket. He's looking good here too
Thrashed through extra cover! This is a slower ball, full outside off and Hope leans into it and hits it hard along the ground

bang! First six of the day, This is a length ball on the stumps that Gous gets inside of the line early on, and larrups this over deep square leg for six. Not a doubt that was headed into the stands the moment it left the bat
Length ball outside off, punched on the up to cover

dropped! Length outside off, Hous tries to play this away on the off side, and gets a big outside edge that flies to the right of short third at a catchable height. The fielder gets his hands on it originally, then lets it spill out of his hands
Goes all the way now! van Schalwyk sticks to that line outside off, but overpitches this and Hope muscles it inside out for a flat six over cover!
length ball on the stumps, flicked through the square leg region for another one
Back of length delivery outside off, Hope muscles a pull down the ground. Goes on the bounce to long-on
back of a length ball outside off, Gous gets the pull shot out, looking for another big one over the deep square leg boundary. Miscues it though, and it bounces well short of the deep fielder there

Neatly done! this is a back of length delivery angling into Charles, who sways back and dabs it fine of the short third fielder. Expensive over for the USA and West Indies finish the powerplay on a high
tossed up just wide of off, driven hard, wide enough of long off to get a couple
Length ball on off, Hope punches it to cover but can't get it past the fielder
flatter one, pitching outside off, Gous goes back and pokes this through cover and they cross
On a length on off, Hope drives it wide of long-off and West Indies pick up two

big shout and given! This looked very out on first viewing, but Kumar has reviewed pretty quickly.  This was looped up on off stump, and Kumar went for a reverse sweep, but the ball dipped beneath the shot and hit Kumar low on the front pad. Kumar did feel the ball on his glove, but that was AFTER it hit his pad. And the projection shows three reds, the ball hitting him in front of off, and crashing into off. Much needed breakthrough for West Indies.
Disdainful! And that's a 26-ball half-century for Shai Hope! A bit of a drag down outside off, Hope clears his front leg and slaps this over mid-off and all the way
backs away first ball, but gets a dart on the stumps that he only manages to bunt back to the bowler
Full on leg going on with the angle, Hope looked to slog sweep but he misses out and the ball also misses the leg stump
flat, but shorter, quick through the air, chopped straight to point
Full on off, Hope drives it down the ground to long-off
fired in on off stump, pushed only to short cover

Holes out at wide long-on! Charles went for the slog on this delivery tossed up on the stumps, but he couldn't clear Milind Kumar in the deep. He had both feet in the air as he grabbed it above head height and he does well to balance on his back leg as he landed just inside the boundary rope. Good catch and Charles' struggles come to an end
Ali Khan slides one down leg side and it's called wide immediately Full outside off and beats Hope on the outside edge as he looks to smash it away on the off side!
length ball just outside off, Gous tries to punch through the off side but gets a big inside edge on to pad that dribbles away behind square and they sprint through
Full toss angled down leg again. Another wide Gets the yorker outside off, Hope reaches out looking to drive on the off side but gets an inside edge through square leg

length ball sprayed down leg that's HUUUUGE. On to the roof beyond cow corner at Kensington, a ground Aaron Jones knows well. That was a back of a length ball outside off stump and Jones absolutely murders it high and long
Back of length delivery, Pooran pulls it square and gets off the mark
comes back with a bouncer, on about off stump, which Jones ducks beneath. Alzarri is not happy with the treatment he got previous ball
Almost yorker length on off, Hope squeezes it out through cover
another short one, about chest high this time, into the body. Fends it away toward the legside and they scamper through
On a length on off and slanting across Pooran, who jabs it towards cover for a single

Gous tries to repeat the Jones six, but holes out to midwicket instead. This was another back of a length ball, but tight into the stumps, and Gous is sliiightly late on the shot. Instead of hitting it over wide long on, he miscues it high towards deep midwicket, who comes in off the boundary about 15 metres to take that catch with comfort. Alzarri has made a good comeback this over.
Full toss on the body, Hope looks to flick it away but it comes off his gloves and rolls through a vacant midwicket, allowing the batters to hare for two
length ball on the stumps to start to Anderson. He just defends back down the pitch
cut away, and that's a rapid two. This was shorter, turning away, and Jones got deep in his crease to beat the point fielder
Full toss outside off, luckily for him Pooran can only drive it out to sweeper cover
attempted reverse sweep, but Motie has beat him with a darted, full delivery outside off stump
Full on leg, eased down the ground to long-on
conventional sweep this time, to another dart on the stumps. Hits it to deep fine
Pooran backs away and Milind follows him with a full ball, dug back out to the bowler
flatter delivery, from over the wicket, pitching on off stump. Hit back to the bowler

This time Milind goes wide as Pooran backs away, but just goes a bit too wide. It also spins away past the keeper allowing the isngle Long hop outside off and Hope rocks back and belts it over midwicket
fired through a bit wide of off, and that's chopped away through cover to get Anderson off the mark
Not as short as the last time, but doesn't matter for Hope, who stands tall and deposits it over midwicket with a mighty heave
down the track, and Motie sees him coming and bowls quickly at him. Jones just drives to long off
