Three in a row! Milind looks to go full and wide now and Hope carts it inside-out over cover! This is some hitting from Hope!

through him like a arrow through chiffon. This is nicely flighted, and beats Aaron Jones' big sweep, and takes out his leg stump. Any top spinner would be happy to beat a batter in the air like that. Tossed it up, tempted him into the shot, then dipped the ball beneath the bat. Jones was looking dangerous.
Length ball on off, Pooran cuts it behind square but can't beat backward point
fired through on the legs, turned towards midwicket and he gets off the mark immediately
Deposited into the stands! Back of length delivery and Pooran stands tall and swipes it over midwicket. That's gone 90 metres! And West Indies go past the 100-run mark
fired through just outside off, Anderson pushes to mid on and they sprint through
slowed up but way down legside another tossed up delivery with a bit of work on it. Comes into Milind Kumar's pads and he turns it around the corner to short fine leg
On a length on off and slanting across, Pooran drags it along the ground to deep midwicket
floated up outside off, Anderson is early into his offside push and sends it on the bounce to short cover
Lands safe! Hope swipes at a back of length delivery but gets a top edge. It clears the in field and short of long-on running in!
flatter again, on the stumps, played straight. Chase runs to his left and cuts it off
Length ball angled across Pooran, but that's too wide Full outside off and Pooran, who was standing around off stump, pummels it down the ground. Couple of bounces and four
length ball on the stumps, defended towards mid on
Back of length delivery around off, lofted down the ground and on the bounce to long-off
short ball, bouncer, over about off stump. Milind thinks about playing at it but gets out of the way
You don't bowl it there to Pooran! Right in the slot outside off and Pooran swings across the line and sends this flying over midwicket!
length ball, slower one I think, outside off stump at 116kph. Opens the face and runs it wide of deep third. Nice little dinky shot.
Carted over cover! Netravalkar goes for the wide yorker but Pooran is able to reach out and carve it over the off side for a 96-metre six! West Indies in a hurry to finish things off
length ball but pushed down the legside full delivery on off stump, driven back to the bowler
On a length outside off, Pooran slaps this wide of long-off but they get just the single
back of a length, and decent bounce for Andre Russell. This was just wide of off, and the batter tried to chop at it, but missed
Hope finishes things off in style! Full outside off and he clears the front leg and lofts this over long-off. His best T20I score, and what a knock it was!

full ball, fired down leg for the second time in the over length ball, wide of off, carved nicely square of deep third who has a lot of work to do. They call two early and run hard, but there's a direct hit at the non-striker's end as Charles collects the ball and tries to catch Anderson short. He's home safely though.
pushed through on off stump, played towards cover and they take another quick one
slows it up a bit, length ball, on the pads. Plays a big sweep but it thuds into pad
fullish, on the stumps, turned towards midwicket and an easy single results

fired through outside off, and there's a thick outside edge that goes to short third. Milind races to the striker's edn and if the throw had been at the non-striker's Anderson would have been in trouble
fullish, quick ball on the stumps, whipped to deep midwicket
flattish ball, just wide of off, chopped away through point
slower ball to start the over from McCoy, bowled into the pitch. ANderson was shaping to drag this ball to leg but is deceived by the lack of pace and it passes through outside off stump
on the stumps this time, and played to leg, but into the midfield. Anderson needs to get moving here
slower one, full on the toes, clipped gently through square leg for one
shortish ball over about leg stump. Milind swivel-pulls it to deep square leg
slower one I think, but that's sent down the legside. West Indies haven't been great with the extras so far back of a length ball over the stumps. Dropped towards point and they take off
shortish ball just outside off. Not much width but that's timed beautifully by Milind, who stands tall and carves it behind point to beat the sweeper there. A much needed boundary for USA.
shortish, wide of off, cut away hard but straight to cover

Anderson goes! Chase nails him in front with a quick delivery, This was headed to middle and leg I think. Anderson was rooted to the crease trying to work this to leg, and is struck on the back pad in front of the stumps. The umpire didn't take long to decide.

another one for CHase, and he's on a hat trick. This was slower through the air, pitched outside off to leftie Harmeet. He tries to push this straight but it takes the outside edge and floats up to Charles at point, who accepts it at about shoulder-height. USA falling away after their strong powerplay.
faster ball, on the pads - not the best for a hat-trick delivery. Worked through square leg
flattish ball, slightly wide of off, cut through point for a single
floated up on the stumps, driven to long off
length ball just outside off, angled across the batter. He just plays it back to the bowler off the inside part of the bat
back of a length ball outside off, dropped into the offside and they sprint through
length ball wide of off, opens the face and slices this square of deep third for a single
bouncer into the body, over about leg stump. Batter tries to get out of the way but it hits him in the fleshy part of the upper arm and they run a leg bye
back of a length ball just outside off, bunted into the offside and they run through
back of a length ball over the stumps, tries to turn this to leg but only manages to hit it back to the bowler who collects on his follow through
flatter one on the pads, flicked through deep square leg for a single
fired in outside off, defended
tossed up outside off, and van Schalkwyk plays his first big shot, unfurling a lovely cover drive and connecting well enough to send it to the boundary
flatter one from around the wicket, angled into the stumps, gets a single towards mid on
flattish outside off, runs this towards short third and they sprint through
flatter, quicker, on off stump. Milind gets across and works it through square leg
tossed up outside off, dropped towards cover and they sprint through
flatter, dragged down, poor ball. This was wide of off as well, and van Schakwyk gets back and clubs this down the ground over the bowler for four. Had the space to free his arms there, and cashes in
quicker, fired through outside off from around the wicket, hit back to the bowler
full ball on the pads, turned around the corner to short fine leg
tossed up, slowed down, pitching on about leg from wide of the stumps. A big sweep is played but Milind doesn't connect.
flattish ball, outside off, cut to the left of backward point. They think about a run but decide against.
smoked! This is a wonderful shot from the No. 8. Fullish side of a length ball, outside off and van Schalkwyk bangs this back past the bowler along the ground

terrible miscommunication. Both batters end up at the striker's end, and that's an easy run out for Motie and Russell. this was a fullish ball flicked to short fine who took it on the bounce. Milind had raced through to the other end while van Schalkwyk was still ball watching. Motie - the short fine leg - threw it to Russell who had ages to take the bails off
fullish, angled across the leftie, pitching outside off. Tires to run it off the face of the bat but misses

van Shcalkwyk has holed out now. This is a slowish back of a length ball, angled across, slightly wide of the stumps, He tries to crash it through the offside, but only provides a straightforward catch to deep point

this is fullish, fired down the leg side woah! That's some hit to get off the mark. That's in the slot, wide of off, fullish. Ali Khan stands tall and tonks it hiiiiigh over the sightscreen and into the media stand. Absolutely nailed that.

smashes that one too. Where have US been hiding Ali Khan? This is fullish again, on the stumps this time. Again Ali Khan clears his front leg and spanks it down the ground, flatter this time. It's a one-bounce four as long on fails to get a hand to it

length ball just wide of off, opens the face and hits to short third. Ali Khan is desperate to get to the other side and tears out of the crease. The shy at the stumps would have brought a run out at the non-striker's if it had hit
back of a length ball wide of, batter throws his bat at it and misses. There's an appeal though, and a review. But it's not out. There was no nick
fullier, outside off, chopped to backward point
yorker outside off, dug out back to the bowler

catching practice for Pooran. This was a slower, back of  a length ball outside off stump. Kenjige tries to get inside the line and scoop this over the keeper, but ends up getting it high on the bat and the ball loops up for a simple catch for wicketkeeper Pooran.
shortish ball, fast one this time. Netravalkar hangs his bat out and tires to chop it square. Misses.
slower one to start, length outside off, dragged towards deep midwicket but into space so they can get a couple
length ball, just wide of off, slower one again I think. Clubbed past the bowler, but not with a lot of power. Long off cleans up
pace on this time, fullish, wide of off. Netravalkar hangs his bat out, but misses
back of a length ball wide of off, another play and a miss

holes out to long on, where Rovman Powell takes an outstanding running, diving catch. This was hard length and Netravalkar tried to bang it down the ground. Does not connect properly though, and it hangs in the air long enough for Powell to make a big charge, and intercept it centimetres above the turf.
tucks this to long leg to get off the mark, some shape back in for Arshdeep to begin with
flighted ball pitching on off stump to start, and Rohit makes room and chips it over mid-off
full and swinging away from outside off, left alone
quicker length ball on off stump, clipped towards short midwicket
beaten as he wafts at an away-going delivery from outside off
flat, fired in to finish around leg stump. Makes room and punches down to long-on
gently pushed to cover, feet stuck to the crease
tossed up on middle and leg, gets forward for a firm clip to short midwicket, who stops it with a dive to his right
flayed over point. Just a hint of width from Arshdeep and he timed that magnificently. Didn't look to keep it down, and that did the trick

length ball turning towards leg stump, and this time they get the single after Kohli clips to the right of that man at short midwicket. A bit of yes-no between Kohli and Rohit initially, but they make it safely enough. Mahmudullah wasn't the quickest to the ball either
gets a thick bottom edge as he looks to punch, Pant dives to his left to stop that on the bounce

first boundary of the day, and it's off either the top edge or the glove. Looks for the sweep against a length ball turning in from outside off, a bit of extra bounce too. Loops over the keeper and outpaces short fine leg to the boundary
starts with a length ball on off, defended to point
full and fairly flat on off stump, pushed down to long-off
hits the deck hard as he angles in a length ball, Litton plays it with soft hands past point
not the best ball considering the wind direction. Fired in, angling into leg stump, and Rohit gets a big stride in to sweep it up and over the backward square leg region
works it gently down to long leg
tossed up slower on middle and off, stretches out to flick to deep square leg
defends back as he stays right behind the line

not the best over from Shakib, this. Floated into Kohli's hitting arc on middle and leg stump, and he clears his front leg and slogs it away dismissively, up and over midwicket for the first six of the match
throws the kitchen sink at that but makes no connection. One of the rare occasions Bumrah's offered width
looks to make room premeditatedly, and has to reach out to try and slap away this off-stump length ball. Thick edge rolls away to the left of backward point
has he got him? That's an absolute peach. Angles in, hits the deck and deviates away to square him up. Think everyone knew there was no edge there.
quickish, angling into off stump from wide of the crease, gets forward and clips to long-on
sashays down the pitch and scorches this half-volley through cover point. Just wide of a diving Jadeja
length ball angling into leg stump, tucked away to long leg
cuts and misses. This kept a touch low
length ball on off stump, shuffles across and clips to the right of square leg
full and moving away from off, solidly defended.
length ball in the corridor, and Kohli stands tall and punches firmly to backward point with a high left elbow
chops the cut over the second slip fielder, Kohli. Runs away to the third man boundary

shot! Hit-me ball, full and angling into middle and leg, but how well does Kohli hit this. Pulls his front leg out of the way and brings his bottom hand into play to whip it into the vacant spaces behind square leg
pushed to cover
length ball on top of off stump, punched firmly to cover point
cuts well, down to deep cover point
length ball angling in and straightening a little towards the top of off, punched towards short extra-cover
slides across the left-hander to beat his attempted late dab
bang. A bit of air, leg-stumpish, and Rohit jumps out, making room to free his arms and launch it high over long-on
hammered to the deep midwicket fence! Axar drops short marginally and Tanzid picked the length very early.
flatter, more round-arm, angling in towards leg stump. Not short enough to pull, and he bottom-edges into his front pad
works it with the spin to deep midwicket
more runs, and this is deftly done by Rohit. Only a touch short, and barely any width, but lovely use of the hands to late-cut this, wide of the keeper and well to the left of backward point
was looking to hit him over cover, but ends up forcing it to long-off as Axar shortens his length

and there's the first wicket. Both these batters have been looking to take their chances, and that doesn't stop despite this already being an expensive over. Looks to make room once more to go over the top, but he's not quite to the pitch of this leg-stump ball. Holds in the pitch a little, and he skews it high in the air, over the mid-off region. Extra-cover and long-off converge on the ball, and the former completes the catch, judging it well even as he loses his balance. It's Shakib's 50th T20 World Cup wicket
works it with the spin to long-on
flighted ball outside off, gets forward to clip to midwicket
jumps outside off and gets down on one knee to sweep him behind square. Lovely
sees Pant looking to step out and fires it full at his pads. Looks to flick hurriedly, and his bat turns in his hands and he skews it to extra-cover, along the ground

too short and way over the batter's head, starts off with a wide advances down the track but Hardik bangs it in to cramp him for room, the ball deflects off the pad into the off side. This hurried onto him off the pitch to beat Tanzid's attempted nudge
back of a length, keeps going away from off stump with the drift. Goes back to punch to long-on, plays it back to the bowler instead
sweep connection! Litton walks across and fetches this short ball from outside off. Clobbered over deep midwicket
similar ball to the previous one, but turns in as expected, and Kohli punches off the back foot to long-on

picks out Surya at deep square! It's a superb catch as well. Litton fetches this slower length ball from way outside off, he didn't go through with the shot for some reason and simply ended up chipping it towards SKY who did well to come in from the ropes and then dive forward to complete the catch. Rohit is pumped.
shuffles out, doesn't get to the pitch of this ball outside off, stretches and blocks it back to the bowler
slower length ball but slips it down leg, on the bounce to Pant as he misses the tickle works it to deep square
fired into the pads, tickled away fine, to the left of short fine leg. Mahmudullah chases back and keeps it in with a slide
right on top of the bounce as he taps it to midwicket
flat length ball angling in towards off stump, not much turn. Gets forward to defend with soft hands, and the ball hits the sticker of the bat. Good bounce off this pitch
punched to deep point
slightly slower and wider, stretches forward and opens his bat face to dab to backward point
high full toss that angles away, Tanzid flays it to deep point.  Looked definitely over the waist, not called no-ball
fullish, slanting away from off stump, and he frees his arms and slaps this away between extra-cover and mid-off. Doesn't quite middle it, and it slows down as it approaches the boundary

bursts through Pant's hands!  Pacy length ball that darts away to take the edge, Tanzid surprised by the fizz on that delivery as he wafted at that. Should've been taken. The speed at it which it went to Pant may have taken him by surprise.
back of a length, slanting across and finishing just outside off. Opens his bat face and dabs to short third
steers this length ball straight to point
length ball finishing just outside off. Punched firmly off the back foot to the extra-cover fielder, who dives to his left, gets a hand to the ball, and keeps it down to a single
pushed to point again, tight line and length
length ball angling into the stumps, tucked away to long leg
sliced off the edge to third man
shot! That's dismissive from Kohli. Good-length ball slanting across to off stump, and that strong bottom hand has no respect for angles. Clears his front leg and swings it away over wide long-on
right behind the line as he defends back this length delivery
full, wide of off stump, reaches out and pushes towards mid-off on the edge of the circle
tossed up just outside off, whipped to short midwicket
pulled to wide long-on
similar line, slightly slower and shorter, gets Kohli to stretch out to clip to long-on
attempted tickle flick the pad to short fine
flat length ball angling into the stumps, tucked away into the square-leg region, closing his bat face so much that the sticker on the back is visible to the bowler
gives him the charge and heaves this to deep square
tossed up outside off, driven to extra-cover
struck on the pad as he tries to get inside the line and help it past short fine
goes deep in his crease to a length ball that turns into him and cramps him for room. Punched to midwicket.
worked with the spin to deep midwicket
full on the stumps, clipped to long-on
slapped to point as Jadeja fires it wide
googly that hits him on the body and rolls to short third as he attempts to pull

waaaay outside off to start, and a full-toss that nearly yorks the keeper. Not much Kohli can do but leave it alone in the slot outside off, and Kohli puts it away. Frees his arms and clatters it straight back, up and over the umpire's head
shortish and into the pitch, keeps very low as Shanto pulls to deep midwicket
wristy. Looped up wide of off stump, and he reaches out and whips it to long-on
pulled against the turn to deep midwicket, had to fetch it from way outside off
after that big off-side wide to the right-hander, he delivers a leg-side wide to Pant. Flat, turning even further down leg, and Pant leaves it flamboyantly full on leg stump, whipped to long-on
shortish, spins away, the turn is slow, Shanto mistimes it to cover
ooh, some turn. Nice length outside off, not quite full enough to drive. Kohli pushes hard at it, and turn and bounce take the ball past his outside edge
punched down to long-on
looks to drag a slog-sweep from wide outside off, but it's a touch too full. All along the ground into the backward square leg region
hits the toe-end and smashes the pad as he attempts a pull

put away. Down the track, gets close to the pitch of this leg-stumpish ball, and whips it with the turn to the forward square leg boundary. Deep midwicket and deep backward square were back on the boundary, and this went into the big open space between them
short of a length delivery on the stumps, defended back

two down. Like Rohit, Kohli keeps taking his chances and falls. As you'd want your batters to do in this situation. Steps out, and I think he's foxed by the slower offcutter here. A bit early through his shot - I think his initial intentions were to hit straight, but he ends up trying to muscle it square on the leg side. Grips and turns past his inside edge and into the stumps
short ball down leg, and Shanto hits this over fine leg. Was hitting it into the wind mind you, but he got enough wood on it. Wayward from Hardik that time.

and he's on his way with a first-ball six. That's not a bad ball at all, a good bouncer from Tanzim that gets up and cramps him slightly for room as he steps across to hook. Manages to connect well enough to clear the backward square leg boundary, though
slower length ball angling away, slapped to mid-off

and Tanzim strikes again! Two wickets in three balls, and it's the extra bounce of this Antigua deck does the trick again. Back of a length in the corridor, and SKY was looking to guide it down to third. Leaps up, and it kisses either the glove or the handle close to the bottom hand on its way into the keeper's gloves
flicks this low full toss to deep fine leg
bouncer first up, angling across the left-hander, and Dube sways his upper body away from the line back of a length outside off, dabbed to backward point
slower ball outside leg and Shanto flicks him with some nonchalance to clear fine leg. Excellent pick up shot, an element of wrist involved as well. Superbly done
back of a length, a fair amount of width, steered down to deep third
struck on the body as he tries to pull him over deep midwicket
shortish, slanting away from off stump, cut away to deep point
pushed through quicker and wide outside off, Tanzid lets it go in anticipation of a wide, not given
flat length ball angling into the stumps, goes deep in his crease to defend
mistimes a pull to square leg for a single
steps out now, not quite to the pitch of this off-stumpish ball, clips it back to the bowler
reverse-swept in front of square to sweeper cover, picked that on the full
back of a length, just outside off, drags the pull to deep midwicket, all along the ground

foxed by the googly, given out on the field but Tanzid reviews. My first impression: may have missed leg, but how wrong I was. He shapes to cut but the ball spins back in alarmingly to catch him by surprise, leaves him no time to have a second line of defence as this thuds into the pad. Ball tracking comes back to show three reds,  the on-field decision of out stays.
flat and quick, top-of-off length. Makes a bit of room and flat-bats to the on side of the pitch. The bowler moves quickly to cut it off to his left
carefully defended as he goes right back int the crease
shortish outside off, leans back to chop it away and backward point dives right to half-stop it
works it with the spin to deep midwicket as they jog the single.
tossed up wide of off, driven wristily to deep point
and he gets greeted by Pant with a disdainful drive that he thumps on the up to bisect cover and mid-off
length ball straightens a touch outside off, shuffles across and works it through square leg
steers this length delivery on off to point
poor ball, short and wide, and sitting up for Shanto to slap away to the left of the diving fielder at cover

heaved over deep midwicket and he has picked the bones out of that! This was a slower length ball that pitches on off, it's right into Pant's swinging arc with the breeze. Held his shape nicely and walloped the ball when it arrived.
again that wide line, angling across and forcing Shanto to go off side, but not as short this time. Chopped into the point region
driven straight to cover as Mustafizur bowls a tight line on the stumps
speared into the pitch, back of a length outside off, pulled to deep midwicket
picks this full toss one bounce for four at deep backward square leg! Juicy outside leg, and Pant absolutely middled it as he flicked it into the gap.
forces him to cut to that fielder at deep cover point again. Back of a length, slanting away from off stump, no real turn back in
punched straight to cover. Big over for India
length ball close to off stump, opens his bat face and dabs to the left of short third

big appeal, and Michael Gough raises that finger once again. Hridoy reviews, but this one looks pretty out to me... Dangled up, straightening along a stump-to-stump line, and the dip beats his attempt to slog-sweep, the ball missing the inside edge of his diagonal bat to smack his back thigh. Pitching on middle and off, impact in front of middle and off, and hitting middle and off, halfway up. Bangladesh lose possibly their most dangerous player in this sort of situation
bowls length on leg-stump, Dube turns it wide of square leg
flat, straightens towards off stump, defended back to the bowler off the back foot

steps out and  clobbers him with the spin over long-on! Some 20 metres back.  And in typical Pant style, the bottom hand came off the bat handle after he made sweet connection. Powerful swing through the line. Incredible from Rishabh
nice dip and turn from a leg-stumpish line. Looks to get forward and clip it leg side, pops a leading edge into the point region

that has been swept into the gap at deep backward square leg. Tossed up and spinning back in from leg-stump, Pant quickly goes down on one knee and sweeps him up and over. Easily done. Rishad under a lot of pressure

Shakib isn't reading Kuldeep yet. Goes back to a length ball that I think he thinks is a wrong'un spinning into the stumps. Ends up being the stock ball, and his attempt to work the ball leg side turns into a hurried stab backward of point

comes back with a wicket! Doesn't hold back as he mouths a send-off to Pant, who in trying to keep up with the aggression has reverse swept this tossed up delivery straight to short third. End of an excellent innings nonetheless.
length ball on middle stump, reverse-swept towards deep point
drills this to cover where a misfield allows Hardik to get off the mark
tossed up full on middle and leg, clipped to deep midwicket
works this gently into the leg side for a single
fires this in but loses direction and bowls down leg, left alone works this tossed up delivery to deep midwicket
and Shanto puts away a hit-me ball. Drags it down while attempting the seam-up arm ball, and Shanto rocks back to pull it handsomely over midwicket for six
drops short and Hardik rocks back to cut to the sweeper
slanted away wide of off stump, looks to slash and misses
cuts straight to point as this skids through a tad low outside off
length ball, turning down leg, misses the flick and is hit on the pad
slaps this to sweeper cover
full on the stumps, clipped to long on
nudged gently into the leg side for a quick single
back of a length, slanting away from off stump, no turn back in. Looks to force it away off the back foot, into the covers, and is beaten on the outside edge
shortish on off, punched to cover. Quiet over following on from the wicket
looks to use that angle again but offers too much width this time. A touch short too. Frees his arms and slashes hard, gets a thick edge that flies into the gap between backward point and short third
length ball wide of off stump, reaches out and slaps to deep point
steered down to third man for a single

tossed up, turning away from off stump, and that's a good hit from Shakib. A straight slog-sweep. Gets his front leg away from the line of the ball to make hitting room, and launches it high over the non-striker
attacks his ribs with a short-ball, Dube mistimes a short-arm jab to square leg

got him now, lovely change of pace from Kuldeep. Dares him to try another big hit by looping it up slightly wider and a lot slower, and I think he released it from quite a way behind the crease too. Shakib looks to go over the on side, but the ball lands shorter than he expects, turns away, and the top edge balloons out to extra-cover, who judges the over-the-shoulder effort excellently
skiddy length ball on middle and leg, tucked to mdiwicket

what a ball. Mahmudullah didn't pick it at all. Loopy, dipping ball that pitches on off stump, and the dip firstly makes Mahmudullah reach well in front of his body to try and work it leg side. But he can't, because it's the wrong'un, and it rips past his outside edge. Does well not to overbalance and get stumped
punched into the gap at point, square third comes around quickly to keep it to a single
fullish on middle and leg, clipped away to the right of midwicket
attacks the stumps with a length ball, tucked to square leg as he jogs the single
now the wrong'un to the left-hander, but it's just about short enough for Shanto to play comfortably off the pitch, shuffling across to work it to deep midwicket
pulled in front of square to deep midwicket
shortish, slanting across to off stump, pulled to deep square leg
mistimes a slog, off the toe-end as it rolls to long-on
shortish outside off, the attempted pull hits the bottom half of the bat and rolls to the right of long-on
pushed through quicker on the stumps from around the wicket, punched to long-on
sees Shanto attempt to create room and bowls it well down the leg side, a shortish ball at his hip. Pulled round to fine leg. Ah, leg bye is the signal, probably off the thigh pad
slapped over cover! Mahedi bowls an absolute half-tracker, there's enough width on offer too and Hardik holds his shape and belts that with the wind.
back of a length outside off, and that's lovely from Mahmudullah, opens his bat face slightly on the punch to place it between short third and deep backward point
more misery for Mahedi! Hardik's tremendous forearm strength to the fore as he drills this through extra cover and picks the gap in the deep. Super stuff.
back-of-a-length offcutter coming in from outside off, hops across and tucks it into the mid-on region
punched to long-off
slower bouncer, finishing above the stumps at head height. Early on the hook, and the ball smacks the back of his helmet
tucked to deep square for a single
length ball, straightens a touch close to off stump. Stays on the back foot and punches watchfully into the covers
can't pick the gap on the off side, hit straight to point
length ball close to off stump, presses forward and dabs to deep third with an open face
slog-swept but the timing's off, good work in the deep as the two converging fielders come up with a fine tag-team effort

gone. Length ball, slanting across, looks like the slower offcutter too. Looks to clear his front leg and hit over the on side, and he's working against the angle, the movement, and a bit of extra bounce too. Best of luck doing that against Bumrah. All he manages is a top-edge to Arshdeep at deep third
fired full but down leg as Dube misses the sweep nails one finally!  Shakib drops short but Dube advances and pulls him wide over long-on. Clean strike that should give him a lot of confidence
and Bumrah greets him with a pinpoint on-pace bouncer. Looks to hook, and the ball zips past his helmet. Good thing he'd stepped across and got himself out of the ball's line
fired full on the stumps again, worked to deep midwicket
back of a length outside off, looks to steer it to third, ends up inside-edging into the square leg region
eased into the gap at point with the spin
full-toss on the stumps, doesn't middle the flick at all. Loops up briefly and bounces in front of deep backward square leg coming in off the boundary
shortish, Dube makes room and slaps it to deep cover

full, slanting away from off stump, and it's the slower ball. Not sure where Jaker was looking to hit that, initially, but he's early on his shot and ends up dragging it towards deep midwicket, off the lower part of the inner half of his bat. No timing or power whatsoever, and Kohli takes a simple catch running in from the boundary
sliced over the infield, on the bounce to third man
back of a length, slanting away from off stump, beats the attempted steer behind point
full, a hint of tail in from middle, driven back. Good stop on his followthrough
back of a length outside off, jumps across and opens his bat face to neatly pick the gap between backward point and deep third
pats this slower length ball down to third man
slower length ball angling into the seventh-stump channel. Throws his bat at it and gets a thick edge down to deep third
right into his swinging arc and Dube has bludgeoned that down the ground! Slower and fuller delivery angling away, Dube had a free swing of the arms as he made sweet connection. That should be eight
shortish outside off, opens his bat face for a chipped punch to the left of deep cover point
swung away into the leg side, towards wide long-on

bang. Thumped away by Rishad. Another slower ball angling across, but it's not angled far enough across to get outside Rishad's reach, and it's short enough for him to adjust to the lack of pace and pull fiercely over midwicket
cuts well but hits it straight to backward point

fullish outside off, shapes to hit over the covers, I think, and he's early on his shot and drags it along the ground through midwicket. I think Axar has been warned for taking too long (more than 60 seconds) to start this overs
that has been sent into the party zone beyond the boundary at deep midwicket! Half-tracker from Rishad, Dube transfers weight back in a jiffy as he muscles that. Biiiiig hit
shot! Rishad is showing some ability here. Tossed up into his arc outside off, and he frees his arms and launches it clean over the long-off boundary

this man has a big heart!  Generously tosses it up, very brave of him to do so, Dube gets enticed into the big hit again but gets this to dip and spin back in to beat Dube's almighty heave. Clean bowled.
slowish length ball outside off, swept along the ground theough square leg
heaved away to deep midwicket to get off the mark
length ball outside off, no timing on this slog down to long-on, along the ground
too short, Hardik rocks back and slaps it uppishly to deep point
back of a length outside off, not quite short enough to pull, inside-edged into the ground near the keeper's feet
too much flight and Hardik goes straight down the ground to clear the sightscreen mighty comfortably.

lovely use of the feet here, jumps out and gets to the pitch of this off-stumpish ball and swings freely through the line to launch it straight back over the bowler's head. Another clean, clean strike
beauty! It's the extra bounce that beats a jabbing Hardik.
shortish on off stump, pulled on the bounce to deep midwicket
beaten by a skiddy length ball that keeps a tad low as it angles away
hard length, into the pitch, angling in towards off stump. Looks to make a bit of room and flat-bat that, but he's cramped for room, hits it on the bounce to extra-cover
scythes this to deep point

and again, hard length and that angle into off stump. I think Rishad is looking to pull this, but he's hurried into his shot and completely cramped for room. All he can do is flap it straight to that man at extra-cover
beaten by the short ball angled into the body. Hardik was looking to arch back and ramp it but is beaten for pace
back of a length outside off, beats the outside edge as he looks to steer it down to third
flat hit for six! Tanzim bowls a back-of-the-hand delivery into the pitch, but this sits up nicely for Hardik to hold his shape and muscle it over deep midwicket.
length ball angling into middle stump, steps across and can't place that clip past midwicket
high full toss, sliced to long-off
a rarity, a boundary off Bumrah, and he finishes with 2 for 13 off his four. Shortish in the corridor, and he lets it come on and dabs it fine, beating deep third to his left
beaten as he tries to arch back to ramp it wide of the keeper

they could still win this if Arshdeep keeps bowling this ball. Slower ball goes wrong, ends up as a wide well down the leg side. Left alone this time the slower short ball comes out just right, angling across Mahmudullah and losing a lot of pace off the pitch, so it bounces a second time before it reaches the keeper. Mahmudullah looks to pull, and the ball dips below his bat
off a thick edge and it flies wide of short third! Hardik was looking to heave this over deep midwicket
fullish on middle and leg, whipped to deep square leg
slapped to deep point
slower length ball outside off, chopped to deep cover point
pulled away towards deep midwicket

oooh, nearly bowls him around his legs! Steps a long way across his stumps and misses the flick off the full ball pitching outside leg. Doesn't miss leg stump by much at all. Mahmudullah wants a wide, but the umpire points out that it would have been perfectly okay if he'd not moved across

walks across and scythes this yorker-length delivery into the gap between deep cover and deep point.  Mustafizur has overstepped to gift Hardik a no-ball. off the toe-end but the ball flies off the edge past the keeper for four! Fizz went fuller but ended up bowling a low full toss.

eight down. Arhseep bowls the slower bouncer again, and gets it up around throat high. Mahmudullah can't really keep the pull down, and he can't really power into it either, and Axar takes a good catch to his left at deep backward square leg
floats this full and way outside off, Hardik tries to reach out to slice this over the infield but misses. Wide beaten as he tries to swipe this over midwicket. Kept a touch low as it skidded through
and that is that. Slower length ball outside off, flat-batted to long-off, and India win by 50 runs

scythed over short third! Brilliantly done to finish with a 27-ball half-century. Mustafizur attempts yorker from around the stumps to tuck him up, but ends up bowling this a touch outside off, Hardik uses the depth of the crease nicely and then jams his bat down with the perfect angle to hit him up and over the fielder inside the ring. Superb finish for India.
Quick and flat to start, angled in. Rifles into the thigh guard
Movement straight away! My word. Back of a length and this just rears up and seams away. Head had no clue as this whizzed past
Clattered but straight at backward point. Mathew Wade with a false cry for a catch, to the bemusement of everyone else
fuller around off, some nice shape away. Defended into the offside
Beats everyone! This goes past Gurbaz's edge as he looks to heave it down the ground, but runs away fine past the keeper and third man

What a start for the Afghans! Head is gone! Naveen has absolutely arrowed in and clattered into middle stump here. What a peach. Outswinger, pitching on a good length and straightening on middle - maybe even going away a touch. Head has a big swing but gets nowhere near it
Angled in on the pads, tucked onside for one
good length from over the wicket as Marsh looks to go with angle and pick this up over the onside. Ball ends up bobbing up off the front pad
Poked into the offside off a length
full and straight from wide of the crease, tucked towards square leg for one
Back foot punch towards point
Warner looks to charge but Naveen drags it back outside off. Warner ends up with a uncertain waft and misses
glanced off the pads! This was slightly off line, no bat but enough on it to take it past short fine
Inside edge for four! This nips in off a back of a length, Gurbaz is cramped for space on the cut and gets a fortuitous inside edge that races away
Nearly! This was full and swinging in towards middle and leg. Marsh has a big swing, and just about gets bat on this. Inside edge in front of square leg for a couple
back of a length outside off, left alone
Glorious! Another inswinger, but this time slightly overpitched. Driven exquisitely straight of mid-off. Timed this perfectly
good length on the money around off, gets forward and pushes this towards point
better length on off, drives again but it's off the inside half of the bat towards mid-on
Left alone outside off
Swing and a miss! Warner looks to swing this right across the line and take it from a length wide of off. The movement takes it past through to the keeper
Scuffed away towards mid-on as Gurbaz looks to charge and swing this away unconvincingly
back of a length, seams in this time. Defended off the back foot
Play and a miss! This is a good length outside off, bit of seam away. Gurbaz looks to punch this on the up but is beaten by the movement
good length on off, reaches for this but only gets the drive as far as point
Lofted over cover! Touch full outside off, plants a strong front foot and eases this over the infield. Nicely timed
skids through on the stumps, pushed back towards Agar
good length on off, pushed towards cover
good length angled in, makes room and punches this inside out past extra cover for a couple

Big, big wicket! Marsh was looking good but he's gone now!  Naveen goes wide of the crease and angles this in full on off. Marsh can't help but go for the drive, but this one is a slower one. Marsh is way to early on the shot and can only hit this one straight up in the air. Nabi snaffles it with glee at mid-off
Induces the edge! This one holds up off a good length. Ibrahim leans forward for the drive as the edge goes towards backward point
full and angled in, no bat but as this deflects off the pads
length on with the arm around off, knocked back towards Agar
full from around the wicket, worked behind square leg off the pads for one
good length on off, punched straight to cover
another slower one. Full outside off, and deceives Maxwell who is early on the drive here. Inside edge into the pads
back of a length, shaping away from off. Opens the face and runs this down behind point
back of a length outside off, rears up past Gurbaz
good length, angled away from off. Nicely takes this on the up and carves it down towards deep backward point
Back of a length, 129kph, but some tennis ball bounce through to the keeper outside off. Gurbaz pulls out of the stroke
Slower one at 115kph, yorker length on off shaping in. Squeezed out into the offside for one
Wafts and misses! Back of a length again outside off, seams away just enough to beat the edge
back of a length, pitches middle and nips away. Maxwell just about pulls his bat in in time
And another that holds up in the surface and seams away. Gurbaz lowers the bat late as this loops past
swing and a miss as Maxwell attempts and fails to drives this fuller one angled away outside off
Gurbaz showing some intent as he charges down the track, but it's back of a length and straight which forces him to adjust and poke this towards the stacked offside field
good length angled in, worked in front of midwicket for a couple
Finally gets a hold of one! This was a touch fuller from Cummins, and Gurbaz needs little invitation. Leans back and muscles this high and straight back down the ground. Just over the ropes
good length, nips away and keeps low just outside off. Warner plays and misses, but it bounces in front of the keeper who can't collect cleanly
good length seaming in, pushes at this leaving a fair gap between bat and pad as the inside edge takes it towards backward square leg
Flicked fine! Back of a length but too straight. Warner steps inside the line and just glances this nice and fine. Fine leg was in the ring and had no chance
Lovely delivery. Pitches just outside off and seams away. Gurbaz pushes at it and is beaten on the outside edge
full on off, driven straight to mid-off
Fantastic riposte! Down the track and swung away high and handsome over long-on! Great intent from Gurbaz
PIcked up exquisitely! Those strong wrists at play here as Maxwell just takes this fullish one from off and whips it in front of square leg
Once more down the track but Hazlewood drags the length back. Pushes and runs towards cover
fuller and wider, carved away but straight to the man at point
Flicked away fine! A rare loose delivery from Hazlewood as he strays on the pads. Fine leg is quite square and it gives Ibrahim a big space fine behind the wicket to get this away
nips in off a back a length, raps Maxwell high on the knee roll
back of a length on off, punched off the back foot to the man at cover

and he strikes straight away! Warner looks to go after him from the off, trying to sweep this from outside off. But he's always reaching for it and can only end up top edging this straight to the man at short fine
back of a length just outside off, chopped behind square. Short third with a good dive to his right to keep this to only one
good length on off, defended watchfully
Gurbaz cops a blow on his hip. Looks to make room and swing this away, but Cummins jags this back in and follows him
fuller on off, looks to work this onside but not past square leg
Oh dear, sloppy stuff in the deep! This was taken off a length and swung away in front of square leg. Agar is the boundary rider, and he gets to it comfortably but lets it bobble through his hands
short of a length on off, swept away nicely but there's a man at deep square leg to collect
Nearly a blinder by Zampa, but four more! This was carved inside out over cover and Zampa on the boundary line gets a hand on it with a despairing dive, but only manages to parry it past the ropes
good length just outside off, backs away and looks to push and run, but cut off by cover rushing in
back of a length angled in, tucked off the hips for one
darted in on the pads now as Maxwell again fails to get it way
short of a length on off, Gurbaz backs away and dabs this to short third for a quick single
good length on off, leg break. Forward defence towards cover
length on the pads, tucked through square leg for one
Lovely stroke! Skips down, gets to the pitch, and lofts it down the ground flat
fired in on off, 98kph, pushed off the back foot towards point for a single
good length on off, carved through cover
floated fuller, 97kph, driven towards wide long-off
Full on off, once more finds the boundary rider on the cover boundary
Pulls out the reverse with precision! This is quick and full on middle and off, but Maxwell is in position early and he gets this fine past short third
tossed up on leg stumps, nudged for a single in front of square leg
full on middle, 95kph, pushed straight to point
tossed up on off, opens the face on the drive and gets this behind point for one
Maximum from Maxwell! This was in the slot and Maxwell said thank you very much, as he got on one knee and absolutely walloped this slog sweep over deep midwicket
darted on the pads, but only as far as short fine
Rips one past the outside edge to start! This was a widish leg break that Stoinis missed on the drive
full and straight, worked through square leg
Strikes the front pad as Stoinis misses the reverse, appeal but not given. Just striking outside off, looks like

back of a length outside off, slapped into the covers. Nearly a mix up though as Gurbaz wants the second and is nearly halfway down the track before being turned back. Throw is at the wrong end though
full on the stumps, eased down to long-on
good length, pushed back towards Maxwell
good length googly on the pads, worked straight to backward square leg
Extra bounce! This was outside off and quicker, Ibrahim looks to cut it but is beaten by the bounce
goes back and punches this legbreak back to Rashid
Sharp turn down leg, this one might have hit a crack punched off the back foot towards mid-off for one
slides it down leg tossed up on the stumps, opens the face and drives this through cover for one
floated up on off, eased down to long-off

Loose start! This was full but down leg, no chance for the keeper and it races away to the fine leg boundary tossed up, and huge appeal for leg before. Stoinis is struck on the pad as he misses the sweep. At the final second Rashid takes the review. This looked like it was pitching outside leg stump on first glance, and it indeed ball tracking confirms that this is the case. Review lost
Steps across the line and looks to sweep. It's the top spinner from Zampa that strikes the front pad, but this is outside the line of off
good length on middle and leg, knocked back to Noor
quicker and fuller, Gurbaz backs away and drives this. But straight to cover
Nails the sweep! Tossed up outside off, but Stoinis manages to drag this to the deep square leg boundary. Absolutely rockets over the surface
Excellent work in the deep! Gurbaz clobbers this sweep, but Cummins hauls it in brilliantly with a dive and saves two
length ball on off, cut square for a single
good length on off, driven to long-off for one
Plays and misses! Maxwell again looks to reverse, but this time can't connect as it goes through to the keeper
darted in fuller, punchy drive straight to cover
full on off, pushed square on the offside for one
angled down leg, gloves this sweep into Wade's pads
length outside off, carved through cover point for one
good length wide of off, looks to cut and misses
good length on the stumps, nudged into the onside for another single
fuller and slower on the pads, gently worked towards square leg, and they run hard to make two
good length googly down leg, goes back and works this square on the onside
good length, off break on the pads, goes back and tucks this through square leg for another single
googly again, this time punched down to long on
goes back again and this time works it down to long-on
Cracking stroke! This was tossed up outside leg, but Maxwell makes room and carves this inside out through extra cover. Finds the gap with precision
Lovely stroke! Lands the slog sweep perfectly, and bisects the two men stationed at deep midwicket and long-on. Afghanistan going very nicely here
good length on off, pushed towards point
full on the stumps, pushed to cover
back of a length ball on off. Jags in sharply. Maxwell uncomfortably fends to the off side
full outside off, carved in the air but safe in front of cover for a couple
knocks this length ball to deep midwicket for a single
full ball on leg stump. Inside out drive to mid off

top edge and Gurbaz calls for it with two more fielders congregating! Naib brings out his guns to celebrate and the short ball does the trick against Stoinis. Extra bounce, got big on Stoinis, and all it needed thereafter was the three Afghanistan fielders not colliding behind the batter
short ball on off. Zadran backs away, making acres of room, and then frees his arms by cutting over cover!
fullish ball on his pads. Clipped to deep backward square leg

chance of a run out? Zadran lifts this full ball with the turn, hitting it over cover. But David at deep extra runs around, picks the ball up, throws it in towards Agar, and we may have Gurbaz short! He did dive... but is he save? Yes, the dive saved Gurbaz
good length ball, fourth-stump line. Blocked to the off side

takes on the fielder and succeeds in pinching two! Knocks this full ball to mid-on, and call for two. But Maxwell runs in from long-on and throws a flat one in. Inches away from the stumps at the keeper's end, and this would've definitely had Zadran struggling
still, six off the over, courtesy this boundary. Back of a length ball that sits up outside off stump. Maxwell pumps a pull in front of square. Naib is disappointed with himself
put away to fine leg! Short from Stoinis, into Gurbaz's body, and pulled fine!
turn and bounce. Full outside off. David steps back to play off the back foot. Ball turns away, to Gurbaz
fullish ball on off. Tucked away to mid-on, and this time they don't take Tim David's arm on
full ball driven to long off for a single

It's all happening - Stoinis drops a tricky chance and there's a run-out chance too! Good length ball on middle and leg. Zadran taps this with the full face of the bat, and the ball pops up. Stoinis sticks his right hand out trying to take a catch on the followthrough, and while he recovers, the batters scurry for two
into his forties... Tossed up on off. The helmet-less Maxwell clears the front leg, keeps a stable head, and then clobbers Rashid over long on
length ball on middle and leg. Knocked off his waist to midwicket for a single, but the throw from there takes an awkward bounce and Zampa - backing up - fumbles. They claim an overthrow
full ball on middle and leg stump. Turning in, hits his pad
length ball,  fifth-stump line.  Misses the cut. On the bounce to Wade
good length ball originates on off stump, turns in sharply onto Maxwell, takes a knock on his body, and very nearly hits the stumps
length ball on off and middle. Rolls his fingers over this one. Zadran misses the clip off his pads, and it hits him.
tucked off his body to the leg side, and he'll keep strike

full ball pitching outside leg. Gurbaz attempts a sweep. Misses deposited straight down! Gurbaz backs away to the leg side as Zampa bowls a full ball on leg stump. That puts Gurbaz in perfect position to hammer a shot down the V, and so he does!
full ball outside off stump and he hits an inside out drive to wide long off

full ball around leg. Gurbaz tries to nudge it, but misses. LBW appeal turned down. But Australia review. Did the ball turn enough from leg stump to stay on the stumps? Australia desperate for a wicket, but there's a spike off the bat. No LBW. Camera pans to the Afghan camp where there's a few claps and smiles.

trapped him in front? Umpire Ahsan Raza raises his finger late. David reviews after a chat. This was a back of a length ball on off that jagged into his pads while also staying low. David missed his flick, and he was hit on the knee-roll. No bat involved... and it's clipping the outside of leg stump! The decision says and Australia are 85/5
a missed stumping! Gurbaz came dancing down the track to this full ball around leg. The wrong'un fools Gurbaz, and perhaps Wade was blinded by the batter, because he can't pick the ball up clean.
gets a single on this occasion
good length ball on middle and leg. Knocked away towards mid on

play and miss. Tries to cut this length ball away from his body. Gurbaz has a throw at the stumps but misses and nobody is backing up so they concede a bye-run. Maxwell was in his crease so probably just a loose throw towards his team-mates

juicy full toss and another misfield! This time it is Agar. Full toss outside off and Zadran tonks it over cover. Agar runs around from wide long off to intercept, but he over-runs it and misses the ball altogether
full ball drilled back to Naib, who gets a fingertip to it
length ball on middle. Worked away to midwicket for a single, and they stick with one despite a fumble

up and over! Lands between long-on and long-off, and then goes for six. The straightness of the shot saved Maxwell with two outfielders lurking, and the ball lands an inch beyond the ropes. Fifty for Maxwell
back of a length delivery around off. Firmly blocked, back towards Josh
around the stumps. Length ball bit wide outside off. Wade attempts a cut. Ball stays low, and it is chopped onto his pad
Team hundred in 13.2 overs! Short of good length ball outside off. Bit of movement away. Zadran stands tall and cuts it over backward point. A third century stand for them at this T20 World Cup
over the stumps. Bowls a length ball very wide outside off. Gently cut to the fielder at deep point but he makes a mess of it, failing to grab it on the run. Janat the man
back of a length around off. Zadran offers a high-elbow punch back to Hazlewood
full ball outside off. Guided to short third for a single, and they scurry across for a quick run. Throw hits the stumps at the keeper's end but Wade was in
back of a length ball just outside leg stump. Lets it go and collects the extra back of a length ball around off. This time he rides the bounce and glances a gentle dab to short third. They pinch one
full ball just outside off stump. Rolls his fingers over this one. Pushed to cover
good length ball angling into his pads. Clipped to fine leg for a single
knocked off his pads to the leg side gently. That buys the pair a chance of nicking two runs. Smart batting, utilising the big pockets of space inside the circle
good length ball around off. Pushed towards Marsh at point for a quick single
good length ball outside off. Cut in front of square to deep extra cover and Rashid has to put in a slide after running around from wide long off
good length ball angling into Zadran. Tentatively fended towards the off side. Arm ball to start his final over
around the stumps. Length ball angling into his body. Fended to the on-side
terrific ball! Lands on middle, Gurbaz looks to close the bat's face and knock it to the leg side. But it turns sharply, past the outside edge, and over off stump
back of a length ball outside off. Cut behind square to deep backward point
slows it down. Fullish on middle. Tucked to square leg and it's a half-century for the man! Raises his bat towards the dugout. Just a little fistpump to himself to soak it in
comes over the stumps now. Digs it short and wide.  Extra bounce too. Maxwell surprised by the bounce and misses the cut. Sideways movement too.... so double whammy for the batter
full ball on middle. Turning away and carefully fended to the off side

BIG BIG WICKET! Noor Ahmad may not have bowled much, but he may have taken the most important catch of his life! Maxwell slices at this length ball outside off, and Noor at backward point dives diagonally forward to take a dipping catch!
good length ball on middle. Zadran backs away and attempts a cut. Thick edge, forcing a dive from short third to stop a potential boundary
full ball just outside off and he caresses a drive through the off side for a couple
Agar finishes with 0-17 as this full ball on leg stump is knocked towards square leg. They run across like a gazelle and that's 15 overs done
Naib closes out an important over by conceding three runs and taking the big wicket of Maxwell. This is a full ball just outside off and it was guided towards backward point
full ball on off and drilled towards long-on for a single. Fifty for Zadran too! Some Afghanistan flags flutter as he soaks in the moment

my oh my! Low, sliding catch from short fine leg but the umpire agrees its a clean catch! Rashid starts his last over by bowling a full ball  outside leg stump. The legbreak takes it further away from him, and the sweep is gloved to short fine leg.
good length ball on leg stump and following Gurbaz as he backs away, exposing all three stumps. He's cramped, and can knock it back only to Stoinis. A stare-off between batter and bowler.
full ball on leg stump, and clipped to the midwicket region for a single

responds with a six over cow corner! Good length ball around off. Spongy bounce. Gurbaz makes a bit of room, picks up the length and change of pace, and then clatters it across the line for an 84m distance
length ball on off. Turning into his pads. Clipped with the turn to short fine leg
fuller. On his pads. Played fine, to fine leg, and Warner in the deep has to slide across the carpet to stretch out and stop the boundary.
full ball on middle. Gently fended back

Stoinis with a send-off! Length ball, angling into Gurbaz, and he charges down the track before clocking a mistimed shot to the leg side. Warner at deep square leg runs in, and ensures this one sticks. Partnership broken via this slower ball
length ball on leg and turning further down good length ball just outside off. Bit of turn away. Misses the cut
full ball on off and middle. Bunted towards point for a dangerous single, and had Maxwell connected with a direct-hit, then Zadran would've been run-out too at the keeper's end
misfield from Noor, and they scurry a single much to Rashid's disappointed. Tapped to the off side for a single, but it was a dangerous single. Rashid finishes with 1-23
full ball on off. Bit of turn away. Cut to the deep for one

overpitched ball, wider outside off stump, but inside the tram-lines. Cummins misses the guide to the off side. Soft caught-behind appeal not given out. Afghanistan consider reviewing, and guess what.. they do! However, there's no bat involved. Afghanistan lose their review
full ball just outside off. Makes some room and hammers a shot through to wide long off
fullish ball outside off stump. Tries to lift it over the off side but misses
one brings two! Length ball on middle, and it skids through. Omarzai backs away to play a leg-side swipe, but he's been beaten by Zampa's guile. Leg-stump rattled

slower ball deceives Cummins, that's Naib's four! Full ball on off and this doesn't bunce much. Cummins tries to play across the line but misses. He's bowled and Naib is off in celebration. However he then takes a tumble, has he hurt himself in glee?
full ball on off. Janat fends this skiddy ball
full ball on middle, and worked off his pads to the leg side
tossed up on middle. Janat toe-ends a shot back towards Zampa, who misfields on the followthrough

chance of a run out, but Noor panics! This was played towards short third and the batters were in no position for a single, especially with the batters stranded in the middle. But Noor releases the throw a shade too early, before Gurbaz could get to the stumps

bouncer from the spinner! And Zadran gets a top-edge. Intentional or not, Zampa bowls a 98kph bouncer on an off-stump line. Gets big on the surprised batter and his attempt at a pull only gets the bat's shoulder. Short third gets under it
knocked square to the off side for a single. Naib finishes with stunning figures of 4-20
full ball just outside off. Darts through to the keeper as the batter misses the drive
length ball, quite wide. Cut to the deep for a single

and now superman Naib stuns in the field! Slot ball just outside off and Agar hammers an important cover drive with a lot of power, but Gulbadin inside the circle dives to his left and takes a low catch on his non-preferred hand! Flexes after that, showing his biceps off
play and miss. Length ball on off stump, and Rashid tried to play across the line, attempting to club it through midwicket, but he misses. He's lucky that didn't take off stump
full ball just outside off. Toe-ends a drive to the off side
short ball, wide outside off. But pace off. Rashid tries too hard to cut behind square and he misses
full ball just outside off. Gently bunted to the off side for a single

there's that slower ball bouncer, but it lobs way, way, wayyy over Rashid's head full ball just outside off. Rashid slices an off-side loft, and Head runs in from the deep but his dive is futile as the ball bursts through his hands. Dropped and they collect two
around the stumps. Good length ball outside off. Misses the cut with the ball swaying away too
short ball on middle and leg. Rashid backs away, trying to make room for a cut over backward point. But he misses and looks at the square-leg umpire asking for a potential wide
full ball just outside off. Lifted over cover but without much power. Just one. Naveen finishes with 3-20

six? No, few metres short! Fullish ball outside off. Rashid comes down the track and tries to helicopter a shot over long on. But the pace is off, and the timing is off too. Tim David at long on does the rest
full ball just outside off stump. Hazlewood attempts to hit it straight back, but goes past the bat's inside edge to Gurbaz. Shouts of shabaash from the keeper
full ball around off stump. Gently knocked back to Hazlewood
length ball around off. Pulls this slower ball to deep midwicket

full ball, wide outside off. Janat tries to cream it over cover but he slices the shot. Ball goes high up into the night sky and Agar at cover turns around to try and take a catch but the ball swirls in the air and comes down with him in a very bad position. Another dropped chance tonight
around the stumps. Full ball outside off, keeping it away from Zampa's range. Through to the keeper

full ball wider outside off. Lifts this slower ball over extra cover and it is destined for four, but Green on the boundary line swoops down and knocks the ball back into play inches away from the boundary line

important boundary for Australia as they bring the target close. Remember, even NRR is important in the grand scheme of things. This was full outside off and he backs away before slicing a lofted shot over backward point

much needed for the Afghans! Although it is a very lucky six. Full ball on middle, and Janat tries to clip aggressively over the leg side. But it takes a leading edge and flies over conventional third man! The photographer on the boundary line had to take evasive action
good length ball, fourth-stump line. Pace taken off. And the batter can only bunt it gently to the off side for a single
back of a length slower ball outside off stump. Pulled towards deep square leg but only a single

over the stumps again. Full ball around leg stump. Gently nurdled towards midwicket for a couple. The fielders try to move around to prepare for the 20th over... but a no-ball has been called! One more extra run, and a free-hit coming up. Reason: too few fielders inside the circle Hazlewood can't get bat on ball. Back of a length ball on middle, and Hazlewood tried to pull, but alas.

full ball just outside off. Nabi keeps a stable base and hammers a drive through wide extra cover. Green at long off tries to put his body behind the ball to stop the four, but on this occasion, he can't stop it, not with the pace Nabi hit that ball
full ball on off stump, and he drags a slog to deep midwicket. Does it have the legs for four runs? Nope

grabbed by David running in from long on! Cummins disguises an off-pace ball, landing it full just outside off. Janat ends up dragging a shot to wide long on where David ran in to take a reverse-cup grab
Afghanistan win! Slower ball, good length delivery around off, and Zampa's swipe across the line finds the man at long-on! Majestic scenes.

another hat-trick for Cummins! That's two hat-tricks in two back-to-back games and on both occasions its across two different overs! Cummins knows its a hat-trick, he's well aware, but the others weren't quite. This was a change-up length ball outside off and Naib can only drag his aggressive shot to the sweeper fielder on the leg side

four wickets in four? Oh no, Warner makes a mess! Back of a length ball outside off. Batter tries to cut it over the off side. Warner runs in from deep point but the ball dips late, and he can only get fingertips to it. Dropped!
back of a length ball on middle. Nabi backs away to slap it towards point but misses
edged but falls just short of Wade. The ball hits him on the knee and rolls away to fine leg. This was a slower ball, full outside off and Nabi's attempt at an off-side slap took the bat's edge
Afghanistan finish on 148/6 as Nabi finishes with a strike-rate of 250. This was a drag-down outside off and Nabi swatted it across the line to find the gap between cow corner and deep square leg
good length over the wicket, hint of swing and a very loose slappy drive, in the air and very close to Salt in the gully. Skews down to deep third
length ball, on the pads, Salt waits on the back foot, just indicating a rare hint of reticence as he blocks to the leg-side, and finds the gap for the single
leading edge, high over cover! Two very streaky shots to open the account, and perhaps a sign that there's late movement, and a bit of stickiness in the pitch
tight to the pads again, shaping into the right-hander, Buttler blocks back down the line
bursts past the outside edge, just going through on the angle as Gous plays down the off-stump line. This is a promising start from Topley
a hint of nibble outside off, leaps off the pitch past the outside edge
less promising from Topley! A leg-stump half-volley, flicked disdainfully up and over fine leg! Thuds the cushion on the full for the USA's first boundary
full length, driven firmly to short cover on the front foot
inswing on a middle-and-leg line, inside-edge into the pads
tight on the pads, deflected to the leg side, for another single

clipped off the toes, and straight to deep midwicket! Topley serves up another leg-stump half-volley, if truth be told, but this time it's a fraction shorter than a half-volley, and Gous's uppish flick lacks the power to clear Salt in the deep. England have their powerplay breakthrough
Firmly onto the front foot, punched out to cover. A solid first over from the USA's star man
turning down the leg side, decent pace and grip but on the wrong line steps into the length, angled in from round the wicket and punched back  to the bowler
full, leg-sided, thuds the pads. Lovely direct lines from Archer, too quick to flick off the toes
fraction shorter and wider, but cuffed straight at cover
slightly over-pitched but gets away with it, a low full-toss, very straight, patted back to the bowler, who claws it down with an outstretched hand
dipping into the toes, again on the angle from round, clipped to midwicket
snorter, climbing past the edge on a tight line across the left-hander. Taylor plays to defend his stumps and is lucky not to nick it
good line and length, straightening on middle and leg and drawing a respectful block
squeezed down to gully, Taylor had given up hope! Livingstone shy fizzed in at Taylor was sent back for the quick single. Could have paused a beat to compose himself
eased into the covers with a flow of the blade. All very steady Eddie
a bit of a rattled hack of a drive, at thin air outside off, keeps low through to Buttler
tidy to close the over, good length once more, on the front foot, finds the gap at mid-off
pressed on the front foot, pierces the gap in the covers but without much timing
elegant drive out to deep cover, doesn't quite have the legs to reach the rope as Livingstone slides, gathers and rises in an athletic manoeuvre
skips to the pitch in a bid to break these shackles. Not totally on top of the stroke, but lofts it over mid-off
open-faced fence out to the off-side
good length from round the wicket, hitting the pitch as Buttler defends with an angled bat to gully
fuller length, angled across the right-hander. Patted out to cover
onto the front foot, and lathered through the covers! Seized on the width early, throwing his hands through the ball as his weight leans into the stroke
punched firmly through the line, Brook pounces well, with a kind bounce helping the ball to hop into his diving grasp

blammed over the sightscreen! Right onto the roof in fact! Netravalkar returned to over the wicket, Buttler held his shape, broke his wrists up into the full length, and that's sailed 104 metres and smashed another solar panel!
drilled over the head of mid-off! A wristy drive, oodles of power through a well-planted front foot, Jordan stuck out one hand  but that was travelling
pace off, but it sails nonetheless! A one-handed wallop, Buttler was done by the change, but committed to the stroke, through the line, and lost his bottom hand in the process! Over wide long-on
back of a length, rolls into a whipped pull but Rashid behind square gathers. England are keeping it tight for the moment
back of a length, tapped into the off side for another single. England are on the move now
leaning forward to the length ball, clipped off the toes to midwicket
on the pads, nudged to the on-side
steps back for a slap into the off side
full length from round the wicket, and pressed to mid-off
cuffed off the back foot, into the off side
clobbered through long-on! Another light-footed wallop, skipping to the pitch, moving leg-side as he does so, and clean to the ropes
driven through the full length, inside-edged to mid-on
reverse-sweep, can't make contact

short, top-edged, flies over deep third! Not remotely in control but they all count. Onto Kumar before he was set, but he committed to the stroke and reaped the rewards, launching a 146kph short ball over the ropes!
gives himself room to leg, the bowler follows him well, drawing a high-elbowed push into the off-side. Beats the diving bowler for a single
gives himself room to leg, Archer fires it through on the full outside off
thuds the pads, down the leg side. A tidy over

Yikes, that's a shocker! One of the worst wides I've ever seen at international level, slung miles down the leg-side, no chance for the keeper. Didn't hit the cut strip! much better, back of a length, tightest line imaginable, blocked on the back foot
on the toes again, this time to the left-hander, who lifts a flick off the toes, short of deep midwicket
spanked down the ground once more! A lusty swing through the length ball, beats long-on
lovely strike, stepping into the full length, and launching with the angle, back over mid-on, composed followthrough too, didn't lose shape by over-hitting it
another bosh to the leg side, slightly early through the stroke so lacks the same power and timing

even better strike! Makes room to leg, Topley tries to follow him, but Kumar is wise to his wiles, and hits sweet and straight, clean through the full length and over long-on! Hell of a catch from a USA fan in the stands, one-handed! I guess that's all that life wearing a mitt...
guided with high hands, into the covers
pulls the length back a touch, poked to the off-side
full length, on the pads, clipped firmly out to deep square, Salt runs hard to turn it into two
back of a length again, pushed across the right-hander, whipped off the pads to the on-side
drilled off the front foot, through the covers! England are on the march and the top of the table is a realistic target now. This now constitutes a match, not that we are expecting rain ...
Topley gets out of his over well, a nudge to the on-side from an in-between length
a skip to the pitch, and tucked off the pads to the on-side
very full from over the wicket, wristy drive out to point
pulled in the air, but just wide of midwicket No pace through the miscue, which saved him
width, hacked, beats the wide slip! More of a short third, to be honest, and no chance of cutting that off
chipped down the ground, but beats the fielder! He slid in flat, the ball plugged in front of him, and wriggled into the rope

gobbled by Moeen at backward point! Taylor rocks back on the cut, but this was out of the back of the hand, no pace to work with, and too tight to his body too. Moeen leapt with two hands to his left and clung on superbly! 50 T20I wickets for Curran
super reverse sweep, rolling the wrists to slam through the gap behind square
round the wicket, hits a good length to the new man who leans out of his crease to block
tickled off the legs to the on-side
deliberate steer through deep third, opening the face on impact to pick off another boundary through deep third
swished out to deep midwicket, in position early for the sweep but without the timing. the sweeper mops up,  but it's another productive over for England
tapped to the on-side, much straighter line, a direct-hit at the far end  but looked safe to the naked eye. Yep, easily home
loopy legbreak to open, nice flight and lack of pace, pressed to the off side
Clipped off the legs, back for the second, the keeper takes a shy at the far end, but Salt has over-run too far and they can't take the overthrows
tossed high above the eyeline, dipping on the crease, tapped to mid-on
down the track, clipped to long-on
compact drive on the front foot, to long-off for the USA fifty
deep in the crease, flicked uppishly out to deep midwicket
rocks back on the cut, skids through a touch flatter, an under-edge eludes Buttler's gloves. Close to the off stump too
yorker length, Buttler times his drive well, out of the  blockhole, but straight to wide long-off
Googly, well disguised, turns into the pads. Can't get that away
fired past the legs, another run ticked off the requirement swinging into the pads, deflected to the on-side
fired through flatter outside off, chopped to point to complete a typically tidy over
back of a length, tight line, clubbed at the top of the bounce into the cover
full length outside off, chopped to backward point
scrambled seam, yorker length, well dug out
wide line, quicker with turn and bounce, left alone
misses his length by a fraction, and Salt deposits that through the covers! Lets his hands fly into the ball and the man in the deep has no chance
tight line, more grip and bounce past a defensive push. Lovely bowling
back of a length, lifted into the leg-side with a pull
genuine edge but no slip! It's a fast edge too as Archer can't cut that off...

attempted slower ball I think, but it's flown down the leg-side, and this one is signalled no-ball, as it was above waist-high... free hit... but an excellent response, Salt made room to leg so he held his length on a fifth-stump line and beat a stretch of the bat
made room to leg, beaten by some decent turn from an off-stump line
tighter line, pushed out to cover
lovely bowling, turn and bounce on the legbreak, Buttler gathers to complete another tidy over
flicked off the pads to the on-side
tossed up on the pads, and tucked to the on-side
flicked off the pads to the on-side
reverse-sweep, good idea but can't beat point
makes room to leg, and piles a drive over long-off!
very wide line, but perfectly inside the blue marker, on a very full length
another six, hoisted off the legs! Buttler's in a rush now... full length, on the toes, lifted over square leg!

impeccable googly! Tossed up invitingly on an off-stump line, but he turned off all the pace, relied entirely on guile and flight, dipped it in his blockhole, and it bit off the deck into the middle stump
brutality on the full length! Explodes his wrists up into the length ball and blammed over the sightscreen!
straight into the sweep to the legbreak outside off, paddled into space behind square
four in a row! Shades of Gibbs versus van Bunge now. Just muscled cruelly over the leg side!
on the legs again, nudged to square leg. Rashid is doing his thing again

w-a-a-a-a-y wide of off stump! Reload... monstrous smash over the leg side! Just violence, a roundhouse slug over the leg side. Full length, on the toes, but frankly it no longer mattered where that pitched
round the wicket for the offbreaks, punched off the front foot to long-off
back of a length, dragged to deep midwicket, gathered on the  bounce ... Buttler has the honours...
inside-out hack, up and over point. Not much power through the stroke but plugs in the deep
length ball, eased on the front foot, to deep cover
drilled firmly through the full length, to long-off. Singles will suit England fine for now
loses his shape a touch on a drag into the leg side, but it matters not
tapped off the pads to the on-side, just another single
width, back of a length, cuffed through deep third! England are into the semi-finals with a formidable display!
another sweep, but dragged a touch from outside off, backward square gathers
back of a length, pulled down into the stroke to deep midwicket, but it's another single to complete the first ten.
lands on leg and spins away sharply. Nurdled into the onside
looked like a googly, if I read his hand right. Bit full, and it was nudged into the onside
I didn't pick this one, but it was a googly again. Neither did Nitish as it raps him on the pads
goes for the booming drive and the googly burns him! Lost his shape trying to slog it straight down the ground, but that leaves a gap between bat and pad, and it smashes into the top of the stumps
prodded to gully and they scamper through for one to get Milind off the mark
backs away and places it into the offside to keep the strike
comes around the wicket, defended into the offside
defended back to the bowler
