transfers weight onto the back foot and slaps it down to long-on
skids this one through quicker at 90.7kph, gets the underedge
leans into a straight drive
dances down the track and manages to flat bat it down the ground despite Livingstone sending it wide of off stump. Great work at long-on to keep the US to a couple
opens the face and runs it down to third man
rolls his fingers over that. Anderson dabs it into the offside and Curran's errant throw allows USA an overthrow
takes a couple of steps down the track and Jordan adjusts his line and length. Slower ball into the body Anderson can only defend
full and fast - 136.1 kph. Anderson squeezes it out to long-on. USA going nowhere at the moment, really
back of a length slower ball Milind can only pull down to Curran at square leg
low full toss dug out and worked to long-off as Anderson keeps the strike
wide outside off. Looked a wide to me, but not to the ump
reverse sweeps and slaps it over gully. It's into the breeze and it sails over the rope for six. First boundary in nearly six overs
clipped through midwicket for a couple
another reverse sweep but Livingstone drags his length back and he can only cloth it into the offside
a bit of flight, clobbered straight past the bowler but only a single as Jordan mops up
top-edged, and Buttler gets underneath it to take a simple catch. There was a touch of extra spin and bounce where drew the edge, and the US lose another after a little partnership had begun to brew
slightly wide down leg and the umpire calls it glanced towards midwicket as the pair exchange ends
gives it a bit of extra air. Batter wasn't sure what to do with it and watches it hit his pad
squares him up with the googly, as the outside edge dribbles to gully
a touch short on leg stump, and it's worked to midwicket
another wrong'un that Anderson tries to heave over cow corner and misses
nearly bowled him round his legs with a googly to sign off. Anderson made room to try and slap it over midwicket but ends up missing as the ball nearly kisses leg stump.
starts off around the wicket and squares him up as he defends it back to the bowler
slightly back of a length, and Harmeet sat on it before depositing it in front of square on the offside for a boundary
goes full this time and the batter can only defend
back of a length again. Harmeet went through his shot too early as he swivelled on the pull and the ball hits him above the hip
dug out down to long-on
fast yorker from Archer to finish off. Not much you can do about this, and this is squirted out into the offside
he lay in wait for the slower ball but can't generate enough pace. Nearly ended up holing out to Bairstow at deep midwicket, who collects on the bounce
slower delivery bowled short again, flicked stylishly to fine leg, where Bairstow mops up
nails the yorker as you'd expect of Jordan, and the single to long-off brings up the 100
full and wide yorker. He dances down the track but misses
length delivery which seams away from the batter, beating the outside edge
comes down the track and Jordan bowls it slow again. Smeared through the onside for another laboured single
bangs another slower ball bouncer into the surface, and all he can do is guide it into the onside
back of the hand slower ball outside off stump, squeezed down to long-off
full toss at pace, and Moeen Ali drops a tough chance at extra cover. He jumped but only managed to get fingertips on it, which probably saved England a couple of runs as it's fielded on the boundary
read the slower ball this time, danced down the wicket and lifted it cleanly over Moeen this time, picking up four runs

sat back in anticipation of the pace on delivery, and when it came, he clobbered it over long-on. Harry Brook stood poised right on the edge and gets a desperate left hand trying to keep it from sailing over, but cannot manage it, and the US pick up six more!

slaps the full toss to long-off, but this one's easy for Chris Jordan, and Sam Curran signs off a costly over with a wicket. It was there to be hit, but Harmeet couldn't catch it out of the middle, and once it was within Jordan's grasp, Harmeet was a dead man walking
low full toss at pace. Those balls are difficult to get away, and all Anderson can do is pick out Brook at long-on. He barely needs to move a muscle as he sends Anderson on his way for a stodgy 29
swing and a miss. It was a length ball there to be hit, but when he missed it whooshed past the top of off stump

almost copy and paste, with the key difference being he knocks over off stump this time. Jordan stuck with the same line and length, and it was just too good for Ali Khan, who tried to chop it behind square

plumb in front! No doubt about that, even though Kenjige reviews. Trapped in front of middle, and he's hit half way up the shin. This will be out as soon as we're finished with the Hawkeye motions. And it is. Jordan on a hat-trick, and England one wicket away from bowling the USA out

gets a hat-trick to sign off!. The Bajan boy gets a hat-trick at the Kensington Oval, and just look at the delight on his face. His teammates mob him as the crowd cheers, and what a ball to seal it, too! Length ball that pierces the gap between bat and bat, and knocks the middle peg out of the ground. Beautiful moment, that, as Jordan leads his side off on the island he was brought up on
four to start off! Back of a length on leg stump. de Kock uses the angle and the pace to help it fine. South Africa are underway!
length just outside off. A hint of shape away and Mayers lets it go
back of a length just outside off. Curves away and de Kock taps it towards cover

back of a length on middle and leg. Mayers lets the ball come to him before tapping it past the bowler. He sets off for the single, only to be sent back, Nortje hits the stumps at the batter's end and concedes a run off the deflection
over the top! Length on middle and off. de Kock gives himself swinging room and goes through the line, banging it over mid off!

back of a length delivery that slides down leg. Some early exercise for umpire Rod Tucker early breakthrough for South Africa! Length outside off and Hope thinks he can crash this through the off side. The ball seems to bounce just a touch extra, though, and Hope can neither get under it nor get over it. Drives it uppishly and Stubbs snaffles it up at cover point. Just the start the Proteas would have been after; just what WI did not need!
deft touch! Slower but shorter on middle and leg. That allows de Kock to stay back and then open his bat face to glide it to backward point's right!

sprayed down leg, and Jansen will have to reload. Had Pooran got a bit of bat on it, that would have raced away to the fence angled in on a length on middle and off. Nips back, goes past the inside edge and raps Pooran on the thigh pad
back of a length just outside off. Spins back into de Kock and he stabs it towards mid wicket
banged in short but well down leg. Third wide of the over fullish in the channel just outside off. Pooran goes searching for it and squirts it off the inside edge towards fine leg
length on middle and off. de Kock chooses to stay back and plays it towards mid wicket
ouch! Bumper on middle and leg. Mayers gets into a slight tangle and cannot get out of the way in time. Takes his eyes off it too and cops a blow on the shoulder blade

and he gets rid of Pooran! Dangles the carrot outside off and Pooran bites. Steps down the track and tries to smash it into next week. Does not get to the pitch of the ball, though, and has to reach out. Clinks it off the bottom half of the bat and long off makes no mistake under the high ball. Pooran was also hitting into the wind and that might have played a part too. A hush around the ground, and the West Indies in an early spot of bother!

big appeal, but umpire Alex Wharf is unmoved! Back of a length delivery that slides down leg. Hendricks tries to glance it fine and there is a noise as the ball passes him. Pooran thinks it is off the bat, and the West Indies go upstairs. Did it brush the thigh pad or was it off the bat? Clear spike when the ball is next to the bat, and Hendricks has been strangled down leg!
and Chase goes after it first ball! Fullish outside off and no half-measures from the new batter. Plants his front foot and lofts it over mid off!
back of a length outside off. A hint of shape away and Markram scuffs it towards extra cover
fuller, angling into middle and leg. Chase comes forward and turns it towards deep mid wicket. Just a hint of spin
hard length just outside off. Markram gets up on his toes and punches it towards mid off
full outside off. Mayers drills it towards extra cover
safe! Length outside off. Markram goes after it and gets under it too much. Luckily for him, he gets enough on it to clear mid off
slower and shorter outside off. Sticks in the surface and Mayers jabs it towards point
off-pace on a full length on leg stump. Markram tips it to mid on and hares across to the other end
flighted up full on off. Mayers seems to shape for the sweep initially before changing his stroke and prodding it towards short third

Russell has two in the over, and the crowd comes alive at the Sir Vivian Richards Stadium! Banged into the track on middle and leg, and de Kock thinks the length is ripe for his trademark pick-up shot. Attacks it but does not account for the slight extra bounce. Gets big on him and he splices it straight down Rutherford's throat at deep backward square leg!
ripper! Fizzed through on a length outside off. Drifts into Markram before pitching and snaking away past the outside edge
full toss on middle and off that seems to shape away late. Chase is squared up (and surprised) and skews it off the leading edge through cover
length outside off. Markram opts to stay back and dabs it towards backward point for a single
more swing for Jansen but this starts on leg and goes further down. Fourth wide he has given up already length on middle and off. Chase presses half forward and plays it back to the bowler
full just outside off. Stubbs comes forward and pushes it past short extra cover to get off the mark
zipped in on a length on leg stump. Chase misses his flick and gets pinged on the pads. Chase unhappy with himself for having missed out
back of a length on off. Markram pushes it towards short extra cover, who misfields but ends up parrying it towards cover
picks the gap! Fuller outside off and Chase pounces. Springs forward, opens his bat face at the last moment and threads it between point and backward point!
gets it through! Darted in fuller on middle and leg. Markram unfurls the reverse and nails it to backward point's left!

goes straight up, and it goes down! Hard length on off. Chase has a massive swipe across the line and the ball slices high up into the air. Nortje settles under it at mid on but cannot hold on to a chance in front of his face. Huge moment in the game!
full on middle and off. Markram comes forward and knocks it to long off

more fortune for West Indies! Sharp bumper on middle and off, and Mayers is not going to be sending Jansen any Christmas cards for this hostility. Tries to get out of the way and the ball brushes the top edge, flying over the keeper's head!
back of a length outside off. Spins back into Chase and he tucks it towards square leg
dug in short on off. Markram hops up onto his toes and turns it into the wide mid on region

oh! Length ball that pitches just outside off and spins back in considerably. Chase looks for the sweep and misses. Not far away from leg stump but called a wide back of a length, starts on the stumps, grips and spins down leg. Another wide back of a length on middle and leg. Chase stabs it with the turn towards square leg
almost! Back of a length just outside off. Skids onto Stubbs and he nearly chops it back onto his stumps
tossed up full outside off. Chase plants his front foot and hacks it towards deep mid wicket
back of a length outside off. Stubbs gets on top of the bounce and punches it towards cover point
darted in on a length on middle and off. Mayers, caught on the crease, plonks it into the mid wicket region
banged in shorter outside off. Stubbs rolls his wrists over it and short-arm jabs it towards mid wicket
back of a length on off. Chase hangs back and pokes it towards deep mid wicket
crrunnchheedddd! Marginally short outside off and Markram climbs into it. Stands up on his toes and crunches it between extra cover and cover point!
floated up full on middle and off. Mayers gets down on one knee and hoicks it towards deep mid wicket. Just a single
back of a length just outside off. Markram opens his bat face and runs it down to short third
full on middle and off. Markram advances and pushes it towards mid on for a sharpish single
Mayers welcomes Maharaj with a boundary! Shortish outside off and the width is the problem for Maharaj. Mayers opens up the off side and knifes it to cover point's right!
length just outside off. Stubbs stays back and taps it towards short extra cover
back of a length on the pads. Mayers tucks it away into the mid wicket region
picks the gap perfectly! Shorter and wider outside off. This gives Stubbs the room he is looking for and he cracks it to short extra cover's left!
short outside off. Chase hops back and jabs it towards extra cover
lovely batting! Short and wide outside off again. Stubbs sits deep in his crease, gets his hands through the ball and knifes it to cover point's left!
fuller just outside off. Chase looks for the drive but scuffs it towards extra cover
angled in on a back of a length on leg stump. Stubbs helps it round the corner towards short fine leg
pushed in on a back of a length on the stumps. Chase plays it back to the bowler
shorter on leg stump. Markram looks for the pull and squirts it off the inside edge towards short fine leg, where McCoy dives over it and ends up conceding an extra run

in the air, and the wind takes it past the fence! Given a bit of air on a length on off. Chase unfurls the slog sweep but has to reach out for it a shade. Does not middle it but hits it with the breeze, and the ball carries over the deep mid wicket fence, with a slight helping hand from the sweeper!
full outside off. Mayers comes forward and pushes it towards short third
slanted in on a length on middle and leg. Stubbs tucks it off his pads towards deep backward square leg
full down leg. Mayers sweeps it towards square leg, who misfields and ends up conceding a single. Oh, looks like that was hit uppishly and Maharaj grassed it. That will go down as a chance!

Markram perishes! And Joseph rips this game open! Fullish just outside off and with mid off up, Markram thinks he can slam this downtown. Does not quite get on top of the stroke, though, and the bat face opens upon contact. Gets height but no distance and mid off, back-tracking a couple of paces, takes the catch. West Indies have the breakthrough they would have wanted after the rain break!
full just outside off. Chase gets forward and shanks it towards long on
length in the channel just outside off. Klaasen presses half forward and guides it with an open bat face towards third man
back of a length outside off. Straightens off the surface and breezes past Mayers' flailing blade
length just outside off. A bit of extra bounce and the ball seems to kiss the shoulder of the bat, trickling away towards third man

huge appeal, and given straightaway! Reviewed even quicker! Full on middle and leg. Mayers has an almighty hack across the line and seems to miss it, getting pinned on the back leg. The quickness of the review, though, suggests he might have gotten a scratch to it. Seems to be a clear enough deflection and UltraEdge confirms it. Mayers survives!

oh dear! Banged into the track outside off. Sails over Klaasen's head and Pooran cannot collect it either. Pooran could have made a better fist of it, and those are five runs WI could have been better off not giving away! hard length just outside off. Klaasen gets behind the line and plays it back to the bowler
pick the bones out of this one! Tossed up slightly on middle and leg, and that is all Mayers needs. Dances down the track and smokes it over long on!
back of a length outside off. Klaasen waits for it and dabs it down to third man
and Motie gets deposited into the stands! Floated up into the slot on middle and off. Klaasen establishes a strong base and thumps it into the sightscreen!
fired in full on the pads. Chase works it enough to deep mid wicket's left and Mayers scurries back to complete the second/ A direct hit might have had him in trouble
full just outside off. Klaasen looks for the big shot again but can only shank it towards long on
shorter outside off. Spins away and Chase cuts it towards deep cover point
flighted up full outside off. Stubbs reaches out for it and pushes it to long off
length just outside off. Mayers opts to stay back and wafts at it. The ball spins back, keeps a little low and sneaks under his bat
agonizingly past Chase at backward point! Shortish outside off. Klaasen rocks back and throws the plumbing at it. Chase flies to his left but cannot get close enough to it!
length on middle and leg. Mayers gets down on one knee and chips it towards deep backward square leg
four more! The wheels are coming off for the West Indies! Darted into the pads, and that is a freebie. Klaasen uses the angle and glances it past short fine leg!
lobbed up on a length outside off. Chase punches it towards extra cover, who misfields and concedes a couple of runs. More shabby work in the field from SA
20 runs off the over! Back of a length just outside off. Klaasen has another hard slash at it and the ball hurtles away off the outside edge, past the keeper!
full on middle and off. Chase lunges forward and slices it towards short third to retain strike
short outside off. Chase throws his hands at it and toe-ends it towards short third
edged and four again! Test match length, in the channel just outside off. Stubbs goes feeling for it and gets a healthy nick that evades Pooran to his right!
flighted up on a length on leg stump. Holds in the surface and straightens. Mayers misses his slog sweep and wears a blow on the body
length outside off. Stubbs gets forward and defends. There was a bit of extra bounce but Stubbs got on top of it well
back of a length just outside off. Mayers stays back and jabs it towards deep cover point
hard length on off. Stubbs turns it away towards deep backward square leg and picks up another run
shortish on the hips. Chase eases it out towards deep square leg
slanted in on a full length on middle and off. Klaasen flicks it towards deep mid wicket

two fielders coming under it, but the ball clears them both! Floated up fuller on middle and leg. Mayers looks to go downtown and miscues it a touch. Goes high up and both long on and long off (Rabada and Jansen) prime themselves for a catch. In the end, the ball just clears them, and it looks like they might have collided in the process too. This does not look good. Jansen seems to have come off worse, and the physio is out to check on him. Let's hope he is alright
shorter outside off. Stubbs waits for it and eases it down to third man
back of a length outside off. Jabbed out towards extra cover

sharp bumper, and Joseph roars in delight! Serious gas on this, and it causes Klaasen all sorts of problems. Hops around his crease, trying to get out of the way but simply cannot do so. The ball keeps angling into him, from a middle and off line, and flicks the glove. Pooran has to back-pedal but watches the ball all the way into his gloves. Excellent catch, and a big wicket for WI, but is it already too late?
hard length on the stumps. Chase tips it down the ground and saunters across to the other end
length delivery way outside off. Beyond the tramlines and called a wide off-pace on a length just outside off. Stubbs presses forward and defends towards backward point
length on middle and leg. Mayers hangs back and pokes it towards mid off
length outside off. Stubbs wafts at it and chalks it down to third man
hard length on leg stump. Mayers looks to hack it away but only gets it as far as his thigh pad

back of a length delivery that slides down leg. McCoy will have to reload this too. WI simply cannot afford any extras slips this down leg again, and that is the third wide in the over back of a length outside off. Miller rides the bounce and runs it down to third man
back of a length on middle and off. Mayers, pre-empting the short ball, hangs back and prods it towards backward point
off-pace on a back of a length just outside off. Stubbs meets it right under his eyes
full on the pads. Chase uses the pace and flicks it towards deep square leg. Seemed like an off-pace delivery
that has flown away to the fence! Full enough outside off and Stubbs capitalises. Plays it late and creams it just behind point for four!

the short ball finally comes and it hurtles through on middle and leg. Mayers has a big swish at it but only connect with fresh air. Seemed a little high but the square leg umpire is happy with the height. Mayers, understandably, isn't
full outside off. Stubbs gets a positive stride in and defends
length just outside off. Miller presses half forward and nudges it in front of point
length just outside off. Chase brings out the reverse and helps it towards short third
hard length on middle and leg. Stubbs gets up on his toes and helps it behind square on the leg side
length on middle and off. Mayers comes half forward and pushes it towards backward point
back of a length just outside off. Miller plays it right under his eyes and taps it towards backward point
tossed up full and wide outside off. Mayers drags it towards long on
short and wide outside off. Miller jumps up onto his toes and slaps it straight to extra cover
flatter, quicker and on a length in and around leg stump. Hurries onto Chase and he gets rapped on the pads. Pitched outside leg, though
dug into the track on middle and off. Miller sizes it up early enough and sways out of the way
back of a length just outside off. Chase plays the trajectory and stays back, stabbing it towards extra cover
shortish just outside off. Miller runs it down to third man and retains strike
very full outside off. Chase squeezes it out past extra cover and picks up a single
back of a length outside off and this keeps awfully low. Miller was looking for the cut but saw the ball squirm under his bat
back of a length delivery, angling into leg stump. Chase has a hack at it and misses. Thuds off the back leg towards backward point
length outside off. Skips off the surface and Miller, wafting at it, is beaten for pace
shortish outside off. Chase gets on top of the bounce and jabs it into the off side
hard length, slanting into off stump. Miller plays it back to the bowler
back of a length just outside off. Mayers gives himself room and powers it straight to extra cover

dug in short on off. Sails over Miller's head and called a wide on height. Russell not best pleased with that decision back of a length just outside off. Rushes onto Miller and he defends, having taken his bottom hand off the bat. Rolls away into the on side
back of a length on middle and leg. Mayers clears his front leg and hacks it straight to Jansen at mid on
back of a length just outside off. Stubbs advances and slashes it down to third man
double-bluffs Mayers and goes full. Ends up as a full toss on the stumps, though, and Mayers can force it into the off side for a single
back of a length on middle and off. Miller plonks it towards Russell, who sprawls to his left and saves a single
sprayed down leg. Chase fails to get bat on it and the umpire has no qualms in calling it a wide dug into the track outside off. Chase cannot get a hold of it and scuffs his pull towards mid on
back of a length on leg stump. Stubbs tucks it off his hips towards deep backward square leg. Thoughts of the second were entertained but they decided against it in the end
googly on a length on middle and leg. Chase reads it off the surface and pokes it past the bowler
back of a length on middle and leg. Miller tugs it towards mid wicket
finds the fence! Length delivery hung wide outside off, perhaps after seeing Mayers advance. He still manages to reach it and generates enough power to crash it over extra cover!
slower and fuller just outside off. Miller comes forward and pokes it towards the bowler
shorter outside off. Mayers sits back in his crease and powers it on the bounce to long off

cleans him up! Now then. Now then! Fizzed through quicker and flatter on a length on off. Miller thinks it is short enough to cut but in truth, it isn't. He plays the trajectory rather than the length, and the ball comes on with the arm to knock back off stump. Another twist in this tale?
six for Roston Chase! Right in the slot on middle and leg, and Chase does not miss out. Drops down to one knee and belts it flat past deep mid wicket!
full just outside off. Jansen comes forward and eases it down the ground to long on
fuller on middle and off. Chase unfurls the reverse and helps it towards backward point
back of a length just outside off. Stubbs taps it towards the bowler, who fields it. Just the two runs off the over and a wicket!

Mayers bites the dust! Shamsi pushes it wide on a length, and that is after watching Mayers advance. Mayers, like he did earlier in the over, has a go at it but cannot control his stroke well enough. Slices it and Stubbs, running in from the deep cover point fence, takes a comfortable catch. Shamsi is off in celebration, and Mayers departs after a 34-ball 35!
hard length on middle and leg. No room to work with and Jansen pats it towards mid wicket
short outside off. Chase goes back and cuts it towards deep cover point
vital boundary! Back of a length delivery that drifts onto the pads. Jansen can get inside the line and tickle it fine past the keeper. Loose delivery, given the circumstances
shortish outside off. Holds in the surface and spins away as Powell jabs it towards deep point
back of a length on off. Jansen lets the ball come to him before defending
back of a length on off. Chase hops back and punches it towards deep cover point
goes for the leg-stump yorker and errs onto the pads. Jansen glances it down to fine leg, who is much finer than he was at the start of the over

does him all ends up! Floated up devilishly on a full length just outside off. Drifts into Powell and drops on him late before snaking away past the outside edge. Powell over-balances, trying to prod at it and that is all de Kock needs to whip off the bails. Easy decision for the umpire, and another significant blow for the West Indies!
full outside off. Stubbs comes forward and drives it towards extra cover
length on middle and off. Spins back into Rutherford, goes past the bat and brushes his pads
speared in full on off. Stubbs gets forward and flicks it to long on to retain strike
flighted up on a length outside off. Rutherford goes feeling for it and is beaten as the ball rags past his inside edge

Stubbs departs now! And Chase is turning this game on its head! Fullish on off, and Stubbs thinks he can deposit this into the ocean. The ball, though, sticks in the surface just enough and seems to get big on Stubbs. Does not get the contact he desires and spoons it straight to Mayers at long on. Wow, this game is alive!
very full on leg stump. Chase digs it out towards the bowler
shortish outside off and this spins back a mile. Almost cuts Maharaj in half and he does well to get some bat on it
shot! Tossed up into the slot just outside off. Chase plants his front foot, swings through the line and pops it over the bowler's head!
dragged down on off stump. Maharaj rocks back and pulls it on the bounce to long on
fuller just outside off. Chase gets to the pitch of the ball and drives it to long off. Brings up his fifty too - off 39 balls!
length outside off. Goes straight on with the arm and takes the outside edge of Jansen's bat, dribbling towards short third
shortish outside off. Fizzes off the surface and goes past Rutherford's attempted cut
length on middle and off. Jansen turns it enough to deep backward square leg's left and scampers back for two. Smart batting!

edged and taken brilliantly by Markram at slip! Given a bit of air on a length outside off. Rutherford nibbles at it without any real footwork and gets an outside edge, unsurprisingly. Flies towards Markram, who swoops down low and gobbles it up. The third umpire has a look at it and concludes the fingers are under the ball. Sharp catch by the South African skipper, and West Indies slide further into trouble!
full outside off. Jansen lunges forward and knocks it past the bowler to retain strike
full on middle and leg. Russell stretches forward and smothers it
full on middle and leg. Jansen flicks it uppishly but fortunately for him, it clears the fielder at mid wicket. Jansen gets two for his toil
length on middle and off. Chase comes forward and knocks it to long off
back of a length just outside off. Jansen gets up on his toes and pushes it towards deep cover point
shortish outside off. Grips in the surface again and Russell defends off the back foot
hard length outside off. Might have been a change-up because it meddles with Maharaj's timing. Misses his dab altogether
length just outside off. Russell has a nervy prod at it and chops it back towards the keeper

hard length on middle and off. Maharaj bunts it into the mid wicket region and Jansen calls him through for the single. Joseph not happy the run was conceded. He wanted the fielder to be sharper and more on his toes
fired in fuller and quicker on the pads. Russell eases it out to deep mid wicket to get off the mark
safe! Shortish outside off. Jansen stands tall and punches it aerially past extra cover. Russell misfields on the fence and that allows Jansen to get back for two
angled in on a length on middle and off. Chase stays back and punches it to long off
dug in short on middle and off. Jansen hops up onto his toes and drops it into the off side
length just outside off. Russell presses half forward and is content to play Maharaj out
back of a length outside off. Maharaj hangs back and stabs it towards the bowler

three for Shamsi, and the West Indies are imploding! Tossed up on a length on leg stump, and Chase's eyes light up. He tries to smack it into next week but does not get to the pitch of the ball as much as he would have liked. Miscues his slog sweep and Rabada does the rest at long on. West Indies 97-6 now!

in the air, and taken! Listen to the noise at the Sir Vivian Richards Stadium! The West Indies believe, and their fans are starting to believe too! Throws up the temptation outside off and Maharaj cannot resist it. Skips down the track, looking to go over long off but all he manages is a shanked attempt straight into Joseph's palms!
peach! Beautifully-disguised googly on a full length outside off. Hosein looks for the drive and is beaten all ends up on the inside
darted in on a length on middle and leg. Rabada nurdles it enough to Powell's left at short mid wicket and gets Jansen on strike
fuller, flatter on middle and leg. Hosein defends with a straight bat
fullish just outside off. Jansen stretches forward and whips it towards deep mid wicket. Just a single
back of a length outside off. Hosein jabs it towards backward point, who misfields and allows Hosein to get off the mark
more extras! Back of a length just outside leg. Rabada has a swipe across the line and misses. Pooran cannot gather either, and SA get two byes!
back of a length on the pads. Russell tucks it away towards deep square leg
what a shot under pressure by Rabada! In the slot outside off and Rabada climbs into it. Channels his inner Brian Lara and crunches this to extra cover's left. Long off had no chance!
Hosein ends Shamsi's spell with a boundary! Shortish and too much width on offer. Hosein camps deep in his crease and opens his bat face to steer it behind point!
Russell is up and running! And the crowd finds its voice too! Marginally short outside off and that is just what Russell is waiting for. Opens up his stance, stands tall and biffs it over long on!

Jansen finishes it with one blow! The West Indies are out, and South Africa win another final-over thriller! The crowd is stunned into silence, and that is because South Africa have come up clutch, on an evening of rain and DLS! Slot ball just outside off, and Jansen gives it the lot. Plants his front foot, swings through the line and clubs it flat over the long on fence. Did not clear the boundary by much but did so by enough. Pumped-up celebrations from those in the South African camp and from their fans, and they are now two games away from winning the entire thing!
back to back sixes for Dre Russ! Short of a length again, this time perhaps closer to the stumps. Russell clears his front leg and scorches it flat over deep mid wicket!
searing yorker, honing into Russell's toes. He nearly falls over but somehow manages to glance it away towards fine leg
back of a length just outside off. Hosein gets behind the line and plays it back to the bowler

back of a length just outside off. Zips off the surface and whistles past the bat as Hosein looks to defend. Replays, though, indicate that the ball grazed the bottom-edge on the way. South Africa did not review and that goes down as a missed opportunity!
hard length on leg stump. Hosein hops up onto his toes and drops it into the on side for a single

oh dear, Russell might have run himself out! Length outside off. Hosein dabs it towards short third and Russell is hell-bent on the single. He calls early enough but that was always going to be a risky single. Made tougher by Nortje hitting the stumps and Russell could be in trouble here. And that is indeed the case. Short by inches, and Russell has to walk back. Russell is livid with himself, and what a moment that could be in this game!
fullish outside off. Joseph presses forward and drives it enough to mid off's left to get off the mark
sharp back of a length delivery outside off. Hosein wafts at it but is beaten for pace
back of a length just outside off. Hosein wants to tip and run to extra cover but Joseph is not interested

Hosein falls too! The softest of dismissals! Length just outside off and this seems to hold in the surface. Might have been a cutter actually and Hosein is early into his stroke. Plonks it straight back to Rabada, who keeps his eyes on it and snares the chance!
back of a length outside off. Motie watches it go through to the keeper
yorker zipped into the pads. Joseph does not get bat on it and the ball deflects off his back leg behind square on the leg side
back of a length delivery angled across the batter outside off. Motie fishes at it and misses the ball by a fair margin. That was bowled at 148.9kph
back of a length outside off. Motie prods it towards backward point
streaky but WI will take it any way they come! Full toss on middle and off, perhaps a yorker gone wrong. Motie has a wild slog across the line and the ball flies off the outside edge past the keeper!

banged into the track outside off. Motie gets under it and the umpires reckon it is too high to be deemed a legal delivery back of a length on middle and leg. Motie aims for the moon and only swats away a few flies in the process
full outside off. Motie clears his front leg and continues swinging like a rusty gate. Makes no contact whatsoever
off-pace on a back of a length just outside off. Joseph has a massive mow across the line but misses it completely. That was not far away from off stump either
banged away over the fence! Half-tracker outside off and this sits up nicely for Joseph. He picks up the length early and dumps it over the deep square leg fence!
hard length just outside off. Joseph stands tall and stabs it into the mid wicket region. Just a single, and he is off-strike too

dug into the track just outside off. Motie swipes at it wildly and misses. Joseph calls him through for the bye and the bye is completed because de Kock misses his shy at the batter's end, which is then followed by Rabada doing the same at the other end
back of a length on off. Joseph backs away and tugs it towards deep mid wicket. Scurries back for two and makes it, much to the delight of the crowd
back of a length outside off. Joseph has a swing at it and scuffs it down the ground to mid off. A single to end the innings but 11 runs have come off the final over!
length ball in the corridor, gets forward and defends to cover point
big full toss! Rohit is a little surprised by that and fences it straight to backward point for no run!
back of a length, a bit of width, and that's nicely played. Gets up on his toes and punches to the left of cover point

full and wide, slashed to slip... I thought on the bounce but Australia are appealing! This came out as another full bunger on a wide line, only just inside the guides. Rohit was feeling for it and there was a loud noise before slip took the catch. But clearly on the replay he had edged it down into the ground. Bump ball, on we go
length ball tight on off stump, straightens just a touch. Defended off the back foot, square on the off side
flipped through midwicket for India's first runs! Starc gets this one to land but Rohit simply steps out and hits with the swing
fullish, close to off stump, just a hint of swing away, defended into the covers
length ball angling across, steered down to deep third

shortish, wide, and it may have kept a touch low. Goes hard at the cut and bottom-edges it, and Pant, moving to his left behind the stumps, is wrong-footed, and can't stop the ball with a dive to his right
pitched up, 137kph/85mph, drilled to cover

gone, that's a lovely delivery and an excellent catch at slip! Superb Test-match length in the corridor, classic left-armer's outswing to the left-hander, and Warner hangs his bat out - he was looking for a push rather than commit fully to defence or attack - and Suryakumar takes the edge throwing himself  to his left
good length on fifth stump, 137kph/85mph and Kohli is forward in predatory fashion, defends
back of a length, angling in towards off stump, chopped into the covers off the back foot
good length in the channel, jabbed through backward point
back of a length, angling into the hip, hops and tucks it down to fine leg
length ball, prancing bounce around the top of off. Kohli defends down into the leg side
length ball angling in and straightening a touch towards off stump, defended off the back foot into the point region
fuller, 134kph/83mph and inviting the drive, punched firmly but straight to cover

ooh, so nearly a chance! Short, and it climbs awkwardly towards Marsh's neck. Gets totally cramped on the pull, and top-edges it high over the short fine leg region. The fielder there is on the boundary, but could Pant have gotten to the ball had he moved a little quicker?

dug in, Kohli pulls... but can't clear midwicket! Tim David races across from mid-on, in fact, and gets under it comfortably, taking the catch as the ball drops over his shoulder. Hazlewood draws first blood for Australia, and it's another failure for Kohli at opener. His previously indomitable T20 World Cup average has taken a battering these last few weeks
back of a length in the corridor, steered towards deep third
pitched up, angling across from over the wicket, pushed into the off side

length ball angling into the stumps. Hangs back, stays leg-side of the ball, and looks to manufacture room to flay it through the covers, but the inward angle prevents that. Inside half of the bat and rolls gently into the off side
length on off, 135kph/84mph and Pant leans out to tap it square. Thinks about one but won't get it
low full-toss, or Marsh converts this into a full-toss by stepping out. Swings into the pads, and he clips it to midwicket
bosh, launched up and over! Full outside off and Rohit goes for broke over cover, gets a good chunk of it. First six of the innings
slower ball, back of a length and angling away from off stump. Looks to stand tall and pull, but is through his shot early and gets beaten

full, wide and clattered again! Rohit has become a free spirit at the top of the batting, and he has arrived wearing long hair, beads and baggy sweats again. Scuds into the boundary cushion at cover point, just about on the full

this time he connects with the pull. On-pace this time, shortish and angling away, but the line is just right - just far enough outside off to allow Marsh to free his arms, but not so far that he has to reach for the ball
slammed down the ground now, third boundary from successive balls! Hammered off a length over mid-on

dropped, but it's a tough chance. Steps out, and Arshdeep goes short and into his hip. Cramped on the flat-bat hit down the ground, and ends up hitting it back to Arshdeep, over his head. Jumps and gets both hands to it but can't cling on

ZOMG, tonked into the crowd at deep midwicket! Pitched up, 144kph outside off but it's basically a slot ball without much swing and Rohit ready and waiting. He was set in front of the stumps and clobbers Starc for six more over the leg side
slower length ball angling away from off stump. Not a lot of width, but Marsh gets into a nice position to punch it away crisply through cover point
wide blockhole, good response. Rohit can't chop down in time

bang, Marsh is getting the hang of Arshdeep now. Short, only gets up to waist height, and he pulls it fiercely and easily clears the square leg boundary. Axar Patel was back on the boundary, and looked to have no idea where the ball was going, but it was clearing him comfortably in any case

goes for the wide yorker again, 142kph. But this one slides outside the tramlines another full toss, top-edged for six more! Starc going around the park. This was angling across and Rohit just threw the plumbing, not too bothered about where it went (which was over deep third on the full)
length ball, fifth-stump line, and that line is too much width when you're bowling to Head. Frees his arms and just flays it away over point. Such a free, unfettered bat swing
back to top-of-off stylings from Hazlewood, Pant shows it some respect
looks to tuck Head up by going a little shorter and angling it into his body, but Head is read for it, meets the pull at just below chest height and puts it away to the forward square leg boundary
back of a length, rising in the channel outside off, 135kph. Pant cross-bats it down towards cover
goes yorker this time, outside off, and Head, well to the leg side of the ball, reaches out and fails to put bat to ball
shortish into the body, tucked towards midwicket where there's a misfield from Cummins as he dives to his right
low full-toss on off stump, and Head is up and running here. Stays leg-side of the ball and carves it away to the right of point
hard length, coming back in, 135kph. Rohit jabs down and thick-edges past his leg stump
slower ball, on a length, angling into leg stump. Tries to make room, but Bumrah has denied him on this occasion. Dabbed gently into the point region
length ball, fourth stump, chopped down to deep third
length ball angling sharply into off stump, defended with soft hands towards mid-on, who's on the edge of the circle, so an easy single can be taken
metronomic line and length from Hazlewood, defended coming across on off
length ball slanting in towards off stump, doesn't quite connect with the sweep, drags it to backward square leg

first ball goes the journey! More tonkage from India's captain, he's hit this on to the roof of the Johnson Charles stand! It was a length ball outside off, Cummins just looking to get going... instead he's obliterated 100 metres over midwicket
and again! Similar ball, similar shot, middled on this occasion, but straight to the man on the circle
banged into the deck, 140kph/87mph and Rohit is tucked up looking to work to leg
bam. Error in line, and Marsh punishes it. Slightly back of a length, but angling into the legs, and Marsh quickly flick-pulls up and over backward square leg
full, wide and slashed through backward point! Cummins had his sweeper squarer, rather than at third, and Head can't get around to cut it off
length ball keeps going with the angle from outside off, defended back to the bowler
dug in, 140kph/87mph and this zips through past the edge with Rohit looking to drive on the up
past the fielder again! Stretches out for another sweep to a ball pitching outside off, and sweeps hard and in the air, just beyond the reach of backward square leg diving to his left at full stretch
skips down, slices over the keeper! Top-edged but safe... Went almost diametrically in the opposite direction to which Rohit was aiming, but races away
slides on with the angle, sweeps to the left of deep midwicket
full outside off, dug out into the covers, that's fifty for Rohit! Coming from just 19 balls, the fastest at the tournament so far. And he's scored all but two runs of India's total!
slower bouncer, ends up well wide outside off stump, left alone fullish, slanting across, looks to slap it into thje covers, and it trickles to the keeper off the inside edge. Another slower ball
back of a length, deflected for one off the padding
on pace this time, and right in the slot for Head. Not the best bowling. Full, on the stumps, and he clears his front leg and drives with a high front elbow, up and over mid-on
looks to do something funky, nearly holes out reverse-scooping Hazlewood! Came off somewhere near the splice, maybe some glove, and fell short of two fielders in the gully region
follows Head's attempt to make room with a back-of-a-length ball at the hip, pulled along the ground to deep midwicket
shortish, swatted leg side
length ball on off stump, steps across to tuck it to the right of deep backward square leg
pitched up, 142kph, Rohit thrashes across the line, gets a thick inside edge for one
length ball angling into middle stump, clipped to deep backward square leg
short and muscled leg side! Pant steps into a pull in front of square, picks up his first boundary. Hitting with the wind and it trundles away to the rope

six more, and India's nemesis is at it again. Clears his front leg nice and early, so he has plenty of swinging room even though this back-of-a-length ball is on leg stump. Free, full swing of the bat to launch it high over midwicket
length ball, 136kph angling across, stabbed to the left of Warner at short third... he gets a hand on it and prevents four
creamed down the ground first ball! Pant skips out and blaps Zampa 85m over long-on. Welcome to the show
tossed up outside leg, swept to short fine leg
flatter, skidding outside the left-hander's off stump, chopped for one on the cut
short, deliberately slanted into a wide line outside off, slapped to the right of sweeper cover
pushed through and nudged to leg, Zampa gives chase himself
looks to sweep one that's too full and quick for it. Straight on the pad on the full, from where it bounces into his helmet. Impact outside leg, so no appeal
flat and sliding across, cut for a single
back of a length, slanted wide of off stump, slapped to sweeper cover
plants the front foot, slog-sweeps another six! Big stride and unafraid to hit against the turn, using the wind to help him out. Launched over the tents at deep midwicket
length ball turning from leg to off, makes room and punches into the covers
worked off the pads for a single to finish another big over for India
stays back to a fairly full ball turning from leg to middle, makes room to punch to sweeper cover
length ball slanting across to off stump, punched to the left of sweeper cover
length ball outside off, defended
superb shot. Slower ball, slanting a long way away from off stump, but somehow Head gets down on his back knee and basically plays a straight slog-sweep over the bowler's head
saunters out and heaves through midwicket! Stoinis aiming for a hard length but Rohit charges at him and smashes yet another boundary into the gap leg side
wow, superb. Back of a length, angling across to off stump, and he clears that front leg again and smacks it against the angle, with the wind, and all the way over the midwicket boundary
clonked into the crowd, six more! Into the breeze, I think, but it flew over deep backward square leg... Rohit is chuckling as he walks down the pitch. He's picking out spectators at will

this time he's hitting against the wind and he miscues it, but the ball hangs in the air and drops just out of reach of Rohit running to his right at cover. Fullish offcutter angled into that wide line outside off, and Head was looking to slog it over the on side or down the ground, and ended up slicing it
spanked over cover ON THE UP! Waltzes down and plays this like Stoinis is some luckless clubbie who's won a competition to bowl. Laced into the boundary boards with a full extension of the arms
slower bouncer, and Marsh didn't seem to pick it at all, pulling out of his attempt at a hook and ducking his head, and it ends up bouncing loopily over his left shoulder and down the leg side
slower short ball outside off, flat-batted down to long-on

miscued and taken! Stoinis hits back, gets Pant off a leading edge at long-off. Takes some of the heat out of the situation for Australia, even if it's not the batter they really want. Pant was looking to flick over the leg side but it ballooned to off
clipped down the ground
low full-toss on middle and leg, clipped down to long-on
90kph and driven into the pitch, tucked off the hip
makes room against a length ball turning from leg to middle, punches to deep cover point
hung enticingly wide of off, 91kph and Rohit reaches for it, slices to deep point on the bounce

did Marsh lift his foot? Rohit at slip thinks so, but Pant not so much, from their respective reactions. Floats this wide of off stump, and Marsh stretches out to sweep and almost overbalances. Pant whips off the bails, but was his foot grounded? Yeah, grounded right through
floated full, punched square, finds the gap! A crisp square drive, breaking the wrists and beating the dive of Warner running around in the deep
short, angling away wide of off, flat-batted down to long-on. He's used this line well as a defensive option today
straighter and nudged off the pads
short, wide, and there's protection out at deep cover point for the back-foot slap
pushed through flat, 94kph on the stumps. Rohit leans into a whip for one out to deep midwicket

WHAT A CATCH, AXAR PATEL!!!!!! That's a really good hit from Marsh in every way other than placement. A touch short from Kuldeep, turning in towards leg stump, and Marsh gets down on his back knee for that pull-sweep that he plays so well. Nails it, and it's travelling at speed, but Axar times his jump perfectly at deep square leg, stretches his right hand up over his head, and plucks the ball out of thin air
bad ball to Head. Back of a length, slanting across to finish outside off. Plenty of room for Head to cut fiercely and easily beat deep cover point to his right
swatted, just clears short fine leg! Spliced on the pull but it brings him four more. Starc, one of the taller men on the field, threw up a hand but couldn't get there
full, slanting away from off stump, and Rohit dives right at cover to stgop this well-hit drive from Head
back of a length in the channel, skips up and beats the outside edge
slower bouncer angling across Head's body, beats the attempted pull

slower ball, comes out all wrong towards the off-side tramlines. SKY leaves it be short and flipped! An easy swing of the arms, not the cleanest hit but it sails away towards fine leg, bouncing just in front of the rope

and there's Head's fifty. Tormenting his favourite opposition again. Full, on off stump, clears his front leg and whips it with power towards Axar at long-on, and he fails to make a routine stop and lets the ball run away to the boundary
127kph, full, straight and squired off the pads to deep midwicket

four more. Slower length ball finishing around off stump, and he stays leg-side of the ball and opens his bat face to manufacture a slice between short third and backward point. He didn't just steer this, it was a slice with a full bat-swing to manufacture power against the slower ball
shortish into the hip, tucked square
short of a length, angling away from off stump, goes hard at a cut and misses
fullish in the corridor outside off, chopped down into the point region for one more
punched into the off side and they get two thanks to a fumble from Warner
and MAxwell begins with a super shot. Quick length ball angling into off stump, and he stays leg-side of the ball and opens his bat face to slice it away between backward point and short third
back of a length outside off, 139kph. Rohit dabs down to deep third
over the same region this time, but this time with the falling reverse-sweep. Similar line and length, just outside off, and he swats it away over the gap between backward point and short third
in the channel, kicking up past the edge as SKY throws the bat, bottom hand coming off
length ball angling into the stumps, clipped into the midwicket region
length again, 143kph outside off. Suryakumar tries to walk into a drive, plinks it to mid-off on the bounce
shortish outside off, cut through backward point
short ball, filleted through backward square leg! SKY reaching the parts others can't. All the way across his stumps and fetched leg side

and Maxwell continues to toy with Jadeja. Quick, on the fuller side of a length  on off stump, and again he manufactures that falling reverse-sweep, in the air over the two fielders behind square on the off side
more pongo, creamed over cover! Full outside off and SKY just dismisses it from his presence, a princely lofted drive that plops gracefully over the rope for six more. Good grief, this is carnage
short, angling down leg, misses the pull and picks up a leg bye off the thigh pad. May have been an inside edge, because there's no leg-bye signal
tossed up on middle and leg, swept down to deep backward square leg
tries to make room but Kuldeep squeezes him with a quick, flat, hard-length ball at his thigh pad. Punched down to long-on

bowled 'im, the yorker from round the wicket does it! Right up in the blockhole and rattles the timbers. Rohit is proven mortal after a godly innings - though he's in such good nick that he manages to get some bat on it, just not enough to stop it trickling back into the stumps via his pads. Sensational knock from Rohit. But a small measure of revenge for Starc
quickish, back of a length, turning down leg. Not short enough to pull and he's smacked on the pad
short and steered down to deep third! Sits back and uses the pace, David can't get around
floated across outside off, slower this time. Reaches out to reverse-sweep to deep backward point. Interesting that he had that fielder back
goes for the yorker again, 136kph from over the wicket, scuds into the pads
wrong'un, loopy and dipping to turn in from off stump. Was looking to make room to play through the off side, only manages to defend into the covers
fired in with the arm and nudged leg side

bang. Such a good over, but he ends it with a hittable ball. Looped up outside off, but not wide enough to be away from Head's hitting arc. Drops down on his back knee and launches it cleanly over Hardik at long-off
pitched up and driven, can't beat the off side ring
looped up and driven down to long-off
back of a length outside off, cut to short third, who's stationed quite wide
full and dipping outside off, 87kph. Dube digs out a drive through extra cover
flat length ball angling in towards off stump, swept along the ground to deep backward square leg
googly, I think, 95kph and cramping SKY for room. Shovelled away to deep square leg
back of a length, slanting away from off stump, chopped to backward point
into the pitch, Dube tucks it off his pads
similar ball, back of a length and keeps going with the angle across. Cut away to deep point

give it some more air... and gets put on to the grass banks! Don't know if he picked the googly but it doesn't matter when you connect with a slog-sweep as cleanly as that. Taken by someone in the crowd, to general delight (expect, perhaps, among Australia fans)
too full to get elevation on the slog-sweep. Meets it outside off and drags it to deep midwicket
pushed through and whipped leg side, they'll get back for two here
uses the angle across Head really well again. Back of a length, angling away wide of off, and it kind of stops on him too. Flat-batted to extra-cover

and it's dropped even further now, as Kuldeep opens his final over with a massive wicket. Wrong'un pitching outside leg stump, and Maxwell steps out and doesn't quite pick it. Looks to clear his front leg and whip it into the leg side, and it dips and turns past him to leave his stumps in a mess
length ball angling in, driven through midwicket
length ball turning in from outside off, defended back to the bowler
pitched up and lashed through long-off! Misses the wide yorker and Dube's reach means he can swipe it back down the ground
short, slow, slanting away into that wide line. Flat-batted to long-on
tucked off the pads
terrific. What a hit. Just a touch short of a good length, turning away from off stump, and he opens up at the hip and whacks this away with a horizontal bat, between long-on and deep midwicket
blootered over the ropes! Pace off but Suryakumar adds it back on with interest, stepping out and swinging Stoinis over long-on
back of a length, straightening towards middle stump, makes room and slaps to deep point
full, 130kph on the stumps, thick-edged down to fine leg
wrong'un turning from outside leg, goes back and works it to deep midwicket
nails his yorker this time, dug out back to the bowler

reverse-swept, straight into the lap of Hardik at backward point! Flat length ball, speared in, angling into the stumps, and Stoinis ends up hitting an in-betweenish shot - neither kept down nor hit with proper elevation, and maybe because he's working against Axar's angle he doesn't quite get the power he needs. Straight to Hardik at waist height, and he catches it on the rebound after fumbling the chance first up
slashed between short third and backward point! Round the wicket on a length from Starc and Suryakumar cracks a back cut past the ring
length ball, using that angle into off stump to deny David room. Gets forward and drives to extra-cover
goes for the wide yorker, skidding through under the toe of the bat
not short enough to cut, and the ball doesn't turn enough against the angle to give him room. Past the edge of his diagonal bat

wide line, pace off, nicked to the keeper! SKY was struggling to reach it and ends up looping a fat top edge through to Wade. He walks off visibly frustrated with himself, given it probably would have been a wide if he'd left it along. Starc gets another, India's momentum checked again
fuller now, angling into the stumps, driven quietly to long-off
goes full at the stumps, jammed down for one
flat, angling away from off stump, and that isn't short but for Head it's short enough. Gets his front leg well out of the way and flat-bats to the right of the diving extra-cover fielder
over the wicket, another decent yorker on middle and leg, 141kph. Dube shovels leg side for one
slows it down, floats it across and wide of off stump. Stretches out for a flat-bat drive to long-off
full outside off from round the wicket, punched to deep backward point
full outside off, makes a bit of room and drives hard but straight to cover
shortish, 133kph, over the top of off. Pandya chops a cut to backward point

full-toss, put away, but not in the intended direction. A bit of reverse on this, swinging into the left-hander, and Head inside-edges the attempted leg-side hoick past his leg stump, and it's out of reach of Pant diving to his right
length ball, maybe pace off, brings a swing and a miss. No, pace on, just hits the seam and keeps coming in
low full-toss veering in towards the base of middle and leg. Clears his front leg and whips it to long-on
wide yorker, Pandya jams it towards short third and takes one
there's that reverse. Yorker, going from leg to middle before it lands, defended into the covers
back of a length, holds in the surface a touch and hits the splice. Dube gets one into the covers
back of a length, stump-to-stump, pulled along the ground towards deep midwicket
full, straight and clipped to deep midwicket
in the blockhole, angling into the stumps, clipped down to long-on

back of a length outside off, Dube stabs it towards backward point and they race through. Hazlewood finishes with pristine figures of 1 for 14 in what has been an otherwise messy canvas for Australia's attack
goes full and flat at the pads, swatted through midwicket
length ball, angling into the stumps. Makes a lot of room and flat-bats to deep midwicket

looped up, top-edged... and Marsh drops a goober at backward point! Australia's catching issues catching up with them again. Went reverse-cup but it hit the hands and bobbled free. Had another go on the way down but still couldn't hold on
full, angling into off stump, gets forward to clip to long-on
another shout of "catch!" as Dube slices a slog across the line. This one doesn't carry to point

and the slower ball does him in! Makes a lot of room again, and Bumrah sends in a dipping slower offcutter on leg stump. Looks to manufacture a leg-side whip while off balance, and all he manages is to skew the ball high over the off side for Rohit to settle under at cover
tossed up straight and swept for one
fullish outside off, gets forward and steers to the right of point
fired in flat at 101kph, Pandya heaves one more out to deep midwicket
hard length in the corridor, and extra bounce beats the bat as David makes room, shuffles out, and aims to slap through the covers
full on the pads again and hoicked away leg side, lands short of deep backward square. Solid from Zampa, just five singles - and he should have had a wicket
full, angling into off stump, clipped to the right of long-on

gone, that's a super catch from Kuldeep at short third. Back of a length outside off, and Wade goes hard at the cut. Slices it much finer than intended, but it's dying as it reaches Kuldeep, who has to dive forward and to his right. Does so, and seems to get his hands under the ball, but the umpires are having a look. Yup, his hands seem to be underneath the ball, though the slomo replays are a touch blurry and indistinct
round the wicket, full and wide, 139kph. Dube thrashes along the carpet wide of long-off for a couple
length ball, middle-stumpish. Looks to make room and hit straight, but doesn't quite middle it. Chipped in the air, bouncing to the right of Kohli racing in from long-off
full toss, flubbed down the ground. He'll get one as long-on charges in

bouncer, just down the leg sie, beats David's attempted hook much-mneeded boundary, but Australia need a lot more of this. Length ball slanting across, finishing just outside off. Makes a bit of room and flat-bats it powerfully over the ducking umpiore. Kohli's despairing dive at long-off isn't enough to stop it
full, 139kph, misses the blockhole, but Pandya can only force a drive to long-on

looks for the yorker, misses his line, ends up as a wide down the leg side after beating David's flick full-toss slanting away from off stump, and David clears the straight boundary despite seeming to mishit it. Kohli was keeping his eyes on the ball on the long-off boundary, and seemed to think he was about to get under the ball, but ended up stepping over the rope and watching the ball clear him comfortably
short ball, pace off, Dube slugs a pull through midwicket
gone, the full-toss sends David back. On the stumps, about knee-high, a bit of reverse away. Looks to whip it away over the leg side and ends up edging it straight to short third
dug in and swatted away through the covers! Seemed to come off the toe of the bat but he finds the gap
another full-toss, quite high but not above waist height, angling into the stumps. Whipped away to the left of deep midwicket
full and slapped down the ground

length ball angling into the stumps, straightens a touch and bounces over off stump after Starc clears his front leg and misses the hoick. They look to steap a bye, and Pant concedes an overthrow with a shy to the bowler's end
Pandya plays a pirouetting smash over cover! Length outside off, and he uses his whole body to manufacture the power required!
slower ball into the pitch, outside off, misses the pull
slot ball, hammered over long-off! Stoinis is trying to prevent him from hitting with the breeze leg side, but Pandya just sets himself and belts a 79m six down the ground

length ball outside off, and that carried way further than it seemed it would when Cummins hit it. Just a flick with no follow-through, and it sails over the straight midwicket boundary, impelled by the wind no doubt
fired in full, yorker on the stumps, dug out for one
in the blockhole outside off, angling in. Looks to open his bat face and squeeze it away but can't make contact

flipped off the pads, straight to the sweeper! Full, straight with a wobbly seam and although Dube gets a clean connection, it holds up nicely for Warner to take charging in off the rope. Didn't quite fire today but still had more impact the Dion Dublin's Dube (IYKYK)
yorker, angling into the base of off and middle. Makes room and jabs it away to the right of backward point, meeting the ball on the full
goes full and wide, sneaks it under the bat
low full-toss angling into the stumps, makes room and clips it down to the right of long-on
pitched up and lashed through the covers
slower ball, back of a length, close to off stump. Flat-batted down towards long-on
round the wicket, dug in short. Jaddu short-arms a pull around the corner

dropped, and by Jadeja of all people. Slower short ball outside off, and Cummins clears his front leg and hits with the turn of the offcutter. Jadeja dives forward at deep midwicket, but this is very much catchable for him. Doesn't get his hands around the ball
goes full and wide, Pandya wings up for the big hit... misses
slower ball, back of a length, angling across the stumps. Pulls and misses
well-directed yorker, 139kph on the stumps. Bunted down to long-on
slower short ball finishes in the corridor, and Starc half-pulls and misses again
pitched up and honked off the pads! Hitting with the wind over deep midwicket. Jadeja joins in with the fun and raises India's 200
another slower short ball, angling across Starc to finish outside off. Again he's flummoxed by the lack of pace, goes for the pull and misses
short ball, swung away leg side for a single
slower offcutter again, dug in short and wider outside off this time. Flat-bats it, and the ball comes to a rest a short distance away in front of cover
short, pace off, Pandya swipes a top-edged pull wide of short fine leg. India finish on 205 for 5, leaving Australia's T20WC in the balance at halfway
full and wide, shaping in. Scuffed drive to mid-off for one
Action from the get go! Gurbaz skips down the track and looks to drop and run, but the through from square leg is a good one. A desperate dive sees Gurbaz just about make his ground.
good length on the stumps, defended watchfully
back of a length outside off. Play and a miss, as this shapes away with some extra bounce
good length but angled in on the pads, deflected towards short fine for one
back of a length, closer to off. Punched off the back foot to the man at point, who can't field this cleanly
Thick edge for four! This is full and wide, and Litton is reaching for this as he looks to loft this over the offside, but it's sails fine to the deep third boundary
good length outside off, left alone
Much more convincing this one! Length ball in the slot, and it's picked up gloriously with the breeze! 91 metres over deep midwicket!
Big swing and a miss! Gurbaz is all intent here as he charges down the track. Looks to go over extra cover but this nips back and is a hair over off stump
good length and wide of off, Litton misses the drive but it bounces in front of Gurbaz who can't gather cleanly. They run the bye
once more shuffles down the wicket, eases this back straight for a single
Starts off poorly. Length down leg, deflects fine off the pads and past the diving short fine for a couple. That might have runaway earlier in the night, but it really slowed down near the ropes
Corker to start! Back of a length just outside off, rears up and goes past Gurbaz's defence as he just about brings his bat in
back of a length, shaping in on off. Chopped to point for one
back of a length on off, defended towards cover

Sharp inswinger convinces the umpire! This was a good length and it tailed in late towards the left-hander, who looked to swing this away over mid-on. He's struck on the back thigh guard in front of off. Only question is height here, I think. But it's a great decision, crashing into the top of middle.
Oof! This one carries through nicely off a good length. Squares Gurbaz right up, pitching just outside off and seaming away. Lovely stuff
good length on off, catches the drive on the inside half of the bat towards midwicket
back of a length and seaming in this time. Gurbaz walks across the stumps and tucks this behind square on the onside for a quick single
good length on the stumps, pitching outside leg. Litton goes early and looks to paddle this, but ends up getting struck on the front thigh
Play and a miss! Probing line and length outside off, seaming away a touch. Ibrahim wafts at this away from his body and is beaten
full outside off, shaping in. Big swing and a miss.

Pace-off cutter. This was a good length outside off and Ibrahim looks to take on the drive on the up, but is beaten by some sharp movement inwards. Misses off stump and bounces in front of the keeper, who can't gather this cleanly

Another appeal for leg before, but not given this time. Afghanistan review This was slightly back of length, and nipping in. Struck high on the front knee roll, might have been sliding down leg. And indeed it's missing the wickets
back of a length outside off, opens the face and runs this down behind point. Third man tumbles to collect and they scamper back for the second
Swung in front of square leg! This was fuller and skid on. Shanto swings and turns his wrists to get this in the gap
Beats everyone! This was a bouncer, but it sails over the batter and the leaping Litton behind the stumps
good length slower one outside off, Shanto through the shot way too early as he misses this
Stonking drive! This was a good length on off, but Ibrahim takes this on the up and in the air, through the covers

This time finds the man in the deep! Nabi had just been stationed at deep midwicket after that earlier boundary, but Shanto decides to take him on aerially with a similar leg side swing. He can't find the connection though and it's a simple catch
Looks to go again, but this time there's some sharp movement away. Plays and misses

Two in two and Shakib is out for a golden duck! This was quick on middle and leg, but it straightened just enough to induce the leading edge as Shakib looks to work this onside. It pops straight back to Naveen who bobbles the chance but holds on in the end
back of a length on off, defended towards extra cover
full on off, shaping away. Soumya plays this with soft hands and runs it down to third man
good length on the stumps, pushed back straight past the bowler for one
full and down leg Picked up over midwicket! This was a good length but a little too straight. Soumya goes for it and finds the space in front of square. Couple bounces over the ropes
back of a length, seaming in towards off. Looks to punch this off the back foot, ends up getting a thick edge down to third man
good length on off, guided towards point for a quick single
Wild swing and a miss! Gurbaz comes down the track for the umpteenth time and looks to spank the leather off this. Misses and this goes over the stumps
slower ball down leg good length slower one angled in, pushed towards cover point for one
Great running. Just nurdles this towards square leg and these two are rapid in between the wickets
back of a length on off, punched to backward point for one
This one rises sharply from a back of a length, has Gurbaz weaving out of the way as this zooms past his chest
fuller outside off, carved into the covers
Once more they run hard. Walks across to the offside and tucks this in front of square leg for two more
full and straight, chipped towards deep square leg for a couple more
back of a length outside off, Gurbaz goes back and across and looks to drop and run, but point is quickly on it to save the single
back of a length slower one just outside off, punched to cover
slides on to the pads with the arm
another slower one, swing and a miss outside off
another arm ball, defended on the front foot
Lifted over backward point! This was short and very wide, as Litton comes down the track and slaps this up and over the infield
Dropped! Ibrahim backs away and slaps this straight at Hridoy at short cover. It's at him in a flash overhead, and he just can't hold on. How big will that miss prove?
good length outside off, looks for the drive and misses
good length on off, driven down the ground for one
another slower one, full outside off. Lofted over mid-off, but this holds up in the soggy outfield
good length on the stumps, goes back and chips this towards mid-on. This one stuck in the surface
full and angled in on off, hacked away towards deep midwicket
good length on off, gets well forward and pushes it down to long-off for one
good length on off, defended on the front foot
On the money! Angled across the right hander, back of a length and seams away a touch. Squares up Gurbaz as this beats the edge
good length off break, dabbed to short third off the back foot for a quick single
Another swing, another miss. Gurbaz walks right across the stumps, and looks to whack this over midwicket. Gurbaz cops a blow on his right shoulder for his efforts
Just short of short third! Soumya chips up the reverse sweep, but it just doesn't reach the fielder
Off line and put away! This was short but a touch too straight. Gurbaz steps inside the line and gets this pull away nice and fine
good length outside off. Defends on the onside as Ishaq picks up and breaks the stumps, they run the deflection. Good urgency
good length, angling and seaming away. Left alone
big slog sweep, but there's a boundary ride at deep midwicket. Litton slips at the non-striker's end so they only get one
length on off, looks to push and run but short cover is on it in a flash
Swing and a miss! Looks to take this from just outside off and clear midwicket, but Nabi fires this in. Just misses off stump
Another one that squares him up. Pitches on off, back of a length, and seams away past the back foot defence
short to start, clubbed down to long-on
tossed up on the stumps, knocked back to Shakib
good length, quicker on leg stump. Looks for the sweep as this glances the pad through to the keeper
good length outside off, goes back and slaps this to deep cover point

no pad this time as it slips down leg Rashid with a lovely skidder! This one is quick and flat and just picks up steam after it pitches. Soumya goes back but is slow on the stroke, as this crashes into middle stump
floated up, bit of a grip and turn. Push and run towards point and they run quickly. Nearly a second after Bangladesh fluffed the backing up, but Gurbaz is wisely sent back
back of a length outside, cut to deep backward point
full on off, driven down to long-off for one
good length googly on the stumps, worked through midwicket. 50 up for Bangladesh
slides on with arm off a good length into the pads. Stifled appeal, but this was clearly sliding down leg
fuller on off, steps across and works it behind square
Gurbaz finally gets a hold of one! Skips down the track, to the pitch, and absolutely smashes this down the ground
good length on off, defended towards midwicket
good length on off, drive and timed on the up in front of cover point for a couple
back of a length on off, defended to short cover
back of a length on off, stands tall and guides this down to deep third
Top edge and grassed! Towhid top edges this pull straight up over the keeper. Farooqi runs back from short fine but the wind makes it so, so tough
fuller on off, pace off. Steps across and nudges this square on the leg side, another excellently run two
Goes for another across the line swipe and it's another top edge, this time it skips away for four fine

Oh dear, oh dear. This one was way too short as it sails over both Gurbaz and the keeper Skips down and scuffs it back towards Tanzim, who picks it up and throws it back at the striker's stumps. He misses, but Gurbaz was in in any case
Slog sweep for four more! Off the bottom of the bat, but it beats the boundary rider at deep square leg
Hops on his toes and dabs this down to third man
fuller on off, worked towards wide long-on for a couple more
back of a length, rears up sharply as Ibrahim misses his attempt to punch this behind square on the offside
loops away off the front pad as Litton misses the sweep to one tossed up on leg
some slow turn on the leg break outside off, goes back and works this through midwicket for a couple
Rashid has another! The dangerous Towhid is gone, as he finds the man at deep midwicket with this slog sweep. He's gone with the wind, but the connection just isn't good enough
Calls for two again, but this time the man at deep midwicket is more alert. 50 stand is up! Fourth of the tournament for this pair.
length on off, chops it behind point for one
good length leg break, sharp turn and bounce away. Play and a miss
shorter outside off, backs away and misses the cut
good length leg break, pitches on leg and straightens. Defended
Clobbered down the ground! Skips down the track and thwacks this hard flat past Rashid
slips this down leg, misses the paddle sweep but Litton also fails to collect. They run a couple of wides good length outside off, slapped down towards deep cover
Deftly done! This is pushed through flat on off, but Litton is equal to it, running it down nice and fine to the third man boundary
good length outside off, top spinner. Gets well forward to defend
good length outside off, slashes this hard on the up. But really well fielded at backward point, who gets a solid hand on it
good length outside off, past the outside edge as Mahmudullah pushes at this
short and pulled away, but there's a man covering at deep backward square
opens the face and runs it down but only to backward point
back of a length, follows Ibrahim who looks to make room. Ends up running this down to third man
fuller on the stumps, nudged to the right of Noor who scrambles to save
short and looks to pull, but this rises sharply and angles away outside off. Plays and misses
Lovely cover drive! Tossed up outside off, and it's crunched through the covers. Pristine timing
good length slower one on off, forces Gurbaz to check his drive. Briefly in the air as it goes to short cover
good length on off, chopped to backward point
another slower one, push and run to mid-off for one
full on off, leading edge to short cover
Length ball outside off, pulled along the ground to long-on
Length ball following Gurbaz down leg. The batter backs away and pulls to deep midwicket
Full length on off, Mahmudullah eases it behind point for a single
Length ball on middle and off, parried back to the bowler
Dropped short-ish outside off, Litton can only punch it to backward point
