Beautiful legbreak, full around off. Ibrahim had backed away and looked to go big inside out, but the ball spins away sharply and beats the bat
Wrong'un on a length outside off, whipped wide of long-on
The pressure tells! Tossed up full around off and Ibrahim looks to go down the ground. He ends up slicing it wide of long-off and Tanzim does well to get under it moving to his left.

Flights a full delivery that spins in sharply and stays under the bat as Mahmudullah swings. Rashid thinks there was an inside edge. Afghanistan review. And there's a small spike as the ball goes past bat! Rashid has a third! How big a moment has this been? Also, how big a performance is this from Rashid Khan today, playing probably the most important match of his career!
Low full toss around off, Omarzai drills it hard and along the ground to the cover fielder

TIMBERRRRR! Rashid Khan knocks Rishad over with a wrong'un! Leggie gets leggie. Rishad went for a big swing and finds air and Rashid is on target. What a massive spell this is from Rashid Khan! Afghanistan are three away!

Beautiful delivery! Flights it full around off, drawing Omarzai forward. The ball dips and then spins away past the outside edge. Omarzai is at full stretch in his stride forward, but manages to keep his back foot behind the crease, and grounded. He survives the stumping chance
Wrong'un n leg, Litton prods forward and gets a leading edge through point
Length ball around off, Gurbaz taps it to backward point
Floats a length ball across him. It was the wrong'un
Back of length delivery outside off, Gurbaz cuts to backward point
Goes past his defence as Tanzim tries to push at this full ball tossed up outside off
Gurbaz misses out! It's overpitched outside off and Gurbaz's eyes light up. He thrashes a grounded drive, but it's gone straight to Shakib at cover, who doesn't let it pass through him
On a length outside off, it spins away as Tanzim presses forward. Mild shouts for caught behind
Digs it in short outside off, Gurbaz wants to ramp but doesn't connect. Four dot balls, top over from Taskin so far
Length ball on off, Tanzim clubs it past cover to wide long-off and gets off the mark
Ten dots on the trot! Back of length and wide of off. Gurbaz skips down the track but pulls out of the shot
Tossed full on off, Litton can only block in front

Maiden over! Just one run and one wicket in the last two overs. Taskin builds brilliantly on the pressure created by Rishad's wicket. This one is a length ball around off that Gurbaz can only block back towards the bowler
Googly, on a length outside off and Tanzim manages to punch it down the ground to long-on as it spins in sharply
Quick and on a length around off, angling into Omarzai, who bunts it out towards point
Short-ish on off, Litton rocks back and pulls it straight of deep midwicket and picks up two
First run in 13 deliveries! This is floated full on off, Omarzai eases it along the ground to long-off
Back of length again and Litton is cramped for room. Manages to punch it down to long-on
Flighted delivery on off, Gurbaz plays it back to the bowler
On a length outside off, Tanzim is able to steer it through point for a single
On a length on middle, Gurbaz backs away and whips it out to deep midwicket
Length ball punched square on the off side
Full around off, clipped down the ground to long-on
On a length around off, Tanzim manages to parry it down
On a length on off, punched back to Shakib's left

Full around off, Litton tucks it through to deep midwicket. Tanzim loses his bat running back for the second. He still puts in a dive and gets in. Direct hit at the non-striker's end would have seen him in trouble
Just safe! Flighted full outside off, Omarzai reaches out as he looks to hammer it inside out and ends up slicing it. The deep cover fielder runs in a long way and puts in a dive, but can't get there
Floated full outside off, Litton presses towards it, but leaves it go as it spins away
Full outside off, driven out to the off side sweeper
Wrong'un again on a length outside off, Litton helps it on to short third
Finally, a boundary! This is tossed up full and very wide, but Gurbaz moves across his stumps and reaches out to slap it over point. Shanto at backward point gives chase but the ball races away
On a length outside off, punched down towards long-on
Tossed full outside off, driven to cover
Full outside off, spins away to beat the outside edge as Tanzim presses forward in defence
Flighted full outside off, Gurbaz sweeps through square leg and they race for two
Googly on a length on off, Tanzim goes back and defends
Full outside off again and this time Gurbaz sweeps it behind square leg for a second boundary from the over. This one was placed in the gap
Leg cutter pushed down to long-on
Just over Shakib! Length ball around off, Omarzai closes his bat face early as he tries to work it down the ground and gets a leading edge. Shakib throws his arm up but it just goes past him
Naib takes Afghanistan closer! Banged in short, Tanzim goes for the pull but gets a thick top edge. Mohammad Nabi takes it easily at cover and Afghanistan inch towards that semi-final spot
Tucked to deep midwicket
On a length around off, pace off, Taskin meets it with the full face of the bat and it goes off the outside half towards point
Slightly short and Omarzai slaps it through point as Afghanistan collect a brace
Banged in short outside off, Taskin ducks under it
Whips a full delivery through midwicket
Length ball angles into Taskin and goes off his thigh pads towards short fine
Full around off, he gets forward and defends
Back of length delivery, Litton pulls it along the ground to deep midwicket
Full on leg, blocked back to the bowler
Goes for the wide yorker, Omarzai squeezes it out on the off side for a single
Comes from around the wicket and tosses up a wrong'un on middle and off. Litton just manages to get his bat down on time!
A swing and a miss! Mustafizur angles a length ball across him. Gurbaz looks to access the leg side with a big swish of the bat, but he misses completely
Swept away for four! Tossed up full outside off, he hammers it over square leg and it goes for a one-bounce four. Brings up a half-century for him as well amid a torrid run of form
Back of length delivery angled across Gurbaz, who dabs it straight of deep third
Back of length googly outside off, spins away out of Litton's arc

Gurbaz cuts to backward point and takes off before turning back when he realises there was no run there. Omarzai was more than halfway down the track and continues running. Rishad picks it up and throws at the striker's end, where both batters ended up but misses the stumps. Both batters now take off for the non-striker's end, but eventually Gurbaz is the one running over to at least get one run out of the debacle
On a length around off, Litton blocks

Toe-ended to the keeper! Mustafizur goes short and across Omarzai who looks to cut. The keeper and bowler go up in appeal but the umpire is unmoved. They review immediately and there's a spike as the ball passes the bat. The Fizz strikes!
On a length outside off, fended to the off side
And he gets off the mark with a boundary! This is full outside off and he smacks it straight down the ground

Traps him on the pad and Noor thinks he has his man. Afghanistan review. This is tossed up full outside off, spinning in to hit him on the front pad as he presses forward. There's no inside edge. Oh, and it's umpire's call on impact so Litton will survive! Noor looks distraught.
Full on leg and angling down, goes off Taskin's pad behind square leg. They get the run

Straight to deep cover! Tossed up full and wide, Gurbaz went inside out. He gets the height, but not the distance. Gurbaz looks frustrated. That is an odd innings, the value of which may only be truly apparent once both teams have batted!
Dug in short outside off, Litton pulls it down to long-on. That's 100 up for Bangladesh
Legbreak tossed full outside off, Nabi lofts it down the ground and it goes on the bounce to long-off
Full on the pads, Taskin flicks it away to deep midwicket
Swing and a miss! Another full, wide legbreak that spins away as Naib looks to fetch it with a sweep
Back of length again, Litton pulls it to deep midwicket for another easy single

That's a brilliant catch running in from deep cover! Full outside off, it's another leg break. Naib was looking to go big over the leg side but gets a thick leading edge. The ball balloons up square on the off side. It looked like it would land sadly, but Soumya is having none of it. He sprints in from the boundary rope and snatches it just when it looked like a chance would go begging
On a length around off, Taskin taps it towards cover. They decide against a risky single
Full around middle and off, Janat looks to work it leg side but gets a thin edge that just drops short of slip!
Big shout for caught behind as Taskin pokes at a back of length delivery from outside off. But probably more in hope than anything else. No review taken
Full and wide and Janat hammers this through covers for a much needed boundary for Afghanistan!
Slower length ball around off, cut away behind point
Bouncer outside off, Nabi has a swipe at it but can't get bat on ball
Back of length delivery, punched with an open face to deep third's left
Short outside off, and goes over the bat as Nabi looks to cut
Naveen puts him down! Full around off, punched back to the bowler, and it bursts through! Oh my!
Another swing and a miss! Taskin sticks to bowiling it back of length outside off and Nabi just can't connect. This time he looks to pull but in vain
Naveen gets him! Taskin chops on! Prods at a full slower ball outside off and gets an inside edge! And that takes the DLS par score to 108! And the rain is coming down again!

And Taskin reaps the rewards! Another short ball outside off, Nabi again looks to cut but loses shape and gets a top edge. The ball goes high in the air and mid-off runs in, settles under it and makes no mistake. The experienced Nabi is gone

He traps him and UP GOES THE FINGER! Afghanistan players race off in celebration, but Bangladesh have reviewed. It looked plumb. Was there an inside edge though? Nope, and that's red on all three! Length ball angles in from outside off and raps him right in front of middle. Afghanistan are through to the semis!
Back of length delivery outside off, stays slightly low maybe, Rashid has a swing across the line but is beaten. That's the 60th dot ball of the innings!
Rashid says that's enough, time for business! This is not as short, and the length ball sits up nicely. Rashid stands tall and powers this over deep midwicket
Length ball around  leg goes through the batter as he looks to fend! This was a cutter and it goes between bat and pad
Length ball around leg, goes off his hips to fine leg
Rashid skips down the track as Mustafizur bowls an offcutter around leg. Looks to swipe across the line but can't connect

Mustafizur sees Rashid go across the stumps and throws it full and wide. Rashid, who was shaping to scoop, adjusts and looks to work it to the off side but can't connect. Not called wide since Rashid had moved across to the off side
Full and wide and past Rashid's bat as he looks to hammer it on the off side!

Slower ball, back of length, and Rashid wants to cut but can't touch it. Excellent over from Mustafizur, showing once again why he is considered a gun death bowler. Excellent spell, in fact, giving away just 17 runs in his four overs
Mid-off can only get fingertips on it! Length delivery outside off and Janat slaps it down the ground. The fielder just touches it and they get just one as Rashid turns down the second
Short, wide and slapped over point for six! Rashid is turning it on in a late assault here

Yorker around leg, Rashid goes for his snake shot, but gets a leading edge to the off side. They run one and Rashid is sprinting back for a second but he is sent back. A furious Rashid loses his bat as he runs back. He lets his partner know of his displeasure. he really wanted that run!
Dug out to the leg side for a single
Full outside off, he goes across and looks to sweep but misses
Smokes the last ball for a six! This is in the slot and Rashid just short-arm jabs it over cow corner. 98 metres that flew! And Afghanistan finish on 115 as the covers come on!
uses his feet straightaway, deflects off the thigh pad down to long leg
pretty full and outside off, keeps low, left alone. Smart little take from Gurbaz behind the stumps
moves outside leg stump, it's back of a length and played up to mid-off. Not there to drive
more signs of variable bounce! On a length and ducks back in with extra bounce, catches de Kock in a tangle and pings him on the midriff
fuller outside off, drives without at footwork, reaching for it and gets a thickish inside edge
pitched further up and outside off, slanting in to the left-hander, who squirts a single to mid-on
edged, short of slip! Length ball around middle, Zadran staying leg side of it, drives and gets a thick edge to the right of slip
excessive bounce for Naveen! He puts it on a length once again, but it bursts off the deck, veers in, and almost kisses the outside edge near the shoulder of the bat
good length at middle, 138kph, defended up the pitch
off-stump yorker, swings in sharply, dug out by Hendricks

comes down the pitch, it's short from Jansen and down the leg side down the leg side again, Gurbaz pulls and doesn't connect, slips past the thigh pad. Trying not to give him any room edged, taken at slip! Huge moment. Adjusts the line, outside off, and much fuller. Brings the drive and it's an edge that travels comfortably to slip around knee height
Naveen goes wide of the crease and swings a full ball back into Hendricks who jams an inside edge onto the pad
pretty full and swinging into middle and leg, de Kock picks it up and whips it away through the vacant spaces at midwicket, to the left of mid-on
driven along the ground to long-off
nice and full outside off, Farooqi takes it away from de Kock, left alone
round the wicket, tossed up at the stumps, lofted strongly straight down the ground. Excellent stroke
good length and largely holds its line outside off, ignored
drags the length back a touch, on off stump, pushed into the covers
full outswinger from Farooqi, he has de Kock reaching out for the ball and missing. Beaten on the outside edge
full at middle, defended to cover

Death. Taxes. Farooqi striking in the powerplay. The off stump has been knocked out. After taking one away from de Kock and beating the outside edge, Farooqi swings this back into de Kock and bursts through his defences
a beauty! Full at off stump, spins sharply past the edge as he comes forward
Farooqi shortens his length, Markram defends it back to the bowler on the back foot
worked off the pads backward of square
short of a length and down the leg side...another wide shorter on off stump, pulled through straight mid-on, strong shot from Naib
short, wide, carved in the air but falls just short of deep third. Travels flat and quick to Omarzai. Rashid isn't pleased with the effort of his outfielder
huge swing and a miss! Fuller, angled across outside off, Naib aiming a big drive down the ground
wide on the crease, back of a length and holds its line outside off, punched on the up to short cover

another one pushed down the leg side, been a mixed bag so far through him! Two for Jansen. Back of a length at middle off, Naib playing from the crease, nips back a touch, scoots past the inside edge and takes off stump. That's a super delivery, in fact
wide on the crease, Naveen creates a sharp angle once again and brings it back into Markram. Blocked on off stump
beaten! Pushing away from his body without any footwork to one angled across him

on a length, angling in from wide on the crease and straightening away off the seam past the outside edge. Did he nick it? Gurbaz gestures he didn't hear anything. UltraEdge detects a spike. Afghanistan miss a trick. Rashid sees the spike on the big screen and isn't pleased one bit
shorter, around leg stump, climbs into the thigh pad
steep bounce for Naveen as he gets it to straighten away off the seam once again

just past leg slip! Almost a blinder from Klassen. Short, into the ribs, fended down the leg side and that was nearly a plan coming off perfectly. Steepling bounce. Given runs, but not sure that was bat or glove
stabbed to mid-off off the inside half
squirted to point
and strikes first ball! Short of a length, nips back past the bat and into the top of leg stump. No real footwork
very full and pushed across off, Hendricks reaches out for a drive and squeezes an inside edge to short fine leg
very full outside off, square drives and well fielded by Miller at point
off-side wide from Farooqi pitched-up delivery outside off, Hendricks drives off the front foot to mid-off
length ball outside off, defended to cover
full and angling into the stumps from round the wicket, push-driven straight past Farooqi
and another! This is carnage. Brilliant bowling from Rabada. Good length, nips sharply off the seam, through the gap between bat and pad. That is a pearler.
slowie from Farooqi, plunges on the batter, who dabs this full-toss to short cover
over the wicket to the left hander, full at the stumps, driven to mid-off
another slowie from Farooqi, but he overpitches this and offers too much width to Hendricks who latches onto it and laces it away between point and cover
this one flies! Short and straight, Kharote looks to upper cut and is beaten by pace and bounce over the top edge
this one leaps! Short of a length, flies around the corner off some glove, I think. This is very tough
wide on the crease, short and angling into the top of the stumps, blocked on the back foot
fuller outside off, square drives without any footwork and is beaten
on a length and outside off, comes slow off the pitch, variable bounce for Naveen once again, spliced to mid-off
angled in at the stumps, 140kph, defended
excessive bounce for Naveen once again. Rears up from a back of a length and ducks in from outside off. Markram squirts an inside edge past leg stump
backs away outside leg, aims a square drive to a back-of-a-length delivery, goes over the flashing blade
back of a length and wide of off, this one comes onto the bat and Markram crunnnnnnnches it away to the left of cover-point
fuller and angled into the pads, neatly worked through square leg
bumper outside off, too high, wide called this pops up over cover-point. Back of a length and outside off, stops on the batter and rears up at the batter once again
short, down the leg side, and it's gloved it! Oh boy. Not a great delivery, was well away from the body, he went after it and got a tickle on the glove
wide on the crease, on a length and on middle and leg, knocked wide of midwicket for an urgent single
full at off stump, he's certainly not in line with that, defends to the bowler
slider on middle and leg, whisked down to long-on. Markram collects a brace
there's a counterpunch! Drives on the up, over the off side, and nearly carries for six
whipped down to long-on once again, this time for just a single
moves well outside off and fends at this, nearly a nick and nearly takes off stump
tossed up on off, draws an inside edge that rolls away behind square on the leg side
back of a length outside off, left alone
full and skidding into middle, played back to Rashid
full at the stumps, drives and it skews off a thick inside edge down to long leg
wrong'un from Rashid, veers in and shoots low. Hendricks makes room and somehow keeps it out
full outside off, played up to mid-off
pumped over the covers for a one-bounce four. Floated up on off, a bit too full from Rashid. Hendricks goes over the top
length outside off, angled to backward point
good length and ducking into middle and leg, keeps low once again. The batter goes low with it to keep it out
beaten! Back of a length, climbs past the edge as Omarzai hangs leg side of it
Markam steps out and flaps a short ball outside off to mid-on
taken at deep cover! Attempts to be aggressive, uses his feet, lofts over the off side but couldn't have picked out the fielder much better
good length and on middle and leg, knocked away to the right of mid-on
beaten! Back of a length, nips back, Rashid shapes to cut
another shooter, this time from Omarzai. Good length and outside off, keeps low, rolls off the toe end to the keeper
a rapid bouncer, he ducks underneath...and it's called wide back of a length, straight, defended and a few words shared
yet another shooter but this isn't on the stumps. Full and just a shade outside off, sneaks underneath the bat
more big movement off the seam, nips back sharply at Rashid who is just able to keep it out
this leaps from a length, Hendricks loosens his grip and somehow fends it down
shortish and outside off, chopped away to deep point
appeal for lbw, perhaps a touch high and leg side as it nips back
short and outside off, carved away to deep third, where Janat, I think, fumbles and gives up a double
short of a length outside off, pushed away from his body, finds backward point
on a length and outside off, the ball doesn't come onto the bat, squirted to cover
fuller at the stumps, not far from getting through, worked down to long leg
fullish and outside off, push-driven to the off-side sweeper for a single
full outside off, drives and finds mid-off
swatted away over midwicket for a one-bounce four. Markram gets on top of a short ball outside off, no excessive bounce here, so Markram puts it away rather easily
great shot! That's a perfect drive. Wasn't a half volley. On the up, threads the gap between cover and mid-off
full and wide of off, slapped away to point
slashed away! Short and wide from Rabada, Rashid puts it away over backward point
another good shot, full at off stump, drives straight of mid-on
spliced away to sweeper cover for a single
good length at off stump, 146kph, defended
back of a length and outside off, Markram stands up tall, gets on top of it and punches it on the up over mid-off. Terrific shot on a tough pitch
huge bounce! Backs away outside leg, slashes and it climbs over the top edge and out of de Kock's reach
shorter and skids back in off the deck, Markram swings to the leg side and manages an inside edge onto his hip
appeal for lbw, slipping down leg...Nortje went fuller at the stumps. And, in fact, Markram has called the review. Hits above the knee roll and angling leg side. Missing the stumps.

full and wide outside off, Markram throws his bat at ball and drags an inside edge past the stumps for a single. Omarzai has overstepped Hooked for six! SA are just one away from the WC final. Free-hit from Omarzai. Banged in short, Hendricks gets on top of it and swings it away over square leg for the first six of the game
short, over leg stump, Janat goes for the pull. Close to another glove
That is that. SA demolish Afghanistan to make their maiden World Cup final. Full and outside off, Hendricks shows the full face of the bat and sweetly punches the ball down the ground
full outside off, nicely onto the front foot, driven firmly to mid-off. A direct hit at the striker's end might have been close
short outside leg stump, pulled through square leg
poor ball again, short and down the leg side, goes down to sweep and doesn't connect very full outside off, driven into the covers

big appeal for lbw, and given! Illingworth's finger went up in a flash. And the review is equally quick. Was full and straight, he played all around it. Has it turned too much? Clipping leg stump and umpire's call.
worked off the stumps into midwicket
given lbw again! And another review. A quicker delivery, pushed through on the stumps, he was playing back. And it's clipping leg stump again
defended on the back foot
short of a length at off stump, driven off the back foot to cover
not many is the answer! Off stump is knocked out of the ground. Back of a length, this one doesn't get up, Rashid shaped to angle it away and was a long way from it
full at off stump, no footwork, pokes the bat at the ball
back of a length, angling in, defended
shorter, at the body, manages to open the face and steer it through backward point
backs away against a short ball, aims to ramp it, doesn't connect
full at off stump, drives down the ground to long off
goes for the reverse sweep, he misses and it deflects off de Kock's pad past slip
a strangled appeal for lbw as he plays forward, might have nicked it
spins into the pads, deflects down into the leg side
misses a sweep, looks very straight, and given...reviews because he can do. Can't see this going anywhere other than middle on first look. Hits the back leg. Smashing middle halfway up.
over the wicket, pitched up and swinging back in. Salt clips off his pads to the leg-side boundary rider
full, angling across, Rohit pushes out playing for swing... nearly nicks off! Buttler lets out a cry of anguish as the ball nestles in his gloves
definite shape back to the right-hander, 134kph/83mph and Buttler pushes forward, comes off the inside half of the bat to leg
here comes the Rohitman, looking to take England down early, just as he did Australia in India's last match. Thick-edged but safely beyond short third and away
Buttler skips out, the ball is dug in and he pulls into the gap between fine leg and deep square
length ball, tapped into the covers for one
fullish, 137kph/85mph and curling back on middle and leg, squirted out square for a single
fullish, not much swing so far, thought Topley might be scrambling the seam. Kohli steers to the fielder in the covers
pitched up outside off, this barely gets off the ground. Slower ball and it slides through under Salt's impetuous thrash
gives Topley the charge, misses! Shape back in as he hacks across the line, the ball beats the bat and slides past the pads, then leg stump through to Buttler
pace off again, back of a length and it comes off the body with Salt looking to swing it away leg side. Good start from Arshdeep
back of a length, tucked off the pads for a leg bye
short of a length, 136kph/84mph into the body. Salt jumps across and nudges behind square
stays low! Archer hits a length in the channel, Kohli throws the hands and misses
fuller and flicked off the pads, Buttler gets a couple more between the boundary riders at fine leg and deep square
angling in and chopped into the leg side for Kohli's first run
full outside off, pace off, 126kph. Buttler stretches into a drive but picks out mid-off
back of a length, banged into the deck on fourth stump. Rohit hops into line and jabs towards cover
full in the channel, Buttler opens the face to drive but picks out backward point
swing and a miss! Shortish in the channel and Rohit tries to haul it into the Atlantic Ocean, fails to connect
edged wide of the keeper, England pick up their first boundary. Buttler played it softly, angling the bat to keep it down, and short third won't cut it off
back of a length, stays low again... Rohit stands legs akimbo after swiping unsuccessfully outside off
fired in at the pads, flicked away to deep square leg for one more
short and slapped through backward point! Phil Salt didn't seem to pick it up at all, not sure how catchable it was. But either way, the ball ends up skedaddling away to the rope
Buttler saunters down and smashes over mid-off! Hardik was the man on the edge of the ring and he threw his arm up but couldn't quite get fingertips to the ball
an offcutter, I think, 128kph/79mph and it spins up past the bat
shorter and swatted away fine! The overcorrection in length is helped away off the body, four more England's captain
full and blapped over cow! Leans into a handsome swipe across the line, Topley's full length goes the journey for the first time today
pace off, mistimed into the pads
pushes across the bows, Kohli closes the face and gets a fat leading edge past mid-off for a couple
another cutter angling across, Buttler steers towards point

bowled 'im, straight through! Kohli's tough tournament continues as Topley pegs back leg stump. Another attempt to assert himself against the new ball but this was the perfect length, shaped back in as he heaved across the line, and flicked off the bails, to English delight. Just Topley's second wicket of the tournament
short and hammered! Pace off but picked this time. Buttler stands tall in the crease and belts it hard and flat in front of square, past the sprawling Jadeja for another boundary
over the wicket, straight line and tapped down to leg
slower bumper again, this one into the body and it's pulled without timing through square leg
back of a length, maybe pace off again. Shovelled to leg and they hurry through as Topley runs across to field

angled in from round the wicket, Buttler looking for the reverse-clump... toe-ended straight up into the air for Pant to take! Axar the axe man, chops down England's totem! Never mind Salt, he's an onlooker as his captain misses a swipe across the line, the ball popping up to the keeper. Gaffaney's finger goes straight up and off walks Buttler
back of a length on the stumps, again seems to stay down as Rohit defends to leg
nudged into the leg side for one
opens the face and runs this past backward point. Two England fielders turn and give chase. Rohit opts for touch above power and picks up two
makes some room and slaps down the ground to long-off
chipped over the off-side ring! Rohit goes for the big shot this time, the bat coming down at a crooked angle, but there was enough of a connection to clear extra cover running back
over the wicket, 95kph on the stumps, Moeen flicks into the gap at deep midwicket
straighter line, tucked away towards fine leg
goes back and bottom-hands one more down to long-on
round the wicket, 144kph/89mph in the channel outside off. Pant steps out and steers through point
fired in full, Salt is forward and driving, gets a couple through the covers
sliced over the infield again, looking to launch down the ground. Again Rohit survives a non-in-control hack
fizzing slower ball, dipping and then spinning away through to the keeper with Moeen groping for it half forward
on the pads, flicked in the air... but short of Rashid at short fine leg! The ball then spins up and causes a fumble that brings them one
tapped down and they hustle through
round the wicket, Rohit is across, hauled through square leg! Half-tracker that doesn't get up, may have been pace off. Clubbed into the gap between two men back
back of a length, this skids on at Salt as he hangs back, jabs to leg
good length, 135kph/84mph on off stump, defended to cover

pace off, and Salt's off... leg stump pinned back! Beautifully bowled, a slow, dipping offcutter, enticing the big air shot from the batter. Salt holds the pose as he looks down the fairway, visualising where that ball was supposed to end up. Instead, India and their fans in the crowd are celebrating again
full and laced through the covers! Steps outside leg stump this time and opens up the off side, Topley aims for the stumps... but gets belted for his troubles
beats the outside edge, seaming away off the pitch with Bairstow looking to commit on the front foot
length ball, angling back in, tucked to leg for one
slung down straight, 138kph/86mph and deflected leg side. No appeal as it thudded into the pads
back of a length and cracked through point to the sweeper

there's another, off stump rattled! And England rattled, too... A wild hack at one that was always coming back in on the angle. No turn but it stayed a touch low (where have you heard that before?), crashing into the outer half of the stump to spark more jubilation among those in blue shirts
good length from over the wicket, Pant nudges to midwicket
flat on off, 92kph and bunted towards cover coming forwards

chipped to midwicket! Tame way for Pant to go, and Curran is delighted. Fullish length ball angling in, may have stopped in the pitch slightly. Didn't get any sort of connection as he flicked across it and picked out Bairstow for a head height catch
goes back this time and steers a punch past the dive of cover in the ring
back of a length, nudged off the pads
pushed through on the stumps and tapped to leg, Axar gives chase
full and worked across the line, Rohit calls for one as Archer jogs in... and Suryakumar suddenly checks himself and nearly gets in a tangle. Always a run there
blasted back down the ground, but absolutely no timing on it. Trundles short of long-off as the off-side sweeper runs around
pinged back down the ground! Curran thrusts out a hand in vain. May have been a slower ball, but SKY drove uppishly and powerfully through the line for four to long-off
darted on off stump and Brook covers up in defence. England end the powerplay severely wounded at 39 for 3
finds the edge but it doesn't carry! Trundles through low in front of Buttler as SKY fiddled outside off

goes for the reverse and gets it away! Buttler was appealing for lbw but this was straight off the bat, chopping down on it late. Archer gave chase but couldn't pull the ball back as he tiptoed towards the rope at deep third
over the wicket, tossed up around off stump. Moeen pushes one down to long-off
flighted, spinning on leg-stump, can't get it away
stays over the wicket, floated up outside off, 86kph and tapped to cover coming forwards
full and swept in orthodox fashion! Powerfully struck as he gets low and across his stumps, into the gap behind deep square leg
gives it a bit more air, Brook steps down and drive to long-off
flatter outside off, chopped into the ground
b-i-i-i-i-i-g turn, dropped on a length and ragging away from the bat as Moeen tries to play forward
looped up and punched down the ground to long-off
tossed up slightly straighter, this doesn't spin as much. Worked off the pads
floated up, 76kph/47mph on leg stump, SKY is hit on the front pad looking to flick to leg. Buttler asks the question but there's not much support from his bowler
flat sweep, smashed through midwicket! Brook is low and as far forward as he can be, extending the arms to crunch his first boundary

has he been stumped after wandering out of his ground...? Moeen is on his knees trying to get back, but Pant thinks he is short. Yes, it's a straightforward one for Joel Wilson and England are four down! Axar fired the ball at Moeen's pads and it clipped the thigh guard as he aimed to leg. Moeen thought the ball had gone much further than it did, and by the time he realised Pant had collected down to his right and broken the stumps, the batter stranded
short with pace off, wide of off stump. Rohit collapses like a deckchair in the wind pulling for one out to deep midwicket
clipped through midwicket
fullish and straight, another slower ball. SKY clips off his pads
Brook turns the strike over
into the pitch, top of off stump, worked out to wide long-on
pushed through on the stumps, Curran finds midwicket

SKY goes aerial! Swung over fine leg! An incredible shot, of the kind he plays regularly... it was a length ball, no room really to get under it, but Suryakumar shuffles across and breaks the wrists to scoop insouciantly all the way for six
tucked through square leg
on the stumps and tucked through midwicket
goes back outside off and attempts to cut, can't get it through
pace on wide of the stumps, 137kph/85mph and Rohit flails at it unsuccessfully

trapped in front playing back, Rod Tucker's finger goes straight up! Curran reviews but perhaps more in hope than expectation. Deep in the crease and he's hit on the front pad playing across the line. Curran has seen enough and is walking... It was a skiddy, low-bouncing wrong'un, would have smashed leg stump according to ball-tracking! India are bossing this, erasing Adelaide line by line from the collective memory
Loopy and full, 89ks on the pads, SKY looks to whip it square and misses. Gets hit on the pad
tossed up and punched through the off side
Flat and fullish, 91ks, lands around fourth and turns away a bit. Slapped to cover
tickled down the ground
SKY's front leg slides towards square leg as he clips the length ball to midwicket. Old school back-foot play
looking for one but Brook is sent back! Livingstone pushed towards point but wasn't interested, leaving his partner scrambling
Slow and full on leg, 88ks, worked to long-on
tossed up on the stumps and worked away square on the leg side
Whipped to the right of long-on, they'll have to settle for one. Was full and at the stumps again, SKY still not going hard
flat, angling away outside off, maybe another googly. Brook stretches and swipes a single off the cue end
And England do get that chop-out over. Rohit happy to work it to long-on again. Gentle, along the ground, single
Goes back and tucks it towards long-on again
fired down on off stump, Brook cuts and gets it past point
Buttler interested in the lbw, umpire doesn't give it.. Bowler, captain chat and won't review. Was a dipping full ball around fourth that beat the sweep. Hit him on the boot
slammed in front of square! Drops deep in the crease and cracks a cut for a much-needed boundary
Dances down, zig zags a bit, and slaps it to the off-side sweeper
fizzed down straight, Brook plays with a straight bat through cover
Length on leg, clipped to deep midwicket
flat outside off, 96kph and Livingstone plays a back-foot punch through point
Rashid delivers a fully, the drift works against him too. Takes it down leg and SKY, was was across to off stump, leans on one knee and sweeps it well over short fine leg
wheels away, hint of turn from a wider line, Brook cuts to the sweeper
Sweeps it around the corner again to retain strike
straighter, 98kph and Livingstone can only jab it back to the bowler's right

Run-out missed, overthrow taken. Was a full ball pushed to cover, went straight to him but Brook took off. Was three-fourth of the way home when the throw was fired towards Kuldeep, who couldn't take it.
Length on fifth, underedges the cut towards backward point
What happened there? Is that a drop? Doesn't look like it. Brook opened the face fully and tried to guide it to third. Was close but no nick, Pant tried jugging but couldn't hold on
Length on leg, clipped against the spin to deep midwicket. Back-foot shot
Reversed straight of short third. It was fullish and Brook lunged really low, scraped it off the floor almost and got it fine
Wide on a length, slapped to deep cover

Uno reverse from Kuldeep, is that England done? Brook went across this time, too far across as it turned it. Kuldeep went length, drifted it away before spinning it back in. Brook smothered it last time, but this one went below bat. Kuldeep leaps and roars in celebration
Livingstone's making India hit to fielders. Goes full on leg with deep midwicket out, that's where SKY flicks it
Full on off, pushed back to the bowler
Rohit premeditates the reverse sweep and ties himself in a knot. Rashid delivered a low full toss on leg, guided to short third. Rohit manages a smile
Goes back to a fullish ball but defends with a straight bat, while standing in front of off
First boundary for Rohit since the break. He holds his shape and tonks it over long-on. This was full and tossed up outside off, Rohit took a big stride, back leg buckled and hands swung freely
Punches it off a length to cover
Tucks it across to the leg side
Dragged down but it doesn't bounce much. SKY has ample time to rock back and adjust to pull through midwicket
Tight on off, worked to long-on
Down the track, guides the googly to midwicket
Pant yells as Jadeja sticks his foot out a few feet to stop it, ball balloons back but not far. Was punched back by the batter
Backs away to make room and hoicks across, gets it off the bottom and it goes to long-on on the bounce. Fifty partnership up
Huge bounce overwhelms Liam as he defends. Looked to have landed on a length but the batter played it in front of the chest
Almost did him in flight. SKY danced down and had a hack, wanted to go over long-on. The loopy ball on a length has him lose his shape and toe it into the grass to the leg side
Dances down to negate that bounce, it's on the heart of a length and is worked across leg side
Rohit wants to leather it across with a pull but gets no pace to work with. The shortish ball spinning away stops a bit and finds the toe of the bat
Length on leg, clipped back to the bowler.
Chops it off the back foot to point
Remarkable launch square of the wicket. It was pitched up around fourth and SKY shaped for the off-drive, presented all optics of the off-drive and opened the bat-face on impact

Huge appeal. Pant's leaping and dancing and Rod Tucker raises the finger. Jordan committing the cardinal sin of playing across the line on this pitch. That and going cross-batted have been poor options. But has this spun too much? Jordan was deep in the crease, with feet almost jammed, as he tried to clip it it with a slightly closed bat-face. It landed on a length at the edge of off stump, spun back to hit him on top of the knee-roll, and... it's clipping top of leg
Works it off the stumps to the leg side
Full ball is punched to cover

Rohit pre-meditates and essentially sweeps it over fine leg to reach a 36-ball fifty. He got on one knee and picked it up, had to wait till it got next to him to place it. Did it brilliantly. Buttler goes to have a word with the bowler
Archer goes back and tries to thrash it through cover. Underedges it towards short fine
Length around off, punched to mid-off
Using the crease well again. Kuldeep going close to the stumps, landing it wide on a length. Scoots low slowly, Liam rocks back and plinks a cut to cover
Slower one gets extra bounce but SKY pumps it. He started to coil but got upright again and pulled it from around waist-height through square leg
Punches it off the back foot, from the crease, to Kuldeep's right
Full ball is worked to long-on.
Goes back and clips it to deep midwicket. Rashid keeping it a little quick
Archer unsure of whether that's coming in or going back. Stays in the crease and just about manages to work it back to the bowler
Flatter length ball on leg, 91ks, Rohit clears the front leg and works it across to long-on
Chops it from outside off to deep point
SKY gets his front leg well outside off and sweeps well inside the line
Makes room and slaps the ball heading towards top of middle, to long-off

Rashid strikes in his last over with a big shooting googly. 81ks length ball landed around fourth and ragged back. Rohit's eyes lit up and he went for a mighty heave while holding his base. In the end, the upper body wound up too much and there was no contact. Ball spinning off the stumps is quite the sight
Jaffa. Fullish ball lands on leg and turns away sharply. Goes over top of middle. So huge bounce too
Doesn't carry to Moeen at slip, he went low to the left but got half-volleyed
Caresses it off the back foot to deep point

Pitch playing tricks now, Rashid's spell done which India might not mind. This pretty much rolled on the floor despite landing in the middle of a length. Spun from around off to fifth, Pandya went across and blocked it late. Lack of pace helped
Pulls it off a length to deep midwicket. Was a fullish length ball on off, and Liam got the front leg well out the way
Goes across and tucks it off the front foot through midwicket. Quick running allows two
Cut with the spin and almost off the keeper's gloves. Archer, running to the left from deep point, has no chance
Backs away and chops it to deep point
Spin again. Legbreak on a length spins away to fourth and is punched back to the bowler
Full and angling in from wide of the crease. Archer goes for the slog swipe over cow corner, gets hit on the pad
Wide and shortish, cut to point
This is at middle and Archer winds up and clubs it downtown. Golf swing with the toes pointing up
Jumps up a bit, punched back to the bowler's left. Length ball landed on off and spun away again

England's last hope gets barbecued. Livingstone ran three-fourth of the way to the other end, Archer came one-fourth before going back. Throw from short fine came at a full toss to Axar's left, who beat Livingstone to the race. Was a length ball close to off, cramped Archer for room and he underedged a cut past the left of the keeper. Looked like Livingstone called and came through but Archer hesitat
Extravagant turn away to have SKY collapse after cutting. Landed around fifth and finished outside the tramline, finds point
Chopped across to the off side
Run-out referral. Hardik didn't slide the bat in but managed to place it inside the crease by the time Buttler collected the throw from short third and whipped off the bails
Chops it to deep point
Legcutter on a back of length outside off, cut to short third

Remarkable athleticism from SKY. Thought that was Jadeja but no. He's a right hander but collected the ball while running to the other side and back-flicked it on the move like a left-hander as Rashid ran in vain.
Not much width but Hardik backs away and carves it through point
More clubbing from Archer, might as well take a few souvenirs. Gorgeous swing again, stood still, clattered it without fuss. Was almost like a shot Hardik plays
Shortish ball follows him as he goes outside leg, squeezed to cover
Into the pitch, Archer top edges a pull to long-on

Slower one is skied, is that six or out? In the air for a while... and Jordan takes it at long-on. Back of handed at 113ks from Archer, slot ball just outside off, looked like SKY picked it. He'd taken the front leg outside leg, had to bring it back and got the momentum into the lofted on-drive. Swung as hard as he could but didn't get enough. Jordan did well, took a few feet in, scuttled back but knew he had a lot of room to settle
Makes room to a back of lengther on middle and leg, heaves across, inside edges to deep fine leg
Pulls the shortish ball to deep-backward square
Slappage over extra cover. England's 100 is up. Wide and full from Pandya with mid-off up, and Archer helped himself by freeing his arms
Slower one on a back of length is tucked to square leg
Slower yorker attempted. Slower low fully delivered. Topley had made a lot of room and reached out to broom it to long-on
Full on leg, following the batter, driven back to the bowler
Length on off, steered with an open face to deep point
Big wind-up and heave across from Pandya, the full ball is plinked to long-on
Length on middle and leg, Topley's in no mood to stay in front of the stumps. Backs away and tries to belt it over mid-on, edges it onto pad
Full one, punch-drive to the bowler's right

That's that. Archer has been given lbw, but he's reviewed. India won't get the full-blown visceral celebration but know they've got this.. He went across, front foot at cover, as the low fully hit the back boot which was in front of middle. Was the angle taking it too far? Bat not close, so that's no issue. Hawk-Eye shows it'd go on to clip leg stump. Third final in ICC tournaments in a year for India!

Spins out far again. Length ball landed on a line just inside the tramline and spun sharply to finish well outside, 81ks, Hardik was through the shot a bit early. Cut uppishly but in the gap and to long-off
Full and wide, slapped to deep cover

Livingstone tried to do what he did a couple balls back but Hardik's onto the plan. Lets it spin off a length from outside off and go wide Underedges a cut back into the pitch and just past the keeper
Into the pitch, 118ks, Hardik makes room and bunt-cuts it through cover

Flat bullet over wide long-on, who was placed well actually but Hardik's slowish back-lift and baseball-y swipe across the line took it over the man, slightly to the right, but arguably without danger
Cutter has been pancaked again. Pandya clearing the front leg and slaps it with all might

Third time's the charm for Jordan, Hardik holes out to long-off. Shot wasn't dissimilar to the six last ball but this was a cutter on a length, unlike the full ball last one. Hardik wound up and clattered with just as much bat speed. Found Curran to perfection. Smiles as he looks at Jordan wile walking back

And nicked off first ball, Jordan on a hat-trick. The first wicket was as T20 as they come, this was Test-y. Fullish length ball on fourth stump and Dube's feet were glued. He felt for it with the bat, opened the face late, but could only guide it to the keeper
Length in the channel, patted to cover
Bunts it off a length to deep point

Cut well by Jadeja, looked like a slower one. Yep, it was on a length and just outside off. Jadeja's back leg buckled and he crouched a bit to get on top of the bounce and used his wrists well to find the gap to backward point's left
Jadeja shapes to paddle but that's a swindle. He comes back into position, guides it through point
Slower one is swept to the right of short fine leg. Great shot, spinner's length ball on fourth. Jadeja got on one knee and hit it into the ground from the top of the bounce
Full at 140ks, angling in towards the stumps, punched firmly and straight o long-on

Axar bamboozled by the length ball following him before leaving him. He was dancing down and was halfway into the straight drive while losing all shape and his head bobbing back to sight the ball that went to the keeper. Archer does manage to close out the over well
Jadeja stays leg side of the slower length ball and slaps it gently. Places it to the left of deep cover, who has to run in diagonally, which allows time for the second
Zips off the pitch and Jadeja doesn't have time to swing his bat. Ends up patting it to long-off. Was a fullish ball around fourth, Jadeja looked to be out of the crease

Slow, wide and length again. No bounce at all, Axar reaches out and cuts it from well in front of the body to deep cover's right. Liam gets to it, the second is taken just after the throw leaves hand, but it's wide for Buttler and Axar makes it back

Axar uses his long levers, bottom lever in fact, and swipes it over long-on. Didn't look like he'd get that but that sailed. Was a slower one into the pitch angling away outside off, it wasn't so much a powerful swing as a controlled one with adjustment
Swatted away... straight to long-on. Jordan hitting a length and bowling at the body. Not much space for Axar to work with. Got cramped but heaved across on the rise
Jordan wasn't sure if he'd throw it hard, underarm. Does the latter in the end at the non-striker's, no direct hit and India get one.
fullish, a bit of swing in towards off stump, defended into the covers
full to start, just a hint of swing to straighten towards off stump. Clipped to the right of mid-on and Rohit is off the mark

edged, but it doesn't carry. Slower ball, and it's the cutter nipping away off the track. Pitches outside off, on a length, and goes further away. Pushes at it without really moving his feet, and the edge bounces a foot or so before reaching Pant
and a four first ball for Kohli! Gets a nice, juicy, wide half-volley first up, and he reaches out and meets it with a slightly open face to place it between backward point and cover point
back of a length, straightens into Henrdicks after pitching outside leg. Misses the flick, rolls away to the left of Pant off the thigh pad
back-to-back fours, and back-to-back freebies from Jansen. Another half-volley, but this one swings into Kohli's pads, and he clips it away neatly to the right of the man at midwicket
a bit of swing. Fullish length, angling in towards middle and swinging towards off, punched to midwicket
another half-volley, just outside off this time, and Kohli gets a nice stride forward, bends his front knee to get his weight into the ball, and plays a checked drive betwen cover and mid-off
length ball close to off stump, chopped down to deep third
good length for the first time in this over, slanting across into the corridor, and immediately there's some carry, de Kock collecting just above his head after Kohli leaves it alone

slower ball, looks to slant it away from Hendricks' reach, and maybe looking for the uppish drive, but he holds his shape, gets his head moving towards the ball, and reaches out to drive between backward point and cover point

another half-volley, close to off stump, and Kohli drives straight this time, between the stumps and the non-striker, and both mid-on and mid-off give chase but neither can catch up with the ball, though Nortje, running from mid-on, gets close enough to attempt a sliding save

good length, slanting across, and I don't think it did anything off the pitch necessarily. Kept going with the angle across, and QdK may have been playing for a bit of swing into him. Beaten while looking to drive on the up through mid-off
just a touch back of a length, not a lot of width, but Rohit makes himself room to try and cut. A bit of extra bounce, a thick edge, and it flies away into the big gap between slip and backward point
full on the pads, misses the flick and Pant, diving right, fumbles the deflection off the pad
India are absolutely flying here. On the shorter side of a length, and the line is outside off, and Rohit spots the line early and brings out the reverse-sweep, slaps it away behind backward point

has anyone bowled a better delivery in a T20 World Cup final? Wow. Reeza tends not to move his feet a great deal early on, and he gets out to the perfect outswinger. Perfect length to hit the top of off stump after angling in and veering away so, so late to beat the outside edge as Hendricks looks to defend with a straight bat. Beautiful. His front leg ended up planted in place, and his feet whrre unable to move thereafter, so he had to basically push his bat out in front of his boy to try and meet it, but a lot of batters may have been bowled by this ball even if they'd moved their feet
tightens his line, good length on off stump, defended to short extra-cover

length ball, close to off stump, and Markram just stands tall and punches it away, letting it come to him, meeting it right under his eyes with a straight bat to send it flying to the right of backward point

gone, what a catch this is from Klaasen! Rohit  continues to try and put pressure on Maharaj. Floated up slow outside off stump - 77kph - and he stretches out to sweep. Middles it, but doesn't really smash it, because he's reaching for the ball - ends up hitting it in the air to the left of square leg, where Klaasen takes a good, low diving catch two-handed
back of a length in the corridor, a hint of away shape, left alone
length ball outside off, presses forward and dabs towards backward point

similar ball to the one that got Reeza, on a length, finishing top of off after a bit of late outswing, but Markram shows how to play it, getting his head right on top of the ball, getting his body moving into the ball, and defending into the covers

is that two wickets in the over for Maharaj? Two wickets off the sweep? South Africa think so. The umpires are checking for a bump ball. Goes for the sweep against a very full ball, and ends up meeting it on the full, in fact, outside off. And he's a goner. Straight up in the air off the top edge of the toe end, and it balloons up behind him to de Kock. What a turnaround in the space of three balls, after India had run away to a flier
full, angling into middle stump, shows the full face and pushes to the right of mid-on
back of a length outside off, and steep bounce through to the keeper after Kohli leaves alone
slower ball, full, slanting away from off stump, reaches out with his hands and stabs it to backward point
length ball close to off stump, defended into the point region

got him, Markram has edged a big drive to the keeper! Wasn't a half-volley. On the fuller side of a length, well wide of off stump, the seam doesn't quite come out of the hand straight, and the ball doesn't swing back in. Just keeps going with the angle across, and Markram, going hard at it with a diagonal bat, gets a thick edge that carries at about ankle height to Pant, falling to his right
fullish, angling in towards off stump, clipped to short midwicket
again he angles a wide length ball across, and Stubbs drives with a roll of the wrists, out to the right of deep point
back of a length outside off, opens his bat face to dab to the left of point

goes short now, angling down leg, and de Kock, looking to hook, is a little cramped for room. Misses, or did he get a little touch on this? Rishabh Pant thinks so, and India review the not-out decision. Was there a tiny nudge of glove on this? De Kock looks a little sheepish, but that's not too far from his usual expression. Nothing on Ultra Edge, and India lose their review
hard length, straightens a touch towards the top of off, with a bit of extra bounce, squared up slightly while defending to short cover
slower ball again, fullish, angling in towards off stump. De Kock spots it, gets a stride forward to push to the right of long-on. Interesting how often he's gone off-pace with this new ball

ooooh, just clears mid-on! Could be one of those sliding-doors moments. Length ball, hits the pitch hard, angling in towards off stump, and SKY goes for the wristy whip over mid-on, but doesn't middle it - the ball hit the bat pretty high up - and it loops up over mid-on, for a moment appearing catchable as the fielder turns around and begins to give chase, but the over-the-shoulder ball doesn't quite land within range

puts it away in the gap, but was he looking to play it that fine. Bumrah angles a hard-length ball across de Kock, and he steers it away between slip and short third. Hit his bat somewhere between its middle and the top edge
tossed up wide of off, driven with a wristy slap to the left of long-off
full, angling across, driven to the right of mid-off
quicker, straightens sharply on an off-stump line, squares up a little while defending off the back foot
length ball angling in towards middle stump, clipped to deep square leg
similar ball, but this time Kohli is right behind it to defend into the covers
fullish, angling into middle and leg, clipped to short midwicket
short, wide, slapped. Just sits up and Kohli stands up and whacks it away to the left of cover
slower ball from Bumrah this time. Fullish outside off, and Stubbs gets a nice stride into the ball to punch it to short cover
drifts in towards middle and leg, clipped to backward square leg
length ball angling into off stump, uses the angle nicely to clip it down to fine leg
length ball close to off stump, goes deep in his crease and cuts to point
steps across immediately to try and sweep this fine, but is struck on the pad by the inward-angling length ball. Struck outside the line
length ball outside off, presses forward and guides to deep third
nicely played. A touch short, perhaps a reaction to the attempted sweep off the last ball, and even though there isn't a lot of width, he times his back-cut perfectly to the left of short third
on the fuller side of a length, close to off stump, punched with a straight bat to the left of mid-off
makes a bit of room to cut again, but a bit slower and straighter, slaps it to cover

three down, and Rabada gets a huuuge wicket. Again, not necessarily a wicket-taking ball, and India's aggressive intent - which has served them so well through this tournament - goes against them. Steps across to a back-of-a-length ball angled in towards the stups, and whips it away, but close enough to fine leg for the fielder to move to his left and take a straightforward catch
down the track, too close to the pitch for an aggressive shot, punches down to long-off
full on the pads, and he puts it away, clips it neatly to the right of the diving square leg fielder
angled across to finish just outside off, and de Kock creates extra room and slaps it away over the covers
full, not quite a half-volley, slanting away from off stump, driven to cover point
back of a length, close to off stump, dabbed to short third

slapped away, and backward point misfields. Maybe some bad bounce for the fielder. Shortish, slanting across into the corridor, gets on top of the bounce and hits it firmly down with a horizontal bat. Rolls away past backward point, but deep third moves left swiftly to cut it off
full, angling into middle and leg, clipped to deep midwicket
flat, angled into the pads. Looks to squeeze any room QDK might have. Tucked to backward square leg
length ball spinning in from outside off, goes back and across to work it to deep midwicket

clear intent from Stubbs here. Makes a lot of room, exposes all his stumps, and throws his bat at a middle-stump length ball. A bit of extra bounce, and the top edge clears backward point but slows down near thje boundary
fired into the pads from round the wicket, clipped into the midwicket region. Replay shows that Markram delivered this from well behind the crease
clears his front leg again and Kuldeep goes fuller, on off stump, quite quick. Doesn't quite get all the way down on his knee, semi-slog-sweeps along the ground to long-on
full, close to off stump, too full for elevation. Whipped down to long-on, all along the ground
again looks to clear his front leg and Kuldeep goes full to deny him elevation. Stump-to-stump line this time, driven to long-on
floated up full on leg stump, whipped to deep midwicket
steps out and can't get to the pitch of this ball outside off. Not much turn, stretches out and defends into the covers
stretches out to whip this length ball from well outside off to the right of long-on

wrong'un, just back of a length, and it doesn't turn enough to deny de Kock room. Creates a bit more room and cuts it away between point and backward point. Was initially shaping for the reverse-sweep but didn't over-commit to that shot
back of a length close to off stump, opens the bat face and steers to deep point
back of a length, keeps going with the angle into the top of the stumps, makes room and chops to the off-side sweeper
hard length, angling across to finish on middle stump. Stays leg side of the ball and looks for the dabbed single towards point, but the ball stops close to the pitch and there's no single available
very full on the stumps, denies elevation, makes room and drives to long-off
length ball slanting across to off stump, steered to deep point with an open face

shot. Lovely hockey swing there on the slog-sweep. Not full enough to deny elevation, but full enough to be in Stubbs' hitting arc for the slog-sweep on off stump. Hits it straight of deep midwicket, on the bounce
back of a length, angling in, looks to tuck it away but can't connect, hits the thigh pad
back of a length, finishes on off stump, makes room and punches to deep cover point
again some steep bounce. Slower bouncer over the stumps, and it takes an age to reach Kohli but it gets up around neck high. Rolls his wrists over the pull to keep it down towards deep square leg
stays round the wicket, fires one at the pads, swept but without much power to short fine leg
length ball on leg stump, clipped to deep midwicket
similar line, a bit slower, through the sweep too early and he inside-edges into his pads
full, angled into leg stump from round the wicket, clipped to long-on

drilled. Superb, quick hands from Stubbs. Loops it up, wants to get it right up to squeeze the room for the drive, but his bat-swing is so quick and free, he steps out and drills it back between the stumps and the non-striker
full on off stump, clipped to deep midwicket
full again, gets forward and clips to deep midwicket

just clears deep midwicket. Takes the risk, but goes with the wind. Tossed up, angling in towards middle stump, turns a little too, but he gets a good stride in to slog-sweep against the turn and connect well enough
full at the pads, clipped to the left of short fine leg
very full now, angling into middle stump, dug out into the off side
hangs back to a length ball on leg stump, clips it towards deep midwicket
slows it down on off stump, goes for the slog-sweep again, drags it towards square leg off the bottom half of the bat
wrong'un, looped up wide of off stump. Looks for the drive through the covers, hits the inside half of the bat and rolls back to the bowler
goes back to a length ball spinning in from outside off, punches with a straight bat to deep midwicket

another wrong'un, but this is right in the slot, close to off stump, for Kuldeep to drop onto his back knee and slog-sweep waaaaay over the midwicket boundary and onto the solar-panelled roof of the stand. Hit that with such a fluid bat-swing. Brings up the 50 partnership, and these two are looking ominous now for India

so good from Stubbs. That was not an easy ball to slog-sweep, it was a touch short to play it comfortably, and started well outside off, but he stepped across, got low, and almost pulled it from there, to the left of the man at deep backward square leg
goes back and punches a length ball down to long-off. Just outside off
makes room, slaps this leg-stump ball out to deep point
uses the angle across the left-hander to almost force him to hit to deep point. Just back of a length too. Not much choice but to play the cut
looks to reverse-sweep, inside-edges onto his pad
full on leg stump, gets forward to clip to long-on
length ball angling in towards off stump, no real turn, makes room and chops to short third
looks to angle it away from Axar's hitting arc again, but doesn't succeed on this occasion. Just full enough, and not quite wide enough, and Axar can bring out the big slog-sweep over deep midwicket

Delhi Capitals gets Delhi Capitals. He'd stepped across once earlier this over to manufacture a boundary, but when he does so this time, Axar fires it full and at the stumps, and pretty much bowls him around his legs as he misses the sweep. Another big moment in a terrific, seesawing final
flatter, mostly goes with the angle away from off stump, goes back and punches to short cover
fired in at the pads, misses the flick and picks up a leg bye off the outside of his pad, into the backward square leg region
nicely bowled. A bit of drift to accentuate the angle across, and Axar goes back and punches to forward square leg, meeting the ball just outside off
back of a length in the corridor, punched off the back foot and short cover dives right to stop it

starts with a wide outside off. Looks to go flat and quick and away from the hitting arc, on the shorter side of a length. Ends up firing it too wide for the batter to attempt a shot full on leg stump, clipped to long-on
length ball angling into off stump, clipped to midwicket, who's stationed very straight, in line with the popping crease at the bowler's end
quick length ball, turns from middle to off, gets forward to defend into the covers
slower ball, into the pitch outside off. Stops on Klaasen who's initially looking for the cut. Ends up dragging it towards midwicket off the inside half of the bat
he's bowling a really good pace here. Axar isn't able to get onto the front foot quickly as this spins fairly sharply away from middle and off. Defended with the turn

what a shot. Shows the small margins for error at this level. Another short slower ball into the pitch, but a bit more width on this occasion and he hops, gets on top of the bounce, and frees his arms to slap that all the way over the point boundary
quick, flat, turns from leg to middle and off. Stays back and clips towards deep midwicket

length ball angling into the stumps, clipped down to long-on. Looks like he's overstepped here. miscued high in the air, and Pant gets under it behind the stumps, but it's a free-hit. On the fuller side of a length, and de Kock looks to swipe it over midwicket. Ends up hitting it behind him, almost vertically in the air

back of a length, turning down leg, clipped away to the left of the diving short fine leg fielder, and they hustle to try and get the second as deep backward square gets to the ball. Has to hurry, but the throw to the keeper's end isn't accurate enough to really make him sweat
shortish at the hip, paddle-pulled down to fine leg
tossed up outside off, and out comes the slog-sweep, along the ground to the left of deep midwicket. Again they hustle and take two, but they have to really push because Stubbs is electric
full length outside off, and a flat hack from Axar! Slower ball, skews off a leading edge, but short of deep third
on the back foot, clubbed out to deep point with a full swing of the bat
pushed across the right-hander, but avoiding the slot length this time, Kohli rocks into a cut to deep point
back of a length, but not by much, hauled with a cross-batted launch to deep midwicket, gets there on the bounce
back of a length, fenced down to short third
pounded up into the length! Klaasen is so good at that stroke. Stepping into the full length, and breaking his wrists up and over long-off!
back of a length, Jansen mixing it up without being too full. Kohli swivels into a pull but doesn't connect cleanly on the leaping bounce
skids through faster and flatter outside off, cuffed to point
slower ball, back of a length, Axar adjusts well on the angle into off, and taps a late cut to deep third
round the wicket, tapped off the pads with no great pace, but there's a long long chase into acres of space, and Jadeja has to make the ground himself
fires in a loopier full length but that slides past the legs leg-sided on the short ball, deflected off the hips
fired through flatter outside off, cut to deep point. A 12-run over keeps South Africa ticking along
skimmies down the track, Kuldeep fizzes it out wider, QDK adjusts in a hurry and toe-ends to point with Pant lurking for the stumping
steps into the full length, and clipped to the on-side
skids through on off stump, cut without power into the covers
flicked off the toes, out to square leg. Tight lines into the stumps from Shamsi

unbelievable skill! Kuldeep fires out a wider line, back of a length with big turn away on the googly, Klaasen sits with his weight back in the crease, yet still manages to lift it high over extra cover. 100 up too
attempted slog-sweep, but this grips on a middle-and-leg line and turns past the flashing blade into the pads
fired down the leg-side, swept hard behind square
on the back foot, turning into the legs, helped off the toes for another single
steps into the length, pushed into the covers
goes big, goes long! Heart in the mouth for a moment with Rabada tracking round from wide long-on, but that was fast and flat, and straight enough to beat the outstretched hand!
top-spin on a wider line, QDK is lured into a loose cut and immediately grimaces as he just gets away with it. No damage done, this partnership endures
drags the length back, chopped up and over point, not a proper contact but into space once more. Axar is playing the innings of the final so far
full, on the toes, flicked uppishly out to deep midwicket
on the pads, tucked square for the single
punched through the line, to long-off, making room to leg as Nortje follows him on the pads
back of a length, QDK rocks inside the line, and hoists it over fine leg! Using the angle across his body from the left-armer, with fine leg up in the ring. Free runs when you're that good!
angled bat on the back foot, Nortje hitting a good in-between length, patted to point

did he even notice the fielder! De Kock goes for the shot once more, rocking inside the line to the angle into his body, but Kuldeep has dropped back onto the rope, and barely needs to move! It was hit well, would have gone for six unlike the previous ball, but that's a giveaway after such a doughty innings
fuller length, squirted out to point on the drive, beats the diving point
good length ball, nipping back into the left-hander, inside-edged onto the pads
short, down the leg side beats the outside edge as Axar attempts to run a single down to deep third, but can't connect as the ball hops past his splice
on the toes, full length, nudged off the legs behind square
back of a length once more, shovelled off the pads to deep square leg. Just five runs off a very tidy comeback over
finds space in the covers and trots back for two more. A productive over in real terms, but Arshdeep bags the key wicket
round the wicket, into the arc, but what a shot! Axar holds his shape magnificently as the ball appears under his eyes, then lifts his hands up into the full length, high and mighty over long-on!
looped up into the toes, clipped with the spin to deep midwicket, "two, two, two" is the call
steps back and across, slams a firm cut/drive out to deep cover
back of a length, pace off outside off, Miller opens the face to flick to backward point

gives it the charge, Rabada bangs in the short ball. Too short for the square leg umpire, but might keep him crease-bound Is this a run-out or overthrows?! South Africa seem very sure it's the former! And it is! De Kock picks up an attempted flick off the legs from Kohli, swooping and shying at the far end! The ball beat Axar's bat by three inches, then deflected away to the rope at long-off! Huge, huge moment! Axar wanted the single, but Kohli had his back to him, and he couldn't get back in time!
into position early for the sweep, hitting down on the full length outside off, picks off the single to deep midwicket
full length, bottom-handed shovel to long-on
nurdled off the toes, out to backward square leg
full length, outswing to the left-hander, big swing from Dube but he loses his shape a touch and inside-edges onto his pads

back of a length, and finds the rope with the cut! A touch short, just outside off, and Miller's hit in front of square just kept eluding the fielder, who looked like he might have made it with a dive, but didn't get close
on the back foot, chopped away to cover. Ten off the over, but what an important wicket
rocks back for the grandslam finish to the over! Kuldeep's figures get the Jansen treatment at the death, a touch too short and straight, and hoisted over deep midwicket!
steps deeper into his crease, lifted dismissively over the bowler's head! So good at hitting off the back foot! The power is preposterous
Dube dumps it long! I think it's on him to keep the pedal to the metal. Sitting back in the crease, swinging up into the length ball, solid over long-on!
fired outside off, Klaasen doesn't flinch wide again, tighter line but same result has a flash with slightly flat feet, no contact
drags the length back, and nudged off the hips to backward square
steps to the off side this time, and it's on the roof! 99 metres of pure muscle! Anticipated the wide line once more, moved effortlessly into position, and launched it!
punched into the on-side
it's close to a run a ball now! Axar has been India's player of the tournament, but Klaasen, deep in his crease again, belts violently on the up and over long-on!
pace off on the short ball, Kohli rolls his wrists into a delayed, controlled pull, to backward square
steps into the length, hits into the wind! Violence and authority, Axar has nowhere to hide as Klaasen plants his front foot into the length and drills it through wide long-off!
full toss, swinging into the pads at an awkward height as Dube looks to release his levers. Tucked into the leg side
width outside off, hacked over the covers, it's a massive over, and if South Africa don't believe now, they never will!
skips to the pitch, big wind-up through a more expansive launch to leg, but he drags it a touch, on the bounce to deep midwicket
round the wicket, hard length angled into the left-hander, inside-edge past the stumps! The worm has turned...
turning into the legs, can't work it square but finds enough of a gap
back over the wicket, full length on the pads, tucked to midwicket. Singles, shockingly, will suffice. But that's a 23-ball fifty, the fastest in a final, from the mighty Klaasen
beauty! Drift, dip and turn, Dube is rather tentative, back in his crease and beaten past the outside edge
full and fast, thuds the pads, raucous appeal but that's clearly missing leg
very full, Dube swings lustily, but under-edges the shot to short third
yorker, so good! Klaasen digs down on the ball rather desperately, but crucially he digs it out
wider line, dragged hard into the leg side, but once again on the bounce to deep midwicket. Who will blink first in a key over?
full on the pads, flicked with the angle, safely into space behind square. Another single, and that frankly is ample against India's dangerman
swung furiously out through midwicket! Tossed up outside off, imparts huge power with his front foot thrust down the pitch, one bounce before the rope

full length, Miller steps into the length outside off, and drives at short cover. A dot, but crucially, a blank as far as the wickets go. Bumrah has six balls left, and he's got to bowl them next over, surely
clubbed hard through the line but only as far as long-on. That was a good over from South Africa's POV. Seam to close it out now
outside off, chopped to deep backward point for the single

wide line, gets the nick! The break in play did the trick! Klaasen reached for the slam through the covers, very full length, but his feet were stuck in clay. He's livid with himself as he departs, but what a sensational knock!
back of a length, Kohli flicks up into the pull as Nortje takes a bit of pace off, the ball flips just out of de Kock's reach as he dives behind the stumps
steps into the length ball, outside off, a compact drive into the covers, and a raise of the hand to declare 'no run!'
back of a length again, thumped back through Nortje's tumbling followthrough, mopped up by mid-on
wide line on the full length, solid bat through ball on the front foot from Jansen, guided down to deep third
surprise fuller length, poked out to point for a diving take. Cover appeals for the crowd catch, but that was down into the crease
tight line, on the pads, nudged to the on-side, and Miller takes the single. 100 balls gone, 20 to go...
short again, rolls the wrists into the pull... out to deep midwicket. Kohli has his fifty... but he hasn't got a boundary since the fourth over
full length, angled in at off stump, draws a tentative push into the leg side, but finds another single. That's ample at this stage
back of a length, carved away for a precious boundary! Dube made room well, shaping to the leg side to create the width that Nortje wasn't offering. Hitting with the breeze too. Quality
slow bouncer, Miller reads it well and settles for a controlled pull to square leg, rolling his wrists on the ball to keep the strike
snorter to start! Tight line from round the wicket, and that misses both the outside edge and the off stump by a whisker! Miller sliding to leg, then drawn back to the line like a magnet
Kohli goes long at last! Length ball outside off, and that's what you want on this pitch. A full slap over long-on, not perfectly timed but cleared by a distance
wicket-to-wicket pace, Miller settles for the full-faced block back down the line of off... two dots!
yorker, in at the toes, Kohli connects with a firm stab of the bat out to deep midwicket, and finds the space to get back for two
a touch more width this time, just back of a length, Miller flashes a drive out to deep cover and takes the single
back of a length, uses the pace well, rolling the wrists as Rabada's slower ball arrives too straight. Hauled behind the square leg sweeper

sensational delivery! Jasprit Bumrah is the bowler from the Gods! Pace, angle, length, lift, Jansen plays the perfect defensive block, and is bowled through the gate as the ball flicks the top of his bails! This is too tense to function. Pass me an umbrella to gnaw!
fuller length, clipped up into the leg-side as Rabada follows his early movements
so tight and full! Aggressive angled length, demanding a front-foot block
