oops, a horrid full wide, that one slipped out of the hand. De Kock did well to prevent the boundary wide yorker, that's what he was loading up, Dube chops down to deep third with a lusty swing outside off
tapped into the covers off the full length, takes the single. Bumrah has delivered, ahem, one wicket and two runs, and even better, he's got Miller off strike
yorker to finish, right into the blockhole, clipped on the up to the leg side, and the 150 comes up
over the wicket, tight line and length, Maharaj presses back down the line, and it's another dot! It was a run a ball not so long ago... it's nearer two a ball now!

Full length outswinger, Jansen reckon Kohli has nicked this, but he's overstepped! It was sent upstairs, then straight back down again for a free hit... free hit... swinging away, inside the tramlines, Kohli makes room to leg and almost swings himself off his feet, trying to make contact
back of a length, angle across the right-hander, good lift, and Maharaj can't lay bat on ball!
full toss, on the pads, free runs! Maybe Markram shouldn't have kept the faith after all. Pretty poor ball at this crucial stage, whipped through backward square
Maharaj slides back and across, good contact on the pull up into the leg-side, one bounce to deep midwicket. There is the single
back of a length, outside off, thumped down the ground, Markram almost rolls his ankle while intercepting, and they get  back for two
hoisted across the line, out to midwicket! Not perfect contact on a forced pull, not quite short enough to clobber. But crucially he's back for the second
another slot ball, another slam-dunk! Outside off, in Kohli's arc, and if the first six was a bit of a mishit, this is utterly munched over wide midwicket!
yorker, fired in at the left-hander's toes, inside-edged for the single to backward square
drags the length back, swung in the air, down to wide long-on, and Kohli is done! It's been a significant knock, but is it the title-winner? All will be revealed
beautiful wide yorker! Maharaj toe-ends his drive, back out of the length, Arshdeep leaps to gather, and claws down the dot ball!
swings into the short ball, big top-edge over the keeper! 17 off the over as Jansen retreats with some pretty bruised figures
full length but too wide, Dube cocks his wrists and waits for the umpire to spread his arms swung lustily off the toes, in the air out to deep midwicket. Full and fast, and couldn't time the contact

wide full toss flogged down the ground for the most sensational catch you can ever imagine! That is a moment for the ages, Miller connected well, but not well enough to take Suryakumar Yadav out of the equation. He hurtled round from wide long-off, clawed down the ball with barely two hands, toppling over the rope as he went, kept his feet inside the rope... and lobbed the ball back into play, and into his own cool-as-cucumber hands!
attempted yorker, comes out as a low full-toss, but at 144kph/89mph, that's hard to put away, thumped to mid-off
Rabada swings for the hills, and a fat edge for four! Crucial boundary for South Africa, they aren't dead yet!
attempted wide yorker, misses his mark by a whisker, and clobbered past mid-on! Such a sweet contact, down the ground with raw power
swing and a miss! Full length, outside off, Rabada can't connect with a huge yahoo to leg... but they sprint the bye

belted hard through the full length, that was travelling seriously quickly and Miller at long-off does well to judge his take, sliding into the ball as it arrives with high velocity. A useful cameo, but a handy dot as well
pinpoint from Hardik, right up to the toes, offering nothing for Maharaj to heave up and into. Deflected to square leg, and now it's six or bust...
wide line, full length, clubbed hard up and over point, but not totally nailed by Jaddu

Over-cooked outside off... that's too wide, and two fours would be a super over... hoisted through the line, but not enough power! Rabada gave it full beans, hitting through the fourth-stump line, but they weren't full enough. SKY can't stay out of the action, and India are moments from the T20 World Cup!
huge swing through the full length, wide of off, a steepling leading edge, and a good diving take at mid-off. South Africa close it out well, but that is a hefty score on the board all the same
flogged in the air to deep midwicket, but it matters not, India win the T20 World Cup!
